label: VA3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external ventral acute muscle 3.

label: embryonic/larval motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911).

label: embryonic/larval nervous system
description: Nervous system of the embryo/larva.

label: ventral acute muscle 3
description: Second-most dorsal of the ventral acute muscles.

label: adult abdominal segment 6 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00003030).

label: adult abdominal segment anterior compartment
description: Any adult segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111573) that is part of some adult abdominal segment (FBbt:00003024).

label: adult abdominal segment 6
description: Any abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: ventral acute muscle
description: A laterally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal posterior muscle attachment site to a ventral anterior one.

label: adult abdominal segment 5 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029).

label: adult abdominal segment 5
description: Any abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: ventral acute muscle 2
description: Second-most dorsal of the ventral acute muscles.

label: A1-7 VA2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external ventral acute muscle 2 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root, fasciculating with the SNc nerve branch.

label: SN motor neuron of A1-7
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscles of larval abdominal segments A1-7 and which fasciculates with the segmental nerve. Its soma is located in the same segment of the muscle it innervates. The dendritic domain of the motor neuron is located posteriorly to the dendritic domain of the motorneurons of ISN motor neurons.

label: VA2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external ventral acute muscle 2.

label: segmental nerve branch SNc of A1-7
description: Posteriorly directed ventral branch of segmental nerve of larval A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the segmental nerve root. It innervates the external ventral acute musculature muscles and carries axons of the ventral sensory cluster.

label: segmental nerve root of A1-7
description: The continuation of the neurite bundle and associated glia of the segmental nerve, inside the ventral nerve cord.

label: segmental nerve of A1-7
description: Segmental nerve of segments A1-7. It contains the axons of motor neurons that innervate the same segment in which their soma is located. Proximally it shares a glial sheath with the intersegmental nerve before branching from it at the ventral edge of the ventral oblique muscles, after which this nerve splits again: the thick, posteriorly directed SNc branch leaves the main trunk of the nerve (SNa) and splits into fine branches - 3 carrying axons from the ventral sensory cluster and a 4th carrying efferents to the ventral acute musculature. The SNa continues dorsally and carries efferent axons innervating the external lateral transverse and oblique muscles and the axons of v'es2 and v'ch1.

label: larval abdominal segment A1-7
description: One of the first seven larval segments (counting from anterior to posterior). Larval segments 1-7 have almost identical musculature, gross tracheal morphology and sensory organ types and distribution.

label: adult abdominal segment 4 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028).

label: adult abdominal segment 4
description: Any abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: adult abdominal segment 3 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027).

label: adult abdominal segment 3
description: Any abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: A1-7 VA1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external ventral acute muscle 1 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root, fasciculating with the SNc nerve branch.

label: VA1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external ventral acute muscle 1.

label: adult sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004).

label: adult sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004).

label: sensillum
description: A sense organ embedded in the integument and consisting of one or a cluster of sensory neurons and associated sensory structures, support cells and glial cells forming a single organized unit with a largely bona fide boundary.

label: adult abdominal segment 2 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00003026).

label: adult abdominal segment 2
description: Any abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: adult abdominal segment 1 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00003025).

label: adult abdominal segment 1
description: Any abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: ventral acute muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most of the ventral acute muscles.

label: pentascolopidial chordotonal organ
description: A chordotonal organ containing 5 scolopidia.

label: chordotonal organ
description: Mechanosensory organ, generally attached to the body wall and consisting of one or more scolopidia.

label: adult abdominal segment
description: Any abdominal segment (FBbt:00000021) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: triscolopidial chordotonal organ
description: A chordotonal organ consisting of 3 scolopidia.

label: LT1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 1.

label: lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Anterior-most of the lateral transverse muscles.

label: adult abdominal segment 10 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00003034).

label: adult abdominal segment 10
description: Any abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00000031) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: cuticle layer
description: A layer of the cuticle.

label: cuticle
description: The outer non-living layer of the integumentary system that is secreted by the underlying epidermis.

label: adult abdominal segment 9 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00003033).

label: adult abdominal segment 9
description: Any abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00000030) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: lateral transverse muscle
description: A laterally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature with a transverse orientation.

label: chorionic layer
description: Layer of the chorion that forms the eggshell.

label: chorion
description: A hard shell external to the vitelline membrane of the egg.

label: adult abdominal segment 8 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00003032).

label: adult abdominal segment 8
description: Any abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00000029) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: embryonic/larval thoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval thorax (FBbt:00001741).

label: embryonic/larval sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: larval thorax
description: Any thorax (FBbt:00000015) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: A1-7 VA3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external ventral acute muscle 3 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root, fasciculating with the SNc nerve branch.

label: adult abdominal segment 7 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00003031).

label: adult abdominal segment 7
description: Any abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: cuticular specialization
description: Specialized structure that is found on the cuticle.

label: embryonic/larval head sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: embryonic/larval head sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: head sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some head (FBbt:00000004).

label: larval head
description: Any head (FBbt:00000004) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: embryonic/larval foregut sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some embryonic/larval foregut (FBbt:00001862).

label: embryonic/larval foregut
description: Anterior-most part of the embryonic/larval alimentary canal. It opens anteriorly at the mouth and is composed of the atrium (to which the salivary glands are attached), the pharynx, and the esophagus and part of the proventriculus.

label: embryonic/larval sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: adult head sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: adult head
description: Head of the adult organism.

label: A1-7 LT3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB3-2 lineage that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 3. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root nerve fasciculating with the SNa nerve branch and innervates the LT3 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: LT3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron from neuroblast NB3-2 lineage that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 3.

label: type Ib motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some muscle cell (FBbt:00005074).

label: 3-2Ms
description: Any motor neuron that develops from NB3-2 and fasciculate with the segmental nerve.

label: A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 3
description: The third anterior-most of the lateral transverse muscles in each of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: neuroblast NB3-2
description: Neuroblast NB3-2 delaminates at S1 and generates as many as 6 motorneurons and a cluster if local interneurons. It is the mirror image of the clone derived from NB4-2.

label: segmental nerve branch SNa of A1-7
description: Dorsally directed branch of segmental nerve of larval A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the segmental nerve root. It innervates the external lateral transverse and oblique muscles and carries axons of sensillum vc5 (also known as vp5) and lch1.

label: adult abdominal segment 4 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028).

label: adult abdominal segment posterior compartment
description: Any adult segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111574) that is part of some adult abdominal segment (FBbt:00003024).

label: lateral transverse muscle 3
description: Third-most anterior of the lateral transverse muscles.

label: adult abdominal segment 3 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027).

label: adult abdominal segment 2 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00003026).

label: lateral transverse muscle 2
description: Second-most anterior of the lateral transverse muscles.

label: A1-7 LT2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB2-2 lineage that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 2. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root nerve fasciculating with the SNa nerve branch and innervates the LT2 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: 2-2M of abdomen
description: Any embryonic/larval motor neuron (FBbt:00007675) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746) and that develops from some neuroblast NB2-2 (FBbt:00001385).

label: LT2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 2.

label: A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 2
description: The second anterior-most of the lateral transverse muscles in each of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: neuroblast NB2-2
description: Neuroblast NB2-2 delaminates at S2 and generates two to three motorneurons that innervate anterior lateral muscles via the SNa. It generates a large number of local interneurons and a smaller number of late-developing intersegmental interneurons. In the larva, it resumes proliferation in all thoracic segments. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 10.

label: adult abdominal segment 1 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00003025).

label: A1-7 LT1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB2-2 lineage that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 1. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root, fasciculating with the SNa nerve branch and innervates the LT1 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 1
description: The most anterior of the lateral transverse muscles in each of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: chorionic specialization
description: Specialized structure of the chorion of the egg.

label: adult abdominal segment 11 anterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111583) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00003035).

label: adult abdominal segment 11
description: Any abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00000032) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: adult prothoracic chordotonal organ
description: Any chordotonal organ (FBbt:00005215) that is part of some adult prothoracic segment (FBbt:00003020).

label: prothoracic chordotonal organ
description: Any chordotonal organ (FBbt:00005215) that is part of some prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000017).

label: adult prothoracic segment
description: Any prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000017) that is part of some adult thorax (FBbt:00003018).

label: inter-ommatidial cell
description: Cell which is part of the boundary between ommatidia.

label: sensory organ cell
description: Any somatic cell (FBbt:00100318) that is part of some sense organ (FBbt:00005155).

label: inter-ommatidial precursor cell
description: Precursor of the inter-ommatidial cells (secondary and tertiary pigment cells). From 10 hours after puparium formation (APF), these cells are part of an unstructured pool of undifferentiated cells surrounding each developing ommatidial core. Around 20-23 hours APF, the primary precursors leave this pool and become part of the ommatidia. Following this, the inter-ommatidial precursors and inter-ommatidial bristle precursors develop into an organized lattice surrounding the ommatidia.

label: retina
description: The array of photoreceptors and the cells that support them in a compound eye.

label: abdominal 6 temporary eclosion muscle SBM
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 6 that develops from abdominal 6 segment border muscle of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal temporary eclosion muscle SBM
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of the adult abdomen that develops from an A1-7 segment border muscle. It extends dorsoventrally, and is located in the intersegmental fold between two abdominal segments.

label: abdominal 6 segment border muscle
description: Any A1-7 segment border muscle (FBbt:00000606) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: A1-7 LT4 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB3-2 lineage that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 4. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root nerve fasciculating with the SNa nerve branch and innervates the LT4 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: LT4 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron from neuroblast NB3-2 lineage that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 4.

label: A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 4
description: The fourth anterior-most of the lateral transverse muscles in each of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: abdominal vch2 neuron
description: Neuron of abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2. Fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: abdominal sensory neuron
description: A sensory neuron that is part of the abdomen.

label: abdominal posterior fascicle neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that fasciculates with some abdominal segmental nerve (FBbt:00002197).

label: vch2 neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 of the ventral cluster in a larval segment.

label: abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ of larval abdominal segments 1-7, innervated by a single neuron - vch2 (vchB).

label: LO1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the external lateral transverse muscle 1.

label: abdominal 7 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 7 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007265).

label: A7 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: lateral transverse muscle 4
description: Posterior-most of the lateral transverse muscles.

label: monoscolopidial chordotonal organ
description: Chordotonal organ with a single scolopidium.

label: embryonic/larval ventral sensory cluster of A1-7
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located ventrally on each side of larval abdominal segments 1-7.
synonyms: larval ventral sensory cluster of A1-7

label: vch neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates a ventral chordotonal organ of the larval abdomen or thorax.

label: photoreceptor cell of Bolwig organ
description: Photoreceptor cell that is part of a Bolwig's organ. Unlike the photoreceptors of the adult eye, eyelet and ocellus, these photoreceptors do not contain rhabdomeres, but instead have apical surfaces which are folded into numerous microtubule containing lamellae.

label: photoreceptor cell
description: Sensory neuron that reacts to the presence of light, due to the presence of rhodopsin.

label: entrainment of circadian clock by photoperiod
description: The synchronization of a circadian rhythm to photoperiod, the intermittent cycle of light (day) and dark (night).

label: Bolwig nerve
description: Larval nerve connecting the Bolwig's organ to the optic lobe. It consists of the axons of the photoreceptor cells of Bolwig organ.

label: Bolwig organ
description: Visual organ of the larva. It consists of a dense cluster of 12 ciliated photoreceptor neurons located on either side of the midline in a dorsomedial position in the anterior region of the larva.

label: eo support cell
description: Cell which makes part of the sheath that encloses the soma and dendrite of an eo-type sensory neuron.

label: eo-type sensillum
description: Sensillum with innervated external cuticular sensory structure consisting of one or more bipolar sensory neurons, and 3 support cells: a trichogen cell which makes the external cuticular sensory structure, a thecogen cell which makes the socket that holds the base of the external sensory structure and a tormogen cell which makes the cuticular matrix (cap) at the tip of the innervating dendrite(s).

label: serotonin secretion, neurotransmission
description: The regulated release of serotonin by a cell, in which released serotonin acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: serotonin secretion
description: The regulated release of serotonin by a cell. Serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine, or 5-HT) is a monoamine synthesised in serotonergic neurons in the central nervous system, enterochromaffin cells in the gastrointestinal tract and some immune system cells.

label: neurotransmitter secretion
description: The regulated release of neurotransmitter from the presynapse into the synaptic cleft via calcium regualated exocytosis during synaptic transmission.

label: rhabdomeric photoreceptor cell
description: Photoreceptor cell that contains rhabdomeres.

label: dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: Third-most dorsal of the dorsal oblique muscles.

label: dorsal oblique muscle
description: A dorsally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal anterior muscle attachment site to a ventral posterior one.

label: tergite anterior compartment
description: Anterior compartment of an adult abdominal tergite.

label: compartment
description: A region of tissue that is partially delimited by a compartment boundary during its development. A compartment boundary is a sharp, stable boundary through a developing tissue that cells do not cross during development and that typically has no morphological correlate. The cells comprising the compartment form a population defined by their inability to cross the compartment boundary.

label: tergite
description: The dorsal plate (sclerite) of an adult abdominal segment.

label: haltere posterior compartment
description: Parts of the adult haltere which develop from the posterior compartment of the haltere disc.

label: haltere disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the haltere disc.

label: haltere
description: Paired dorsal 'appendage' of the adult mesothoracic segment. It is a freely movable, capitate stalk. It develops from the dorsal mesothoracic disc. It is used for flight balance.

label: A1-7 DO3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB3-2 lineage. It innervates the internal dorsal oblique muscle 3 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DO3 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: DO3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal oblique muscle 3.

label: 3-2Mar
description: Any motorneurons that develops from NB3-2 and fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve, exiting the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root.

label: ISN motor neuron of the lateral neuropil of A1-7
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal ISN innervated muscles of larval abdominal segments A1-7. The dendritic domain of the motor neuron is located in the lateral neuropile.

label: A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most dorsal oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: anterior intersegmental nerve root of A1-7
description: Anterior root of the intersegmental nerve of abdominal segments 1 to 7, through which the motor neurons of the next anterior segment project to, to innervate the muscles.

label: intersegmental nerve of A1-7
description: Intersegmental nerve of larval segments A1-A7. With a couple of exceptions, the motor neurons whose axons it carries have their cell bodies in the segment anterior immediately to the muscles they innervate. Proximally it shares a glial sheath with segmental nerve before branching from it at the ventral edge of the ventral oblique muscles. It then runs dorsally, anterior to the segmental nerve. Its branches include (from ventral to dorsal): two motor branches that innervate the internal muscles- ISNb and ISNd, which innervate the ventral oblique and ventral muscle fibers; and a sensory branch that penetrates the lateral transverse fibers to reach the lateral sensory cluster. Upon entering the dorsal muscle group, it splits to form an externally directed sensory branch connected to the dorsal sensory cluster, and an internally directed branch which carries efferent axons to the dorsal musculature.

label: haltere anterior compartment
description: Parts of the adult haltere which develop from the anterior compartment of the haltere disc.

label: haltere disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the haltere disc.

label: LL1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the lateral longitudinal muscle 1.

label: lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: A laterally located, longitudinally orientated hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature. No segment contains more that one of these.

label: A1-7 LL1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the fifth ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1. It innervates the internal lateral longitudinal muscle 1 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the intermediate domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the LL1 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: ISN motor neuron of the intermediate neuropile of A1-7
description: Motor neuron that innervates the ventral and lateral ISN innervated muscles of larval abdominal segments A1-7. The dendritic domain of the motor neuron extends from the lateral to the intermediate regions.

label: U5 neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the fifth ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The only lateral longitudinal muscle in each of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: leg posterior compartment
description: Parts of the adult leg which develop from the posterior compartment of the leg disc.

label: leg disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the leg disc.

label: leg
description: The walking appendages of each segment of the ventral adult external thorax.

label: leg anterior compartment
description: Parts of the adult leg which develop from the anterior compartment of the leg disc.

label: leg disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the leg disc.

label: dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Third-most dorsal acute muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature.

label: dorsal acute muscle
description: A dorsally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal posterior muscle attachment site to a ventral anterior one.

label: A1-7 DA3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the fourth ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1. It innervates the internal dorsal acute muscle 3 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DA3 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: DA3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal oblique muscle 3.

label: U4 neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the fourth ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: wing blade posterior compartment
description: Parts of the wing blade and margin which develop from the posterior compartment of the wing pouch.

label: wing posterior compartment
description: Parts of the wing which develop from the posterior compartment of the wing disc.

label: wing disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the wing disc.

label: wing margin
description: The border or edge of the wing. It separates the dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: wing blade
description: The flat part of the wing that forms by the apposition of the dorsal and ventral surfaces of the wing pouch.

label: wing blade anterior compartment
description: Parts of the wing blade and margin which develop from the anterior compartment of the wing pouch.

label: wing anterior compartment
description: Parts of the wing which develop from the anterior compartment of the wing disc.

label: wing disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the wing disc.

label: A1-7 DO2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the third ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1. It innervates the internal dorsal oblique muscle 2 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DO2 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: U3 neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the third ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most dorsal oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: abdominal 2 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 2 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007266).

label: A2 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal segment 11 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00000032).

label: embryonic segment posterior compartment
description: Posterior compartment of an embryonic segment.

label: adult DL2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast DL2.

label: neuroblast lineage clone
description: A clone of cells, all of which are descended from a single neuroblast.

label: adult brain
description: Brain of the adult.

label: lobe system of mushroom body
description: The mushroom body lobe system consists of a vertical (dorsal) branch composed and a medial branch.

label: superior intermediate protocerebrum
description: A small synaptic neuropil domain located around and posterior to the mushroom body vertical lobe, in front of the superior fiber system and above the superior clamp. This domain is rich in loose fibers that project from the anterior optic tubercle in a medial-posterior direction. It also houses the arborizations of many neurons that connect with the vertical lobes.

label: gorget
description: A thin plate-like, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain that protrudes medially from below the inferior clamp to the area between the great commissure and the central body. Its medial tip extends towards the noduli.

label: superior clamp
description: Superior (dorsal) part of the clamp, above the dorsal surface of the mushroom body pedunculus and in front of the mushroom body calyx. It is located above the superior ellipsoid commissure (SEC) and superior arch commissure (SAC).

label: lateral accessory lobe
description: A bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain with a roughly pyramidal shape that is located inferior-lateral to the ellipsoid body and anterior-inferior to the bulb (lateral triangle). It lies behind the antennal lobe and in front of the ventral complex.

label: anterior optic tubercle
description: Synaptic neuropil domain of the adult protocerebrum that receives extensive arborizations from visual projection neurons from the lobula and the medulla, projecting via the anterior optic tract. It protrudes from the anterior-most area of the ventro-lateral neuropils and is slightly detached from the ventro-lateral protocerebrum. This neuropil is absent from the larval brain, being formed during pupal development.

label: posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum
description: A glomerular, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain lying in front of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP), and above the wedge. The great commissure is at the boundary in the mid-level between the PLVP and PLP. It is contiguous with posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP), which lies behind it. It houses many optic glomeruli formed by the terminals of neurons projecting from the optic lobe, primarily from the lobula. The boundary with the PLP, except at mid-level, is defined as the boundary between these glomeruli with different origins (lobula or lobula plate).

label: antler
description: Thin, elongated, antler-shaped, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain spanning from the inferior bridge to the inferior edge of the superior lateral protocerebrum. It runs through the space between the protocerebral bridge and the fan-shaped body, along the medial surface of the medial antennal lobe tract.

label: crepine
description: A thin, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain that wraps around the medial lobe of the mushroom body. Many neurons in this domain enter the lobes to form extensive connections with Kenyon cell fibers.

label: superior medial protocerebrum
description: Medial synaptic neuropil domain of the superior neuropils that lies above the area flanked by the mushroom lobes, pedunculus, and calyx. It is separated from the pedunculus by the superior clamp and insulated from the medial lobe by the crepine. The fan-shaped body protrudes deeply into this neuropil, separating it into anterior (ASMP) and posterior (PSMP) regions.

label: calyx of adult mushroom body
description: Mushroom body calyx of the mature adult mushroom body.

label: lateral horn
description: Dorso-lateral most synaptic neuropil domain of the adult midbrain. This horn-like projection houses the terminals of various antennal lobe projection neurons. It is not separated from other neuropils by a glial sheath, but by the extent of arborization and synapsing of these antennal lobe projection neurons.

label: posterior lateral protocerebrum
description: A bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain that contains many glomeruli and is located behind the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) and above the wedge. The mid-level of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP) is separated from the PVLP by the great commissure, but above and below this the two neuropils are contiguous. The PLP houses many optic glomeruli formed by the terminals of neurons projecting from the optic lobe, primarily from the lobula plate. The boundary with the PVLP is defined by the boundary between these glomeruli that have different origins (lobula or lobula plate).

label: superior lateral protocerebrum
description: Lateral synaptic neuropil domain of the superior neuropils. It lies behind the anterior optic tubercle, in front of the mushroom body calyx and above the superior clamp and lateral horn. Its boundary with the anterior optic tubercle (AOTU), mushroom body calyx and lateral horn is demarcated by the extent of arborization of visual projection neurons and antennal lobe projection neurons. Boundaries with the superior clamp, anterior and posterior ventro-lateral protocerebrum are defined using clearly distinguishable fiber bundles.

label: anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum
description: An aglomerular, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain of the ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP) that protrudes from the anterior brain between the optic lobe and the antennal lobe. It is located in front of the posterior VLP and below the anterior optic tubercle and superior clamp. It receives input from neurons projecting from the optic lobe.

label: adult DL2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DL2 (FBbt:00050083).

label: neuron
description: Electrically active cell of the nervous system which has an axon and/or dendrite and which is synapsed with other cells and/or has other cells synapsed to it.

label: adult LHp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHp1 (FBbt:00050080).

label: adult LHp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHp1.

label: type II neuroblast
description: Neuroblast that asymmetrically divides to produce a large daughter neuroblast cell and a smaller secondary neuroblast (also called a transit-amplifying GMC) that can generate up to ten daughter neurons or glial cells (Boone and Doe, 2008, Viktorin et al., 2011).

label: adult WEDa1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast WEDa1 (FBbt:00050086).

label: adult WEDa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast WEDa1.

label: protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the protocerebrum.

label: type I neuroblast
description: Neuroblast that asymmetrically divides to produce a large daughter neuroblast cell and a smaller GMC cell that generates two daughter neurons.

label: DO4 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal oblique muscle 4.

label: dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Second-most ventral of the dorsal oblique muscles.

label: tergite posterior compartment
description: Posterior compartment of an adult abdominal tergite.

label: saddle
description: Synaptic neuropil domain covering the dorsal and posterior surface of the gnathal ganglia. It contains the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC).

label: wedge
description: An aglomerular, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain that is the inferior-most domain of the ventrolateral neuropils, lying between the anterior and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP and PVLP) and posteriorlateral protocerebrum (PLP), and the saddle and gnathal ganglion. The wedge is lateral to the inferior fiber system and vest. It receives synaptic input from the saddle and the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) within it. This includes direct sensory input from antennal mechanosensory neurons that also innervate the AMMC.

label: adult subesophageal zone
description: Neuropil mass below the esophagus in the adult brain. It encompasses the gnathal ganglion, the prow and the saddle.

label: inferior posterior slope
description: Inferior (ventral) part of the posterior slope. It flanks both sides of the esophagus, and is posterior and medial to the wedge. Below the plane of the inferior VLP commissure and the posterior optic commissure.

label: abdominal 3 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 3 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007267).

label: A3 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 3 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 4 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007268).

label: A4 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: adult SLPpm3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpm3 (FBbt:00050089).

label: adult SLPpm3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpm3.

label: leg ventral compartment
description: Parts of the adult leg which develop from the ventral compartment of the leg disc.

label: leg disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the leg disc.

label: larval abdominal segment 4
description: Any abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: portion of tissue
description: Anatomical structure, that consists of similar cells and intercellular matrix, aggregated according to genetically determined spatial relationships.

label: A1-7 DO4 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB3-2 lineage. It innervates the internal dorsal oblique muscle 4 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DO4 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most dorsal oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7. Its posterior end is attached to a site in the segment posterior to that in which it originates.

label: abdominal 5 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: larval abdominal segment 5
description: Any abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: larval abdominal segment 2
description: Any abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: larval abdominal segment 3
description: Any abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: abdominal 1 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007271).

label: A1 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: larval abdominal segment 7
description: Any abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: abdominal 5 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007269).

label: A5 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 vch2 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch2 neuron (FBbt:00007257) that is part of some abdominal 6 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007270).

label: A6 neuron
description: Any abdominal neuron (FBbt:00001987) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch2 (FBbt:00007255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: Dorsal-most of the ventral longitudinal muscles.

label: ventral longitudinal muscle
description: A ventrally located, longitudinally orientated hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature.

label: adult thoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any adult segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111574) that is part of some adult thoracic segment (FBbt:00003019).

label: adult thoracic segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some adult thorax (FBbt:00003018).

label: adult metathoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any adult thoracic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111575) that is part of some adult metathoracic segment (FBbt:00003022).

label: adult thoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any adult segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111573) that is part of some adult thoracic segment (FBbt:00003019).

label: adult metathoracic segment
description: Any metathoracic segment (FBbt:00000019) that is part of some adult thorax (FBbt:00003018).

label: adult mesothoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any adult thoracic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111575) that is part of some adult mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00003021).

label: adult mesothoracic segment
description: Any mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000018) that is part of some adult thorax (FBbt:00003018).

label: ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Third-most ventral of the ventral longitudinal muscles.

label: adult prothoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any adult thoracic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111575) that is part of some adult prothoracic segment (FBbt:00003020).

label: ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Second-most ventral of the ventral oblique muscles.

label: ventral oblique muscle
description: A ventrally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal anterior muscle attachment site to a ventral posterior one.

label: adult segment
description: Segment of the adult.

label: A1-7 DO5 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB3-2 lineage. It innervates the internal dorsal oblique muscle 5 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DO5 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 5
description: The ventral-most of the dorsal oblique muscles of A1-7.

label: leg dorsal compartment
description: Parts of the adult leg which develop from the dorsal compartment of the leg disc.

label: leg disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the leg disc.

label: adult ALad1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346).

label: adult antennal lobe
description: The adult antennal lobe is a bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain of the deutocerebrum lying in front of the protocerebral synaptic neuropil domains. It is divided into approximately 50 glomeruli and is clearly separated from adjacent neuropil domains by an extensive glial sheath. The two antennal lobes are connected by the antennal commissure and receive olfactory receptor neuron axons from the antennal nerve and subesophageal tract. It is also connected to the antennal lobe tracts and the broad root.

label: adult ALad1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346).

label: BAmv3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAmv3 neuroblast (ALad1).

label: adult PSp3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast PSp3.

label: cantle
description: A small, bilaterally paired, triangular synaptic neuropil domain that lies at the posterior end of the saddle. It is clearly demarcated by glial boundaries.

label: flange
description: A small, bilaterally paired, triangular synaptic neuropil domain that lies above the anterior end of the saddle, on both sides of the esophagus. It lies at the root of the median bundle, behind the prow.

label: lobula
description: Anterior domain of the adult lobula complex. It houses many columnar neurons.

label: bulb
description: A bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain located lateral to the ellipsoid body and anterior lateral to the fan-shaped body. It contains 80 microglomeruli characterized by their granular texture. It is formed primarily by the collateral arborizations of neuronal fibers that project to the ellipsoid body and by the terminals of the fibers projecting from the anterior optic tubercle and other neuropils.

label: inferior bridge
description: Posterior-most synaptic neuropil domain of the midline. It is the only synaptic neuropil domain outside of the central complex that is fused across the midline. It is located behind the fan-shaped body and below the protocerebral bridge.

label: superior posterior slope
description: Superior (dorsal) part of the posterior slope. It lies behind the great commissure, gorget and vest and below the inferior clamp and inferior bridge. It has no clear glial boundary with the surrounding neuropils.

label: inferior clamp
description: Inferior (ventral) part of the clamp, between the pedunculus and the central complex. It is located below the superior ellipsoid commissure (SEC) and superior arch commissure (SAC).

label: vest
description: Bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain that is the largest and most medial domain of the ventral complex. Its inferior (ventral) boundary with the saddle is demarcated by a glial sheath and the medial and lateral sides are flanked respectively by the esophagus and inferior fiber system.

label: epaulette
description: A small, bilaterally paired synaptic neuropil domain of the ventral complex, lying below the inferior clamp and superior-lateral to the vest.

label: adult PSp3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast PSp3 (FBbt:00050092).

label: adult LHd1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHd1 (FBbt:00050097).

label: adult LHd1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHd1.

label: ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Third-most dorsal of the dorsal oblique muscles.

label: larval abdominal segment 1
description: Any abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: class I dendritic arborizing neuron
description: A dendritic arborizing md sensory neuron with a long, dorsally directed primary dendrite which branches repeatedly along its length into antero-posteriorly oriented secondary dendrites. The dendrites are smooth and their branching pattern is relatively simple, with few side branches or varicosities.

label: dendritic arborizing neuron
description: Sensory multidendritic neuron of the PNS with branching dendrites that spread directly below and in close association with the epidermal cell layer.

label: larval abdominal segment 6
description: Any abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: adult metathoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any adult thoracic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111579) that is part of some adult metathoracic segment (FBbt:00003022).

label: labial complex
description: Cluster of sense organs in the labial segment of the embryonic/larval head.

label: sensory cluster
description: A cluster of sense organs in the integument or connected to it.

label: larval labial segment
description: Any labial segment (FBbt:00000014) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: adult mesothoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any adult thoracic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111579) that is part of some adult mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00003021).

label: adult prothoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any adult thoracic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111579) that is part of some adult prothoracic segment (FBbt:00003020).

label: anatomical cluster
description: Anatomical group whose component anatomical structures lie in close proximity to each other.

label: anatomical group
description: Material anatomical entity generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome and whose component parts are not all connected to each other.

label: non-connected functional system
description: An anatomical group whose component structures share a common function.

label: class IV dendritic arborizing neuron
description: A dendritic arborizing md sensory neuron with a highly complex branching pattern that completely fills large regions of the body wall with its arbors. Each cell may have 800-900 terminal branches and more than 6 branch orders.

label: class II dendritic arborizing neuron
description: A dendritic arborizing md sensory neuron with multiple long and sinuous dendrites. Their branching pattern is relatively symmetrical. Higher order branches are generally short stubs extending from the major trunks.

label: class III dendritic arborizing neuron
description: A dendritic arborizing md sensory neuron with long primary and secondary dendrites that have spiked protrusions along most of their length and at the ends of major branches.

label: abdominal segment motor neuron
description: Motor neuron located in an abdominal segment of the embryo/larva.

label: haltere disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the haltere disc.

label: dorsal thoracic disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the dorsal thoracic disc.

label: haltere disc
description: Dorsal imaginal disc of the metathorax. Precursor of structure of the adult dorsal metathorax including the haltere.

label: metathoracic leg disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the metathoracic leg disc.

label: metathoracic leg disc
description: Imaginal disc of the ventral metathoracic segment. Precursor of structures of the adult ventral metathorax including the metathoracic (3rd) leg.

label: ISN innervated muscle of A1-7
description: Muscles of the body wall that are innervated by the intersegmental nerve in the larval abdominal segments A1-7.

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdomen
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: ISN motor neuron of A1-7
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscles of larval abdominal segments A1-7 and which fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve. Its soma is located in the next anterior segment of the muscle it innervates. The dendritic domain of the motor neuron is located anteriorly to the dendritic domain of the motorneurons that innervate external muscles.

label: metathoracic leg disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the metathoracic leg disc.

label: abdominal nerve
description: Any nerve (FBbt:00005105) that is part of some abdomen (FBbt:00000020).

label: segmental nerve root
description: The continuation of the neurite bundle and associated glia of the segmental nerve, inside the ventral nerve cord.

label: SN innervated muscle of A1-7
description: Muscles of the body wall that are innervated by the segmental nerve in the larval abdominal segments A1-7.

label: mesothoracic leg disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the mesothoracic leg disc.

label: mesothoracic leg disc
description: Imaginal disc of the ventral mesothoracic segment. Precursor of structures of the adult ventral mesothorax including the mesothoracic (2nd) leg.

label: mesothoracic leg disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the mesothoracic leg disc.

label: intersegmental nerve root
description: The continuation of the neurite bundle and associated glia of the intersegmental nerve, inside the ventral nerve cord.

label: posterior intersegmental nerve root of A1-7
description: Posterior root of the intersegmental nerve of abdominal segments 1 to 7, through which the motor neurons of the same segment project to, to innervate the muscles.

label: prothoracic leg disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the prothoracic leg disc.

label: prothoracic leg disc
description: Imaginal disc of the ventral prothoracic segment. Precursor of structures of the adult ventral prothorax including the prothoracic (1st) leg.

label: prothoracic leg disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the prothoracic leg disc.

label: ISN motorneuron of the medial neuropil of A1-7
description: Motor neuron that innervates the most ventral ISN innervated muscles of larval abdominal segments A1-7. The dendritic domain of the motor neuron extends from the lateral to the medial regions.

label: antennal disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the antennal disc.

label: imaginal disc ventral compartment
description: Ventral compartment of an imaginal disc.

label: antennal disc
description: Posterior portion of the eye-antennal disc. It gives rise to the adult antennal segments and the maxillary palp, as well as contributing to the head capsule.

label: antennal disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the antennal disc.

label: imaginal disc dorsal compartment
description: Dorsal compartment of an imaginal disc.

label: abdominal intersegmental nerve neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911) and that fasciculates with some abdominal intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002319).

label: haltere disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the haltere disc.

label: dorsal thoracic disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the dorsal thoracic disc.

label: labial organ sensillum
description: Any external sensillum (FBbt:00007231) that is part of some embryonic/larval labial organ (FBbt:00002720).

label: embryonic/larval labial segment sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval labial segment (FBbt:00001740).

label: external sensillum
description: Sensillum which is embedded in the body wall and has a specific cuticular structure involved in the transduction of some sensory signal as a part.

label: embryonic/larval labial organ
description: A compound external sense organ of the late embryo or larva. It is located in the lower lip of the external opening of the atrium. It consists of 3 sensilla, one with 3 neurons and the others with one each. Neurons of the labial organ and hypophysis (labial sensory organ) form a large cluster flanking the salivary duct.

label: epiphysis
description: Paired compound sense organ of the labral complex in the larval head. It consists of 6 sensilla in the larval pharynx: one tri-dendritic, 2 bi-dendritic and 3 mono-dendritic. Projections from the epiphysis generally, though not exclusively, target the contralateral subesophageal ganglion area 1 (Colomb et al., 2007).

label: external compound sense organ
description: Compound sense organ that is located within the epidermis.

label: embryonic/larval labral segment sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some larval labral segment (FBbt:00001734).

label: integumentary specialisation
description: Specialized structure that is found on the integument.

label: region of integument
description: A region of cuticle and its underlying epidermis.

label: tagmatic subdivision of integument
description: Region of integument of a tagma.

label: integument of adult abdominal segment 1
description: Region of integument that is part of adult abdominal segment 1.

label: segmental subdivision of integument
description: A segmental subdivision of the integument of the whole animal.

label: integumentary system
description: The organ system that forms the covering layer of the animal.

label: DO1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal oblique muscle 1.

label: dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most dorsal oblique muscles.

label: eye disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the eye disc.

label: imaginal disc anterior compartment
description: Anterior compartment of an imaginal disc. During growth of the disc, cells of the anterior compartment do not cross into the posterior compartment. With the exception of the eye-antennal disc, the boundary between these two compartments is defined at the time of disc specification by a parasegment boundary running through the disc anlage.

label: eye disc
description: Anterior, bulbous portion of the eye-antennal disc that gives rise to the eye as well as contributing to the head capsule (Cohen, 1993).

label: eye disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the eye disc.

label: imaginal disc posterior compartment
description: Posterior compartment of an imaginal disc. During growth of the disc, cells of the posterior compartment do not cross into the anterior compartment. With the exception of the eye-antennal disc, the boundary between these two compartments is defined at the time of disc specification by a parasegment boundary running through the disc anlage.

label: clypeo-labral disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the clypeo-labral disc.

label: clypeo-labral disc
description: Imaginal disc that in the adults gives rise to the labrum, anterior and posterior cibarial plates, fish trap bristles, epipharyngeal sclerite and clypeus (Cohen, 1993).

label: clypeo-labral disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the clypeo-labral disc.

label: labial disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the labial disc.

label: labial disc
description: Imaginal disc that, in the adult, gives rise to the proboscis, including the prementum, prestomal cavity, labellum, labellar cap and pseudotrachea (Cohen, 1993).

label: dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most acute muscle of a segment of the embryonic/larval musculature.

label: dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Second-most dorsal acute muscle of a segment of the embryonic/larval musculature.

label: labial disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the labial disc.

label: dorsal thoracic disc
description: Imaginal disc that is a precursor of dorsal thoracic structures of the adult.

label: A1-7 DA1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the internal dorsal acute muscle 1 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DA1 muscle with type Ib boutons. By embryonic stage 16, it has a short contralaterally projecting neurite extending into the posterior commissure. It receives input from the contra- and ipsilateral larval A27h neuron.

label: aCC neuron
description: Motor neuron born from the first GMC to bud from neuroblast NB1-1. It has a large round cell body that sits at the dorsal surface of the CNS, in the next anterior segment which it innervates, just posterior to the posterior commissure and longitudinal connective.

label: DA1 motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00110221) and that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911).

label: A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: larval A27h neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 27. Its primary neurite extends anteriorly, with the most anterior branch crossing the midline. It outputs to the A27e neuron and ipsi- and contralateral A1-7 DA1 motor neuron.

label: posterior commissure
description: Most posterior of the two commissures found in each neuromere of the ventral nerve cord.

label: dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: Second-most dorsal of the dorsal oblique muscles.

label: eye disc ventral compartment
description: The ventral compartment of the eye disc.

label: DO2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal oblique muscle 2.

label: eye disc dorsal compartment
description: The dorsal compartment of the eye disc.

label: endocrine cell
description: Any cell (FBbt:00007002) that capable of some endocrine hormone secretion (GO:0060986).

label: endocrine system component
description: Any material anatomical entity (FBbt:00007016) that capable of some endocrine hormone secretion (GO:0060986).

label: cell
description: Anatomical structure that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

label: endocrine hormone secretion
description: The regulated release of a hormone into the circulatory system.

label: region of integument defined by pigmentation pattern
description: A region of integument whose boundaries are defined by the boundaries of an element of a pigmentation pattern.

label: sensory neuron of trichoid sensillum
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184).

label: eo neuron
description: Sensory neuron that is part of an eo-sensillum and whose dendrite innervates the cuticular external sensory structure of that sensillum.

label: sensillum trichodeum
description: A sensillum of which the external part is a seta.

label: syncytium
description: A multi-nucleate cell having no internal boundaries between nuclei.

label: abdominal segment 11 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00000032).

label: embryonic segment anterior compartment
description: Anterior compartment of an embryonic segment.

label: embryonic/larval prothoracic dorsal sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located dorsally on each side of the prothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval thoracic/abdominal dorsal sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located dorsally on each side of each thoracic segment and of abdominal segments 1-7. The axons of neurons in this cluster fasciculate with the intersegmental nerve.

label: integument of larval prothoracic segment
description: The integument of the larval prothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval thoracic/abdominal lateral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located in the lateral region on each side of each thoracic segment and of abdominal segments 1-7. The axons of neurons in this cluster fasciculate with the intersegmental nerve.

label: embryonic/larval mesothoracic dorsal sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located dorsally on each side of the mesothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval T2/3 dorsal sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located dorsally on each side of the larval mesothoracic and metathoracic segments.

label: integument of larval mesothoracic segment
description: The integument of the larval mesothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located in the ventral region on each side of each thoracic segment and of abdominal segments 1-7. The axons of neurons in this cluster fasciculate with either the posterior fascicle or segmental nerve.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the antennal disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the antennal disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of imaginal disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides an imaginal disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the ventral thoracic disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the ventral thoracic disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of imaginal disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides an imaginal disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: ventral thoracic disc
description: Imaginal disc that is a precursor of ventral thoracic structures of the adult.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the ventral thoracic disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the ventral thoracic disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: compartment boundary
description: Portion of tissue consisting of the cells immediately adjacent to a sharp, stable boundary through a developing tissue that cells do not cross during development and that typically has no morphological correlate.

label: imaginal disc
description: A sac shaped epithelial structure in the larva that gives rise to part of the adult integumentary system. One side of the sac consists of peripodial epithelium, the other of columnar epithelium. A single anterior-posterior compartment boundary bisects both peripodial membrane and columnar epithelium. Cells do not cross this boundary during growth and development of the disc.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the haltere disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the haltere disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the haltere disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the haltere disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the eye disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the eye disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the eye disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the eye disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the antennal disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the antennal thoracic disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: core layer of the larval mushroom body
description: Middle layer of the third instar larval mushroom body, encompassing the pedunculus and lobes. It is surrounded by the inner layer. The larval-born alpha'/beta' type Kenyon cells are contained in this layer.

label: synaptic neuropil layer
description: Laminar or concentric subdivision of a synaptic neuropil domain along its long axis delimited by a discontinuity in synaptic or fiber density.

label: embryonic/larval mushroom body
description: Mushroom body of the larva. It is composed of two lobes only, medial and vertical, in contrast to the adult. Mushroom body neuroblasts continue to supply increasing numbers of Kenyon cells through the larval stages. The axons of these neurons follow the tracts laid down during embryonic development. Which tracts they contribute to varies depending on the stage of development: from first instar to third instar stage 1, they contribute to the gamma lobe; during third instar stage 2 and puparium formation each axon bifurcates and contributes to the alpha' and beta' lobes (during the pupal stage they contribute to the alpha and beta lobes). At third instar stage, four layers at the level of the pedunculus and lobes: surface, outer, inner layers and core. Three types of intrinsic neurons can be identified at this stage that occupy specific layers: embryonic-born gamma type (surface layer), larval-born gamma type (outer and inner layers) and larval-born alpha'/beta' type (core layer) neurons.

label: developmental compartment
description: A region of developing tissue that is partially delimited by a compartment boundary. A compartment boundary is a sharp, stable boundary through a developing tissue that cells do not cross during development and that typically has no morphological correlate. The cells comprising the compartment form a population defined by their inability to cross the compartment boundary.

label: adult pars intercerebralis
description: Pars intercerebralis of the adult.

label: pars intercerebralis
description: Region of the cortex that lies in a medial cleft dividing the left and right superior protocerebrum, anterior to the calyces of the mushroom bodies and dorsal to the central complex. It contains numerous large and small somata of neurosecretory and neuromodulatory neurons. In the larva, these neurons are split into bilaterally symmetric clusters on either side of the medial cleft whereas in the adult they are one unpaired cluster (Siegmund and Korge, 2001, Velasco et al., 2007).

label: adult brain cell body rind
description: Superficial layer of the brain, composed of glia and the cell bodies of neurons (soma).

label: bract primordium
description: The primordium of the bract cell. It is an epithelial cell, located proximally to the sensory bristles, which is induced to become a bract during pupal stages.

label: epithelial cell
description: Cell that has as its part a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and which has apical-basal cell polarity.

label: primordium
description: Primordia are populations of contiguous cells that are morphologically distinct and already correspond in extent to a later organ/tissue.

label: developing embryonic structure
description: Any developing material anatomical entity (FBbt:00007006) that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: outer layer of the larval mushroom body
description: Outer layer of the third instar larval mushroom body, encompassing the pedunculus and lobes. It is surrounded by the surface layer. Part of the larval-born gamma type Kenyon cells are contained in this layer.

label: optic lobe neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has synaptic terminals in some optic lobe (FBbt:00003701).

label: optic lobe
description: A region of the adult brain that processes visual information from the compound eyes.

label: inner layer of the larval mushroom body
description: Inner layer of the third instar larval mushroom body, encompassing the pedunculus and lobes. It is surrounded by the outer layer. Part of the larval-born gamma type Kenyon cells are contained in this layer.

label: synaptic neuropil block
description: A closely associated group of synaptic neuropil domains.

label: embryonic/larval optic lobe
description: Region of the embryonic or larval protocerebrum that will give rise to the adult protocerebrum.

label: adult protocerebrum
description: Protocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: adult cerebral ganglion
description: The pre-oral neuropils of the adult brain located above, around and partially below the esophagus, including the optic lobes. It excludes the gnathal ganglion. Developmentally, it comprises three fused neuromeres: protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the wing blade
description: A compartment boundary that divides the wing blade into dorsal and ventral compartments.
synonyms: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the wing

label: surface layer of the larval mushroom body
description: Surface layer of the third instar larval mushroom body, encompassing the pedunculus and lobes. The embryonic-born gamma type Kenyon cells are contained in this layer.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the wing blade
description: A compartment boundary that divides the wing blade into anterior and posterior compartments.
synonyms: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the wing

label: lamina
description: Lateral-most synaptic neuropil domain of the adult optic lobes, lying just beneath the compound eyes. It is composed of an array of repetitive cartridge-like units, each of which receives axons from specific sets of ommatidia in the compound eyes.

label: synaptic neuropil domain
description: Region of synaptic neuropil whose boundaries are largely discontinuities in the density of presynaptic terminals: high density in the synaptic neuropil domain, lower or zero density outside this region. These boundaries often correspond to a boundary with glial sheath, tract neuropil or cortex.

label: lamina anlage
description: A zone of proliferating neuroblasts that forms at mid third instar, at the lateral rim of the outer optic anlage. Descendants of these neuroblasts form the adult lamina.

label: larval abdominal segment A2-7
description: One of the six larval segments, starting from the second anterior segment (counting from anterior to posterior). Larval segments 2-7 have identical musculature, gross tracheal morphology and sensory organ types and distribution.

label: larval abdominal segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: enteroendocrine cell of posterior adult midgut epithelium
description: Enteroendocrine cell of the posterior adult midgut epithelium.

label: enteroendocrine cell
description: Diploid endocrine cell which is part of the adult midgut epithelium.

label: enteroblast of posterior adult midgut epithelium
description: Enteroblast of the adult posterior midgut epithelium.

label: adult posterior midgut epithelium
description: A columnar - cuboidal epithelial monolayer with a brush border consisting predominantly of large polyploid enterocytes tied together by smooth septate junctions. Scattered through this epithelium are clusters of diploid intestinal stem cells and occasional enteroendocrine cells.

label: optic lobe pioneer neuron 1
description: One of the three optic lobe pioneer neurons, that persist through development.

label: optic lobe pioneer neuron
description: Neuron located in the distal region of the optic lobe (Tix et al., 1989), which persists through development and pioneers Bolwig's nerve.
