description: Anterior commissure of the sixth abdominal neuromere.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi3
description: Medullary intrinsic wide-field neuron with both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layers M3, M6 and M8, but with only fine arborizations in medulla layer M9 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal bipolar neuron dbp
description: Any abdominal dorsal bipolar neuron dbp (FBbt:00002442) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 anterior commissure
description: Anterior commissure of the seventh abdominal neuromere.

label: abdominal 7 lateral multidendritic neuron ldaA
description: Any abdominal lateral multidendritic neuron ldaA (FBbt:00002434) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm6
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the ventral region of the cell body rind of the medulla. It branches extensively at the distal surface of the medulla forming a broad arbor with each branch making a distinctive bleb-type terminal in the boundary between M1 and M2 layers from which short, fine terminal branches project into M2. The arborization overlaps with both the sublayers occupied by Dm1/Dm18, and Dm14/Dm17/Dm19. The arborizations in M1/M2 are enriched in presynaptic terminals. The arbor varies in shape between cells, covering around 30-40 columns, with these areas overlapping. It is located in a intracolumnar position, in the same region as the terminals of lamina monopolar neuron L2, and more central than that of Dm1 and Dm14. There are around 30 Dm6 neurons per hemisphere

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm5
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron that has a moderately broad, fine terminal arborization in layers M4-6. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: bipolar dendrite neuron
description: Multidendritic neuron with bipolar dendrites that grow in opposite directions without major side branches. These neurons are located inside the body and are often associated with muscles.

label: larval Jaam1 neuron
description: Interneuron of the larval abdominal neuromere. In each abdominal segment, the primary neurite extends into the neuromere forming one arbor that extends anteriorly and bifurcates mediolaterally. One neurite crosses the midline and forms a medial arbor that extends anteriorly, and a lateral arbor that extends both anterior- and posteriorly. These three arbors overlap mainly with the dendrites of the A08e2 local neuron. It is synapsed by Jaam2 and Jaam3. It receives input from the ipsilateral proprioceptor dorsal bipolar neuron dbp and contralateral ventral bipolar neuron vbp and posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap. It outputs to the contralateral A08e2 neuron. There is one neuron per segment.

label: larval A03a1 neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 3. Its primary neurite extends from the ventral edge of the ventral nerve cord dorsally to terminate in the most dorsal region. The dendritic branches are located at the midpoint in the dorsal/ventral axis, whereas the axonal ones are in the most dorsal region. It receives input from the ipsilateral dorsal bipolar neuron dbp (axo-axonic connection) and A02b neuron. It outputs to the ipsilateral A1-7 dorsal motor neuron.

label: larval A08e2 local neuron
description: Even-skipped lateral neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. In each abdominal segment, the primary neurite extends into the neuromere crossing the VL fascicle and projecting dorsally across the CI fascicle. It forms two arbors that extend anteriorly. One neurite crosses the midline in between the DM and VM fascicles, extends dorsally, to just dorsal to the CI fascicle, and bifurcates to project a short distance anterior- and posteriorly. It receives input from the ipsilateral proprioceptor neuron dbd, and contralateral Jaam1. It outputs to the contralateral RP2, U1, U2, and dorsal motorneurons, and contralateral SA1 and SA3 interneurons. There is one neuron per segment.

label: larval A08e1 local neuron
description: Even-skipped lateral neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. In each abdominal segment, the primary neurite extends into the neuromere crossing the VL fascicle and projects dorsally across the CI fascicle. One neurite crosses the midline in between the DM and VM fascicles, extends dorsally, to just dorsal to the CI fascicle, and bifurcates to project anterior- and posteriorly. Both its ipsilateral and contralateral projections extend more anteriorly and posteriorly, respectively, than the ones from A08e2 and A08e3 neurons. It is synapsed by and synapses onto A08e3. It receives input from the ipsilateral proprioceptor neuron dbd, and contralateral Jaam3. It outputs to the contralateral RP2, U2 and dorsal motorneurons and contralateral SA1 and SA3 interneurons. There is one neuron per segment.

label: larval A02l neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 2. Its primary neurite extends dorsally, from the ventral region of the ventral nerve cord, close to the midline. It then crosses the midline and follows the dorsal edge of the ventral nerve cord laterally, to terminate in the dorsolateral region. It receives input from the ipsilateral dorsal bipolar neuron dbp and outputs to the contralateral A31k neuron.

label: larval A02a neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 2. Its primary neurite extends, from the ventral region of the ventral nerve cord, close to the midline, to the dorsolateral region. It then does a U-turn and extends ventrally. It receives input from the ipsilateral dorsal bipolar neuron dbp, and A02b neuron. It outputs to the ipsilateral A27j and ipsi- and contralateral A02b neurons.

label: abdominal 1 anterior commissure
description: Anterior commissure of the first abdominal neuromere.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal bipolar neuron dbp
description: Any abdominal dorsal bipolar neuron dbp (FBbt:00002442) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 anterior commissure
description: Anterior commissure of the second abdominal neuromere.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal bipolar neuron dbp
description: Any abdominal dorsal bipolar neuron dbp (FBbt:00002442) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 anterior commissure
description: Anterior commissure of the third abdominal neuromere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm7
description: Distal medullary amacrine neuron that branches in layer M6. The branches spread along the layer, forming an arbor in M6 with terminals of mixed morphology. Some collaterals from this arbor extend to M4 where they also spread to form an arbor with terminals of mixed morphology.

label: female germline cell
description: Cell that develops into or is itself an egg.

label: cystocyte
description: Female germline cell born during one of four rounds of cell division following the birth of a cystoblast from a female germline stem cell until the point where one of the resulting 16 cells (the presumptive oocyte) enters meiosis. Cystocytes are interconnected by ring canals. The oocyte develops from one of two cystocytes that contain 4 ring canals, the other 15 cystocytes differentiate as nurse cells.

label: germarium
description: Anterior region of the ovariole, that is connected to posterior egg chambers.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal bipolar neuron dbp
description: Any abdominal dorsal bipolar neuron dbp (FBbt:00002442) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 8 anterior commissure
description: Anterior commissure of the eighth abdominal neuromere.

label: larval abdominal segment 8
description: Any abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00000029) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: abdominal 9 anterior commissure
description: The only ventral midline-crossing commissure in A9 of the larval ventral nerve cord.

label: larval abdominal segment 9
description: Any abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00000030) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi5
description: Medullary intrinsic narrow field neuron with both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layer M8 and the serpentine layer, but with only fine arborizations in medulla layer M6 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi7
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron with both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layer M6, but with only fine arborizations in medulla layers M1, M3, M5 and M8. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi6
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron with both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layers M2, M5, M6 and M8, but with only fine arborizations in medulla layers M3 and M4.

label: abdominal segmental nerve
description: Segmental nerve found in the abdominal segments of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal 4 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal vch neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates a ventral chordotonal organ of the larval abdomen. There are two chordotonal organs in each segment.

label: abdominal posterior commissure
description: Posterior-most of the two midline-crossing commissures that develop in the posterior half of each abdominal neuromere, except for a9 which only has one commissure. The posterior commissure contains fewer fibers than the anterior commissure and is located approximately at the level of the posterior neuromere boundary.

label: larval abdominal neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment (FBbt:00001747).

label: transmedullary neuron
description: An intrinsic columnar neuron of the optic lobe whose cell body lies in the distal cortex of the medulla and that projects through the medulla and optic chiasm into the lobula. All neurons arborize in the lobula and most, but not all, in the medulla (Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989).

label: second optic chiasma
description: Chiasma lying between the medulla and the lobula/lobula plate of the optic lobe. Axons reverse the anterior posterior order between the medulla and the lobula, with axons from the anterior medulla columns projecting to the lateral lobula columns.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi12
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron with fine, extensive and bushy arborizations in medulla layers M2, M8 and M9.

label: abdominal 5 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 1 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the first abdominal neuromere.

label: abdominal 6 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 2 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the second abdominal neuromere.

label: narrow field transmedullary neuron
description: A transmedullary neuron that whose arborizations are restricted to a single column. Typically, wide-field transmedullary neurons that contact layers which photoreceptors R7 and R8 innervate, project to more superficial domains in the lobula compared to those wide-field transmedullary neurons that only have arborizations in the lower medulla, and do not contact the terminals of photoreceptors R7 and R8 (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: optic column
description: A subdivision of the optic lobe neuropil that maps to a single ommatidium. In the lamina and distal medulla these correspond to the projections and arborization of photoreceptor cells. Narrow field columnar neurons define continuation of these columns medial to this.

label: abdominal 7 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 3 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the third abdominal neuromere.

label: thoracic posterior commissure
description: Any posterior commissure (FBbt:00001120) that is part of some nervous system of embryonic/larval thorax (FBbt:00007485).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi8
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron with a bushy mix of bleb-type and fine terminal arborization in layers M1-3. The projection of this neuron branches at the boundary with M10 to form varicose recurrent terminal specializations that extend back through M9.

label: abdominal 1 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: thoracic 1 posterior commissure
description: Any thoracic posterior commissure (FBbt:00001121) that is part of some embryonic prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000168).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi11
description: Medullary intrinsic wide-field neuron with extensive fine arborizations in medulla layers M6, M8, M9, M10 and the serpentine layer (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: abdominal 2 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: thoracic 2 posterior commissure
description: Any thoracic posterior commissure (FBbt:00001121) that is part of some embryonic mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000169).

label: abdominal 3 vch neuron
description: Any abdominal vch neuron (FBbt:00002452) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: thoracic 3 posterior commissure
description: Any thoracic posterior commissure (FBbt:00001121) that is part of some embryonic metathoracic segment (FBbt:00000170).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi10a
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron with both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layers M3, M4, M5 and M8, but with only fine arborizations in medulla layer M9. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: abdominal 4 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the fourth abdominal neuromere.

label: abdominal vch1 neuron
description: Neuron of abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1. Fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: vch1 neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 of the ventral cluster in a larval segment.

label: abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ of larval abdominal segments 1-7, innervated by a single neuron - vch1 (vchA).

label: abdominal 1 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002905).

label: abdominal 1 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 5 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the fifth abdominal neuromere.

label: transmedullary neuron Tm5
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layer 5 with bleb-type arborizations. It displays fine arborizations in medulla layers M3 and M6 and other, depending on the subtype. It has bleb-type terminals in layers M6 and M8. It has three subtypes.

label: transmedullary Y neuron TmY5a
description: Transmedullary Y narrow field neuron that terminates with both fine and bleb-type arborizations in lobula layers 4, 5 and 6, and in lobula plate layer 3, but only has fine arborizations in lobula plate layer 1. It displays both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layers M6 and M8, and has fine arborizations in medulla layers M2, M3, M4, M5 and M9 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich (1989). It receives input from Tm4 (Takemura et al., 2013).

label: abdominal 2 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 2 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002906).

label: abdominal 2 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 6 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the sixth abdominal neuromere.

label: abdominal 7 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 7 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002911).

label: abdominal 7 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: transmedullary neuron Tm11
description: Transmedullary wide-field neuron that terminates in lobula layer 5 with both fine and bleb-type arborizations. It displays fine arborizations in medulla layers M6, M8 and M9, and has bleb-type arborizations in layers M6 and M8 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: wide field transmedullary neuron
description: A transmedullary neuron that arborizes across multiple columns. Typically, narrow field transmedullary neurons that contact only one of the medulla layers to which the photoreceptors R7 or R8 project to (mainly M6 and M3, respectively), have very discrete axonal projections with small terminals in the most superficial lobula layers; whereas narrow field transmedullary neurons that arborize in layers which are innervated by photoreceptors R7 and R8, project deeper to an intermediate layer of the lobula.

label: transmedullary neuron Tm10
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layers 2, 3 and 4 with both fine and bleb-type arborizations. It displays fine arborizations in medulla layers M1, M3, M6 and M9, and has bleb-type arborizations in layer M1.

label: abdominal vesA neuron
description: Sensory neuron of vc1. Fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: vesA neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7, the pro-, meta- or mesothoracic segments (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). In the thoracic segments it innervates the anterior lateral hair of the Keilin's organ. In the abdominal segments it is located ventral to vesB.

label: abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: A campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7. It is the ventral-most sensillum of these segments, and is innervated by the dendrite of a single neuron - vesA.

label: proneural cluster
description: An equivalence group of the neurectoderm where all cells can, although only one will, become a neural progenitor cell.

label: abdominal 1 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002864).

label: abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: C1 chordotonal organ precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell which delaminates during stage 10 and which is a precursor of lch5.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system.

label: abdominal 3 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 3 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002907).

label: abdominal 3 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 7 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the seventh abdominal neuromere.

label: transmedullary neuron Tm7
description: Transmedullary wide-field neuron that terminates in lobula layer 5 with both fine and bleb-type arborizations. It has fine arborizations in medulla layers M3, M4, M6 and M8, and bleb-type arborizations in layer M6 (Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989; Morante and Desplan, 2008). It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: abdominal 4 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 4 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002908).

label: abdominal 4 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 8 posterior commissure
description: Posterior commissure of the eighth abdominal neuromere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm8a
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. It branches extensively in medulla layer M6A and extends small centrifugal processes to medulla layer M4. The highest arbor density is found in the center of the cell, within one column, with these regions tiling, while the whole arbor overlaps considerably. In medulla layer M6A, it extends over 10-15 columns in both the anterior-posterior and dorsal-ventral axes. In layer M6A, it is postsynaptic to photoreceptor cells R7 (Gao et al., 2008; Takemura et al., 2013) and R8 (Jagadish et al., 2014) and presynaptic to Tm5c (Gao et al., 2008; Karuppudurai et al., 2014). It also makes synaptic contacts with Tm9 (in M4) (Gao et al., 2008). The contacts with Tm5c are clustered in the center of the dendritic field of Dm8a, which corresponds to approximately one column. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Gao et al., 2008; Karuppudurai et al., 2014).

label: abdominal 5 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002909).

label: abdominal 5 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: presumptive embryonic/larval system
description: The sum of all the developing presumptive components of a specific embryonic/larval system in an embryo.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval nervous system.

label: abdominal 6 vch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002460) that is part of some abdominal 6 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002910).

label: abdominal 6 ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Any abdominal ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002904) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: anlage
description: Anlagen are populations of contiguous cells, typically arranged in one plane, that are morphologically indistinct, but that already correspond in extent to a later organ/tissue.

label: transmedullary neuron Tm8
description: Transmedullary wide-field neuron that terminates in lobula layers 5 and 6 with bleb-type arborizations. It displays fine arborizations in medulla layers M4, M6, M8 and M9, and has bleb-type arborizations in layers M4 and M8 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: peritreme of thoracic spiracle
description: The two-lipped external rim of an adult thoracic spiracle. Contraction of the spiracular occlusor muscle (FBbt:00013335) brings the two lips together, closing the spiracle.

label: peritreme of spiracle
description: The rim of an adult spiracle.

label: adult thoracic spiracle
description: A spiracle of the adult thorax. There are 2 pairs of these, in segments T2 and T3. Each has a two lipped external rim that can be closed by the action of an associated spiracular occlusor muscle (FBbt:00013335).

label: synaptic transmission, GABAergic
description: The process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA).

label: neuron-neuron synaptic transmission
description: The process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse.

label: abdominal 2 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 2 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002865).

label: abdominal 2 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 3 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002866).

label: abdominal 3 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: embryonic nervous system of thorax
description: The portion of the embryonic nervous system that is part of the thorax.

label: abdominal 4 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002867).

label: abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002868).

label: abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: catecholamine transport
description: The directed movement of catecholamines, a group of physiologically important biogenic amines that possess a catechol (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl) nucleus and are derivatives of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine.

label: monoamine transport
description: The directed movement of monoamines, organic compounds that contain one amino group that is connected to an aromatic ring by an ethylene group (-CH2-CH2-), into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: organic hydroxy compound transport
description: The directed movement of an organic hydroxy compound (organic alcohol) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. An organic hydroxy compound is an organic compound having at least one hydroxy group attached to a carbon atom.

label: abdominal 2 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 2 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002873).

label: abdominal vesB neuron
description: Sensory neuron of vc2. Fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: abdominal 2 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 3 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002874).

label: abdominal 3 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 6 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002869).

label: abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 vesA neuron
description: Any abdominal vesA neuron (FBbt:00002468) that is part of some abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002870).

label: abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002863) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: vesB neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7, the pro-, meta- or mesothoracic segments (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). In the thoracic segments it innervates the anterior medial hair of the Keilin's organ, together with the vesC neuron. In the abdominal segments it is located dorsal to vesA and ventral to vesC.

label: abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: A ventrally located campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7, innervated by the dendrite of a single neuron - vesB. Fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: abdominal 1 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002872).

label: abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 5 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002876).

label: abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002877).

label: abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002878).

label: abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal vesC neuron
description: Sensory neuron of vc3. Fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: vesC neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7, the pro-, meta- or mesothoracic segments (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). In the thoracic segments it innervates the anterior medial hair of the Keilin's organ, together with the vesB neuron. In the abdominal segments it is located dorsal to vesB.

label: abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3
description: A ventrally located campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7, innervated by the dendrite of a single neuron - vesC. The tormogen (socket) cell of this sensillum is unusual in having numerous short cytoplasmic extensions (Barolo et al., 2000). It fasciculates in branch c of the segmental nerve, SNc (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: abdominal 4 vesB neuron
description: Any abdominal vesB neuron (FBbt:00002476) that is part of some abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002875).

label: abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002871) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 vesC neuron
description: Any abdominal vesC neuron (FBbt:00002484) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3 (FBbt:00002884).

label: abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3 (FBbt:00002879) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 1 vesC neuron
description: Any abdominal vesC neuron (FBbt:00002484) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3 (FBbt:00002880).

label: abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc3 (FBbt:00002879) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 vesC neuron

label: salivary canal
description: An epithelial tube that runs from the salivary pump, with which it is continuous, through the hypopharynx and opens at its tip into the labial groove.

label: adult salivary gland
description: The salivary gland of the adult. It consists of two slender long, unbranched epithelial tubes of secretory epithelium that taper to form narrow ducts at their anterior end, which join to an unpaired duct (FBbt:00003137) in the neck region. The common duct connects to the salivary canal which runs through the hypopharynx and opens at its tip into the labial groove. The posterior ends of the lobes of the gland extend straight through the thorax on either side of the ventriculus and end in compact blind coils in the base of the abdomen. A suspensory muscle (FBbt:00003542) is attached to the anterior end of each lobe, near the cardia. (Miller, 1950 pg 440-1, 451).

label: adult salivary gland proper
description: The secretory part of the adult salivary gland, located posterior to the left and right salivary gland ducts. It consists of an epithelial tube 5-10 cells around surrounded by a thin basement membrane. The cells are cuboidal cells with small basal nuclei and a single large vacuole which fills most of the cell.

label: gland
description: Any multicellular structure (FBbt:00100313) that capable of some secretion (GO:0046903).

label: epithelial tube
description: A tubular epithelium.

label: saliva secretion
description: The regulated release of saliva from the salivary glands. In man, the saliva is a turbid and slightly viscous fluid, generally of an alkaline reaction, and is secreted by the parotid, submaxillary, and sublingual glands. In the mouth the saliva is mixed with the secretion from the buccal glands. In man and many animals, saliva is an important digestive fluid on account of the presence of the peculiar enzyme, ptyalin.

label: abdominal v'esA neuron
description: Sensory neuron of vc4. Fasciculates in branch b of the intersegmental nerve, ISNb (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: v'esA neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7, the pro-, meta- or mesothoracic segments (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). In the abdominal segments it is located dorsal to vesC, and ventral to v'esB. In the thoracic segments 2 and 3 it is located ventral to the cluster of vesA-E neurons, but is located anterior to it in thoracic segment T1.

label: intersegmental nerve branch ISNb of A1-7
description: A ventral branch of the intersegmental nerve of segments A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve. Its branching point is dorsal to that of ISNd. It consists mostly of motorneuron axons whose soma is located in the next anterior segment, which innervate various ventral somatic muscles including muscles VO1-3 and VL1.

label: abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4b
description: A ventrally located campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7, innervated by the dendrite of a single neuron - v'esA.

label: abdominal 1 v'esA neuron
description: Any abdominal v'esA neuron (FBbt:00002492) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4b (FBbt:00002896).

label: adult VLPl1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl1.

label: adult DM3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast DM3.

label: ellipsoid body
description: A doughnut shaped synaptic neuropil domain of the central complex of the adult brain that lies just anterior to the fan-shaped body. Its hole (the ellipsoid body canal) points anteriorly and has an axon tract (the anterior bundle) running through it. It is divided into concentric layers and into 16 radial segments, 8 per hemisphere, numbered 1-8 from superior medial to inferior medial.

label: fan-shaped body
description: The largest synaptic neuropil domain of the adult central complex, covered by an extensive glial sheath. It is located posterior to the ellipsoid body. The fan-shaped body is a regular structure of 6-8 horizontal layers and 16 vertical slices (sometimes called staves, columns or segments), 8 per hemisphere numbered from medial to lateral - arranged in 4 closely associated pairs. Its inferior part is much narrower than its superior part, forming a fan shape. Fibers emerging from the basal-most area of the fan project to the noduli. Rostro-caudally, it can be divided into 4 shells on the basis of the extent and position of small field arborizations.

label: nodulus
description: Paired synaptic neuropil domain of the adult brain located just caudal to the ellipsoid body and ventral to the fan-shaped body, on either side of the midline. It is a glomerular structure composed of 4 subunits: three subunits are stacked as discs and the fourth subunit is posterior to these. There is asymmetry between the noduli, with one nodulus always lying slightly more anterior than the other.

label: adult DM3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DM3 (FBbt:00050100).

label: adult VPNd1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNd1.

label: adult VPNd1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNd1 (FBbt:00050106).

label: adult VLPl1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl1 (FBbt:00050103).

label: adult SMPpv2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPpv2 (FBbt:00050112).

label: adult SMPpv2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPpv2.

label: prow
description: Anteriormost and superior synaptic neuropil domain below the esophagus. It lies inferior and anterior to the opening of the esophageal foramen. It houses the superior pharyngeal sensory center (SPhS), containing the terminals of peripheral axons from the pharyngeal nerve.

label: adult VESa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VESa1.

label: adult LHd2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHd2.

label: adult LHd2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHd2 (FBbt:00050115).

label: adult VESa2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VESa2.

label: adult VESa2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VESa2 (FBbt:00050109).

label: adult ostiolar valve
description: An ostiolar valve of the adult heart. These consist of deep inflections in the heart wall around each ostium, forming a pair of inwardly projecting flaps that acts as a valve.

label: ostiolar valve
description: A pair of inwardly directed, striated muscle flaps that flank each ostium, forming a valve. Each flap consists of a single cardiomyocyte.

label: adult heart
description: The caudal, pulsatile region of the adult dorsal vessel. It extends from the first to the sixth abdominal segment, lying just below the surface of the cuticle, and has four pairs of ostia (Curtis et al., 1999). It is supported along the midline of the body by a series of paired alary muscles, suspensory fibrils and a rudimentary dorsal diaphragm (Miller, 1950). The caudal end is closed and is attached to the 6th abdominal tergite and to the dorsal wall of the rectal sac. The wall of the heart consists of a single muscular layer containing circular striated fibers and scattered lateral nuclei. On the ventral side, an outer layer or longitudinal muscles extends the whole length except for the caudal end.

label: embryonic nervous system of abdomen
description: The portion of the embryonic nervous system that is part of the abdomen.

label: adult abdominal pericardial cell
description: Pericardial cell of the adult abdomen. These are serially arranges in a row of 20-25 on each side of the hear from the first to the 6th segment.

label: adult pericardial cell
description: A discrete, large, ovoid cell attached to the dorsal diaphragm in the abdomen and near the anterior end of the ventriculus in the thorax. Some of these cells are binucleate.

label: adult abdomen
description: Abdomen of the adult.

label: adult thoracic pericardial cell
description: Pericardial cell of the adult thorax. These cells are binucleate. There are about 10 on each side, anterior and lateral to the cardia, associated with the lower wall of the trachea leading to the fist spiracle and with the adult salivary gland suspensor muscle (FBbt:00003542).

label: adult thorax
description: Thorax of the adult.

label: adult VLPl&p2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl&p2 (FBbt:00050145).

label: adult VLPl&p2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl&p2.

label: reflex
description: An automatic response to a stimulus beginning with a nerve impulse from a receptor and ending with the action of an effector such as a gland or a muscle. Signaling never reaches a level of consciousness.

label: response to external stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an external stimulus.

label: adult CREa1 (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa1 (female).

label: adult LHp2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHp2.

label: adult DM6 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast DM6.

label: neuroblast DM6
description: A type II neuroblast that produces mostly neurons and rarely glial cells (Viktorin et al., 2011).

label: adult DM6 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DM6 (FBbt:00050142).

label: adult LHp2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHp2 (FBbt:00050139).

label: signaling
description: The entirety of a process in which information is transmitted within a biological system. This process begins with an active signal and ends when a cellular response has been triggered.

label: biological_process
description: Any process specifically pertinent to the functioning of integrated living units: cells, tissues, organs, and organisms. A process is a collection of molecular events with a defined beginning and end.

label: adult VLPa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPa1.

label: adult VLPa1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPa1 (FBbt:00050157).

label: adult SLPal4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal4 (FBbt:00050154).

label: adult SLPal4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal4.

label: adult CREa1 (female) lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast CREa1 (female) (FBbt:00050148).

label: adult SLPal3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal3.

label: adult SLPal3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal3 (FBbt:00050151).

label: signal release
description: The process in which a signal is secreted or discharged into the extracellular medium from a cellular source.

label: secretion by cell
description: The controlled release of a substance by a cell.

label: cell-cell signaling
description: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another. This process includes signal transduction in the receiving cell and, where applicable, release of a ligand and any processes that actively facilitate its transport and presentation to the receiving cell.  Examples include signaling via soluble ligands, via cell adhesion molecules and via gap junctions.

label: adult SLPad1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPad1.

label: adult SLPad1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPad1 (FBbt:00050124).

description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DM2 (FBbt:00050121).

description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv3 (FBbt:00050127).

description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv3.

label: adult VESa1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VESa1 (FBbt:00050118).

label: BAla3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAla3 neuroblast (VESa1).

label: integument of larval segment A1-7
description: The integument of the larval abdominal segments.

label: embryonic/larval prothoracic lateral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located laterally on each side of the prothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval metathoracic dorsal sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located dorsally on each side of the metathoracic segment.

label: integument of larval metathoracic segment
description: The integument of the larval metathoracic segment.

label: adult EBa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast EBa1.

label: adult VLPa2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPa2.

label: embryonic/larval mesothoracic ventral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located ventrally on each side of the mesothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval T2/3 ventral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located ventrally on each side of the larval mesothoracic and metathoracic segments.

label: adult VLPa2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPa2 (FBbt:00050133).

label: embryonic/larval metathoracic ventral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located ventrally on each side of the metathoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval prothoracic ventral sensory cluster
description: A paired cluster of sense organs and multi-dendritic sensory neurons located ventrally on each side of the prothoracic segment.

description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast EBa1 (FBbt:00050136).

label: embryonic/larval mesothoracic lateral sensory cluster

label: embryonic/larval T2/3 lateral sensory cluster

description: Any mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000018) that is part of some larval thorax (FBbt:00001741).

label: larval metathoracic segment

label: adult FLAa2 lineage neuron

label: embryonic/larval head nerve
description: Any nerve (FBbt:00005105) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: nerve
description: A bundle of axons connecting the peripheral nervous system to the central nervous system.

label: cardial cell
description: Contractile cell which forms the inner, contractile tube of the dorsal vessel.

label: detection of stimulus involved in sensory perception
description: The series of events involved in sensory perception in which a sensory stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: sensory perception, sensory transduction of stimulus

label: hypodermal muscle of A1-7
description: Muscles that are part of the body wall of larval abdominal segments A1-7. These muscles are usually innervated by three motorneurons: a specific glutamatergic motor neuron via type Ib terminal boutons, a common glutamatergic motor neuron via type Is boutons and a common modulatory motorneuron via type II or III terminal boutons.

label: adult oenocyte band
description: One cell thick band of oenocytes that lies under the surface of an adult abdominal segment.

label: abdominal intersegmental nerve
description: Any intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00001997) that is part of some larval abdominal segment (FBbt:00001747).

label: ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron developing from the VUM midline precursor. It innervates the ventral oblique and longitudinal muscles.

label: VUM motorneuron
description: Ventral unpaired median motorneuron that is part of the median neuroblast lineage that innervates the larval body wall muscles. There are three of these cells per segment. They are modulatory motor neurons, with one VUM motor neuron innervating the dorsal, and the other the ventral ISN innervated muscles; the third VUM neuron innervates the SN innervated lateral muscles.

label: VUM precursor
description: Midline precursor neuroblast of the ventral nerve cord located posteriorly to MP3 precursor and anteriorly to MNB neuroblast. It gives rise to one motorneuron and one interneuron. There are 3 VUM precursors in each segment (MP4-6).

label: adult AOTUv2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv2 (FBbt:00050181).

label: adult AOTUv2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv2.

label: deutocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the deutocerebrum.

label: adult DL1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast DL1.

label: adult DL1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DL1 (FBbt:00050184).

label: adult FLAa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast FLAa1.

label: embryonic aortic cardioblast
description: Cardioblast which is the precursor of cardial cells of the aorta. These cells become distinct from heart cardioblasts during stage 14: they remain small and cuboidal while the heart cardioblasts enlarge and elongate to become columnar.

label: embryonic cardioblast
description: Precursor of cardial cells that make the inner, contractile layer of the dorsal vessel. These cells become morphologically distinct during stage 14, when they stretch, flatten and develop dorsally directed processes. During dorsal closure, they squeeze between the amnioserosa and epidermis. The dorsal vessel is formed when cardioblasts from the left and right side of the embryo meet at the midline and interdigitate dorsally and ventrally, with the medial surface forming the lumen.

label: embryonic ostial cardioblast
description: An embryonic heart cardioblast that forms the embryonic/larval ostia. These cardioblasts become distinct during late stages of embryogenesis. They are found in metamerically repeated clusters close to the sites of attachment of alary muscles.

label: embryonic heart cardioblast
description: Cardioblast which is a precursor of embryonic/larval heart cardial cell. During stage 14, these cells increase in size and elongate in the transverse axis to adopt a columnar shape.

label: dorsal vessel primordium
description: Primordium that makes the inner, contractile layer of the embryonic/larval dorsal vessel. This primordium originates in the mesodermal crest on each side of the embryo. Its component cells (embryonic cardioblasts) become distinct by stage 14. The dorsal vessel is formed by fusion of left and right primordia during, and immediately following, dorsal closure.

label: embryonic/larval cardial cell
description: Contractile cell that forms the inner tube of the embryonic/larval dorsal vessel.

label: intersegmental nerve branch ISNd of A1-7
description: A ventral branch of the intersegmental nerve of segments A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve. Its branching point is ventral to that of ISNb. It consists mostly of motorneuron axons whose soma is located in the next anterior segment, which innervate various ventral somatic muscles.

label: epidermal cell
description: Any epithelial cell (FBbt:00000124) that is part of some epidermis (FBbt:00004993).

label: epidermis
description: Tissue composed of epithelial cells. It secretes and underlies the cuticle.

label: adult SMPp&v1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPp&v1.

label: adult SMPp&v1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPp&v1 (FBbt:00050193).

label: adult FLAa1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast FLAa1 (FBbt:00050190).

label: adult VLPp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPp1.

label: adult ALv1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast ALv1.

label: adult ALv1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALv1 (FBbt:00067348).

label: BAla1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAla1 neuroblast (ALv1).

label: antennal segment 3 thermosensory organ
description: Thermosensory organ of antennal segment 3.

label: thermosensitive sensory organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that capable of some detection of temperature stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050961).

label: antennal segment 3 sensillum
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some third segment of antenna (FBbt:00004515).

label: detection of temperature stimulus involved in thermoception
description: The series of events in which a temperature stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal as part of thermoception.
synonyms: thermoception, sensory detection of thermal stimulus

label: third segment of antenna
description: Largest segment of the antenna. It is bulbous, light grey in colour and it bears numerous hairs and sensilla, including sensilla trichoidea, basiconica, intermedia and coeloconica. It has an articulated joint with the second segment of the antenna. It contains the sacculus.

label: Pcv6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the ventral central protocerebrum.

label: ventral central protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the ventral region of the central protocerebrum.

label: embryonic/larval intercalary segment sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some larval intercalary segment (FBbt:00001736).

label: intercalary segment sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some intercalary segment (FBbt:00000010).

label: larval intercalary segment
description: Any intercalary segment (FBbt:00000010) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: Pcv7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the ventral central protocerebrum.

label: tagmatic subdivision of organ system
description: The part of an organ system that is part of some specified tagma.

label: AC thermosensory neuron
description: Thermosensory neuron located in the adult brain, anterior to the antennal lobe, that is necessary for warmth avoidance behavior (Hamada et al., 2008). AC thermosensory neurons innervate the antennal lobe glomerulus compartments VL2a and VL2p, with dendrites extending from the cell body. Its axon branches near the antennal lobe, projecting obliquely towards the ipsilateral posterior superior lateral protocerebrum before branching again to give extensive symmetrical arborizations in the superior medial protocerebrum in both hemispheres. The AC neurons are serotonergic (Shih and Chiang, 2011).

label: serotonergic neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some serotonin secretion, neurotransmission (GO:0060096).

label: thermosensory neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some detection of temperature stimulus involved in thermoception (GO:0050960).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VL2p
description: Posterior- and ventral-most compartment of glomerulus VL2. It lies along the ventroposterior edge of the anterior compartment, and dorsolateral to glomerulus VL1.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VL2 posterior compartment

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VL2a
description: Anterior- and dorsal-most compartment of glomerulus VL2. It lies along the dorsoanterior edge of the posterior compartment, and ventrolateral to the dorsal compartment of glomerulus DL2.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VL2 anterior compartment

label: Pcv5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the ventral central protocerebrum.

label: multicellular structure
description: Anatomical structure that has multiple cells as parts.

label: segmental subdivision of organ system
description: The part of some organism that is part of some specified segment.

label: Pcv1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the ventral central protocerebrum.

label: A1-7 DT1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB3-2 lineage that innervates the dorsal transverse muscle 1 of abdominal segments 1 to 7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior intersegmental nerve root nerve fasciculating with the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DT1 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: DT1 motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some dorsal transverse muscle (FBbt:00000471) and that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911).

label: A1-7 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: The only dorsal transverse muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: adult LALv1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LALv1.

label: eye photoreceptor cell
description: Photoreceptor cell that forms the core of each ommatidium in the adult eye. Eight of these photoreceptors are arranged in each ommatidial core, bundled like the staves of a barrel. Each has a photosensitive rhabdomere that projects into the barrel cavity and adjacent supporting membrane, the stalk (Wolff and Ready, 1993). Each extends an axon into the optic lobe. Activation of the photoreceptor by light results in depolarization and in histamine release at the synapses of these axons (Sarthy, 1991).

label: histaminergic neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some histamine secretion, neurotransmission (GO:0061538).

label: detection of light stimulus involved in visual perception
description: The series of events involved in visual perception in which a light stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: visual perception, sensory transduction of light stimulus

label: histamine secretion, neurotransmission
description: The controlled release of histamine by a cell, in which the histamine acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: ommatidium
description: One of the facets of the compound eye. It is composed of eight light-sensing photoreceptor cells (photoreceptor cell R1-R8) and accessory cells. There are around 800 ommatidia in each compound eye.

label: VT1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron from neuroblast NB4-1 lineage that innervates the external ventral transverse muscle 1.

label: ventral transverse muscle 1
description: Anterior-most ventral transverse muscle.

label: adult LALv1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LALv1 (FBbt:00050166).

label: BAmv1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the LALv1 (BAmv1) neuroblast.

label: A1-7 SBM motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB2-4 lineage that innervates the external segment border muscle of abdominal segments 1 to 7. The motor neuron exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root nerve fasciculating with the SNa nerve branch and innervates the SBM muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: SBM motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the segment border muscle.

label: A1-7 segment border muscle
description: Any segment border muscle (FBbt:00000483) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: neuroblast NB2-4
description: Neuroblast NB2-4 delaminates at S4 and generates a contralaterally projecting motorneuron and approximately 8 local interneurons.

label: lateral oviduct circular muscle
description: A striated array of circular muscle fibers forming an almost continuous sheet around the lateral oviduct.

label: adult circular muscle
description: Circular muscle of the adult. It surrounds the intestinal tract and ducts of the reproductive system, together with a layer of longitudinal muscle.

label: lateral oviduct
description: Epithelial tube that connects an ovary to the common oviduct. It is lined with a chitinous intima.

label: dorsal transverse muscle
description: The only dorsally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature with a transverse orientation. It is only present in the abdominal segments.

label: serotonergic SP1 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in the anterodorsal brain. There is a cluster of neurons in each hemisphere. In adults, there are three neurons per cluster, with two of these being generated during metamorphosis.

label: serotonergic SP neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron of the larval or adult brain located in one of two groups in the supraesophageal ganglion, in either the anterodorsal cortex (SP1) or slightly more posteriorly but also in the dorsal cortex region (SP2) (Valles and White, 1988).

label: inner photoreceptor cell
description: Eye photoreceptor cell whose rhabdomere is located in the centre of each ommatidium.

label: A1-7 LO1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB3-3 lineage that innervates the external lateral oblique muscle 1 of abdominal segments 1 to 7. The motor neuron exits the ventral nerve cord via the segmental nerve root nerve fasciculating with the SNa nerve branch and innervates the LO1 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: A1-7 lateral oblique muscle 1
description: The only lateral oblique muscle in each of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: neuroblast NB3-3
description: Neuroblast NB3-3 delaminates predominantly at S4 (Schmidt et al., 1997). It generates a single motorneuron positioned midway along the dorsoventral axis, though slightly lateral and posterior. It also generates 10-18 interneurons that project across the anterior commissure (Schmid et al., 1999). In the third instar larva, the lineage originated by this neuroblast is located at the ventro-lateral anterior half of the neuromere.

label: abdominal nerve to the ovary
description: Paired nerve that branches from the abdominal nerve trunk and projects to the junction of the ovaries and the lateral oviduct where it branches repeatedly. Some branches radiate anteriorly across the peritoneal sheath, on which they terminate, mainly in the anterior two thirds of the ovary. Varicosities occur along these branches as well as at their ends. These branches do not penetrate the peritoneal sheath. Other branches innervate the lateral oviduct and the upper portion of the common oviduct. Two types of branches innervate the common oviduct - wandering fibers similar to those on the peritoneal sheath, and branches running circularly, parallel to the underlying myofibers.

label: common oviduct circular muscle
description: A striated array of circular muscle fibers forming an almost continuous sheet around the common oviduct.

label: peritoneal sheath
description: A network of anastomosing muscle fibers that covers the ovary. The muscle is striated with an irregular interdigitation of thick and thin filaments and perforated Z-discs.

label: abdominal nerve trunk
description: An unpaired nerve that projects posteriorly in a medial line from the posterior of the abdominal neuropile.

label: Pcv8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the ventral central protocerebrum.

label: segment border muscle
description: An embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle that runs along the transverse apodeme at the segment boundary.

label: abdominal nerve to the uterus
description: Paired nerve that branches from the abdominal nerve trunk and projects to the uterus where it innervated both the extrinsic muscles and the circular muscle fibers. One branch projects to the inner layers of the uterus.

label: uterine circular muscle
description: Circular muscle that surrounds the adult female uterus.

label: Pcv9 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 9 of the ventral central protocerebrum.

label: adult VPNp&v1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp&v1.

label: adult VPNp&v1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNp&v1 (FBbt:00050160).

label: adult PSp2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast PSp2 (FBbt:00050163).

label: adult PSp2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast PSp2.

label: ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Third-most dorsal of the ventral oblique muscles.

label: antennal coeloconic sensillum C2
description: Coeloconic sensillum of antennal segment 3 that is innervated by two olfactory receptor neuron dendrites.

label: sensillum coeloconicum of antennal segment 3
description: Olfactory sensillum coeloconicum that is part of antennal segment 3. A short conical peg arising from a broad basal platform, basally smooth but distally having deep longitudinal grooves. The peg has a double cuticular wall. The inner wall encloses a central lumen innervated by olfactory receptor neuron dendrites. Distally, the central lumen is connected to the outer, sensillum lymph-filled chamber by radial spoke channels.

label: embryonic/larval midgut longitudinal visceral muscle
description: Longitudinal muscle of the embryonic or larval visceral muscles of the midgut.

label: embryonic/larval visceral muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic/larval intestinal tract. Circular and longitudinal fibers surround the entire intestinal tract, with the exception of the recurrent layer of the proventriculus. The circular fibers derive from a bilaterally symmetrical band of mesodermal cells extending continuously throughout most of the germ band. The longitudinal fibers derive from clusters of mesodermal cells which appear during stage 12 at the posterior end of the embryo and migrate anteriorly.

label: A1-7 VO3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB4-2 lineage. It innervates the internal ventral oblique muscle 3 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the medial domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve, fasciculating with the ISNb nerve branch and innervates the VO3 muscle with type Ib boutons.

label: VO3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing that innervates the ventral oblique muscle 3.

label: A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: neuroblast NB4-2
description: Neuroblast NB4-2 delaminates at S2 in the intermediate column and produces the well characterized RP2 motorneuron (FBbt:00001453), which innervates muscles 2, 9 and 11. It also produces the Cousins if RP2 motorneurons (CoR), which generate the entirety of the SNc, innervating muscles 26, 27 and 29. It also generates local interneurons and, in a small number of cases, an epidermal subclone (http://www.neuro.uoregon.edu/doelab/lineages/NB4-2.html).

label: antennal coeloconic sensillum C3
description: Coeloconic sensillum of antennal segment 3 that is innervated by three olfactory receptor neuron dendrites.

label: multi-tissue structure
description: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more portions of tissue of at least two different types and which, through specific morphogenetic processes, forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct structural units of different types.

label: wing pouch
description: Region of dorsal mesothoracic disc that will develop into the wing blade. Its boundary is delimited by folds in the third instar disc epithelium. The cells in this region can also be distinguished from surrounding cells in the third instar disc by their basal accumulation of lipid granules. The wing pouch is bisected by the anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the disc.

label: wing
description: A flight organ of the adult external thorax that is derived from a dorsal mesothoracic disc.

label: A2-7 VT1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from neuroblast NB4-1 lineage that innervates the ventral transverse muscle 1 of abdominal segments 2 to 7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the transverse nerve root fasciculating with the transverse nerve.

label: TN motor neuron of A1-7
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscles of larval abdominal segments A1-7 and which fasciculates with the transverse nerve. Its soma is located in the same segment of the muscle it innervates. The dendritic domain of the motor neuron is located posteriorly to the dendritic domain of the motorneurons of ISN motor neurons.

label: A2-7 ventral transverse muscle 1
description: The only ventral transverse muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 2-7 (this muscle is absent from abdominal segment 1).

label: neuroblast NB4-1
description: Neuroblast NB4-1 delaminates at S3 in the medial column. It produces the putative motorneuron of the transverse nerve (FBbt:00001996) and a variety of intersegmental and local interneurons. In the third instar larva, the lineage originated by this neuroblast is located anteriorly in the medial region of the hemineuromere. In the larva, it resumes proliferation in all thoracic segments. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 14.

label: transverse nerve root of A1-7
description: The continuation of the neurite bundle and associated glia of the transverse nerve in abdominal segments A1-7.

label: transverse nerve of A1-7
description: Transverse nerve of segments A1-7. It contains the axons of motor neurons that innervate the same segment in which their soma is located.

label: thoracic neuroblast d
description: A neuroblast that is part of one of the three bilateral pairs of deep (rather than superficial) neuroblasts, located rostral to the single medial neuroblast in each larval thoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval neuroblast
description: Any neuroblast (FBbt:00005146) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: thoracic neuroblast
description: Any neuroblast (FBbt:00005146) that is part of some thorax (FBbt:00000015).

label: larval thoracic segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some larval thorax (FBbt:00001741).

label: somatic stem cell
description: Stem cell that is a progenitor of somatic cells.

label: stem cell
description: Undifferentiated cell which retains its identity while budding off cells which differentiate.

label: longitudinal visceral muscle primordium
description: This primordium first becomes distinct at around stage 11 as a group of cells at the posterior tip of the visceral mesoderm (the tail end of the germ-band). During germ-band retraction these cells migrate anteriorly and split into two clusters - one on either side of the posterior midgut primordium. When these cell reach the anterior tip of the posterior midgut primordium they disperse anteriorly as two rows along the germband. Finally, during midgut closure these cells spread regularly over the underlying circular visceral muscle primordium.

label: adult serotonergic LP2 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell bodies are located in 2 pairs of clusters (a and b) in the adult brain in the cortex of optic peduncle, adjacent to the medulla layer. These cells are born during metamorphosis. There are 8-10 neurons in this cluster.

label: gonadal somatic stem cell
description: Any somatic stem cell (FBbt:00007344) that is part of some gonad (FBbt:00004858).

label: gonad
description: The organ of the reproductive system in which the germ cells reside.

label: ventral transverse muscle
description: A ventrally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature with a transverse orientation.

label: thoracic neuroblast b
description: Neuroblast located in two pairs, lateral to the M neuroblast, on the ventral border of each thoracic neuromere of the larva.

label: pharate adult
description: The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.

label: organism
description: An individual member of the species Drosophila melanogaster.

label: pupa
description: The pupa is the name given to the organism at the period of the life cycle that begins once larval/pupal apolysis is complete, as indicated by the expulsion of the larval armature. Early in this stage the legs and wings reach full extension along the abdomen. The stage ends when the pupal cuticle separates from the underlying epidermis (pupal/adult apolysis), and the eye cup becomes yellow at its periphery. The duration of this stage is approximately 32 hours at 25 degrees C, and spans from 132.2-164.3 hours after egg laying, or is the period of 12.2-44.3 hours after puparium formation.

label: haltere trichome
description: Trichome/hair of the haltere. Compared to wing hairs, they are smaller and present at a higher density.

label: trichome
description: Non-innervated projection of the cuticle around an actin-rich cellular process of an underlying epidermal cell.

label: VO4-6 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing that innervates the ventral oblique muscles 4, 5 and 6.

label: ventral oblique muscle 5
description: Second-most ventral of the ventral oblique muscles.

label: ventral oblique muscle 4
description: Fourth-most dorsal of the ventral oblique muscles.

label: ventral oblique muscle 6
description: Most ventral of the ventral oblique muscles.

label: adult FLAa3 (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast FLAa3 (female).

label: antennal sensillum trichodeum T2
description: Antennal segment 3 sensillum trichodeum innervated by the dendrites of two olfactory receptor neurons.

label: sensillum trichodeum of antennal segment 3
description: Olfactory sensillum of antennal segment 3 whose external sensory part is a sharply pointed hair arising from a conspicuous cylindrical base. The walls of the hair are perforated by irregularly distributed pores connecting to a lymph filled lumen containing 1-3 ORN dendrites, unbranched except occasionally near the hair tip.

label: adult peritracheal cell
description: Neuropeptide-expressing cell located at the base of the adult trachea (two per segment).

label: peritracheal cell
description: Neuropeptide-expressing cell located at the base of the trachea (one per hemisegment).

label: adult tracheal system
description: Tracheal system of the adult. It retains the same basic pattern of the larval tracheal system, except for the presence of air sacs and the disappearance of the last tracheal segment. It is composed of nine tracheal metameres.

label: A1-7 VO4/5 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB7-1 lineage. It innervates the internal ventral oblique muscles 4 and 5 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the medial domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve, fasciculating with the ISNd nerve branch and innervates the VO4 and VO5 muscles with type Ib boutons.

label: VO4/5 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing that innervates the ventral oblique muscles 4 and 5.

label: 7-1M
