description: Any embryonic/larval motor neuron (FBbt:00007675) that develops from some neuroblast NB7-1 (FBbt:00001380).

label: A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 5
description: The fifth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7. Its posterior end is attached to the anterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina1) of the segment immediately posterior to its segment of origin (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein 1985, fig 3.10).

label: A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7. Its posterior end is attached to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2) of the segment immediately posterior to its segment of origin (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein 1985, fig 3.10).

label: neuroblast NB7-1
description: Neuroblast NB7-1 is the largest neuroblast lineage generating 40 cells or more, including the U motorneurons and a large number of local interneurons. It also frequently generates the putative segment boundary cells. In the larva, it resumes proliferation in segments S3 to A1. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 3, located at the posterior border of the neuromere.

label: Tv neuron
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron whose cell body is located close to the lateral border of the thoracic neuromere, ventrolaterally to the ventrolateral tract of the midline. It projects its axon below the ventrolateral tract, central lateral and central intermediate tracts and approaches the dorsal median tract from below, where it arborizes extensively. It fasciculates with the contralateral Tv neuron and innervates the thoracic neurohemal organ. The Tv neuron is one of the neurons of the cluster of apterous-expressing neurons of the lateral cluster of the thorax. The arborization at the dorsal median tract of the 3 pairs of Tv neurons overlaps and extends until the region between the first and second abdominal neuromeres (Benveniste et al., 1998; Marques et al., 2003; Santos et al., 2007).

label: apterous-expressing neuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax Ap4
description: Interneuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax. It expresses apterous (FBgn0000099). It is the last neuron of the cluster to be generated, after the Ap3 neuron. It is a peptidergic neuron. In the larva, it corresponds to the Tv neuron that innervates the thoracic neurohemal organ.

label: endocrine neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some endocrine hormone secretion (GO:0060986).

label: embryonic/larval endocrine system
description: Endocrine system of the embryo/larva.

label: dorsal neurohemal organ
description: Bilaterally paired neurosecretory organ of the larval thoracic segments, formed by the axons of Tv neurons, wrapped around support cells, forming a compact, globular structure that projects dorsally above the surface of the central nervous system.

label: sensillar lymph space
description: Cuticle enclosed space within a sensillum that contains sensillar lymph.

label: antennal sensillum trichodeum T1
description: Antennal segment 3 sensillum trichodeum innervated by a single ORN dendrite.

label: embryonic/larval peritracheal cell
description: Cell located at the base of the larval trachea (one per hemisegment). It is part of a cluster of 3 cells, of which one is a non-neuronal peptidergic cell (PM cell). This peptidergic cell shows a complex morphology and extends several cytoplasmic processes. The two non-peptidergic cells (PMa cells) have less processes and are located adjacent to the branch point from which the transverse tracheal connective leaves the main longitudinal trachea (O'Brien and Taghert, 1998; Laneve et al., 2013).

label: embryonic/larval tracheal system
description: Tracheal system of the embryo or larva. The three larval instars retain the same basic pattern of the tracheal system, but with increasing complexity of branch trachea. It is composed of ten tracheal metameres.

label: stomodeum
description: The anterior part of the embryonic digestive system deriving from the stomodeal invagination of the ectoderm.

label: adult SMPad3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad3.

label: foregut anlage
description: Anlage of the embryonic foregut.

label: adult PBp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast PBp1.

label: dorsal closure embryo
description: A collective term for stages 13-15.

label: adult PBp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast PBp1 (FBbt:00050169).

label: late extended germ band embryo
description: A collective term for stages 11 and 12.

label: adult SLPal5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal5.

label: adult SLPal5 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal5 (FBbt:00050175).

label: adult SMPad3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad3 (FBbt:00050172).

label: FLAa3 (female) lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast FLAa3 (female) (FBbt:00050178).

label: basiconic sensillum LB-II2
description: Large olfactory sensillum basiconicum of antennal segment 3, with a pore size of about 100nm and a pore density of about 30 pores per square micrometer, innervated by 2 highly branched ORN dendrites.

label: large sensillum basiconicum of antennal segment 3
description: Large, blunt tipped, olfactory basiconic sensillum of antennal segment 3. The external sensory structure is perforated by pores, arranged along a complicated pattern of branched lines, that connect to a lymph-filled lumen containing the highly branched dendrites of 2-4 ORNs.

label: abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF
description: Multidendritic ddaF neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval abdominal segments.

label: dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF
description: Neuron whose cell body is located most dorsally in the dorsal group of dendritic arborization neurons. It has long primary and secondary branches marked by spiked protrusions (1-20um) along most of its length (Grueber et al., 2002).

label: dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron developing from the VUM midline precursor. It innervates the dorsal oblique and acute muscles.

label: basiconic sensillum LB-II4
description: Large olfactory sensillum basiconicum of antennal segment 3, with a pore size of about 100nm and a pore density of about 30 pores per square micrometer, innervated by 4 highly branched ORN dendrites.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF (FBbt:00006025) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: A1-7 VL2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that synapses to the ventral longitudinal muscle 2 of A1-7 with a type Ib bouton.

label: 3-1M
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911) and that develops from some neuroblast NB3-1 (FBbt:00001394).

label: A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: neuroblast NB3-1
description: Neuroblast NB3-1 delaminates at S3 in the medial column of neuroblasts. It generates the well characterized RP1 (FBbt:00001452), RP3 (FBbt:00001455), RP4 (FBbt:00001456) and RP5 (FBbt:00001457) motorneurons and a cluster of intersegmental interneurons. It also generates a variable number of local interneurons. In the third instar larva, the lineage originated by this neuroblast is located near the midline and corresponds to postembryonic lineage 4.

label: antenno-subesophageal tract
description: Tract that emerges from the root of the maxillary labial nerve in the inferior gnathal ganglion (GNG), connecting it to inferior-posterior surface of the antennal lobe. It contains axons projecting from the GNG to the antennal lobe.

label: ipsilateral tract
description: A tract of the central nervous system that does not cross the midline.

label: adult deutocerebrum
description: Deutocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: eo glial cell
description: Glial cell associated with eo neuron. Daughter of pIIb; sibling of pIIIb.

label: PNS glial cell
description: Glial cell that is part of the peripheral nervous system.

label: external sensory organ precursor cell IIb
description: Second-order precursor cell. It develops from external sensory organ precursor cell I, and divides to give rise to the thecogen cell and the neuron of an external sensory organ.

label: peripheral nervous system
description: The outer parts of the nervous system that perform sensory and motor functions.

label: ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: Second-most dorsal of the ventral longitudinal muscles.

label: basiconic sensillum LB-I
description: Large olfactory sensillum basiconicum of antennal segment 3, with a pore size of about 50nm and a pore density of about 19 pores per square micrometer, innervated by 2 highly branched ORN dendrites.

label: dorsal multidendritic neuron
description: Any multidendritic neuron (FBbt:00005209) that is part of some embryonic/larval thoracic/abdominal dorsal sensory cluster (FBbt:00007296).

label: antennal olfactory receptor neuron
description: Odorant receptor neuron (ORN) whose dendrite transduces signals from some antennal sensillum. The axons of these neurons fasciculate in the antennal nerve and innervate the antennal lobe.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron
description: Any olfactory receptor neuron (FBbt:00005926) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004).

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of smell
description: The series of events involved in the perception of smell in which an olfactory chemical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: sensory transduction of chemical stimulus during perception of smell

label: adult antennal nerve
description: Nerve carrying the majority of afferents to the antennal lobe. Near its entrance to the brain it consists of about 1700-1800 axons. Approximately 1200 of these are sensory fibers from the third antennal segment, mainly axons from olfactory receptor neurons that project into the antennal lobe ventrally, at its antero-ventral corner (Stocker and Gendre, 1988; Kamikouchi et al., 2006). The remaining 500-600 fibers stem mainly from Johnston's organ neurons and mechanosensory sensilla of the anterior head capsule (Kamikouchi et al., 2006). These axons bypass the antennal lobe and target various neuropil domains including the antennal mechanosensory and motor center.

label: antenna
description: Paired, segmented, jointed, sensory appendage attached to the anterior of the head capsule, between the eyes.

label: lch5 ligament attachment cell
description: A cell that anchors the scolopidial ligament cell of abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 to the cuticle.

label: abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Pentascolopidial chordotonal organ located in the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval abdominal segment. Dendrites from this chordotonal organ point dorsoposteriorly.

label: A1-7 VO4-6 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the neuroblast NB7-1 lineage. It innervates the internal ventral oblique muscles 4, 5 and 6 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7 (for VO6, only A2-A7). Its dendritic arborization occupies the medial domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve, fasciculating with the ISNd nerve branch and innervates the VO4, VO5 and VO6 muscles with type Ib boutons.

label: A2-7 ventral oblique muscle 6
description: The sixth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 2-7.

label: maxillary palp olfactory receptor neuron
description: Odorant receptor neuron (ORN) whose dendrite transduces signals from some maxillary palp basiconic sensillum. The axons of these neurons fasciculate in the labial nerve and the antenno-subesophageal tract (AST) and innervate the antennal lobe.

label: adult labial nerve
description: The labial nerve is a mixed sensory-motor nerve of the gnathal ganglion (GNG). It contains axons from sensory cells of the labium entering the labial neuromere of the GNG. The ~10um adult labial nerve arises from the ventral side of the GNG. Proximally, it gives off branches to the basiproboscis and haustellum (a branch consisting of ~10 motorneurons (Nayak and Singh, 1983)), and the labellar glands and sense organs (Miller, 1950). The labial nerve is anastomosed with the maxillary nerve until the latter branches off to the maxillary palpus (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: maxillary palp sensillum basiconicum
description: Olfactory basiconic sensillum of the maxillary palp. The surface of the sensillum is perforated by numerous pores, arranged along a complicated pattern of branched lines, connecting to a lymph space innervated by branched dendrites from two ORNs. These sensilla are located predominantly on the distal half of the dorsal surface and the lateral edge of each maxillary palp.

label: external sensory organ precursor cell IIIb
description: Daughter of pIIb; born during pupal stage; sibling of eo glial cell.

label: external sensory organ precursor cell
description: Precursor cell that gives rise to an external sensory organ.

label: antennal sensillum trichodeum T3
description: Antennal segment 3 sensillum trichodeum innervated by the dendrites of three olfactory receptor neurons.

label: lch5 cap attachment cell
description: A cell that anchors the scolopidial dendritic cap cells of abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 to the cuticle. There are two of these per chordotonal organ of this type.

label: columnar neuron
description: Interneuron of the optic lobe whose primary projection extends along the long axis of a single optic column to which it, but not necessarily its collaterals, is restricted.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi5 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventral side of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP). The primary neurite extends ventromedially and bifurcates: the dorsal branch projects anteriodorsally to innervate the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone A; the ventral branch projects posteriomedially to form postsynaptic terminals in the posterior gnathal ganglion, saddle and inferior posterior slope.

label: cell body rind of lateral neuropils
description: Region of cell body rind between the central brain and the optic lobes. It includes the regions lateral to anterior optic tubercle, superior lateral protocerebrum (including the pars lateralis), lateral horn, ventrolateral protocerebrum, wedge, saddle, inferior posterior slope and posterior lateral protocerebrum.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi4 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the ventroposterior region of the gnathal ganglion. The primary neurite extends dorsolaterally to form postsynaptic terminals in the posterior gnathal ganglion and presynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone D.

label: projection neuron
description: An interneuron that projects from some primary sensory neuropil (e.g. the antennal lobe) to a higher brain neuropil.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center zone D
description: Antennal mechanosensory and motor center zone D is a synapse rich sub-region of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) that arises from the bifurcation that terminates the lateral core bundle. (The other half of the bifurcation forms zone C). It is rich in the presynapses of zone D Johnston's organ neurons (zone D JONs).

label: glutamatergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe
description: Glutamatergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe. The minority of local interneurons of the adult antennal lobe fall into this class. Most of the cell bodies of these interneurons belong to the ventral neuroblast lineage, and a few to the lateral neuroblast lineage.

label: local interneuron of adult antennal lobe
description: A local interneuron that is part of an adult antennal lobe.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi3 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the ventroposterior region of the gnathal ganglion. The primary neurite extends dorsally to innervate the posterior gnathal ganglion and extends anterodorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center B projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that receives input in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm10
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. It has a distinct tri-stratified layer pattern, branching extensively in medulla layers M1, M3B and M5. Its arbor resembles an ellipse, with the long axis aligned with the dorsal-ventral axis, and covering less than 10 columns. The processes in M1 and M3B to M5 are located in an intracolumnar position. There are around 300 Dm10 neurons per hemisphere.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center local AMMC Bi2 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the ventral region of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The primary neurite extends dorsally to innervate the ipsilateral AMMC zones B and E. Presynaptic terminals are found in both zones.

label: unilateral intrinsic neuron
description: An intrinsic neuron that does not cross the midline.

label: intrinsic antennal mechanosensory and motor center neuron
description: Interneuron that innervates only the adult antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC).

label: cell body rind of anterior neuropils
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the anterior neuropils. It includes the regions anterior to the superior neuropils, anterior and ventral to the optic tubercle, anterior to the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum and crepine, antero-, laterodorsal, lateral and ventral to the antennal lobe and medioventral to the saddle.

label: embryonic/larval crepine
description: Small synaptic neuropil domain of the larval protocerebrum that is located anterior to the medial mushroom body lobe. It contains numerous fine axons which project medially and contribute to the anterior transverse tract (ATT) and the medial cervical tract (MCT). It is the larval counterpart of the adult crepine.

label: embryonic/larval protocerebrum
description: Protocerebrum of the embryo/larva.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center local AMMC Bi1 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the anteromedial region of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The primary neurite extends posterioventrally to form predominantly postsynaptic sites in the ipsilateral AMMC zone B and presynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral zone C.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center zone C
description: Antennal mechanosensory and motor center zone C is a synapse rich sub-region of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) that arises from the most lateral half of the bifurcation that terminates the lateral core (lc) bundle. (The other half of the bifurcation forms zone D). It is rich in the presynapses of Johnston's organ neurons (JONs) (Kamikouchi et al., 2006).

label: proximal medullary amacrine neuron PmLM7
description: Proximal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron that arborizes extensively in medulla layer M7 and a few in M8-M10. The finest terminals in the medulla are dendritic, forming post-synaptic terminals (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: proximal medullary amacrine neuron
description: An amacrine neuron that is intrinsic to the medulla and that branches and arborizes in the proximal medulla. Generally, the soma is located in the cortex adjacent to the medulla and that projects through the proximal surface of the medulla, to form wide (sometimes very wide) terminal arborizations mainly or completely restricted to a single layer of the medulla.

label: anterior transverse tract
description: Tract of the larval brain connected to the central anterior synaptic neuropil domain.

label: embryonic/larval anterior superior medial protocerebrum
description: A synaptic neuropil subdomain of the larval brain that is located anterior and dorsal to the medial lobe of the mushroom body, and which is separated from the posterior superior medial protocerebrum by a neuropil glial sheath slightly posterior to the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. It is the larval counterpart of the adult anterior superior medial protocerebrum.

label: proximal medullary amacrine neuron Pm9-10
description: Proximal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron that arborizes extensively in medulla layers M9 and M10. The terminals in the medulla form both pre- and post-synaptic terminals (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: PB slice 8-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in protocerebral bridge slice 8, segment pair W (column 4) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: PB 1 glomerulus-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborization in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge, fan-shaped body layers 3 and 6 and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: fan-shaped body layer 6
description: Sixth most ventral layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped body segment pair W
description: Most lateral segment pair of the fan-shaped body.

label: non-connected developing system
description: The sum of all the anlagen and primordia that will develop into a single system.

label: PB slice 7-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall ipsilateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in protocerebral bridge slice 7, segment pair W (column 4) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the ipsilateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: transmedullary neuron TmLM7
description: Transmedullary wide-field neuron that arborizes extensively in medulla layer M7, and also in M8-M10. The finest terminals in the medulla are dendritic, forming post-synaptic terminals. It projects to the lobula (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: neuropil glial sheath
description: Layer of glial cells which largely surrounds a region of neuropil in the central nervous system.

label: central nervous system
description: Collective name for all the nerve centers and their connective in the insect's body. In the context of Drosophila refers to the part of the nervous system consisting of the brain and ventral ganglia.

label: transmedullary neuron TmLM8
description: Transmedullary wide-field neuron that arborizes extensively in medulla layer M8, and also in M9-M10. The finest terminals in the medulla are dendritic, forming post-synaptic terminals. It projects to the lobula (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: PB slice 7-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in protocerebral bridge slice 7, segment pair X or W (column 3 or 4) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: fan-shaped body segment pair X
description: Second most lateral segment group of the fan-shaped body.
synonyms: fan shaped body segment pair X

label: single-organism catabolic process
description: A catabolic process - chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances - which involves a single organism.

label: catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances, including the breakdown of carbon compounds with the liberation of energy for use by the cell or organism.

label: single-organism metabolic process
description: A metabolic process - chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances - which involves a single organism.

label: octopaminergic AL2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster in the ventromedial border of the antennal lobe. One neurite runs along the esophagus foramen to the posterior slope where it branches, forming spiny dendritic arborizations. It has axonal projections that innervate the optic lobe. There are seven cells in this cluster that belong to two main subtypes, OA-AL2i and AL2b (Busch et al., 2009).
synonyms: octopaminergic neuron of the antennal lobe

label: extrinsic neuron
description: An interneuron that extends projections between different neuropil domains.

label: octopaminergic neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some octopamine secretion, neurotransmission (GO:0061540).

label: octopamine secretion, neurotransmission
description: The controlled release of octopamine by a cell, in which the octopamine acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: posterior slope
description: Synaptic neuropil domain of the adult brain that is the inferior (ventral) part of the posterior cerebral ganglion, covering the area between the inferior bridge and the gnathal ganglion with its superior part lying behind the ventral complex. It contains extensive arborizations of ascending and descending neurons. Its superior boundary is the level above which such arborizations do not occur. It also contains the terminals of axons from the ocellar ganglia, projecting via the ocellar nerve.

label: cell body rind of antennal lobe
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the antennal lobe.

label: single-organism process
description: A biological process that involves only one organism.

label: metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances. Metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

label: octopaminergic AL2i neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates the ipsilateral optic lobe. Secondary processes originating in the posterior slope terminate in the optic lobe, forming varicose terminals. In the posterior slope, thin processes branch off the neurite that projects to the optic lobe, innervating the ventral inferior posterior slope forming varicose terminals. There are four different subtypes of AL2i neurons, AL2i1-4, which differ in their arborization patterns (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi8 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP). The primary neurite extends posterioventromedially to innervate the anterior antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B and the wedge. It then extends further to form presynaptic terminals in the saddle and gnathal ganglion.

label: tract
description: A neuron projection bundle linking two or more synaptic neuropil domains or subdomains within the CNS.

label: embryonic/larval brain
description: Brain of the embryo/larva.

label: dorsal posterior protocerebral tract
description: A vertical axon tract of the larval brain connecting the dorso-posterior compartment (DP) to the subesophageal ganglion. The tract dives ventrally through the centro-posterior intermediate compartment (CPI) towards the posterior boundary of the basoposterior medial compartment where it joins the posterior cervical tract (PCT).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi7 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the dorsal region of the anterior antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The primary neurite extends medially and turns sharply, at the ventrolateral side of the lateral accessory lobe to project ventrolaterally and form postsynaptic terminals in the AMMC zone B. It then forms three branches: the medial one extends through the inferior AMMC commissure to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral AMMC zone E; the ventromedial branch forms postsynaptic terminals in the gnathal ganglion and presynaptic ones in the saddle; the dorsal branch projects posteriodorsally and turns laterally at the lateral side of the vest to form presynaptic terminals in the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) glomerulus targeted by LC4 neurons.

label: octopaminergic AL2i1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates the ipsilateral medulla and lobula complex. Secondary processes branch off the neurite that projects from the posterior slope to the optic lobe and innervate the posteriolateral, posterioinferior medial and ventromedial protocerebra, and protocerebral bridge, forming varicose terminals (Busch et al., 2009).

label: extrinsic pb neuron
description: Any extrinsic neuron (FBbt:00003660) that has synaptic terminals in some protocerebral bridge (FBbt:00003668).

label: lobula complex
description: A synaptic neuropil block in the adult brain consisting of the two medial-most synaptic neuropil domains of the optic lobe: the lobula and the lobula plate.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi6 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the gnathal ganglion. The primary neurite extends ventromedially along the ventrolateral rim of the anterior gnathal ganglion. It then turns posteriodorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion. It further extends dorsolaterally to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, wedge and anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center A projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that receives input in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone A.

label: dorsal posterior commissure
description: Commissure of the larval brain which is connected to (among others) the posterior transverse tract.

label: embryonic/larval posterior superior medial protocerebrum
description: A synaptic neuropil subdomain of the larval brain that is located posterior and dorsal to the medial lobe of the mushroom body and which is separated from the anterior superior medial protocerebrum by a neuropil glial sheath slightly posterior to the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. Axons from this compartment converge with those from part of the clamp (CPL) to form the posterior transverse tract (PTT). It is the larval counterpart of the adult posterior superior medial protocerebrum.

label: posterior transverse tract
description: Tract of the larval brain formed by axons converging from the dorso-posterior and centro-posterior lateral compartments. This tract runs medial along the neuropil glial sheath between the dorso-posterior compartment and the mushroom body calyx before it joins the dorsal posterior commissure.

label: embryonic/larval clamp
description: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain located posterior to the medial lobe of the mushroom body. It is separated from the posterior inferior protocerebrum by the antenno-cerebral tract and peduncle. Its axons project mainly into the posterior transverse tract and it receives a branch of the antenno-cerebral tract. It is the larval counterpart of the adult clamp.

label: single-organism behavior
description: The specific behavior of a single organism in response to external or internal stimuli.

label: behavior
description: The internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of whole living organisms (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli.

label: octopaminergic VPM neuron
description: A bilaterally paired octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster, whose cell body is located slightly lateral to the midline of the subesophageal zone of the adult brain. VPM neurites do not join the median tract and show asymmetric arborization patterns in the brain and gnathal ganglion, except for OA-VPM1. Spiny dendritic processes are present in the posterior slope, with projections in different areas of the brain forming varicose terminals. Five different subtypes can be identified: OA-VPM1-5 (Busch et al., 2009).

label: octopaminergic VM neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located along the ventral midline of the adult gnathal ganglion of the adult brain. Two main subtypes can be identified: VPM and VUM (Busch et al., 2009).

label: cell body rind of ventral midline of adult gnathal ganglion
description: Region of the cell body rind of the adult brain at the ventral midline of the gnathal ganglion.
synonyms: ventral midline cortex of adult gnathal ganglion

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi15 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posteriomedial region of the lobula. The primary neurite extends anterioventrally and forms postsynaptic terminals in the ventral posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP), ventral anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP) and antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B. Arborization is also observed in the AMMC zone A.

label: octopaminergic VPM1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster of the adult brain, whose cell body is located at the anterior margin of the subesophageal zone midline, in the mandibular segment. Its main neurite projects along the ventral esophagus and innervates the ventromedial protocerebrum and subesophageal zone, forming varicose terminals. These arborizations are mirror-symmetric. The descending secondary neurite emerges from the ventrolateral esophagus laterally into the ipsilateral half of the gnathal ganglion and turns ventrally to descend through the cervical connective. It innervates the three ipsilateral thoracic neuromeres and the abdominal one (Busch et al., 2009, Certel et al., 2010, Busch and Tanimoto, 2010).

label: cervical connective
description: Nerve connecting the posterior-most subesophageal ganglion to the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the adult CNS. It consists of 4 bundles of neurites.

label: ventral complex
description: A group of synaptic neuropil domains in the adult brain located below (ventral to) the central complex, behind the lateral accessory lobes and in front of the great commissure. In includes the vest, epaulette and gorget.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi14 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The primary neurite extends anteriodorsally and forms three branches in the ventral posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP). The lateral branch projects anteriodorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the PVLP. The ventral branch projects anteriomedially to form postsynaptic terminals in the ventral anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP) and antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B. The dorsal branch turns medially to form presynaptic terminals in the gorget.

label: octopaminergic AL2b1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates both the ipsilateral and contralateral lobulae. The neurite that innervates the lobulae originates in the dorsolateral esophagus foramen. Additional processes branch off this neurite and form varicose terminals in the posteriolateral, posterioinferior lateral and ventrolateral protocerebra (Busch et al., 2009).

label: octopaminergic AL2b neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates both the ipsilateral and contralateral optic lobes. Secondary processes originating in the esophagus foramen bilaterally innervate both lobulae. Additional processes branch off this neurite to innervate the posteriolateral, posterioinferior lateral and ventrolateral protocerebra, forming varicose terminals. There is one subtype of OA-AL2b neurons: AL2b1 (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi13 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the lateral horn. The primary neurite extends ventromedially to arborize in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone A, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP) and wedge.

label: cell body rind of lateral horn
description: The region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the lateral horn.

label: embryonic/larval periesophageal neuropils
description: One of a group of synaptic neuropil domains of the larval brain which are located ventral to the mushroom body and are grouped around the long axon tracts connecting the larval protocerebrum to the ventral nerve cord. This compartment contacts the antennal lobe posteriorly and guides the medial cervical tract (MCT). It is the larval counterpart of the adult periesophageal neuropils.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi12 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventrolateral region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP). The primary neurite extends posteriolaterally and bifurcates in the ventral AVLP. The dorsal branch forms postsynaptic terminals in the AVLP. The ventral branch projects to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, and forms postsynaptic terminals in the wedge, AVLP and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP).

label: octopaminergic AL2i4 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates the ipsilateral inner medulla, forming varicose terminals (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi11 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventrolateral region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP). The primary neurite extends posteriomedially and bifurcates in the ventral AVLP. The dorsal branch arborizes in the AVLP. The medial branch projects to the wedge and antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone A. Postsynaptic terminals are found in the AVLP, AMMC zone A and wedge.

label: plasma membrane region
description: A membrane that is a (regional) part of the plasma membrane.

label: plasma membrane part
description: Any constituent part of the plasma membrane, the membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: membrane
description: A lipid bilayer along with all the proteins and protein complexes embedded in it an attached to it.

label: plasma membrane
description: The membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: embryonic/larval antennal lobe
description: Paired synaptic neuropil domain of the larval deutocerebrum, located ventral to the mushroom body, that is the major target of innervation for axons carried by the antennal nerve. It is also connected to the antero-basal tract (ABT). Its posterior boundary contacts the lateral accessory lobe, ventromedial cerebrum, ventrolateral protocerebrum and periesophageal neuropils. It is the larval counterpart of the adult antennal lobe, and consists of around 22 glomeruli.

label: antennal lobe
description: Synaptic neuropil domain of the deutocerebrum that is the main target for innervation from the antennal nerve.

label: embryonic/larval deutocerebrum
description: Deutocerebrum of the embryo/larva.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi10 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP). The primary neurite extends ventromedially and bifurcates in the AVLP. The dorsal branch projects posteriomedially to form postsynaptic terminals in the AVLP and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP). The ventral branch projects ventromedially to form postsynaptic terminals in the anterior antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, and wedge, and presynaptic terminals in the saddle and in the gnathal ganglion.

label: octopaminergic AL2i2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates the ipsilateral inner medulla and lobula. Secondary processes branch off the neurite that projects from the posterior slope to the optic lobe and innervate the ipsilateral posteriolateral and ventromedial protocerebra, forming varicose terminals (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antero-basal tract
description: Tract of the larval brain which is connected to the baso-anterior synaptic neuropil domain (BA; antennal compartment). This tract travels along the neuropil glial sheath which forms the boundary between baso-anterior (BA) and baso-central (BC) synaptic neuropil domains. The tract then turns dorsally to make the antennal root of the antenno-cerebral tract (ACT).

label: octopaminergic AL2i3 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the AL2 cluster which innervates the ipsilateral outer medulla. Secondary processes branch off the neurite that projects from the posterior slope to the optic lobe and innervate the ipsilateral posteriolateral and ventromedial protocerebra, forming varicose terminals (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi9 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP). The primary neurite extends ventromedially and bifurcates in the AVLP. The dorsal branch projects posteriomedially to form postsynaptic terminals in the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP). The ventral branch projects medially to form postsynaptic terminals in the anterior antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, the wedge, AVLP and PVLP. It then extends further to form presynaptic terminals in the gnathal ganglion.

label: single organism signaling
description: A signaling process occurring within a single organism.

label: multi-organism reproductive process
description: A biological process that directly contributes to the process of producing new individuals, involving another organism.

label: reproductive process
description: A biological process that directly contributes to the process of producing new individuals by one or two organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: multi-organism process
description: A biological process which involves another organism of the same or different species.

label: multi-multicellular organism process
description: A multicellular organism process which involves another multicellular organism of the same or different species.

label: multicellular organismal process
description: Any biological process, occurring at the level of a multicellular organism, pertinent to its function.

label: single-multicellular organism process
description: A biological process occurring within a single, multicellular organism.

label: abdominal 4 temporary eclosion muscle DA1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 4 that develops from abdominal 4 dorsal acute muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal temporary eclosion muscle DA
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of the adult abdomen that develops from an A1-7 dorsal acute muscle.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000591) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 temporary eclosion muscle DA3
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 4 that develops from abdominal 4 dorsal acute muscle 3 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: male germline cyst
description: Unit of spermatogenic differentiation consisting of a pair of cyst cells enclosing the developing germline cells.

label: germline cyst
description: A developing unit of gametogenesis consisting of germline cells encapsulated by a layer of somatic cells.

label: testis
description: Tube of the male reproductive system connected to the seminal vesicle at the basal end. It is a tube 1.9mm long and 90-100 micrometers in diameter, with the basal half helically coiled and the distal half forming a freely extended arc. The coiled portion is spirally wound twice around a centre occupied by the testicular duct and the distal portion of the seminal vesicle. The wall of the testis consists of two very thin layers containing widely spaced nuclei: an inner sheath and an outer sheath composed of small flattened polygonal cells that contain yellow pigment granules. The development of germline cells takes place in the testis.

label: octopaminergic VPM3 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster, whose cell body is located posterior to that of OA-VMP1 and VMP2, in the mandibular segment of the adult brain. Its main neurite projects to the ventral esophagus where it crosses the midline. It then passes the posterior margin of the contralateral antennal lobe and runs further dorsally to the anterior superior medial protocerebrum. There it turns posteriorly and medially to cross the midline again and to terminate in the ipsilateral middle superior medial and lateral protocerebra. Various processes branch off the main neurite innervating the contralateral superior medial and lateral protocerebra, the fan-shaped body, the contralateral noduli, the contralateral gamma lobe and spur (slices 1, 3, 4 and 5) and outer region of the calyx of the mushroom body (Busch et al., 2009, Busch and Tanimoto, 2010). There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body calyx
description: A synaptic neuropil domain containing the dendrites of mushroom body intrinsic cells and receiving sensory interneuron afferents, mainly from the antennal lobes. It is located on the posterior side of the brain, close to the cortex where the cell bodies of the Kenyon cells are located. The peduncle extends anteriorly from the calyx to the base of the lobes.

label: spur of adult mushroom body
description: Synaptic neuropil domain of the adult mushroom body, that is a small protrusion, lateral to the pedunculus divide. It is formed either by the gamma Kenyon cells that run through the lateral part of the pedunculus divide and project to the gamma lobe.

label: mushroom body gamma lobe slice 1
description: Proximal-most slice of the mushroom body gamma lobe.

label: mushroom body alpha' lobe slice 3
description: Distal-most tip slice of the mushroom body alpha' lobe.

label: mushroom body gamma lobe slice 3
description: Central-most slice of the mushroom body gamma lobe.

label: mushroom body gamma lobe slice 4
description: Second most distal slice of the mushroom body gamma lobe.

label: mushroom body gamma lobe slice 5
description: Distal-most slice of the mushroom body gamma lobe.

label: mushroom body beta' lobe slice 2
description: Distal-most slice of the mushroom body beta' lobe.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bb3 neuron
description: Bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the antennal lobe. The primary neurite forms several branches to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B and the glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons. Presynaptic terminals are found in the ipsilateral saddle, gnathal ganglion and wedge. The contralateral branch arises at the ventrolateral side of the epaulette and crosses the midline to form presynaptic terminals in the contralateral glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons.

label: adepithelial cell of peripodial stalk
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the peripodial stalk.

label: adepithelial cell
description: Small, spindle-shaped adult muscle precursor cell that is distinct from, but closely apposed to, the surface of an imaginal disc epithelium.

label: female germline cyst
description: A cyst of female germ cells interconnected by ring canals. Each cyst originates as a single cystoblast which divides to form 16 cystocytes. These become enveloped in a follicle cell epithelium as they pass through region 2 of the germarium. Cysts that have left the germarium are termed egg chambers.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bb2 neuron
description: Bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the antennal lobe. The primary neurite extends posterioventromedially and bifurcates in antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The lateral branch forms postsynaptic terminals in the AMMC zone B and turns posterioventrally to arborize in the saddle. The contralateral branch extends to form presynaptic terminals in the contralateral glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons.

label: octopaminergic VPM4 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster, whose cell body is located posterior to that of OA-VMP3, and slightly lateral, in the labial segment of the adult brain. Its main neurite projects to the ventral esophagus where it crosses the midline. Its secondary neurite shares the tract with OA-VMP3, running further along the posterior margin of the antennal lobe to the anterior superior medial protocerebrum. There it turns posteriorly and medially to cross the midline again along the dorsal margin of the fan-shaped body. Various processes branch off the main and secondary neurites, innervating the contralateral superior, inferior and ventrolateral protocerebra, the whole contralateral gamma lobe and spur of the mushroom body, the subesophageal zone and the ipsilateral middle inferior lateral and middle inferior medial protocerebra (Busch et al., 2009, Busch and Tanimoto, 2010). There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: subalar sclerite
description: Sclerite embedded in the soft cuticle beneath the wing base located posterior to the basalar sclerite (Sink, 2006).

label: wing sclerite
description: Any sclerite (FBbt:00004475) that is part of some wing hinge (FBbt:00004731).

label: head air sac
description: Any tracheal air sac (FBbt:00003101) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: tracheal air sac
description: Air filled epithelial sac of the adult tracheal system. These highly dilated trachea consist of thin epithelium with very thin chitinous lining, lacking `taenidia` (FBbt:00005045). Consequently they are highly flexible and can collapse or expand with changes in pressure around them.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bb1 neuron
description: Bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The primary neurite extends anteriodorsally and turns sharply to bifurcate in the great commissure. The ipsilateral branch forms postsynaptic terminals in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone A, including the most ventral region, wedge, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP) and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP). The contralateral branch fasciculates with the great commissure and extends to form presynaptic terminals in the gorget, inferior clamp and postsynaptic ones in the AVLP, PVLP and epaulette.

label: great commissural interneuron
description: Any interneuron (FBbt:00005125) that fasciculates with some great commissure (FBbt:00007080).

label: great commissure
description: Commissure of the adult brain located ventral to the fan-shaped body and posterior to the noduli. It connects the left and right ventro-lateral protocerebrum, and its main component connects the lobula of both optic lobes. The commissure also contains many other fibers that connect different neuropils. It demarcates the boundaries of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (posterior region), posterior lateral protocerebrum (anterior region), noduli (posterior region), inferior bridge (anterior region), superior posterior slope (anterior region), vest (posterior-superior region), epaulette (posterior region) and gorget (inferior region).

label: cell body rind of posterior neuropils
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the posterior neuropils. It includes the regions posterior to the superior medial and lateral protocerebrum, lateral horn, calyx, protocerebral bridge, inferior bridge, superior posterior slope and posterior lateral protocerebrum.

label: dorsal air sac primordium
description: Primordium formed by tracheoblasts that bud from the tracheal branch which adheres to the wing disc during the late larval stage. During pupal stages this primordium forms an epithelial sac. Cells at the tip of this primordium show extensive protrusive activity - producing filopodia and lamellopodia - while maintaining epithelial integrity (including adherens junctions with their neighbors) .

label: air sac primordium
description: Primordium of an air sac (a large, air filled sac of the adult tracheal system).

label: cuboidal/columnar epithelium
description: An epithelium consisting of columnar shaped cells.

label: octopaminergic VPM2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster, whose cell body is located slightly lateral to the subesophageal ganglion midline, in the mandibular segment. Its main neurite projects to the area surrounding the ventral esophagus foramen where it crosses the midline. It then bifurcates at the ventral area of the contralateral ventrolateral protocerebrum. These processes innervate the contralateral ventrolateral, ventromedial, anterioinferior medial protocerebra and the subesophageal ganglion, and fasciculate with the antennal nerve. There is also some innervation in the ipsilateral subesophageal ganglion (Busch et al., 2009, Certel et al., Busch and Tanimoto, 2010).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bi16 neuron
description: Ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the antennal lobe. The primary neurite extends medially and broadly forms postsynaptic terminals in the antennal lobe. It then turns posteriodorsally to project towards the fan-shaped body (FB) and turns posteriolaterally at the ventrolateral side of the FB to form presynaptic terminals in the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The neurite turns anterioventrally to form presynaptic terminals in the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) and arborize in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron
description: Interneuron whose dendrite innervates the antennal lobe and whose axon innervates some higher brain centre - generally the mushroom body calyx and/or the lateral horn.

label: dorsal air sac
description: Large, multi-lobed air sac of the dorsal adult thorax. It arises from an outgrowth of the lateral trunk between the branches to the second and third legs. It comprises the postnotal, lateroscutal, medioscutal, scutellar, pleural and notopleural air sacs.

label: air sac subdivision
description: Subdivision of an adult tracheal air sac.

label: baso-medial protocerebral tract
description: An axon tract of the larval brain which is a branch of the lateral cervical tract. The branch point, at the center of the basal synaptic neuropil domain (the neuropil glial sheath between baso-posterio medial (BPM), baso-central (BC) and baso-posterior lateral (BPL)) compartments is known as the anterior hub. It crosses the baso-posterior lateral compartment (BPL) where it splays out into several terminal branches.

label: embryonic/larval ventrolateral protocerebrum
description: One of a group of synaptic neuropil domains of the larval brain which are located ventral to the mushroom body and are grouped around the long axon tracts connecting the larval protocerebrum to the ventral nerve cord. This compartment contacts the antennal lobe posteriorly, and is lateral to the lateral accessory lobe and ventromedial cerebrum. It grows anteriorly during larval development. It is the larval counterpart of the adult ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label: lateral cervical tract
description: Tract of the embryonic brain that pioneers part of the cervical connective. It is formed by axons of the P3m cluster which extend anteriorly and ventrally to reach P1 fiber tract founder cluster. It fasciculates with the axons of P1 neurons, extending ventrally toward the subesophageal commissure and subesophageal ganglion to join the cervical connective.

label: larval optic focus
description: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain formed during larval stages by axons originating from the lobula primordium in the optic lobe and dorso-lateral protocerebrum. These axons form terminal branches beyond the borders of the centro-posterior lateral and baso-lateral compartments which then become enclosed by a glial sheath, forming this compartment.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 12
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the transverse nerve (TN), anterior to the ISN and lateral to ePG8 (von Hilchen et al., 2008). It develops from a sensory organ precursor cell (Bodmer et al., 1989).

label: embryonic/larval glial cell
description: Glial cell of the embryo/larva.

label: peripheral glial cell
description: Glial cell in a nerve that is directly associated with its neurites and is not part of subperineurial layer that wraps the nerve. Early in development, cells of this type are involved in axon pathfinding. Later, cells of this type ensheath neurites and some are located at branching points.

label: abdominal transverse nerve
description: Abdominal transverse nerve that exits the ventral nerve cord at a dorsomedial position, splits into a left and right branch and extends ventrally along the segment boundary (Gorczyca et al., 1994). Formed by the axons of the abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron (isbp) and the abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron (istd) (Campos-Ortega, J.A., Hartenstein, V., 1997).

label: PB slice 4-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 4 and in the ipsilateral segment pairs Z and Y (columns 1 and 2) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: PB 1 glomerulus-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in one protocerebral bridge slice and in the ipsi- or contralateral two segment pairs of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the ipsi- or contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: fan-shaped body layer 4
description: Fourth most ventral (third most dorsal) layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped body layer 2
description: Second most ventral layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped body segment pair Z
description: Medial-most segment pair of the fan-shaped body.
synonyms: fan shaped body segment pair Z

label: fan-shaped body segment pair Y
description: Third segment pair of the fan-shaped body (counting from lateral to medial).

label: PB slice 3-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 3 and in the ipsi- and contralateral segment pair Z (column 1) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: Va neuron
description: Larval neurosecretory abdominal neuron whose cell body is located near the ventrolateral tract of the midline. It projects its axon dorsomedially through the neuropil passing below the central intermediate and dorsal median tracts. The axon reaches the midline near the transverse projection 3 where it joins with the axon of the contralateral Va neuron. The two axons project dorsally together a short distance before diverging and forming a loop inside the neuropil and dorsal cortex. The loop closes just before the neurites leave the ventral ganglion and innervate the abdominal neurohemal organ. There are 3 bilateral pairs of Va neurons, one bilateral pair in each of the first 3 abdominal neuromeres (Santos et al., 2007).

label: embryonic/larval neuron
description: A neuron that is part of the embryonic/larval nervous system.

label: abdominal neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some abdomen (FBbt:00000020).

label: abdominal neurohemal organ
description: Bilaterally paired neurosecretory organ of the larval abdominal segments, formed by the axons of Va neurons when they leave the ventral ganglion, pass through the medial nerve and innervate the proximal part of the transverse nerve of the first 3 abdominal neuromeres (Santos et al., 2007).

label: PB slice 2-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 2 and in the contralateral two segment pairs Z and Y (columns 1 and 2) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: adult antennal mechanosensory and motor center projection neuron
description: Any projection neuron (FBbt:00007392) that has postsynaptic terminals in some antennal mechanosensory and motor center (FBbt:00003982).

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 11
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the abdominal dorsal bipolar neuron dbp, posterior to the ISN (von Hilchen et al., 2008). It develops from a sensory organ precursor cell (Bodmer et al., 1989).

label: PB slice 2-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial ipsilateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 2 and in the ipsilateral two segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the ipsilateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: horizontal fiber system neuron
description: Neuron whose cell body lies in the cortex just dorsal to the protocerebral bridge and with dendritic arbors in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge and in a segment pair of the fan-shaped body, and axon terminals in the one or both of the lateral accessory lobes. Bundles of 3 or 4 horizontal fiber system neurons connect each glomerulus to a fan-shaped body segment and then run horizontally in layer 4 where they arborize in all 4 shells. Arborizations in the protocerebral bridge are spiny, terminals in the lateral accessory lobes are blebs, both types of terminals are formed in the fan-shaped body.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 8
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN) laterally to ePG7. It develops from neuroblast 2-5 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: intermediate peripheral glial cell of ISN
description: A peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN) that is located between PG1 (ePG4) and PG3 (ePG10). There are 4 of these (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: neuroblast NB2-5
description: Neuroblast NB2-5 delaminates at S1 and generates a diverse array of cell types including motorneurons, intersegmental interneurons, local interneurons, glial cells and sometimes a PNS sub-clone. In the larva, it resumes proliferation in T1 to A1 segments. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 17.

label: intersegmental nerve
description: Larval nerve of segments T1-A7. It exits the ventral ganglion at a position adjacent to the anterior commissure as a fascicle which shares a glial sheath with the segmental nerve (posterior fascicle), running dorsally until it encounters the ventral oblique musculature, at which point it splits into separate segmental and intersegmental nerves with their own glial sheaths. The intersegmental nerve runs dorsally along a path anterior to the segmental nerve. It branches to various sensory clusters and muscles.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 9
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN) laterally to ePG8. It develops from neuroblast 1-3 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: neuroblast NB1-3
description: Neuroblast located at the embryonic segment border close to the tracheal pit that produces only glial cells (Schmidt et al., 1997, Schmid et al., 1999).

label: PB 2 glomeruli-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in both protocerebral bridge slices 2 and in the contralateral two segment pairs Y and X (columns 2 and 3) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: spermatogonial cyst
description: A male germline cyst consisting of 2 cyst cells and one primary spermatogonial cell. The latter is the mitotic founder of a cyst of secondary spermatogonia. Following 4 mitotic divisions, the spermatogonial cyst becomes a primary spermatocyte cyst.

label: PB slice 7-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 7, in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: PB 1 glomerulus-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in one protocerebral bridge slice (except for slices 8 and 9) and in two segment pairs of the contra- or ipsilateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e), and axon terminals in the ipsi- or contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: male fusome
description: Fusome of the male germline stem cell or its progeny.

label: fusome
description: Cytoplasmic membrane-rich zones found in developing germline stem cells and their progeny. A small spherical fusome (spectrosome) grows during germline stem cell formation into a large branched structure (polyfusome) that extends through the ring canals into every cystocyte in germarium region 2a. Once the germline cyst has stopped dividing, the fusome begins to break down, usually disappearing soon after the progeny of the germline stem cell leaves the germarium.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 7
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN) and located laterally to ePG6. It develops from neuroblast 1-3 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: PB slice 6-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 6, in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: PB slice 6-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 6 and in the ipsilateral segment pairs Y and X (columns 2 and 3) or X and W (columns 3 and 4) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: neurohemal organ
description: Gland of the endocrine system from which neurosecretory substances are released into the hemolymph.

label: SP3 neuron
description: A larval neuro-secretory neuron whose cell body is located in the superior protocerebrum. There is one cell per brain hemisphere (McCormick and Nichols, 1993) and its axon innervates the corpus cardiacum (Wegener et al., 2011).

label: nervus corporis cardiaci I
description: Bilaterally paired nerve bundle that connects the larval ring gland to the brain. It comprises, among others, the axons of neurons from the neurosecretory cells of the pars intercerebralis. It joins the nervus corporis cardiaci II (NccII) at the medial edge of the protocerebrum, continuing towards the ring gland (de Velasco et al., 2007; Hartenstein, 2006).

label: cell body rind of larval brain
description: Region of the larval cell body rind that overlies the brain.

label: embryonic/larval corpus cardiacum
description: A bilaterally paired neuro-endocrine structure of the embryonic/larval ring gland. In the late embryo it is composed of 6-8 small cells on each side, arranged in a U-shape around the floor of the aorta. The cells send short processes ventromedially, forming a bundle that is attached to the ventral wall of the aorta.

label: PB slice 5-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 5 and in the ipsilateral segment pairs Y and X (columns 2 and 3) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: female fusome
description: Fusome of the female germline stem cell or its progeny.

label: adult tritocerebrum
description: Tritocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: tritocerebrum
description: Neuromere of intercalary segment. Located in between the deutocerebrum and the gnathal ganglia, which comprises the three caudal neuromeres (mandibular, maxillary, labial).

label: adult intercalary segment
description: Any intercalary segment (FBbt:00000010) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: PB slice 7-FB layers 1 to 4-IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 7 and in the ipsilateral segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the contralateral crepine (medial hammer body).

label: embryonic/larval antennal lobe tract
description: Tract of the larva that connects the antennal lobe to other neuropils in the protocerebrum, including mushroom body and lateral horn.

label: antennal lobe tract
description: A tract connecting the antennal lobe to various neuropils of the protocerebrum.

label: embryonic/larval posterior inferior protocerebrum
description: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain located posterior to the medial lobe of the mushroom body. It is separated from the clamp by the antenno-cerebral tract to which it is connected via a branch. Most of the posterior inferior protocerebrum (CPM domain) is displaced during pupal development. The region at the most posterior edge remains and gives rise to part of the adult posterior inferior protocerebrum. The adult central complex arises from secondary axonal tracts of several lineages that invade the CPM, forming dense layers of neuropil and displacing it.

label: protocerebrum
description: The most anterior of the segmental subdivisions of the insect CNS; thought to represent the first pre-oral segment of the brain. The protocerebrum comprises many discrete neuropil regions including the central body complex and mushroom bodies.

label: adult labral segment
description: Any labral segment (FBbt:00000008) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: deutocerebrum
description: The middle neuromere of the insect brain, located in between the protocerebrum and tritocerebrum, connected to antennal nerve trunk.

label: adult antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (FBbt:00000009) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: eye disc posterior to the morphogenetic furrow
description: Portion of the eye disc which is posterior to the morphogenetic furrow. It contains developing ommatidial clusters whose maturity increases with distance posterior to the furrow.

label: early ommatidial precursor cluster
description: An ommatidial precursor cluster containing 5 prospective photoreceptors and 1-2 mystery cells. The definitive 5 cell ommatidial precluster is formed when these mystery cells are expelled from this structure and join the surrounding undifferentiated epithelium.

label: ommatidial precursor cluster
description: A cluster of cells in the eye-disc that is the precursor to an adult ommatidium. Eventually there are approximately 750 ommatidial precursor clusters per eye-disc, the first forming at approximately 70hrs before pupation along the morphogenic furrow. A new row of adult ommatidial precursors then emerges from the morphogenic furrow roughly every 1.5 hours.

label: germinal proliferation center hub
description: A cone shaped cluster of densely packed cells at the center of the germinal proliferation center. It is anchored to the tip of the testis via apical connections to the thick, convoluted basal lamina found there.

label: germinal proliferation center
description: Structure formed by the male germline stem cells, cyst progenitor cells and the hub around which they are clustered and to which they are attached. It is located at the apical (blind) end of the testis.

label: eye disc anterior to the morphogenetic furrow
description: Portion of imaginal disc epithelium which is anterior to the morphogenetic furrow of the eye disc.

label: inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum IVLP-VLP neuron
description: Neuron whose cell body is located between the optic lobe and the central brain, laterally to the AMMC. It arborizes extensively in the ipsilateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (IVLP) and projects dorsally to innervate a small region of the ipsilateral ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP). These neurons receive input in the IVLP from AMMC-B1b neurons among others, and establish postsynaptic contacts in the VLP. They are broadly tuned to respond to 100, 300 Hz, 700Hz or pulse song stimuli (Lai et al., 2012).

label: auditory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of sound (GO:0007605).

label: sensory perception of sound
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive an auditory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Sonic stimuli are detected in the form of vibrations and are processed to form a sound.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center B1b projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located dorsally to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and innervates the AMMC zone B and both the ipsilateral and the contralateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (IVLP) regions. These neurons receive input in the AMMC zone B from Johnston's organ neurons and establish presynaptic connections in the lateral region of the IVLP. These neurons are activated by an acoustic stimuli and are broadly tuned to respond to 100, 300 Hz or pulse song stimuli (Lai et al., 2012).

label: cell body rind of ventrolateral protocerebrum
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label: PB slice 1-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in both protocerebral bridge slices 1, segment pair W (column 4) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: mechanosensory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of mechanical stimulus (GO:0050954).

label: auditory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of sound.

label: PB slice 8-EB posterior-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that connects the protocerebral bridge slice 1, both slices 8 of the posterior ring of the ellipsoid body and the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body).

label: PB 1 glomerulus-EB posterior-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that connects one slice of the protocerebral bridge, two slices of the posterior ring of the ellipsoid body and the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body).

label: ellipsoid body posterior ring
description: Concentric subdivision of the ellipsoid body that lies posteriorly between the outer and inner rings.

label: ellipsoid body slice 8
description: Bottom-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center A2 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located dorsally to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). It projects to the ipsilateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (IVLP) region and AMMC zones A and B. It also projects contralaterally via the inferior AMMC commissure to arborize in the AMMC zones A and B. Its dendrites receive input in the AMMC zone A and establish postsynaptic connections in the IVLP. These neurons are broadly tuned to respond to 100, 300 Hz, 700Hz or pulse song stimuli (Lai et al., 2012).

label: inferior AMMC commissure
description: Commissure that connects the AMMC of both hemispheres. It runs below the esophagus, ventral to the superior AMMC commissure (Lai et al., 2012).
synonyms: inferior antennal mechanosensory and motor center commissure

label: inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum local IVLP-IVLP neuron
description: Neuron whose cell body is located in the ventromedial subesophageal region and innervates the ipsilateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (IVLP) in both hemispheres, with pre- and postsynaptic sites found in this region. These neurons receive input from AMMC-B1b projection neurons in the IVLP.
