IVLP-IVLP are GABAergic neurons and are activated by an acoustic stimuli of 100Hz, 300Hz or pulse song stimuli (Lai et al., 2012).

label: intrinsic wedge neuron
description: Interneuron that innervates only the adult wedge (or IVLP).

label: bilateral intrinsic neuron
description: A midline crossing bilateral intrinsic neuron that projects only within some pair of bilaterally symmetric synaptic neuropil domains and their connecting tracts. For example within the left and right antennal lobes and antennal commissure.

label: PB slice 1-EB posterior-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that connects the protocerebral bridge slice 1, both slices 8 of the posterior ring of the ellipsoid body and the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body).

label: small field neuron of the central complex
description: A small field neuron that innervates the central complex. The majority of small field neurons of the central complex are intrinsic to it, and they typically connect one central complex domain to another. Some also connect subdomains within a single central complex domain.

label: ellipsoid body slice
description: A radial subdivision of the ellipsoid body arising from the arborization patterns of small field radial fibers. There are 16 of these per ellipsoid body, 8 per hemisphere numbered 1-8, from superior medial to inferior medial.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center B1 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located dorsally to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The primary neurite projects medially and makes a steep turn ventrally to form two branches dorsal to the AMMC. The ventrolateral branch forms postsynaptic terminals in the AMMC zone B. The dorsal branch bifurcates in the ipsilateral epaulette, projecting above the esophagus, to form presynaptic terminals both the ipsilateral and the contralateral wedge. These neurons are activated by an acoustic stimuli and two subtypes can be recognized, AMMC-B1a and AMMC-B1b, which differ with respect to JO neuron connectivity and auditory response. The former responds to 100 Hz stimuli and the latter responds to 100 and 300 Hz stimuli (Lai et al., 2012).

label: Johnston organ neuron
description: Scolopidial (mechanosensory) neuron of Johnston's organ. Its axon innervates the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). A small number of fibers also innervate the contralateral AMMC via the commissure of JON. Subset of JO neurons extend into the ventral region of the ventrolateral protocerebrum and posterior part of the subesophageal ganglion.

label: wedge commissure
description: Commissure lying posterior and inferior to the great commissure and anterior to the posterior optic commissure. It connects of both hemispheres. It demarcates the superior posterior slope (inferior region) and inferior slope (superior region).

label: cell body rind region
description: A subdivision of the CNS cortex on the basis of underlying neuropil structure. It includes the neuronal cell bodies.

label: PB slice 3-FB layers 1 to 4-bilateral IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 3 and in the ipsilateral two segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the crepine (medial hammer body) of both hemispheres.

label: PB 1 glomerulus-FB layers 1 to 4-bilateral IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in one protocerebral bridge slice and in the ipsilateral two segment pairs of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the crepine (medial hammer body) of both hemispheres.

label: segment of antenna
description: Any appendage segment (FBbt:00007018) that is part of some antenna (FBbt:00004511).

label: PB slice 1-FB layers 1 to 4-bilateral IDFP HB-medial neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 1 and in the ipsilateral two segment pairs Z and Y (columns 1 and 2) of the fan-shaped body layers 1 to 4 (layers c to f), and axon terminals in the crepine (medial hammer body) of both hemispheres.

label: adult ALl1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALl1 (FBbt:00067347).

label: superior AMMC commissure
description: Component of the great commissure. It branches off anteriorly from the great commissure, posterior to the epaulette, and ends in the AMMC. It runs above the esophagus, dorsal to the inferior AMMC commissure.
synonyms: superior antennal mechanosensory and motor center commissure

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center B1a projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located dorsally to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and innervates the AMMC zone B and both the ipsilateral and the contralateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (IVLP) regions. These neurons receive input in the AMMC zone B and establish presynaptic connections in the lateral region of the IVLP. These neurons are activated by an acoustic stimuli and are narrowly tuned to respond to 100 Hz stimuli (Lai et al., 2012).

label: dopaminergic VUM neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located ventromedially in the gnathal ganglion of the adult brain. It arborizes extensively in the ventroanterior area of the subesophageal zone with presynaptic terminals found throughout. It is involved in modulating the proboscis extension response (PER) with its activity being sufficient to trigger PER (Marella et al., 2012).

label: dopaminergic neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some dopamine secretion, neurotransmission (GO:0061527).

label: dopamine secretion, neurotransmission
description: The regulated release of dopamine by a cell in which the dopamine acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: proboscis extension reflex
description: The extension, through direct muscle actions, of the proboscis (the trunk-like extension of the mouthparts on the adult external head) in response to a sugar stimulus.
synonyms: behavioral response to sugar stimulus, proboscis extension

label: transmedullary neuron Tm3-6
description: Transmedullary neuron that arborizes in medulla layers M3, M6, M7-M10, and projects to the lobula (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: PB slice 3-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in protocerebral bridge slice 3, segment pair Y (column 2) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: segment of leg
description: Any appendage segment (FBbt:00007018) that is part of some leg (FBbt:00004640).

label: adult antennal sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some antenna (FBbt:00004511).

label: antennal sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some antennal segment (FBbt:00000009).

label: adult maxillary neuromere
description: Second caudal neuromere of the gnathal ganglion, posterior to the mandibular neuromere.

label: adult gnathal neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some adult gnathal segment (FBbt:00003014).

label: adult maxillary segment
description: Any maxillary segment (FBbt:00000013) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: PB slice 6-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in protocerebral bridge slice 6, segment pair X (column 3) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: adult mandibular neuromere
description: First caudal neuromere of the gnathal ganglion, anterior to the maxillary neuromere.

label: adult mandibular segment
description: Any mandibular segment (FBbt:00000012) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: PB slice 4-FB layers 3 and 6-ventral gall neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with arborizations in protocerebral bridge slice 4, segment pair Z (column 1) and layers 3 and 6 of fan-shaped body and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of IDFP).

label: transmedullary neuron TmR7 P and Y
description: Transmedullary wide-field neuron that arborizes in medulla layers M3, M7 and M8. It enters the medulla along a specific column and then extending its arborizations to cover two to ten columns. It projects to the lobula (Morante and Desplan, 2008).

label: anterior bundle
description: Tract of the adult brain which runs through the hole in the middle of the ellipsoid body (the ellipsoid body canal).

label: cell cluster organ
description: A cluster of cells of various types which form a discrete structure with a largely bona fide boundary.

label: sense organ
description: Multicellular anatomical structure with largely bona fide boundary that transduces some sensory stimulus to the nervous system.

label: embryonic/larval antennal lobe glomerulus
description: Any glomerulus (FBbt:00005386) that is part of some embryonic/larval antennal lobe (FBbt:00007127).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus
description: Discrete, glial bound partition of the antennal lobe.

label: PB slice 1-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slice 1, ipsi- or contralateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair W (column 4), and axon terminals in the ipsi- or contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: PB 1 glomerulus-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge and the fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d), and axon terminals in the rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: rubus
description: The rubus is a small subregion that is embedded in the crepine, lying behind the mushroom body medial lobe. It consists of a small rough-surfaced round-ish structure. Fibers from the central complex form specific output terminals in this subregion, an project further towards the gall.

label: fan-shaped body layer 5
description: Fifth most ventral layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: EB slice 8-GA-PB slice 9 neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 8, and axon terminals in the contralateral gall and ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slice 9.

label: eb-pb-vbo neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in a large dorso-lateral area of the ellipsoid body (including the inner, outer and posterior layers) and axon arborizations in the ellipsoid body, one or two glomeruli of the protocerebral bridge and either the ipsilateral or contralateral dorsal or ventral gall (ventral body or dorsal or ventral spindle body of the IDFP). Forms club-like terminals in the protocerebral bridge and spiny arborizations in the ellipsoid body. Neuron subtypes can be distinguished by their patterns of dendritic innervation in the ellipsoid body rings and/or gall.

label: ellipsoid body inner ring
description: Inner concentric subdivision of the ellipsoid body. It contains the arborization of R1 ring neurons.

label: EB-IDFP VSB-PB slice 8 glomerulus neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layer of slices 6 and 8, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 7, the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of the IDFP) and ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slice 8.

label: EB-IDFP VSB-PB 1 glomerulus neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of the IDFP) and one contralateral even numbered protocerebral bridge slice.

label: ellipsoid body slice 7
description: Seventh from top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: ellipsoid body slice 6
description: Sixth from top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: ellipsoid body outer ring
description: Outer concentric subdivision of the ellipsoid body. It contains the arborization of R4d and R4m ring neurons.

label: EB-IDFP VSB-PB slice 6 glomerulus neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slices 2 and 4, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 3, the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of the IDFP) and ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slice 6.

label: ellipsoid body slice 4
description: Fourth from top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: ellipsoid body slice 2
description: Second from top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: EB-IDFP VSB-PB slice 4 glomerulus neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slices 1 and 3, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 2, the ipsilateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of the IDFP) and contralateral protocerebral bridge slice 4.

label: ellipsoid body slice 3
description: Third from top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: ellipsoid body slice 1
description: Top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: PB slice 5-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 5, ipsilateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair Y (column 2), and axon terminals in the contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: PB slice 4-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 4, ipsi- or contralateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair Z (column 1), and axon terminals in the contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: PB slice 3-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 3, contralateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair Y (column 2), and axon terminals in the contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: PB slice 2-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 2, contralateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair X (column 3), and axon terminals in the contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: larval dopaminergic TM2 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located along the midline in the larval thoracic segment T2.

label: cell body rind of larval thorax
description: Region of the larval cell body rind that overlies the thoracic neuromeres.

label: maxillary subesophageal commissure
description: Second caudal segment of the gnathal ganglion, posterior to the mandibulary segment.

label: larval dopaminergic TM1 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located along the midline in the ventromedial larval thoracic segment T1. It is found as a triplet group. It arborizes in the subesophageal ganglion and in the ventral nerve cord.

label: subesophageal ganglion
description: Region of the brain beneath the esophagus, consisting of the fused ganglia of the three gnathal segments.

label: adult labial neuromere
description: Third caudal neuromere of the gnathal ganglion, posterior to the maxillary neuromere.

label: larval dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is dorsolaterally located in each hemisegment of abdominal segments A1-A7.

label: cell body rind of larval abdomen
description: Region of the larval cell body rind that overlies the abdominal neuromeres.

label: adult labial segment
description: Any labial segment (FBbt:00000014) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: abdominal 2 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A2.

label: larval dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located along the midline in each segment of the larval ventral abdominal segments.

label: abdominal 3 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A3.

label: abdominal 4 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A4.

label: abdominal 5 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A5.

label: wing blade dorsal compartment
description: Parts of the wing blade and margin which develop from the dorsal compartment of the wing pouch.

label: abdominal 6 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A6.

label: wing blade ventral compartment
description: Parts of the wing blade and margin which develop from the ventral compartment of the wing pouch.

label: abdominal 7 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A7.

label: ventral arm of pharyngeal sclerite
description: Ventral process (arm) of the pharyngeal sclerite that directly contacts the pharynx.

label: pharyngeal sclerite
description: Pharyngeal component of the cephalopharyngeal skeleton of the embryo or larva.

label: larval dopaminergic TM3 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located along the midline in the larval thoracic segment T3.

label: dorsal arm of pharyngeal sclerite
description: Paired dorsal process of the pharyngeal sclerite. This structure, into which the cibarial muscle inserts, is situated in the narrow lumen of the dorsal pouch. It is connected anteriorly to the dorsal bridge (also known as latticed process) and ventrally to the vertical bridge (also known as vertical plate).

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 1
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN). It is the most medially located peripheral glial cell, close to the transition zone between the CNS and the PNS (exit area). It develops from neuroblast 1-3 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: PNS exit glial cell
description: Any exit glial cell (FBbt:00001253) that is part of some embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system (FBbt:00005893).

label: PB slice 2-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 2, the contralateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs Z and Y (columns 1 and 2), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: PB slice 1-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 1, the contralateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs Y and X (columns 2 and 3), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 2
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the segmental nerve (SN). It is located in the transition zone between the CNS and the PNS (exit area), laterally to ePG1 and medially to ePG3. It develops from neuroblast 5-6 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: neuroblast NB5-6
description: Neuroblast NB5-6 generates lateral sub-perineural glial cells and interneurons. This neuroblast dies by apoptosis at embryonic stage 16.

label: segmental nerve
description: Larval nerve of segments T1-A7. It exits the ventral ganglion at a position adjacent to the anterior commissure as a fascicle which shares a glial sheath with the intersegmental nerve (posterior fascicle). This combined nerve runs dorsally until it encounters the ventral oblique musculature, at which point it splits into separate segmental and intersegmental nerves with their own glial sheaths. The segmental nerve runs dorsally along a path posterior to the intersegmental nerve between the musculature and the epidermis. It branches to various sensory clusters and muscles.

label: PB slice 1-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral ipsilateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 1, the ipsilateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4), and axon terminals in the ipsilateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2 alpha'
description: A mushroom body ventral lobe arborizing neuron 2 that innervates across the shaft of the alpha' lobe (slice 3) of the ipsilateral mushroom body and projects bilaterally to the same regions of the lateral horn (ventral and medial domains), superior intermediate protocerebrum and superior lateral protocerebrum. There are two subtypes, one arborizes in the alpha' anterior-posterior domain (MBON-16, MBON-alpha'3ap) and the other the middle domain (MBON-17, MBON-alpha'3m). The axons of the former extend to a region ventral to the lateral horn, whereas the axons of the latter stop at the lateral horn. There is one neuron of the subtype MBON-16 and 2 MBON-17 in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2
description: A neuron, whose cell body is located in the posterior dorsal superior lateral protocerebrum, lateral to the calyx of the adult brain. The cell body fiber runs near the calyx and forms arborizations in the superior neuropils posterior to the tip of the alpha lobe, before entering and arborizing in the tip of the vertical lobe. The fibers further turn ventrally and terminate on the alpha (MB-V2 alpha) or alpha' lobes (MB-V2 alpha'). Near the tip of these lobes, two fibers emerge: one of which projects posteriolaterally to the lateral horn, whereas the other projects medially to the contralateral middle superior lateral protocerebrum just posterior to the vertical lobes, the lateral horn and the superior intermediate protocerebrum (Tanaka et al., 2008, S?journ? et al., 2011, Aso et al., 2014). Contacts with Kenyon cells are visible in the apex of the alpha' lobe, the upper shaft of the alpha' and alpha lobes and a very fine region at the tip of the alpha-posterior lobes (Pech et al., 2013).

label: S-type sensilla S0
description: Most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: short labellar taste bristle
description: Shortest subclass of taste bristle of the labellum: each bristle is around 15 micrometres long and is curved in the medial direction. These bristles are located in the most medial and ventral regions of the outside labellum. These taste bristles contain the sensory dendrites of 4 gustatory receptor neurons (Shanbhag et al., 2001) sensitive to: sugars; low concentrations of salt; bitter or high salt concentrations; water or low osmolarity (Meunier et al., 2003; Fujishiro et al., 1984).These taste bristles also contains the sensory dendrite of one mechanosensory neuron (Shanbhag et al., 2001).

label: PB 2 glomeruli-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in both protocerebral bridge slices 2 and ipsi- or contralateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) and segment pairs X and W (columns 3 and 4), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body).

label: lobula columnar neuron vGlutLcnnew2
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that arborizes in lobula layers 3, 4 and 5 and extends its processes to the central brain. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: lobula columnar neuron
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that innervates the lobula.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2 alpha
description: A mushroom body ventral lobe arborizing neuron 2 that innervates across the shaft of the alpha lobe (slice 2) in the surface and core layers of the ipsilateral mushroom body and projects bilaterally to the superior intermediate protocerebrum, superior lateral protocerebrum and dorsal lateral horn. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body alpha lobe slice 2
description: Largest, central-most slice of the mushroom body alpha lobe.

label: mushroom body alpha lobe surface layer
description: Surface layer of the mushroom body alpha lobe.
synonyms: mushroom body alpha lobe surface stratum

label: mushroom body alpha lobe core layer
description: Inner-most layer of the mushroom body alpha lobe.

label: PB slice 7-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 7, ipsilateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair W (column 4), and axon terminals in the contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: PB slice 6-FB layers 3-5-IDFP RB neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge slice 6, ipsilateral fan-shaped body layers 3, 4 and 5 (layers b, c, d) and segment pair X (column 3), and axon terminals in the contralateral rubus (round body of IDFP).

label: gene
description: A region (or regions) that includes all of the sequence elements necessary to encode a functional transcript. A gene may include regulatory regions, transcribed regions and/or other functional sequence regions.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 5
description: An embryonic peripheral glial cell located distally to the transition zone between the CNS and the PNS (exit area) on the intersegmental nerve near the point where ii splits from the segmental nerve (SN). It develops from the same sensory organ precursor cell located in the ventral neuroectoderm as embryonic peripheral glial cell 4 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 6
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN) and located laterally to ePG5. It develops from neuroblast 2-5 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: PB slice 5-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 5, in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs Y and X (columns 2 and 3), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: PB slice 4-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 4, in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from segment pairs Z and Y (columns 1 and 2), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: embryonic peripheral glial cell 3
description: Embryonic peripheral glial cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (ISN). It is the most lateral cell located in the transition zone between the CNS and the PNS (exit area), laterally to ePG2. It develops from neuroblast 1-3 (von Hilchen et al., 2008).

label: adult dorsomedial neurosecretory cell
description: Neurosecretory cell of the adult pars intercerebralis that innervate the corpus cardiacum and corpus allatum, and branch before exiting the brain. It extends thin branches laterally in the dorsal protocerebrum, shorter branches along the cell neurites in the dorsal part of the median bundle and extensive arborizations in the tritocerebrum (Enell et al., 2010). A single axon extends ventrally, branching just before exiting the brain, and emerging as two branches that follow the aorta and innervate the corpus cardiacum in the ring gland and the hypocerebral ganglion, near the cardiac valve of the midgut. One of the branches follows the stalk of the crop, whilst the other bifurcates, with each of these branches extending along each side of the midgut (Cao and Brown, 2001). There are seven of these cells from each hemisphere with their cell bodies clustering in the pars intercerebralis at late pupal stages (Cao and Brown, 2001, Broughton et al., 2005, Cao et al., 2014).

label: dorsomedial neurosecretory cell
description: Neurosecretory cell of the larval and adult pars intercerebralis.

label: adult midgut
description: The middle region of the adult alimentary canal, the epithelium of which is lined with peritrophic membrane rather than chitinous intima as for the foregut and hindgut. The radius along the midgut is not uniform, with 6 major constrictions delimiting 6 regions (R0-R5). The anterior midgut (R1-R2) functions in absorption, the posterior (R4-R5) plays a role in reabsorption, and the middle acidic region (R3), which contains the copper cells (adult cuprophilic cell), in secretion and absorption.

label: adult corpus cardiacum
description: Corpus cardiacum of the adult. It is located on the ventral region of the ring gland, above the esophagus and anterior to the proventriculus.

label: adult corpus allatum
description: Corpus allatum of the adult. A single round mass of tissue lying on the dorsal wall of the aorta in the prothorax, directly above the stomodeal ganglion. It contains about 14 vesicular nuclei, located near the periphery.

label: adult aorta
description: The anterior portion of the adult dorsal vessel. It consist of a slender, thin walled tube extending from the heart, through the thorax and neck and into the occipital region of the head. At its junction with the heart it is widened to form a triangular chamber. From there it runs anteriorly, directly above the gut and beneath the median dorsal muscles of the thorax and finally opens into the hemocoel behind the brain. The open end is a funnel-shaped structure, the aortic funnel which is attached to the median occipital ridge. A pair of muscles (muscle 16) extend from the terminal opening at the anterior end, through the esophageal foramen of the brain to the frontal pulsatile organ (FBbt:00003175). The wall of the aorta is thin and lacks muscle striations.

label: median bundle
description: Tract located in the anterior midline of the adult brain. It emerges as a paired tract from a broad area around the esophagus, merging into a single tract at the tip of the flange and terminates in the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label: crop
description: Pedunculate sac evaginating from the adult foregut just before it meets the midgut. It is a bi-lobed structure capable of considerable extension, whose function is the storage of ingested liquid food.

label: hypocerebral ganglion
description: Small ganglion of the stomatogastric nervous system. It is located between the two brain hemispheres. In the adult, it is part of the ring gland.

label: PB slice 3-FB layer 2-IDFP HB-lateral neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 3, in the fan-shaped body layer 2 (layer e) from both segment pairs Z (columns 1), and axon terminals in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body) and crepine.

label: abdominal 5 ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in the larval abdominal segment A5.

label: abdominal ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in the larval abdomen.

label: abdominal 6 ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in the larval abdominal segment A6.

label: abdominal 7 ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in the larval abdominal segment A7.

label: abdominal 1 dopaminergic AM neuron
description: Dopaminergic medial neuron of larval abdominal segment A1.

label: neuroblast BLV
description: Neuroblast located medially adjacent to the outer optic anlage.

label: procephalic neuroblast
description: A neuroblast of the brain.

label: abdominal 8 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A8. It is found in a triplet group.

label: A8 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00000029).

label: ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron located ventrolaterally in each segment of the larval ventral nerve cord. There is a pair of these neurons (one medial, one lateral) on either side of the midline in T2 to A7, with three in T1 and one in A8.

label: serotonergic abdominal neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of two clusters either side of the ventral midline in the abdominal segments or neuromere. There is a medial and a lateral neuron in abdominal segments A1-A7, and only one in abdominal segment 8.

label: abdominal 1 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A1.

label: abdominal 2 ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A2.

label: abdominal 3 ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A3.

label: abdominal 4 ventro-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventrolaterally located in the larval abdominal segment A4.

label: PB slice 9-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 9 and axon terminals in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: PB-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge (except glomerulus 1) and axon terminals in fan-shaped body layer 2 and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: PB slice 8-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 8 and axon terminals in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body segment pair X (column 3) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: PB slice 7-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 7 and axon terminals in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body segment pair Y (column 2) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: terminal filament
description: Anterior most region of the germarium, forming the tip. It contains a group of terminal filament somatic cells. Only the most posterior cells contact the germline stem cells.

label: PB slice 6-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 6 and axon terminals in both fan-shaped body segment pair Z (column 1) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: vitellarium
description: Ovariole excluding the germarium.

label: ovariole
description: An egg assembly line. Consists of a germarium at the anterior tip connected to a chain of egg chambers, each one more mature than the preceding, more anterior egg chamber in the chain. Each ovariole is encased in an ovarian sheath. A typical ovary contains about 16 ovarioles.

label: polar follicle cell
description: Follicle cell at the anterior or posterior pole of the egg chamber. The anterior polar follicle cells become border follicle cells. The posterior polar follicle cells are precursors of the posterior aeropyle.

label: follicle cell
description: The cells that make up the inner lining of the ovariole.

label: centripetally migrating follicle cell
description: A follicle cell that migrates from the dorso-anterior of the oocyte associated follicular epithelium, in between the nurse cells and the oocyte. These cells are precursors of the operculum.

label: PB slice 6-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 6 and axon terminals in both fan-shaped body segment pair Z (column 1) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: PB-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge (except glomerulus 1) and axon terminals in fan-shaped body layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: nodulus subunit III posterior domain
description: Large, posterior domain of nodulus subunit III in the adult brain.

label: PB slice 5-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 5 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair Y (column 2) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: nurse follicle cell
description: Follicle cell of the germarium that migrates posteriorly and covers the nurse cells during stage 9. There are approximately 50 follicle cells that flatten to form a squamous domain over the nurse cells.

label: nurse cell associated follicular epithelium
description: A squamous epithelium which covers the nurse cells from the start of stage 9 of oogenesis.

label: PB slice 4-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 4 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair X (column 3) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: follicle stem cell
description: Stem cell from which the follicle cells that envelop the germline cyst derive from. There are two follicle stem cells in each germarium, located at opposite sides of the lateral wall of the germarium, in between regions 2a and 2b.

label: PB slice 3-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 3 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: terminal filament basal cell
description: Somatic cell in the anterior germarium region 1, near the germline stem cells. There is a group of 3 cells asymmetrically positioned.

label: PB slice 2-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 2 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: border follicle cell
description: A follicle cell that migrates from the anterior pole of the egg chamber, between the nurse cells, to the anterior of the oocyte where they participate in formation of the micropyle. About 6-10 border cells per egg chamber migrate as a tightly associated cluster.

label: egg chamber
description: Female germline cyst that is not part of a germarium. It consists of three cell types: an oocyte, nurse and follicle cells.

label: abdominal segment A3 vA neuron
description: Ventral group vA neuron of larval abdominal segment A3.

label: ventral group vA neuron
description: Peptidergic neuron located at the ventral surface of the larval ventral nerve cord in abdominal segments A2-A4.

label: abdominal segment A4 vA neuron
description: Ventral group vA neuron of larval abdominal segment A4.

label: central dome sensillum
description: Dome shaped cuticular process of the larval dorsal organ, innervated by seven circularly arranged triplets of olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) dendrites. The wall of the dome has numerous pore channels, consistent with a role as an olfactory sense organ.

label: embryonic/larval antennal segment sensillum
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some larval antennal segment (FBbt:00001735).

label: dorsal organ
description: An external compound sense organ of the antenno-maxillary complex of the larval head consisting of a dome shaped cuticular process, innervated by seven circularly arranged triplets of olfactory receptor neuron dendrites. Six small papillae surround the base of the central dome.

label: adult rectal sac
description: Broadly expanded, thin walled sac-like structure that tapers posteriorly to the narrower rectum proper terminating at the anus, at the posterior end of the adult hindgut.

label: posterior adult hindgut
description: Posterior-most region of the adult hindgut. It consists of a broadly expanded rectal sac (rectal ampulla) that tapers posteriorly to the narrow rectum proper, terminating at the anus. Protruding from the walls into the lumen of the rectal sac are two pairs of conical rectal papillae.

label: adult pylorus
description: Posterior most portion of the adult midgut that joins the hindgut and receives the Malpighian tubules.

label: adepithelial cell of leg disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with a leg imaginal disc.
synonyms: adepithelial cell of ventral thoracic disc

label: thoracic adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any embryonic precursor cell of adult muscle (FBbt:00003232) that is part of some thorax (FBbt:00000015).

label: EB-IDFP DSB-PB 1 glomerulus neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers, and axon terminals in the ipsi- or contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body of the IDFP) and one odd-numbered protocerebral bridge slice (except slice 9).

label: interfollicle cell
description: Cell that is part of the stalk connecting adjacent egg chambers in a vitellarium. Each stalk is usually composed of 5-8 interdigitating cells.

label: basal stalk
description: Stalk that connects the female ovarioles in the posterior tip of the ovary to the oviduct. It is formed by 5-7 interfollicle cells.

label: EB-IDFP DSB-PB 2 glomeruli neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slices 7 and 8, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 8, the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body of the IDFP) and both protocerebral bridge slices 1.

label: PB slice 9-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 9 and axon terminals in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: oviduct
description: Duct of the female genitalia that connects the ovaries to the uterus. It is divided into 2 lateral and one common regions.

label: common oviduct
description: Epithelial tube that connects the lateral oviducts to the uterus. It is lined with a chitinous intima.

label: PB slice 8-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 8 and axon terminals in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body segment pair X (column 3) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: presumptive oviduct
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the oviduct.

label: uterus
description: An elongate muscular pouch that is the site of egg fertilization. It is lined with a thin chitinous intima and is connected to the common oviduct anteriorly and the vulva posteriorly. The uterus holds a single egg at a time, with its micropyle near the opening of the seminal receptacle.

label: PB slice 7-FB-NO subunit 3 posterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 7 and axon terminals in the ipsilateral fan-shaped body segment pair Y (column 2) and layer 1 (layer f) and the contralateral posterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: abdominal segment A2 vA neuron
description: Ventral group vA neuron of larval abdominal segment A2.

label: calyx of oviduct
description: The anterior-most, cup-shaped region of the lateral oviduct.

label: genital disc
description: Imaginal disc that gives rise to the internal and external genitalia, analia and adult hind gut (Cohen, 1993).

label: ovary
description: Female gonad. It contains about 16 ovarioles.

label: EB-IDFP VSB-PB slice 2 glomerulus neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slices 5 and 7, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 6, the ipsilateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body of the IDFP) and contralateral protocerebral bridge slice 2.

label: ellipsoid body slice 5
description: Fifth from top-most ellipsoid body slice.

label: female accessory gland
description: Small, bilaterally paired gland that lies behind the spermathecae and is connected to the uterus by a duct. The gland wall consists of a single layer of polygonal cells, each with a large vacuole and a minute acidophillic granule towards the gland lumen.

label: secretion
description: The controlled release of a substance by a cell or a tissue.

label: EB-IDFP DSB-PB slice 7 neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slices 4 and 6, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 5, the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body of the IDFP) and ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slice 7.

label: EB-IDFP DSB-PB slice 5 neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 1 and contralateral slice 2, and axon terminals in the contralateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 1, the ipsilateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body of the IDFP) and contralateral protocerebral bridge slice 5.

label: EB-IDFP DSB-PB slice 3 neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic and axonal arbors in the inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 3 and contralateral slice 5, and axon terminals in the ipsilateral ellipsoid body inner, outer and posterior ellipsoid body layers of slice 4, the ipsilateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body of the IDFP) and contralateral protocerebral bridge slice 3.

label: female accessory gland duct
description: A duct connecting a female accessory gland to the uterus, opening just behind the spermathecal ducts. It consists of a tube of thin epithelium lined with a thin chitinous intima, irregularly ringed with sharp ridges that project into the lumen.

label: Tv2 neuron
description: Tv neuron of the larval thoracic segment 2.

label: thoracic T2 neuron
description: Neuron that is part of the mesothoracic segment.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V3
description: Glomerulus that is innervated by extrinsic neurons that project from the larval subesophageal ganglion and that is usually located on the ventral surface of the larval mushroom body calyx.

label: larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus
description: Any glomerulus (FBbt:00005386) that is part of some calyx of larval mushroom body (FBbt:00007191).

label: calyx of larval mushroom body
description: Calyx of the larval mushroom body.

label: Tv3 neuron
description: Tv neuron of the larval thoracic segment 3.

label: thoracic T3 neuron
description: Neuron that is part of the metathoracic segment.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus D1
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from larval uniglomerular projection neuron 33b/47a. This is a large,landmark glomerulus that lies in a central position, posterior to glomerulus L3.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus A1
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from larval uniglomerular projection neuron 82a. It is usually located anterolaterally within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus A2
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that is usually located ventrolaterally within the calyx.

label: olfactory receptor neuron of dorsal organ
description: Odorant receptor expressing bipolar neuron whose dendrite innervates the central dome sensillum of the larval dorsal organ, whose cell body is part of the dorsal organ ganglion and whose axon is carried by the antennal nerve to innervate a larval antennal lobe glomerulus. There are 21 neurons of this type.

label: embryonic/larval olfactory receptor neuron
description: Any olfactory receptor neuron (FBbt:00005926) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: embryonic/larval antennal nerve
description: Nerve that carries axons from larval sense organs in the head, including the dorsal organ, to the larval antennal lobe.

label: dorsal organ ganglion
description: Ganglion situated posterior to the larval dorsal organ which contains the cell bodies of the odorant receptor cells which send dendrites into the dorsal organ and axons to the antennal lobe via the larval antennal nerve.

label: single-organism cellular process
description: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, occurring within a single organism.

label: cellular process
description: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: single-organism transport
description: The directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, or within a multicellular organism by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore, involving a single organism.

label: single-organism localization
description: A localization which involves only one organism.

label: transport
description: The directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) or cellular components (such as complexes and organelles) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, or within a multicellular organism by means of some agent such as a transporter, pore or motor protein.

label: abdominal 1 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A1.

label: abdominal 2 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A2.

label: abdominal 3 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A3.

label: abdominal 4 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A4.

label: abdominal 5 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A5.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus A3
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 45a. It is usually located anteromedially within the calyx.

label: abdominal 6 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A6.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V4
description: Glomerulus of the larval mushroom body calyx that is located in a ventral position, posterior to glomerulus A3.

label: abdominal 7 dopaminergic AL neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment 7.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L1
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from larval uniglomerular projection neuron 13a. It is usually the most dorsoposterior glomerulus of the calyx.

label: Tv1 neuron
description: Tv neuron of the larval thoracic 1 segment.

label: thoracic T1 neuron
description: Neuron that is part of the prothoracic segment.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus M3
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from larval uniglomerular projection neuron 83. It is usually located at the ventromedial corner of the calyx.

label: spermathecum
description: A bilaterally paired, mushroom-shaped organ consisting of a capsule connected to the uterus by a slender duct. The capsule is an, inverted, double-walled bowl, the outer wall of which is a layer of cuboidal epithelium and the inner wall of which is chitinous intima secreted by the epithelium. After copulation, the lumen of the capsule is filled with a concentrically coiled mass of the spermatozoa.

label: sperm storage
description: The retention of sperm by a female following mating.

label: presumptive spermathecum
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the spermathecum.

label: pedicel of ovarian sheath
description: The posterior end of the ovarian sheath, between the most posterior egg or egg chamber and the lateral oviduct.

label: female genital disc
description: Genital disc that gives rise to the vagina and vaginal plates, uterus, parovaria, spermatheca, seminal recepticle, oviducts, female analia and hindgut. (Cohen, 1993).

label: ovarian sheath
description: A tubular structure which surrounds the ovarian basement membrane (tunica propria) around each ovariole and which consists of a thin layer of muscle and abundant tracheoles sandwiched between two epithelial layers.

label: spermathecal duct
description: Duct connecting the capsule of the spermathecum to the uterus. It opens into the uterus on its dorsal wall, just posterior to the mouth of the oviduct and close to the openings of the accessory gland ducts.

label: seminal receptacle
description: A compactly coiled tube epithelial tube connected to the anterior end of the uterus. The tube is long (1.7-2.7 mm) and slender, consisting of a proximal duct around 22 micrometres wide with a narrow lumen (2.5 - 4.5 micrometres) and a wider distal half (around 28 micrometres) with a much larger lumen (12-19 micrometres). It is lined with a thin chitinous intima and surrounded by a nucleated sheath. The coil as a whole is surrounded by a sparsely nucleated peritoneal envelope. After copulation, the lumen of this tube is filled with spermatozoa, arranged longitudinally with their heads towards the closed tip of the tube.

label: presumptive seminal receptacle
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the seminal receptacle.

label: male germline stem cell
description: Male germline cell and stem cell from which all other male germline cells develop. Male germline stem cells are part of the germinal proliferation center of the testis. They are arranged around a central hub made up of densely packed hub cells (apical cells), to which they are attached via adherens junctions.

label: male germline cell
description: Cell that develops into or is itself a spermatozoon.

label: germline stem cell
description: Stem cell that is the precursor of gametes.

label: vagina
description: An elongate muscular pouch, the anterior part of which is the uterus, where eggs are fertilized, and the posterior part of which, the vulva is the copulatory orifice and site of exit for eggs.

label: presumptive vagina
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the vagina.

label: presumptive uterus
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the uterus.

label: vulva
description: Broad area with chitinous papillae and long and narrow ridges which surrounds the vaginal opening.

label: presumptive vulva
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the vulva.

label: BLP1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLP1 neuroblast.

label: BLP2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLP2 neuroblast.

label: BLP3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLP3 neuroblast.

label: BLP4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLP4 neuroblast.

label: BLP5 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLP5 neuroblast.

label: BLVa1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLVa1 neuroblast.

label: BLVa2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLVa2 neuroblast.

label: BLD3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLD3 neuroblast.

label: BLD4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLD4 neuroblast.

label: BLD5 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLD5 neuroblast (VPNp1).

label: abdominal 5 dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A5.

label: abdominal dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in the larval abdomen.

label: abdominal 4 dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A4.

label: cyst cell
description: One of a pair of somatic cells that envelope each cyst of developing male germline cells.

label: cyst progenitor cell
description: A somatic stem cell; Mother of cyst cells; Associated with the hub of the germinal center and with male germline stem cells.

label: abdominal 7 dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A7.

label: primary gonial cell
description: Daughter of a male germline stem cell. Unlike its sister, which will remain a stem cell, the primary gonial cell is displaced laterally from the hub cells, where it becomes enclosed by two 'cyst cells'. Morphology is much like its stem cell sister.

label: spermatogonium
description: Male germline cell found in the spermatogonial cyst.

label: abdominal 6 dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A6.

label: hub cell
description: Cell which is part of the hub of the germinal proliferation center. It is attached to male germline stem cells and somatic stem cells via adherens junctions.

label: abdominal 6 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A6.

label: spermatocyte ring canal
description: Cytoplasmic bridge that connects the 16 primary spermatocytes in a cyst.

label: ring canal
description: Cytoplasmic bridge that connects the male or female germline cells in a 16-cell cyst.

label: primary spermatocyte cyst
description: Male germline cyst containing primary 16 spermatocytes.

label: abdominal 3 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonin neuron of abdominal segment A3.

label: spermatocyte
description: Male germline cell that is part of the 16-cell spermatocyte cyst.

label: spermatocyte cyst
description: A male germline cyst containing 2 cyst cells surrounding 16-32 spermatocytes.

label: abdominal neuroblast
description: Any neuroblast (FBbt:00005146) that is part of some abdomen (FBbt:00000020).

label: abdominal 5 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A5.

label: abdominal 4 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A4.

label: spermatocyte fusome
description: Fusome found in the cytoplasm of the spermatocyte.

label: BLAd1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAd1 neuroblast.

label: BLAd2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAd2 neuroblast.

label: BLAd3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAd3 neuroblast.

label: BLAd4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAd4 neuroblast.

label: BLAl lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAl neuroblast.

label: BLAvm lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAvm neuroblast.

label: BLD1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLD1 neuroblast.

label: BLD2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLD2 neuroblast.

label: BLAv1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAv1 neuroblast.

label: BLAv2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLAv2 neuroblast.

label: abdominal 4 ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in larval abdominal segment A4.

label: abdominal ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in the larval abdomen.

label: Nebenkern
description: Mitochondrial mass which is the result of fusion of mitochondria into one structure, found in developing spermatids. At the onion stage, the Nebenkern consists of a densely packed sphere of tightly packed multiple layers of wrapped mitochondrial membranes, that resembles an onion at cross section. At leaf stage, the Nebenkern unfurls to resemble a spear point or leaf blade, and later at comet stage it elongates and splits into two mitochondrial derivatives.

label: cell component
description: Anatomical structure that is a direct part of a cell.

label: onion stage spermatid
description: A round spermatid containing a spherical Nebenkern with an onion-like arrangement of mitochondrial material. The axoneme begins to grow out from the basal body inserted at the base of the nucleus and the Golgi complexes have fused to form the acroblast and acrosomal granule located at the apical side of the nucleus, opposite the basal body. There is a prominent protein body in the nucleus.

label: abdominal 3 ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in larval abdominal segment A3.

label: spermatid
description: One of 64, post meiotic, haploid male germ cells in a spermatid cyst, connected to other spermatids by cytoplasmic bridges. The loss of these cytoplasmic bridge (individualisation) marks the end of the spermatid stage.

label: spermatid cyst
description: A male germline cyst consisting of 2 cyst cells and 64 spermatids.

label: abdominal 6 ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in larval abdominal segment A6.

label: clew stage spermatid
description: A round spermatid in which fusion of mitochondria into a single, spherical mass with a clew-like (spherical Nebenkern) arrangement is complete. During this stage the centriole inserts into the base of the nucleus to become the basal body. The spermatid has increased in diameter to 6 micrometers. The second nuclear membrane no longer covers the part of the nucleus opposite the basal body and is often continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum.

label: abdominal 5 ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in larval abdominal segment A5.

label: protein body
description: Protein aggregate that forms a dark and dense structure found in the nucleus of a developing spermatid. It is first visible at the agglomeration stage, gradually increasing in size during the pre-elongation stage.

label: secondary spermatocyte
description: Spermatocyte from the end of the first meiotic division (meiosis I) to the end of the second meiotic division (meiosis II).

label: primary spermatocyte
description: Male germ cells of the 16-cell cyst from the end of the S-phase that precedes meiosis I to the end of meiosis I. This S-phase occurs very early in the 16-cell cyst stage so almost all 16 cell cysts are at the primary spermatocyte stage.

label: Y chromosome loop
description: Loop in the Y chromosome in the nucleus of primary spermatocytes. Y loops are caused by the transcription of male fertility factors present on the Y chromosome.

label: abdominal 1 medial neuroblast
description: Medially located neuroblast of the abdominal segment.

label: acroblast
description: Organelle formed by the fusion of the Golgi complexes, in an onion stage spermatid. It is located at the apical side of the nucleus, opposite the basal body, in the same area as the acrosomal granule. Together with the acrosomal granule it serves as the site of formation of the acrosome.

label: abdominal 7 ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in larval abdominal segment A7.

label: waste bag
description: After individualisation of spermatids, the excess cytoplasm and organelles are dumped in a waste bag at the tail end of the spermatid cyst. This bag pinches off and eventually degrades.

label: axial complex
description: The complex formed by the axoneme and Nebenkern derivatives that extends the length of the sperm tail at the end of the elongation stage. The position between the axoneme and the Nebenkern derivatives is characteristic, although they become somewhat independent regarding rotation after the sperm bundle coils during individualization stage.

label: individualization stage spermatid
description: A fully elongated spermatid, undergoing individualisation.

label: elongation stage spermatid
description: A spermatid which is no longer round, in which the nuclear shape changes from round to needle-shaped, and in which the mitochondrial derivatives unfolds, splits into two parts, and elongates along with the growing axoneme, with the two derivatives becoming unequal in size. The mitochondrial derivatives assume a characteristic position to a plane that splits the central pair of axoneme microtubules which changes slightly through elongation.

label: acrosomal granule
description: Granule found in the acroblast in an onion stage spermatid. It is located at the apical side of the nucleus, opposite the basal body. Together with the acroblast, it serves as the site of formation of the acrosome.

label: neuroblast DPL
description: Neuroblast located in the dorsolateral aspect of the protocerebrum.

label: neuroblast CP
description: Neuroblast located over the posterior apex of the brain.

label: neuroblast BLA
description: Neuroblast located anterior to the outer optic anlage, lateral to the spur of the mushroom body.

label: neuroblast BLD
description: Neuroblast located dorsally of the optic lobe.

label: neuroblast BLP
description: Neuroblast flanking the posterior slope of the optic lobe.

label: neuroblast DAL
description: Dorsoanterior lateral neuroblast flanking the spur and dorsal lobe of the mushroom body anteriorly and laterally.

label: neuroblast BA
description: Basoanterior neuroblast located around the antennal compartment.

label: neuroblast CM
description: Centromedial neuroblast located in the posterior deutocerebrum.

label: neuroblast TR
description: Tritocerebral neuroblast that medioventrally borders the anterior deutocerebrum.

label: tritocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the tritocerebrum.

label: neuroblast DPM
description: Neuroblast located in the dorsoposterior medial protocerebrum.

label: spermatozoon
description: A mature, haploid male gamete.

label: gamete
description: A mature reproductive cell containing a single set of chromosomes.

label: minor mitochondrial derivative
description: Smaller mitochondrial derivative that develops from mid elongation spermatid stage onwards. It lies at a 30 degrees angle to a plane that splits the central pair of axoneme microtubules.

label: Nebenkern derivative
description: Structure that develops from the Nebenkern during spermatid elongation. During late onion stage, the Nebenkern begins to unfurl and elongate. At comet stage it splits into two mitochondrial derivatives, which elongate and become unequal in size during mid elongation stage. The mitochondrial derivatives assume a characteristic position to a plane that splits the central pair of axoneme microtubules which changes slightly through elongation.

label: cell body rind of the central nervous system
description: Superficial neuronal layer of the central nervous system, composed of glia and the cell bodies of neurons (soma). The cell body rind lies under the perineurium.
synonyms: cortex of the central nervous system

label: testis pigment cell
description: Flat, polygonal, pigmented epithelial cell which is part of the outer layer of the testis sheath.

label: testis sheath
description: This testis sheath consists of an outer epithelial layer of pigment cells and a thin, circumferential layer of muscle cells, separated from each other by a basal lamina. A second basal lamina separates the muscle layer from the testis lumen.

label: brain
description: The supra-esophageal ganglion of the central nervous system, composed of three primitive ganglia known as protocerebrum, deutocerebrum and tritocerebrum. In the context of Drosophila it refers to the pre-oral ganglionic mass of the central nervous system containing the ventral ganglia.

label: gonadal sheath
description: Thin covering of the gonads, usually containing on or more epithelial and a muscle layers.

label: spermatid axoneme
description: Flagellar organelle that grows out from the basal body embedded at the base of the nucleus, on an onion stage spermatid. It elongates throughout the elongation stage to extend the length of the sperm tail. It is surrounded by a double membrane (axonemal sheath) and has the characteristic 9+2 disposition, with 9 outer doublet microtubules surrounding a central pair of singlet microtubules. During development, a projection from each doublet microtubule extends to form an accessory microtubule which becomes densely stained. Radial spokes develop that connect the outer doublets with the central region of the axoneme.

label: major mitochondrial derivative
description: Bigger mitochondrial derivative that develops from mid elongation spermatid stage onwards. It initially lies at a 90 degrees angle to a plane that splits the central pair of axoneme microtubules. This decreases gradually to 60 degrees during elongation, returning to 90 degrees during the later stages of spermatid differentiation. Late in the elongation stage, there is a deposition of a paracrystalline array of densely staining granules closely juxtaposed to the axonemal sheath.

label: neuromere
description: A segmental subdivision of the nervous system.

label: labral segment
description: Procephalic segment anterior to the antennal segment. In the adult it bears the clypeo-labrum.

label: supraesophageal ganglion
description: The pre-oral neuropils of the brain located above and some of it below the esophagus, comprising three fused ganglia (protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum) in the head.

label: seminal vesicle
description: Enlarged distal region of the vas deferens. It connects the testis, via the testicular duct, to the main region of the vas deferens. The seminal vesicles taper into the twisted narrow portions of the vasa deferentia, which in turn opens into the anterior ejaculatory duct.

label: male genital disc
description: Genital disc that gives rise to the penis and external genitalia, sperm pump, ejaculatory duct, paragonia and vas deferens, anal plates and adult hindgut (Cohen, 1993).

label: vas deferens
description: Paired tube of the male genitalia which opens into the anterior ejaculatory duct. Its distal portion is enlarged, forming the seminal vesicle. The twisted narrow portions of the vasa deferentia merge just before the junction with the anterior ejaculatory duct. In recently emerged flies, three distinct wall layers of the vas deferens are visible: a thick inner epithelium, with columnar cells containing small nuclei, a thin inner sheath with inconspicuous, widely spaced and flattened nuclei and an outer sheath of finely reticular cytoplasm containing an occasional large nucleus.

label: testicular duct
description: Duct connecting the testis and the seminal vesicles in the adult male genitalia. It is 80 micrometers long and 23 micrometers in diameter, making a single spiral turn. It has a narrow lumen, surrounded by a thick epithelium containing small, closely spaced nuclei. It is covered in an inner sheath and an outer pigment sheath, as in the seminal vesicles.

label: DN1 neuron
description: DN (dorsal Period-expressing neuron of adult brain) whose cell body is located dorsal to the projections of the `s-LNv Pdf neurons` (FBbt:00003764). There are about 17 of these per cluster.

label: adult DN period neuron
description: Period (FBgn0003068) expressing neuron of the adult brain whose cell body is located in the posterior, dorsal-most cortex.

label: adult pacemaker neuron
description: Pacemaker neuron that is part of the adult nervous system.

label: male accessory gland
description: Paired distended tubular accessory gland of the male genitalia which opens into the ejaculatory duct just behind the vas deferens. It is composed of binucleate cells.

label: presumptive male accessory gland
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the male accessory gland.

label: DALv3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALv3 neuroblast.

label: BAmd2 neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAmd2 neuroblast.

label: TRvm lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the TRvm neuroblast.

label: secondary neuroblast
description: Progeny of the type II neuroblast that divides between 4 and 8 times to produce another secondary neuroblast and GMC, which further divides to produce a pair of neurons, glia or mixed neuronal/glial progeny (Bayraktar et al., 2010, Viktorin et al., 2011).

label: neuroblast
description: A neural stem cell that delaminates from the ectoderm and that buds off new ganglion mother cells during the course of development.

label: neuroblast DAM
description: Dorsoanterior medial neuroblast located anterior and medial of the mushroom body.

label: BLVa3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLVa3 neuroblast.

label: BLVp1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLVp1 neuroblast.

label: LVp2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the LVp2 neuroblast.

label: BLVp5 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BLVp5 neuroblast.

label: abdominal 7 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Neuron of the embryonic or larval abdominal segment that is located laterally, posteriorly to the segmental nerve root. There are around 14 of these cells.

label: ejaculatory duct
description: Unpaired duct that connects the male accessory glands and vasa deferentia to the ejaculatory bulb in the adult male genitalia.

label: presumptive ejaculatory duct
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the ejaculatory duct.

label: small field neuron
description: An interneuron whose arborization fields are small.

label: ejaculatory bulb plate
description: Basal plate of the ejaculatory bulb apodeme of the adult male genitalia.

label: ejaculatory bulb apodeme
description: Sclerotized rod-like apodeme on the upper side of the ejaculatory bulb of the adult male genitalia.

label: A1-7 DO1 motor neuron
description: U1 neuron of A1-7.  It innervates dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609). Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domains of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DO1 muscle of the next posterior segment with type Ib boutons. It receives input from the contralateral larval A08e1 and A08e3 local neurons.

label: U1 neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the first ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most dorsal oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: larval A08e3 local neuron
description: Even-skipped lateral neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. In each abdominal segment, the primary neurite extends into the neuromere crossing the VL fascicle and projecting dorsally across the CI fascicle. It forms one arbor that bifurcates and extends in a circular manner. One neurite crosses the midline in between the DM and VM fascicles, extends dorsally, to just dorsal to the CI fascicle, and forms an arbor that extends anteriorly in a circular manner. It is synapsed by and synapses onto the contralateral A08e3 and A08e1. It receives input from the ipsilateral proprioceptor neurons vbd and lesA, and the GDL neuron. It outputs to the contralateral RP2, U1, U2, and dorsal motorneurons, A06l neuron, and contralateral SA1 and SA3 interneurons. There is one neuron per segment.

label: abdominal 1 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000694) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: pontine neuron
description: Interneuron that is intrinsic (local) to a single neuropil domain of the central complex and that connects two substructures of it.

label: intrinsic neuron
description: A neuron arborizing exclusively within a given neuropil domain. Intrinsic (local) interneurons may be ipsilateral, restricted to one of side of a paired neuropil domain, or bilateral, extending a process across the midline and arborizing in both sides of a pair of bilaterally symmetric neuropil domains.

label: anterior ejaculatory duct
description: Duct that connects the vasa deferentia and accessory glands to the ejaculatory bulb in the male adult genitalia. It is 1.2mm long with an anterior dilated portion with a diameter of 120 micrometers, tapering to a narrow tube of 20 micrometers in diameter which enter the ejaculatory bulb. In the abdomen, it extends dorsally, then curves downward and to the left and loops over the rectum to the right side of segment 5 or 6. The duct wall consists of a single thick layer of epithelial cells lined with a thin chitinous intima surrounded by an inconspicuous outer sheath.

label: pb-fb tract
