description: Tract that connects an adjacent pair of protocerebral bridge glomeruli to either a single fan-shaped body slice or a pair of adjacent fan-shaped body slices.

label: posterior ejaculatory duct
description: Duct that connects the ejaculatory bulb to the aedeagus in the male adult genitalia. It is 300 micrometers long with a diameter of 11-18 micrometers, continuous with the intima lining the ejaculatory bulb. Its wall is chitinous and 0.5 micrometers thick, with small scattered nuclei on its surface. The duct passes below the rectum and opens below the ninth and tenth abdominal segments.

label: abdominal 2 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 3 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000739) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: DN2 neuron
description: DN (dorsal Period-expressing neuron of adult brain) whose medium-sized cell body is located posteriorly in the dorsal superior brain, ventral to the projections of the `s-LNv Pdf neurons` (FBbt:00003764). There are 2 cells in each DN2 cluster.

label: male accessory gland secondary cell
description: Cell type found in at the distal tip of both lobes of the male accessory gland. These cells are large, spherical and binucleate with large vacuoles. There are approximately 43 secondary cells interspersed with around 1000 main cells per lobe.

label: male accessory gland main cell
description: Cell type found in both lobes of the male accessory gland. These cells are flat, hexagonal and binucleate, which secrete their products into the lumen of each lobe. There are approximately 1000 main cells per lobe, interspersed with around 43 secondary cells.

label: adult apodeme
description: Apodeme that is part of an adult.

label: ejaculatory bulb
description: Bilaterally symmetric structure with two anterior and two posterior lateral lobes, a sclerotized rod-like apodeme arising from its upper side and muscles fibres radiating from the end of the rod to the side walls. The anterior ejaculatory duct enters the bulb on the upper side and the posterior ejaculatory duct arises between the paired projections on the opposite side. The walls of the bulb consists of a thick columnar epithelium lined with a well developed intima, enclosing a chamber filled with clear viscous fluid.

label: abdominal 5 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: DN3 neuron
description: DN (dorsal Period-expressing neuron of adult brain) with a cell body located in the lateral-most cluster of Period expressing DN neurons. There are around 40 cells in each cluster.

label: presumptive ejaculatory bulb
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the ejaculatory bulb.

label: abdominal 3 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 4 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000784) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: eb-no neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex that innervates only the ellipsoid body and the nodulus.

label: organ system
description: A division of the whole organism into specialized systems.

label: presumptive vas deferens
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the vas deferens.

label: abdominal 4 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000829) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000874) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000919) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: fb-no neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex that has small arborizations with club-like fiber endings in the fan-shaped body and terminates with spines and blebs in the contralateral nodulus.

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of salty taste
description: The series of events required for a salty taste stimulus to be received and converted to a molecular signal.
synonyms: perception of salty taste, sensory transduction of chemical stimulus

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of taste
description: The series of events involved in the perception of taste in which a gustatory chemical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: perception of taste, sensory transduction of chemical stimulus

label: sensory perception of salty taste
description: The series of events required to receive a salty taste stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of sweet taste
description: The series of events required for a sweet taste stimulus to be received and converted to a molecular signal.

label: sensory perception of sweet taste
description: The series of events required to receive a sweet taste stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of bitter taste
description: The series of events required for a bitter taste stimulus to be received and converted to a molecular signal.
synonyms: sensory detection of chemical stimulus during perception of bitter taste

label: sensory perception of bitter taste
description: The series of events required to receive a bitter taste stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: abdominal 2 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 3 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000731) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: A1-7 DA2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the second ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1. It innervates the internal dorsal acute muscle 2 of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral and intermediate domains of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the DA2 muscle with type Ib boutons. It receives input from the contralateral larval A08e1-3 local neurons.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: pb-eb-eb neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge and two sectors of the ellipsoid body.

label: assembly zone
description: Inner layer of the procuticle, that directly overlies the epidermis.

label: procuticle
description: Lamellate innermost layer of cuticle between the epicuticle and the epidermis. It consists largely of protein and chitin. Within each lamella layer, chitin-protein fibers are arranged parallel to each other and to the surface of the underlying epidermis. The lamellae themselves are arranged in a helicoid fashion. In the pupa, it is composed of three distinct layers: exocuticle, endocuticle and assembly zone. In the adult, the exo- and endocuticle layers are not distinct.

label: pb-fb-fb neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge and either two adjacent segments of one layer of the fan-shaped body or adjacent layers of a single segment.

label: abdominal 3 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 4 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000776) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 5 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000821) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: pb-fb-eb neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge, the ellipsoid body and the fan-shaped body.

label: exuvial fluid
description: Fluid that is secreted by the epithelial cells of the cuticle at each molt and that fills the space between the old and the new cuticle. It contains enzymes that degrade the old cuticle.

label: portion of organism substance
description: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body.

label: pb-eb-no neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in one protocerebral bridge glomerulus (except glomerulus 1) and axon terminals in the posterior ring of two adjacent ellipsoid body domains and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: nodulus subunit I
description: Most dorsal subunit of the nodulus.

label: cuticular pore
description: Pore found in the cuticle.

label: abdominal 5 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 6 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000866) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: fb-eb-no neuron
description: A small field neuron intrinsic to the central complex that arborizes in only the fan-shaped body, the ellipsoid body and the nodulus.

label: epicuticle
description: Amorphous layer between the cuticulin layer and the procuticle which consists largely of protein and is generally free of chitin.

label: fb-eb neuron
description: A small field neuron intrinsic to the central complex that arborizes in only the fan-shaped body and the ellipsoid body.

label: cuticulin layer
description: Outermost layer of the cuticle consisting of proteins and waxes which functions as an impermeability barrier. It overlies the epicuticle.

label: abdominal 7 DO1 motor neuron
description: Any U1 neuron (FBbt:00001565) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: pb-no neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge and the noduli.

label: endocuticle
description: The middle layer of the procuticle of the pupa, that forms after the pupal molt. It is composed of chitin, and it has a lighter pigmentation and less dense structure than the exocuticle. This layer is only found in pupa.

label: pupal cuticle
description: Cuticle of the pupal stage.

label: U2 neuron
description: Motor neuron developing from the second ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: abdominal 1 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000686) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: fb-ltr neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the fan-shaped body and the bulbs (lateral triangles).

label: exocuticle
description: The outer layer of the procuticle of the pupa, that forms before the pupal molt. It is composed of chitin and other hardening substances, which gives it a darker pigmentation and denser structure than the endocuticle. This layer is only found in pupa.

label: abdominal 6 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000911) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: ring neuron
description: A large field neuron that forms ring-shaped arborizations in the ellipsoid body that circle the ellipsoid body canal. These arborizations may form complete or partial rings.

label: large field neuron of the central complex
description: Large field neuron that innervates the central complex. Typically these neurons innervate a single neuropil domain with the central complex, arborizing in either the entire domain or some entire subdomain, as well as innervating additional regions external to the central complex.

label: large field neuron
description: Interneuron with one or more large arborization fields relative to the neuropil domain(s) it innervates.

label: neuropil
description: Multi-cell component structure of the central nervous system consisting largely of neuron projections (tracts and synaptic neuropil domains) and associated glial cells. This corresponds to the part of the CNS that is enclosed by the cortex.

label: abdominal 7 DA2 motor neuron
description: Any U2 neuron (FBbt:00001566) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: ring neuron R1
description: Ring neuron R that arborizes in an inner ring of the ellipsoid body, close to the ellipsoid body canal. Arborizing branches originate in the ellipsoid body canal and extend outwards.

label: ring neuron R
description: Ring neuron whose soma is located in a cluster in the cortex just dorso-lateral to the antennal lobes and ventro-lateral to the lateral accessory lobes (ventral bodies) and which, in addition to forming ring arborizations with bleb-type (Hanesch et al., 1989) presynaptic terminals (Young and Armstrong, 2010) in the ellipsoid body, has a very small, compact arborization of thin (Hanesch et al., 1989) postsynaptic (Young and Armstrong, 2010) fibers in the ipsilateral bulb (lateral triangle). The fibers of these neurons run through the RF-tract. Their soma are very small - similar in size to those of the Kenyon cells.

label: dorsal thick hair
description: Small and broad dorsal hair of the dorsal region of the larval cuticle. There are 2 to 3 rows of hairs per segment. These rows are posterior to the smooth cuticle and anterior to the rows of dorsal fine hairs.

label: dorsal hair
description: Hair on the dorsal surface of the larva on all segments except the prothorax, which is devoid of them. Members of this group are distributed in a well defined pattern. In the thoracic segments, three types of hairs are seen, organized in regions from anterior to posterior. In the abdominal segments, there are only two types, corresponding to the types seen in the anterior region of the thoracic segments. The polarity of the hairs is also different between the thoracic and abdominal segments.

label: embryonic/larval cuticle
description: Cuticle of the late embryo or larva.

label: abdominal 3 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal desA neuron
description: Sensory neuron associated either with abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 or with abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: extrinsic ring neuron ExR2
description: Extrinsic ring neuron that arborizes with blebs in the posterior of the ellipsoid body. It branches in the median protocerebrum.

label: extrinsic ring neuron
description: Ring neuron with arborizations outside the central complex.

label: puparium cuticle
description: Cuticle of the puparium stage.

label: third instar larval cuticle
description: Cuticle of the third instar larva.

label: extrinsic ring neuron ExR1
description: Extrinsic ring neuron with a large soma located in the pars intercerebralis. It projects ventrally and ipsilaterally, arborizing in the superior medial protocerebrum (smpr), the upper fan-shaped body and lateral accessory lobes (ventral bodies). Its main projection then encircles the ellipsoid body and sends multiple evenly spaced projections that arborize in an anterior ring corresponding to the arborization domain of R3 neurons. Arborizations of this neuron are spiny (Hanesch et al., 1989). They are presynaptic in the fan-shaped body and ellipsoid body and postsynaptic in the lateral accessory lobes and smpr (Armstrong and Young, 2010).

label: ellipsoid body anterior ring
description: Concentric subdivision of the ellipsoid body that lies anteriorly between the outer and inner rings. It contains the arborization of R2 and R3 ring neurons.

label: abdominal 4 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: median fan-shaped neuron Fm
description: Fan-shaped neuron that projects through the ellipsoid body canal via the median bundle to arborize with bleb-like terminals in the second layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped neuron F2
description: Any fan-shaped neuron (FBbt:00003657) that has synaptic terminals in some fan-shaped body layer 2 (FBbt:00007488).

label: puparial opercular seam
description: Fine seam of the puparium that appears ventrally to the anterior spiracles. It runs across the front of the puparium, curves posteriorly and extends along the sides. It bends upwards in the fourth segment where the right and left seams meet dorsally.

label: puparial operculum
description: Dorsal surface of the puparium circumscribed by the puparial opercular seam.

label: fan-shaped neuron
description: Neuron with a large arborization field that forms a quasi-horizontal strata within the fan-shaped body that fills it in both the transverse and longitudinal directions. They mostly extend caudally from the anterior margin of the fan-shaped body. This pattern makes some of them look like a fan, although the strata in most cases do not show a separation into 8 (or 16) segments. Some subtypes are specific to a single fan-shaped body layer.

label: abdominal 6 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: ring neuron R3
description: Ring neuron R that arborizes in the anterior layer of the inner and outer rings of the ellipsoid body. Arborizing branches originate in the ellipsoid body canal and extend outwards.

label: embryonic/larval integumentary system
description: Integumentary system of the late embryo or larva.

label: ring neuron R2
description: Ring neuron R that arborizes only in the outer ring of the ellipsoid body. Arborizing branches originate in the ellipsoid body canal and radiate outwards.

label: dorsal fine hair
description: Thin and long dorsal hair of the dorsal region of the larval cuticle. There are 7 rows of hairs per segment. These rows are posterior to the rows of dorsal thick hairs.

label: desA neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: second instar larval cuticle
description: Cuticle of the second instar larva.

label: abdominal 1 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: ring neuron R4
description: Ring neuron R that arborizes only in the outer ring of the ellipsoid body. Arborizing branches originate in the periphery of the ellipsoid body canal and extend inwards.

label: embryonic/first instar larval cuticle
description: Cuticle of the late embryo or first instar larva.

label: CP4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the CP4 neuroblast.

label: abdominal 7 desA neuron
description: Any abdominal desA neuron (FBbt:00002321) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: lateral fan-shaped neuron Fl
description: Fan-shaped neuron with a fiber that reaches the fan-shaped body laterally and that extends along its anterior surface.

label: abdominal desB neuron
description: Sensory neuron associated either with abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 or with abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: desB neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: DPLp1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLp1 neuroblasts.

label: DPLp2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLp2 neuroblast.

label: DPLm1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLm1 neuroblast.

label: DPLm2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLm2 neuroblast.

label: DPLcv lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLcv neuroblast.

label: CP1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the CP1 neuroblast.

label: CP2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the CP2 neuroblast.

label: CP3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the CP3 neuroblast.

label: prepupal cuticle
description: Cuticle of the prepupal stage.

label: prepupal integumentary system
description: Integumentary system of the prepupa.

label: adult cuticle
description: Cuticle of the adult.

label: adult integumentary system
description: Integumentary system of the adult.

label: abdominal 1 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: DPLl3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLl3 neuroblast.

label: abdominal 6 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: gut suspension muscle 4
description: The most posterior of the embryonic/larval gut suspension muscles. It has a longitudinal orientation, with its posterior end attached to the posterior integument and anterior end to the hindgut.

label: gut suspension muscle
description: Embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle, one end of which inserts into the epidermis and the other into the distal hindgut.

label: lateral ellipsoid body tract
description: A transverse tract within the protocerebrum of the adult brain that is connected to the inferior medial/lateral protocerebrum and the central complex.

label: intrinsic protocerebral bridge neuron
description: Interneuron that innervates only the adult protocerebral bridge. Its fiber enters the protocerebral bridge laterally. The soma of these neurons are located in the posterior cortex, medial and ventral to the Kenyon cell soma.

label: abdominal 7 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: embryonic/larval apodeme
description: Apodeme that is part of the embryo/larva. Apodemes are not a continuous structure, but are split into two halves. In the embryo, this break is visible laterally. In the larva, the dorsal and ventral halves in the thoracic and abdominal segments are staggered, with the dorsal part being posterior to the ventral one.

label: apodeme
description: A cuticular ingrowth of the endoskeleton, sometimes only a peg, frequently ridge-like, and often serving as a muscle attachment site. Does not generally correspond to superficial invaginations.

label: late embryo
description: A collective term for stages 16 and 17.

label: abdominal desC neuron
description: Sensory neuron of abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: desC neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: A dorsal, mono-innervated campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal apodeme
description: Any apodeme (FBbt:00005091) that is part of some late embryo (FBbt:00005333) and that is part of some abdomen (FBbt:00000020) and that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: abdominal apodeme
description: Any apodeme (FBbt:00005091) that is part of some abdomen (FBbt:00000020).

label: abdomen
description: The most posterior of the three tagma (FBbt:00000002).

label: embryonic/larval protocerebral bridge primordial
description: The primordium of the adult protocerebral bridge in the larval brain. It consists of bilaterally symmetrical tubular shaped region containing both differentiated and undifferentiated synapses, in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (IPp or CPM). It curls around the dorsal side from the posterior, growing during the larval period towards the midline. Fusion of the two halves only occurs at 48h after pupariation.

label: abdominal 1 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 1 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002800).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme
description: Apodeme located at the boundary between two segments.

label: abdominal 2 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic/larval hindgut
description: Posterior part of the embryonic/larval alimentary canal.

label: extrinsic al-pb neuron
description: A serotonergic neuron that innervates the antennal lobe, projects along the lateral antennal lobe tract (lALT) and innervates the protocerebral bridge and the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label: lateral antennal lobe tract
description: Tract that emerges from the posterior ventral part of the antennal lobe, at the horizontal level of the top of the V glomerulus (ventral root). It runs posteriorly, turns dorsolaterally and runs through the ventrolateral protocerebrum to project to the medial periphery of the lateral horn. It contains axons of antennal lobe projection neurons.

label: epidermoblast
description: Progenitor of an epidermal cell.

label: extrinsic no neuron
description: Any extrinsic neuron (FBbt:00003660) that has synaptic terminals in some nodulus (FBbt:00003680).

label: abdominal 3 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: gut suspension muscle 1
description: The anterior-most of the embryonic/larval gut suspension muscles. It has an oblique orientation, with its posterior end attached to the hindgut.

label: intrinsic lateral accessory lobe neuron
description: Interneuron that innervates only the adult lateral accessory lobe (ventral body).

label: abdominal 4 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: gut suspension muscle 2
description: The second anterior-most of the embryonic/larval gut suspension muscles. It has an oblique orientation, with its posterior end attached to the hindgut.

label: abdominal 5 desB neuron
description: Any abdominal desB neuron (FBbt:00002329) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: gut suspension muscle 3
description: The third anterior-most of the embryonic/larval gut suspension muscles. It has an acute orientation with its anterior end attached to the hindgut.

label: oenocyte
description: Large cell located in a cluster or row under the abdominal epidermis, to which it is as attached.

label: abdominal 2 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 2 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002801).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal intersegmental apodeme
description: Apodeme located at the boundary between two abdominal segments.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 1 intersegmental apodeme
description: Any embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme (FBbt:00001007) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval A1-7 intersegmental apodeme
description: Intersegmental apodeme of embryonic/larval segments A1-7. It is the insertion site for longitudinal and ventral oblique muscles of A1-7 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 172).

label: abdominal 3 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 3 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002802).

label: abdominal 3 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 4 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002803).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 2 intersegmental apodeme
description: Any embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme (FBbt:00001007) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 1 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 1 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002808).

label: abdominal desD neuron
description: Sensory neuron of abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 7 intersegmental apodeme
description: An embryonic/larval apodeme at the boundary of A7 and A8.

label: central body
description: Region of synaptic neuropil consisting of the fan-shaped body and the ellipsoid body.

label: abdominal 2 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 2 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002809).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic/larval intrasegmental apodeme
description: An embryonic/larval apodeme that is located within a segment, not at the boundary between segments.

label: abdominal 3 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 3 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002810).

label: abdominal 3 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: muscle attachment site
description: The place where the muscle system attaches to the body wall.

label: A1-7 longitudinal muscle
description: Any longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000480) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: A1-7 ventral oblique muscle
description: Any ventral oblique muscle that is part of larval abdominal segments 1-7. All of these attach to the intersegmental apodeme of their segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 172).

label: dopaminergic PPL1 neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 12 cell bodies in the cortex of the posterior inferior lateral protocerebrum of the adult brain, immediately lateral to the mushroom body calyx. Members of this group project to various parts of the mushroom body: the tip of the alpha lobe; the tip of the alpha' lobe; the upper portion of the alpha lobe segment 2; alpha lobe segment 1 and the lower part of segment 2; and the pedunculus and spur (Mao and Davis, 2009). Long-range fibers project bilaterally to and arborize in the tips and stalks of the alpha and alpha' lobes, the heel and the peduncle (Claridge-Chang et al., 2009). Other members of this group arborize in areas other than the mushroom body: the edge of the medial portions of the medial lobes; broad areas surrounding the ipsilateral vertical lobes; areas posterior to the ipsilateral vertical lobes; the entire span of the superior arch (Mao and Davis, 2009) and the central complex (Claridge-Chang et al., 2009).

label: embryonic/larval fan-shaped body primordial
description: The primordium of the adult fan-shaped body in the larval posterior inferior protocerebrum (IPp or CPM). It consists of a bilaterally symmetrical slightly curved, horizontal, bar-shaped structure of tufts of filopodia, with undifferentiated synapses, branching off axon bundles stretching from the midline region posteriorly and adjacent to the mushroom body medial lobe, to a plexus slightly medial to the peduncle. In the late larval brain both halves are interconnected by a plexus of commissural fibers.

label: abdominal 4 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 4 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002811).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 5 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002804).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 3 intersegmental apodeme
description: Any embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme (FBbt:00001007) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 4 intersegmental apodeme
description: Any embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme (FBbt:00001007) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 6 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 6 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002805).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 desC neuron
description: Any abdominal desC neuron (FBbt:00002337) that is part of some abdominal 7 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002806).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002799) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 5 intersegmental apodeme
description: Any embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme (FBbt:00001007) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: desD neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a dorsal external sense (des) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: A dorsal, mono-innervated campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 6 intersegmental apodeme
description: Any embryonic/larval intersegmental apodeme (FBbt:00001007) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 1 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Anterior-most of the two intrasegmental apodemes located in each embryonic/larval segment A1-7. It is the site of insertion of A1-7 ventral acute muscles 1 and 2 (also known as vs3 and vs2 respectively).

label: embryonic/larval lateral accessory lobe
description: One of a group of synaptic neuropil domains of the larval brain which are located ventral to the mushroom body and are grouped around the long axon tracts connecting the larval protocerebrum to the ventral nerve cord. This medially located compartment is posterior to the antennal lobe. It is the larval counterpart of the adult lateral accessory lobe.

label: lateral complex
description: A synaptic neuropil block in the adult brain that lies anterior and lateral to the central complex, with which it is closely associated. Unlike components of the central complex, it is not separated from surrounding neuropils by a glial sheath.

label: abdominal 5 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 5 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002812).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 6 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002813).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 1 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Posterior-most of the two intrasegmental apodemes located in each embryonic/larval abdominal segment. It is the insertion site for A1-7 ventral acute muscle 3 (also known as vs1).

label: abdominal 7 desD neuron
description: Any abdominal desD neuron (FBbt:00002345) that is part of some abdominal 7 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002814).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002807) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal segment
description: Metameric subdivision of the abdomen.

label: A1-7 ventral acute muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral acute muscle of larval abdominal segments A1-7. This muscle is attached to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2) of its segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 172).

label: A1-7 ventral acute muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most ventral acute muscle of larval abdominal segments A1-7.

label: abdominal 4 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 4 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002843).

label: abdominal lesA neuron
description: Sensory neuron of abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It outputs to the ipsilateral larval A08e3 local neuron.

label: abdominal 4 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 6 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: mushroom body
description: Bilaterally paired neuropil structure situated postero-dorsally in the protocerebrum that functions in olfactory associative learning and memory. The mushroom body is divided into: the calyx, which is closest to the cortex and receives sensory interneuron afferents; the pedunculus, which is a thick axon bundle extending from the calyx to the base of the lobes; and the mushroom body lobe system, which consists of a vertical branch composed of two intertwined lobes (alpha and alpha') and a medial branch consisting of three parallel lobes (beta, beta' and gamma).

label: abdominal 5 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 5 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002844).

label: abdominal 5 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 7 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 6 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 6 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002845).

label: abdominal 6 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: A1-7 ventral acute muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most ventral acute muscle of larval abdominal segments A1-7. This muscle is attached to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2) of its segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 172).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 2 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: lesA neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Lateral mono-innervated hair of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 2 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult mushroom body
description: Bilaterally paired neuropil structure situated postero-dorsally in the protocerebrum that functions in olfactory associative learning and memory. The mushroom body is divided into: the calyx, which is closest to the cortex and receives sensory interneuron afferents; the pedunculus, which is a thick axon bundle extending from the calyx to the base of the lobes; and the mushroom body lobe system, which consists of a vertical branch composed of two intertwined lobes (alpha and alpha') and a medial branch consisting of three parallel lobes (beta, beta' and gamma).

label: abdominal 1 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 1 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002840).

label: abdominal 1 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 3 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: mushroom body pedunculus
description: A bundle of neuron projections of Kenyon cells, dense with synapses, that extends from the calyx of the mushroom body to the base of the mushroom body lobe system.

label: abdominal 2 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 2 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002841).

label: abdominal 2 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 4 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 3 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 3 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002842).

label: abdominal 3 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 5 intrasegmental apodeme 1
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 1 (FBbt:00001021) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: Kenyon cell
description: A Kenyon cell is an intrinsic neuron of the mushroom body. Its cell body, situated in the cortex above the calyx of the mushroom body, is smaller than those in the surrounding midbrain cortex. Four short fascicles extend from the cell bodies of the Kenyon cells into the calyx. Each fascicle corresponds to axons from a set of cell bodies descended from a single mushroom body neuroblast. These 4 smaller fascicles converge in the calyx where they arborize and form pre- and post-synaptic terminals (Christiansen et al., 2011).They emerge from the calyx as a thick axon bundle referred to as the peduncle that bifurcates to innervate the dorsal and medial lobes of the mushroom body.

label: adult MBp lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some mushroom body neuroblast (FBbt:00007113).

label: mushroom body intrinsic neuron
description: An interneuron that innervates only the mushroom body.

label: mushroom body neuroblast
description: A neuroblast that is the precursor of the Kenyon cells. The Kenyon cells of each mushroom body descend from 4 mushroom body neuroblasts. These neuroblasts remain mitotically active throughout larval stages and into the late pupal stage.

label: cell body rind of mushroom body
description: Region of the cell body rind overlying the mushroom body calyx. It is distinct from the surrounding cortex because it contains the cell bodies of Kenyon cells (globuli cell bodies) which are smaller than other neuronal cell bodies (soma) in the midbrain cortex.

label: abdominal 7 lesA neuron
description: Any abdominal lesA neuron (FBbt:00002353) that is part of some abdominal 7 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002846).

label: abdominal 7 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002839) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: mushroom body vertical lobe
description: Bundle of Kenyon cell projections that arises from the anterior end of the pedunculus and projects dorsally. It consists of two components: the alpha lobe and alpha' lobe.

label: abdominal lesB neuron
description: Sensory neuron of abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: lesB neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Lateral mono-innervated campaniform sensilla of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 3 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 1 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 1 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002856).

label: abdominal 1 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 4 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: mushroom body medial lobe
description: A bundle of Kenyon cell projections that arises from the anterior end of the pedunculus and projects medially. It consists of three components: the beta lobe, beta' lobe and gamma lobe.

label: abdominal 2 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 2 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002857).

label: abdominal 2 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 5 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 7 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 7 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002862).

label: abdominal 7 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: larval heart dorsal fibers
description: Fibers attaching the dorsal vessel to the roof of the dorsal sinus.

label: ocellar nerve
description: Nerve containing the axons from the ocellar ganglion projecting to the superior posterior slope.

label: ocellus
description: A simple visual organ on the top of the adult head. There are three of these, arranged in a triangle.

label: abdominal lesC neuron
description: Sensory neuron of abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: lesC neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ of the abdominal, mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Lateral mono-innervated hair of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: larval heart caudal fibers
description: Fine fibers from the posterior of the embryonic/larval heart that, along with the caudal ostial fibers, anchor the posterior of the heart between the posterior spiracles.

label: larval heart caudal ostial fibers
description: Fine fibers from the embryonic/larval ostia 3 that, along with the caudal end fibers, anchor the posterior of the heart between the posterior spiracles.
synonyms: caudal ostial fibers of larval heart

label: abdominal 3 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 3 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002858).

label: abdominal 3 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 6 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 4 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 4 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002859).

label: abdominal 4 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 7 intrasegmental apodeme 2
description: Any embryonic/larval A1-7 intrasegmental apodeme 2 (FBbt:00001028) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: optic glomerulus
description: Small and discrete area of the ventrolateral neuropils. Optic glomeruli are the target of many of the visual projection neurons.

label: glomerulus
description: Roundish subunit structure of synaptic neuropil, often ensheathed by glial lamellae and reflecting the terminal arborization domain(s) of one or more neurons.

label: ventrolateral neuropils
description: Synaptic neuropil block in the adult brain located along the ventrolateral side of the adult central brain.

label: abdominal 5 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 5 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002860).

label: abdominal 5 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: visceral muscle
description: Muscle that moves the viscera and has only one or, commonly no attachment to the body wall. Visceral muscles differ from skeletal muscles in several respects: adjacent fibers are held together by desmosomes, each fiber is uninucleate and the contractile material is not grouped into fibrils but packs the whole fiber. Visceral muscles appear striated. The visceral musculature comprises circular and longitudinal fibers which surround the entire intestinal tract, with the exception of the recurrent layer of the proventriculus, and ducts of the reproductive system. The circular fibers derive from a bilaterally symmetrical band of mesodermal cells extending continuously throughout most of the germ band. The longitudinal fibers derive from clusters of mesodermal cells which appear during stage 12 at the posterior end of the embryo and migrate anteriorly.

label: embryonic/larval muscle system
description: Muscle system of the embryonic/larval stage.

label: abdominal 6 lesB neuron
description: Any abdominal lesB neuron (FBbt:00002361) that is part of some abdominal 6 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002861).

label: abdominal 6 lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002855) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: embryonic/larval heart
description: The embryonic/larval dorsal vessel from the middle of A4 to its posterior tip. It is broader and has a larger lumen then the aorta. The larval heart has three chambers, each with one pair of ostial valves.

label: abdominal 2 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 2 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002849).

label: abdominal 2 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle
description: T-shaped muscle that is attached dorsally to the cardiac tube. It extends processes anteriorly and posteriorly along the pericardial cells, with a single process extending ventrally along the segment border to a dorsolateral attachment site on the epidermis. Contractions of the alary muscles control hemolymph inflow and support the cardiac tube.

label: abdominal 3 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 3 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002850).

label: abdominal 3 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 1
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A1/A2.

label: abdominal 4 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 4 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002851).

label: abdominal 4 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 2
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A2/A3.

label: abdominal 5 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 5 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002852).

label: abdominal 5 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 3
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A3/A4.

label: abdominal 1 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 1 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002848).

label: abdominal 1 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 2 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002833).

label: abdominal lch5 neuron
description: Neuron of abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5. Fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve.

label: abdominal 2 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: larval heart circular muscle
description: Circumscribing muscle on the outside of the embryonic/larval heart.

label: embryonic/larval esophageal muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic or larval esophagus.

label: embryonic/larval esophagus
description: Region of the embryonic/larval foregut posterior to the pharynx and anterior to the proventriculus. It has an approximately uniform diameter and is much narrower than the pharynx.

label: abdominal 6 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 6 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002853).

label: abdominal 6 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 4
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A4/A5.

label: abdominal 7 lesC neuron
description: Any abdominal lesC neuron (FBbt:00002369) that is part of some abdominal 7 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002838).

label: scolopidial neuron
description: Sensory neuron of chordotonal organ. The tip of its dendrite is associated with a rod-like structure called a scolopale rod.

label: abdominal 7 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 5
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A5/A6.

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 6
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A6/A7.

label: abdominal 1 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 1 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002832).

label: abdominal 1 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval alary muscle 7
description: Paired embryonic/larval alary muscle located on the border of embryonic/larval segments A7/A8.

label: abdominal 5 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 5 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002836).

label: abdominal 5 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: embryonic/larval midgut muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic or larval midgut.

label: embryonic/larval midgut cell
description: Cell of the embryonic or larval midgut.

label: embryonic/larval midgut
description: Middle part of the embryonic/larval alimentary canal. The midgut runs from the proventriculus to its posterior end, where it meets the hindgut, immediately anterior to the insertion of the Malpighian tubules. In the larva, there are the 4 gastric caeca at the anterior end.

label: abdominal 6 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 6 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002837).

label: abdominal 6 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: outer sheath cell
description: Cell on the outer surface of the embryonic midgut. It is mesodermal in origin and derives from precursors cells that form a row attached to the dorsal side of the visceral mesoderm at stage 12. There are a group of these.

label: abdominal 7 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 7 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002838).

label: embryonic/larval hindgut muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic or larval hindgut.

label: hindgut muscle
description: Muscle fibers of the hindgut, the posterior part of the alimentary canal. It contains longitudinal and circular muscle fibers.

label: abdominal dorsal/lateral multidendritic neuron
description: Multidendritic neuron of the dorsal or lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval abdominal segments.

label: multidendritic neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the PNS having multiple dendrites.

label: anterior fascicle sensory neuron
description: Any sensory neuron (FBbt:00005124) that fasciculates with some intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00001997).

label: embryonic/larval gonadal sheath muscle
description: Gonadal sheath muscle of the embryo or larva.

label: gonadal sheath proper primordium
description: The primordium of the gonadal sheath. This arises from clusters of cells in parasegments 10, 11 and 12 of the dorsal branch of the fat body/gonad primordium which split off during stage 14 and then cluster around the germ cells.

label: abdominal 3 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 3 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002834).

label: abdominal 3 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 lch5 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch5 neuron (FBbt:00002019) that is part of some abdominal 4 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002835).

label: abdominal 4 lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5
description: Any abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5 (FBbt:00002831) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic/larval proventricular muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic or larval proventriculus.

label: embryonic/larval proventriculus
description: Proventriculus (cardia) of the embryo or larva.

label: visual primordium
description: Primordium of the early extended germ band embryo that will give rise to the larval Bolwig organ, larval optic anlage and adult eye. It is a dorsoposterior strip of the embryonic procephalon that invaginates at stages 12-13. It can be subdivided into 4 different regions. The most anterior gives rise to the embryonic primordium of adult eye. Posterior to it, the anterior lip develops into the embryonic inner optic lobe primordium, that will give rise to the larval inner optic anlage. Posteriorly, the posterior lip develops into the embryonic outer optic lobe primordium, that will give rise to the larval outer optic anlage. The most posterior region will develop into the Bolwig organ primordium.

label: visual anlage
description: Anlage of the visual system in the gastrula embryo that will give rise to the visual primordium.

label: early extended germ band embryo
description: A collective term for stages 9 and 10.

label: abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Multidendritic neuron in the dorsal sensory cluster of larval abdominal segments 1-7. Based on its dendritic pattern, it is a class III dendritic arborizing neuron.

label: dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Neuron whose cell-body is located ventrally in the dorsal group of dendritic arborization neurons (da). It has long primary and secondary branches marked by spiked protrusions (1-20um) along most of its length (Grueber et al., 2002).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: presumptive embryonic/larval central nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval central nervous system.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: ectoderm
description: The outermost germ layer of the embryo.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: procephalic neurogenic region
description: Tissue which becomes morphologically distinct shortly after cephalic furrow formation as two strips of about 80 enlarged cells which extend dorso-ventrally on either side of the developing head.

label: embryonic head
description: Any head (FBbt:00000004) that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: anterior ectoderm
description: The region of the ectoderm anterior to the cephalic furrow.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: embryonic/larval supraesophageal ganglion
description: Region of the embryonic/larval brain located above the esophagus, comprising three fused neuromere (protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum).

label: dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Neuron whose cell body is located ventrally in the dorsal group of dendritic arborization neurons, slightly dorsal to the dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA. It has long and sinuous dendrites with few higher order branches (Grueber et al., 2002).

label: embryonic protocerebral neuromere
description: The most anterior of the supraesophageal neuromeres of the embryo. It is part of the labral segment and is located anterior to the deutocerebral neuromere.

label: embryonic labral segment
description: Any labral segment (FBbt:00000008) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: embryonic brain
description: Brain of the embryo.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB (FBbt:00002394) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic deutocerebral neuromere
description: The middle of the supraesophageal neuromeres of the embryo. It is part of the antennal segment and is located posterior to the protocerebral neuromere.

label: embryonic antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (FBbt:00000009) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB (FBbt:00002394) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: embryonic tritocerebral neuromere
description: The most posterior of the supraesophageal neuromeres of the embryo. It is part of the intercalary segment and is located posterior to the deutocerebral neuromere.

label: embryonic intercalary segment
description: Any intercalary segment (FBbt:00000010) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA (FBbt:00002386) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: ventral neurectoderm
description: The ventrally/medially located ectodermal region of the trunk from which neuroblasts delaminate to form the ventral nerve cord. This region becomes distinct during stage 8 when its cells become enlarged compared to those in the adjacent dorsal ectoderm.

label: epithelium
description: Portion of tissue, that consists of one or more layers of cells with distinct apical-basal polarity, connected to each other by cell junctions.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB (FBbt:00002394) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: embryonic protocerebrum
description: Protocerebrum of the embryo.

label: protocerebrum primordium
description: Primordium of the embryonic protocerebrum.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB (FBbt:00002394) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic deutocerebrum
description: Deutocerebrum of the embryo.

label: abdominal 5 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB (FBbt:00002394) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: embryonic tritocerebrum
description: Tritocerebrum of the embryonic brain.

label: embryonic stomatogastric nervous system
description: The stomatogastric system of the embryo.

label: stomatogastric nervous system
description: A group of small, interconnected ganglia situated posterior to and between the two brain hemispheres and associated with the pharynx, esophagus and aorta.

label: intermediate vesicle of iSNSP
description: One of the three iSNSP pouches at embryonic stage 12, located in a intermediate position. It has around 25 cells. At late stage 14, it has lost its epithelial structure and forms an elongated cluster that merges anteriorly, where the frontal ganglion will develop. The anterior part of the vesicle contributes to the frontal ganglion, whereas the posterior part gives rise to the hypocerebral ganglion.

label: invaginating stomatogastric nervous system precursor
description: Precursor cell of the stomatogastric nervous system that develops from part of the esophagus roof as part of three pouches that invaginate from the esophagus at embryonic 12.

label: caudal vesicle of iSNSP
description: One of the three iSNSP pouches at embryonic stage 12, located in a intermediate position. It has around 25 cells. At stage 15, it has lost its epithelial structure and forms a cluster of cells. Half of these cells remains at the junction between the esophagus and proventriculus and develop into the proventricular ganglion. The other half migrates dorsally and anteriorly along the esophagus and possibly contributes to the frontal and/or hypocerebral ganglion.

label: tip stomatogastric nervous system precursor
description: Precursor cell of the embryonic stomatogastric nervous system that delaminates from the tip of each of the three iSNSPs pouches at mid-embryonic stage 12. After delamination, they move anteriorly and become part of the frontal ganglion.

label: precursor cell of the stomatogastric nervous system
description: Precursor cell of the stomatogastric nervous system of the embryo. These cells can develop by invagination or delamination. There are three distinct populations, iSNSP, dSNSP and tSNSPs, that can be recognized from embryonic stage 10-12.

label: rostral vesicle of tSNSP
description: Precursor cell of the stomatogastric nervous system at mid-embryonic stage 12 that delaminates from the tip of the rostral iSNSP pouch.

label: rostral vesicle of iSNSP
description: One of the three iSNSP pouches at embryonic stage 12, located in a rostral position. It has around 25 cells. At late stage 14, it has lost its epithelial structure and forms an elongated cluster that merges anteriorly, where the frontal ganglion will develop. The anterior part of the vesicle contributes to the frontal ganglion, whereas the posterior part gives rise to the paraesophageal ganglion.

label: intermediate vesicle of tSNSP
description: Precursor cell of the stomatogastric nervous system at mid-embryonic stage 12 that delaminates from the tip of the intermediate iSNSP pouch.

label: caudal vesicle of tSNSP
description: Precursor cell of the stomatogastric nervous system at mid-embryonic stage 12 that delaminates from the tip of the caudal iSNSP pouch.

label: delaminating stomatogastric nervous system precursor
description: Precursor cell of the embryonic stomatogastric nervous system that delaminates from a region that partially overlaps with the iSNSP primordium from embryonic stage 10. At this stage there are 4-6 cells, with the number increasing to 20. There are three clusters, one in front and one on each side of the rostral pouch of the invaginating dSNSPs. The clusters become part of the frontal ganglion.

label: embryonic labial neuromere
description: The most posterior of the embryonic subesophageal neuromeres. It is part of the labial segment, and it is located posterior to the maxillary neuromere.

label: gnathal neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some gnathal segment (FBbt:00000011).

label: embryonic subesophageal neuromere
description: Neuromere of the embryonic subesophageal ganglion, posterior to the supraesophageal ganglion. There are three of these neuromeres: mandibular, maxillary and labial.

label: embryonic labial segment
description: Any labial segment (FBbt:00000014) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: embryonic maxillary neuromere
description: The middle of the embryonic subesophageal neuromeres. It is part of the maxillary segment, and it is located anterior to the labial neuromere and posterior to the mandibular one.

label: embryonic maxillary segment
description: Any maxillary segment (FBbt:00000013) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: embryonic mandibular neuromere
description: The most anterior of the embryonic subesophageal neuromeres. It is part of the mandibular segment, and it is located anterior to the maxillary neuromere, and posterior to intercalary segment and its neuromere, the tritocerebrum.

label: embryonic mandibular segment
description: Any mandibular segment (FBbt:00000012) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: embryonic ventral neuromere
description: Neuromere of the embryonic ventral nerve cord.
