label: embryonic ventral nervous system
description: Ventral nervous system of the embryo.

label: medial delaminating stomatogastric nervous system precursor
description: Medial cluster of the delaminating stomatogastric nervous system precursor, located in front of the rostral pouch of the invaginating dSNSPs.

label: lateral delaminating stomatogastric nervous system precursor
description: One of the two lateral clusters of the delaminating stomatogastric nervous system precursor, located on either side of the rostral pouch of the invaginating dSNSPs.

label: ventral nervous system
description: Nervous system subregion that excludes the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion
description: Region of the embryonic/larval brain consisting of the fused ganglia of the three gnathal segments. The anterior-most part of this ganglion lies between the two brain hemispheres. Its posterior boundary with the thoracic ganglia lies within the ventral nerve cord. During metamorphosis this posterior boundary constricts to form the cervical connective.

label: embryonic thoracic neuromere
description: Any embryonic ventral neuromere (FBbt:00001087) that is part of some embryonic thoracic segment (FBbt:00000167).

label: thoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some thoracic segment (FBbt:00000016).

label: embryonic thoracic segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some embryonic thorax (FBbt:00000166).

label: embryonic prothoracic neuromere
description: Any embryonic thoracic neuromere (FBbt:00001088) that is part of some embryonic prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000168).

label: prothoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000017).

label: sensory perception of humidity
description: The series of events required for an organism to detect some level of humidity in its environment, convert this detection into a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: sensory perception
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: adult ALv2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALv2 (FBbt:00050035).

label: adult ALv2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast ALv2.

label: antennal lobe neuroblast
description: Neuroblast that is the progenitor of interneurons that innervate the antennal lobe.

label: adult SMPpv1 lineage neuron

label: detection of humidity stimulus involved in sensory perception
description: The series of events in which a humidity stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal as part of the sensory perception of humidity.

label: detection of humidity
description: The series of events in which a humidity stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: detection of external stimulus
description: The series of events in which an external stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label: detection of abiotic stimulus
description: The series of events in which an (non-living) abiotic stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHa2.

label: V1 segment of the vertical lobe
description: Ventral-most segment of the vertical lobe of the larval mushroom body, ventral to V2.

label: vertical lobe of larval mushroom body

label: adult SLPpl3 lineage neuron

label: adult SLPpl3 lineage clone

label: V3 segment of the vertical lobe
description: Dorsalmost segment of the vertical lobe of the larval mushroom body, dorsal to V2.

label: V2 segment of the vertical lobe
description: Medial segment of the vertical lobe of the larval mushroom body, ventral to V3 and dorsal to V1.

label: abdominal 5 temporary eclosion muscle DA1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 5 that develops from abdominal 5 dorsal acute muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 5 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000591) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: adult WEDa2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast WEDa2.

label: adult VPNl&d1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNl&d1.

label: adult VPNl&d1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNl&d1 (FBbt:00050012).

label: adult WEDa2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast WEDa2 (FBbt:00050015).

label: adult FLAa3 (male) lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast FLAa3 (male) (FBbt:00050009).

label: adult FLAa3 (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast FLAa3 (male).

label: H-cell
description: Dopaminergic midline interneuron of the ventral nerve cord whose cell body is dorsal to the VUM and MNB cells.

label: MP3 precursor
description: Midline precursor neuron of the ventral nerve cord posterior to MP1 precursor. It divides once to give rise to the interneurons H-cell and the H-cell sib.

label: adult SLPpl2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpl2.

label: posterior midline glial cell
description: Neuropil associated CNS glial cell located along the midline in the ventral nerve cord at embryonic stage 13, in the posterior region of the neuromere. This group of 6 cells degenerates by embryonic stage 16, and does not contribute to the population of mature midline glia.

label: neuropil associated CNS glial cell
description: Glial cell associated with neuropil regions, including regions of synaptic neuropil, axons, tracts, commissures and nerve roots. There are between 90-100 neuropil associated glial cells in a single late larval brain hemisphere (Hartenstein, 2011).

label: adult mesothoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some adult mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00003021).

label: adult thoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some adult thoracic segment (FBbt:00003019).

label: adult metathoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some adult metathoracic segment (FBbt:00003022).

label: adult AOTUv4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv4.

label: adult DM5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast DM5.

label: neuroblast DM5
description: A type II centromedial neuroblast of the posterior deutocerebrum.

label: adult DM5 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DM5 (FBbt:00050059).

label: adult VLPl&p1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl&p1.

label: adult VLPl&p1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl&p1 (FBbt:00050065).

label: adult AOTUv4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv4 (FBbt:00050062).

label: adult SLPpl2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpl2 (FBbt:00050068).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center
description: Neuropil domain located in the deutocerebrum, postero-ventral to the antennal lobe. It contains the terminals of mechanosensory fibers mainly from the first and second antennal segments, most of which come from Johnston's organ neurons. This neuropil is absent from the larval brain, being formed during pupal development.

label: commissure of JON
description: Commissure that connects the AMMC of both hemispheres via which the JO neurons innervate the contralateral AMMC. It runs below the esophagus foramen (Kamikouchi et al., 2006).

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I1
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that is located lateral and internal in the larval mushroom body calyx. It is located internal to larval mushroom body calyx L6 and L1.

label: VUM interneuron
description: Ventral unpaired interneuron that is located ventrally in the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord midline, ventral to the VUM motorneurons. It is a GABAergic neuron. There are three of these cells per segment.

label: ventral neuron of the ventral midline
description: Neuron of the ventral region of the embryonic or larval ventral midline. Three neuron types can be distinguished: UMI, VUM interneuron and VUM motorneuron.

label: VUM neuron
description: The cell body of the VUM neuron is located medially in the ventral and posterior cortex region of the neuromere. Fibers from VUM neurons run tightly fasciculated dorsally towards the neuropil where they separate to form a motorneuronal projection bifurcating in the dorsal part of the anterior commissure, and an interneuronal projection bifurcating in the ventral part of the posterior commissure (Bossing and Technau, 1994). There are six VUM neurons per neuromere.

label: ventral midline
description: The middle underside of the embryo and larva, where the ventral midline neurons and midline glia develop.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L2
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 24a. It is usually located on the lateral edge of the calyx.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center A1 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located dorsally and posterior to the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The primary neurite projects anteriorly towards the great commissure, where it forms several branches which form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, the wedge, the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP), the glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum where LC4 neurons arborize (PVLP) region as well as the nonglomerular region. It crosses the midline forming a very thick commissure which runs along the great commissure (superior AMMC commissure) to form presynaptic terminals in the contralateral gorget and nonglomerular region of the PVLP. It is electrically synapsed to the giant fiber neuron.

label: giant fiber neuron
description: A large, descending neuron that controls jump escape behavior (GO:0007630). Each adult has a bilaterally symmetric pair of these neurons, each with a large cell body at the posterior of the protocerebrum and a long primary neurite (GO:0070852) that branches to forms an extensive dendritic tree in the brain and an axon that projects, via the cervical connective, to the mesothorax. Targets of dendritic arborization include the ipsilateral zones A and B of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) (Kamikouchi et al., 2009), the glomerular region of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) including the glomerulus targeted by LC4 neurons, the gorget and inferior clamp. In the mesothorax, the axon forms electrical synapses with tergotrochanteral muscle motor neuron (TTMn) and peripherally synapsing interneurons (PSI)) of the mesothorax that in turn synapse to the motor neurons of the dorso-longitudinal flight muscles.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus D3
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 49a. It is usually located dorsomedially within the calyx.

label: H-cell sib
description: Glutamatergic midline interneuron of the ventral nerve cord whose cell body is dorsal to the VUM and MNB cells.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus M1
description: Glomerulus that is located medially in the larval mushroom body calyx. It lies ventral to calyx glomerulus D4.

label: adult SIPp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SIPp1 (FBbt:00050077).

label: adult SIPp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SIPp1.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I2
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that is located anterior and internal in the larval mushroom body calyx. It lies internal to the larval mushroom body calyx A1.

label: medial lobe of larval mushroom body
description: The medial lobe of the larval mushroom body (Pauls et al., 2010).

label: lobe system of larval mushroom body
description: The larval mushroom body lobe system consists of a dorsal branch and a medial branch (Pauls et al., 2010).

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus A4
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 1a. It is usually located anteromedially within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L7
description: Glomerulus that is located at the lateral edge of the larval mushroom body calyx. It lies anterior or ventral to calyx glomerulus L3.

label: spur of larval mushroom body
description: Synaptic neuropil domain of the larval mushroom body, that is a small protrusion, lateral to the anterior pedunculus.

label: mushroom body spur
description: Synaptic neuropil domain that is a small protrusion, lateral to the anterior end of the pedunculus.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus D5
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that is usually located dorsomedially, anteromedial to the larval mushroom body calyx D3. It is not always distinct from glomerulus D4 (FBbt:00007212).

label: pedunculus of larval mushroom body
description: Pedunculus of the larval mushroom body.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I7
description: A glomerulus located in the interior of the larval mushroom body calyx, interior to the larval mushroom body calyx M1.

label: adult WEDd2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast WEDd2 (FBbt:00050071).

label: adult WEDd2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast WEDd2.

label: adult VLPl&d1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl&d1.

label: adult VLPl&d1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl&d1 (FBbt:00050074).

label: abdominal 5 temporary eclosion muscle SBM
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 5 that develops from abdominal 5 segment border muscle of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 5 segment border muscle
description: Any A1-7 segment border muscle (FBbt:00000606) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: M1 segment of the larval medial lobe
description: Medial segment of the medial lobe of the larval mushroom body, medial to M2.

label: M2 segment of the larval medial lobe
description: Lateral segment of the medial lobe of the larval mushroom body, lateral to M1.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L5
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 74a. It usually lies in a ventrolateral position within the calyx.

label: pupal central nervous system
description: Central nervous system of the pupa.

label: pupal nervous system
description: Nervous system of the pupa.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V6
description: Glomerulus that is located ventrally in the larval mushroom body calyx, anterolateral to glomerulus V1.

label: pupal brain
description: Brain of the pupa.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus D4
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 45b. It is usually located at the posteromedial edge of the calyx.

label: medial appendix of larval mushroom body
description: Axonal side branch in the medial region of the medial lobe of the larval mushroom body, near the end of the lobe.

label: nervous system
description: All the nerve centers and nerve fibers in the central, visceral and peripheral nervous systems.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V7
description: Glomerulus that is located ventrally in the larval mushroom body calyx, anterior to glomerulus M4.

label: lateral appendix of larval mushroom body
description: Axonal side branch in the lateral region of the medial lobe of the larval mushroom body, before the bifurcation of the pedunculus into the lobes.

label: octopaminergic VUMa4 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMa cluster that arborizes extensively in the ventrolateral and ventromedial protocerebra. One branch enters and arborizes in the middle inferior medial protocerebrum, between the fan-shaped body and the pedunculus (Busch et al., 2009).

label: octopaminergic VUMa neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUM cluster, whose cell body is located more anteriorly than those of OA-VUMd neurons, in either the mandibular or maxillary segments. Its primary neurite projects dorsally through the median tracts. It bifurcates in the area ventral to the esophagus foramen and form spiny dendritic arborizations in the posterior slope. Pairs of secondary processes emerge from these arbors and project to distinct brain regions, forming varicose nerve terminals (Busch et al., 2009, Busch and Tanimoto, 2010).

label: inferior neuropils
description: Block of synaptic neuropil domains in the adult brain located below the superior neuropils, around the level of the mushroom body medial lobe and pedunculus. It includes the antler, clamp, crepine and inferior bridge.

label: adult LHl1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl1.

label: adult LHl1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl1 (FBbt:00050047).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di4 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventral region of the mushroom body calyx. The primary neurite extends anterioventrally to form postsynaptic terminals in the wedge, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP), in the glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons and in the non-glomerular region, and in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B. One branch extends posterioventromedially to form presynaptic terminals in the saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: octopaminergic VUMa2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMa cluster with symmetric secondary neurites projecting from the region ventrolateral to the esophagus foramen to the posterior margin of the antennal lobes, where both neurites bifurcate. One branch ramifies within the antennal lobe and runs further to the anterior subesophageal ganglion. The second branch joins the medial antennal lobe tract and innervates the lateral horn. In addition, there are numerous terminals in calyx of the mushroom body (Busch et al., 2009). There are two neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: medial antennal lobe tract
description: A tract of about 200 axons that emerges from the posterior dorsomedial area of the antennal lobe (dorsomedial root), the same root as the mediolateral antennal lobe tract (mlALT) and transverse antennal lobe tract (tALT). It runs dorsoposteriorly along the posterior surface of the fan-shaped body, turns laterally in front of the protocerebral bridge, passes in front of the mushroom body calyx and terminates in the lateral horn. It contains axons of antennal lobe projection neurons. It demarcates the boundaries of the lateral accessory lobe (medial region), vest (superior region), epaulette (medial region), fan-shaped body (lateral region), gorget (superior region), inferior clamp (lateral and superior-lateral regions), inferior bridge (superior-lateral region), antler (lateral region), superior clamp (posterior-superior region), mushroom body calyx (anterior region) and superior lateral protocerebrum (inferior region).

label: adult SLPpm1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpm1 (FBbt:00050044).

label: adult SLPpm1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpm1.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I6
description: A glomerulus that is located in the interior of the larval mushroom body calyx. It is located medial to the larval mushroom body calyx I4.

label: octopaminergic VUMa3 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMa cluster with symmetric secondary neurites projecting dorsally, bypassing the anterior margin of the ellipsoid body. In the anterior superior medial protocerebrum, these neurites turn laterally and posteriorly. They ramify densely in the superior posterior slope and posterior protocerebrum surrounding the mushroom body pedunculi. One branch also innervates the middle lateral protocerebrum (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di3 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the dorsal region of the superior posterior slope (SPS). The primary neurite extends anterioventrally and forms several branches at the medial side of the inferior posterior slope. The dorsal branch projects anteriodorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the epaulette and SPS. The anteriolateral and medial branches form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones B and E, respectively. The ventral branch extends posteroventrally to exit the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: localization
description: Any process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported, tethered to or otherwise maintained in a specific location. In the case of substances, localization may also be achieved via selective degradation.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di2 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventrolateral region of the gnathal ganglion. The primary neurite extends dorsomedially and arborizes in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones B and E. It then turns ventromedially to exit the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: octopaminergic VUM neuron
description: An unpaired octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster whose cell body is located on the midline of the gnathal ganglion of the adult brain. The primary neurites of OA-VUM neurons join one of the three median tracts along the anterioposterior axis and mainly innervate the periesophageal region. These neurites follow the tracts toward the posterior ventral area of the esophagus foramen where they symmetrically branch out to innervate the cerebral ganglion and subesophageal zone and in some cases the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. Two main subtypes can be identified: OA-VUMa and OA-VUMd (Busch et al., 2009, Certel et al., 2010).

label: octopaminergic VUMa1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMa cluster with symmetric and complex processes throughout the ventromedial protocerebra, including the posterior margin of the antennal lobes and the ventral margins of the mushroom body pedunculi. Another neurite originating from the region ventrolateral to the esophagus foramen innervates the inferior posterior slope, forming varicose terminals (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di1 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventroposterior region of the gnathal ganglion. The primary neurite extends anterodorsolaterally and branches to arborize the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone D and to form postsynaptic terminals in the posterior gnathal ganglion. One of the branches turns ventromedially to exit the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus D2
description: A dorsal glomerulus at the posterior edge of the larval mushroom body calyx.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC P3b neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose large cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The primary neurite extends anteroventrally and branches to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, wedge and the glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons. One of the branches bifurcates in the AMMC to extend posterioventromedially to form presynaptic boutons in the saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: octopaminergic VPM5 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VM cluster, whose cell body is located posterior to that of OA-VMP3, and slightly lateral, in the labial segment of the adult brain. It bifurcates ventrally to the esophagus to innervate both the ipsi- and, sparsely, contralateral antennal lobe. A single neurite from the contralateral branch joins the inner antennocerebral tract to innervate the calyx of the mushroom body and the lateral horn (Busch et al., 2009, Busch and Tanimoto, 2010). There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I4
description: Glomerulus of the larval mushroom body calyx. It is located internal to the larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus L7.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Bb4 neuron
description: Bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the lateral region of the antennal lobe. The primary neurite extends posteriomedially and branches to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B and wedge. The neurite further extends ventromedially to form presynaptic terminals in the saddle and gnathal ganglion. One of the branches projects dorsally and bifurcates at the ventral side of the ipsilateral epaulette. The lateral branch forms presynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons whereas the medial branches crosses the midline to do the same in the contralateral region.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus M4
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 30a. Glomerulus that is located medially in the larval mushroom body calyx. It is usually located medially.

label: adult ALlv1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALlv1 (FBbt:00050038).

label: adult SMPad1 (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad1 (female).

label: adult SMPad1 (female) lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad1 (female) (FBbt:00050041).

label: octopaminergic VUMd2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMd cluster that exhibits a fan-shaped projection in the brain. Secondary neurites that originate in area surrounding the ventral esophagus foramen project to the lateral inferior posterior slope where they turn ventrally and fasciculate with the cervical connective. Projections to the posterior subesophageal ganglion and the inferior posterior slope form varicose terminals (Busch et al., 2009).

label: octopaminergic VUMd neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUM cluster, whose cell body is located more posteriorly than those of OA-VUMa neurons, in the labial segment. Its primary neurite projects dorsally through the median tracts. In the area ventral to the esophagus foramen, the neurite branches and forms a pair of secondary neurites that descend through the cervical connective and innervate the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. Similarly to OA-VUM neurons, VUMd neurons form spiny dendritic arborizations in the posterior slope and project to distinct brain regions, forming varicose nerve terminals (Busch et al., 2009, Busch and Tanimoto, 2010).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db2 neuron
description: Descending bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the inferior clamp (ICL). The primary neurite extends anteriorly and bifurcates in the gorget. The lateral branch projects ventrolaterally to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B, wedge, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP), including the glomerulus targeted by LC4 neurons, posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP), gorget and superior posterior slope (SPS). The medial branch crosses the midline, extends posterioventrally and forms presynaptic terminals in the saddle and bilaterally in the gnathal ganglion. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db1 neuron
description: Descending bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the inferior bridge. The primary neurite extends anterioventrolaterally and bifurcates in the superior posterior slope (SPS). The lateral branch projects ventrolaterally to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones B, C and E, and gnathal ganglion. The medial branch crosses the midline dorsally to the esophagus, turns posterioventrally and forms presynaptic terminals in the gnathal ganglion and inferior posterior slope (IPS). It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: octopaminergic VUMd3 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMd cluster that exhibits a fan-shaped projection in the brain. Secondary neurites that originate in area surrounding the ventral esophagus foramen fasciculate with the cervical connective. Apart from forming spiny arborizations in the posterior slope, this neuron does not innervate other areas in the brain (Busch et al., 2009).

label: embryonic/larval antennal lobe projection neuron
description: An antennal lobe projection neuron that is part of the embryonic/larval brain. These neurons innervate the larval antennal lobe and send an axon to higher brain centers, typically including the larval antennal lobe. The soma of these neurons are located in a single, anterodorsal cluster lateral.

label: antennal lobe projection neuron
description: Interneuron whose dendrite innervates the antennal lobe (larval or adult) and whose axon innervates some higher brain centre (generally the mushroom body calyx and/or lateral horn).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di7 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the ventral region of the antennal lobe. The primary neurite extends posterioventrolaterally towards the wedge to branch and form postsynaptic terminals in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B, wedge, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP), including the glomerulus targeted by LC4 neurons, posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP), antennal lobe and superior posterior slope (SPS). Presynaptic terminals are found in the vest. One of the branches further extends posterioventromedially to form presynaptic terminals in the AMMC zone E, saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V5
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 63a. It usually occupies a ventral position within the calyx.

label: octopaminergic VUMd1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VUMd cluster that exhibits a fan-shaped projection in the brain. Two laterally projecting neurites that originate in the ventral esophagus arborize in the ventrolateral protocerebrum, antennal nerve, the subesophageal ganglion and the antennal motor and mechanosensory center. A pair of descending axons project from the ventral esophagus into the cervical connective (Busch et al., 2009).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di6 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The primary neurite extends anteriorly to broadly form postsynaptic terminals in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, wedge, anterior and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP and PVLP), PLP, superior posterior slope (SPS), clamp, gorget and epaulette. One of the branches further extends ventromedially from the medial side of the PVLP to form presynaptic terminals in the saddle. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: clamp
description: Synaptic neuropil domain lying between the fan-shaped body, the protocerebral bridge and mushroom body pedunculus, including the area above and below the pedunculus (the space occupied by the pedunculus forms a deep tunnel-like recess on its inferior lateral side). Few neurons in the clamp penetrate the pedunculus, but some enter the glomerular posterior lateral protocerebrum and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PLP, PVLP), forming a characteristic cylindrical architecture around the pedunculus. Some fibers spanning the superior surface project into the superior arch commissure.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V8
description: Glomerulus that is located ventrally in the larval mushroom body calyx, anterior to glomerulus V6.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Di5 neuron
description: Descending ipsilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). The primary neurite extends anteriomedially, turns ventrally at the medial side of the PLP and branches, to form postsynaptic terminals in the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, wedge, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP), the glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) which is targeted by LC4 neurons, inferior clamp and gorget. One of the branches further extends posterioventrally to form presynaptic terminals in the saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I3
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 33a. It usually lies in a lateral/internal position within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus I5
description: Glomerulus of the larval mushroom body calyx. It is located ventral to the larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus D1.

label: plasma membrane bounded cell projection
description: A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label: cell projection
description: A prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a flagellum or axon.

label: octopaminergic ASM1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the ASM cluster which arborizes extensively in the ipsilateral side of the posterior protocerebrum and the anterior superior lateral protocerebrum. From the posterior ramifications a single branch emerges and bifurcates in the area dorsolateral to the esophagus foramen. One process projects to the ipsilateral inner medulla and lobula. The other process crosses the midline dorsal to the fan-shaped body and innervates the contralateral inner medulla and lobula (Busch et al., 2009).

label: octopaminergic ASM neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the ASM cluster, whose cell body is located in the anterior superior medial protocerebrum. This neuron sends a process to the posterior protocerebrum where it branches out. Three different subtypes can be distinguished based on their arborization patterns in the posterior protocerebrum: OA-ASM1, OA-ASM2 and OA-ASM3 (Busch et al., 2009).

label: anterior superior medial protocerebrum
description: Region of the superior medial protocerebrum anterior to the fan-shaped body.

label: adult SLPav3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPav3.

label: octopaminergic ASM2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the ASM cluster which arborizes extensively in the ipsilateral side of the posterior protocerebrum. The primary neurite bifurcates dorsolaterally to the fan-shaped body. The main ipsilateral process projects laterally and ramifies extensively in the ipsilateral posterior protocerebrum, around the pedunculus of the mushroom body. The other process bifurcates again above the fan-shaped body, with the resulting branches running laterally to the midline. Then they project to the posterior where they turn toward the ipsilateral and contralateral inferior protocerebrum, respectively. The contralateral branch crosses the midline dorsal of the fan-shaped body. Each of the two branches arborizes in the inferior and ventrolateral protocerebrum (Busch et al., 2009).

label: posterior superior medial protocerebrum
description: Region of the superior medial protocerebrum posterior to the fan-shaped body.

label: posterior superior lateral protocerebrum
description: Posterior subregion of the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db4 neuron
description: Descending bilateral neuron whose large cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the inferior posterior slope (IPS). The primary neurite extends anterioventromedially and bifurcates at the midline of the posterior gnathal ganglion. The ipsilateral branch broadly arborizes in the IPS and posterior gnathal ganglion forming postsynaptic terminals. The contralateral neurite bifurcates in the medial region of the contralateral gnathal ganglion. The anteriolateral branch forms postsynaptic terminals on the lateral region of the posterior gnathal ganglion and antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone D. The posterioventral branch exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion.

label: adult SLPav3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPav3 (FBbt:00050056).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db3c neuron
description: Subtype of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-Db3a neuron whose ipsilateral innervation includes an additional short branch to the gorget.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db3 neuron
description: Descending bilateral neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind on the posterior region of the inferior posterior slope (IPS). The primary neurite extends anteriodorsally and branches in the posterior region of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP). The lateral branch extends to the lobula and forms postsynaptic terminals. The ventral branch forms a dense arbor with postsynaptic terminals that includes the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B, wedge, anterior and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP and PVLP), including the glomerulus targeted by LC4 neurons and the non-glomerular regions, and posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP). A thin neurite projects medially and fasciculates with the great commissure. Contralaterally, it turns ventrally and forms presynaptic terminals in the saddle and bilaterally in the posterior gnathal ganglion. It then exits the brain, projecting into the thoracic-abdominal ganglion. There are three subtypes, which innervate additional neuropils ipsilaterally.

label: octopaminergic VL2 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VL cluster whose descending neurite runs posteriorly along the lateral margin of the subesophageal ganglion (Busch et al., 2009).

label: octopaminergic VL neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VL cluster, whose cell body is located between the antennal lobe and the ventrolateral protocerebrum of the adult brain. This neuron sends a process to the subesophageal zone where it crosses the midline. Bilateral ramifications arborize in the antennal lobes and the gnathal ganglion. On the ipsilateral side, ramifications extend to the inferior lateral and ventrolateral protocerebra. A descending axon diverges from the main neurite medial to the antennal nerve. Two different subtypes can be distinguished, which differ on the projection pattern of this descending neurite: OA-VL1 and OA-VL2. There are two neurons per cluster (Busch et al., 2009).

label: cell body rind of anterior superior medial protocerebrum
description: Region of the cell body rind that overlies the anterior superior medial protocerebrum.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db3b neuron
description: Subtype of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-Db3a neuron whose ipsilateral innervation includes an additional short branch to the epaulette.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC Db3a neuron
description: Subtype of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-Db3a neuron whose ipsilateral innervation is restricted to the lobula, antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B, wedge, anterior and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP and PVLP), including the glomerulus targeted by LC4 neurons and the non-glomerular regions, and posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP).

label: cell body rind of posterior lateral protocerebrum
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the posterior lateral protocerebrum.

label: local interneuron of larval antennal lobe
description: A local interneuron that connects glomeruli within the larval antennal lobe.

label: octopaminergic VL1 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the VL cluster whose descending neurite projects through the subesophageal ganglion, joins the cervical connective and innervates the ipsilateral side of all three thoracic neuromeres (Busch et al., 2009).

label: larval antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (FBbt:00000009) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: adult PSa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast PSa1.

label: adult PSa1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast PSa1 (FBbt:00050050).

label: adult CLp2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast CLp2 (FBbt:00050053).

label: adult CLp2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast CLp2.

label: adult abdominal neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some adult abdominal segment (FBbt:00003024).

label: external sensory organ
description: Sensory organ that has external structures that detect mechanical or chemical stimuli.

label: compound sense organ
description: Any compound cell cluster organ (FBbt:00007230) that capable of some detection of stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050906).

label: adult prothoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some adult prothoracic segment (FBbt:00003020).

label: internal compound sense organ
description: Compound sense organ that is located in the inside of the body, including chordotonal organ.

label: embryonic/larval wrapping glial cell
description: Glial cell of the embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system that extends thin processes and ensheathes axons completely by third larval stage. The layer formed by wrapping glial cells is below the subperineurial glial layer.

label: embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system
description: Peripheral nervous system of the embryo or larva.

label: internal sensillum
description: Sensillum that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.

label: internal sense organ
description: Sense organ that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.

label: asymmetrical body
description: A round synaptic neuropil embedded on the right side of the central complex, ventral to layer 1 of the fan-shaped body and dorsal to the nodulus. This structure displays asymmetrical innervation: it is either exclusive to the right hemisphere, or bilateral, but more prominent on the right hemisphere (Pascual et al., 2004; Jenett et al., 2012).

label: compound cell cluster organ
description: An anatomical structure consisting of multiple cell cluster organs and which does not contain portions of tissue.

label: octopaminergic ASM3 neuron
description: Octopaminergic neuron of the ASM cluster which arborizes extensively around the peduncle of the mushroom body of the adult brain. The main neurite bifurcates dorsolaterally to the fan-shaped body. One process runs laterally, arborizing in the superior protocerebrum; the other process crosses the midline dorsal to the fan-shaped body. These processes give rise to complicated ramifications in the posterior protocerebrum (around the mushroom body pedunculus), ventrolateral protocerebrum and in the subesophageal zone (Busch et al., 2009).

label: adult fruitless pMP-a (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM1.

label: adult fruitless pMP-a (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-a (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110498) and that develops from some neuroblast DM1 (FBbt:00050018) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless pIP-j lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless pIP-j neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-j lineage clone (FBbt:00110496).

label: cell body rind of inferior neuropils
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the inferior neuropils.

label: adult fruitless pIP-i lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum.

label: air sac primordium tip cell
description: Air sac tracheoblast at the tip (leading edge) of the developing air sac primordium. It forms extensive filopodia.

label: air sac tracheoblast
description: Cell that is a precursor of cells of some adult tracheal air sac.

label: adult fruitless pIP-i neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-i lineage clone (FBbt:00110494).

label: air sac primordium stalk cell
description: Air sac tracheoblast that is not at the tip or leading edge of an air sac primordium.

label: dorsal air sac primordium stalk cell
description: Air sac tracheoblast that is not at the tip or leading edge of an air sac primordium.

label: air sac tracheoblast of dorsal air sac primordium
description: Air sac tracheoblast that is part of the dorsal air sac primordium. These cell originate as a clump of cells on the surface of the wing disc that have budded from the from the tracheal branch that adheres to the wing disc.

label: fan-shaped body layer
description: Horizontal, laminar subdivision of the fan-shaped body that results from the stratification of large field neurons. There are 6-8 layers that run parallel to each other.

label: dorsal air sac primordium tip cell
description: Air sac tracheoblast at the tip (leading edge) of the developing air sac primordium. It forms extensive filopodia.

label: nervous system of embryonic/larval abdomen
description: The portion of the embryonic/larval nervous system that is part of the abdomen.

label: embryonic thorax
description: Any thorax (FBbt:00000015) that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: transverse antennal lobe tract
description: Smaller tract that shares a common root (dorsomedial root) with the medial antennal lobe tract (mALT) and mediolateral antennal lobe tract (mlALT) and connects the antennal lobe to the mushroom body calyx, lateral horn or posterior lateral protocerebrum. Fibers can run above, through or below the mushroom body pedunculus, running posterior to the fan-shaped body. The tract contains around 60 fibers.

label: adult antennal lobe tract
description: Antennal lobe tract of the adult. It connects the antennal lobe to various neuropils of the protocerebrum.

label: transverse tract multiglomerular projection neuron AL-t2PN1
description: Unilateral multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron that fasciculates with the transverse antennal lobe tract. The cell body is located lateral to the antennal lobe and arborize in multiple glomeruli in the ventral antennal lobe. The main fiber turns dorsally and joins the common root of the mALT/mlALT/tALT. The axon enters the pedunculus where it turns posteriorly and bifurcates. One branch terminates in the anterior region of the calyx whilst the other turns laterally and terminates in the ventral posterior area of the lateral horn. One branch projects ventrally from the subesophageal zone and terminates in the middle area of the subesophageal zone.
synonyms: inner-middle antenno-cerebral tract multi-glomerular projection neuron

label: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron
description: Any multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron (FBbt:00007384) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624).

label: transverse antennal lobe tract projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that fasciculates with the transverse antennal lobe tract of the adult brain.

label: mushroom body extrinsic neuron
description: Neuron that innervates the mushroom body and other neuropils.

label: adult fruitless pIP-a (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast PSp3. Its cell bodies are located laterally in a cluster close to the tract entrance below the protocerebral bridge. A neurite projects anteriorly before branching. The dorsal branch leads to dense arborizations in the ventral and medial ipsilateral ring. The dorsal projection travels lateroventrally forming dense arborizations in multiple regions including the lateral accessory lobe, posterior antennal mechanosensory motor center and subesophageal zone before exiting the brain. In the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, the projections travel along a lateral tract and arborize mostly in the meso- and metathoracic neuromeres. This clone is rare in females.

label: adult fruitless pIP-a (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-a (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110478) and that develops from some neuroblast PSp3 (FBbt:00050092) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless M lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the medulla.

label: adult fruitless M neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless M lineage clone (FBbt:00110476).

label: adult fruitless Lo lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lobula.

label: adult fruitless Lo neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless Lo lineage clone (FBbt:00110474).

label: adult fruitless aSP-m lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPa&l1.

label: adult fruitless aSP-m neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-m lineage clone (FBbt:00110472) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPa&l1 (FBbt:00050003).

label: adult fruitless pIP-b neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-b lineage clone (FBbt:00110480) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNp1 (FBbt:00050249).

label: adult VPNp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNp1 (FBbt:00050249).

label: adult fruitless pIP-b lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp1. The cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite projects ventrally, arborizing in the dorsal anterior lobula. The neurite then fasciculates with the great commissure to terminate in the contralateral lobula.

label: adult fruitless pIP-c lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp&v1. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites are likely to project to a region in the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label: adult VPNp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp1.

label: adult fruitless pIP-f neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-f lineage clone (FBbt:00110488).

label: adult fruitless pIP-f lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless pIP-e (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-e (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110486) and that develops from some neuroblast DL1 (FBbt:00050184) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless pIP-e (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DL1. The cell bodies are located in the posteriolateral brain. Neurites project anteriorly forming arbors in the entire ring and regions ventral to the ring. One branch projects medially and crosses the midline.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp10
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: translobula plate neuron
description: An intrinsic columnar neuron of the optic lobe whose cell body lies in the cortex of the lobula plate, and that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: adult fruitless pIP-d neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-d lineage clone (FBbt:00110484) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNd2 (FBbt:00110383).

label: adult VPNd2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNd2 (FBbt:00110383).

label: adult fruitless pIP-d lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNd2.

label: superior neuropils
description: A block of synaptic neuropil domains in the adult brain arranged in a layer covering the superior (dorsal) surface of the brain. In encompasses the superior intermediate, superior lateral and superior medial protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless pIP-c neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-c lineage clone (FBbt:00110482) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNp&v1 (FBbt:00050160).

label: adult VPNd2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNd2.

label: lobula plate giant neuron
description: A very large optic lobe tangential neuron with extensive arborization in the lobula plate.

label: lobula plate tangential neuron
description: Tangential neuron of the optic lobe that projects and arborizes along the plane of one or more layers of the lobula plate.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp15
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: lobula plate tangential neuron Lpt1
description: A lobula plate tangential neuron that projects along and arborizes in lobula plate layer 4. This arborization remains very close to the projection and includes both bleb-type and fine terminals.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp12
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp11
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp14
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp13
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: lobula plate tangential neuron Lpt2
description: A lobula plate tangential neuron that projects along lobula plate layer 4 and that has short branches along its length that terminate as blebs in lobula plate layers 3 and 4.

label: adult fruitless pIP-h (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum. The cell bodies are located medial to pIP-a neurons. Neurites enter the neuropil through the same tract opening as pIP-a and branches. One branch travels dorsoanteriorly, towards the medial ring. Another projects to the ventromedial region of the contralateral ring. The third branch crosses the midline above the oesophageal foramen and travels ventrally and exits the brain to terminate in the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: periesophageal neuropils
description: Group of synaptic neuropil domains in the adult brain located between the antennal lobe/ventromedial neuropils and above the gnathal ganglia. In addition, it includes one synaptic domain that is part of the ventral cerebral ganglion-the prow.

label: adult fruitless pIP-h (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-h (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110492) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless pIP-g lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM5.

label: adult fruitless pIP-g neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-g lineage clone (FBbt:00110490) and that develops from some neuroblast DM5 (FBbt:00050059).

label: adult fruitless aSP-e lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior superior protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless aSP-e neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-e lineage clone (FBbt:00110456).

label: cell body rind of superior neuropils
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the superior neuropils (superior protocerebrum) and lateral horn.

label: adult fruitless aSP-d lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa2.

label: adult CREa2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa2.

label: Y neuron
description: Intrinsic columnar neuron of the optic lobe that has a cell body in the cortex of the lobula plate and that arborizes in the lobula plate before bifurcating in the second optic chiasm, with one branch innervating the lobula and the other the proximal medulla.

label: adult fruitless aSP-d neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-d lineage clone (FBbt:00110454) and that develops from some neuroblast CREa2 (FBbt:00050273).

label: adult CREa2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast CREa2 (FBbt:00050273).

label: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi
description: An interneuron that innervates only the lobula plate (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: adult fruitless aSP-c lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad4.

label: adult SMPad4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad4.

label: adult fruitless aSP-c neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-c lineage clone (FBbt:00110452) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad4 (FBbt:00110411).

label: adult SMPad4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad4 (FBbt:00110411).

label: adult fruitless aSP-b (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad2. Its cell bodies are located in the dorsal pars intercerebralis. Neurites project ventroposteriorly and then bifurcate. One branch projects ipsilaterally and terminates in the medial protocerebrum. The other branch projects ventromedially, turns dorsally at the midline and then joins the path of the same cluster on the contralateral side possibly arborizing in the contralateral hemisphere. The dendritic arbors are likely to be located in the lateral junction while the axonal arbors are in the ventral medial protocerebrum.

label: adult SMPad2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad2.

label: adult fruitless aSP-b (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-b (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110450) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad2 (FBbt:00050201) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult SMPad2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad2 (FBbt:00050201).

label: horizontal system neuron
description: Giant neuron whose arbor fans out widely over the dorsal, central or ventral part of lobula plate layer 1. The dendritic arborization in the lobula plate is flattened in the anterior-posterior axis, and the axon extends medially and ventrally to innervate the adult protocerebrum (Scott et al., 2002). It is involved in the optomotor response (Heisenberg et al., 1978) (Schnell et al., 2010) and respond to horizontal motion with graded membrane potential changes in a directional-selective way (Schnell et al., 2010).

label: optomotor response
description: Eye, head or whole body movements that help to compensate movements of the environment in order to stabilize its image on the retina. In the case of whole body movements, these motor actions may also stabilize a locomotor course in response to some disturbance. Examples include: the optokinetic reflex, which allows human eyes to follow objects in motion while the head remains stationary reflex; the optomotor responses of flying insects and swimming fish.

label: Y neuron Y5
description: Y neuron that arborizes relatively broadly in all lobula plate layers and with a mix of terminal morphologies. Its branch in the lobula has a branched, terminal arborization with mixed terminal morphologies in lobula layers 1-3. Its branch in the medulla forms a mixed-morphology, highly branched, terminal arborization in medulla layers M7-10 with one or more very wide branches projecting along M10.

label: equatorial giant horizontal cell HSE
description: Horizontal system neuron whose dendritic arbor extends over the central lobula plate (Scott et al., 2002). It has both synaptic input and output in the axon terminal in the protocerebral region (Raghu et al., 2007). The area covered by its dendrite corresponds to the centre of the large equatorial field of vision. It is electrically coupled to HSN and HSS (Schnell et al., 2010).

label: ventral giant horizontal cell HSS
description: Horizontal system neuron whose dendritic arbor extends over the ventral lobula plate. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: dorsal giant horizontal cell HSN
description: Horizontal system neuron whose dendritic arbor extends over the dorsal lobula plate (Scott et al., 2002). The area covered by its dendrite corresponds to the center of the large dorsal field of vision. It is electrically coupled to HSE and HSS (Schnell et al., 2010).

label: Y neuron Y1
description: Wide-field Y neuron with a wide, unstratified arborization field in all layers of the lobula plate, a wide, thin, terminal arborization domain in lobula layer 5 and a small terminal arborization domain in medulla layer M8 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: adult fruitless aSP-f (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior superior protocerebrum. Neurites project ventrally in the dorsal lateral protocerebrum and form arbors extending down to the lateral crescent.

label: Y neuron Y4
description: Y neuron whose cell body fiber projects through the lobula plate without arborizing. It branches extensively in the second optic chiasm, with one branch doubling back to form a fine terminal arborization in lobula plate layers 1 and 2, multiple branches arborizing throughout the lobula with a mix of terminal morphologies and a single branch projecting into the medulla where it forms a wide asymmetric terminal arbor that projects mainly along medulla layer M9.

label: adult fruitless aSP-f (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-f (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110458) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: Y neuron Y3
description: Wide-field Y neuron with a mix of bleb-type and fine arborizations in the lobula plate. These show some stratification, but cover all layers to some extent. The medulla branch has a relatively wide, terminal arborization field in M8-10 with a mix of bleb-type and fine arborization. The lobula innervating branch has narrow arborizations, also of mixed type in layers 2-5 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989).

label: adult fruitless aSP-g (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal2. The cell bodies are located away from the neuropil, lateroanteriorly from the lateral horn. A neurite enters a neuropil tract anterior to lateral horn and projects medially to arborize in the dorsolateral protocerebrum. It also projects to the contralateral hemisphere.

label: adult SLPal2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal2.

label: adult fruitless aSP-j neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-j lineage clone (FBbt:00110466) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv4 (FBbt:00050062).

label: adult fruitless aSP-j lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv4.

label: adult fruitless aSP-k (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl1. The cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. The neurites first curve ventrally before entering a tract in neuropil region below lateral horn, then projects medially forming arborizations in the region medial to the lateral horn.

label: adult fruitless aSP-i (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-i (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110464) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv3 (FBbt:00050127) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless aSP-i (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv3. Its cell bodies are located ventrally to the anterior optic tubercle. Neurites project medially to arborize in the ipsilateral anterior optic tubercle. Arborization localizes to the dorsal region of the anterior optic tubercle. A neurite also branches to cross the midline in a distinctive V shape to arborize in the contralateral anterior optic tubercle.

label: optic chiasma
description: The projection of axons between the lamina and medulla (first optic chiasma) or between the medulla and lobula (second optic chiasma). The linear order of axons along each horizontal row of retinotopic cartridges or columns is reversed by the chiasma.

label: neuron projection bundle
description: A fasciculated bundle of neuron projections (GO:0043005), largely or completely lacking synapses.

label: tract neuropil
description: The part of the neuropil consisting largely of neuron projections without synapses.

label: adult fruitless aSP-h (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-h (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110462) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl2 (FBbt:00050032) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless aSP-h (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl2.

label: adult fruitless aSP-g (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-g (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110460) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal2 (FBbt:00050267) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult SLPal2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal2 (FBbt:00050267).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VP2
description: Ventro-posterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies just medial to glomerulus VP1.

label: adult antennal lobe glomerulus
description: Any glomerulus (FBbt:00005386) that is part of some adult antennal lobe (FBbt:00007401).

label: neuron of aristal sensillum
description: Sensory neuron of aristal sensillum. Each sensillum contains a pair of sensory dendrites. The outer segment of these dendrites is encased in an electron-dense dendritic sheath and each of the pair has a distinct morphology: one is short and cylindrical proximally, but flattened distally; the other is larger and has a plasma membrane that form 2 interdigitating spiral whorls of lamellae and has periodically arranged electron dense particles protruding from the plasma membrane into the extracellular space (Foelix et al., 1989). The inner-segments of these dendrites are delimited from the outer segments by a ciliary region and are rich in vesicles, mitochondria and ribosomes. The somata sit in a small ganglion near the base of the arista. The axons project via the aristal nerve, which merges with the antennal nerve, and innervate glomeruli VP2 and/or VP3 of the adult antennal lobe. (Stocker et al., 1983).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VP
description: Ventro-posterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VP1
description: Ventro-posterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It is located dorsomedial to glomerulus VP3, dorsoposterior to glomerulus V.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VP3
description: Ventro-posterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies dorsolateral to glomerulus VP1.

label: antennal segment
description: Segment anterior to the intercalary segment. In the adult it bears the antennae.

label: adult fruitless aSP-k (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-k (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110468) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl1 (FBbt:00050047) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: DL fascicle
description: Dorsal-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the lateral fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: fascicle
description: A slender neuron projection bundle that doesn't cross the midline.

label: lateral longitudinal fascicle
description: Lateral-most of the Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicles of the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: adult fruitless aSP-l lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPav2. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite makes a distinct turn, travels on the surface of the neuropil around the lateral horn to the posterior superior lateral protocerebrum to form broad superficial web-like arborizations in the superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum. A neurite also crosses the midline and arborizes in a small region at the medial end of the contralateral superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum.

label: adult SLPav2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPav2.

label: adult fruitless aSP-l neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-l lineage clone (FBbt:00110470) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPav2 (FBbt:00050237).

label: adult SLPav2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPav2 (FBbt:00050237).

label: adult fruitless aIP-c (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl_d1.

label: lobula plate columnar neuron
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that innervates the lobula plate.

label: lobula complex columnar neuron LPLC4
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body rind. It projects to a posterior and ventral optic glomerulus of the PVLP, in the same area as LC22.
synonyms: lobula plate and lobula columnar neuron 4

label: lobula complex columnar neuron
description: Extrinsic columnar neuron of the optic lobe that innervates both the lobula and the lobula plate.

label: optic glomerulus of the PVLP
description: Any optic glomerulus (FBbt:00003698) that is part of some posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (FBbt:00040042).

label: adult fruitless aIP-c (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-c (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110434) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl&d1 (FBbt:00050074) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: abdominal 3 median nerve
description: Any abdominal median nerve (FBbt:00002597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: lobula complex columnar neuron LPLC3
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body rind. Its processes extend the throughout the ventral half of the lobula and lobula plate. It projects to a small, posterior and  ventral optic glomerulus of the PVLP, dorsal to LPC1.
synonyms: lobula plate and lobula columnar neuron 3

label: adult fruitless aIP-b (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPa1.

label: abdominal 4 median nerve
description: Any abdominal median nerve (FBbt:00002597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DA2
description: Dorso-anterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies dorsal to glomerulus VA6 and medial to glomerulus DA4.

label: adult fruitless aIP-b (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-b (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110432) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPa1 (FBbt:00050157) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: lobula complex columnar neuron LPLC2
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body rind. It has its main dendritic arbors in lobula layers 4 and 5B, with minor processes in layer 5A. Presynaptic sites are observed in the layer 4. Its processes extend the full length of the lobula plate. It projects to an optic glomerulus of the PVLP, anterior to LPLC1 and dorsal to LC4. There are around 81 cells of this type.
synonyms: lobula plate and lobula columnar neuron 2

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DA1
description: Dorso-anterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies ventrolateral to glomerulus DL3 and lateral to glomerulus DL4.

label: abdominal 5 median nerve
description: Any abdominal median nerve (FBbt:00002597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: lobula complex columnar neuron LPLC1
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body rind.
