description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002887) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DP1m adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DP1m. This is the first neuron born from the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). The axonal terminals in the lateral horn branch extensively and occupy large regions of this neuropil.

label: persistent antennal lobe projection neuron
description: An adult antennal lobe projection neuron that develops by remodelling of larval antennal lobe projection neuron. Both axons and dendrites of these neurons are extensively remodelled during metamorphosis.

label: adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron adPN
description: An adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron that is derived from the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346). All of these neurons have axons that fasciculate with the medial antennal lobe tract (mALT) and except for V adPN neurons, innervate the mushroom body calyx (via a collateral) and the lateral horn.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DP1m
description: Medial-most compartment of glomerulus DP1. It lies lateral to glomerulus DM1.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus DP1 medial compartment

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or67a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or67a (FBgn0036009). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM6 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM6. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab10.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab10
description: Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from other small bidendritic ab sensilla by its odor response profile (de Bruyne and Baker, 2008) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (49a/85f and 67a).

label: transmedullary neuron Tm3Y
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4 with bleb-like terminal arborizations. It has fine arborizations in medulla layers M1, M4, and M5, and has bleb-type arborization in medulla layers M1, M4, M9 and M10. It differs from the transmedullary neuron Tm3 or TmY3 in that an individual of a retinotopic set may or may not form branches in the lobula plate.

label: abdominal v'es2 neuron
description: Sensory neuron of v'es2. Fasciculates in branch a of the segmental nerve, SNa (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

label: v'es2 neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7 (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There are 3 of these neurons with two closely apposed dendrites. It is located posterioventral to lesA.

label: abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: A ventrally located campaniform sensillum of larval abdominal segments 1-7 whose external sensory structure is surrounded by a ruffled annulus and which is innervated by the 2 dendrites of the v'es2 neurons.

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt3
description: Medullary tangential neuron which extends superficially throughout the anterior-posterior expanse of the distal medulla. It shows both fine and bleb-like arborizations throughout medulla layers M1, M2 and M3 (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989).

label: medullary tangential neuron
description: Tangential neuron of the optic lobe that projects and arborizes along the plane of one or more medulla layers.

label: abdominal 1 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005224).

label: abdominal 1 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: adult odd neuron of the central brain
description: Neuron of the adult brain whose soma is located in the cell body rind of the lateral neuropils. It arborizes in several neuropils, including the superior protocerebrum, clamp, crepine, bulb, antler, lateral accessory lobe, inferior clamp, ventral complex, ventrolateral protocerebrum, wedge and lateral horn. It forms both pre- and postsynaptic terminals, except in the wedge where they are exclusively the of latter type. The morphology of these neurons is varied regarding the neuropils and hemisphere (ipsi- or contralateral) they arborize in. It expresses odd skipped (FBgn0002985).
synonyms: adult Odd neuron of the central brain

label: adult odd neuron of the calyx
description: Neuron of the adult brain whose soma is located in the cell body rind of the lateral neuropils. It arborizes in several neuropils, including the superior protocerebrum, clamp, crepine, bulb, antler and forms postsynaptic terminals in the mushroom body calyx. It expresses odd skipped (FBgn0002985).
synonyms: adult Odd neuron of the calyx

label: abdominal 4 v'esB neuron
description: Any abdominal v'esB neuron (FBbt:00002500) that is part of some abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002891).

label: abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002887) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: proximal medullary amacrine neuron Pm2
description: Proximal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron that projects along M7 and branches extensively at the M7/M8 boundary with each branch projecting into medulla layer M9 where it forms an arbor with mixed bleb-type and fine terminals (Morante and Desplan, 2008; Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 5 v'esB neuron
description: Any abdominal v'esB neuron (FBbt:00002500) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002892).

label: abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002887) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: metathoracic leg taste bristle segmental tarsal chemosensory neuron
description: Gustatory neuron innervating a metathoracic leg taste bristle in the fifth tarsal segment. Its projections are restricted to the metathoracic neuromere of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. There are 9 to 10 neurons.

label: metathoracic leg taste bristle chemosensory neuron
description: Gustatory neuron innervating a metathoracic leg taste bristle. There are between 2 and 4 per bristle (Stocker 1994).

label: metathoracic leg tarsal taste bristle
description: Gustatory bristle found on the tarsal segments of the metathoracic (3rd) leg of the adult. It has a straight tip. In the female, most sensilla are organized in symmetric pairs (with two exceptions), with lateral sensilla having a counterpart on the medial side of the leg. The male sensilla appear similar to the female ones. The organization of taste sensilla is similar in all three legs with a few exceptions.

label: metathoracic tarsal segment 5
description: Fifth tarsal segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 4, and distally it with the pretarsus.

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt2
description: Medullary tangential neuron with a giant projection that extends across the anterior-posterior length of medulla layer 10, with some bleb-type arborizations here. It extensively arborizes with both fine and bleb-type arborizations throughout the whole of medulla layer M8, and occasionally crosses into layer M9. It displays both fine and bleb-type arborizations in medulla layers M3, M5 and M6.

label: abdominal 6 v'esB neuron
description: Any abdominal v'esB neuron (FBbt:00002500) that is part of some abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002893).

label: abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002887) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: metathoracic leg taste bristle ascending tarsal chemosensory neuron
description: Gustatory neuron innervating a metathoracic leg taste bristle in the fifth tarsal segment. It projects to the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, displaying axon collaterals, and ascends via the cervical connective to terminate in the gnathal ganglion. The neuron innervates a pair of short, distal-most ventral taste bristle beneath the unguis. There are 2 to 4 neurons.

label: abdominal 7 v'esB neuron
description: Any abdominal v'esB neuron (FBbt:00002500) that is part of some abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002894).

label: abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc4a (FBbt:00002887) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt1
description: Neuron with a giant projection that extends along the serpentine layer sending out collaterals that arborize in medulla layers M4 to M9. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: small sensillum basiconicum of antennal segment 3
description: Small olfactory basiconic sensillum on antennal segment 3. The surface of the sensillum is perforated by longitudinal rows of pores, connecting to a lymph space innervated by 2 branched olfactory receptor neuron dendrites.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DC1 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DC1. This neuron is born from the 11th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or10a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or10a (FBgn0030298) and the gustatory receptor Gr10a (FBgn0045502). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL1. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab1.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab1
description: A large olfactory basiconic sensillum of the antenna, innervated by 4 ORNs.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or65
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or65 (Or65a ; FBgn0041625, Or65b ; FBgn0041624, Or65c ; FBgn0041623). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL3. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at4.

label: antennal trichoid sensillum at4
description: Olfactory trichoid sensillum of antennal segment 3 that is innervated by 3 ORNs. It is distinguishable from at3 by its odor response profile (de Bruyne and Baker, 2008) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (47b, 65a/b/c, 88a; Couto et al., 2005; de Bruyne and Baker, 2008).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or19
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or19a (FBgn0041626), Or19b (FBgn0062565). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC1. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at3.

label: antennal trichoid sensillum at3
description: Olfactory trichoid sensillum of antennal segment 3 that is innervated by 3 ORNs. It is distinguishable from at4 by its odor response profile (de Bruyne and Baker, 2008) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (2a, 19a/b and 43a; Couto et al., 2005; de Bruyne and Baker, 2008).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM3 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DM3. Neurons of this class are born during the 18th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or13a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or13a (FBgn0030715). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconica sensillum ab6.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab6
description: Thin antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from ab5 - ab10 by its odor response profile (De Bruyne et al., 2001) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (49b; Couto et al., 2005; de Bruyne and Baker, 2008).

label: A1-7 V motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron that develops from the neuroblast 5-2 and innervates the ventral longitudinal muscle 1. It fasciculates with the ISNb or ISNd intersegmental nerve branches, innervating VL1 via type III boutons.

label: V motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron that innervates the ventral longitudinal muscle 1.

label: type III motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that synapsed via type III bouton to some muscle cell (FBbt:00005074).

label: A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: larval dopaminergic pPAM1 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the pPAM cluster, whose cell body is located in the anteriomedial region of the larval brain. The primary neurite extends posteriorly to the base of the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. It then branches: one branch extends dorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the dorsal protocerebrum, in an area medial and lateral to the vertical lobe of the mushroom body; the other branch runs basomedially to form, mostly presynaptic terminals, in the most lateral domain of the medial lobe of the mushroom body, and lateral to the innervation of the other pPAM neurons. A single projection crosses the midline to innervate the same domain in the contralateral medial lobe of the mushroom body.

label: larval dopaminergic pPAM neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in the anteriomedial region of the larval brain. The primary neurite extends posteriorly to an area medial to the base of the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. It then branches: one branch extends dorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the dorsal protocerebrum, medial to the vertical lobe of the mushroom body; the other branch runs basomedially to form, mostly presynaptic terminals, in a specific domain of the medial lobe of the mushroom body. A single projection crosses the midline to innervate the same domain in the contralateral medial lobe of the mushroom body. There are 4 neurons in this cluster, belonging to different subtypes.
synonyms: primary-lineage protocerebral anterior medial cluster neuron

label: abdominal 3 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 3 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005226).

label: abdominal 3 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt7
description: Medullary tangential neuron that enters the medulla through its proximal face at the level of the serpentine layer. It shows extensive fine and bleb-like arborizations in medulla layers M4, M5, M6, the serpentine layer and M8. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: TN innervated muscle of A1-7
description: Muscles that are innervated by the transverse nerve in the larval abdominal segments A1-7.

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt6
description: Medullary tangential neuron that arborizes in the medulla.

label: abdominal 4 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005227).

label: abdominal 4 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: larval odd neuron of the inferior protocerebrum
description: Neuron of the larval brain that arborizes in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (CPM). It expresses odd skipped (FBgn0002985). There are 5 of these neurons, with some extending contralaterally.
synonyms: larval Odd neuron of the inferior protocerebrum

label: motor neuron
description: A neuron that sends movement impulses to the muscle system.

label: ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most of the ventral longitudinal muscles.

label: abdominal 5 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005228).

label: abdominal 5 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt9
description: Medullary tangential neuron whose axon extends along the proximal side of the medulla, and then extends along the top of the medulla neuropil, only sparing the most posterior part of it. It displays bleb-like terminals throughout the top of medulla layer M1, with a few entering the proximal side of layer M2.

label: larval odd neuron of the calyx
description: Neuron of the larval brain that forms postsynaptic terminals in the mushroom body calyx and presynaptic ones in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (CPM). It expresses odd skipped (FBgn0002985). There are 3 of these neurons, with two extending contralaterally.
synonyms: larval Odd neuron of the calyx

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt8
description: Medullary tangential neuron that arborizes in the medulla.

label: abdominal 6 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005229).

label: abdominal 6 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: antennal trichoid sensillum at2
description: Olfactory trichoid sensillum of antennal segment 3 that is innervated by two ORNs.

label: adult odd neuron of the lobula plate
description: Neuron of the adult brain that arborizes in the ventrolateral protocerebrum, wedge and lobula plate, forming pre- and postsynaptic terminals in the latter. The morphology of these neurons is varied regarding the hemisphere (ipsi- or contralateral) they arborize in. It expresses odd skipped (FBgn0002985). There are 3 of these neurons.
synonyms: adult Odd neuron of the lobula plate

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or67d
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses OR67d (FBgn0036080). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA1. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at1.

label: antennal trichoid sensillum at1
description: Mono-innervated olfactory trichoid sensillum of antennal segment 3.

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt5
description: Medullary tangential neuron that extends along the proximal face of the medulla. It shows extensive fine and bleb-like arborizations in medulla layers M8, M9, and M10.

label: abdominal 2 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 2 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005225).

label: abdominal 2 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt4
description: Medullary tangential neuron that principally extends along the border of the serpentine layer and medulla layer M8 for approximately their anterior two-thirds. It shows extensive fine and bleb-like arborizations in medulla layers M8 and M9, but only fine arborizations in the serpentine layer and layer M6. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: abdominal 2 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Multidendritic neuron in the anterior ventral sensory cluster of larval abdominal segments 1-7. Based on its dendritic pattern, it is a class IV dendritic arborizing neuron.

label: lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron developing from the VUM midline precursor. It innervates the lateral transverse muscles.

label: prothoracic Keilin's organ
description: Any Keilin's organ (FBbt:00005198) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: Keilin's organ
description: A sensillum of the embryonic/larval thorax whose external sensory structure consists of a cluster of three hairs. It is innervated by 5 dendrites.

label: embryonic/larval prothoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: CI fascicle
description: Centrointermediate Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the intermediate/central fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section. This fascicle is loosely organized, and contains three distinct tracts: C1, C2 and C3.

label: intermediate longitudinal fascicle
description: Central-most of the Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicles of the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: transverse nerve root
description: The continuation of the neurite bundle and associated glia of the transverse nerve, inside the ventral nerve cord.

label: transverse nerve
description: Nerve of the embryonic or larval ventral nerve cord, that extends form the dorsal midline to the periphery.

label: abdominal 7 v'es2 neuron
description: Any abdominal v'es2 neuron (FBbt:00002508) that is part of some abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00005230).

label: abdominal 7 ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5
description: Any abdominal ventral sensillum campaniformium vc5 (FBbt:00002903) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt11
description: Medullary tangential neuron that enters the medulla via Cuccatti's bundle at the level of the serpentine layer. It shows bleb-like terminals in the serpentine layer and medulla layer M6 and covers almost the whole visual field. It seems capable of both glutamatergic and GABAergic neurotransmission.

label: larval dopaminergic pPAM4 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the pPAM cluster, whose cell body is located in the anteriomedial region of the larval brain. The primary neurite extends posteriorly to the base of the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. It then branches: one branch extends dorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the dorsomedial and basomedial protocerebrum; the other branch runs basomedially to form, mostly presynaptic terminals, in the medial region of the medial lobe of the mushroom body, and between the innervation of pPAM2 and pPAM3 neurons. A single projection crosses the midline to innervate the same domain in the contralateral medial lobe of the mushroom body.

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt10
description: Medullary tangential neuron that has bleb-like terminals in medulla layers M5 and M6. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: ventral multidendritic neuron
description: Any multidendritic neuron (FBbt:00005209) that is part of some embryonic/larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007295).

label: larval dopaminergic pPAM3 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the pPAM cluster, whose cell body is located in the anteriomedial region of the larval brain. The primary neurite extends posteriorly to the base of the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. It then branches: one branch extends dorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the medial dorsal protocerebrum, dorsal to the innervation of the pPAM2 neuron; the other branch runs basomedially to form, mostly presynaptic terminals, in the dorsal tip of the medial lobe of the mushroom body, and dorsal to the innervation of the other pPAM neurons. A single projection crosses the midline to innervate the same domain in the contralateral medial lobe of the mushroom body.

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt13
description: Medullary tangential neuron that extensively innervates the medulla.

label: posterior fascicle sensory neuron
description: Any sensory neuron (FBbt:00005124) that fasciculates with some segmental nerve (FBbt:00002037).

label: larval dopaminergic pPAM2 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the pPAM cluster, whose cell body is located in the anteriomedial region of the larval brain. The primary neurite extends posteriorly to the base of the vertical lobe of the mushroom body. It then branches: one branch extends dorsally to form postsynaptic terminals in the dorsal protocerebrum, medial to the vertical lobe of the mushroom body; the other branch runs basomedially to form, mostly presynaptic terminals, in the basal tip of the medial lobe of the mushroom body, and ventral to the innervation of the other pPAM neurons. A single projection crosses the midline to innervate the same domain in the contralateral medial lobe of the mushroom body. Often, a second contralateral branch crosses the midline, dorsal to the other branch and terminates in the dorsomedial protocerebrum.

label: abdominal 1 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt12
description: Medullary tangential neuron that innervates the proximal medulla.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or22
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or22a (FBgn0026398) and Or22b (FBgn0026397). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab3.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or67b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or67b (FBgn0036019). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA3. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab9.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab9
description: Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from other small bidendritic ab sensilla the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (69a and 67b).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL5 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the embryonic born ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL5. This neuron is born from the 16th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or67c
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or67c (FBgn0036078). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC4. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab7.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab7
description: Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from ab5 - ab10 by its odor response profile (De Bruyne et al., 2001) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (49b and 98a; Couto et al., 2005; de Bruyne and Baker, 2008).

label: adult abdominal segment 6 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00003030).

label: abdominal 5 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: adult abdominal segment 5 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029).

label: abdominal 6 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt14
description: Medullary tangential neuron that extensively innervates the medulla. It does not seem to possess an axon.

label: lobula anlage
description: Anlage of the embryo/larva that is the precursor to the adult lobula.

label: abdominal 3 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa
description: Any abdominal anterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdaa (FBbt:00002517) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: medullary tangential neuron Mt15
description: Medullary tangential neuron that extensively innervates the layers around the serpentine layer of the medulla.

label: prothoracic leg anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: prothoracic leg
description: Leg of the prothoracic segment.

label: eye dorsal compartment
description: Parts of the adult eye which develop from the dorsal compartment of the eye disc.

label: eye
description: A bilaterally paired compound sense organ of the adult head that functions in visual perception.

label: eye ventral compartment
description: Parts of the adult eye which develop from the ventral compartment of the eye disc.

label: adult abdominal segment 11 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00003035).

label: adult abdominal segment 10 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00003034).

label: abdominal 1 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: heterolateral columnar neuron
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that connects the two lobulas and projects via the great commissure.

label: adult abdominal segment 9 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00003033).

label: Olt neuron
description: Bilateral tangential neuron that arborizes across layers 2 and 3 of the lobula and that crosses the second optic chiasm and enters the medulla where it arborizes across layers M8 and M9. It also forms a few terminals in the lobula plate layer 1 and medulla layer M10.

label: abdominal 2 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult abdominal segment 8 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00003032).

label: abdominal 3 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: adult abdominal segment 7 posterior compartment
description: Any adult abdominal segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111595) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00003031).

label: abdominal 4 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: lobula tangential neuron
description: Tangential neuron of the optic lobe that projects and arborizes along the plane of one or more layers of the lobula.

label: abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Multidendritic neuron in the ventral sensory cluster of larval abdominal segments 1-7. Based on its dendritic pattern, it is a class III dendritic arborizing neuron.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt6
description: A lobula tangential neuron with a thick projection that branches extensively immediately after entering the proximal side of the lobula. Each branch extends across the lobula, with some bifurcating, before all form terminal arbors that collectively cover the length of lobula layers 2 to 6. Terminals are of mixed morphology. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: prothoracic leg posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt5
description: A lobula tangential neuron that projects along the distal surface of the lobula (closest to the second optic chiasm), and send branches into lobula layer 2, where they form bleb-type terminals.

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: metathoracic leg anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: metathoracic leg
description: Leg of the metathoracic segment.

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt8
description: Lobula tangential neuron that arborizes in the lobula.

label: mesothoracic leg anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: mesothoracic leg
description: Leg of the mesothoracic segment.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt7
description: A lobula tangential neuron that branches extensively as it enters the lobula in layer 6, with each branch forming a fine, bushy arbor. Together, these arbors cover the whole width of layer 6.

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt2
description: Lobula tangential neuron that arborizes in the lobula.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt1
description: A lobula tangential neuron that sends a thick projection into the proximal lobula that bifurcates with the combined terminal arbors of both branches covering the length of lobula layers 2 and 3 (Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). Its axon innervates the ventrolateral protocerebrum (Otsuna and Ito, 2006).

label: abdominal 5 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt4
description: A lobula tangential neuron that enters the lobula through its proximal side where it arborizes to cover much of layer 5 and 6 with distinctive bleb-type terminals from which short fine terminal branches project. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 6 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap
description: Any abdominal posterior ventral multidendritic neuron vdap (FBbt:00002525) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt3
description: A lobula tangential neuron that extends along the length of lobula layer 2, forming bleb-type terminals from short colaterals within the layer.

label: metathoracic leg taste bristle
description: Spine shaped gustatory bristle, between 12-45 micrometres long, found on the metathoracic (3rd) leg of the adult. There are approximately 31-32 of these bristles per metathoracic leg.

label: metathoracic tarsal segment
description: Any tarsal segment (FBbt:00004646) that is part of some metathoracic leg (FBbt:00004707).

label: mesothoracic leg taste bristle
description: Spine shaped gustatory bristle, between 12-45 micrometres long, found on the mesothoracic (2nd) leg of the adult. There are approximately 30 of these bristles per mesothoracic leg.

label: mesothoracic tarsal segment
description: Tarsal segment of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: prothoracic leg taste bristle
description: Spine shaped gustatory bristle, between 12-45 micrometres long, found on the prothoracic (1st) leg of the adult. There are approximately 37 of these bristles per female prothoracic leg, and 50 per male prothoracic leg (Stocker 1994).

label: prothoracic tarsal segment
description: Tarsal segment of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt10
description: A lobula tangential neuron that branches in lobula layer 6 to form linking fibers that arborize in lobula layers 2 and 3. The combined arbor covers the length of these layers. There is only a single neuron of this class per optic lobe. Its cell body is located in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body region.

label: median neuroblast MNB interneuron
description: Interneuron located at the midline at the anterior segmental border of each ventral nerve cord segment that is the progeny of the neuroblast MNB. There is a cluster of 5-8 cells.

label: neuroblast MNB
description: An unpaired neuroblast delaminating in stage 4 along the ventral midline of the CNS. It gives rise to a cluster of 5-8 interneurons and motorneurons with short bilateral projections in the anterior and posterior commissures and long fibers that enters the intersegmental nerve. In the larva, this neuroblast is reactivated in segments S3 to A1. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast give rise to postembryonic lineage 0.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt9
description: A lobula tangential neuron that arborizes throughout lobula layer 1. The dendrites of this neuron frequently form conspicuous loops extending into the second optic chiasm.

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: lateral locomotor LLN interneuron
description: Interneuron located at the dorsolateral region of the anterior segmental border of each ventral nerve cord segment. It can project ipsi- or contralaterally. The latter cross the midline in either the anterior or posterior commissure and project to the adjacent segment. There are 25 of these neurons per hemisegment.

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: metathoracic leg posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: mesothoracic leg posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or9a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or9a (FBgn0030204). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM3. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab8.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab8
description: Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from other small bidendritic ab sensilla by its odor response profile (de Bruyne and Baker, 2008) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (43b and 9a).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or59b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or59b (FBgn0034865). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM4. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab2.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab2
description: A large olfactory basiconic sensillum of the antenna, innervated by 2 ORNs. It is distinguishable from ab3 by its odor response profile (De Bruyne et al., 2001) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (59b and 85a/33b; Couto et al., 2005).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or2a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or2a (FBgn0023523). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA4 medial compartment and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA4 medial compartment. Its dendrite transduces signals from trichoid sensillum at3.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or59c
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or59c (FBgn0034866). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral `antennal lobe glomerulus VM7v` (FBbt:00007092) and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral `antennal lobe glomerulus VM7v` (FBbt:00007092). Its dendrite transduces signals from `maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb3` (FBbt:00067006).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VM7v
description: Ventral compartment of ventro-medial glomerulus 7.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VM7 ventral compartment

label: maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb3
description: Basiconic olfactory sensillum of maxillary palp that is innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from pb1 and pb2 by its odor response profile (Goldman et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (59c and 85d; Couto et al., 2005; Goldman et al., 2005).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or7a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or7a (FBgn0030016). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL5 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL5. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab4.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab4
description: Thin antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from ab5 - ab10 by its odor response profile (De Bruyne et al., 2001) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it 7a and 56/33a; Couto et al., 2005).

label: antennal basiconic sensillum TB-2
description: Thin ab basiconic sensillum innervated by 2 olfactory receptor neurons (ORNs). In some subtypes the innervating dendrites are highly branched, while in others are innervated by unbranched, hollow dendrites.

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn6
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body is in the dorsal lateral cell body rind. It has its main dendritic arbors in lobula layers 4 and 5B, with additional processes in layers 3, 5A and 6. There is some evidence of presynaptic sites in layers 4 and 5B. The processes of adjacent cells overlap. It fasciculates in the anterior optic tract, fasciculating with Lcn9 (Otsuna and Ito, 2006), and innervates an optic glomerulus in the dorsolateral PVLP, ventral to the one from LC16. There are around 77 cells of this type.

label: anterior optic tract
description: Tract that emerges from the medial part of the lobula. One branch ends in the anterior optic tubercle (AOTU) whilst the other makes a medial turn to terminate in the superior medial posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP) of the adult brain. It demarcates the boundaries of the PVLP (lateral region), anterior VLP (superior and lateral region), AOTU (inferior-lateral region) and lateral horn (inferior region).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or49b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or49b (FBgn0028963). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA5 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA5. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab6.

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn5
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that branches in lobula layer 5 with the branches forming fine terminal arbors in lobula layers 4, 5 and 6. It seems to be capable of both glutamatergic and GABAergic neurotransmission.

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn8
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that branches multiple times in layers 5 and 4 and forms a broad arborization in layer 3 with both bleb-type and fine terminals. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn7
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that enters the lobula at its proximal surface. It has sparse, thin colaterals along its length up to layer 2 where it forms a broad arborization with blebs, and finer arborizations that extend into layer 3.

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron v'dap (FBbt:00002533) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn2
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that arborizes in lobula layers 3-5. The distal part of this arborization is fine and bushy while the proximal part has thick projections with bleb-type terminals. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn1
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that arborizes with fine and bleb-type terminals in lobula layers 5 and 6. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: One of four dendritic arborizing neurons found in each larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster. Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Gr21a/63a
description: Ipsilateral odorant receptor neuron that expresses Gr21a (FBgn0041250) (Couto et al., 2005) and Gr63a (FBgn0035468) (Kwon et al., 2007). It innervates antennal lobe glomerulus V. Unlike many other antennal olfactory receptor neurons, it does not send an axon branch through the antennal commissure to innervate the equivalent contralateral glomerulus. Suh et al., (2004) and Kwon et al., (2007) identify this neuron as being sensitive to CO2 levels. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab1.

label: carbon dioxide sensitive neuron
description: Neuron involved in the detection of carbon dioxide (GO:0003031).

label: lobula columnar neuron Lcn4
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body is in an extended region of the lateral cell body rind. It has its main dendritic arbors in lobula layers 2 and 4, with some processes projecting to layer 1 and multiple branches passing through layer 3. The processes of adjacent cells overlap. It projects to an optic glomerulus in the PVLP that is medial to the one from Lcn12 and ventral to LPLC2 and LPLC1. There are an estimated 66 neurons of this type. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or56a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or56a (FBgn0034473) and Or33a (FBgn0026392). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab4.

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or98a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or98a (FBgn0039551). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM5v and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM5v. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab7.

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002541) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Multidendritic neuron in the ventral sensory cluster of larval abdominal segments 1-7. Based on its dendritic pattern, it is a class IV dendritic arborizing neuron.

label: ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: One of four dendritic arborizing neurons found in each larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster. Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or88a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or88a (FBgn0038203). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA1d and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA1d. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at4.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VA1d
description: Large, dorsal-most compartment of glomerulus VA1. It lies ventral to glomerulus DA1, and dorsal to the lateral compartment of glomerulus VA1.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VA1 dorsal compartment

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or47b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or47b (FBgn0026385). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA1v and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA1v. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at4.

label: lobula complex columnar neuron Lccn2
description: Extrinsic columnar neuron of the optic lobe whose soma lies in the cortex of the lobula plate. It bifurcates close to the soma, with one branch entering the lobula plate and in which it arborizes with both fine and bleb-type terminals at layers 1-4. It terminates in lobula layer 4 with an arbor that also has both fine and bleb-type terminals. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or49a/85f
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or49a (FBgn0033727) and Or85f (FBgn0037685). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL4. Its dendrite transduces signals from basiconic sensillum ab10.

label: lobula complex columnar neuron Lccn1
description: Extrinsic columnar neuron of the optic lobe that enters the lobula plate proximally. It bifurcates in the proximal lobula with both branches innervating both the lobula and the lobula plate. Between them the two branches innervate all layers of the lobula and lobula plate.

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or92a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or92a (FBgn0038798). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab1.

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: One of four dendritic arborizing neurons found in each larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster. Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve.

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: lobula intrinsic neuron Li1
description: Neuron whose cell body lies in the cortex of the lobula. It displays both fine and bleb-like terminals in lobula layers 4, 5 and 6. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: lobula plate anlage
description: Anlage of the embryo/larva that is the precursor to the adult lobula plate.

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002549) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: lobula intrinsic neuron Li2
description: Neuron whose cell body lies in the cortex proximal to the lobula and that projects along the posterior edge of the lobula and then along the plane of lobula layer 1 where it arborizes with both fine and bleb-type terminals.

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp2
description: Translobula plate neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4 with bleb-type terminals. It displays both fine and bleb-type arborizations in lobula plate layer 1, but only fine, bushy arborizations in lobula plate layer 2. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp1
description: Translobula plate neuron that terminates in lobula layer 5 with bleb-type terminals. It displays both fine and bleb-like extensive arborizations in lobula plate layers 1, 2 and 4, but only fine arborizations in lobula plate layer 3. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Class III dendritic arborizing neuron of larval segments A1-7. Its cell body is located in the ventral cluster of sense organs within the vmd5 group.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp8
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp7
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp9
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab5
description: Thin antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from ab5 - ab10 by its odor response profile (De Bruyne et al., 2001) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (82a and 47a; Couto et al., 2005; de Bruyne and Baker, 2008).

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp4
description: Translobula plate neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4 with fine terminals. It displays both fine and bleb-type arborizations in lobula plate layer 2, but only fine arborizations in lobula plate layer 3.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or42a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or42a (FBgn0033041). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM7 dorsal compartment and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM7 dorsal compartment. Its dendrite transduces signals from maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb1 (Couto et al., 2005; Endo et al., 2007).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VM7d
description: Dorsal compartment of ventro-medial glomerulus 7.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VM7 dorsal compartment

label: maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb1
description: Basiconic olfactory sensillum of maxillary palp that is innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from pb2 and pb3 by its odor response profile (Goldman et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (42a and 71a; Couto et al., 2005; Goldman et al., 2005).

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp3
description: Translobula plate neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4 with both fine and bleb-type terminals. It displays both fine and bleb-type arborizations in lobula plate layer 3 and 4. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or71a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or71a (FBgn0036474). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC2. Its dendrite transduces signals from maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb1.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp6
description: Translobula plate neuron that arborizes in the lobula and lobula plate.

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002557) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: One of four dendritic arborizing neurons found in each larval thoracic/abdominal ventral sensory cluster. Its axon fasciculates with the segmental nerve.

label: translobula plate neuron Tlp5
description: Translobula plate neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4 with bleb-type terminals. It displays both fine and bleb-type arborizations in lobula plate layers 1 and 2, but only fine arborizations in lobula plate layer 3.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or33c/85e
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or33c (FBgn0026390) and Or85e (FBgn0026399). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC1. Its dendrite transduces signals from maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb2.

label: maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb2
description: Basiconic olfactory sensillum of maxillary palp that is innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from pb1 and pb3 by its odor response profile (Goldman et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (85e/33c and 46a; Couto et al., 2005; Goldman et al., 2005).

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or69a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or69a (FBgn0041622). It innervates antennal lobe glomerulus D in both antennal lobes: its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus D and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus D. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab9.

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or23a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or23a (FBgn0026395). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA3. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at2.

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002565) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or35a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses the Odorant receptor (Or) 35a (FBgn0028946) and the co-receptor Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 76b (FBgn0036937). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC3 (Couto et al., 2005). Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal coeloconic sensillum ac3 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: antennal coeloconic sensillum ac3
description: Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that is innervated by two olfactory receptor neurons (ORN). It is distinguishable from ac1, ac2 and ac4 by its odor response profile (Yao et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (Benton et al., 2009). The sensilla are present in the posterior antennal surface (Benton et al., 2009).

label: antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1
description: Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that is innervated by three olfactory receptor neurons (ORN). It is distinguishable from ac2, ac3 and ac4 by its odor response profile (Yao et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it. The sensilla are present in the anterior antennal surface just ventral to the arista (Benton et al., 2009).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or43b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or43b (FBgn0026393). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab8.

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Tracheal associated multidendritic neuron of the ventral cluster of segments A1-7. Unlike other sensory neurons of the abdominal segments, it and vtd2 do not project their neurons within the segment where they originate but project more anteriorly up to segment T3 where they cross the midline.

label: ventral procephalic subperineural glia cluster
description: Glioblast of the embryo that gives rise to subperineurial glia. It is located at the boundary between the pro- and deutocerebrum, as a cluster of cells. At early stage 11 there are around 2-3 cells, with this number increasing to . During stage 12, cells of this cluster spread out to cover the anterior and lateral surface of the deutocerebrum and basal protocerebrum.

label: embryonic glioblast
description: Glioblast of the embryo.

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: basal procephalic longitudinal glia cluster
description: Glioblast of the embryo that gives rise to subperineurial glia. It is located close to the boundary between the trito- and deutocerebrum, as a cluster of cells. At stages 11-12 there are around 12 cells. During stage 12, cells of this cluster spread out to cover the anterior and lateral surface of the deutocerebrum and basal protocerebrum.

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: anterior deutocerebral subperineurial glia cluster
description: Glioblast of the embryo that gives rise to subperineurial glia. It is located in the anterior deutocerebrum, as a cluster of cells. At early stage 12 it comprises 2 cells, and by late stage 12 it has increased to 4-5 cells. These cells spread out and by stage 14, together with the PDSG clusters, forms a band of cells that cover the ventral surface of the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or47a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or47a (FBgn0026386) and Or33b (FBgn0026391). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM3. Its dendrite transduces signals from basiconic sensillum ab5.

label: tracheal innervating neuron
description: Multidendritic neuron with several dendritic branches that innervate trachea.

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or46a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or46a (FBgn0026388). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA7l and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA7 lateral compartment. Its dendrite transduces signals from maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb2.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VA7l
description: Lateral-most compartment of glomerulus VA7. It lies along the lateral border of the medial compartment and dorsomedial to glomerulus VA5.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VA7 lateral compartment

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: glioblast
description: Cell that divides to give rise to of glia cells.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or85d
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or85d (FBgn0037594). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA4. Its dendrite transduces signals from maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb3.

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: dorsal procephalic subperineural glia cluster
description: Glioblast of the embryo that gives rise to subperineurial glia. It is located at the dorsoposterior edge of the protocerebrum, as a cluster of cells. At early stage 12 there are 2-3 cells and it increases to 5-6. Until stage 15, cells of this cluster stay together in a wedge-shaped formation, but later spread out to cover the dorso-posterior surface of the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or83c
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or83c (FBgn0037399). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC3. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at2.

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd1 (FBbt:00002573) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or42b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or42b (FBgn0033043). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM1. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab1.

label: abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Tracheal associated multidendritic neuron of the ventral cluster of segments A1-7. Unlike other sensory neurons of the abdominal segments, it and vtd1 do not project their neurons within the segment where they originate but project more anteriorly up to segment T3 where they cross the midline.

label: posterior deutocerebral subperineural glia cluster
description: Glioblast of the embryo that gives rise to subperineurial glia. It is located in the posterior deutocerebrum, as two clusters of cells. These cells spread out and by stage 14, together with the ADSG cluster, forms a band of cells that cover the ventral surface of the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: abdominal 1 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or82a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or82a (FBgn0041621). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA6 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VA6. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab5.

label: abdominal 2 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or85a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or85a (FBgn0037576) and Or33b (FBgn0026391). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM5 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM5. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab2.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Or43a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or43a (FBgn0026389). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA4l and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA4l. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at3.

label: abdominal 7 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: subperineurial glial cell
description: Glial cell that forms the subperineurial glial sheath. These cells are polyploid.

label: glial cell of the perineurium
description: Any glial cell (FBbt:00005144) that is part of some perineurium (FBbt:00007090).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell
description: A large subperineural glial cell of the embryo or larva that lies anterior to the anterior segment border and anterior commissure and medial to the longitudinal connective in each abdominal and thoracic neuromere, (Klambt and Goodman, 1991; Ito et al., 1995). It sends a process to the dorsoventral channel (Ito et al., 1995).

label: abdominal 3 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: channel glial cell
description: Surface associated glial cell that lies along the dorsoventral channels of the ventral nerve cord. The cell bodies lie close to and send processes along the channel surface. The nuclei of these glial cells are smaller and more spherical compared to the flattened nuclei of the subperineurial glia.

label: abdominal 6 ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2
description: Any abdominal ventral multidendritic neuron vtd2 (FBbt:00002581) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 2 ventral bipolar neuron vbp
description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell (supraesophageal)
description: Any A-subperineurial glial cell (FBbt:00001259) that is part of some embryonic/larval supraesophageal ganglion (FBbt:00110637) and that is part of some subperineurial glial sheath (FBbt:00007091).

label: abdominal 3 ventral bipolar neuron vbp
description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of optic lobe
description: A-subperineurial glial cell of optic lobe of the larva.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of optic lobe
