description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell (subesophageal)
description: Any A-subperineurial glial cell (FBbt:00001259) that is part of some embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion (FBbt:00100138) and that is part of some subperineurial glial sheath (FBbt:00007091).

label: abdominal 5 ventral bipolar neuron vbp
description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of thorax
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in a thoracic segment.

description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 median nerve
description: Any abdominal median nerve (FBbt:00002597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 1
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 1.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 1

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of abdomen
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in the abdominal hemineuromeres. It lies at 20-30% along the medio-lateral axis.

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 2
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 2.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 2

label: abdominal 6 ventral bipolar neuron vbp
description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of thoracic segment 1
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in thoracic segment 1.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of thoracic segment 1

description: Any abdominal ventral bipolar neuron vbp (FBbt:00002589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in thoracic segment 2.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of thoracic segment 2

description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in thoracic segment 3.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of thoracic segment 3

label: abdominal 1 median nerve
description: Any abdominal median nerve (FBbt:00002597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 7 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 7

label: abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: An adult muscle precursor cell found in embryonic abdominal segments A1-7 that is located in a dorso-lateral cluster of abdominal adult muscle precursors. This cluster begins life as a pair of cells associated with the intersegmental nerve and connected to other abdominal adult muscle precursor cells in the same segment by filopodia (Figeac et al., 2010). The cluster remains associated with this nerve through most of development, but migrates to the epidermal histoblast nests where muscle formation is initiated during metamorphosis (Bate, 1993).

label: abdominal 3 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 3

label: abdominal 2 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 2

label: abdominal 1 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 1

label: abdominal adult muscle precursor cell
description: An adult muscle precursor cell found in the embryonic abdomen. In each of embryonic segments A1-7, these form 4 clusters (dorsal, dorso-lateral, lateral and ventral) (Bate, et al., 1991) that are associated with peripheral nerves (Bate, 1993) and, during late embryogenesis, are connected to each other by a network of fine filopodia (Figeac et al., 2010). During metamorphosis, they migrate along the nerves to the sites of muscle formation at the epidermal histoblast nests (Bate, 1993).

label: abdominal 6 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 6

label: abdominal 5 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 5

label: abdominal 4 dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorso-lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00013243) that is part of some abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025).
synonyms: dorsolateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 4

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 4
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 4.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 4

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 5
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 5.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 5

description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 6.

description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 7.

description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 3.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 3

label: B-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 3
description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 3.

label: B-subperineurial glial cell of abdomen
description: Large subperineural glial cell that sits over the posterior commissure just medial to the longitudinal connectives (Klambt and Goodman, 1991; Ito et al., 1995). It sends processes in three directions: medially to the midline, anteriorly and posteriorly (Ito et al., 1995). Unlike the A-subperineural glial cell, the B-subperineural glial cell is only found in abdominal segments of the embryo and larvae, and lies at approximately the centre of the segment along the antero-posterior axis (Ito et al., 1995).

label: A-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 8
description: A-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 8.
synonyms: A subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 8

description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 1.

description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 2.

description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 6.

label: B-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 7
description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 7.

label: B-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 8
description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 8.

label: medial dorsal subperineurial glial cell
description: Surface-associated, subperineurial glial cell located on the ventral surface of the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord. It lies between the intersegmental nerve roots, at 30-60% along the medio-lateral axis, slightly antero-lateral to the medial intersegmental nerve root glial cell.

label: B-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 4
description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 4.

label: B-subperineurial glial cell of abdominal segment 5
description: B-subperineurial glial cell located in abdominal segment 5.

label: lateral dorsal subperineurial glial cell
description: Surface-associated, subperineurial glial cell located on the ventral surface of the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord. It lies near, but slightly above, the exit point of the peripheral nerve, at 80-90% along the medio-lateral axis.

label: dorsal lateral subperineurial glial cell
description: Surface-associated, subperineurial glial cell located on the lateral surface of the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord, and is located dorsal to the ventral lateral subperineurial glial cell. It lies at about 30% along the ventro-dorsal axis, and occasionally there are two of these cells per neuromere.

label: ventral lateral subperineurial glial cell
description: Surface-associated, subperineurial glial cell located on the lateral surface of the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord, and is located ventral to the dorsal lateral subperineurial glial cell. It lies at about 30% along the ventro-dorsal axis, and occasionally there are two of these cells per neuromere.

label: lateral ventral subperineurial glial cell
description: Surface-associated, subperineurial glial cell located on the ventral surface of the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord, and lies antero-lateral to the medial ventral subperineurial glial cell. In the abdominal segments, it lies 0-10% along the antero-posterior axis and 60-90% along the medio-lateral axis.

label: medial channel glial cell
description: Surface-associated, channel glial cell that lies just beneath the ventral side of the cortex/neuropil interface. There are 3-4 medial channel glial cells and they send their processes to and along the dorsoventral channel.

label: medial channel glial cell 1
description: Anterior-most of the two medial channel glial cells.

label: medial channel glial cell 2
description: Posterior-most of the two medial channel glial cells.

label: ventral channel glial cell
description: Surface-associated, channel glial cell that lies at the ventral-end of the channel above the neuropil. There are two of these cells per hemisegment and their processes form, along with processes from the dorsal channel glia, a sheath structure that covers the inner surface of the dorsoventral channel.

label: medial ventral subperineurial glial cell
description: Surface-associated, subperineurial glial cell located on the ventral surface of the embryonic/larval ventral nerve cord, and lies more medially than the lateral ventral subperineurial glial cell. In the abdominal segments, it lies 50% along the antero-posterior axis and 30-50% along the medio-lateral axis, but it lies slightly more medially in the thoracic segments.

label: dorsal channel glial cell
description: Surface-associated, channel glial cell that lies at the dorsal-end of the channel above the neuropil. The cells send processes ventrally along the channel, while receiving processes from the A-SPG cells. There are two dorsal channel glial cells per hemisegment and their processes form, along with processes from the ventral channel glia, a sheath structure that covers the inner surface of the dorsoventral channel.

label: adult AOTUv1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv1 (FBbt:00050222).

label: adult AOTUv1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv1.

label: cortex associated CNS glial cell
description: Glial cell lying amongst the neuronal cell bodies of the lateral and ventral cortex (Ito et al., 1995).

label: adult SLPpl1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpl1.

label: medial-most cell body glial cell
description: Cell body glial cell that lies close to the midline in the center of the embryonic/larval segment. It lies between 10-20% along the mediolateral axis, and at approximately 50% along the anterioposterior axis, and flanks the ventral unpaired median (VUM) neuron cluster on the midline. The thoracic hemineuromere has two medial-most cell body glial cells, whilst the abdominal hemineuromere has only one.

label: adult SLPal1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal1.

description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal1 (FBbt:00050219).

description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPd1 (FBbt:00050231).

description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpl1 (FBbt:00050228).

label: adult CLp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast CLp1 (FBbt:00050204).

label: adult CLp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast CLp1.

label: adult VLPd&p1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPd&p1.

label: adult VLPd&p1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPd&p1 (FBbt:00050207).

label: adult PSp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast PSp1.

label: adult VLPp2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPp2.

label: adult VLPp2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPp2 (FBbt:00050210).

label: adult SLPpm2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpm2.

label: adult SLPpm2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpm2 (FBbt:00050216).

label: adult PSp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast PSp1 (FBbt:00050213).

label: detection of stimulus
description: The series of events in which a stimulus is received by a cell or organism and converted into a molecular signal.

label: histamine transport
description: The directed movement of histamine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Histamine is a physiologically active amine, found in plant and animal tissue and released from mast cells as part of an allergic reaction in humans.

label: ammonium transport
description: The directed movement of ammonium into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Ammonium is the cation NH4+ which is formed from N2 by root-nodule bacteria in leguminous plants and is an excretory product in ammonotelic animals.

label: azole transport
description: The directed movement of azoles, heterocyclic compounds found in many biologically important substances, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: adult SLPav1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPav1 (FBbt:00050264).

label: adult SLPav1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPav1.

label: adult VLPl4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl4 (FBbt:00050258).

label: adult VLPl4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl4.

label: adult LHl4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl4.

label: adult LHl4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl4 (FBbt:00050261).

label: leg taste bristle
description: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some leg (FBbt:00004640) and that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of taste (GO:0050912).

label: leg sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some leg (FBbt:00004640).

label: taste bristle
description: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of taste (GO:0050912).

label: tergotrochanteral muscle motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the mesothoracic extracoxal depressor muscle 66 (tergotrochanteral muscle) and is electrically synapsed to the giant fiber neuron. It functions in jump response escape behavior. It projects through the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve to the mesothoracic neuromere.

label: posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve
description: A nerve that arises from the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, just posterior to the root of the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It projects posteriolaterally before branching, with one branch innervating the tergal depressor of the trochanter (muscle 66), while the other branch forms further, terminal branches that innervate targets including the dorsal medial muscle (dorsal longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00003362)).

label: cell body rind of mesothoracic neuromere
description: Region of the adult thoracico-abdominal ganglion cell body rind that overlies the mesothoracic neuromere.

label: mesothoracic extracoxal depressor muscle 66
description: Extracoxal depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic trochanter. This large muscle attaches dorsally onto the lateral scutum, adjacent to the wing base. It extends ventrally to converge to a single tendon that attaches onto a medial projection of the trochanter within the coxa. This muscle is the principal executor of the jump response. It is innervated by the tergotrochanteral muscle motor neuron.

label: adult SIPa1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SIPa1.

label: adult SIPa1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SIPa1 (FBbt:00050276).

label: adult oligo-glomerular local interneuron of the lateral AL neuroblast
description: Local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe that is derived from the lateral AL neuroblast lineage and that innervates only some of the adult antennal lobe glomeruli.

label: CSD interneuron
description: A large serotonergic interneuron of the adult brain whose cell body is located close to the antennal lobe, whose dendrites innervate the antennal lobe in the same hemisphere as the cell body and whose axons innervate the contralateral antennal lobe and higher brain centers including the mushroom body cortex, the dorsal horn and the posterior superior protocerebrum. There are only two CSD interneurons per brain (one cell body per hemisphere).

label: adult serotonergic IP neuron
description: Adult serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located in the cortex of the inferior-medial protocerebrum.

label: serotonergic IP1-1 neuron
description: Serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located anteriorly to the dorsal basolateral protocerebrum. A primary neurite projects to and innervates the antennal lobe. Another process projects dorsally to innervate the lateral and medial region of the posterior brain, including the region around the mushroom body. A single neurite crosses the midline and arborizes in the contralateral antennal lobe.

label: GABAergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe
description: A GABAergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe. The majority of the local interneurons of the adult antennal lobe fall into this class.

label: cholinergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe
description: Cholinergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe. The minority of local interneurons of the adult antennal lobe fall into this class.

label: adult MBp1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp1.

label: adult MBp lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from the neuroblasts MBp1-4.

label: adult MBp1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast MBp1 (FBbt:00050270).

label: large labellar taste bristle
description: Largest taste bristle subtype of the outside labellum: each bristle is around 35 micrometres long. These bristles are located in the region between the intermediate bristles on the lobe periphery and the medial-ventrally located short taste bristles. These taste bristles contain 4 gustatory receptor neurons (Shanbhag et al., 2001) sensitive to: sugars, low concentrations of salt, bitter or high salt concentrations and water or low osmolarity (Meunier et al., 2003; Fujishiro et al., 1984) and one mechanosensory neuron (Shanbhag et al., 2001).

label: labellar taste bristle
description: Gustatory bristle on the outer surface of the labellum. Three different types are present: short, intermediate and large bristles. They are innervated by 2 or 4 chemosensory neurons and one mechanosensory neuron.

label: labellar cap
description: Chitinous dorsal half of the labellum which is covered in bristles.

label: intermediate labellar taste bristle
description: Intermediate sized taste bristle of the outside of the labellum: each bristle is around 25 micrometers long. These bristles are located dorsally, on the labellar lobe periphery. These taste bristles house the sensory dendrites of 2 gustatory receptor neurons (Shanbhag et al., 2001): one sensitive to sugars and low concentrations of salt and the other to bitter and high salt concentrations (Hiroi et al., 2004). These taste bristles also contains the sensory dendrite of one mechanosensory neuron (Shanbhag et al., 2001).

label: tracheal lumen
description: Lumen of the trachea.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum TB
description: Olfactory basiconic sensillum of antennal segment 3 with about the same length as the large ab sensilla, but thinner and with longitudinal rows of pores like those found in the small ab sensilla.

label: sensillum basiconicum of antennal segment 3
description: Any sensillum basiconicum (FBbt:00005185) that is part of some third segment of antenna (FBbt:00004515).

label: adult CREa1 (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa1 (male).

label: adult SMPad1 (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad1 (male).

label: adult SMPad1 (male) lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad1 (male) (FBbt:00050243).

label: outer optic anlage neuroblast
description: A neuroblast that is located in the larval outer optic anlage and that will give rise the to neurons of the adult lamina and outer medulla. It develops from a neuroepithelial cell in the medial region of the outer optic anlage. Neuroblasts in the medial edge give rise to the outer medulla neurons, whereas neuroblasts at the lateral edge give rise to lamina neurons.

label: optic lobe forming neuroblast
description: A neuroblast in the larva that is the precursor of the adult optic lobe neurons. It develops from neuroepithelial cells in the medial region of the inner and outer larval optic anlage.

label: larval outer optic anlage
description: The lateral, outer layer of the larval optic lobe. It consists of neuroepithelial cells (and later of proliferating neuroblasts) that will give rise the to neurons of the adult lamina and outer medulla. By the late first instar, it is dome shaped and perforated at its centre by a pore, through which axons of the optic stalk pass (Meinertzhagen and Hanson, 1993). It becomes distinguished from the inner optic anlage during the second half of the first instar period (Meinertzhagen and Hanson, 1993). In the third instar, neuroepithelial cells in the medial region give rise to neuroblasts that divide asymmetrically to generate the adult optic lobe neurons.

label: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron lPN
description: Adult antennal lobe projection neuron that is derived from the lateral AL neuroblast lineage and that innervates multiple antennal lobe glomeruli. The dendritic arbors of these neurons do not outline individual glomeruli and their axons project through the medial antennal lobe tract to various higher brain centers such as the posterior-lateral protocerebrum and the superior protocerebrum.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron lPN
description: Any antennal lobe projection neuron (FBbt:00007422) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALl1 (FBbt:00067347).

label: antennal lobe projection neuron iPN
description: Adult antennal lobe projection neuron that fasciculates with the medial antennal lobe tract. There are about 100 of these per tract. Most (all?) of these neurons arborize extensively in the mushroom body calyx, whilst the accessory calyx is free from termini. These neurons are cholinergic (Yasuyama et al., 2003).

label: GABAergic adult local interneuron type A of the lateral AL neuroblast
description: GABAergic local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe that is derived from the lateral AL neuroblast and that arborizes throughout the antennal lobe without outlining individual glomeruli.

label: adult CREa1 (male) lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast CREa1 (male) (FBbt:00050246).

label: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron vPN
description: Adult antennal lobe projection neuron that is derived from the ventral AL neuroblast lineage and that innervates multiple antennal lobe glomeruli. The dendritic arbors of these neurons do not form glomerular shapes (Lai et al., 2008). All of these neurons have an axon that innervates the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron vPN
description: Any antennal lobe projection neuron (FBbt:00007422) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast ALv1 (FBbt:00067348).

label: adult WEDd1 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast WEDd1 (FBbt:00050240).

label: adult WEDd1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast WEDd1.

label: lamina furrow
description: A region of the lamina anlage marked by a fold. Like the morphogenetic furrow in the developing eye, this fold progresses from posterior to anterior, reflecting posterior to anterior progression of differentiation.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum TB-4
description: Thin ab basiconic sensillum innervated by the branched dendrites of 4 olfactory receptor neurons (ORNs).

label: adult LHl3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl3 (FBbt:00050255).

label: adult LHl3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl3.

label: DN1a neuron
description: Anteriorly located member of the Period-expressing DN1 cluster of the adult brain. There are two DN1a neurons per cluster located between 15 and 30 micrometers anterior to the DN1p cluster.

label: adult DM4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast DM4.

label: neuroblast DM4
description: A type II centromedial neuroblast of the posterior deutocerebrum. This neuroblast produces a mixed glial/neuronal progeny, although it gives rise to only a few glial cells (Viktorin et al., 2011).

label: adult DM4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast DM4 (FBbt:00050252).

label: cellular localization
description: A cellular localization process whereby a substance or cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within a cell including the localization of substances or cellular entities to the cell membrane.
synonyms: establishment and maintenance of cellular localization

label: Pdf negative s-LNv neuron
description: s-LNv neuron of the adult brain that does not express Pdf (FBgn0023178). There is one of these in each ventral cluster of LN period neurons. It is located more dorsally than the s-LNv Pdf neurons (Helfrich-Forster, 2007; Rieger et al., 2006). It extends a single neurite through the medulla that invades the lamina, forming thin arborizations in the lamina cortex near the retina that terminate at the border of the fenestrated glia (Damulewicz and Pyza, 2011). In the central brain, it extends arborizations that predominantly terminate in the neuropil region close to the pars intercerebralis.

label: dorsal fusion commissure
description: Commissure of the adult dorsal protocerebrum that carries the projections of a number of pacemaker neurons: DN1, DN2 and LNd.

label: DN3a neuron
description: DN (dorsal Period-expressing neuron of adult brain) with a medium-sized cell body, located in the lateral-most cluster of per expressing DN neurons. There are two cells per hemisphere, each of which project anteriorly to the aMe (Helfrich-Forster et al., 2007).

label: LP neuron
description: Period-expressing neuron located in a cluster of 3-4 cells in the lateral central brain, medial to the LNd cluster and near the posterior of the brain (Shafer et al., 2006; Helfrich-Forster, 2005).

label: DN1p neuron
description: Posteriorly located member of the Period-expressing DN1 cluster of the adult brain that expresses glass (FBgn0004618). There are 14-17 DN1p cells per cluster. Many, perhaps all cells in this cluster project through the dorsal fusion commissure (Helfrich-Forster et al., 2007).

label: establishment of localization in cell
description: Any process, occuring in a cell, that localizes a substance or cellular component. This may occur via movement, tethering or selective degradation.

label: establishment of localization
description: Any process that localizes a substance or cellular component. This may occur via movement, tethering or selective degradation.

label: cell
description: The basic structural and functional unit of all organisms. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: antennal lobe projection neuron lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron that derives from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron adPN
description: An adult antennal lobe projection neuron that is derived from neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346). All of these neurons have axons that fasciculate with the medial antennal lobe tract (mALT) and innervate the lateral horn.

label: endocrine system
description: Non-connected system of anatomical structures which have some endocrine function.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VL1 vPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ventral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VL1. Its axon exhibits a diffuse and highly complex pattern of arborization along the ventral border of the lateral horn.

label: adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron vPN
description: Adult, uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron descended from the ventral antennal lobe (AL) neuroblast. All neurons in this class fasciculate with the mediolateral antennal lobe tract (mlALT) (Lai et al., 2008; Jefferis et al., 2007) and innervates the lateral horn (Jefferis et al., 2007).

label: adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron
description: Any uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron (FBbt:00007383) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DL6
description: A small, densely innervated glomerulus located just anterior to DL1.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL6 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL6. This neuron is born from the ninth division of neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA7l adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA7l. This neuron is born from the 13th division of neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VC2 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VC2. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA4 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA4. The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the dorsoposterior edge of the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA6 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA6. This neuron is born during the eighth division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis. The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the ventroposterior edge of the lateral horn.

label: rhabdomere of eye photoreceptor cell
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some eye photoreceptor cell (FBbt:00006009).

label: rhabdomere
description: The rod-like component of a photoreceptor cell of an ommatidium.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM7v adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM7v (also known as glomerulus 1). Neurons of this class derive from the ninth larval division of the ALad1 neuroblast (FBbt:00067346).
synonyms: adult antennal lobe projection neuron 1 adPN

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM7 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM7. Neurons of this class are derived from the 10th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VL2p lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VL2p. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM1 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM1. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VL2p adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage (embryonic born) whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VL2p. This neuron is born in the third division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult VPNp3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast VPNp3 (FBbt:00110395).

label: adult VPNp3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp3.

label: embryonic/larval corpus allatum innervating neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911) and that has synaptic terminals in some embryonic/larval corpus allatum (FBbt:00001725).

label: embryonic/larval corpus allatum
description: A component of the embryonic/larval ring gland composed of a cluster of about 10 cells that sit medially on top of the aorta.

label: negative gravitaxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism away from the source of gravity.

label: gravitaxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to gravity.

label: prothoracic gland innervating neuron PG-LP
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron that secretes prothoracicotropic hormone (FBgn0013323; McBrayer et al., 2007) and innervates the prothoracic gland. The somata of these neurons (2 per hemisphere) lie in the cortex of the lateral protocerebrum. Their axons, which form extensive collaterals in the brain, run along the anterior brain at the cortex/neuropil interface before traversing the midline and entering the contralateral nervus corporis cardiaci I (NccI) through which they travel to the ring gland. Within the ring gland these axons bypass the corpora cardiaca to innervate the prothoracic gland where they arborize extensively.
synonyms: Prothoracic gland innervating neurosecretory neuron of the lateral protocerebrum

label: prothoracic gland innervating neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has synaptic terminals in some prothoracic gland (FBbt:00001724).

label: larval anteriolateral neurosecretory cell
description: Neurosecretory cell of the larval pars lateralis that innervates the corpus cardiacum, corpus allatum and prothoracic gland (Siegmund and Korge, 2001; Velasco et al., 2007).

label: prothoracic gland
description: A component of the embryonic/larval ring gland composed of a cluster of 10-20 cells on either side of the aorta. Ventrally, it is continuous with the corpus cardiaca, dorsally with the corpus allatum. It degenerates after metamorphosis.

label: adult LHa3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast LHa3.

label: adult LHa3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast LHa3 (FBbt:00050279).

label: serotonergic corpus cardiacum innervating neuron CC/A
description: Serotonergic neuron that fasciculates with the nervus corporis cardiaci I (NccI) and arborizes in the corpus cardiacum and along the aorta.

label: embryonic/larval aorta
description: The embryonic/larval dorsal vessel from its anterior tip to the middle of segment 4, where it broadens to become the heart.

label: corpus cardiacum innervating neuron CC/A-PI 1
description: Octopaminergic larval neurosecretory neuron whose soma is located in the pars-intercerebralis and whose axon innervates the corpus cardiacum and the aorta. There are six of these per animal.

label: corpus cardiacum innervating neuron CC/A-PI
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron whose soma is located in the pars-intercerebralis and whose axon innervates the corpus cardiacum and the aorta. They each project caudally along the midline. At a distance of about 50 micrometres from the soma, the projection splits: one branch follows the midline down to the subesophageal ganglion, and the second branch crosses the midline, enters the contralateral nervus corporis cardiaci I (NccI), and arborizes in the corpus cardiacum, extending further along the aorta.
synonyms: corpus cardiacum innervating neurosecretory neuron of the pars intercerebralis

label: corpus cardiacum innervating neuron CC/A-PI 2
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron that is not octopaminergic and whose soma is located in the pars-intercerebralis and whose axon innervates the corpus cardiacum and the aorta. There are two of these per animal.

label: corpus cardiacum innervating neuron CC-LP
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron whose soma is located in the cortex of the lateral protocerebrum and whose axon innervates the corpus cardiacum. The soma of these neurons are located in 2 clusters of seven (one per hemisphere), between CA-LP1 an CA-LP2.
synonyms: corpus cardiacum innervating neurosecretory neuron of the lateral protocerebrum

label: corpus allatum innervating neuron CA-LP 2
description: Bilaterally paired, larval neurosecretory neuron whose soma is located in the cortex of the lateral protocerebrum and whose axon innervates the corpora allatum. Their axons follow an anterior path towards the mushroom bodies and the soma of CA-LP 1, where they split. One branch follows the same path as the axon of corpus allatum neuron CA-LP 1 to the corpus allatum via the nervus corporis cardiaci I (NccI). The other branch runs towards the midline. There are only two of these cells per hemisphere.
synonyms: Corpus allatum innervating neurosecretory neuron of the lateral protocerebrum 2

label: larval dorsomedial neurosecretory cell
description: Neurosecretory cell of the larval pars intercerebralis. Its axonal projection bifurcates, with one of the main branches projecting to the contralateral side and exiting the brain and bifurcating again. One of these secondary branches fasciculates with the nerve tracts that innervate the corpus cardiacum in the ring gland and also innervates the hypocerebral ganglion. The other follows the aorta and innervates the heart (Cao and Brown, 2001, Rulifson et al., 2002, Ikeya et al., 2002). The other main projection innervates the subesophageal ganglion, the esophagus (Rulifson et al., Ikeya et al., 2002) and the tritocerebrum (de Velasco et al., 2007). In third instar larva, the axonal processes project contralaterally and posteriorly, make a U-turn and extend anteriorly to terminals outside the brain. The dendritic processes extend ventrally and laterally (Cao et al., 2014). These cells are present in the mNSC bilateral cell body cluster of seven cells in each hemisphere (Cao and Brown, 2001, Rulifson et al., 2002, Ikeya et al., 2002, Cao et al., 2014).

label: corpus allatum innervating neuron CA-LP 1
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron whose soma is located in the cortex of the antero-dorsal region of the lateral protocerebrum and whose axon innervates the corpora allatum. This axon runs caudally on a slightly curved path from to the nervus corporis cardiaci I (NccI). It emerges from the NccI at the ring gland and passes the copora cardiaca and the lateral limb of the prothoracic gland before innervating the corpora allatum. There is only one bilaterally symmetric pair of these cells per animal.
synonyms: Corpus allatum innervating neurosecretory neuron of the lateral protocerebrum 1

label: larval Hugin neuron of the corpus cardiacum
description: Larval neuron that expresses Hugin (FBgn0028374) whose soma is located in the cortex of the medial subesophageal ganglion, directly below the esophagus and whose axon innervates the contralateral corpus cardiacum. It also shows an ipsilateral neurite that can vary in length. There are 4 of these per animal.

label: corpus cardiacum innervating neuron CC-MS 2
description: Larval neurosecretory neuron whose soma is located in the posteriorly in the cortex of the medial subesophageal ganglion and whose axon innervates the corpus cardiacum (CC). Its axon runs on an outwardly curved path toward the dorsal mid-line, crosses it, and joins the axons of the CC-MS 1 on their way to the CC. There is one of these per animal.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 8
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00000180).

label: abdominal tracheal primordium
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment (FBbt:00000172).

label: imaginal tracheoblast
description: Precursor cell of the adult tracheal branches, found in the embryo or larva. Imaginal tracheoblasts originate from the spiracular branches in tracheal metamere 2 to 9, near the junctions with the transverse connectives and from several scattered positions in tracheal metameres 1 and 2.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DP1l adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ALad1 neuroblast (FBbt:00067346) lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DP1l.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DP1l
description: Lateral-most compartment of the DP1 glomerulus. It lies dorsomedial to the dorsal compartment of glomerulus DL2.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus DP1 lateral compartment

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VC1 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VC1.

label: dorsal anastomosis 1
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 2 (FBbt:00000267).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right dorsal branches of an embryonic/larval tracheal metamere. Forms during stage 16.

label: tracheal branch of Tr1
description: Any embryonic/larval trachea (FBbt:00000211) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026).

label: tracheal metamere 1
description: Metameric subdivision of the tracheal system that originates in the mesothoracic segment (T2). As well as tracheating the mesothoracic segment, the major trachea of this metamere extends into all segments anterior to T2.

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 2
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027).

label: secondary trachea
description: Trachea formed by a single tracheolar cell folded back on itself and making an auto-cellular junction to form a tube. Secondary trachea first begin to form in the embryo during stage 13.

label: trachea
description: Cuticle-lined epithelial tube that forms part of the tracheal system. The thinnest trachea consist of a single tracheocyte folded back on itself to form a tube.

label: tracheolar cell
description: Specialized cell of the tracheal system that forms the secondary and terminal branches (tracheoles) of the tracheal tree. Each forms a secondary branch of a primary trachea. This secondary branch itself branches into multiple tracheoles within fine cytoplasmic projections that invade (tracheate) target tissues. Tracheolar cells are the main site of respiratory gaseous exchange within the tracheal system.

label: primary trachea
description: Trachea that is two or more cells (tracheocytes) in circumference. During embryogenesis, primary trachea are formed from the tracheal primordium between stages 11 and 15.

label: adult fruitless vAB1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the abdominal segment. It projects to the ipsilateral metathoracic neuromere.

label: adult fruitless dMT1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMT1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111104).

label: adult fruitless dMT1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region of the metathoracic segment. It projects outs of the abdominal segment.

label: adult fruitless dMS6 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMS6 lineage clone (FBbt:00111102).

label: adult fruitless dMS6 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region between the mesothoracic and metathoracic segments, close to an entry tract. Neurites project ventrally.

label: adult fruitless dMS5 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMS5 lineage clone (FBbt:00111100).

label: adult fruitless dMS5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region between the mesothoracic and metathoracic segments, very close to those of the dMS4 lineage clone. Arborization is confined in the mesothoracic neuromere. This clone is not found in males.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V9
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 42a. It usually occupies a ventral position within the calyx.

label: adult fruitless vAB2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vAB2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111108).

label: cell body rind of abdominal neuromere
description: Region of the adult thoracico-abdominal ganglion cell body rind that overlies the abdominal neuromere.

label: adult fruitless vAB2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the midline of the abdominal segment. It projects along the thoracico-abdominal ganglion to the brain.

label: adult fruitless vAB1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vAB1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111106).

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus M6
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 59a. It usually occupies a ventromedial and slightly posterior position within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus V1
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 35a. It usually occupies an anteroventral position within the calyx.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 85c
description: Glomerulus 85c is located in the middle layer of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies lateral to glomerulus 42a and posteromedial to glomerulus 24a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or85c (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L3
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 94b. This glomerulus usually has a dorsolateral location within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L4
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 22c. This glomerulus usually lies in a posterior, ventral position within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L6
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 30a. It is usually located on the lateral edge of the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L8
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 1a. It is usually located laterally within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L9
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 42b. It is usually located ventrolaterally within the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L10
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 85c. It is usually located ventrolaterally in the calyx.

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus L11
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 45a. It usually has a ventrolateral location in the calyx.

label: adult fruitless vMS4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS4 lineage clone (FBbt:00111116).

label: adult fruitless vMS4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventroanterior region of the mesothoracic segment, adjacent to the vMS2 lineage clone. A neurite projects medially and branches. The ipsilateral branch projects anteriorly to the prothoracic neuromere to arborize in the anterior region. The other branch crosses the midline and forms a contralateral arbor in the prothoracic neuromere before projecting to the metathoracic neuromere.

label: adult fruitless vMS3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111114).

label: adult fruitless vMS3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anteriolateral region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites project medially and slightly posteriorly, bifurcating into an ipsilateral and a contralateral branches that run along close to the midline. Both branches terminate in the prothoracic neuromere possibly connecting to the foreleg afferents. The contralateral branch then exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: adult fruitless vMS2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111112).

label: adult fruitless vMS2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventroanterior region of the mesothoracic segment. Its neurite projects dorsally forming thick arbors in the dorsal mesothoracic neuromere. One branch exits the VNC via the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve to innervate direct and indirect flight muscles (basalar muscles and coxal tergal remotor muscles, respectively).

label: coxal tergal remotor muscle
description: An indirect flight muscle that functions as a wing elevator. It extends from the mid notum ventrally to the metathoracic preepisternum, dorsoanterior to the coxa. It is posterior to the tergosternal and anterior to the lateral oblique dorsal muscles. It is innervated by the adult fruitless vMS2 neuron.

label: basalar muscle
description: Muscle of the epipleural muscle group that are involved in extending the wing and pulling the anterior wing margin down, thereby pronating the wing (Sink, 2006). It is innervated by the adult fruitless vMS2 neuron.

label: adult fruitless vMS1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111110).

label: adult fruitless vMS1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventrolateral region of the mesothoracic segment. It arborizes extensively in the ipsilateral mesothoracic neuromere before exiting the thoracico-abdominal ganglion to the mesothoracic legs.

label: adult fruitless vMS5 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS5 lineage clone (FBbt:00111118).

label: adult fruitless vMS5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventromedial region of the anterior mesothoracic segment. The ipsilateral branch projects anteriorly and terminates in the prothoracic neuromere. The other branch crosses the midline and projects posteriorly. The arborization is similar to that of the vMS4 lineage clone.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 83a
description: Glomerulus 83a is located at the dorsomedial edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies medial to glomerulus 59a, and dorsal to glomerulus 42a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or83a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 94b
description: Glomerulus 94b is located along the lateral edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies immediately ventral to glomerulus 45b, and lateral to glomerulus 33b/47a. It is innervated by axons from larval olfactory receptor neuron Or94b (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: adult fruitless vMS6 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located on the midline in the ventroanterior region of the mesothoracic segment. Its neurite projects dorsally.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 49a
description: Glomerulus 49a is located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL), ventromedially to glomeruli 63a and 33a, and dorsal to glomerulus 82a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or49a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 59a
description: Glomerulus 59a is centrally located along the dorsal edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies medial to glomerulus 33a, and lateral to glomerulus 83a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or59a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 82a
description: Glomerulus 82a is located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL), dorsomedially to glomerulus 30a, lateral to glomerulus 45a, and dorsolateral to glomerulus 67b. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or82a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 35a
description: Glomerulus 35a is located along the ventromedial edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies posterior to glomerulus 42b, and anterior to glomerulus 74a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or35a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: mesothoracic leg disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the mesothoracic leg disc.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 42a
description: Glomerulus 42a is centrally located at the medial edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies immediately medial to glomerulus 24a, and dorsomedial to glomerulus 42b. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or42a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: prothoracic leg disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the prothoracic leg disc.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 42b
description: Glomerulus 42b is located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL), ventromedially to glomerulus 24a, medial to glomerulus 22c, and ventrolateral to glomerulus 42a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or42b (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: prothoracic leg disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the prothoracic leg disc.

label: larval uniglomerular projection neuron 45a-A3
description: Larval projection neuron whose dendrites innervate larval antennal lobe glomerulus 45a. It projects to larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus A3.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 45a
description: Glomerulus 45a is centrally located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies medial to glomerulus 82a, and lateral to glomerulus 13a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or45a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval uniglomerular projection neuron 45a-A3+L11
description: Larval projection neuron whose dendrites innervate larval antennal lobe glomerulus 45a. It projects to larval mushroom body calyx glomeruli A3 and L11.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 45b
description: Glomerulus 45b is located along the lateral edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies immediately dorsal to glomerulus 94b, and lateral to glomerulus 33b/47a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or45b (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: dorsal thoracic disc anterior compartment
description: Any imaginal disc anterior compartment (FBbt:00007109) that is part of some dorsal thoracic disc (FBbt:00001776).

label: dorsal thoracic disc posterior compartment
description: Any imaginal disc posterior compartment (FBbt:00007111) that is part of some dorsal thoracic disc (FBbt:00001776).

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus A5
description: A larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus that receives synaptic input from a larval uniglomerular projection neuron 59a. It is usually located anteroventrally within the calyx.

label: metathoracic leg disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the metathoracic leg disc.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 33a
description: Glomerulus 33a is located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL), dorsolaterally to glomerulus 59a, dorsal to glomerulus 49a, and anteromedial to glomerulus 63a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or33a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: metathoracic leg disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the metathoracic leg disc.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 33b/47a
description: Glomerulus 33b/47a is a large glomerulus located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL), medially to glomeruli 45b and 94b. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or33b/Or47a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: mesothoracic leg disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the mesothoracic leg disc.

label: larval uniglomerular projection neuron 30a-M4
description: Larval projection neuron whose dendrites innervate larval antennal lobe glomerulus 30a. It projects to larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus M4.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 30a
description: Glomerulus 30a is located at the ventrolateral edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies ventrolateral to glomerulus 82a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or30a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval MB calyx glomerulus M5
description: Glomerulus that is located medially in the larval mushroom body calyx, posteriomedial to glomerulus L1.

label: labial disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the labial disc.

label: labial disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the labial disc.

label: larval uniglomerular projection neuron 1a-A4
description: Larval projection neuron whose dendrites innervate larval antennal lobe glomerulus 1a. It projects to larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus A4.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 1a
description: Glomerulus 1a is located at the dorsomedial edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies dorsomedial to glomerulus 13a, and dorsomedial to glomerulus 74a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or1a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval uniglomerular projection neuron 1a-A4+L8
description: Larval projection neuron whose dendrites innervate larval antennal lobe glomerulus 1a. It projects to larval mushroom body calyx glomeruli A4 and L8.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 13a
description: Glomerulus 13a is located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL), medially to glomerulus 45a, and ventrolateral to glomerulus 1a. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or13a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: antennal disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the antennal disc. The compartment boundary that defines this compartment forms during the third instar larval stage.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 22c
description: Glomerulus 22c is located at the ventrolateral edge of the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies ventrolateral to glomerulus 24a, and lateral to glomerulus 42b. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or22c (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: antennal disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the antennal disc. The compartment boundary that defines this compartment forms during the third instar larval stage.

label: larval antennal lobe glomerulus 24a
description: Glomerulus 24a is centrally located in the larval antennal lobe (LAL). It lies immediately lateral to glomerulus 42a, dorsomedial to glomerulus 22c, and dorsolateral to glomerulus 42b. It is innervated by an axon from the larval olfactory receptor neuron Or24a (Masuda-Nakagawa et al., 2009).

label: larval uniglomerular projection neuron 30a-L6
description: Larval projection neuron whose dendrites innervate larval antennal lobe glomerulus 30a. It projects to larval mushroom body calyx glomerulus L6.

label: clypeo-labral disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the clypeo-labral disc.

label: clypeo-labral disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the clypeo-labral disc.

label: presynaptic process involved in chemical synaptic transmission
description: The pathway leading to secretion of a neurotransmitter from the presynapse as part of synaptic transmission.

label: presynapse
description: The part of a synapse that is part of the presynaptic cell.

label: chemical synaptic transmission
description: The vesicular release of classical neurotransmitter molecules from a neuron, across a chemical synapse, the subsequent activation of neurotransmitter receptors of a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) and the effects of this activation on the postsynaptic membrane potential and ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol. This process encompasses both spontaneous and evoked release of neurotransmitter and all parts of synaptic vesicle exocytosis. Evoked transmission starts with the arrival of an action potential at the presynapse.

label: trans-synaptic signaling
description: Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft.

label: CL fascicle
description: Central-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the lateral fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: VL fascicle
description: Ventral-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the lateral fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: ventral brain cluster neuron
description: A neuron that is part of a cluster of atonal expressing neurons whose cell bodies are located ventrally in the central adult brain. It projects along the brain lobula border.

label: DM fascicle
description: Dorsal-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the medial fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: medial longitudinal fascicle
description: Medial-most of the Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicles of the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: membrane part
description: Any constituent part of a membrane, a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

label: cellular_component
description: The part of a cell, extracellular environment or virus in which a gene product is located. A gene product may be located in one or more parts of a cell and its location may be as specific as a particular macromolecular complex, that is, a stable, persistent association of macromolecules that function together.

label: C3 fascicle
description: Ventral-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the intermediate/central fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: C1 fascicle
description: Second dorsal-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the intermediate/central fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: C2 fascicle
description: Third dorsal-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the intermediate/central fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: DI fascicle
description: Dorsal-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the intermediate/central fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: short arista lateral
description: Short lateral of the arista. There are 5-7 of these, about 20-30 micrometers long that extend from the dorsal side of the central core shaft.

label: arista lateral
description: A bristle-like, non-innervated outgrowth of the arista central core. Each lateral is formed from the outgrowth of a single polyploid central core cell. They extend both anteriorly and posteriorly, with 8-11 long laterals and 5-7 smaller laterals present.

label: VM fascicle
description: Ventral-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the medial fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: male abdominal tergite 8
description: Small tergite of abdominal segment 8 in adult males.

label: abdominal tergite 8
description: Tergite of adult abdominal segment 8. It is sexually dimorphic.

label: cell part
description: Any constituent part of a cell, the basic structural and functional unit of all organisms.

label: sensory neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some detection of stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050906).

label: thermosensory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of temperature stimulus (GO:0050951).

label: mechanosensory neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050974).

label: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception
description: The series of events in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal as part of sensory perception.

label: head mesoderm derived embryonic hemocyte
description: Hemocyte that is derived from the head mesoderm of the embryo. These hemocytes populate the embryo and continue to replicate throughout larval stages with some persisting in pupa and adults.

label: embryonic hemocyte
description: Hemocyte of the embryo.

label: prohemocyte
description: An immature hemocyte. These cells are highly basophilic, round to polygonal cells measuring 4 to 6 micrometers in diameter. The nucleus is rich in nucleoli and the cytoplasm is abundant in ribosomes, mitochondria, Golgi bodies and lysosomes. These cells exhibit few cytoplasmic inclusions and a poorly developed rough endoplasmic reticulum.

label: lymph gland derived hemocyte
description: Hemocyte that is produced in the lymph glands. These hemocytes are released into circulation at the end of third larval instar and at the onset of metamorphosis, and contribute to the pupal and adult hemocyte population.

label: embryonic/larval hemocyte
description: Circulatory cell of the embryonic/larval hemolymph that is involved in the cellular immune response.

label: embryonic/larval lymph gland
description: Hematopoietic organ of the larva, located along the dorsal vessel, behind the brain. It produces the plasmatocytes, crystal cells and lamellocytes which are released at the end of the larval instar and onset of metamorphosis. It is composed of 3 pairs of bilateral lobes: an anterior primary lobe, a posterior secondary lobe and the most posterior lobe (or multiple lobes), the tertiary lobe. Each lobe is separated by pericardial cells. In the late embryo, the lymph gland consists of a single pair of lobes (primary lobes) containing around 20 cells each that flank the dorsal vessel. By the second larval instar, the lymph gland is composed of two or three new pairs of posterior lobes, and the primary lobes have increased in size to contain around 200 cells. During the first and early second larval instars, the lymph gland comprises only the hematopoietic progenitor population. The lymph gland increases in size ten-fold by the late third instar, and at this stage the progenitor cells (prohemocytes) become restricted to the medial region (medullary zone) of the primary lobe and become quiescent. The differentiated hemocytes are found in the periphery (cortical zone) of the primary lobe and these cells proliferate extensively. The posterior signalling center is a group of about 30 cells at the posterior tip of the primary lobe that secretes several signalling molecules and functions as a stem-cell niche. The secondary and tertiary lobes contain prohemocytes, and rarely a differentiated cell. Lymph glands are eliminated at metamorphosis.

label: arista central core
description: Central core of the arista from which long and small laterals extend. It is around 300 micrometers long and 10-20 micrometers in diameter.

label: long arista lateral
description: Long lateral of the arista. It is around 140 micrometers long. There are 3-4 of these on the anterior side, and 5-7 on the posterior side of the arista.

label: synapse part
description: Any constituent part of a synapse, the junction between a nerve fiber of one neuron and another neuron or muscle fiber or glial cell.

label: hygrosensitive neuron
description: Any sensory neuron (FBbt:00005124) that capable of some detection of humidity stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0098512).

label: hygrosensory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of humidity (GO:0098509).

label: Ppd1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the posterior dorsal protocerebrum.

label: dorsal posterior protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the dorsal region of the posterior protocerebrum.

label: ventral posterior protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the ventral region of the posterior protocerebrum.

label: chemosensory neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050907).

label: chemosensory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of chemical stimulus (GO:0007606).

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception
description: The series of events in which a chemical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal as part of sensory perception.
synonyms: sensory perception, sensory transduction of chemical stimulus

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 2
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027).

label: Ppv3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the posterior ventral protocerebrum.

label: gustatory receptor neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of taste (GO:0050912).

label: gustatory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of taste (GO:0050909).

label: Ppv2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the posterior ventral protocerebrum.

label: Ppv1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the posterior ventral protocerebrum.

label: olfactory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception of smell (GO:0007608).

label: Ppd8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: intrascutal suture
description: Suture that forms the boundary between the prescutum and the scutum.

label: mesothoracic suture
description: Any suture (FBbt:00004479) that is part of some mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000018).

label: mesothoracic tergum
description: The dorsal sclerites (tergites) of the mesothorax.

label: scutoscutellar suture
description: A suture that divides the scutum from the scutellum.

label: Ppd9 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 9 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: Ppd6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: notopleural suture
description: Suture of the adult lateral mesothorax that extends posteriorly from the humerus, until meeting the vertical cleft, separating the scutum from the anepisternum.

label: Ppd7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: pleural suture
description: Suture that extends from the base of the pleural wing process (FBbt:00004595) and which divides the mesothoracic episternum (FBbt:00004596) from the epimeron (FBbt:00004556).

label: ventral mesothorax
description: Ventral region of the adult external mesothorax.

label: Ppd4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the posterior dorsal protocerebrum.

label: Ppd5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: suture
description: The meeting line of two primary body plates, as a rule forming a furrow-like impression.

label: adult anterior thoracic spiracle
description: The anterior-most spiracle of the adult thorax. It is located in the ventral mesothorax and opens out into the propleural air sac.

label: propleural air sac
description: A ventrally located air sac of the prothorax. It arises from the lateral trunk and extends ventrally just posterior to the first leg. The anterior thoracic spiracle opens into this air sac.

label: Ppd12 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 12 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: vertical cleft
description: Suture of the adult lateral mesothorax that extends dorsoventrally on the posterior border of the anepisternum, separating the anepisternum from the anepimeron.

label: mesothoracic cleft
description: Suture of the adult lateral mesothorax.

label: Ppd13 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 13 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: mesothoracic phragma
description: Infolding of the cuticle in the adult lateral mesothorax that forms from the external pleural cleft. It acts as a support for the wing and the leg articulation.

label: phragma
description: Infolding of the integument forming an internal membrane or plate.

label: Ppd10 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 10 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: Ppd11 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 11 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: pleural cleft
description: Fold of the adult lateral mesothorax that extends dorsoventrally from the leg articulation to the base of the wing by a sinuous course. Internally, it forms an infolding or phragma that acts as a support for the wing and the leg articulation.

label: wing vein segment
description: Subdivision of a wing vein along its length.

label: Ppd19 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 19 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: mesothoracic leg foramen
description: Foramen of the mesothoracic segment from which the mesothoracic leg articulates.

label: mesothoracic foramen
description: Foramen of the adult ventral mesothorax.

label: wing foramen
description: Foramen of the mesothoracic segment from which the wing articulates.

label: Ppd20 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 20 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: Ppd17 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 17 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: mesothoracic ventral articulation
description: Articulation of the mesothoracic coxa with the adult ventral mesothorax.
