label: mesothoracic articulation
description: Articulation of the adult mesothorax.

label: Ppd18 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 18 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: articulation
description: A moveable joint or junction between two sclerites.

label: Ppd15 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 15 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: Ppd16 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 16 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: foramen
description: An aperture in some gross body part. Most commonly used for apertures in the exoskeleton, but also used for internal structures such as the esophageal foramen of the brain.

label: Ppd14 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 14 of the dorsal posterior protocerebrum.

label: prealar apophysis
description: Small protuberance from the mesopleura at the anterior base of the wing hinge.

label: apophysis
description: Any spiniform or tubercular projection of the exo- or endoskeleton of the insect body, when internal frequently giving support for muscle attachment.

label: anepisternum
description: The dorsal part of the mesothoracic episternum. It is derived from the dorsal mesothoracic disc. Its posterior boundary is the pleural suture and its posterior/lateral regions is adjacent to the anterior of the wing hinge. It is separated from the ventral mesothoracic episternum (katepisternum or sternopleurite) by the anapleural suture.

label: primary spermatocyte in meiotic anaphase I
description: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic anaphase I (GO:0007133).

label: meiotic primary spermatocyte
description: Primary spermatocyte during meiosis I (GO:0007127).

label: primary spermatocyte in meiotic metaphase I
description: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic metaphase I (GO:0007132). The chromatin is highly condensed, the parafusorial or paranuclear membranes (three to five layers of double membranes) encircle the nucleus and the astral membranes (stack of approximately 13 umbrella-shaped layers, each with a central hole) cup each pole of the spindle-shaped nucleus. The mitochondria are clustered around the equator of the spindle region and oriented parallel to the long axis of the cell.
synonyms: primary spermatocyte during metaphase of the first meiotic division

label: primary spermatocyte in meiotic telophase I
description: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic telophase 1 (GO:0007134). In early telophase the daughter nucleus forms within the karyoplasm and the remnants of karyoplasmic structures. At late telophase, two nuclear membranes have formed around the nucleus of the future secondary spermatocyte, the parafusorial or paranuclear membranes (three to five layers of double membranes) have dissolved and the cell wall has thickened at the site of maximal invagination.

label: Dd3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: mesothoracic precoxal bridge
description: Plate that connects the anterior region of the adult mesothoracic coxa and the mesothoracic preepisternum.

label: mesothoracic coxal bridge
description: Plate the connects the adult coxa of the mesothoracic segment to the thoracic sclerites.

label: mesofurca
description: Forked paired apophysis of the adult mesothorax. It arises from the sternal plates, supported on a median inflection of the sternum.

label: Dd1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: primary spermatocyte in meiotic prophase I
description: Primary spermatocyte during meiotic prophase I (GO:0007128).

label: Dd2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: mesothoracic postcoxal bridge
description: Plate that connects the posterior region of the adult mesothoracic coxa and the metathoracic preepisternum.

label: mature primary spermatocyte
description: Late, fully grown primary spermatocyte with a large central nucleus, blocky in appearance, often with indentations or grooves, containing Y-loops and a prominent nucleolus. The second nuclear membrane is fully formed. It has a highly developed endoplasmic reticulum, with mitochondria between the cisternae.

label: secondary spermatocyte in meiotic metaphase II
description: Secondary spermatocyte during meiotic metaphase II (GO:0007137).

label: meiotic secondary spermatocyte
description: Secondary spermatocyte during meiosis II (GO:0007135).

label: secondary spermatocyte in meiotic prophase II
description: Secondary spermatocyte during meiotic prophase II (GO:0007136).

label: secondary spermatocyte in meiotic telophase II
description: Secondary spermatocyte during meiotic telophase II (GO:0007139).

label: secondary spermatocyte in meiotic anaphase II
description: Secondary spermatocyte during meiotic anaphase II (GO:0007138).

label: interphase secondary spermatocyte
description: Spermatocyte at the interphase stage between the two meiotic divisions. This stage is very brief.

label: presumptive axillary cord
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the axillary cord. This is located at the posterior margin of the wing disc in the wing hinge primordium.

label: presumptive 3rd axillary sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the 3rd axillary sclerite.

label: presumptive 4th axillary sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the 4th axillary sclerite.

label: Dd10 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 10 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: ventral metathorax
description: Ventral region of the adult external metathorax.

label: adult external metathorax
description: The third thoracic segment of the adult external thorax.

label: metathoracic laterotergite
description: A narrow sclerite between the (mesothoracic) postnotum (FBbt:00004588) and the first abdominal segment.

label: sclerite
description: A region of integument whose external cuticular part is a hard, sclerotized plate.

label: metathoracic tergum
description: Tergum that covers the adult metathoracic segment.

label: Dd11 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 11 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: Dd8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: metathoracic epimeron
description: Narrow sclerite that is located in the posterior part of the pleura in the metathoracic segment of the adult thorax, posterior to the metathoracic episternum.

label: epimeron
description: Large lateral plate of the thorax, behind the pleural suture.

label: metathoracic pleurum
description: Lateral region of the adult external metathoracic segment.

label: Dd9 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 9 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: pleurum
description: The lateral and ventral region of the adult external thorax.

label: presumptive 2nd axillary sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the 2nd axillary sclerite.

label: Dd6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: Dd7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: tergum
description: The upper, originally unpaired plate of the segmented insect body, which either independently or fused with a ventral plate covers the body dorsally, specifically that of the thorax.

label: dorsal metathorax
description: Dorsal region of the adult external metathorax.

label: Dd4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: presumptive 1st axillary sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the 1st axillary sclerite.

label: Dd5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: metathoracic preepisternum
description: Anterior and major portion of the metathoracic episternum.

label: preepisternum
description: Anterior and major portion of the thoracic episternum.

label: metathoracic episternum
description: A sclerite, lacking bristles, that is located anterior to the metathoracic epimerom and adjacent to the metathoracic coxa and sternum. It develops from the metathoracic leg disc.

label: episternum
description: The anterior part of the pleuron (lateral plate of the adult thorax), above the coxa.

label: presumptive metathorax structures from metathoracic leg disc
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into part of the katepimeron and the metathoracic episternum.

label: Dd12 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 12 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: Dd13 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 13 of the dorsal deutocerebrum.

label: metathoracic foramen
description: Foramen of the adult ventral metathorax.

label: presumptive unnamed wing hinge sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the unnamed wing hinge sclerite.

label: Dv1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: presumptive tegula
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the tegula.

label: Dv8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: ventral cervical muscle 27
description: Ventral cervical muscle that connects to a more anterior region than muscle 26. It is the largest of the ventral cervical muscles. It is strap-shaped and comprises 2-3 fibers.

label: ventral cervical muscle
description: Muscle of the adult neck, located ventrally. It attaches broadly to the lateral region of the sternal apodeme of the prothorax, extends through the neck and inserts onto the head.

label: metathoracic coxal bridge
description: Plate the connects the adult coxa of the metathoracic segment to the thoracic sclerites.

label: ventral cervical muscle 26
description: Ventral cervical muscle that connects to a more anterior region than muscle 25. It is spindle-shaped and comprises 3-4 fibers.

label: metathoracic leg foramen
description: Foramen of the metathoracic segment from which the metathoracic leg articulates.

label: dorsal tritocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the dorsal region of the tritocerebrum.

label: Dv6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: promotor muscle
description: Thoracic muscle that has its insertion site more anterior, as compared to thoracic remotor muscles.

label: metathoracic postcoxal bridge
description: Plate that connects the posterior region of the adult metathoracic coxa and the abdomen.

label: Dv7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: adult somatic muscle
description: Muscle attached to the inner surface of the adult body wall, extending between articulated or flexibly joined areas, that serves to move the parts of the exoskeleton.

label: metathoracic precoxal bridge
description: Plate that connects the anterior region of the adult metathoracic coxa and the mesothoracic preepisternum.

label: Dv4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: lateral cervical muscle 24
description: Lateral cervical muscle that connects to a cervical sclerite anteriorly, extending then laterally and posteriorly, and inserting in the same region as dorsal cervical muscle 21.

label: lateral cervical muscle
description: Muscle of the adult neck, located laterally.

label: adult metathoracic spiracle
description: Spiracle of the adult metathoracic segment. This spiracle is part of the haltere sclerite. It opens into the hypopleural air sac.

label: presumptive metathoracic spiracle
description: Region of the lateral haltere disc, posterior to the presumptive metathoracic papilla, that develops into the adult metathoracic spiracle.

label: haltere sclerite
description: A sclerite at the base of the haltere that bears the metathoracic spiracle, and the metathoracic papillae (FBbt:00004409).

label: Dv5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: haltere foramen
description: Foramen of the metathoracic segment from which the haltere is articulated.

label: ventral cervical muscle 25
description: Ventral cervical muscle that connects to a more posterior region than muscle 26. It is spindle-shaped and comprises 5-6 fibers.

label: metathoracic ventral articulation
description: Articulation of the metathoracic coxa with the adult ventral metathorax.

label: metathoracic articulation
description: Articulation of the adult metathorax.

label: Dv2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: Dv3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the ventral deutocerebrum.

label: skeletal muscle of neck
description: Somatic muscle that is part of the adult neck.

label: sternal promotor muscle
description: Promotor muscle of the adult thorax that attaches to the inner surface of the sternum.

label: metathoracic phragma
description: Anterior extension of the genital arch that continues into the body forming a phragma.

label: presumptive metathoracic phragma
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the metathoracic phragma.

label: tergopleural promotor muscle
description: Promotor muscle that arises from the tergum.

label: metafurca
description: Forked paired apophysis of the adult metathorax. It arises from the sternal plates, supported on a median inflection of the sternum.

label: pleural promotor muscle
description: Promotor muscle of the adult thorax that attaches to the inner surface of the pleura.

label: Td1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: Td2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: appendage
description: Organism subdivision that protrudes from the head or trunk.

label: photoperiodism
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of detection of, or exposure to, a period of light or dark of a given length, measured relative to a particular duration known as the 'critical day length'. The critical day length varies between species.

label: entrainment of circadian clock
description: The synchronization of a circadian rhythm to environmental time cues such as light.

label: Tv2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the ventral tritocerebrum.

label: anterior rotator muscle
description: Rotator muscle found in the anterior region of the coxal base.

label: rotator muscle
description: Muscle capable of rotating a body part.

label: joint
description: Articulation of the leg segments.

label: VI fascicle
description: Ventral-most Fas2-immunopositive (FBgn0000635) fascicle of the intermediate fascicles in the embryonic/larval VNC, when seen in transverse section.

label: Td7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: adductor muscle
description: Muscle that draws some body part back to position.

label: metatarsus
description: The first of the tarsal segments of the adult leg. It is located between the tibia and the second tarsal segment and is longer than the other tarsal segments. It has 8 longitudinal rows of bristles around the circumference.

label: presumptive metatarsus
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the metatarsus.

label: Td8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: posterior rotator muscle
description: Rotator muscle found in the posterior region of the coxal base.

label: amide transport
description: The directed movement of an amide, any compound containing one, two, or three acyl groups attached to a nitrogen atom, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: Td5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: tergal remotor muscle
description: Remotor muscle of the adult thorax that attaches to the inner surface of the tergum.

label: remotor muscle
description: Thoracic muscle that has its insertion site more posterior, as compared to thoracic promotor muscles.

label: tibia
description: Fourth most proximal segment of the adult leg. It is located between the femur and the first tarsal segment. It has 10 rows of longitudinal mechanosensory bristles around the circumference.

label: presumptive tibia
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the tibia.

label: Td6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: coxa
description: Proximal most segment of the adult leg. It connects proximally to the thorax and distally to the trochanter.

label: presumptive coxa
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the coxa.

label: pleural remotor muscle
description: Remotor muscle of the adult thorax that attaches to the inner surface of the pleura.

label: presumptive femur
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the femur.

label: Td3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: Td4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the dorsal tritocerebrum.

label: sternal remotor muscle
description: Remotor muscle of the adult thorax that attaches to the inner surface of the sternum.

label: trochanter
description: Small, second most proximal segment of the adult leg. It is located between the coxa and femur.

label: presumptive trochanter
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter.

label: depressor muscle
description: Skeletal muscle that lowers an appendage.

label: skeletal muscle of leg
description: Somatic muscle that is part of a leg.

label: tarsal segment 2
description: Second most proximal tarsal segment of the adult leg.

label: presumptive tarsal segment 2
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the second tarsal segment.

label: Tv4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the ventral tritocerebrum.

label: Tv5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the ventral tritocerebrum.

label: extracoxal depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle connecting the coxa and the thoracic exoskeleton.

label: tarsal segment 4
description: Fourth most proximal tarsal segment of the adult leg.

label: presumptive tarsal segment 4
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the fourth tarsal segment.

label: Tv3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the ventral tritocerebrum.

label: tarsal segment 3
description: Third most proximal tarsal segment of the adult leg.

label: presumptive tarsal segment 3
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the third tarsal segment.

label: amine transport
description: The directed movement of amines, including polyamines, organic compounds containing one or more amino groups, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: nitrogen compound transport
description: The directed movement of nitrogen-containing compounds into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: Pcd12 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 12 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: dorsal central protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the dorsal region of the central protocerebrum.

label: intracoxal levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult coxa that extends along the coxa and attaches to the distal coxa.

label: levator muscle
description: Muscle that raises an appendage.

label: ungulfus
description: Median process of the pretarsus that articulates with the claws (unguis).

label: pretarsus
description: The most distal segment of the adult leg. This segment is highly derived and bears the claws.

label: pulvillar membrane
description: Membrane that is found between the pulvillus and the unguis (claw).

label: TP4
description: Second most ventral transverse projection.

label: transverse projection
description: Transverse fascicle that intersect the longitudinal connectives in the larval ventral nerve cord. There are 5 of these, spanning the dorsal/ventral axis. The two most dorsal correspond to the intersegmental nerve roots.

label: intracoxal mesal levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult coxa that extends along the medial coxa and attaches to the distal coxa.

label: empodium
description: A spine-like process that lies in a medial position on the base of the foot (pretarsus) between the two claws (unguis).

label: TP5
description: The most ventral of the transverse projections.

label: intracoxal lateral levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult coxa that extends along the lateral coxa and attaches to the distal coxa.

label: unguitractor plate
description: A small ventral, median sclerite of the pretarsus that is partially invaginated into the end of the 5th tarsal segment and is the attachment site of the attachment of a long tendon connected to the pretarsal depressor muscle.

label: tibial depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic leg that extends along the femur and attaches to the proximal tibia.

label: TP3
description: Third most dorsal transverse projection.

label: intracoxal depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic leg that extends along the medial coxa and attaches to the distal coxa.

label: pretarsal depressor muscle
description: Muscle attached via a long tendon to the unguitractor plate of the pretarsus.

label: pulvillus
description: A lateral lobe of the pretarsus that is covered in cuticular hairs. There are two of these per pretarsus, ventral to the auxiliae and proximal to the claws (unguis).

label: tarsal depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult tarsus that extends along the tibia, attaching to the proximal tarsus.

label: auxilia
description: A small, lateral sclerite of the pretarsus. Each pretarsus has a symmetrical pair of these structures - one proximal to each claw (unguis).

label: tibial levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult tibia that extends along the femur and attaches to the proximal tibia.

label: Pcd15 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 15 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: unguis
description: The paired, hollow chitinous hooks at the end of the pretarsus. These are sclerotized extensions of the integument (i.e. they consist of underlying epidermis and overlying cuticle).

label: presumptive unguis
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the unguis.

label: Pcd16 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 16 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: Pcd13 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 13 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: reductor muscle
description: Small muscle of the adult leg that originates at the base of the trochanter and attaches to the proximal femur.

label: retineria
description: Tiny hollow hairs on the distal pretarsus (foot) through which viscous substances are secreted.

label: Pcd14 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 14 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: tarsal levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult tarsus that extends in the distal tibia, attaching to the proximal tarsus.

label: unguis scale
description: Scale present on the dorsal surface of the unguis, close to the mid-point of the long axis of the unguis.

label: organic acid transport
description: The directed movement of organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: prothoracic pleural remotor and abductor muscle 29
description: Pleural remotor muscle of the adult prothoracic coxa that arises dorsally and extends ventrally to the posterior rim of the coxa.

label: prothoracic remotor muscle
description: Remotor muscle of the prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic tergopleural promotor muscle 28
description: Large pleural promotor muscle of the adult prothoracic coxa that arises dorsally on the tergum and extends ventrally to the anterior angle of the coxa.

label: prothoracic promotor muscle
description: Promotor muscle of the prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic femur
description: Segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the trochanter and distally with the tibia.

label: presumptive prothoracic femur
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic femur.

label: des2 neuron
description: A neuron innervating the dorsal Kolbchen of the embryonic/larval prothorax (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There are two such neurons innervating each dorsal Kolbchen.

label: prothoracic dorsal Kolbchen dbd
description: Dorsal Kolbchen of the embryonic/larval prothoracic (T1) segment. It is innervated by two neurons (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986) and is located more dorsally in the segment than the dorsal-most Kolbchen of the meso- and metathoracic (T2-T3) segments.

label: Pcd21 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 21 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: prothoracic sternal muscle
description: Sternal muscle of the anterior adult prothorax.

label: skeletal muscle of prothorax
description: Somatic muscle that is part of the prothorax.

label: prothoracic pleural promotor muscle 30
description: Pleural promotor muscle of the adult prothoracic coxa that arises on the episternum and extends posteriorly, to the coxal base anterior to the pleural articulation. There are usually two muscles of this type.

label: Pcd19 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 19 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: prothoracic coxa
description: The coxa of the prothoracic leg. It is much larger than the coxae of the other two legs.

label: presumptive prothoracic coxa
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic coxa.

label: Pcd20 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 20 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: femoral reductor muscle
description: Reductor muscle of the adult leg that originates at the base of the trochanter and attaches to the proximal femur.

label: prothoracic trochanter
description: Segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the coxa and distally with the femur.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter.

label: desE neuron
description: Most dorsal of the sensory neurons of the peripheral nervous system that innervate a dorsal external sense (des) organ of the mesothoracic, metathoracic or prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986).

label: Pcd17 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 17 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: Pcd18 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 18 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: prothoracic tibia
description: Segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the femur and distally with the first tarsal segment. On its anterior side it has 5-7 transverse rows of bristles.

label: presumptive prothoracic tibia
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tibia.

label: prothoracic sternal anterior rotator muscle 31
description: Sternal rotator muscle of the prothoracic coxa, that extends mediolaterally, anterior to the sternal posterior rotator muscle 32 and dorsal to the sternal adductor muscle 33. It attaches laterally to the anterior segment of the coxa and medially to the medial plate of the prothoracic furca. It is composed of 6-7 fibers.

label: prothoracic tarsal segment 2
description: Second tarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the metatarsus, and distally with the third tarsal segment.

label: presumptive prothoracic tarsal segment 2
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tarsal segment 2.

label: prothoracic metatarsus
description: First tarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the tibia and distally with the second tarsal segment. Its surface is covered with eight longitudinal rows of bristles and with transverse rows of bristles (TR) in the anterior compartment, between proximo-distal rows 7 and 8. There is sexual dimorphism in the number of TRs (transverse row bristles, TR). In males, 2 TRs are replaced by the sex comb and one central bristle.

label: presumptive prothoracic metatarsus
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic metatarsus.

label: dch3 neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates a triscolopidial chordotonal organ, located in the dorsal region of a larval thoracic segment. There are three of these neurons.

label: prothoracic sternal adductor muscle 33
description: Sternal adductor muscle of the prothoracic coxa, that extends anteroposteriorly, ventral to the sternal anterior rotator muscle 31 and posterior rotator muscle 32. It attaches to a broad region on the medial region of the sternal apodeme and tapers to insert into the coxal segment of the prothoracic leg. It is composed of 3-4 fibers.

label: prothoracic tarsal segment 4
description: Fourth tarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 3, and distally with the fifth tarsal segment.

label: presumptive prothoracic tarsal segment 4
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tarsal segment 4.

label: prothoracic sternal posterior rotator muscle 32
description: Sternal rotator muscle of the prothoracic coxa, that extends dorsoventrally, posterior to the sternal anterior rotator muscle 31 and dorsal to the sternal adductor muscle 33.

label: prothoracic tarsal segment 3
description: Third tarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 2, and distally with the fourth tarsal segment.

label: presumptive prothoracic tarsal segment 3
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tarsal segment 3.

label: les3 neuron
description: A neuron innervating the lateral Kolbchen of the embryonic/larval meso- or metathoracic segment (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There are three such neurons innervating each dorsal Kolbchen.

label: lateral Kolbchen lbd
description: Laterally located club-like sensory structure found in the mesothoracic and metathoracic segments of the larva.

label: prothoracic tibial depressor muscle 40
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic tibia that extends along the medial femur, proximal to the tibial depressor muscle 41.

label: prothoracic tibial depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic tibia.

label: prothoracic ungulfus
description: Any ungulfus (FBbt:00004657) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: prothoracic pretarsus
description: Any pretarsus (FBbt:00004653) that is part of some prothoracic leg (FBbt:00004663).

label: prothoracic depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: prothoracic pulvillar membrane
description: Any pulvillar membrane (FBbt:00004656) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: lch3 neuron
description: Scolopidial neuron that innervates the laterally located triscolopidial chordotonal organ lch3.

label: prothoracic tibial depressor muscle 41
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic tibia that extends mediolaterally in the distal femur, distal to the tibial depressor muscle 40.

label: skeletal muscle of prothoracic leg
description: Skeletal muscle of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: presumptive prothoracic tarsal segment 5
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tarsal segment 5.

label: prothoracic intracoxal depressor muscle 35
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic trochanter that extends along the medial coxa, ventral to the extracoxal depressor muscle 34.

label: prothoracic pulvillus
description: Any pulvillus (FBbt:00004655) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: lesD neuron
description: Sensory neuron of the peripheral nervous system that innervates a lateral external sense (les) organ of the prothoracic segment of the embryo/larva.

label: prothoracic extracoxal depressor muscle 34
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic trochanter that extends mediolaterally and anteroposteriorly through the coxa, anterior to the sternal adductor muscle 33.

label: prothoracic auxilia
description: Any auxilia (FBbt:00004654) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: polar primary spermatocyte
description: Early primary spermatocyte with a spherical, asymmetrically placed nucleus and with mitochondria aggregated at the pole of the cell opposite the nucleus. The second nuclear membrane has started to form, the nucleolus is compact with few cavities and the centrioles are in the central region of the cell.

label: secondary spermatogonium
description: Male germline cell during its first 4 mitoses. The end result of these mitotic divisions is a cyst of 16 primary spermatocytes.

label: apolar primary spermatocyte
description: Mid primary spermatocyte, with a large central nucleus which has an undulating surface. The nucleus of this cell is in the process of becoming surrounded by a second nuclear membrane, and has a large nucleolus filled with irregularly shaped cavities.

label: comet stage spermatid
description: An early elongation-stage spermatid of length 35-120 micrometers resembling a comet, with a bipartite parallel mitochondrial derivative that developed from the Nebenkern, with its diameter decreasing from 5 to 1 micrometers. The cytoplasmic inclusions in the mitochondrial derivative gradually disappear. The nucleus is round and clear.

label: early elongation stage spermatid
description: A spermatid which has initiated axoneme elongation, but which is relatively short (up to 200 micrometers in length) and retains a round nucleus. The two parts of the mitochondrial derivative are roughly equal in size.

label: leaf blade stage spermatid
description: An early elongation-stage spermatid of length 15-35 micrometers, with a Nebenkern resembling a spear point of leaf blade and with cytoplasmic inclusions. A protein body is visible in the nucleus, the centriole adjunct forms and the axoneme elongates.

label: agglomeration stage spermatid
description: A round spermatid in which the mitochondria have coalesced into one or more agglomerations that together form a crescent shaped mass, and in which a small spherical protein body has formed in the spherical nucleus.

label: pre-elongation spermatid
description: One of 64 haploid germ-cells present in the spermatid cyst from the end of meiosis II to the beginning of tail elongation.

label: coalescence stage spermatid
description: A round spermatid with a crescent-shaped group of mitochondria at the same pole of the cell as the centriole and with a small spherical nucleus that lacks a protein body.

label: prothoracic pretarsal depressor muscle 44
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic pretarsus that extends along the tarsal segments.

label: prothoracic unguis
description: Claw at the distal end of the prothoracic pretarsus of the prothoracic leg.

label: presumptive prothoracic unguis
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic unguis.

label: prothoracic tarsal depressor muscle 43
description: Depressor muscle of the adult prothoracic tarsus that extends along the tibia, medial to the tarsal levator muscle 42.

label: prothoracic empodium
description: Any empodium (FBbt:00004659) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: prothoracic intracoxal lateral levator muscle 36
description: Levator muscle of the adult prothoracic trochanter that extends along the lateral coxa and is lateral to the mesal levator muscle 37.

label: prothoracic levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: prothoracic retineria
description: Any retineria (FBbt:00004662) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: prothoracic unguis scale
description: Any unguis scale (FBbt:00004661) that is part of some prothoracic unguis (FBbt:00004682).

label: prothoracic unguitractor plate
description: Any unguitractor plate (FBbt:00004658) that is part of some prothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004675).

label: skeletal muscle of mesothorax
description: Somatic muscle that is part of the mesothorax.

label: prothoracic femoral reductor muscle 38
description: Reductor muscle of the adult prothoracic femur that extends along the trochanter.

label: prothoracic reductor muscle
description: Reductor muscle of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: mesothoracic femur
description: Segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the trochanter and distally with the tibia. In the posterior compartment many of the bristles are missing, including the very large bristles (zone of no bristles, ZNB).

label: presumptive mesothoracic femur
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic femur.

label: prothoracic tibial levator muscle 39
description: Levator muscle of the adult prothoracic tibia that extends along the lateral femur.

label: mesothoracic coxa
description: The coxa of the mesothoracic leg.

label: presumptive mesothoracic coxa
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic coxa.

label: prothoracic intracoxal mesal levator muscle 37
description: Levator muscle of the adult prothoracic trochanter that extends along the medial coxa and is medial to the lateral levator muscle 36.

label: mesothoracic trochanter
description: Segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the coxa and distally with the femur. It has more bristles than either the pro- or metathoracic trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter.

label: dopamine transport
description: The directed movement of dopamine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Dopamine is a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: prothoracic tarsal levator muscle 42
description: Levator muscle of the adult prothoracic tarsus that extends in the distal tibia, lateral to the tarsal depressor muscle 43.

label: mesothoracic tibia
description: Segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the femur and distally with the first tarsal segment.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tibia
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tibia.

label: acetylcholine transport
description: The directed movement of acetylcholine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Acetylcholine is an acetic acid ester of the organic base choline and functions as a neurotransmitter, released at the synapses of parasympathetic nerves and at neuromuscular junctions.

label: temporary eclosion muscle
description: An adult somatic muscle that drives movements necessary for eclosion and that dies shortly after eclosion.

label: dorsal medial muscle
description: An indirect flight muscle that functions as a wing depressor. It extends anterioposteriorly, connecting the thorax and the postnotum. The six pairs of dorsal medial muscles function to depress the wings by longitudinal arching of the scutum (Miller, 1950).

label: indirect flight muscle
description: Muscle involved in flight that is not directly attached to the wing base.

label: mesothoracic tarsal segment 2
description: Second tarsal segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the metatarsus, and distally with the third tarsal segment.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tarsal segment 2
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tarsal segment 2.

label: flight muscle
description: Muscle involved in the mechanism of flight. The indirect flight muscles are involved in the deformation of the thoracic terga that bear the wings but are not directly attached to the wing, whereas the direct flight muscles are attached directly to the wing and aid in fine control of its movement.

label: mesothoracic metatarsus
description: First tarsal segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the tibia and distally with the second tarsal segment. Its surface is covered with eight longitudinal rows of bristles, with ventral rows 1 and 8 having thicker and shorter bristles. In contrast to the pro- and metathoracic metatarsi.

label: presumptive mesothoracic metatarsus
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic metatarsus.

label: dorsal medial muscle 45b
description: The second most dorsal of the dorsal medial muscles. It is innervated by the indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN5.

label: indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN5
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal medial muscle 45b and dorsal medial muscle 45a. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a very large soma, located contralateral to dorsal medial muscles 45a and 45b, near the midline.

label: mesothoracic tarsal segment 4
description: Fourth tarsal segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 3, and distally with the fifth tarsal segment.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tarsal segment 4
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tarsal segment 4.

label: dorsal medial muscle 45a
description: The most dorsal and shortest of the dorsal medial muscles. It is innervated by the indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN5.

label: mesothoracic tarsal segment 3
description: Third tarsal segment of the mesothoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 2, and distally with the fourth tarsal segment.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tarsal segment 3
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tarsal segment 3.

label: lateral multidendritic neuron ldaC
description: Multidendritic neuron located in the lateral complex of the second and third thoracic segments of the larva.

label: mesodermal derivative
description: Any germ layer derivative (FBbt:00000000) that is part of some late extended germ band embryo (FBbt:00004450) and that develops from some mesoderm (FBbt:00000126).

label: lateral oblique dorsal muscle
description: An indirect flight muscle that functions as a wing elevator. It extends from the posterior notum ventrally to the postnotum.

label: lateral multidendritic neuron ldaD
description: Multidendritic neuron located in the lateral complex of the second and third thoracic segments of the larva.

label: dorsal medial muscle 45d
description: The fourth most dorsal of the dorsal medial muscles. It is innervated by the indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN3.

label: indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN3
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal medial muscle 45d. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a large soma, located ipsilateral to dorsal medial muscle 45d, in the ventrolateral part of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion at the border of the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres.

label: mesothoracic pretarsus
description: Any pretarsus (FBbt:00004653) that is part of some mesothoracic leg (FBbt:00004685).

label: dorsal medial muscle 45c
description: The third most dorsal of the dorsal medial muscles. It is innervated by the indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN4.

label: indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN4
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal medial muscle 45c. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a large soma, located ipsilateral to dorsal medial muscle 45c, in the ventrolateral part of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion at the border of the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tarsal segment 5
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tarsal segment 5.

label: dorsal medial muscle 45f
description: The most ventral of the dorsal medial muscles. It is innervated by the indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN1.

label: indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN1
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal medial muscle 45f. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a large soma, located ipsilateral to dorsal medial muscle 45f, in the ventrolateral part of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion at the border of the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres.

label: mesothoracic pulvillus
description: Any pulvillus (FBbt:00004655) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: dorsal medial muscle 45e
description: The second most ventral of the dorsal medial muscles. It is innervated by the indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN2.

label: indirect flight muscle motor neuron MN2
description: Motor neuron that innervates the dorsal medial muscle 45e. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a large soma, located ipsilateral to dorsal medial muscle 45e, in the ventrolateral part of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion at the border of the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres.

label: mesothoracic auxilia
description: Any auxilia (FBbt:00004654) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: tergosternal muscle 47a
description: The most anterior of the tergosternal muscles.

label: tergosternal muscle
description: An indirect flight muscle that functions as a wing elevator. It extends from the anterior notum ventrally to the mesothoracic preepisternum, anterior to the coxa.

label: tergosternal muscle 47c
description: One of the posterior tergosternal muscles, ventral to the tergosternal muscle 47b in the notum.

label: tergosternal muscle 47b
description: One of the posterior tergosternal muscles, dorsal to the tergosternal muscle 47c in the notum.

label: vesD neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the posterior hair of the Keilin's organ in the embryonic/larval thoracic segments, together with the vesE neuron. It is located in the ventral cluster of a larval thoracic segment.

label: lateral oblique dorsal muscle 46b
description: The most posterior of the lateral oblique dorsal muscles.

label: lateral oblique dorsal muscle 46a
description: The most anterior of the lateral oblique dorsal muscles.

label: vesE neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the posterior hair of the Keilin's organ in the embryonic/larval thoracic segments, together with the vesD neuron. It is located in the ventral cluster of a larval thoracic segment.

label: coxal tergal remotor muscle 48a
description: The anterior of the lateral oblique dorsal muscles.

label: direct flight muscle
description: Tubular muscle that inserts on apodemes at the base of the wing hinge and allow for the fine control of movements that are necessary for wing positioning and steering during flight (Kozopas and Nusse, 2002).

label: coxal tergal remotor muscle 48b
description: The posterior of the lateral oblique dorsal muscles.

label: v''esA neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval prothoracic segment (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986) that innervates a papillar sensilla. It lies on the anterior border, ventral to v''esB.

label: direct flight muscle 58b
description: Posterior-most of a pair of direct flight muscles that function to depress the anal portion of the wing (Miller, 1950).

label: v''esB neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval prothoracic segment (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986) that innervates a papillar sensilla. It lies on the anterior border, dorsal to v''esA.

label: basalar muscle 52
description: Direct flight muscle connected to the basalar sclerite more anteriorly than muscle 51. It is innervated by the dorsal and ventral tp motor neurons.

label: dorsal tp motor neuron
description: One of the two motor neuron that innervates the basalar muscle 52. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (ADMN). It has one primary branch. It has a small spherical soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 52, mediolateral and ventral to the root of the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a tufted morphology.

label: ventral tp motor neuron
description: One of the two motor neuron that innervates the basalar muscle 52. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (ADMN). It has one primary branch. It has a small spherical soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 52, mediolateral and ventral to the level at which the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. It has a tufted morphology.

label: basalar muscle 51
description: Direct flight muscle that depresses the anterior border of the wing (Miller, 1950). It is innervated by the b2 motor neuron.

label: b2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the basalar muscle 51. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (ADMN). It has four primary branches: medial, lateral, dorsal and a posterior group. It has a spherical soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 51, ventral to the root of the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve. It has a fibrous morphology.

label: direct flight muscle 49
description: Tergo-pleural muscle extending from the anterior notum to the basalar of the wing (Sink, 2006). It serves to draw the wing horizontally forwards (Miller, 1950). It is innervated by the b1 motor neuron.

label: b1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the direct flight muscle 49. Its axon is large and exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (ADMN). It has a characteristic posterior branch, that branches close to the soma and contralateral projections. It has a large disk-shaped soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 49, ventral to the root of the ADMN. It has a stubbly morphology.

label: direct flight muscle 58a
description: Anterior-most of a pair of direct flight muscles that function to depress the anal portion of the wing (Miller, 1950).

label: v'es3 neuron
description: Sensory PNS neuron of embryonic/larval pro-, meta- or mesothoracic segments (Dambly-Chaudiere and Ghysen, 1986). There are 3 of these neurons with apposed dendrites. It is located dorsal to v'esB neuron.

label: direct flight muscle 50
description: Tergo-pleural muscle extending from the notum to the posterior of the basalar. Together with flight muscle 49, it functions to extend the wing (Sink, 2006).

label: muscle of first axillary 53
description: Direct flight muscle connected to the anterior of the first axillary sclerite that, together with muscle 56, serves to raise the wing and draw it backwards (Miller, 1950). It is innervated by the I1 motor neuron.

label: axillary muscle
description: Direct flight muscle that inserts at one of the wing axillary sclerites (Sink, 2006).

label: I1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscle of first axillary 53. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (ADMN). It has one primary branch. It has a spherical soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 53, ventral to the point at which the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. It has a fibrous morphology.

label: 1st axillary sclerite
description: Sclerite of the wing hinge that articulates with the notal wing processes and the 2nd axillary sclerite. Its anterior end is immediately posterior to the humeral sclerite (FBbt:00004734).

label: axillary sclerite
description: One of a small group of small sclerites in the middle and posterior of the wing hinge that function in articulation of the wing. Except for the proximal region of the 4th axillary sclerite, they are hairless.

label: muscle of third axillary 54
description: Direct flight muscle connected to the anterior of the third axillary sclerite that, together with muscle 55, serves to depress the anal portion of the wing (Miller, 1950). It is innervated by the III1 motor neuron.

label: III1 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscle of third axillary 54. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the accessory mesothoracic nerve. It has four primary branches: medial, anterior lateral and dorsal lateral. It has a teardrop-shaped soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 54, ventral to the root of the accessory mesothoracic nerve. It has a fibrous morphology.

label: 3rd axillary sclerite
description: A small sclerite of the wing hinge, located immediately anterior to the alula (FBbt:00004747).

label: prothoracic nerve
description: Any nerve (FBbt:00005105) that is part of some prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000017).

label: mesothoracic pleurosternal muscle 60
description: Small mesothoracic pleurosternal muscle. It attaches ventrally and medially on the mesofurca and dorsolaterally on the thoracic joint of the prealar apophysis. It is located ventrally to the pleurosternal muscle 59.

label: mesothoracic pleurosternal muscle
description: An indirect flight muscle that is involved in generating tension in the thoracic flight box, which determines wing beat frequency. It attaches ventrally and medially on the mesofurca and dorsolaterally on the prealar apophysis.

label: mesothoracic pleurosternal muscle 59
description: The main of the mesothoracic pleurosternal muscles. It is located dorsally to pleurosternal muscle 60.

label: prothoracic intersegmental nerve
description: Intersegmental nerve of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic anterior fascicle neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: mesothoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 62
description: Ventral longitudinal muscle of the mesothorax, located medially to the mesothoracic pleurosternal muscle 59.

label: mesothoracic lateral intrasegmental muscle 61
description: Oblique muscle attached ventroanteriorly on the mesothoracic sternal apophysis and dorsoposteriorly on the anterior margin of the metathoracic episternum.

label: prothoracic desA neuron
description: Any desA neuron (FBbt:00001999) that is part of some prothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002731) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: muscle of first axillary 56
description: Direct flight muscle connected to the posterior of the first axillary sclerite that, together with muscle 53, serves to raise the wing and draw it backwards (Miller, 1950).

label: muscle of third axillary 55
description: Direct flight muscle connected to the posterior of the third axillary sclerite that, together with muscle 54, serves to depress the anal portion of the wing (Miller, 1950). It is innervated by the III3 motor neuron.

label: III3 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscle of third axillary 55. Its axon exits the thoracico-abdominal ganglion in the accessory mesothoracic nerve. It has three primary branches, two of which larger than the other: the medial, lateral and inconsistent branches, respectively. It has a large tear-shaped soma, located ipsilateral to muscle 55, ventral to the root of the accessory mesothoracic nerve. It has a stubbly morphology.

label: subalar muscle 57
description: Direct flight muscle connecting to the subalar sclerite that serves to draw the wing backwards toward the body (Miller, 1950).

label: prothoracic desB neuron
description: Any desB neuron (FBbt:00002000) that is part of some prothoracic dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002729) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: The most ventral of the two trichodeum sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic sternal remotor muscle 65
description: Sternal remotor muscle of the adult mesothoracic coxa that arises anteriorly in the same region as the mesothoracic sternal promotor muscle 64 and extends posteriorly to the posterior rim of the coxa.

label: adult fruitless aSG1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located at the ventral midline of the oesophageal foramen, dorsal to the adult subesophageal zone. Neurites project posteriorly before making a turn anteriorly.

label: mesothoracic pleural remotor muscle 63
description: Pleural remotor muscle of the adult mesothoracic coxa that arises dorsally and extends ventrally to the posterior rim of the coxa.

label: prothoracic desC neuron
description: Any desC neuron (FBbt:00002001) that is part of some prothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002732) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless aIP4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP4 lineage clone (FBbt:00111187).

label: adult fruitless aIP4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located laterally in the ventrolateral protocerebrum. Neurites terminate at the anterior region of the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum and wedge, and posterior region of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLPr).

label: prothoracic desD neuron
description: Any desD neuron (FBbt:00002002) that is part of some prothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc3 (FBbt:00002733) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc3
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless aSP4 (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located between the anterior optic tract and the ventrolateral protocerebrum, immediately medial to aSP5 lineage clone. A neurite projects ventrally before turning dorsally and extends superficially along the arch to the contralateral hemisphere. Arbors span the lateral junction. Females do not have extensive arbors in the ring structure.

label: prothoracic lch3 neuron
description: Lateral triscolopidial chordotonal organ of the embryonic/larval prothorax (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1985).

label: prothoracic lateral triscolopidial chordotonal organ lch3
description: Triscolopidial chordotonal organ of the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless pSP3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111195).

label: adult fruitless pSP3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located laterally to the posterior lateral horn. Neurites project medially then bend lateral dorsally. It seems to arborize locally in the lateral horn.

label: prothoracic dorsal/lateral multidendritic neuron
description: Multidendritic neuron of the dorsal or lateral sensory clusters in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment. It fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve.

label: prothoracic dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaA
description: Multidendritic ddaA neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless aSP10 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP10 lineage clone (FBbt:00111193).

label: adult fruitless aSP10 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located dorsolaterally in the ventrolateral protocerebrum. Neurites enter the tract below the anterior optic tubercle and branches. The first branch arborizes in the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum and wedge, and posterior region of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLPr). The other branch continues medially, with one branch of the neurite arborizing in the lateral junction while the other crosses the midline and arborizes in the contralateral lateral junction.

label: prothoracic dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaB
description: Multidendritic ddaB neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic desE neuron
description: Any desE neuron (FBbt:00002003) that is part of some prothoracic dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00002730) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: The most dorsal of the two trichodeum sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless aSG2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSG2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111191).

label: adult fruitless aSG2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located at the anterior midline of the adult subesophageal zone, ventral to the aSG1 lineage clone. Neurites project posteriorly, towards the oesophageal foramen. The path each neuron takes is highly variable.

label: prothoracic lesA neuron
description: Any lesA neuron (FBbt:00002012) that is part of some prothoracic lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1 (FBbt:00002736) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic lateral sensillum campaniformium lc1
description: The most ventral of the two campaniformium sensilla of the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic lesB neuron
description: Any lesB neuron (FBbt:00002013) that is part of some prothoracic lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1 (FBbt:00002735) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic lateral sensillum trichodeum lh1
description: Trichodeum sensillum of the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless aSG1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSG1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111189).

label: prothoracic lesC neuron
description: Any lesC neuron (FBbt:00002014) that is part of some prothoracic lateral sensillum campaniformium lc2 (FBbt:00002737) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002064).

label: prothoracic lateral sensillum campaniformium lc2
description: The most ventral of the two campaniformium sensilla of the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaC
description: Multidendritic ddaC neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaD
description: Multidendritic ddaD neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: lymph gland stem cell
description: Stem cell that gives rise to hematopoietic precursors (prohemocytes) that are found in the larval lymph gland medullary zone. Around 30 of these cells form a niche in the posterior signalling centre of lymph gland primary lobe.

label: posterior signalling centre of lymph gland primary lobe
description: A cluster of (about 30) cells at the posterior tip of the primary lobes of the lymph gland in the third instar larva that serves as a niche for stem cells that are the precursors of plasmatocytes, crystal cells and lamellocytes.

label: adult fruitless aSP4 (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP4 (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00111197) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: prothoracic dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaE
description: Multidendritic ddaE neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic segmental nerve
description: Segmental nerve of the prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic posterior fascicle neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic vesA neuron
description: Any vesA neuron (FBbt:00002041) that is part of some prothoracic Keilin's organ (FBbt:00111639) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic vesB neuron
description: Any vesB neuron (FBbt:00002042) that is part of some prothoracic Keilin's organ (FBbt:00111639) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaA
description: Multidendritic ldaA neuron of the lateral sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaB
description: Multidendritic ldaB neuron of the lateral sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaC
description: Multidendritic ldaC neuron of the lateral sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic lateral multidendritic neuron ldaD
description: Multidendritic ldaD neuron of the lateral sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless pMP2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medial to the mushroom body calyx. A neurite projects medially and forms two branches. The lateral branch forms dendritic arbors in the medial ring and lateral crescent. The ventral branch travels long the contralateral midline and forms axonal arbors in the adult subesophageal zone before leaving the brain. In the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, there is an A-shaped axonal arbor near the dorsal anterior region. The other terminals in the thoracico-abdominal are located at the dorsal metathoracic segment and the abdominal segment. This clone is not found in females.

label: adult fruitless aSG3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSG3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111167).

label: adult fruitless aSG3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medially at the ventral adult subesophageal zone. A neurite projects dorsally towards the oesophageal foramen.

label: prothoracic vesC neuron
description: Any vesC neuron (FBbt:00002043) that is part of some prothoracic Keilin's organ (FBbt:00111639) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: adult fruitless pSP4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP4 lineage clone (FBbt:00111165).

label: adult fruitless pSP4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located lateroventral to the mushroom body calyx. A neurite projects medially, crossing the mushroom body pedunculus towards the medial protocerebrum.

label: prothoracic vesD neuron
description: Any vesD neuron (FBbt:00002044) that is part of some prothoracic Keilin's organ (FBbt:00111639) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic vesE neuron
description: Any vesE neuron (FBbt:00002045) that is part of some prothoracic Keilin's organ (FBbt:00111639) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: adult fruitless pSG2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located posteroventrally to the adult subesophageal zone. Neurites project ventrally to the dorsal oesophageal foramen.

label: prothoracic v''esB neuron
description: Any v''esB neuron (FBbt:00002053) that is part of some prothoracic slit papilla sensillum py (FBbt:00002727) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic slit papilla sensillum py
description: The most dorsal of the two slit papillar sensilla of the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment, located close to the anterior boundary.

label: adult fruitless pMP7 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP7 lineage clone (FBbt:00111173).

label: adult fruitless pMP7 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located posterior to the protocerebral bridge. A neurite projects ventrally then laterally, along the posterior optic commissure to arborize sparsely the lobula. Two arborization regions are observed: one in the posterior adult subesophageal zone and a smaller region in the lateral subesophageal zone.

label: prothoracic vch1 neuron
description: Any vch1 neuron (FBbt:00002040) that is part of some prothoracic ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1 (FBbt:00002742) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic ventral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ vch1
description: Monoscolopidial chordotonal organ of the ventral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic ventral multidendritic neuron
description: A multidendritic neuron of the ventral cluster sensory cluster of the larval prothoracic segment. There are four of these per cluster, all of which have axons that fasciculate with the prothoracic segmental nerve.

label: adult fruitless pMP3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111171).

label: adult fruitless pMP3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medial to the mushroom body calyx. A neurite forms a dorsal branch soon after entering the neuropil and projects to the lateral junction. The ventral branch crosses the midline to arborize in a region near the ventral medial antennal lobe.

label: prothoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002055) that is part of some embryonic/larval prothoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007306).

label: prothoracic v'esA neuron
description: Any v'esA neuron (FBbt:00002048) that is part of some prothoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002740) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: The most ventral of the two campaniformium sensilla of the ventral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless pMP2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111169).

label: prothoracic v'esB neuron
description: Any v'esB neuron (FBbt:00002049) that is part of some prothoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002741) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: The most dorsal of the two campaniformium sensilla of the ventral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic v'es3 neuron
description: Any v'es3 neuron (FBbt:00002051) that is part of some prothoracic ventral Kolbchen vbd (FBbt:00002739) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic ventral Kolbchen vbd
description: Kolbchen ventrally located in the embryonic/larval prothorax. It is part of the prothoracic ventral sensory cluster.

label: prothoracic v''esA neuron
description: Any v''esA neuron (FBbt:00002052) that is part of some prothoracic slit papilla sensillum px (FBbt:00002726) and that fasciculates with some prothoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002085).

label: prothoracic slit papilla sensillum px
description: The most ventral of the two slit papillar sensilla of the lateral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment, located close to the anterior boundary.

label: organic substance catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

label: organic substance metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

label: adult fruitless aSG4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located near the midline of the adult subesophageal zone. Neurites project dorsally to the dorsal oesophageal foramen.

label: adult fruitless pSP2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111177).

label: adult fruitless pSP2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located lateral to the mushroom body calyx. A neurite enters the neuropil close to a small ridge medial to the posterior lateral horn and projects medially. The projection extends towards the lateral junction.

label: adult fruitless pSG2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111175).

label: adult fruitless pSP1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111185).

label: adult fruitless pSP1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located posterior to the posterior superior lateral protocerebrum. A neurite projects medially and arborizes in the posterior region of the dorsal superior intermediate protocerebrum and in the anterior part of the dorsal superior medial protocerebrum (MSMPr).

label: adult fruitless pIP3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111183).

label: adult fruitless pIP3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. It arborizes in the posterior lobula, with a neurite projecting medially to arborize in the medial region of the ring.

label: adult fruitless aSG6 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSG6 lineage clone (FBbt:00111181).

label: adult fruitless aSG6 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located lateral to the ventral adult subesophageal zone. Neurites arborize extensively in the ipsilateral subesophageal zone.

label: adult fruitless aSG4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSG4 lineage clone (FBbt:00111179).

label: adult fruitless vPR6 (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the female adult thoracico-abdominal ganglion that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located laterally near the border of the prothoracic and mesothoracic ganglia. Its neurons extend neurites medially and posteriorly within the wing neuropil. This clone is dimorphic, with differences in arborization in the mesothoracic triangle between males and females.

label: adult fruitless dAB1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal abdominal segment, between the metathoracic segment and the abdominal segment. It arborizes in the dorsal anterior region of the metathoracic segment. One branch of the neurite leaves the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: adult fruitless aSG8 neuron
description: Neuron of the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell body is located on the gnathal ganglion. A neurite arborizes the ipsilateral gnathal ganglion.

label: subesophageal ganglion neuron
description: Neuron of the subesophageal ganglion.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt32
description: A lobula tangential neuron whose cell body is located lateral to the esophageal foramen. The cell body fiber runs posteriorly along the esophagus and turns upwards near the posterior end of the brain where it forms a Y-shaped branch. One branch runs laterally to project to the lobula, and the other crosses the midline to innervate the contralateral lobula. Along the trajectory towards the lobula, the fiber forms another collateral branch which innervates the posterior lateral protocerebrum. The main branch reaches the lobula and forms extensive tree-like arborizations with varicosities in lobula layers 5 and 6. There is only one neuron of this type per brain hemisphere.

label: adult fruitless aSG7 neuron
description: Neuron of the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell body is located on the gnathal ganglion. A neurite branches to arborize both hemispheres of the gnathal ganglion.

label: abdominal medial-most cell body glial cell
description: Medial-most cell body glia of the embryonic/larval abdominal hemineuromere. There is only one of these per hemineuromere.
synonyms: abdominal medial most cell body glial cell

label: embryonic abdomen
description: Abdomen of the embryo.

label: adult fruitless vPR9 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR9 lineage clone (FBbt:00111144).

label: adult fruitless vPR9 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located on the midline, immediately posterior to the prothoracic neuromere. A neurite projects dorsally.

label: thoracic medial-most cell body glial cell
description: Medial-most cell body glia of the embryonic/larval thoracic hemineuromere. There are two of these per hemineuromere.
synonyms: thoracic medial most cell body glial cell

label: thoracic medial-most cell body glial cell 1
description: Anterior-most of the two thoracic medial-most cell body glial cells.

label: adult fruitless vPR8 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR8 lineage clone (FBbt:00111142).

label: cell body rind of prothoracic neuromere
description: Region of the adult thoracico-abdominal ganglion cell body rind that overlies the prothoracic neuromere.

label: adult fruitless vPR8 lineage clone
