description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventromedial region of the prothoracic segment. A neurite projects dorsally and branches. The lateral branch projects to the anterior region of the prothoracic neuromere while the medial branch projects dorsally to the midline.

label: thoracic medial-most cell body glial cell 2
description: Posterior-most of the two thoracic medial-most cell body glial cells.

label: extra metathoracic nerve
description: A nerve that originates in the dorsal-most region of the metathoracic neuromere and that projects postero-laterally to the most posterior-lateral corner of the thorax, where it innervates transverse tubular muscles.

label: metathoracic nerve
description: Any nerve (FBbt:00005105) that is part of some metathoracic segment (FBbt:00000019).

label: first lateral abdominal nerve
description: Lateral-most of the two bilaterally paired nerves connected to the abdominal neuropile.

label: lobula columnar neuron LC12
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the anterior area of the lateral cell body rind. It has its main dendritic arbors in lobula layers 2 (excluding most distal part) and 4, with connecting processes and some branches in layer 3. It projects to the second most lateral of the ventral optic glomerulus of the PVLP, medial to LC17. There are around 208 cells of this type.

label: cell body rind of optic lobe
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the optic lobe. It includes the regions that overlie the lamina, medulla, lobula and lobula plate.

label: lobula columnar neuron LC13
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the ventral area of the lateral cell body rind. It has a complex multilayer pattern, with denser arbors in lobula layers 3 and 5B, and other arbors in layers 2, 4, 5A and 6. Presynaptic sites are observed in layers 3 and 4. It projects to a large, very posterior optic glomerulus of the PVLP, ventral to LC11. There are around 108 cells of this type.

label: lobula columnar neuron LC14
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body rind. It projects from the ipsilateral lobula, along the great commissure and contacts the surface of the contralateral lobula, but does not penetrate into any of its layers. Synaptic contacts are only observed in the lobula. There are 32-38 neurons in this group.

label: adult fruitless vPR6 (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR6 (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00111149).

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt12
description: A lobula tangential neuron whose cell body is located in the anterior area of the lateral cell body region. The cell body fiber bifurcates at the neck of the lobula. The branch towards the lobula arborizes at the posterior edge of the lobula and enters the neuropil in lobula layer 4. The branch towards the central brain projects along the lobula/lobula-plate bundle and terminates in the medial ventrolateral protocerebrum. There is only one neuron of this type per hemisphere.

label: lobula tangential neuron Lt31
description: A lobula tangential neuron whose cell body is located in the central brain cortex, posterior to the posterior lateral protocerebrum (plpr). The cell body fiber runs anteriorly through the plpr neuropil and bifurcates in the ventrolateral protocerebrum. The lateral branch makes a turn and runs ventroposterior towards the neck of the lobula. From there the neuron forms extensive tree-like branches in lobula layer 4. The medial branch makes a right-angle turn to run ventroposterior towards the posterior plpr. It forms terminals in the area that is close to the position of the cell body. There is only a single neuron in this class per hemisphere.

label: adult fruitless pSG1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located at the ventral midline. A neurite projects anteriorly and dorsally towards the anterior oesophageal foramen.

label: adult fruitless pMP6 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP6 lineage clone (FBbt:00111157).

label: adult fruitless pMP6 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located anterior to the protocerebral bridge. Neurites project ventrally through a tract posterior to the fan-shaped body and extends anteriorly towards region above the antennal lobe and in the anteriomedial protocerebrum. Arborizations are found in the bulb and in part of the superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum.

label: lobula columnar neuron LC9
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body is in the dorsal lateral cell body rind. It has its main dendritic arbors in lobula layers 3 and 5B, and other processes in layers 2 and 4. The arbors in layers 3 and 4 are mainly presynaptic. The axon of Lcn9 fasciculates in the anterior optic tract with Lcn6 and terminates in a dorsal and anterior glomeruli of the PVLP, medial to Lcn6. There are around 150 cells of this type.

label: adult fruitless aSG5 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSG5 lineage clone (FBbt:00111155).

label: adult fruitless aSG5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located lateral to the midline, ventral to the subesophageal zone. A neurite projects mostly ipsilaterally forming extensive networks in the subesophageal zone.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM3 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage (embryonic born) whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM3. Neurons of this class are born during the 17th and 19th divisions of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: lobula columnar neuron LC10
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body region. Its axon crosses ipsilaterally along the anterior optic tract, projecting to the anterior optic tubercle (AOTU). There are 2 main subtypes, which differ in how they project in the AOTU. For each subtype the relative order of the terminals along the dorsal/ventral axis of the AOTU matches the order along the anterior/posterior axis in the lobula.

label: cell body rind along the midline
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the midline. It includes the regions medio- anterior, dorsal and posterior to the superior medial protocerebrum (including the pars intercerebralis), medial to the crepine and antler.

label: lobula columnar neuron LC11
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron whose cell body lies in the dorsal area of the lateral cell body rind It has its main dendritic arbors in lobula layers 2 (excluding most distal part), 3, 4 and 5B (from recurrent branches). Presynaptic sites are observed in layers 4 and 5B. It projects to an elongated optic glomerulus in the PVLP, located in an intermediate position between the dorsal LC6 (Lcn6) and the ventral LC4 (Lcn4) glomeruli. There are around 68 cells of this type.

label: adult fruitless pMP1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111163).

label: adult fruitless pMP1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medial to the mushroom body calyx. Neurites project initially medially, then dorsally to form a fork at the pars intercerebralis. A lateral branch arborizes in the lateral junction. The ventral branch continues ventrally along the median bundle and descends into the thoracico-abdominal ganglion to terminate in the abdominal segment.

label: adult fruitless pSP5 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP5 lineage clone (FBbt:00111161).

label: adult fruitless pSP5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located lateral to the mushroom body calyx, ventral to the pSP4 lineage clone. A neurite projects medially, entering and crossing the tract containing the mushroom body pedunculus. The projection continues towards the lateral junction.

label: adult fruitless pSG1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111159).

label: embryonic/larval cholinergic antennal lobe projection neuron
description: An embryonic/larval antennal lobe projection neuron that is cholinergic. These neurons constitute about 50% of the embryonic/larval antennal lobe projection neurons that have an anterodorsally located soma (Python and Stocker, 2002).

label: adult fruitless vMS10 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventromedial region of the anterior mesothoracic segment. The neurite projects to the contralateral prothoracic neuromere.

label: adult fruitless vMS9 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS9 lineage clone (FBbt:00111126).

label: adult fruitless vMS9 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the mesothoracic segment. The neurite projects dorsally.

label: adult fruitless vMS8 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS8 lineage clone (FBbt:00111124).

label: adult fruitless vMS8 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites project dorsally and curves anteriorly. The projection pattern is highly variable between neurons of this clone.

label: adult fruitless vMS7 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS7 lineage clone (FBbt:00111122).

label: adult fruitless vMS7 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventroposterior region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites project dorsally and anteriorly to arborize locally in the mesothoracic neuromere. It is similar to the arborization pattern of the vAB1 lineage clone.

label: adult fruitless vMS6 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS6 lineage clone (FBbt:00111120).

label: adult fruitless vMS10 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMS10 lineage clone (FBbt:00111128).

label: adult fruitless vMT1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vMT1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111130).

label: adult fruitless vMT1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventrolateral region of the metathoracic segment. Neurites enter the neuropil close to the anterior region of the metathoracic neuromere and projects anteriorly.

label: adult fruitless vPR5 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR5 lineage clone (FBbt:00111138).

label: adult fruitless vPR5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventrolateral region of the prothoracic segment, very close to the soma of vPR4 lineage clone neurons. The neurite projects dorsally and arborizes in the anterior medial prothoracic neuromere.

label: adult fruitless vPR4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR4 lineage clone (FBbt:00111136).

label: adult fruitless vPR4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventrolateral region of the prothoracic segment. The neurite projects medially in the prothoracic neuromere. The arborization is located in the anterior prothoracic neuromere.

label: adult fruitless vPR3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111134).

label: adult fruitless vPR3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior region of the prothoracic segment. The neurite projects posteriorly in the prothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless vPR2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111132).

label: adult fruitless vPR2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior region of the prothoracic segment. The neurite enters the prothoracic neuromere and projects laterally, seeming to exit the thoracico-abdominal ganglion to innervate the foreleg.

label: adult fruitless vPR7 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR7 lineage clone (FBbt:00111140).

label: adult fruitless vPR7 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the posterior prothoracic segment, close to the midline. Neurites project dorsomedially towards the midline and form arborizations in the medial prothoracic neuromere.

label: adult glial cell
description: Glial cell that is part of the adult.

label: adult CNS glial cell
description: Glial cell that is part of the adult central nervous system.

label: abdominal 8 lateral transverse muscle
description: Any lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000472) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: abdominal 8 transverse muscle
description: Any transverse muscle (FBbt:00000470) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: abdominal 8 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: The only dorsal transverse muscle in larval abdominal segment 8.

label: transverse muscle
description: A hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature with a transverse orientation (i.e. perpendicular to the anterior-posterior axis of the body).

label: abdominal 8 ventral transverse muscle 2
description: The second anterior-most transverse muscle in larval abdominal segment 8, located close to abdominal 8 ventral transverse muscle 1.

label: abdominal 8 ventral transverse muscle
description: Any ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000473) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: abdominal 8 ventral transverse muscle 1
description: The anterior-most transverse muscle in larval abdominal segment 8, located close to the segment boundary with A7.

label: abdominal 8 lateral transverse muscle 1
description: The only lateral transverse muscle in larval abdominal segment 8.

label: abdominal 8 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000482) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: abdominal 8 longitudinal muscle
description: Any longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000480) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: longitudinal muscle
description: A longitudinally orientated hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature.

label: labral nerve
description: Nerve that is associated with the adult labrum or the larval anterior sense organs.

label: supraesophageal nerve
description: Nerve that is part of the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: adult labral nerve
description: The adult labral nerve supplies the labrum. It enters the brain at the level of the tritocerebrum. It is fused with the frontal nerve, forming a labro-frontal nerve.

label: labrum
description: A small, sclerotized, apically pointed flap, distal to the clypeus. It lies in a groove along the median region of the mediproboscis. The oral opening is behind and at the base of this flap.

label: anterior intercalating leading edge cell
description: Leading edge cell that originates in the anterior compartment in the second row of the dorsal epidermis during dorsal closure and which intercalates into the leading edge adjacent to the compartment boundary at the same time as the mixer cell crosses the segment boundary.

label: embryonic leading edge cell
description: Cell at the leading edge of the dorsal epidermis during dorsal closure.

label: posterior intercalating leading edge cell
description: Leading edge cell that originates in the posterior compartment in the second row of the dorsal epidermis during dorsal closure and which intercalates into the leading edge adjacent to the compartment boundary at the same time as the mixer cell crosses the segment boundary.

label: alimentary canal
description: The entire anatomical structure through which food and its digestion products are ingested, digested and excreted. At its anterior and posterior ends this includes structures that are not foregut or hindgut.

label: pupal/adult digestive system
description: Digestive system of the pupa or adult.

label: adult anal pad
description: Sclerotized 10th tergite plate flanking the adult anus (Ferris, 1950).

label: anal pad
description: Plate or plates that surrounds the anus.

label: adult hindgut
description: Posterior part of the of the adult alimentary canal, extending from the posterior end of the midgut, where the Malpighian tubules meet, to the rectum, including the rectal pouch and rectal papillae.

label: Kolbchen
description: Club-like sensory structure found in the thoracic segments of the embryo/larva.

label: abdominal 8 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle in larval abdominal segment 8.

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdominal 9
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00001756).

label: abdominal 8 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle in larval abdominal segment 8.

label: abdominal 8 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle in larval abdominal segment 8.

label: abdominal 8 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle in larval abdominal segment 8.

label: diverticulum of gut
description: Branch from the gut that forms a blind sac.

label: leading edge mixer cell
description: A leading edge cell that moves from the anterior compartment of one segment to the posterior compartment of the segment immediately anterior to it during dorsal closure. There is one of these per abdominal segment, initially located in the dorso-anterior corner of each anterior compartment at the dorsal-end of the groove that marks the segment boundary.

label: primary lobe of embryonic/larval lymph gland
description: Anterior-most and largest of the 3-6 lobe pairs of the third instar embryonic/larval lymph gland. These lobes are bulbous. Three distinct zones are identified: the medullary zone in the center, the cortical zone in the periphery and the posterior signaling center. At the late third instar the posterior signalling center functions as a stem-cell niche, the medullary zone contains quiescent prohemocytes, and the cortical zone the proliferating hemocytes (plasmatocytes) and procrystal and crystal cells.

label: cortical zone of lymph gland primary lobe
description: Peripheral region of the primary lobes of the lymph gland, consisting of differentiated hemocytes that proliferate extensively (plasmatocytes) and procrystal and crystal cells.
synonyms: cortical zone of anterior lymph gland pair

label: medullary zone of lymph gland primary lobe
description: Core region of the primary lobes of the lymph gland, consisting of undifferentiated hemocyte progenitors (prohemocytes). Prohemocytes become restricted to this region at late third instar stage.
synonyms: medullary zone of anterior lymph gland pair

label: anatomical structure
description: Material anatomical entity that has inherent 3D shape, whose parts are all connected and that is generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

label: gut section
description: A subdivision of the gut along its long axis.

label: fiber system
description: Area of the brain where fascicles from various directions meet and merge. They are largely or completely devoid of synapses.

label: superior antennal lobe commissure
description: Dorsal-most of two commissures connecting the antennal lobes and running in front of the ellipsoid body.

label: superior fiber system
description: The superior fiber system is a prominent fiber system in the superior brain. It lies superior-lateral to the fan-shaped body and anterior to the superior part of the medial antennal lobe tract. It demarcates the boundaries between the superior lateral protocerebrum (posterior-medial region), superior intermediate protocerebrum (posterior region), superior medial protocerebrum (posterior-lateral region) and superior clamp (superior-medial region).

label: vertical ventrolateral protocerebral fascicle
description: The vertical ventrolateral protocerebral fascicle emerges from cells in the lateral cell body region and terminates in the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label: medial equatorial fascicle
description: The medial equatorial fascicle is a thick fascicle that emerges from cells in the medial posterior rind region below the mushroom body calyx and branches out in the region inferior-lateral to the fan-shaped body. It demarcates the boundaries of the inferior bridge (lateral region), inferior clamp (superior-medial), superior posterior slope (superior region), gorget (superior region) and fan-shaped body (inferior-lateral region).

label: lateral equatorial fascicle
description: The lateral equatorial fascicle emerges from the lateral posterior rind region and ends in the inferiormost part of the inferior clamp. It runs lateral to the medial equatorial fascicle. It demarcates the boundaries of the inferior clamp (inferior-lateral region), posterior lateral protocerebrum (medial region), superior posterior slope (superior-lateral), and gorget (lateral region).

label: posterior cerebro-cervical fascicle
description: The posterior cerebro-cervical fascicle derives from the superior lateral part of the cervical connective and terminates in the inferior fiber system. It demarcates the boundaries of the superior slope (inferior region), inferior slope (superior region) and wedge (superior-medial). It contains the axon of the giant fiber neuron.

label: medial cerebro-cervical fascicle
description: The medial cerebro-cervical fascicle derives from the superior medial part of the cervical connective and ends in the medial part of the posterior gnathal ganglion.

label: anterior cerebro-cervical fascicle
description: The anterior cerebro-cervical fascicle derives from the inferior medial part of the cervical connective. It runs by the posterior maxillary sensory center (PMS) and converges to the inferior fiber system. It demarcates the boundary between the flange and saddle.

label: lateral cerebro-cervical fascicle
description: The lateral cerebro-cervical fascicle derives from the inferior lateral part of the cervical connective and projects towards the lateral surface of the saddle and wedge, demarcating their lateral boundaries.

label: insemination
description: The introduction of semen or sperm into the genital tract of a female.

label: multicellular organismal reproductive process
description: The process, occurring above the cellular level, that is pertinent to the reproductive function of a multicellular organism. This includes the integrated processes at the level of tissues and organs.
synonyms: reproductive process in a multicellular organism

label: terminal transverse muscle 1
description: Posterior-most transverse muscle of the larva. Its dorsal end attaches near the base of the posterior spiracle.

label: horizontal ventrolateral protocerebral fascicle
description: Emerging from cells located in the lateral cell body region, the horizontal ventrolateral protocerebral fascicle terminates in an area between the lateral accessory lobe, inferior clamp and epaulette. It contains fibers projecting towards the inferior and ventromedial neuropils. It demarcates the boundaries of the lateral accessory lobe (posterior region), inferior clamp (inferior region) and epaulette (superior region).

label: ventromedial neuropils
description: A group of synaptic neuropil domains in the adult brain located above or and lateral to the esophagus, below the mushroom body calyx and inferior neuropils, behind the lateral accessory lobe and medial to the ventrolateral neuropils.

label: terminal oblique muscle
description: Embryonic/larval oblique muscle whose posterior end is attached to the posterior integument and whose anterior is attached to the vertical-median septum of the A8/9 intersegmental apodeme (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 121).

label: oblique muscle
description: A hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal anterior muscle attachment site to a ventral posterior one.

label: pyriform fascicle
description: Tract emerging from the superior-most lateral area of the superior medial protocerebrum and ending in the region between the superior lateral protocerebrum and lateral horn of the adult brain. It demarcates the boundary between these two regions.

label: anterior superior lateral protocerebrum fascicle
description: Emerging from cells located in the lateral cell body region, the anterior superior lateral protocerebrum fascicle exhibits a J-shape and terminates in the boundary between the superior intermediate protocerebrum and the superior lateral protocerebrum (SLP) just posterior to the anterior optic tubercle of the adult brain. It demarcates the inferior boundary of the SLP with the superior intermediate protocerebrum, anterior and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum and superior clamp.

label: adult frontal nerve
description: The adult frontal nerve contains a variety of fibers, largely from interneurons, and connects the tritocerebrum and the frontal ganglion (an unpaired structure on the anterior side of the esophagus).

label: adult recurrent nerve
description: The adult recurrent nerve runs from the frontal ganglion posteriorly along the esophagus and foregut. It contains fibers of the enteric nervous system.

label: stomodeal nerve
description: Nerve arising from the corpus cardiacum (Rajashekhar and Singh, 1994), located along the dorsal surface of the esophagus. After it exits from the esophageal canal it loops ventrally and anastomoses with the pharyngeal nerve to form the recurrent nerve (Rajashekhar and Singh, 1994). It enters the tritocerebrum, ascends dorsally and arborizes near the midline.

label: pharyngeal nerve
description: The pharyngeal nerve of the adult brain is 7um thick and contains axons connecting with the lower, anterior half of the adult head capsule including sensory organs along the esophagus. It fuses with the accessory pharyngeal nerve at its exit from the gnathal ganglion, probably from the mandibular neuromere. After branching to the cibarial sense organ, it loops beneath cibarial muscle 9 near the cibarial-esophageal junction to anastomose medially with the stomodeal nerve and the contralateral pharyngeal nerve. From the region of these anastomoses a single median nerve extends ventrally and gives a number of branches to the dilator muscle of the cibarial pump (Miller, 1950).

label: labial nerve
description: Nerve that connects the adult labium or the larval head.

label: maxillary nerve
description: Nerve that connects to the maxillary appendages.

label: mandibular nerve
description: The mandibular nerve is a mixed sensory-motor nerve of the adult gnathal ganglion (GNG). It contains axons from the sensory cells of the mandibles entering the mandibular neuromere of the GNG and GNG motor axons to mandibular musculature.

label: response to extracellular stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an extracellular stimulus.

label: pupal ventral branch
description: Tracheal branch of the pupa that connects the two lateral trunks ventrally via a ventral anastomosis.

label: pupal trachea
description: Tracheae of the pupa. The basic framework (primary trachea) develop using the larval trachea of tracheal metameres 1-5 as a template (Whitten, 1957). But the new branches that develop from this basic framework are limited to the pupal and pharate adult stages have a distinct morphology. New pupal branches appear as many grape-like clusters of tracheoles lying free in the body cavity. Each cluster contains many fine tracheoles, with as many as 100 arising from a single point. Each tracheolar initially cell has a tightly coiled, snail-like tracheolar lumen that uncoils during the pupal period, extending towards and attaching to the developing pharate adult tissues.

label: pupal ventral anastomosis
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right ventral branches at the midline in the pupal tracheal system.

label: pupal lateral trunk
description: Pupal trachea that runs parallel and lateral to the dorsal trunk from tracheal metamere 5 to the T1 pupal spiracle.

label: pupal ventral branch 0
description: Most anterior of the 3 anastomosing ventral branches. Branches arising from this trachea tracheate the prothoracic neuromere and the developing prothoracic leg.

label: pupal ventral anastomosis 0
description: Tracheal node (anastomosis) connecting the left and right pupal ventral branch 0.

label: pupal ventral branch 1
description: Second most anterior (middle) of the 3 anastomosing ventral branches. Branches arising from this trachea tracheate the mesothoracic neuromere and the developing mesothoracic leg.

label: pupal ventral anastomosis 1
description: Tracheal node (anastomosis) connecting the left and right pupal ventral branch 1.

label: pupal ventral branch 2
description: Most posterior of the 3 anastomosing ventral branches. Branches arising from this trachea tracheate the metathoracic neuromere and the developing metathoracic leg.

label: tracheal metamere 2
description: The tracheal system of the metathoracic segment (T3).

label: pupal ventral anastomosis 2
description: Tracheal node (anastomosis) connecting the left and right pupal ventral branch 2.

label: hair plate of metathoracic trochanter
description: Hair plate found on the trochanter of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: hair plate of trochanter
description: Hair plate located on the trochanter of the adult leg.

label: metathoracic leg hair plate
description: Hair plate found on the adult metathoracic leg.

label: metathoracic trochanter
description: Segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the coxa and distally with the femur.

label: hair plate of prothoracic trochanter
description: Hair plate found on the trochanter of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: prothoracic leg hair plate
description: Hair plate located on the prothoracic leg.

label: glial cell of adult antennal nerve
description: Glial cell that is part of the adult antennal nerve.

label: cell body rind of ventral complex
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the ventral complex.

label: embryonic/larval ostial valve
description: Paired cardiomyocytes forming a valve around each ostium of the embryonic/larval dorsal that permits hemolymph to enter the heart for circulation.

label: anterior cardioblast
description: Cardioblast associated with the developing cardiac outflow muscles in the embryo and that develops into the cardiac outflow tract.

label: mesothoracic leg hair plate
description: Hair plate located on the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: hair plate
description: A cluster of short mechanosensory hairs usually situated near, and stimulated by, joints.

label: hair plate of mesothoracic coxa
description: Hair plate found on the coxa of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: hair plate of coxa
description: Hair plate located on the coxal segment of the adult leg.

label: hair plate of metathoracic coxa
description: Hair plate found on the coxa of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: metathoracic coxa
description: The coxa of the metathoracic leg.

label: hair plate of prothoracic coxa
description: Hair plate found on the coxa of the adult prothoracic leg.

label: hair plate of mesothoracic trochanter
description: Hair plate found on the trochanter of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: carboxylic acid transport
description: The directed movement of carboxylic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Carboxylic acids are organic acids containing one or more carboxyl (COOH) groups or anions (COO-).

label: organic anion transport
description: The directed movement of organic anions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Organic anions are atoms or small molecules with a negative charge which contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: cell periphery
description: The part of a cell encompassing the cell cortex, the plasma membrane, and any external encapsulating structures.

label: pedunculus neck of adult mushroom body
description: The proximal (posterior or posterior superior) point of the pedunculus at which Kenyon cell fibers converge beneath the calyx to form the pedunculus.

label: pedunculus divide of adult mushroom body
description: The anterior end of the pedunculus of the adult mushroom body, where the Kenyon cell fibers bifurcate to project to the vertical and medial lobes.

label: mushroom body lateral calyx
description: The lateral subregion of the main mushroom body calyx that contains two of the four neuroblast clones of Kenyon cells.

label: neuron projection
description: A prolongation or process extending from a nerve cell, e.g. an axon or dendrite.

label: neuron part
description: Any constituent part of a neuron, the basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. A typical neuron consists of a cell body (often called the soma), an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

label: mushroom body accessory calyx
description: A small subregion of the main mushroom body calyx that does not receive direct olfactory input. It protrudes from the anterior-dorsal edge of the main calyx into the superior lateral protocerebrum, above and anterior to the medial antennal lobe tract.

label: mushroom body medial calyx
description: The medial subregion of the main mushroom body calyx that contains two of the four neuroblast clones of Kenyon cells.

label: medulla dorsal rim area
description: Region of the dorsal medulla that receives input from the lamina dorsal rim area.

label: lamina dorsal rim area
description: Region of the dorsal lamina that receives input from the dorsal rim ommatidia.

label: corpus allatum
description: An unpaired neurosecretory organ forming part of the ring gland. In the embryo and larva, it is located on top of the dorsal vessel. In adults, it is found in front of the proventriculus.

label: mushroom body primordium
description: Embryonic structure from which the mushroom body is derived. The development of the mushroom body proceeds as follows: axonogenesis of embryonic Kenyon cells starts late in embryonic stage 14. The axons from these cells extend towards the lateral protocerebral tract (LTP). During stage 16, a second set of Kenyon cell fibers form a second tract, closely apposed to the first. By late stage 16, both tracts extend anteriorly beyond the LTP to form the distal part of the peduncle. These tracts make a sharp medial turn close to the boundary with the deutocerebrum to form the medial lobe. By late stage 17 the vertical lobe has emerged as a collateral outgrowth from the point where these tracts bend. Finally, the calyx forms near to the end of embryogenesis.

label: dendritic cap cell
description: Cell that envelopes a dendrite.

label: sperm derived structure
description: The sperm flagellum structures, which are composed of proteins and mitochondrial derivatives. They are observed in the embryo cytoplasm shortly after fertilization. By cellular blastoderm stage these structures are observed in the yolk cytoplasm where they remain until the formation of the embryonic digestive tract. After larval hatching they are observed in the midgut, and shortly after excreted through defecation.

label: dorsal pouch
description: Epidermal pouch in the head of the embryo or larva.

label: photoreceptor
description: A light sensitive sense organ.

label: Bolwig organ primordium
description: Primordium of the late extended and dorsal closure embryo that gives rise to the larval Bolwig organ. It corresponds to the most posterior region that develops from the visual primordium.

label: chiasma
description: A tract of crossing fibers, that remaps or systematically permutates the linear order between two neuropils. passing between neuropils on opposite sides of the nervous system, organized such that the linear order of axons on one side is reversed on the other.

label: myotube
description: Multinucleated muscle cell formed by several fusion events between fusion competent myoblasts and one founder cell. The size of a myotube is correlated to the number of fusion competent cells that fuse with a founder cell or developing myotube.

label: muscle cell
description: Somatic, contractile cell that makes up a muscle. It is formed  by several fusion events between fusion competent myoblasts and one founder cell.

label: muscle system
description: Comprising skeletal and visceral muscles, the muscle system consist of a multitude of contractile fibers arranged in groups and layers.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 4
description: Cholinergic neuron whose cell body is located in the dorsal-most area of the subesophageal ganglion, ventromedial to the antennal lobe of the adult brain. The cell body fiber ascends through the median bundle to the level of the gamma lobe before making a steep lateral turn and forming extensive axonal terminals in the crepine, superior medial protocerebrum and a few terminals in the superior intermediate protocerebrum. The main fiber further extends towards the vertical lobe and forms extensive dendrites in the alpha' lobe slice 2. There are 2 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 1
description: A neuron, whose cell body is located in front of the inferior neuropils, anterior to the middle part of the medial lobe of the adult brain. A neurite projects dorsolaterally and forms arborizations further in the inferior neuropils and within the superior neuropils. Some of these branches extend ventromedially and arborize in the medial-most segments of the gamma lobe and the beta-s and beta'-a strata. Some of the fibers further project to the contralateral medial lobes.

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 3
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster whose cell body is found on the inferior neuropils near the junction of the lobes. The cell body fiber arborizes in the inferior and superior neuropils. The main fiber runs medially towards the tip of the medial lobe. Before entering the beta lobe, fibers branch off to project to the opposite hemisphere. The axonal fibers entering the beta lobe arborize sparsely in the posterior and surface layers of the medial segment (Tanaka et al., 2008) and in the anterior layer of the beta' lobe medial segment (Aso et al., 2010). There are less than 3 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body medial-vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2
description: A glutamatergic neuron whose cell body is located in front of the ventral complex, ventral to the junction of the lobes in each adult brain hemisphere. The cell body fiber runs dorsomedially to the opposite hemisphere. It bifurcates behind the tip of the beta' lobe: one of the fibers runs ventrally and enters the medial-most part of the beta lobe arborizing all three slices; its axon runs dorsolaterally towards the tip region of the vertical lobe, with terminals found in the three alpha lobe slices and in the superior medial, intermediate and lateral protocerebrum. In the alpha lobe slice 3, the terminals are concentrated in the posterior and surface layers. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body pedunculus-medial lobe arborizing neuron 1
description: A neuron whose cell body is located on the inferior neuropils, lateral to the calyx of each adult brain hemisphere. The cell body fiber runs anteriormedially and diverges above the ellipsoid body, with most of the branches arborizing in the crepine, superior medial and lateral protocerebrum. Another fiber turns ventromedially and projects to the opposite hemisphere. A third fiber turns ventrolaterally, runs in front of the anterior surface of the gamma lobe and then below the gamma lobe, and arborizes in the spur of the gamma lobe (slice 1) and inner core of the pedunculus. It is a dopaminergic neuron of the PPL1 cluster. There are 1-2 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body pedunculus-vertical lobe arborizing neuron 1
description: A neuron, which is part of a cluster of at least two neurons, whose cell body is located on the inferior neuropils, near the junction of the mushroom body lobes of each adult brain hemisphere. The cell body fiber bifurcates near the vertical lobe. One of these fibers turns ventromedially to the tip of the medial lobe, whereas the other runs dorsally. The ventromedially directed branch innervates the medial lobe through the border between the gamma and beta' lobes. One branch runs medially to the opposite medial lobe whereas the other runs laterally to the basal segments of the alpha lobe and the inner core of the pedunculus. From the alpha lobe, one branch runs dorsally, turns dorsolaterally behind the alpha lobe and terminates in the posterior of the superior neuropils where it arborizes and further spreads laterally to the anterior dorsal superior lateral protocerebrum and the inferior neuropils.

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 6
description: A bilateral neuron whose cell body is located on the superior neuropils, anterior to the pars intercerebralis of the adult brain. The cell body fiber travels ventrally towards the medial lobe, arborizing in the anterior layer of beta' lobe slice 2 and running along the anterior surface of the gamma lobe, turning medially at the bottom of the gamma lobe and forming a terminal in the most medial segment of the gamma lobe (slice 5). The main fiber then enters the opposite gamma lobe, arborizes in the beta' lobe slice 2 and gamma lobe slice 5. The major axon projects ipsilaterally to the superior medial protocerebrum, whereas a very thin axon projects to the CRE and SMP in the other hemisphere. There is one neuron of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 3
description: cholinergic neuron whose cell body is located in the dorsal-most area of the subesophageal ganglion, ventromedial to the antennal lobe of the adult brain. The cell body fiber ascends through the median bundle to the level of the gamma lobe, and then projects towards the tip of the alpha lobe (slice 3) where it forms a dense arborization, with sparse terminals in the superiormedial protocerebrum. On the way to the alpha lobe, the axon branches off forming terminals in the superior medial, intermediate and lateral protocerebrum. There are 2 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: haltere disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells of larval haltere imaginal disc.

label: imaginal disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells of a larval imaginal disc.

label: eye-antenna disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells of larval eye-antennal imaginal disc.

label: terminal epithelium of testis
description: A columnar epithelium inside the testis basal lamina in the terminal (basal) 10% of the testis.

label: dense body
description: Synaptic ribbon at a neuromuscular junction.

label: neuromuscular junction
description: Region of the peripheral nervous system where a motor neuron axon makes synaptic contacts on a target muscle.

label: CNS-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells of the central nervous system.

label: cultured cell-line
description: Somatic cell that originates from a cell-line that is being cultured in vitro, under controlled conditions.

label: terminal epithelial cell of testis
description: Epithelial cell of the terminal epithelium of the testis. These cells engulf the head cyst cell of a spermatid cyst during coiling, so anchoring the head of the coiling spermatid. These cells also phagocytose the waste bags and cyst cells left over at the end of spermatogenesis.

label: embryonic outer optic lobe primordium
description: Primordium of the late extended germ band and closure embryo that gives rise to the larval outer optic anlage. It develops from the posterior lip of the visual primordium.

label: antenna disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells of posterior portion of the larval eye-antennal imaginal disc.

label: adult neuromuscular junction
description: Any neuromuscular junction (FBbt:00005142) that is part of some adult peripheral nervous system (FBbt:00005892).

label: embryonic head sensory system
description: Sensory system of the embryonic head.

label: embryonic sensory system
description: Sensory system of the embryo.

label: adult peritrophic membrane
description: Peritrophic membrane of the adult.

label: peritrophic membrane
description: Non-cellular matrix composed of chitin and glycoprotein secreted into the lumen of the proventriculus (cardia), between the outer and intermediate layers by a group of cells in the anterior proventriculus. It covers the luminal side of the midgut posterior to the proventriculus, separating the midgut epithelial cells from the gut contents. It can be divided into 4 distinct layers in the proventriculus and 2 layers in the midgut.

label: mushroom body medial lobelet
description: Protrusions in the beta accessory calyx layer (posterior, beta-p) in the medial lobe, formed by the fibers of the alpha/beta posterior Kenyon cells.
synonyms: mushroom body beta accessory calyx fibers

label: mushroom body beta lobe posterior layer
description: Posterior-most layer of the mushroom body beta lobe.
synonyms: mushroom body beta lobe posterior stratum

label: mushroom body vertical lobelet
description: Protrusions in the alpha accessory calyx layer (posterior, alpha-p) in the vertical lobe, formed by the fibers of the alpha/beta posterior Kenyon cells.
synonyms: mushroom body alpha accessory calyx fibers

label: mushroom body alpha lobe posterior layer
description: Posterior-most layer of the mushroom body alpha lobe.

label: posterior tentorial pit
description: Paired tentorial pit at the back of the head capsule, at the boundary between the post-gena and the tentorial bridge.

label: tentorial pit
description: Paired depression of the head capsule corresponding to an articulation of the tentorial bar (arm). There is an anterior and posterior tentorial pit.

label: gamma-aminobutyric acid transport
description: The directed movement of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA, 4-aminobutyrate), an amino acid which acts as a neurotransmitter in some organisms, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: amino acid transport
description: The directed movement of amino acids, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: monocarboxylic acid transport
description: The directed movement of monocarboxylic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: anterior tentorial pit
description: Lateral paired tentorial pit ventral to the eye, at the boundary between the head capsule and the mouthparts.

label: presumptive ocellus
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the ocelli.

label: ocellar triangle
description: Region of the integument of the dorsal postfrons in the adult head where the ocelli are located. The cuticle is smooth, in contrast to the rest of the postfrons.

label: imaginal precursor
description: Structure that proliferates to produce a larval imaginal disc and which gives rise to adult tissues (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

label: posterior tentorial bar
description: Bar across the ventral base of the occipital foramen.

label: adult tentorium
description: Internal sclerite of the adult head, ventral to the occipital foramen. On each side, it is fused with the head wall for some distance, and then becomes free, extending down to the anterior tentorial pit. It is formed by inward growths of the epidermis. The tentorium provides many of the apodemes for cervical muscles, called tentorial pits.

label: head capsule
description: The fused, compact cephalic plates that comprise the head, excluding the eyes, antennae and mouthparts.

label: type I bouton
description: Bouton that displays the largest presynaptic swellings. There are two subtypes, one with bigger boutons (type Ib) and another with smaller (type Is). Type I boutons are glutamatergic.

label: NMJ bouton
description: Any bouton (FBbt:00005116) that is part of some neuromuscular junction (FBbt:00005142).

label: medial ocellus
description: Medial ocellus located on the ocellar triangle of the dorsal postfrons of the adult head, just anterior to, and in between the two medial ocelli. It has around 100 photoreceptors.

label: lateral ocellus
description: Lateral ocellus located on the ocellar triangle of the dorsal postfrons of the adult head, medial to the interocellar bristles. There are two of these, each one with around 75 photoreceptors.

label: eye equator
description: Line on the dorsoventral midline of the adult eye that separates the dorsal and ventral ommatidia, forming a line of mirror image symmetry.

label: embryonic/larval neuromuscular junction
description: Any neuromuscular junction (FBbt:00005142) that is part of some embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system (FBbt:00005893).

label: bouton
description: A swelling specialized for the release of neurotransmitter that most commonly occurs along, or at the end of an axon.

label: early-mid elongation-stage spermatid
description: An elongating spermatid, 200-500 micrometers in length and in which nuclear shaping has begun. The two parts of the mitochondrial derivative become unequal in size.

label: Pad5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: dorsal anterior protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the dorsal region of the anterior protocerebrum.

label: second segment of antenna
description: Second segment of the antenna located ventrolaterally to the first segment. It is larger than the first segment and somewhat swollen. It has on average 25 bristles of various sizes. The Johnston's organ is contained in this segment.

label: presumptive second segment of antenna
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the second segment of antenna.

label: first segment of antenna
description: Proximal-most segment of the antenna. It is a narrow ring which bears on its dorsal side a medial group of four and a single lateral bristle. Its pigmentation and hair pattern are similar to those of the prefrons.

label: presumptive first segment of antenna
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the first segment of antenna.

label: Pad6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: Pad3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: fourth segment of antenna
description: A small ring at the base of the 5th segment, where it attaches to the 3rd segment.

label: basal cylinder
description: The adult antennal segments basal to the arista. It includes antennal segments 4 and 5.

label: Pad4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: presumptive third segment of antenna
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the third segment of the antenna.

label: Pad1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: head cyst cell
description: The member of a cyst cell pair that envelopes the head of a developing spermatid.

label: spermatid cyst cell
description: Cyst cell of a spermatid cyst.

label: Pad2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: type II bouton
description: Bouton that displays the smallest presynaptic swellings. The terminals bearing them are very long and the most elaborate of all axon terminal types. In the larva, these boutons contain glutamate and octopamine; in the adult some type II boutons contain the latter.

label: type III bouton
description: Bouton that displays medium size presynaptic swellings. In the larva, these boutons contain an insulin-like peptide.

label: adult external head
description: External structures that are part of the adult head.

label: apolar primary spermatocyte cyst cell
description: A cyst cell which is part of an apolar spermatocyte cyst.

label: spermatocyte cyst cell
description: A cyst cell which is part of a spermatocyte cyst.

label: polar primary spermatocyte cyst cell
description: A cyst cell which is part of a polar spermatocyte cyst.

label: mature primary spermatocyte cyst cell
description: A cyst cell which is part of a mature spermatocyte cyst.

label: late elongation-stage spermatid
description: A nearly fully elongated spermatid bigger than 1.2 mm length, with a needle-shaped nucleus.

label: mid-late elongation-stage spermatid
description: An elongating spermatid 0.8-1.2 mm in length, with a nucleus resembling a canoe.

label: organism subdivision
description: Anatomical structure that is a primary subdivision of whole organism. The mereological sum of these is the whole organism.

label: fifth segment of antenna
description: Segment of the antenna at the base of the arista.

label: Pad7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: Pad8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: presumptive arista
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the arista.

label: tail cyst cell
description: The member of a cyst cell pair that envelopes the tail of a developing spermatid. During spermatid elongation, tail cyst cells become very long and thin as they extend to cover the growing sperm flagellum.

label: Pad9 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 9 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: Pad16 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 16 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: prestomal cavity
description: Oral opening at the distal end of the labrum, which is surrounded by the discal sclerite.

label: discal sclerite
description: Horse-shoe shaped sclerite on the distal end of the labrum, bordering the oral opening.

label: presumptive discal sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the discal sclerite.

label: Pad17 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 17 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: embryonic dorsal pouch
description: Epidermal pouch in the embryonic head that incorporates the acron and dorsal regions of the head segments. It forms following the movement of the dorsal fold over the clypeolabrum and procephalic lobe.

label: anion transport
description: The directed movement of anions, atoms or small molecules with a net negative charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: Pad14 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 14 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: cibarial plate
description: One of the two sclerotized plates of the cibarium.

label: adult cibarium
description: The proximal portion of the adult pharynx, which functions as a sucking pump. It consists of two arched sclerotized plates. The posterior plate is fixed in position by its connections with the clypeus. The anterior plate fits against the concave side of the posterior plate and bears a ridge shaped apodeme (apodemal carina) that is attached to large dilator muscles that attach to clypeus. Their contraction pulls the anterior plate forward, enlarging the cibarial lumen and thus producing suction.

label: Pad15 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 15 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: adult pharynx
description: Anterior-most portion of the adult foregut, extending from the opening of the labrum to the esophagus. The posterior of the pharynx is the cibarium. The anterior portion is the labral channel, the posterior wall of which is the epipharynx and the anterior wall of which is the hypopharynx. The salivary duct connects to the pharynx just anterior to the cibarium.

label: basiproboscis
description: The most proximal region of the proboscis, contiguous to the mediproboscis. It contains the cibarial pump and clypeus, among other structures.

label: Pad12 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 12 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: clypeus
description: The anterior part of the head between the frons and the labrum, which occasionally may fuse with either one to form the frontoclypeus and the clypeolabrum. In the context of Drosophila refers to a round structure on the center of the frontal adult external head.

label: Pad13 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 13 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: mouthpart
description: Structure that is part of the adult mouth. It includes the clypeus, labrum, lacinia (maxillary lobe) and labellum.

label: anterior labial plate
description: Elongated plate of variable sclerotization in the dorsal or anterior surface of the mediproboscis, distal to the labrum.

label: presumptive anterior labial plate
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the anterior labial plate.

label: Pad10 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 10 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: Pad11 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 11 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: posterior plate of cibarium
description: Fixed, arched, sclerotized plate on the posterior side of the cibarium. It is attached to the clypeus.

label: anterior plate of cibarium
description: Mobile, arched, sclerotized plate on the anterior side of the cibarium. It bears a ridge shaped apodeme (apodemal carina) that is attached to large dilator muscles that attach to clypeus.

label: Pad18 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 18 of the dorsal anterior protocerebrum.

label: Pcd5 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 5 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: lacinia
description: Paired inner lobate structures with fringed borders, sitting on the apical margin of the basiproboscis, medial to the base of the maxillary palps. It is continuous with the maxillary apodeme (or cardio-stipital element of lacinia) that extends into the head cavity.

label: maxillary apodeme
description: Very small and sclerotized apodeme of the basiproboscis, in the adult maxillary segment. It is T-shaped, and extends into the head cavity like the handle of a dagger, being continuous with the external lacinia (or maxillary lobe). Distinct anterior, dorsal and ventral arms can be recognized. The muscles that move the maxilla are inserted into this apodeme, including the maxillary muscle 4.

label: proboscis
description: The trunk-like extension of adult head, forming a protrusible sucking proboscis for the ingestion of liquid food (pg 425 Miller et al., 1950; pg 383, Ferris et al., 1950).

label: Pcd6 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 6 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: Pcd3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: ventral arm of lacinia
description: Long and slender ventral arm of the sclerotized T-shaped maxillary apodeme.

label: Pcd4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: anterior arm of lacinia
description: Long and slender anterior arm of the sclerotized T-shaped maxillary apodeme.

label: Pcd1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 1 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: Pcd2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: labellum
description: The broadened, cushion-like, apical part of the rostral mouth parts. It consists of two regions; its lateral surface has a hemispherical, on which there are approximately 33-34 gustatory (chemosensory) and two mechanosensory bristles. The gustatory bristles are arranged into three ill-defined rows of 10-11 bristles: two medial and one located peripherally. The mechanosensory bristles are located in the most dorsolateral area of the labella surface and are shorter than the gustatory sensilla. The inner (medial) surface bears a series of open collecting channels, the pseudotrachea, that converge medially and conduct food to the tip of the labrum. Taste pegs are present in between the pseudotrachea, with 30-40 on each side.

label: distiproboscis
description: The most distal region of the proboscis, contiguous to the mediproboscis. It contains the labellum.

label: prementum
description: Rectangular sclerotized plate which is present in the posterior region of the mediproboscis. It contains about 11 large bristles placed in a characteristic pattern.

label: presumptive prementum
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the prementum.

label: mediproboscis
description: Cylindrical membranous tube that is the medial part of the proboscis, located between the basi- and distiproboscis. It contains the labrum and prementum, among other structures.

label: Pav1 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the ventral anterior protocerebrum.

label: ventral anterior protocerebral neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the ventral region of the anterior protocerebrum.

label: presumptive labellar cap
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the labellar cap.

label: adult fat body
description: Fat body of the adult.

label: fat body
description: Collective term for the masses and sheets of adipose tissue that are distributed throughout the organism's body.

label: adult adipose system
description: Adipose system of the adult.

label: adipose system
description: The system of organs and cells involved in fat storage.

label: dorsal arm of lacinia
description: Long and slender dorsal arm of the sclerotized T-shaped maxillary apodeme.

label: Pcd8 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 8 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: Ppd2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the posterior dorsal protocerebrum.

label: peripheral adult fat mass
description: Component part of the adult fat body that is found in sheets beneath the body wall (Bate, 1993).

label: presumptive mediproboscis
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the mediproboscis.

label: Pcd7 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 7 of the dorsal central protocerebrum.

label: Pcd9 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 9 of the central dorsal protocerebrum.

label: corpus cardiacum
description: Unpaired neuroendocrine structure that forms part of the ring gland. In the embryo and larva it is found around the floor of the aorta. In adults, it is found anterior to the proventriculus.

label: adult endocrine system
description: Endocrine system of the adult.

label: salivary stylet
description: Papilla located just posterior to the oral opening that bears the opening of the adult salivary duct at its apex.

label: presumptive maxillary palpus
description: Region of the anterior antennal disc that will develop into the maxillary palpus.

label: adult muscle system
description: Muscle system of the adult.

label: cervical sclerite
description: A small sclerite of the neck. There are 2 pairs, located laterally on either side of the neck. The anterior plate is extremely small and partially fused to the posterior plate. Anteriorly it articulates with the head, and posteriorly with the prothoracic episternum.

label: neck
description: Structure connecting the head to the body, through which the esophagus, cervical connective, two salivary gland ducts, two tracheal trunks and two stomodeal nerves pass.

label: pericardial adult fat mass
description: Dense layer of adult fat body that surrounds the pericardial septum, which covers the heart chamber in the first abdominal segment.

label: adult heart chamber 1
description: First, anterior-most chamber of the adult heart. It is funnel-shaped, widening to 120um anteriorly at its junction with the expanded end of the aorta, and is located in abdominal segments 1 and 2. This chamber develops during the last day of pupal stage.

label: adult maxillary structure
description: Structure of the adult maxillary segment.

label: deep adult fat mass
description: Part of the fat body that is found in the body cavity of the adults, and it derives largely from larval cells surviving through the pupal stage. It degenerates a few days post-eclosion (Bate, 1993).

label: Ppd3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the posterior dorsal protocerebrum.

label: abdominal adult fat mass
description: Fat body of the adult abdomen.

label: mentum
description: The distal part of the labium originally paired, secondarily fused into one broad plate bearing on its apical margin usually a prementum, and the paired appendages of the labial palp, the glossa and the paraglossa. In the context of Drosophila refers to the adult maxillary structures.

label: embryonic precursor cell of adult muscle
description: Cell persisting from the embryonic stage that contributes to the adult musculature. During metamorphosis, myoblasts aggregate and fuse together to form the adult muscle either on the remnants of larval muscles or independently on the newly forming adult epidermis (Bate, 1993).

label: Fell hair
description: Darkly pigmented and straight hair found dorsally on the base of the stigmatophore. There are around 7 rows of hairs, that densely cover this area.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 8 sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: stigmatophore
description: External protrusion of the integument at the posterior terminal of the larva that houses the posterior spiracles. When the larva is buried in the semi-liquid medium where it feeds, the stigmatophore periscopes out of the medium, allowing the larva to continue breathing.

label: eye photoreceptor cell stalk
description: Apically located membrane that supports the eye photoreceptor rhabdomere.

label: Pcd10 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 10 of the central dorsal protocerebrum.

label: adepithelial cell of clypeo-labral disc
description: Any adepithelial cell (FBbt:00003219) that connected to some clypeo-labral disc (FBbt:00001765).

label: Pcd11 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 11 of the central dorsal protocerebrum.

label: adepithelial cell of labial disc
description: Any adepithelial cell (FBbt:00003219) that connected to some labial disc (FBbt:00001764).

label: adepithelial cell of haltere disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the haltere imaginal disc.
synonyms: adepithelial cell of dorsal metathoracic disc

label: adult external prothorax
description: The first thoracic segment of the adult external thorax.

label: adepithelial cell of mesothoracic leg disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the mesothoracic leg imaginal disc.
synonyms: adepithelial cell of ventral mesothoracic disc

label: sternum
description: In the general sense, the ventral half of a body segment, more specifically, the underside of the thorax in insects that may be a unified whole or may comprise several parts.

label: photoreceptor cell R5 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R5 (FBbt:00004221).

label: adepithelial cell of genital disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the genital imaginal disc.

label: photoreceptor cell R6 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R6 (FBbt:00004223).

label: adepithelial cell of metathoracic leg disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the metathoracic leg imaginal disc.
synonyms: adepithelial cell of ventral metathoracic disc

label: dorsal prothorax
description: Dorsal region of the adult external prothorax.

label: humeral disc
description: Dorsal imaginal disc of the prothoracic segment that is the precursor of structures of the adult dorsal prothorax including the humerus.

label: photoreceptor cell R3 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R3 (FBbt:00004217).

label: adepithelial cell of dorsal prothoracic disc
description: Any adepithelial cell (FBbt:00003219) that connected to some humeral disc (FBbt:00001777).

label: photoreceptor cell R4 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R4 (FBbt:00004219).

label: adepithelial cell of eye-antennal disc
description: Any adepithelial cell (FBbt:00003219) that connected to some eye-antennal disc (FBbt:00001766).

label: eye-antennal disc
description: Imaginal disc that, in the adults, gives rise to the eye, antenna, head capsule (including all bristles and external membranes) and the maxillary palps (Cohen, 1993).

label: adepithelial cell of wing disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the wing imaginal disc.
synonyms: adepithelial cell of dorsal mesothoracic disc

label: photoreceptor cell R1 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R1 (FBbt:00004213).

label: photoreceptor cell R2 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R2 (FBbt:00004215).

label: adepithelial cell of prothoracic leg disc
description: Adepithelial cell associated with the prothoracic leg imaginal disc.
synonyms: adepithelial cell of ventral prothoracic disc

label: adepithelial cell of female genital disc
description: Any adepithelial cell of genital disc (FBbt:00003229) that connected to some female genital disc (FBbt:00001787).

label: pronotum
description: Sclerite that is at the anterior end of the adult dorsal thorax, closely fused with the mesonotum.

label: prothoracic tergum
description: Tergum that covers the adult prothoracic segment.

label: Pcv2 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 2 of the central ventral protocerebrum.

label: photoreceptor cell R8 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R8 (FBbt:00004227).

label: myoblast
description: Muscle progenitor cell.

label: embryonic primordium of adult muscle precursor
description: Primordium of the late extended germ band and dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the embryonic precursor of the adult muscle.

label: adepithelial cell of male genital disc
description: Any adepithelial cell of genital disc (FBbt:00003229) that connected to some male genital disc (FBbt:00001785).

label: humerus
description: Sclerite that sits on the anterolateral margin of the prothorax.

label: photoreceptor cell R7 stalk
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell stalk (FBbt:00005883) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R7 (FBbt:00004225).

label: photoreceptor cell R7
description: Inner photoreceptor cell of the ommatidium whose centrally located rhabdomere extends across the distal two thirds (approximately) of each ommatidium. Each has a single axon that extends through a single lamina optic cartridge without making synapses. This axon crosses the first optic chiasm and extends through a single column of the medulla where it makes pre-synaptic contacts, mainly with medulla layers M1 and M5 (Takemura et al., 2008) before terminating in M6. It also receives synaptic input from photoreceptor cell R8 (Takemura et al., 2008, 2013), mostly in M3, and is presynaptic to Dm8a (in M6). Its subtype, photoreceptor cell R7 of yellow ommatidium is also presynaptic to Tm5a (yellow ommatidium) and Tm5b (Gao et al., 2008; Karuppudurai et al., 2014).

label: abdominal 3 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 3

label: abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: An adult muscle precursor cell found in embryonic abdominal segments A1-7 that is located in the dorsal-most cluster of abdominal adult muscle precursors. This cluster begins life as a single cell associated with the intersegmental nerve (Bate et al., 1991) and connected to abdominal adult muscle precursor cells in the same segment by filopodia (Figeac et al., 2010). The cluster remains associated with this nerve through most of development, but migrates to the epidermal histoblast nests where muscle formation is initiated during metamorphosis (Bate, 1993).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal

label: prothoracic sternum
description: A sclerite, lacking bristles, that is located adjacent to the prothoracic coxa, episternum and epimeron. It develops from the prothoracic leg disc.

label: presumptive prothoracic structures from prothoracic leg disc
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic episternum, sternum, epimeron, the sensillum trichodeum of cervical membrane of prothoracic leg, the ball of the proximal joint of prothoracic coxa.

label: ventral prothorax
description: Ventral region of the adult external prothorax.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 2

label: prothoracic epimeron
description: A sclerite, lacking bristles, that is located posterior to the episternum and adjacent to the prothoracic coxa and sternum. It develops from the prothoracic leg disc.

label: prothoracic pleurum
description: Pleurum of the adult prothoracic segment.

label: dorsal cluster neuron
description: A neuron that is part of a cluster of atonal expressing neurons whose cell bodies are located dorsally in the cortex of the adult brain between the optic lobe and the central brain. It innervates the ipsilateral lobula, forming dense, dendrite-like trees, and projects to the contralateral hemisphere via a supraesophageal commissure to innervate the lobula. A third of DCN neurons also extend their axons into the contralateral medulla. The DCN cluster contains around 40 neurons.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 4

label: ventral lobula cluster neuron
description: A neuron that is part of a cluster of atonal expressing neurons whose cell bodies are located ventrally in the lobula of the adult brain. It densely innervates the ventral lobula and extends towards the medulla.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 1

label: prothoracic preepisternum
description: Anterior and major portion of the thoracic episternum.

label: prothoracic episternum
description: A sclerite, lacking bristles, that is located anterior to the epimerom and adjacent to the prothoracic coxa and sternum. It develops from the prothoracic leg disc.

label: Pcv3 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 3 of the central ventral protocerebrum.

label: Pcv4 neuroblast
description: Neuroblast 4 of the central ventral protocerebrum.

label: abdominal 6 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 6

label: prothoracic leg foramen
description: Foramen of the prothoracic segment from which the prothoracic leg articulates.

label: abdominal 5 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 5

label: prothoracic postcoxal bridge
description: Plate that connects the posterior region of the adult prothoracic coxa and the mesothoracic preepisternum.

label: abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: An adult muscle precursor cell found in embryonic abdominal segments A1-7 that is located in a lateral cluster of abdominal adult muscle precursors. This cluster begins life as a pair of cells associated with a posterior branch of the segmental nerve that innervates the segment border muscle (muscle 8) (Bate et al., 1991) and connected to abdominal adult muscle precursor cells in the same segment by filopodia (Figeac et al., 2010). The cluster remains associated with this nerve through most of development, but migrates to the epidermal histoblast nests where muscle formation is initiated during metamorphosis (Bate, 1993).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal

label: prothoracic furca
description: Forked paired apophysis of the adult prothorax. It arises from the sternal plates, supported on a median inflection of the sternum.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal dorsal adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003235) that is part of some abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028).
synonyms: dorsal adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 7

label: prescutal suture
description: Suture that forms the boundary between the prescutum and the humerus.

label: furcasternum
description: Sclerite of the ventral adult prothorax that is located over the midline, posterior to the prothoracic preepisternum.

label: abdominal 6 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 6
