label: abdominal 5 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 5

label: dorsal mesothorax
description: Dorsal region of the adult external mesothorax.

label: adult external mesothorax
description: The second thoracic segment of the adult external thorax.

label: abdominal 2 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 2

label: prothoracic phragma
description: Phragma found on the posterior margin of the adult pronotum.

label: abdominal 1 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 1

label: prothoracic pleural apophysis
description: Apophysis that arises from the pleural fold in the adult subcoxal region of the prothorax. It extends into the body and fuses with the arms of the mesofurca.

label: abdominal 4 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 4

label: abdominal 3 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 3

label: prothoracic articulation
description: Articulation of the prothoracic coxa with the adult ventral prothorax.

label: abdominal 1 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 1

label: abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: An adult muscle precursor cell found in embryonic abdominal segments A1-7 that is located in a ventral cluster of abdominal adult muscle precursors. This cluster begins life as a single cell associated with the ventral branch of the segmental nerve (Bate et al., 1991) and connected to abdominal adult muscle precursor cells in the same segment by filopodia (Figeac et al., 2010). The cluster remains associated with this nerve through most of development, but migrates to the epidermal histoblast nests where muscle formation is initiated during metamorphosis (Bate, 1993).

label: scutum
description: The part of the mesothoracic tergum between the intrascutal suture (FBbt:00004602) and the scutoscutellar suture (FBbt:00004602).

label: presumptive scutum
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the scutum.

label: prescutum
description: The anterior part of the mesothoracic tergum, partially separated from the scutum by the intrascutal suture and separated from the humerus by the prescutal suture (FBbt:00004573).

label: presumptive prescutum
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the prescutum.

label: abdominal 3 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 3

label: anterior notal wing process
description: Anteriorly located process of the scutum that extends to into the wing hinge where it articulates with the 1st axillary sclerite. It bares a cluster of 3 campaniform sensilla.

label: notal wing process
description: A sclerotized process that projects from mesothoracic tergum into the wing hinge where it articulates with axillary sclerites.

label: presumptive anterior notal wing process
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the anterior notal wing process.

label: abdominal 2 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 2

label: abdominal 7 lateral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal lateral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003243) that is part of some abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028).
synonyms: lateral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 7

label: trident
description: Region of mesothoracic tergum defined by a trident-shaped pattern of dark pigmentation.

label: abdominal 5 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 5

label: scutellum
description: A small shield-like plate at the posterior of the mesothoracic tergum. Its posterior boundary is the scutoscutellar suture (FBbt:00004602).

label: presumptive scutellum
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the scutellum.

label: abdominal 4 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 4

label: posterior notal wing process
description: Posteriorly located process of the scutum that extends to into the wing hinge where it articulates with the 1st and 4th axillary sclerites.

label: presumptive posterior notal wing process
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the posterior notal wing process.

label: adult fruitless dAB2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dAB2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111088).

label: adult fruitless dAB2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal abdominal segment. It projects anteriorly along the midline, forming arbors in the pro- and mesothoracic segments, close to the terminals of the leg sensory afferents. It also arborizes in the brain.

label: abdominal 7 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 7

label: mesothoracic laterotergite
description: Sclerite of the lateral adult mesothorax, that is lateral to the postnotum.

label: abdominal 6 ventral adult muscle precursor cell
description: Any abdominal ventral adult muscle precursor cell (FBbt:00003251) that is part of some abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027).
synonyms: ventral adult muscle precursor cluster abdominal 6

label: postnotum
description: The most posterior part of the mesothoracic tergum. It lies partially under the scutellum with just a small crescent tergite posterior to the scutellum visible from above. It forms a deep phragma (FBbt:00004480) that projects into the thorax (Ferris, 1950).

label: presumptive postnotum
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the postnotum.

label: adult fruitless dAB3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal abdominal segment, between the metathoracic and the abdominal segments. Bilateral dendritic arborizations are located in the dorsal anterior region of the metathoracic segment, with axon terminals found in the dorsal abdominal segment.

label: adult fruitless dMS4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region between the mesothoracic and metathoracic segments. A neurite enters the neuropil laterally and projects anteriorly.

label: proboscis muscle 2
description: Muscle involved in proboscis retraction. It is connected to the maxillary apodeme and is shorter than proboscis muscle 1.

label: proboscis muscle
description: Muscle involved in the retraction of the proboscis (muscle 1 and 2), or that acts as a proboscis flexor (muscle 3).

label: katepimeron
description: Ventral part of the thoracic epimeron. Part of this sclerite develops from the mesothoracic leg disc and part from the metathoracic leg disc.

label: presumptive mesothoracic structures from mesothoracic leg disc
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic episternum (katepisternum or sternopleurite), epimeron (katepimeron or hypopleurite) and the katepisternal bristles.

label: mesothoracic epimeron
description: The posterior part of the pleura in the mesothoracic segment of the adult thorax. It is divided transversely by the transepimeral suture into an upper part, the anepimeron (pteropleuron) and a lower part, the katepimeron (barrete). The mesothoracic epimeron is separated from the anterior mesothoracic episternum by the pleural suture.

label: adult fruitless dMS3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMS3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111096).

label: adult fruitless dMS3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region of the prothoracic segment, at the midline. A neurite enters the neuropil and projects anteriorly, exiting the VNC.

label: proboscis muscle 1
description: Muscle inserted in the dorso-posterior of the head capsule that is involved in proboscis retraction.

label: anepimeron
description: Sclerite immediately ventral (pleural) to the posterior of the wing. It lies immediately posterior to the pleural suture and is mesothoracic in origin.

label: presumptive anepimeron
description: The region of the wing disc, ventral to the wing pouch, that will develop into the anepimeron (pteropleura).

label: maxillary muscle 4
description: A muscle connecting the maxillary apodeme to the clypeus.

label: skeletal muscle of head
description: Somatic muscle that is part of the adult head.

label: mesothoracic episternum
description: The anterior part of the pleura in the mesothoracic segment of the adult thorax. It is divided transversely by the anapleural suture into an upper part, the anepisternum (mesopleuron) and a lower part, the katepisternum (sternopleuron or preepisternum). The mesothoracic episternum is separated from the mesothoracic epimeron by the pleural suture.

label: mesothoracic pleurum
description: Pleurum of the adult mesothoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless dMS2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMS2 lineage clone (FBbt:00111094).

label: adult fruitless dMS2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites enter the neuropil via a tract entrance in the dorsal anterior region of the mesothoracic segment. It projects ventromedially and turns back dorsally. Dendritic arbors are located in the dorsal region while the axonal arbors are located in the ventral region of the mesothoracic segment.

label: proboscis muscle 3
description: Muscle of the proboscis attached to the anterior face of the haustellum that acts as a proboscis flexor (forward motion).

label: pleural wing process
description: A process that extends from the pleural suture (FBbt:00004603) into the wing hinge where it arches around the axillary pouch (FBbt:00004745) and articulate with the 2nd axillary sclerite on the dorsal side of the hinge.

label: adult fruitless dMS1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMS1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111092).

label: adult fruitless dMS1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal posterior region of the prothoracic segment. Neurites project medially entering the neuropil through a tract entrance located laterally to the region between the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres.

label: adult fruitless dAB3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dAB3 lineage clone (FBbt:00111090).

label: haustellum muscle
description: Muscle of the haustellum, which function to extend or spread the adult labellum (labial palps).

label: adult labial motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the muscles of the haustellum, which extend or spread the adult labellum (labial palps). Its soma is found in the posterior cortex region of the adult subesophageal zone.

label: mesothoracic preepisternum
description: Anterior and major portion of the mesothoracic episternum or katepisternum.

label: labral muscle 5
description: Short muscle connected to the labrum, probably involved in compression of the labrum and dilation of the food canal.

label: presumptive anepisternum
description: The region of the wing disc, ventral to the wing pouch, that will develop into the anepisternum (mesopleura).

label: haustellum muscle 7
description: A muscle of the haustellum (mediproboscis) that functions in spreading of the labella.

label: adult fruitless dMS4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dMS4 lineage clone (FBbt:00111098).

label: haustellum muscle 6
description: A muscle of the haustellum (mediproboscis) that functions in extension of the labella.

label: katepisternum
description: The lower part of the mesothoracic episternum. It is separated from the dorsal mesothoracic episternum (anepisternum or mesopleuron) by the anapleural suture.

label: ventral head epidermis
description: The epidermis of the ventral region of the embryonic head.

label: embryonic head epidermis
description: Epidermis of the embryonic head.

label: dorsal head epidermis anlage in statu nascendi
dorsal head epidermis
description: The epidermis of the dorsal region of the embryonic head.

label: cibarial dilator muscle
description: Muscle involved in the dilation of the adult cibarium.

label: cibarial muscle
description: Muscle involved in the movement of the cibarium.

label: cibarial muscle 10
description: Muscle of the cibarium that, together with cibarial muscle 9, rotates the pharynx up into the head. It is a shorter muscle than cibarial muscle 9, extending in a dorso-posterior orientation.

label: cibarial dilator muscle 12
description: Cibarial dilator muscle that originates in the clypeus and connects to the expanded ventral portion of the anterior cibarial plate (roof of the cibarium) (Miller, 1950). It functions together with cibarial muscle 11 to execute the pumping behavior. Contraction of muscle 12 leads to cibarial expansion.

label: cibarial pump muscle 12 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. It arborizes bilaterally in the adult subesophageal zone and innervates the cibarial muscle 12. It is synapsed by the cibarial pump muscle 12 motor neuron.

label: cibarial dilator muscle 11
description: Cibarial dilator muscle that originates in the clypeus and connects to the median apodemal carina at the upper portion of the anterior cibarial plate (Miller, 1950). It is located more posteriorly than cibarial dilator muscle 12. It functions together with cibarial muscle 12 to execute the pumping behavior. Contraction of muscle 11 leads to fluid ingestion downstream of pumping, allowing the fluid to exit the cibarium to the esophagus.

label: cibarial pump muscle 11 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. It arborizes bilaterally in the adult subesophageal zone and innervates the cibarial muscle 11. It is involved in regulating feeding behaviour. It is synapsed by the cibarial pump muscle 11 motor neuron.

label: haustellum muscle 8
description: A transversely oriented muscle located the proximal haustellum (mediproboscis) that assists in the in extension of the labella.

label: cibarial muscle 9
description: Muscle of the cibarium that, together with cibarial muscle 10, rotates the pharynx up into the head. It is a longer muscle than cibarial muscle 10, and extends in a dorsomedial-anteriolateral orientation, originating on the cranial wall just below and anterior to the eye. It is required for the proboscis extension reflex. It is synapsed by the cibarial pump muscle 9 motor neuron.

label: cibarial pump muscle 9 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. It arborizes broadly in the adult subesophageal zone, mostly ipsilaterally, exits the brain by fasciculating with the pharyngeal nerve, and innervates the cibarial muscle 9. It is involved in initiating the proboscis extension reflex.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 2
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the ventral region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the posterior dorsal region of the M6 layer, covering around 80 columns. This neuron subtype includes GABAergic neurons, among other neurotransmitters.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local  neuron
description: Local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the ventral or dorsal regions of the lateral cell body rind. In contrast to directional M6 local neurons, dendrites and axon terminals are not segregated, and overlap. Thirteen subtypes are recognized, that differ in their location and column coverage.

label: second antennal segment muscle
description: Muscle involved in the movement of the second antennal segment.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 1
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the ventral region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the anterior dorsal region of the M6 layer, covering around 60 columns. This neuron is GABAergic.

label: salivary pump muscle 13
description: A slender muscle that arises on the posterior wall of the cibarium and is attached to the posterior wall of the salivary pump, which it functions in dilating.

label: salivary pump
description: A chamber in the adult salivary gland common duct at the base of the hypopharynx that is connected to a slender dilatory muscle (muscle 13 FBbt:00003277).

label: medulla directional M6 local neuron
description: Local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the medial or dorsal regions of the lateral cell body rind. In contrast to non-directional M6 local neurons, dendrites and axon terminals are segregated. Putative dendrites are found in the anterior region of the M6 layer and axons at the posterior one. Individual neurons vary greatly on how many columns they cover, with a range between 65 and 157. This neuron type includes glutamatergic neurons, among other neurotransmitters.

label: second antennal segment muscle 14
description: Small muscle of the adult second antennal segment, located more laterally than muscle 15.

label: central brain anlage
description: Anlage of the embryonic central brain in the gastrula embryo that will give rise to the central brain primordium.

label: central brain anlage in statu nascendi
description: Anlage in statu nascendi of the embryonic central brain in a stage 5 embryo. It will give rise to the central brain anlage.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 9
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoanterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 40 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: transverse-ptilinal muscle 18b
description: A large temporary transverse muscle extending horizontally from one side of the ptilinum to the other, above the level of the antenna. It functions as a compressor of the ptilinal membrane after each distension pulsation and to permanently invaginate it after emergence. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it soon degenerates and is not found in older flies.

label: ptilinum
description: Membranous sac that is part of the front of the head capsule. It is everted at eclosion and serves to break open the operculum at the end of the puparium. Following eclosion, it is withdrawn into the head where it collapses and becomes sclerotized, externally leaving the ptilinal suture.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 8
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoanterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 148 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: ptilino-pharyngeal muscle 18a
description: Temporary muscle extending from the ptilinum to the cibarium. It functions as a retractor of the ptilinum. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it soon degenerates and is not found in older flies.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 7
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes across the whole of the M6 layer, covering around 387 columns.

label: geno-tentorial muscle 19b
description: A temporary eclosion muscle that connects the postgena to the anterior portion of the gena. It arises from the same tendons as the ptilino-tentorial muscles. It is inserted over a wide dorsoventral area on each gena between the compound eyes and the frontal suture. Contraction of these muscles results in the shape of the head being returned to normal, as hemolymph is withdrawn into the abdomen. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it has almost disappeared by 24h after adult emergence.

label: postgena
description: A posterior region of the head capsule behind the gena.

label: gena
description: The bilateral part of the head capsule below the eyes, delimited by the occipital suture behind and the mouthparts below.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 6
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the ventral region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsalmost region of the M6 layer, covering around 102 columns.

label: fronto-tentorial muscle 19a
description: A temporary eclosion muscle that connects the tentorium to the frons. It arises from the same tendons of the tentorium and occipital sclerites though more centrally than the geno-tentorial muscles 19b. They are inserted in large dorsoventral groups on the lateral margins of the fronto-clypeus. Contraction of these muscles causes the head volume to decrease. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it degenerates 72h after adult emergence.

label: frons
description: An anterior part of the head capsule between the vertex and the clypeus, bounded laterally by the frontal suture and bearing a median ocellus.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 5
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the ventral region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the ventralmost region of the M6 layer, covering around 114 columns.

label: frontal pulsatile organ muscle 16
description: Muscle that attaches anteriorly to the rear wall of the frontal pulsatile organ and posteriorly to the terminal opening of the aorta.

label: frontal pulsatile organ
description: A thin-walled ovoid ampulla about 20 x 10 um in size, located medially against the front wall of the head, directly beneath the ptilinal fold and antennae. The frontal pulsatile organ muscle 16 is inserted on its rear wall, and connects this organ to the adult aortic funnel at the anterior region of the aorta.

label: adult aortic funnel
description: The funnel-shaped region of the aorta at its anterior, open end. It is connected to the frontal pulsatile organ by the frontal pulsatile organ muscle 16.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 4
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the ventral region of the M6 layer, covering around 157 columns.

label: second antennal segment muscle 15
description: Small muscle of the adult second antennal segment, located more medially than muscle 14 and very close to the body midline.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 3
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the ventral region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the posterior dorsal region of the M6 layer, covering around 148 columns. This neuron subtype includes GABAergic neurons, among other neurotransmitters.

label: fronto-pharyngeal muscle 17
description: Temporary muscle extending from the ocellar triangle to the cibarium. It is inserted partly on the ocular sclerites and partly on the lateral margins of ocellar triangle, caudal to the oculo-antennal muscles. These muscles appear to pull in the ocellar triangle during the deflation of the head. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it soon degenerates and is not found in older flies.

label: ptilino-tentorial muscle
description: Temporary muscle that is inserted on the ptilinum at each side dorso-laterally as a narrow band, immediately in front of the line of demarcation between the vertex and the ptilinum. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it degenerates 20h after adult emergence.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 12
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoposterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 54 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: transverse vertex muscle
description: Temporary muscle that lies underneath the adult head ocellar triangle (vertex) and extends transversely between the compound eyes. The contraction of this muscle layer diminishes the volume of the head. As with other temporary eclosion muscles, it soon degenerates and is not found in older flies.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 11
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the most dorsal region of the M6 layer, covering around 51 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 10
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoanterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 110 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: lunula muscle
description: Unpaired, long and thin muscle that arises from the dorsal rim of the occipital foramen and connects to the lunule of the fronto-clypeus. It retracts the ptilinum and the fronto-clypeus after adult emergence.

label: adult fruitless dAB1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dAB1 lineage clone (FBbt:00111148).

label: antennal intermediate sensillum I3
description: Intermediate sized sensillum of the third antennal segment that contains three receptor cells.

label: dorsal cervical muscle 21
description: Dorsal cervical muscle that connects to a cervical sclerite anteriorly, lateral to muscle 20, extending then ventrally.

label: dorsal cervical muscle
description: Muscle of the adult neck, located dorsally.

label: tyraminergic neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some tyramine secretion, neurotransmission (GO:0061546).

label: tyramine secretion, neurotransmission
description: The regulated release of a tyramine by a cell in which the tyramine acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: dorsal cervical muscle 20
description: Dorsal cervical muscle that connects to a cervical sclerite anteriorly, extending then dorsally and medially.

label: dorsal cervical muscle 23
description: Dorsal cervical muscle that connects to a cervical sclerite anteriorly, in the same region as muscle 20. It then extends laterally and posteriorly.

label: dorsal cervical muscle 22
description: Dorsal cervical muscle that is posterior to muscle 20, extending then ventrally.

label: ocular-antennal muscle
description: Muscle inserted on the adult ocular sclerites at the dorso-cephalic margin of the compound eyes, connecting to the second antennal segment. It functions to deflate the head during emergence by approximating the ocellar triangle and the fronto-clypeus and to retract the antenna. By 72h after emergence, the muscles have completely disintegrated.

label: gustatory receptor neuron of terminal organ distal group
description: Gustatory receptor neuron whose dendrites innervate the terminal organ on the surface of the larval head and whose soma is located in the terminal organ ganglion (terminal organ distal group). The axons of these neurons project via the maxillary nerve into area 4 of the subesophageal ganglion. There are 21 of these neurons per terminal organ.

label: gustatory receptor neuron of terminal organ
description: Gustatory receptor neuron associated with the terminal organ on the surface of the larval head. There is around 23 of these neurons, 3 in the dorso-lateral terminal organ group and 21 in the distal group.

label: embryonic/larval maxillary nerve
description: Larval subesophageal nerve carrying axons from the embryonic or larval head, including the terminal organ and the ventral organ, terminating in the subesophageal ganglion.

label: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 2
description: Large chemosensory target area located adjacent to area 1 of the larval subesophageal ganglion. This region receives input from the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ, the ventral pharyngeal sense organ, the posterior pharyngeal sense organ, the dorsal pharyngeal organ, the terminal organ, and the ventral pharyngeal sense organ (Colomb et al., 2007).

label: terminal organ ganglion
description: Ganglion of the larval terminal organ. It contains the cell bodies of approximately 32-33 neurons (Python and Stocker, 2002), dendrites from which terminate in the terminal organ, and axons from which travel to the larval brain by way of the maxillary nerve.

label: medulla non-directional M6 local neuron 13
description: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the posterior region of the M6 layer, extending anterioposteriorly, covering around 74 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: pb-eb neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge and the ellipsoid body.

label: mushroom body output neuron 21
description: A neuron whose dendrites arborize in gamma lobe slices 4 and 5. There is 1 neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: larval gnathal neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval gnathal segment (FBbt:00001737).

label: larval gnathal segment
description: Any gnathal segment (FBbt:00000011) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: adult gnathal segment
description: Any gnathal segment (FBbt:00000011) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: pb-eb-ltr neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge, the ellipsoid body and the contralateral lateral accessory lobe.

label: pb-fb neuron
description: A small field neuron of the adult central complex that innervates only the protocerebral bridge and the fan-shaped body.

label: protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron of glomerulus 6
description: Subtype of the protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron that has axonal terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus 6 and contralateral glomerulus 3.
synonyms: protocerebral bridge 15 glomeruli neuron of glomerulus 5

label: protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron
description: Large field neuron of the central complex that is intrinsic to the protocerebral bridge. It has dendritic arbors in 18 glomeruli, and axon terminals distributed in two glomeruli spaced seven glomeruli apart. There are three subtypes that differ on the location of the axon terminals. One subtype has terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus 7 and contralateral glomerulus 2; another with terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus 6 and contralateral glomerulus 3; and the last with terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus 5 and contralateral glomerulus 4.

label: protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron of glomerulus 7
description: Subtype of the protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron that has axonal terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus 7 and contralateral glomerulus 2.

label: protocerebral bridge 4 glomeruli neuron
description: Large field neuron of the central complex that is intrinsic to the protocerebral bridge. It has ipsilateral dendritic arbors in 4 glomeruli (6 to 8) and axon terminals distributed in the most lateral glomerulus 9.

label: dorsal rim area
description: The array of photoreceptors in the dorsal part of the retina, which include only dorsal margin photoreceptor cells R7 and R8.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2 alpha' middle
description: Subtype of the mushroom body ventral lobe arborizing neuron 2 alpha'. It arborizes in the alpha' middle domain and its axon projects to the lateral horn. There are two neurons of this subtype in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body alpha' middle layer
description: Middle-most layer of the mushroom body alpha' lobe.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2 alpha' anterior-posterior
description: Subtype of the mushroom body ventral lobe arborizing neuron 2 alpha'. It arborizes in the alpha' anterior-posterior domain and its axon projects to a region ventral to the lateral horn. There is one neuron of this subtype in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body alpha' anterior-posterior layer
description: Anterior-most layer of the mushroom body alpha' lobe.

label: adult heart circular muscle
description: Circular muscle of the adult heart that makes up the wall of the heart. It consists of a single layer, internal to the longitudinal muscle layer.

label: adult heart muscle
description: Muscle of the adult that is associated with the heart.

label: gamma main Kenyon cell
description: Gamma mushroom body neuron subtype whose dendritic arbor occupies the main calyx, and its axon extends to the gamma lobe. There are around 600 neurons of this subtype per hemisphere.

label: gamma Kenyon cell
description: Mushroom body neuron that innervates the mushroom body vertical and medial lobes of larvae, but is pruned back during early pupal stages to innervate only the gamma lobe (Awasaki and Ito, 2004; Awasaki et al., 2006). The gamma neurons are the first born of the Kenyon cells, born before the alpha' and beta' neurons. In the pedunculus, the gamma axons occupy the periphery, with the alpha/beta neurons occupying the core stratum and the alpha'/beta' neurons in the intermediate stratum (Awasaki and Ito, 2004; Awasaki et al., 2006; Tanaka et al., 2008). The gamma neuron also arborizes in the calyx, forming pre- and post-synaptic terminals (Christiansen et al., 2011). There are around 675 neurons of this type per hemisphere, with two subtypes identified.

label: protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron of glomerulus 5
description: Subtype of the protocerebral bridge 18 glomeruli type 2 neuron that has axonal terminals in the ipsilateral glomerulus 5 and contralateral glomerulus 4.
synonyms: protocerebral bridge 15 glomeruli neuron of glomerulus 4

label: larval thoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval thoracic segment (FBbt:00001742).

label: dopaminergic PPL1 neuron 2
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PPL1 cluster that has sparse terminals in the gamma lobe slice 1. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron L1 adPN
description: Multiglomerular adult antennal lobe projection neuron of the adPN lineage. It is born from the 18th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346), after the division that produced VC3 adPN. Its innervation targets include parts of glomeruli DC3, VC3 and VM4.

label: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron adPN
description: An adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron that is derived from the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346). All of these neurons have axons that fasciculate with the medial antennal lobe tract (mALT) and except for V adPN neurons, innervate the lateral horn.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 14
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects to the middle layer of beta' lobe slice 1. Dendritic arborizations are found in the superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum and crepine.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 100 cell bodies in the cortex of the anterior inferior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain. At least some members of this group project to areas posterior to the mushroom body medial lobe (Mao and Davis, 2009). Neurons in this cluster project bilaterally to the medial portion of the mushroom body beta-lobe (Claridge-Chang et al., 2009). Contacts with Kenyon cells are visible in the horizontal lobes, namely in the medial regions of the gamma, beta and beta' lobes.

label: mushroom body beta' middle layer
description: Middle-most layer of the mushroom body beta' lobe.

label: mushroom body beta' lobe slice 1
description: Proximal-most slice of the mushroom body beta' lobe.

label: multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron L2 adPN
description: Multiglomerular adult antennal lobe projection neuron of the adPN lineage. It is born from the 19th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346), after the division that produced L1 adPN. Its innervation targets include parts of glomeruli VM4 and VL2p.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 13
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects to the anterior-posterior layer of beta' lobe slice 1. Dendritic arborizations are found in the superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum and crepine. There are between 13-14 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body beta' anterior-posterior layer
description: Anterior-most layer of the mushroom body beta' lobe.

label: multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron L3 adPN
description: Multiglomerular adult antennal lobe projection neuron of the adPN lineage. It is born from the 20th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346), after the division that produces L2 adPN. Its dendrites innervate glomeruli VL2p, VL2a and DL1l.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DL1l
description: Lateral region of antennal lobe glomerulus DL1.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 11
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects to the alpha lobe slice 1 and the pedunculus. Dendritic arborizations are found in the superior medial, intermediate and lateral protocerebrum. There are less than 6 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body pedunculus-medial lobe and vertical lobe arborizing neuron 1
description: A neuron, which is part of a cluster of at least seven neurons, whose cell body is located on the inferior neuropils, near the junction of the mushroom body lobes of each adult brain hemisphere. The cell body fiber bifurcates in front of the vertical lobes. One of these branches turns ventromedially to the tip of the medial lobe, whereas the other runs dorsally. The first branch innervates the medial lobe through the border between the gamma and beta' lobes and bifurcates both medially and laterally at the border between the beta and beta' lobes. One bundle of fibers runs medially to the opposite lobe, whereas the other runs laterally to the basal segments of the beta and alpha lobe (slice 1) as well as the core of the pedunculus. The second of the initial branches diverges in the superior neuropils near the tip of the vertical lobe. One branch turns laterally, runs through the anterior side of the vertical lobe and terminates in the superior intermediate protocerebrum and superior medial protocerebrum. Another branch turns medially and terminates in the anterior dorsal superior medial protocerebrum. Some branches turn laterally, innervating the posterior dorsal superior medial protocerebrum and posterior dorsal superior lateral protocerebrum, and terminate in the anterior dorsal superior lateral protocerebrum. Three subtypes have been recognized: one that arborizes in the beta lobe slice and pedunculus (PAM-09), another that arborizes the beta lobe slice 1 (PAM-10) and another that arborizes in the alpha lobe slice 1 (PAM-.

label: mushroom body alpha lobe slice 1
description: Proximal-most slice of the mushroom body alpha lobe.

label: multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron L4 adPN
description: Multiglomerular adult antennal lobe projection neuron of the adPN lineage. It is born from the 21st larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346), after the division that produces L3 adPN. Its innervation targets include parts of glomeruli VL2a, Dl1l, DL2v and DL2d.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DL2v
description: Ventral-most compartment of glomerulus DL2. It lies on the ventromedial margin of the dorsal compartment and immediately ventral to glomerulus DL1.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DL2d
description: Dorsal-most compartment of antennal lobe glomerulus DL2. It lies at the dorsoventral margin of the ventral compartment and ventral to glomerulus DA1.

label: hormone transport
description: The directed movement of hormones into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: regulation of hormone levels
description: Any process that modulates the levels of hormone within an organism or a tissue. A hormone is any substance formed in very small amounts in one specialized organ or group of cells and carried (sometimes in the bloodstream) to another organ or group of cells in the same organism, upon which it has a specific regulatory action.

label: larval metathoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: superior bulb
description: Region of the bulb that lies in a superior position between the mushroom body pedunculus and the ellipsoid body. It contains many small glomeruli.

label: larval mesothoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: inferior bulb
description: Region of the bulb that lies in an inferior position between the mushroom body pedunculus and the ellipsoid body. It contains many small glomeruli.

label: larval prothoracic neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: anterior bulb
description: Region of the bulb that lies beneath the mushroom body pedunculus, closer to the somata of the ellipsoid body neurons than the superior and inferior bulb. It is formed by the antero-lateral and inferior extension of the lateral region of the superior bulb.

label: plexiform lamina
description: The main part of the lamina that does not contain the terminals of photoreceptors from dorsal rim ommatidia.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DA4l adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DA4l. This neuron is born from the fifth division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: larval abdominal 7 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: larval abdominal 6 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: larval abdominal 5 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: larval abdominal 4 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: larval abdominal 3 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: serotonergic thoracic neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of three clusters either side of the ventral midline in the pro-, meso- and metathoracic segments.

label: larval abdominal 2 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: larval abdominal 1 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: antennal lobe hub
description: Central, non-glomerular region of the adult antennal lobe. It is distinguished from the antennal lobe glomeruli in that olfactory receptor neurons do not terminate here, though antennal lobe projection neurons and many local neurons run through this area. The density of synapses is lower than in the antennal lobe glomeruli.

label: larval abdominal 11 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00001758).

label: larval abdominal segment 11
description: Rudimentary larval abdominal segment that surrounds the anal opening.

label: inferior antennal lobe commissure
description: Ventral-most of two commissures connecting the antennal lobes and running in front of the ellipsoid body.

label: larval abdominal 10 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00001757).

label: larval abdominal 9 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00001756).

label: superior ellipsoid commissure
description: Commissure lying above the ellipsoid body connecting the superior medial protocerebrum (SMP), superior intermediate protocerebrum (SIP), superior clamp (SCL) and inferior clamp (ICL). It demarcates the boundaries of the ellipsoid body (superior region), SMP (inferior region), SIP (inferior region), SCL (inferior region) and ICL (superior region).

label: larval abdominal 8 neuromere
description: Any neuromere (FBbt:00005140) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).

label: posterior posteriolateral protocerebral commissure
description: Commissure running above the esophagus and below the inferior bridge, connecting the middle levels of the posterior lateral protocerebrum. It demarcates the boundary between the inferior bridge and superior posterior slope.

label: subesophageal ganglion serotonergic SE neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 3 clusters on either side of the ventral midline in the subesophageal ganglion.

label: mushroom body output neuron 9
description: A GABAergic neuron whose dendrites arborize in gamma lobe slice 3 in both hemispheres, and in the contralateral beta' lobe slice 1. Axonal terminals are found in the contralateral gamma lobe slice 3, crepine and superior medial protocerebrum. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body output neuron 8
description: A GABAergic neuron whose dendrites arborize in the gamma lobe slice 3 in both hemispheres, and with axonal terminals in the contralateral gamma slice 3. Axonal terminals are also found in the crepine and superior medial protocerebrum. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body output neuron 7
description: A glutamatergic neuron whose dendrites arborize in alpha lobe slice 1 and its axons project to the superior intermediate and lateral protocerebrum and back to the alpha lobe slice 1, 2 and 3. There are two neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: serotonergic SE2 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 3 clusters on either side of the ventral midline in the ventral nerve cord of the maxillary segment. Axons from this cluster cross the midline in the maxillary segment. In the adult they are located in the posterior-lateral subesophageal ganglion.

label: mushroom body output neuron 5
description: A glutamatergic neuron whose dendrites arborize in the contralateral gamma lobe slice 4 and its axon projects back to the lobes to gamma lobe slices 1 and 2 and to the crepine and superior medial protocerebrum. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body gamma lobe slice 2
description: Second most proximal slice of the mushroom body gamma lobe.

label: FMRFamide SE3 neuron
description: Bilaterally paired (Kolhekar et al., 1997) FMRFamide expressing interneuron of the subesophageal neuromere. They are located more posteriorly than the FMRFamide SE2 neurons (Schneider et al., 1993).

label: ventral superficial trachea 9
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034).

label: ventral superficial trachea
description: Ventral branch of the superficial trachea in the adult abdomen. There is generally one ventral superficial trachea in each spiracle-bearing segment.

label: tracheal metamere 9
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 7.

label: ventral superficial trachea 8
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: tracheal metamere 8
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 6.

label: ventral organ ganglion
description: Ganglion that contains the cell bodies of neurons associated with the larval ventral organ. It connects to the central nervous system via the maxillary nerve.

label: ventral superficial trachea 7
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: tracheal metamere 7
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 5.

label: antennal intermediate sensillum I2
description: Intermediate sized sensilla of antennal segment 3 that contains two receptor cells.

label: ventral superficial trachea 6
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: tracheal metamere 6
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 4.

label: mushroom body output neuron 12
description: A cholinergic neuron whose dendrites arborize in gamma lobe slice 2 and alpha' lobe slice 1 with axonal terminals found in the crepine and superior medial protocerebrum. There are 2 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body alpha' lobe slice 1
description: Proximal-most base slice of the mushroom body alpha' lobe.

label: mushroom body output neuron 10
description: A GABAergic neuron whose dendrites arborize in beta' lobe slice 1, and in neighboring neuropils including crepine, superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum. Axonal terminals are found in the lateral accessory lobe. There are around 7-9 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM5d adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM5d. Neurons of this class are derived from the 15th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: mushroom body output neuron 15
description: A cholinergic neuron whose dendrites arborize unilaterally in alpha' lobe slice 1. The thin dendritic branches project through the edge of the alpha' lobe slices 2 and 3 compartments to the contralateral hemisphere, sharing an axon tract with MB-V2 alpha'. Axon terminals are found in the superior intermediate and lateral protocerebrum, and lateral horn. There are 2 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM5v adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM5v. Neurons of this class are derived from the 16th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VC3 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VC3. Neurons of this class are derived from the 17th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL2v adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL2v. Neurons of this class are derived from the 22nd larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL2d adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL2d. Neurons of this class are derived from the 23rd larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 6
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects bilaterally to the middle layer of the beta' lobe slice 2. Dendritic terminals are found in the superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum and crepine. There are between 12-15 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 5
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects bilaterally to the posterior layer of the beta' lobe slice 2. Dendritic terminals are found in the superior medial protocerebrum and crepine. There are between 14-17 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 2
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster whose dendrites arborize the superior medial protocerebrum and crepine. The axon projects to the anterior layer of the beta' lobe slice 2. There are around 6-9 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VL2a adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VL2a. This neuron is born from the tenth division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). It innervates the antero-ventral lateral horn (Grosjean et al., 2011). Its terminals in this region overlap extensively with the terminals of DA1 and VA1lm projection neurons, which have been implicated in a pheromone-sensing pathway (Jefferis et al., 2007).

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 1
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster whose dendrites arborize the superior medial protocerebrum. The axon projects to the gamma lobe slice 5. There are around 8-21 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: adult fruitless aSP13 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP13 lineage clone (FBbt:00110548).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM4 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DM4. This neuron is born from the 15th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: mushroom body output neuron 4
description: Glutamatergic neuron whose cell body is located on the superior neuropils of each hemisphere, anterior to the pars intercerebralis. The cell body fiber is sent ventrally towards the medial lobe, crossing the midline. Dendritic arborizations are found in the anterior and posterior layers of beta' lobe slice 2, with the main axon projecting bilaterally to the crepine and superior medial protocerebrum.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL4 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage (embryonic born) whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL4. Neurons of this class are born during the 20th and final division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). It innervates the posteriomedial region of the lateral horn and the mushroom body calyx.

label: mushroom body output neuron 20
description: A neuron whose dendrites arborize in gamma lobe slices 1 and 2. There is 1 neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VC4 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VC4. Neurons of this class are derived from the 14th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: mushroom body output neuron 2
description: A glutamatergic neuron whose dendrites arborize bilaterally in the beta lobe slice 2 and anterior layer of beta' lobe slice 2. Its axon projects ipsilaterally to the superior intermediate and lateral protocerebrum. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: mushroom body beta lobe slice 2
description: Distal-most slice of the mushroom body beta lobe.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DA3 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage (embryonic born) whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DA3. Neurons of this class are born during the 2nd larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: mushroom body output neuron 19
description: A cholinergic neuron whose dendrites arborize unilaterally in the posterior layer of alpha lobe slices 2 and 3 and projects to the superior medial protocerebrum. There are 2 neurons of this type in each hemisphere.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 7
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that, unusually, has dendritic arborizations in gamma lobe slices 1 and 2, superior medial protocerebrum and crepine. It projects to the gamma lobe slice 4. There are between 13-17 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 9
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects to the beta lobe slice 1 and pedunculus. There are between 1-3 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body beta lobe slice 1
description: Proximal-most slice of the mushroom body beta lobe.

label: multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron emb adPN
description: Multiglomerular adult antennal lobe projection neuron of the adPN lineage. It is born from the antero-dorsal neuroblast, from the 12th embryonic division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) after the division that produce DC1 adPN.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 8
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster that projects to the gamma lobe slice 4, with dendritic arborizations found in the superior medial protocerebrum and crepine.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM4 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM4. This neuron is born from the sixth division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM6+VP1 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM6+VP1. This neuron is born from the seventh division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75a/b
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptors (Ir) 75a (FBgn0036757) and 75b (FBgn0261402) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704) (Silbering et al., 2011). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL2. Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac3. It is distinguishable from the other ORN ac3 (Ir76b/Or35a) by its odor response profile. A subset of these neurons also expresses Ir75c (FBgn0261401) (Benton et al., 2009).

label: larval CCAP T3 IN thoracic neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and Bursicon (FBgn0038901) of the metathoracic neuromere. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects ventrolaterally in the contralateral neuropil and branches in a T-shape at the VL fascicle: a long posterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its posterior end and then bend medially; a shorter anterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its anterior end at the border between the subesophageal ganglion and brain, and then bends medially forming small arborizations.

label: larval CCAP T3 thoracic neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and Bursicon (FBgn0038901), and whose soma is located ventrally around the metathoracic neuromere, approximately at the height of the VL fascicle. There are two neurons in each hemineuromere, one interneurons and one efferent neuron.

label: larval CCAP subesophageal EN-2 neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located in the subesophageal ganglion. The primary neurite extends medially, forming arborizations close to the cell body and between the ipsilateral DM and VM fascicles in the same segment. It then crosses the midline where it projects dorsally and then ventrally, and exits the brain via the maxillary nerve.

label: larval CCAP subesophageal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located in the subesophageal ganglion. There are three neurons in each hemisphere, one in each neuromere, aligned from anterior to posterior.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75d ac4
description: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptors (Ir) 75d (FBgn0036829) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VL1 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4. It is distinguishable from Ir75d ac1 and Ir75d ac2 by its odor response profile (Benton et al., 2009).

label: antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4
description: Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that is innervated by three olfactory receptor neurons (ORN). It is distinguishable from a1, ac2 and ac3 by its odor response profile (Yao et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (Benton et al., 2009).

label: larval CCAP subesophageal IN-2 neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located in the subesophageal ganglion. The primary neurite crosses the midline and arborizes close to it, and branches: a long posterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its posterior end and then bend medially; a shorter anterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its anterior end at the border between the subesophageal ganglion and brain, and then bends medially forming small arborizations.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75d ac2
description: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 75d (FBgn0036829) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VL1 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2. It is distinguishable from IR75d ac1 and IR75d ac4 by its odor response profile (Benton et al., 2009).

label: antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2
description: Coeloconic olfactory sensillum of the antenna that is innervated by three olfactory receptor neurons (ORN). It is distinguishable from ac1, ac3 and ac4 by its odor response profile (Yao et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (Benton et al., 2009).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir41a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 41a (FBgn0040849) and the co-receptors 25a (FBgn0031634) and 76b (FBgn0036937). It innervates the antennal lobe glomeruli VC5. Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VC5
description: Ventro-central antennal lobe glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe, dorsal to antennal lobe glomerulus VC3 lateral compartment (Endo et al., 2007).

label: larval CCAP subesophageal IN-1 neuron
description: The most anterior of the larval neurons that express CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located in the subesophageal ganglion. The primary neurite projects medially, forming extensive arborizations along the midline between the DM and VM fascicles in the subesophageal ganglion.

label: larval CCAP protocerebrum IN-2 neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is in the protocerebrum rind. The primary neurite branches medially in the dorsomedial protocerebrum and projects ventrally through the posterior basomedial protocerebrum forming short neurites in the basomedial protocerebrum. It then projects ventrally, exiting the brain and terminating at a position between the abdominal neuromere A4 to A7. One neurite from the dorsomedial protocerebrum crosses the midline and projects ventrally similar to the ipsilateral neurite.

label: larval CCAP protocerebrum neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is near the protocerebrum. There are two neurons in each hemisphere.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir76b/92a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 92a (FBgn0038789) and the co-receptors Ir25a (FBgn0031634) and Ir76b (FBgn0036937). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM1 compartment (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 75a (FBgn0036757) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DP1 lateral compartment and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DP1 lateral compartment (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac2 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: larval CCAP protocerebrum IN-1 neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is in the protocerebrum rind. It branches in the ipsilateral dorsomedial protocerebrum with some neurites reaching the dorsolateral protocerebrum and extending to the contralateral dorsomedial protocerebrum. Often, an ipsilateral neurite extends ventrally through the posterior basomedial protocerebrum to terminate in the subesophageal ganglion.

label: DPLal2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLal2 neuroblast.

label: larval CCAP neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir31a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 31a (FBgn0051718) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2 posterior compartment and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2 posterior compartment (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: DPLal3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLal3 neuroblast.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir75d ac1
description: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 75d (FBgn0036829) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VL1 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac1. It is distinguishable from IR75d ac2 and IR75d ac4 by its odor response profile (Benton et al., 2009).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VP2/VP3 t3ALT PN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron whose dendrites innervate the antennal lobe glomeruli VP2 and VP3. It fasciculates with the transverse antennal lobe t3ALT tract to innervate the lateral horn, posterior slope and posterior lateral protocerebrum. This neuron responds to fast increases and decreases in temperature.

label: transverse antennal lobe t3ALT tract
description: Transverse antennal lobe tract that innervates the posterior lateral protocerebrum, passing ventral to the mushroom body pedunculus and posterior to the fan-shaped body.

label: DPLd lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLd neuroblast.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir76a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptors (Ir) 76a (FBgn0260874) and the co-receptors Ir76b (FBgn0036937) and Ir25a (FBgn0031634). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM4 (Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir64a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptor (Ir) 64a (FBgn0035604) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating an ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the corresponding contralateral lobe glomerulus. Two subtypes are identified: one innervates the antennal lobe DC4 glomerulus and the other innervates the medial compartment of DP1 glomerulus. Its dendrite transduces signals from the grooved sensillum of chamber III of the sacculus (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: grooved sensillum of sacculus
description: Sensillum of chamber III of the sacculus of the antenna. The sensilla are double-walled and bear alternating longitudinal grooves and ridges for three-quarters of their length from the tip. They are innervated by two sensory neurons (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: larval CCAP T3 EN thoracic neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and Bursicon (FBgn0038901) of the metathoracic neuromere. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects mediodorsally and dorsolaterally until it leaves the central neuropil. It then diverges in the dorsal cortex, projects via the segmental nerve to the periphery and forms type III terminals on body wall ventral longitudinal muscles 1 and 2.

label: metathoracic posterior fascicle neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that fasciculates with some metathoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002163).

label: metathoracic segmental nerve
description: Segmental nerve of the metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: abdominal 1 temporary eclosion muscle DA2
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle 2 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000592) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 temporary eclosion muscle DA1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000591) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 temporary eclosion muscle DA3
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle 3 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: larval CCAP A1-A4 EN abdominal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), Bursicon (FBgn0038901), Partner of Bursicon (FBgn0264810) and Myoinhibiting peptide precursor (FBgn0036713) of the abdominal neuromere. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects mediodorsally and dorsolaterally until it leaves the central neuropil. It then diverges in the dorsal cortex, projects via the segmental nerve to the periphery and forms type III terminals on body wall ventral longitudinal muscles 1 and 2.

label: larval CCAP A1-A4 abdominal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), Bursicon (FBgn0038901), Partner of Bursicon (FBgn0264810) and Myoinhibiting peptide precursor (FBgn0036713). The soma is located around the abdominal neuromeres A1 to A4, in a varied position from more medial to more dorsal. There are two neurons in each hemineuromere.

label: larval CCAP A1-A4 IN abdominal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), Bursicon (FBgn0038901), Partner of Bursicon (FBgn0264810) and Myoinhibiting peptide precursor (FBgn0036713) of the abdominal neuromere. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects ventrolaterally in the contralateral neuropil and branches in a T-shape at the VL fascicle: a long posterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its posterior end and then bend medially; a shorter anterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its anterior end at the border between the subesophageal ganglion and brain, and then bends medially forming small arborizations.

label: DPMm3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMm3 neuroblast.

label: DPMl1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMl1 neuroblast.

label: DPMl2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMl2 neuroblast.

label: DPMl3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMl3 neuroblast.

label: abdominal 1 temporary eclosion muscle LL1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal temporary eclosion muscle LL1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of the adult abdomen that develops from an A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle.

label: abdominal 1 lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000600) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: DPMl4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMl4 neuroblast.

label: DPLam lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLam neuroblast.

label: DPLal1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLal1 neuroblast.

label: sensillum of sacculus
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some sacculus (FBbt:00004179).

label: sacculus
description: A three-chambered pit organ on antennal segment 3 that contains many sensilla. It extends ventrodorsally, with an opening to the posterior side of the antennal segment (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-AL1 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located ventrally around the gnathal ganglion. It innervates the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and the subesophageal zone (SEZ) bilaterally, and the contralateral antennal lobe.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VLP5 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located posteriorly to the ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP). Ipsilaterally, it innervates the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC), wedge (IVLP) and anterior VLP. It projects across the midline via the superior AMMC commissure to innervate the anterior VLP region.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VLP projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that arborizes in both the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and in the ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VLP3 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located ventrolaterally to the gnathal ganglion. It innervates the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC), anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP), wedge (inferior VLP) and the subesophageal zone (SEZ). It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: chamber II of sacculus
description: Middle chamber of the sacculus of the antenna. It has several compartments, each containing a single sensillum (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: chamber III of sacculus
description: Dorsal-most and largest chamber of the sacculus of the antenna. It has a ventral and a dorsal compartment, which differ in the type of sensilla they contain. The compartments are separated by a thick cuticular flap that extends lateromedially (Shanbhag et al., 1995).
