label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VLP2 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located ventrolaterally to the gnathal ganglion. It innervates the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC), anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP), wedge (inferior VLP) and the subesophageal zone (SEZ). A few neurites cross the midline in the ventral SEZ.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VLP1 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located posteriorly to the ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP). Ipsilaterally, it innervates the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and posterior VLP. It projects across the midline via the superior AMMC commissure to innervate the posterior VLP region.

label: chamber I of sacculus
description: Ventral-most chamber of the sacculus of the antenna, where the opening is located (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: embryonic hemocyte anlage
description: Anlage which is part of the head mesoderm and gives rise to embryonic hemocytes.

label: head mesoderm
description: Mesoderm that originates anterior to the cephalic furrow. It forms two vertical plates that flank the anterior midgut rudiment, and from stage 10 onwards, the stomodeum.

label: abdominal 1 temporary eclosion muscle VL1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal temporary eclosion muscle VL
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of the adult abdomen that develops from an A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle.

label: abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000601) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 temporary eclosion muscle VL2
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 (FBbt:00000603) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: tachykinin neuron
description: Neuron that expresses tachykinin (FBgn0037976).

label: main tegula sensillum campaniformium
description: Sensillum campaniformium found on the medial surface of the tegula of the adult wing. There are 18 elliptical sensilla with high profile and with a socket (type 5). Fourteen of these form a compact central population oriented with their major axis perpendicular to the proximodistal axis of the wing. Two larger sensilla of the same type flank this population, oriented parallel to the wing axis.

label: campaniform sensillum of tegula
description: Campaniform sensillum of the tegula in the adult wing. There are two distinct fields of elliptical sensilla with high profile and with a socket (type 5): a main one with 18 sensilla and two peripheral sensilla located more anteriorly.

label: tegula
description: The most proximal part of the anterior margin of the wing hinge. It is tightly packed with sensilla, bearing ~16 campaniform, 7 trichoid, 3 macrochaetae, 4 microchaetae.

label: TRdm lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the TRdm neuroblast.

label: anatomical entity
description: Anatomical entity which is part_of Drosophila melanogaster.

label: ventrolateral protocerebrum local VLP1 neuron
description: Neuron whose cell body is located posteriorly to the ventrolateral protocerebrum (VLP). The primary neurite innervates the ipsilateral posterior VLP region.

label: intrinsic ventrolateral protocerebrum neuron
description: Neuron that innervates the ventrolateral protocerebrum region only.

label: Leucokinin neuron
description: Neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418).

label: TRdl lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the TRdl neuroblast.

label: abdominal 1  temporary eclosion muscle SBM
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 1 that develops from abdominal 1 segment border muscle of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 1 segment border muscle
description: Any A1-7 segment border muscle (FBbt:00000606) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: Trco lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the Trco neuroblast.

label: DPMpl1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMpl1 neuroblast.

label: DPMpl2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMpl2 neuroblast.

label: TRvl lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the TRvl neuroblast.

label: DPMpl3 lineage neuron.
description: Neuron developing from the DPMpl3 neuroblast.

label: DPMpl4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPMpl4 neuroblast.

label: adult CCAP/burs abdominal neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), Bursicon (FBgn0038901) and Partner of Bursicon (FBgn0264810), whose soma is located in the cell body rind of the abdominal ganglion. There is 1 neuron in each hemineuromere from A1 to A7. The main neurite extends towards the midline and arborizes. It then crosses the midline and exits the central nervous system posteriorly via one of the abdominal nerves.

label: adult CCAP abdominal neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), whose soma is located in the cell body rind of the abdominal ganglion. There are around 2 neurons in each hemineuromere.

label: adult transverse nerve
description: Thin, peripheral adult nerve that branches from the segmental nerve in the dorsal midline of the thoracico-abdominal of each abdominal neuromere. Each transverse nerve from A1 to A5 extends obliquely forward to the next preceding abdominal neuromere where it terminates on the alary muscles of the heart chamber.

label: adult alary muscle
description: Bilateral adult heart muscle that is involved in modulation of the flow of hemolymph into the cardiac tube, and support of the dorsal vessel during locomotion.

label: adult CCAP heart abdominal neuron
description: A subset of CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) neurons of the adult abdominal ganglion. It has a bipolar morphology, with one of the neurites fasciculating with the adult transverse nerve in each neuromere, to innervate the alary muscles of the heart chambers that extend along the midline. There is one in each hemineuromere from A1 to A6.

label: adult CCAP neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007).

label: adult CCAP thoracic neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), whose soma is located in the cell body rind of the thoracic ganglion. There is 1 neuron in each thoracic hemineuromere.

label: larval CCAP T2 thoracic neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and bursicon (FBgn0038901), and whose soma is located around the mesothoracic neuromere. There is one neuron in each hemineuromere. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects ventrolaterally in the contralateral neuropil and branches in a T-shape at the VL fascicle: a long posterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its posterior end and then bend medially; a shorter anterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its anterior end at the border between the subesophageal ganglion and brain, and then bends medially forming small arborizations.

label: larval CCAP thoracic neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located around the thoracic neuromeres. There is one neuron located ventrolaterally in the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres, and two neurons in the metathoracic neuromere. It sends a neurite beneath the transversal projection TP4 ventromedially, where the neurites from both sides join in proximity to the VM fascicle. These neurites from extensive arborizations along the midline between the DM and VM fascicles, more prominently in the metathoracic neuromere.

label: larval CCAP T1 thoracic neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located around the prothoracic neuromere. There is one neuron in each hemineuromere. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects ventrolaterally in the contralateral neuropil and branches in a T-shape at the VL fascicle: a long posterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its posterior end and then bend medially; a shorter anterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its anterior end at the border between the subesophageal ganglion and brain, and then bends medially forming small arborizations.

label: metatarsus of male prothoracic leg
description: First tarsal segment of the male prothoracic leg. In contrast to females, it has a sex comb, central bristle and 5 to 6 transverse rows of bristles (TR).

label: embryonic/larval oenocyte precursor
description: Embryonic/larval oenocyte precursors first become apparent during stage 11 when a small group of cells encircling each chordotonal organ precursor cell C1 become sickle shaped, making a double ringed 'whorl' around C1. Shortly afterwards (stage 11-12) these cells delaminate in two waves, (inner cells first) and migrate away to form an 'abdominal larval oenocyte group'.

label: mushroom body beta lobe layer
description: Subdivision of the mushroom body beta lobe along its longitudinal axis.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VP3 t5ALT PN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron whose dendrites innervate the antennal lobe glomerulus VP3. It fasciculates with the transverse antennal lobe t5ALT tract to innervate a subregion of the mushroom body calyx. This neuron responds to cooling, showing weak adaptation to sustained temperature decreases.

label: transverse antennal lobe t5ALT tract
description: Transverse antennal lobe tract that innervates the mushroom body calyx.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir21a
description: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 21a (FBgn0031209) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomeruli VP3. Its dendrite transduces signals from the grooved sensillum of chamber III of the sacculus.

label: mushroom body alpha' lobe layer
description: Subdivision of the mushroom body alpha' lobe along its longitudinal axis.

label: tracheal stalk cell
description: Y-shaped cell that bifurcates at the distal end to connect to the two subtype of tip cells, terminal or fusion. It forms an autocellular tube. The interface between a stalk cell and a terminal cell is simple, whereas the one between a stalk cell and a fusion cell is more complex. The stalk cell extends its seamed tube into the fusion cell, such that the apical membrane of the first surrounds almost the entire fusion cell lumen.

label: tracheal fusion cell
description: Tracheal tip cell that mediates the fusion of tracheal branches during embryogenesis and later develops into a node cell. These cells are short and unbranched.

label: terminal tracheal cell
description: Tracheal tip cell that does not fuse with other trachea, but instead develops into a tracheolar cell - forming secondary trachea and tracheoles. These cells form intracellular seamless tubes that branch extensively.

label: mushroom body beta lobe slice
description: Subdivision of mushroom body perpendicular to the beta lobe axis whose boundaries correspond to the boundaries of terminal arborization of mushroom body extrinsic neurons.

label: mushroom body alpha lobe layer
description: Subdivision of the mushroom body alpha lobe along its longitudinal axis.

label: larval CCAP A8-A9 abdominal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and Myoinhibiting peptide precursor (FBgn0036713), whose soma is located around the abdominal neuromeres A8 to A9. There are two neurons in each hemineuromere, one located more ventrolaterally (in A8) and the other more medially (in A9), near the posterior tip of the abdominal ganglion. The primary neurite crosses the midline and exits the neuropil via the hindgut nerve.

label: larval CCAP abdominal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located around the abdominal neuromeres. There are two neurons in each hemineuromere, except in A8 and A9 where there are 3. It sends a neurite beneath the transversal projection TP4 ventromedially, where the neurites from both sides join in proximity to the VM fascicle. These neurites from extensive arborizations along the midline between the DM and VM fascicles.

label: larval CCAP A5-A7 abdominal neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and whose soma is located laterally around the abdominal neuromeres A5 to A7, between the height of the VL and DL fascicles. The primary neurite extends to the midline and arborizes dorsally between the DM and VM fascicles, up to the segment borders. It then projects ventrolaterally in the contralateral neuropil and branches in a T-shape at the VL fascicle: a long posterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its posterior end and then bend medially; a shorter anterior branch follows the VL fascicle until its anterior end at the border between the subesophageal ganglion and brain, and then bends medially forming small arborizations.

label: mushroom body alpha' lobe slice
description: Subdivision of mushroom body perpendicular to the alpha' lobe axis whose boundaries correspond to the boundaries of terminal arborization of mushroom body extrinsic neurons.

label: mushroom body gamma lobe slice
description: Subdivision of mushroom body perpendicular to the gamma lobe axis whose boundaries correspond to the boundaries of terminal arborization of mushroom body extrinsic neurons.

label: mushroom body alpha lobe slice
description: Subdivision of mushroom body perpendicular to the alpha lobe axis whose boundaries correspond to the boundaries of terminal arborization of mushroom body extrinsic neurons.

label: disc epithelium proper
description: A columnar epithelial monolayer with marked apical-basal polarity: the apical side faces the disc lumen, the basal side is underlain by a basal lamina. The anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the imaginal discs runs through the middle of this epithelium. Cells in this epithelium are coupled by gap junctions, but this coupling is much reduced across the anterior-posterior compartment boundary.

label: mushroom body beta' lobe slice
description: Subdivision of mushroom body perpendicular to the beta' lobe axis whose boundaries correspond to the boundaries of terminal arborization of mushroom body extrinsic neurons.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VP3 mALT adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron whose dendrites innervate the antennal lobe glomerulus VP3 bilaterally. It fasciculates with the medial antennal lobe tract mALT to innervate the mushroom body and lateral horn. This neuron responds to cooling.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir84a
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 84a (FBgn0037501) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2a and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VL2a (Grosjean et al., 2011; Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the antennal coeloconic sensillum ac4 (Benton et al., 2009).

label: mushroom body beta' lobe layer
description: Subdivision of the mushroom body beta' lobe along its longitudinal axis.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VP3 lALT PN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron whose dendrites innervate the antennal lobe glomerulus VP3, uni- or bilaterally. It fasciculates with the lateral antennal lobe tract lALT to innervate the posterior slope and posterior lateral protocerebrum. This neuron responds to cooling, showing strong adaptation to sustained temperature decreases.

label: lateral antennal lobe tract projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that fasciculates with the lateral antennal lobe tract of the adult brain. This class includes various multiglomerular projection neurons that do not innervate the mushroom body and some uniglomerular projection neurons (with dendrites in VL1 and VP1) whose axons terminate in the mushroom body calyx and the lateral horn.

label: oocyte associated follicular epithelium
description: A columnar epithelium which surrounds the oocyte except at the anterior where the oocyte contacts the nurse cells. The basal side of this epithelium is associated with a basement membrane and faces away from the oocyte. The apical side faces the vitelline membrane, which separates this epithelium from the oocyte.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VP2/VP3 lALT PN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron whose dendrites innervate the antennal lobe glomeruli VP2 and VP3. It fasciculates with the lateral antennal lobe tract lALT to innervate the lateral horn, posterior slope and posterior lateral protocerebrum. This neuron responds to heating.

label: DPLc1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLc1 neuroblast.

label: enterocyte of posterior adult midgut epithelium
description: A large polyploid cuboidal or low-columnar epithelial cell with its nucleus in the middle and a mass of microvilli (brush border) on its apical surface. On its basal side, extensive infoldings of the plasma membrane form a labyrinth which fills the lower half of the cell. It is attached to adjacent enterocytes by smooth septate junctions.

label: enterocyte
description: Specialised epithelial cell of the adult midgut. A large polyploid cuboidal or low-columnar epithelial cell with its nucleus in the middle and a mass of microvilli (brush border) on its apical surface. On its basal side, extensive infoldings of the plasma membrane form a labyrinth which fills the lower half of the cell. It is attached to adjacent enterocytes by smooth septate junctions.

label: DPLc2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLc2 neuroblast.

label: DPLc3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLc3 neuroblast.

label: anterior adult hindgut
description: Segment of the adult hindgut extending from the pylorus to the rectal valve.

label: DPLc4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLc4 neuroblast.

label: DPLc5 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLc5 neuroblast.

label: chitinous intima of the adult foregut
description: The chitinous intima which lines the adult foregut.

label: chitinous intima
description: Chitinous layer lining an internal epithelium.

label: adult foregut
description: Anterior-most region of the adult alimentary canal. It consists (from anterior to posterior) of the posterior the pharynx (cibarium), esophagus, the crop, the stomodeal valve and part of the proventriculus.

label: DPLl1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLl1 neuroblast.

label: chitinous intima of the adult hindgut
description: Chitinous intima which lines the adult hingut.

label: DPLl2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DPLl2 neuroblast.

label: adult sex peptide abdominal ganglion neuron
description: Ascending neuron located in the female adult abdominal ganglion. Its soma is located either on the dorsal or ventral surface of the abdominal ganglion. It arborizes extensively within the abdominal ganglion, in the same region as the adult sex peptide sensory neuron, and sends an ascending projection along the dorsal midline into the brain. There, it projects ipsilaterally in the periesophageal region and bilaterally in the dorsal protocerebrum, including the pars intercerebralis. These neurons are only found in females. There is one on either side of the midline.

label: adult sex peptide sensory neuron
description: Sensory neuron located in the female abdominal ganglion that responds to sex peptide. These neurons are located along the reproductive tract, with one on each lateral oviduct and 3 on either side of the uterus. They project fine processes between the muscle and epithelial cell layer and the lumen of the uterus. An additional branch bifurcates close to the soma and innervates the lower region of the common oviduct.

label: optic-lobe-associated cortex glial cell
description: Glial cell that makes up the layer of optic-lobe-associated cortex glia. It is located underneath the subperineurial glial sheath, closest to the neuroepithelium in third instar larva and adults.

label: subretinal pigment layer
description: Thick layer of pigmented cells that lies directly underneath the retina, surrounded by the pigment rim, and immediately below the basal laminal of the retina. The pigment cells in this layer contain the same pigments as secondary and tertiary pigment cells. Subretinal glial cells are also found in this layer.

label: pigment rim
description: Thick band of secondary and tertiary-like pigment cells that circumscribes the retina of the adult eye and runs from the surface to the base. Basally, it surrounds the subretinal pigment layer.

label: structure
description: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

label: morphology
description: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

label: serotonergic SE0 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located anterior to the SE1 cluster. It the larva, there is one cluster on either side of the ventral midline in the dorsal tip of the subesophageal zone, in the tritocerebrum. There around 4 cells in this cluster, 3 of which innervate the prothoracic gland.

label: adult moonwalker descending neuron
description: Descending neuron whose soma is located on the midline, near the medial posterior protocerebrum of the adult brain. It arborizes bilaterally in the medial ventral protocerebrum and subesophageal zone. Axonal terminals are located in the subesophageal zone and bilaterally in the thoracic neuromeres. This neuron is involved in triggering backward walking in flies.

label: adult moonwalker ascending neuron
description: Ascending neuron located in the adult thoracico-abdominal ganglion. Its soma is located in the cell rind of the metathoracic ganglion. It arborizes in the metathoracic ganglion and projects into the medial subesophageal zone in the brain. Some presynaptic terminals are also observed in the metathoracic ganglion, wing neuropil and in other areas of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. This neuron is involved in facilitating backward walking in flies.

label: peripheral perisynaptic glial cell
description: Glial cell in a neuromuscular junction that interacts with fine terminal axon branches of a motor neuron that synapse with the muscle. Its cell body is located in the periphery, near the terminal branches of the motor axons. Several perisynaptic glial cell are present over the muscle surface, with each one occupying a distinct territory and contacting local synapses.

label: adult male Ilp7 posterior abdominal ganglion neuron
description: Serotonergic motor neuron of the adult male that is located in the posterior region of the abdominal ganglion. It innervates the seminal vesicle. There are 4 of these neurons, in a dorsal cluster.

label: adult posterior abdominal ganglion neuron
description: Neuron located in the posterior region of the abdominal ganglion. These neurons are sexually dimorphic, fasciculate with the abdominal nerve trunk and innervate the reproductive organs of the adult. These neurons are generated by post-embryonic neurogenesis in late L3 larvae.

label: DALcl2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALcl2 neuroblast.

label: adult anterior midgut epithelium
description: Columnar epithelium with a clear apical border (i.e. no brush border).

label: DALl1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALl1 neuroblast.

label: chitinous intima of the cardial valve
description: Cuticle layer that lines the regions of the adult proventriculus (cardia) that derive from the foregut, including the inner and intermediate layers. The cuticle is thicker in the inner layer than in other regions of the proventriculus, forming several longitudinal folds and causing the esophageal lumen to appear irregular in cross-section.

label: DALcm1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALcm1 neuroblast.

label: DALcm2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALcm2 neuroblast.

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle DA1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000591) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle DA3
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 3 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle DA2
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle 2 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: DAMd2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DAMd2 neuroblast.

label: DAMd3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DAMd3 neuroblast.

label: ventral trunk epidermis primordium
description: Primordium of the ventral trunk epidermis of the late extended germ band and dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the embryonic ventral trunk epidermis.

label: DALv1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALv1 neuroblast.

label: adult midgut pyloric epithelium
description: Squamous epithelium which forms the posterior-most region of the midgut epithelium, from the Malpighian tubules to the beginning of the hindgut.

label: trunk ectoderm
description: The region of the ectoderm posterior to the cephalic furrow.

label: DALcl1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DAlcl1 neuroblast.

label: adult cardial valve muscle
description: Layer of longitudinal muscle fibers found between the inner and intermediate layers of the adult proventriculus (cardia). These muscle fibers are embedded in an extracellular matrix that fills the available space.

label: adult visceral muscle
description: Visceral muscle of the adult.

label: cardial valve
description: A deep fold in the posterior-most part of the adult foregut epithelium that is formed by the two inner layers of the adult proventriculus (cardia). The space between the two layers of this fold, hilus of the cardia, is filled with longitudinal muscle fibers. The cells of the epithelium are cuboidal to columnar and are vacuolate.

label: transverse antennal lobe t4ALT tract
description: Transverse antennal lobe tract that bifurcates to innervate the lateral horn and the posterior lateral protocerebrum. The branch that extends to the lateral horn passes dorsal to the mushroom body pedunculus, whereas the other branch runs ventral to it. Both branches run posteriorly to the fan-shaped body.

label: transverse antennal lobe t2ALT tract
description: Transverse antennal lobe tract that innervates the lateral horn and mushroom body calyx, passing through the mushroom body pedunculus and posterior to the fan-shaped body.

label: transverse antennal lobe t1ALT tract
description: Transverse antennal lobe tract that innervates the lateral horn, passing dorsal to the mushroom body pedunculus and posterior to the fan-shaped body.

label: larval serotonergic SE0 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located anterior to the SE0 cluster. There is one cluster on either side of the ventral midline in the dorsal tip of the subesophageal zone, in the tritocerebrum. The soma of these neurons is located close to where the antennal nerve extends out of the brain. These neurons fasciculate with the antennal nerve and project anteriorly to the pharyngeal muscle, as well as posteriorly along the esophagus by fasciculating with the recurrent nerve and then the frontal nerve, to terminate in the anterior region of the midgut. They also innervate the prothoracic gland, by fasciculating with the nervus corporis cardiaci I, and the proventriculus. three of these neurons innervate only the prothoracic gland and proventriculus.

label: pharyngeal muscle
description: A hypodermal muscle of the larval head that is connected to the pharynx or some closely associated structure.

label: anterior embryonic/larval midgut
description: Anterior region of the embryonic/larval midgut.

label: adult CCAP/burs subesophageal neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007) and Bursicon (FBgn0038901) and Partner of Bursicon (FBgn0264810), whose soma is located in the subesophageal zone. There are 2 neurons in each hemisphere, one in a more medial position and one more posterior. The main neurite of the posterior neuron extends towards the midline and arborizes. It then crosses the midline and descends into the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, arborizing mainly in the contralateral thoracic and abdominal neuromeres. In the latter, the arborizations are at similar locations to the ones of the bursicon abdominal neurons. It exists the central nervous system via one of the abdominal nerves.

label: adult CCAP subesophageal neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), whose soma is located in the subesophageal zone. There are 4 neurons in each hemisphere: one more anterior, 2 in a medial position and one more posterior. These neurons descend into the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: adult CCAP protocerebrum neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses CCAP (Crustacean cardioactive peptide) (FBgn0039007), whose soma is located in the protocerebrum. There is 1 neuron in each hemisphere.

label: procephalic glioblast
description: Any glioblast (FBbt:00005145) that is part of some central brain primordium (FBbt:00005542).

label: DAMv1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DAMv1 neuroblast.

label: DAMv2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DAMv2 neuroblast.

label: adult cerebrum
description: The cerebral ganglion, minus the optic lobes. It includes the first three neuromeres: protocerebrum, deutocerebrum and tritocerebrum.

label: DAMd1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DAMd1 neuroblast.

label: embryonic/larval anterior optic tubercle primordial
description: The primordium of the adult anterior optic tubercle in the larval brain. It consists of a circular domain of tufts of filopodia, with undifferentiated synapses, that branch off axon bundles at the anterior protocerebrum, lateral and adjacent to the vertical lobe of the mushroom body.

label: embryonic/larval superior medial protocerebrum
description: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain that is located dorsal to the medial lobe of the mushroom body. It is the larval counterpart of the adult superior medial protocerebrum.

label: lipid localization
description: Any process in which a lipid is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: macromolecule localization
description: Any process in which a macromolecule is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: CM5 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the CM5 neuroblast.

label: neuroblast CM5
description: A type II centromedial neuroblast of the posterior deutocerebrum.

label: embryonic/larval ventromedial cerebrum
description: One of a group of synaptic neuropil domains of the larval brain which are located ventral to the mushroom body and are grouped around the long axon tracts connecting the larval protocerebrum to the ventral nerve cord. This medially located compartment contacts the antennal lobe posteriorly. The lateral cervical tract ascends through the center of this compartment. It is the larval counterpart of the adult ventromedial neuropils.

label: BAlp1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAlp1 neuroblast.

label: BAlp2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAlp2 neuroblast.

label: BAlp3 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAlp3 neuroblast.

label: Balv lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the Balv neuroblast.

label: CM2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the CM2 neuroblast.

label: neuroblast CM2
description: A type II centromedial neuroblast of the posterior deutocerebrum.

label: frontal median commissure
description: Commissure located dorsal and anterior to of the fan-shaped body which connects the two superior medial protocerebrum neuropils of the adult brain.

label: lateral accessory lobe commissure
description: Commissure connecting the lateral accessory lobes running in front of the ellipsoid body, dorsal and anterior of the fan-shaped body of the adult brain.

label: BAla4 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAla4 neuroblast.

label: anterior dorsal commissure
description: A commissure located anterior and dorsal of the fan-shaped body which connects the two superior lateral protocerebrum synaptic neuropil domains of the adult brain.

label: DALd1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the DALd1 neuroblast.

label: BAmd1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAmd1 neuroblast.

label: inferior ventral body commissure
description: Commissure of the adult brain located anterior and ventral of the fan-shaped body which connects left and right ventral bodies.

label: BAmv2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAmv2 neuroblast.

label: superior posterior lateral protocerebrum commissure
description: Commissure of the adult brain that is located dorsal to the mushroom body pedunculus and between the fan-shaped body and antler. It passes near the lateral horn but does not enter the neuropil. It demarcates the boundary between the superior and inferior clamp.

label: sub-ellipsoid commissure
description: Commissure located anterior and ventral of the fan-shaped body that connects left and right ventral bodies.

label: BAmas1 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAmas1 neuroblast.

label: superior arch commissure
description: Commissure located above the fan-shaped body (FB), connecting the superior medial protocerebrum (SMP), superior clamp and inferior clamp. It demarcates the boundaries of FB (superior region) and SMP (inferior region).

label: BAmas2 lineage neuron
description: Neuron developing from the BAmas2 neuroblast.

label: anterior cross
description: Commissure located dorsal and anterior of the fan-shaped body which links the two superior medial and lateral protocerebra of the adult brain.

label: abdominal sternite 2
description: Any sternite (FBbt:00004477) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00003026).

label: sternite
description: The ventral plate (sclerite) of an adult abdominal segment.

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 2
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 2
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal sternite 4
description: Any sternite (FBbt:00004477) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028).

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 4
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 4
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal sternite 3
description: Any sternite (FBbt:00004477) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027).

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 3
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 3
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: Wheeler's organ
description: A chordotonal organ associated with the anterior of abdominal sternite 2. It is visible externally as a raised patch of smooth cuticle without trichomes or bristles. It consists of two clusters of scolopidia (FBbt:00005217), one on either side of the ventral midline (Smith and Shepherd, 1996). The sensory neurons of Wheeler's organ project through the second segmental nerve of the abdomen and then through the abdominal neuromeres via dorso-lateral tract of the ventral fasciculus (DLV), to terminate in the prothoracic neuromere (Smith and Shepherd, 1996).

label: abdominal sternite 6
description: Sternite of the 6th abdominal segment. In females this is a single, midline crossing sclerite. In males, it is a bilaterally sclerite - the two plates meet anteriorly at the ventral midline.

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 6
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 6
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal sternite 5
description: Any sternite (FBbt:00004477) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029).

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 5
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 5
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal sternite 11
description: Any sternite (FBbt:00004477) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00003035).

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 7
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 7
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: fascicle of optic foci
description: Longitudinal tract of the adult midbrain connecting anterior and posterior domains within the ventro-lateral protocerebrum and deutocerebrum.

label: medial fascicle
description: A vertical axon tract within the protocerebrum connected to the superior/inferior medial protocerebrum and to the ventral body.

label: sensory perception of pain
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a painful stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Pain is medically defined as the physical sensation of discomfort or distress caused by injury or illness, so can hence be described as a harmful stimulus which signals current (or impending) tissue damage. Pain may come from extremes of temperature, mechanical damage, electricity or from noxious chemical substances. This is a neurological process.

label: posterior lateral fascicle
description: An arch-like bundle of neuronal fibers connecting the posterior lateral protocerebrum (PLP) and the superior intermediate protocerebrum (SIP). It demarcates the boundary between the superior clamp and lateral horn/superior lateral protocerebrum (SLP). The posterior lateral fascicle makes a steep curve near the anterior medial edge of the lateral horn (LH), where it narrowly intersects the trajectories of the mALT, mlALT and lALT. It can be divided into two sections: the lateral section between the PLP and the LH tip, and the superior section between the LH tip and the SIP (Tanaka et al., 2012).

label: lateral medial fascicle
description: A transverse axon tract in the protocerebrum which is connected to the inferior lateral protocerebrum, the ventro-lateral protocerebrum and inferior medial protocerebrum.

label: neural lamella
description: Acellular sheath which forms the outermost layer of the central nervous system. It consists, in part, of a matrix of 'collagen-like' fibers and is invaded by tracheoles.

label: perineurium
description: The outer two layers of glial cells that cover the central nervous system and the nerves. The outer layer is the perineurial sheath (sometimes referred to as the perineurial sheath outer layer); the inner layer is the sub-perineural glial sheath (sometimes referred to as the perineurial sheath inner layer).

label: posterior tract of the ventral body
description: Longitudinal tract of the adult midbrain connecting the ventral body and central complex to the inferior medial/lateral protocerebrum.

label: embryonic/larval cardial valve
description: A deep fold of the posterior-most part of the foregut epithelium that is part of the embryonic/larval proventriculus (cardia). It consists of a short neck and a blunt conical head, with the esophageal lumen opening at its apex. It is composed from the two inner layers of the proventriculus.

label: cell communication
description: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: neurotransmitter transport
description: The directed movement of a neurotransmitter into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Neurotransmitters are any chemical substance that is capable of transmitting (or inhibiting the transmission of) a nerve impulse from a neuron to another cell.

label: anterograde trans-synaptic signaling
description: Cell-cell signaling from pre to post-synapse, across the synaptic cleft

label: adult abdominal spiracle 7
description: Most posterior of the adult abdominal spiracles. It is located lateral to the posterior of tergite 6.

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 9
description: Tracheal branch of the seventh abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 10) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: adult abdominal spiracle 6
description: Any adult spiracle (FBbt:00003120) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00003030) and that connected to some adult abdominal spiracular branch 8 (FBbt:00003080).

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 8
description: Tracheal branch of the sixth abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 8) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: adult abdominal spiracle 3
description: Any adult spiracle (FBbt:00003120) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027) and that connected to some adult abdominal spiracular branch 5 (FBbt:00003077).

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 5
description: Tracheal branch of the third abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 5) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: adult spiracle
description: Spiracle of the adult.

label: pleural membrane
description: Membrane that is found laterally, between the tergites, on the dorsal side, and the sternites on the ventral side of the adult external abdomen. The abdominal spiracles are found on the most anterior region of the pleural membrane.

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch
description: Tracheal branch of an abdominal segment (tracheal metameres 3-10) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: adult abdominal spiracle 5
description: Any adult spiracle (FBbt:00003120) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029) and that connected to some adult abdominal spiracular branch 7 (FBbt:00003079).

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 7
description: Tracheal branch of the fifth abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 7) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: adult abdominal spiracle 4
description: Any adult spiracle (FBbt:00003120) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028) and that connected to some adult abdominal spiracular branch 6 (FBbt:00003078).

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 6
description: Tracheal branch of the fourth abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 6) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus 2
description: Glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe located on the same frontal plane as glomerulus DM3 (a landmark glomerulus). It lies dorsomedial to the posterior part of glomerulus V, and lateral to glomerulus VM6.

label: synaptic transmission, cholinergic
description: The process of communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse using the neurotransmitter acetylcholine.

label: adult external abdomen
description: The external structures that make up the adult abdomen.

label: female analia
description: The entire set of external structures in the distal half of the female abdomen, i.e. segments 7--11, that makes up the anal apparatus. It develops from the female genital disc.

label: analia
description: The entire set of external structures in the distal half of the abdomen, i.e. segments 7--11, that makes up the anal apparatus. It develops from the genital disc.

label: female terminalia
description: Collective name for the internal and external structures of the most posterior segments of the adult female that develop from the female genital disc.

label: terminalia
description: The entire set of internal and external structures of the genitalia and analia in the distal half of the abdomen, i.e. segments 7--11. It develops from the genital disc.

label: genitalia
description: A collective name for the external and internal organs directly participating in the propagation of the species.

label: male analia
description: The entire set of external structures in the distal half of the male abdomen, i.e. segments 7--11, that makes up the anal apparatus. It develops from the male genital disc.

label: male terminalia
description: Collective name for the internal and external structures of the genitalia and analia of the most posterior segments of the adult male that develop from the male genital disc.

label: male genitalia
description: The entire set of internal and external structures in the distal half of the male abdomen, i.e. segments 7--11, that makes up the genital apparatus. It develops from the male genital disc.

label: female genitalia
description: The entire set of internal and external structures in the distal half of the female abdomen, i.e. segments 7--11, that makes up the genital apparatus. It develops from the female genital disc.

label: epiproct
description: The dorsal anal plate of the female. It has an average of 18 bristles of which two are large.

label: presumptive epiproct
description: Region of the thickened posterior part of the dorsal epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the epiproct.

label: female gonopod
description: Paired chitinous vaginal plate bordered by 11-16 thorn bristles, one long bristle and three sensilla trichoidea.

label: presumptive female gonopod
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the female gonopod.

label: hypoproct
description: The ventral anal plate of the female. It has an average of 19 bristles of which four are large.

label: presumptive hypoproct
description: Region of the thickened posterior part of the dorsal epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the hypoproct.

label: abdominal 7 female lateral muscle 141
description: Muscle of the adult female abdominal segment 7 that extends along the lateral abdominal sternite wall, posterior to lateral muscle 140.

label: female abdominal muscle
description: Any skeletal muscle of abdomen (FBbt:00003447) that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: male abdominal 5 muscle
description: Bilaterally symmetrical muscle spanning the fifth abdominal segment in adult males.

label: male abdominal muscle
description: Abdominal muscle that is specific to males.

label: male abdominal sternite
description: Sternite of the adult male abdomen.

label: abdominal 7 female lateral muscle 140
description: Muscle of the adult female abdominal segment 7 that extends along the lateral abdominal sternite wall, anterior to lateral muscle 141.

label: genital arch
description: Horseshoe-shaped tergite which, dorsally, surrounds the male anal plates. It contains about 15 peripheral bristles. The left and right sides of the genital arch are connected by the pons.

label: presumptive genital arch
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the genital arch.

label: female rectal muscle
description: Muscle of the posterior adult hindgut (rectum).

label: anal plate
description: Paired tergite that lies immediately lateral to the anus in males.

label: presumptive anal plate
description: Region of the thickened posterior part of the dorsal epithelium of the male genital disc that will develop into the anal plate.

label: abdominal 8 female transverse ventral muscle 151
description: Muscle of the adult female abdominal segment 8 that extends dorsoposteriorly from the ventral region of the segment.

label: clasper
description: Paired hook-shaped chitinous lobe that extends ventrally from the pons and surrounds the male genital opening. It contains 25 thorn-like bristles (clasper teeth) in a curved band and one long bristle at the end.

label: presumptive clasper
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the clasper.

label: lateral plate
description: Tergite ventral to the posterior lobe and clasper in the male genitalia. It contains about 15 long thin bristles.

label: female ventral rectal muscle 153
description: Muscle of the female rectum that extends anterioposteriorly in the ventral region of the sclerite. It is ventral to the dorsal rectal muscle 152.

label: female dorsal rectal muscle 152
description: Muscle of the female rectum that extends dorsoventrally in the dorsal region of the sclerite. It is dorsal to the ventral rectal muscle 153.

label: male gonopod
description: Recurved, slender process on either side of the base of the penis. It articulates anteriorly with the hypandrium, and posteriorly with the 10th sternite, bridging the caudal ends of the hypandrium.

label: penis
description: Distal part of the aedeagus consisting of a median, scleratised, pointed lobe through which the ejaculatory duct discharges.

label: pons
description: A bridge-like component of the male terminalia that connects the two sides of the genital arch.

label: presumptive pons
description: Region of the male genital disc that will develop into the pons.

label: abdominal 8 female lateral ventral muscle 150
description: Muscle of the adult female abdominal segment 8 that extends along the lateral abdominal sternite wall from anterior to posterior.

label: presumptive lateral plate
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the lateral plate.

label: abdominal 7 female sternal muscle 144
description: Muscle of the adult female abdominal segment 7 that extends from the anterior border of the segment dorsoposteriorly. It attaches anteriorly to the same region as the ventral muscle 142.

label: posterior lobe
description: Lobe on the posterior region of the genital arch of the adult male terminalia. It is dorsal to the clasper and lateral plate.

label: primary metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving those compounds which are formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

label: decasternum
description: The sternite of the male abdominal segment 10.

label: hypandrium
description: The ninth abdominal sternum of the male extended beneath the genital chamber.

label: presumptive hypandrium
description: Region of the male genital disc that will develop into the hypandrium.

label: hypandrial process
description: Paired process of the hypandrium which encloses the foramen of the penis. It contains one large and a group of three small hypandrial bristles, and a group of fine hypandrial hairs.

label: multicellular organism metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways in a single multicellular organism that occur at the tissue, organ, or organismal level. These processes, unlike cellular metabolism, can include transport of substances between cells when that transport is required.

label: basal apodeme of penis
description: Long, slender apodeme extending from the base of the aedeagus into the body.

label: aedeagus
description: The main part of the male genitalia used for copulation. The distal portion, through which the male ejaculates, is the penis. Four, slender, recurved processes are immovably attached to the base of the penis. Internally the aedeagus is connected to the aedeagal apodeme and the ejaculatory bulb.

label: ventral paramere
description: Recurved, slender process on the ventral side of the base of the penis. There are two of these.

label: dorsal paramere
description: Recurved, slender process on the dorsal side of the base of the penis. There are two of these.

label: adult longitudinal muscle
description: Longitudinal muscle of the adult. It surrounds the intestinal tract and ducts of the reproductive system, together with a layer of circular muscle.

label: phallic foramen
description: Foramen of the adult male genitalia through which the aedagus is extruded.

label: presumptive penis
description: Region of the anterior lobe and ventral lateral region of the male genital disc that will develop into the penis.

label: adult esophageal muscle
description: Visceral muscle of the adult esophagus.

label: adult esophagus
description: Portion of the adult foregut that extends from the cibarium anteriorly, through the brain to the proventriculus posteriorly.

label: adult esophageal circular muscle
description: Circular muscle of the adult esophagus. There is a single layer of circular muscles forming bands 4-6um wide and 3um thick. The fiber muscles at the anterior end of the esophagus, near the cibarium, are 6-7.5um thick.

label: abdominal 4 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000838) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: A1-7 VO2 motor neuron
description: RP1 motor neuron of A1-7. Its dendritic arborization occupies the lateral domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve and innervates the VO2 muscle (Mauss et al., 2009) of the segment immediately posterior to it via type Ib boutons.

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: adult midgut circular muscle
description: Circular muscle of the adult midgut. Circular muscles are surrounded by the outer longitudinal fibers.

label: adult midgut muscle
description: Muscle of the adult midgut. These muscles surround the thick epithelium and are loosely lined by a peritrophic membrane. The musculature of the hindgut is weakly developed (Miller, 1950).

label: abdominal 5 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000838) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000928) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: hindgut
description: A posterior part of the alimentary canal derived from the ectoderm. It extends anteriorly from close to the point of attachment of the Malpighian tubules to the anus. It is lined on its luminal side by an impermeable cuticle (Skaer, 1993).

label: germarium cap cell
description: Somatic cell found posterior to the terminal filament. There is a group of 2-6 cells which are usually positioned asymmetrically on one side of the germarium tip, capping the underlying germ line stem cells.

label: adult midgut longitudinal muscle
description: Longitudinal muscle of the adult midgut. The longitudinal fibers surround the circular muscle fibers.

label: abdominal 7 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: adult esophageal sphincter muscle
description: Circumferential muscle fibers that forms a narrow band around the esophagus, at the anterior end of the cardia.

label: abdominal 1 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000703) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult cardial muscle
description: Thin scattering of muscle fibers that covers the outer layer of the adult proventriculus (cardia). It is one cell thick, except at the anterior end of the proventriculus, where the muscle of the outer layer meets the muscle of the esophagus.

label: adult proventriculus
description: Bulb-shaped organ at the junction of the foregut and midgut that regulates the passage of food into the midgut. The proventriculus folds back on itself to produce three epithelial layers: internally the posterior region of the esophagus, an intermediate (recurrent) layer derived from the ectodermal foregut and midgut and an external anterior projection of the endodermal midgut, which grows over the esophageal region. The inner two layers form the gastric valve (cardial valve) while the outer layer is defined as the wall of the proventriculus. The cuticle the lines the inner wall is thicker than other regions in the cardia, and it forms several longitudinal folds, causing the esophageal lumen to appear irregular in cross section. Between the inner and intermediate layers is the hilus which contains muscle in a fibrous extracellular matrix. Between the intermediate and outer wall is the cardia lumen, which opens posteriorly into the lumen of the midgut. The anterior region secretes the peritrophic membrane into the cardia lumen.

label: abdominal 2 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 3 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000748) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 3 VO2 motor neuron
description: Any RP1 motor neuron (FBbt:00001452) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 4 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000793) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: adult crop circular muscle
description: Circular muscle fibers of the of adult crop. In the stalk, it consists of wide bands 1.5um thick and 3-7um wide. In the sac, thick muscle fibers extend around the base of each lobe, converging posteriorly, and the distended portions of the wall are covered with a plexus of branched and interlacing fibers 1-3um thick.

label: polyfusome
description: A gelatinous mass assembled by the fusion of the adjacent fusomes formed at consecutive cystocyte divisions in Drosophila, resulting in a large branched structure.

label: spectrosome
description: Small and spherical fusome found on the anterior region of the germline stem cell or cystoblast, in region 1 of the germarium. It becomes branched in the progeny of the latter, in the cystocytes.

label: RP2 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron whose large cell body is located in the next anterior segment which it innervates, at the extreme dorsal surface of the CNS above the junction of the anterior commissure and the longitudinal connective.

label: type Is motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that synapsed via type Is bouton to some muscle cell (FBbt:00005074).

label: A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000467) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: A1-7 dorsal acute muscle
description: Any dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000475) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: adult posterior hindgut circular muscle
description: Circular muscle of the adult posterior hindgut, located as an outside layer to the inner longitudinal fibers. It is a single layer of thick, closely set circular fibers. Muscular fibers are 3um thick and 10um wide in the rectal sac, and 3-5um thick in the posterior rectum.

label: adult hindgut muscle
description: Muscle of the adult hindgut.

label: germarium region 2
description: Large middle portion of the germarium that contains 16-cell cysts.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult posterior hindgut longitudinal muscle
description: Longitudinal muscle of the adult posterior hindgut, located as an inside layer to the outer circular fibers. Longitudinal fibers are 3-5um wide and 1um thick.

label: germarium region 2b
description: Posterior region of germarium region 2. Individual cysts in this region have been fully separated by inwardly migrating follicle cells.

label: germarium region 2a
description: Anterior region of germarium region 2. Cysts in this region have not been fully enclosed by follicle cells, and directly contact neighboring cysts.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: adult alary muscle 1
description: Anterior most of the alary muscles, connecting the adult heart, close to ostia 1, to the front edge of the third abdominal tergite.

label: abdominal tergite 3
description: Any tergite (FBbt:00004476) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027).

label: oogonial cell
description: Female germline stem cell. Each division of an oogonial cell gives rise to one cystoblast and one female germline stem cell.

label: cystoblast
description: Female germline cell which is the daughter of a female germline stem cell. It is found in region 1 of the germarium. It divides four times to give rise to 16 daughter cystocytes, which together form a germline cyst. Division is through a cleavage-like process, with the daughter cells being smaller than the parent cystoblast.

label: female germline stem cell
description: Female germline cell and stem cell from which all other female germline cells develop.

label: A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: RP3 motor neuron of A1-7. It innervates the internal ventral longitudinal muscles 3 and 4. Its dendritic arborization occupies the intermediate domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve fasciculating with the ISNb nerve branch and innervates the VL3/4 muscles of the next posterior segment with type Ib boutons.

label: RP3 motor neuron
description: RP motor neuron of the 3-1 lineage whose cell body is located ventral and lateral to RP1 and RP4, and which projects an axon contralaterally.

label: A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: abdominal 1 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: adult alary muscle 3
description: Third anterior-most of the alary muscles, connecting the adult heart, close to ostia 3, to the front edge of the fifth abdominal tergite.

label: abdominal tergite 5
description: Any tergite (FBbt:00004476) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029).

label: nurse cell ring canal
description: Cytoplasmic bridge that connects a nurse cell to other nurse cells or oocyte.

label: adult alary muscle 2
description: Second anterior-most of the alary muscles, connecting the adult heart, close to ostia 2, to the front edge of the fourth abdominal tergite.

label: abdominal tergite 4
description: Any tergite (FBbt:00004476) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028).

label: nurse cell
description: One of a group of 15 germ cells that lie anterior to the oocyte within the egg chamber. Their cytoplasm is contiguous with the oocyte via ring canals.

label: abdominal 2 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: adult salivary gland suspensor muscle
description: A muscle that extends from the anterior end of the salivary gland to the cardia. (Miller, 1950 pg 440-1, 451).

label: rectal circular muscle
description: Circular muscle of the adult narrow posterior end of the rectum, that forms part of the adult rectal sphincter. The rectal epithelium forms numerous longitudinal folds and the circular muscles act as an anal sphincter.

label: germarium region 3
description: Posterior region of the germarium. It is where stage 1 egg chambers are found, before they separate from the germarium.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: adult heart suspensory fibril
description: Fine fibril that is found in a meshwork layer between the outer ventral longitudinal muscle layer and the circular muscle layer of the adult heart. The fibrils run parallel to the longitudinal axis of the heart and are crosslinked by elements of a similar nature.

label: abdominal 5 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal motor neuron (FBbt:00002207) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 3 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: adult alary muscle 4
description: Posterior-most of the alary muscles, connecting the adult heart, close to ostia 4, to the front edge of the fifth abdominal tergite.

label: abdominal tergite 6
description: Any tergite (FBbt:00004476) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00003030).

label: abdominal 4 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: lipid digestion
description: The whole of the physical, chemical, and biochemical processes carried out by living organisms to break down ingested lipids into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: multicellular organismal catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances in multicellular organisms that occur at the tissue, organ, or organismal level. These processes, unlike cellular metabolism, can include transport of substances between cells when that transport is required.

label: nurse cell ring canal rim
description: The outer edge of a nurse cell ring canal.

label: ejaculatory bulb muscle
description: Muscle fibres that stretch from the end of the ejaculatory bulb apodeme to the side walls.

label: outer nurse cell ring canal rim
description: Electron opaque outer rim of a nurse cell ring canal.

label: adult heart ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Longitudinal muscle of the adult heart that spreads over the outer layer of the ventral side of this organ.

label: inner nurse cell ring canal rim
description: Electron dense inner rim of a nurse cell ring canal.

label: abdominal 5 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: multicellular organismal lipid catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids, occurring at the tissue, organ, or organismal level of a multicellular organism.

label: lipid catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids, compounds soluble in an organic solvent but not, or sparingly, in an aqueous solvent.

label: abdominal 2 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 3 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000747) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: A1-7 VO1 motor neuron
description: RP4 neuron of embryonic/larval segments A1-7. It innervates the internal ventral oblique muscle 1. Its dendritic arborization occupies the intermediate domain of the ventral nerve cord neuropil. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve fasciculating with the ISNb nerve branch and innervates the VO1 muscle (Mauss et al., 2009) of the next posterior segment via type Ib boutons.

label: abdominal 3 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: ovarian sheath muscle
description: Muscle layer of the ovarian sheath.

label: gonadal sheath muscle
description: Muscle layer of the adult gonadal sheath.

label: endobody
description: Spherical structure associated with the karyosome of the oocyte.

label: abdominal 3 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 4 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000792) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000837) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: testis sheath muscle
description: Muscle layer of the testis sheath.

label: karyosome
description: The condensed chromosomes of an oocyte.

label: abdominal 5 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000882) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: nurse cell fusome
description: A tube-shaped gelatinous mass that extends through each ring canal formed during the cycle of cystocyte divisions.

label: penis protractor muscle
description: Muscle of the adult male 9th sternite that originates from the basal part of the sternite and inserts upon the base of the penis. There is a pair of these muscles.

label: nurse cell spectrosome
description: Spherical fusome found in the cystocytes that will develop as nurse cells.

label: abdominal 7 VL3/4 motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 VL3/4 motor neuron (FBbt:00002215) that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: spermathecal duct longitudinal muscle
description: Longitudinal muscle that surrounds the duct that connects the spermatheca to the uterus.

label: presumptive oocyte
description: Cystocyte that will develop into the oocyte.

label: RP4 motor neuron
description: Motor neuron of the 3-1 lineage with a large cell body located adjacent to that of RP1.

label: A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of embryonic/larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: abdominal 1 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000702) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 6 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000927) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 VO1 motor neuron
description: Any RP4 motor neuron (FBbt:00001456) that synapsed via type Ib bouton to some A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) and that has soma location some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: thoracic neuroblast t
description: Neuroblast that is located in one of a bilateral pair of clusters of 3 neuroblasts at the dorsal margin of the cortex of each larval thoracic neuromere, just posterior to the al neuroblast.

label: pole granule
description: Dense organelles found in the pole plasm of female eggs. They are 0.2 to 0.5 micrometers in diameter, changing size during development. They lack a membrane and contain RNA granules, among other components.

label: A1-7 ventral motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the internal ventral oblique (except VO3 and VO6) and longitudinal muscles of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve fasciculating with the ISNb nerve branch. It is one of the common exciters of the A1-7 muscles, innervating the VL and VO muscles via type Is boutons (Mauss et al., 2009).

label: RP5 motor neuron
description: An RP motor neuron from neuroblast NB3-1 lineage. It is the most anteriorly located of the RP neurons.

label: A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any ventral longitudinal muscle that is part of larval abdominal segments 1-7. All of these span the segment - extending from one intersegmental apodeme to the next (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 171 and pg 119).

label: abdominal 5 ventral motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: thoracic neuroblast l
description: Neuroblast that is located in one of a bilateral pair of clusters of 6 neuroblasts at the lateral margin of each larval thoracic neuromere, just posterior to the al neuroblast.

label: ovarian basement membrane
description: An acellular membrane some 50 micrometers thick that is attached to the surface of the terminal filament, the germarium, and all developing egg chambers. The ovarian sheath sits on top (outside) of this.

label: epithelial sheath
description: Inner epithelial layer of the ovarian sheath.

label: abdominal 6 ventral motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 ventral motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron that innervates the internal dorsal acute and oblique muscles of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the posterior root of the intersegmental nerve and fasciculates with the ISNb or ISNd intersegmental nerve branches. It innervates the DO's and DA's via type II boutons.

label: abdominal 1 ventral motor neuron
