description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 ventral motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: thoracic neuroblast c
description: Lateral neuroblast of larval thoracic segment. One of a pair of these neuroblasts is present per thoracic segment - adjacent to but deeper than the al neuroblast at the lateral margin of the CNS.

label: abdominal 3 ventral motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 ventral motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral motor neuron (FBbt:00002231) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: thoracic neuroblast g
description: Neuroblast located in one of a bilateral pair of neuroblasts at the dorsal margin of the cortex near the posterior boundary of each larval thoracic neuromere.

label: ventral neurectoderm medial zone
description: A 2-3 cell wide mitotic domain of cells in the ventral neurectoderm that divide approximately synchronously during late stage 9 to early stage 10 and that extends laterally from the medial edge of the ventral neurectoderm to the medial edge of mVN (FBbt:00015550).

label: thoracic neuroblast x
description: One of a bilaterally symmetric pair of neuroblasts located near the anterior boundary of each thoracic segment, lateral to the lateral-most thoracic neuroblast s.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: thoracic neuroblast s
description: Neuroblast that is one of two rows of neuroblasts per hemi-neuromere of the larval thorax, 2 on either side of the midline per row.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron that innervates the internal ventral oblique and longitudinal muscles of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the posterior root of the intersegmental nerve and fasciculates with the ISNb or ISNd intersegmental nerve branches. It innervates the VO's and VL's via type II boutons.

label: type II motor neuron
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that synapsed via type II bouton to some muscle cell (FBbt:00005074).

label: thoracic neuroblast b1
description: Medial-most (?) of each pair of b neuroblasts.

label: thoracic neuroblast d3
description: Lateral-most (?) thoracic neuroblast d.

label: abdominal 1 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: thoracic neuroblast d2
description: Middle (?) thoracic neuroblast d.

label: abdominal 6 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 dorsal VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002239) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: thoracic neuroblast d1
description: Medial-most (?) thoracic neuroblast d.

label: ventral neurectoderm lateral zone 2
description: A segmentally repeated posterior mitotic domain of lVN. Division in this domain is slightly earlier than in lVN1 (FBbt:00015562).

label: ventral neurectoderm lateral zone
description: A 2-3 cell wide mitotic domain of cells in the ventral neurectoderm that divide approximately synchronously during late stage 8 to early stage 9 and that extends medially from the lateral edge of the ventral neurectoderm (FBbt:00001061).

label: ventral neurectoderm intermediate zone 1
description: Most anterior of the 4 segmentally repeated mitotic domains of iVN (FBbt:00015559), located within the engrailed stripe of each abdominal segment A1-7.

label: ventral neurectoderm intermediate zone
description: A 2-3 cell wide mitotic domain of cells in the ventral neurectoderm that divide approximately synchronously during mid-stage 9 and that extends medially from the medial edge of lVN (FBbt:00015558) to the lateral edge of mVN (FBbt:00015550).

label: ventral neurectoderm intermediate zone 2
description: The second most anterior of the 4 4 segmentally repeated mitotic domains of iVN (FBbt:00015559).

label: abdominal 3 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: thoracic neuroblast al
description: Anterior lateral neuroblast of larval thoracic segment. One of a pair of these neuroblasts is present per thoracic segment - located superficially and at the lateral margin of the CNS.

label: thoracic neuroblast w
description: Small neuroblast located medially, one either side of the midline, between the two rows of s neuroblasts.

label: abdominal 4 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: thoracic neuroblast M
description: Medial, superficial neuroblast of the larval thorax. A single neuroblast is located caudally in each thoracic segment, on the ventral midline.

label: abdominal 6 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: thoracic neuroblast b2
description: Lateral-most (?) of each pair of b neuroblasts.

label: abdominal 3 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Neuromodulatory motor neuron that innervates the internal ventral oblique and longitudinal muscles of larval abdominal segments A1 to A7. It exits the ventral nerve cord via the posterior root of the intersegmental nerve and fasciculates with the ISNb or ISNd intersegmental nerve branches. It innervates the VO's and VL's via type II boutons.

label: abdominal 4 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 7 ventral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 ventral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002247) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: A1-7 lateral transverse muscle
description: Any lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000472) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: abdominal 1 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: ventral neurectoderm medial zone 3
description: The second most posterior of the 4 segmentally repeated mitotic domains of mVN (FBbt:00015550).

label: ventral neurectoderm medial zone 4
description: The most posterior of the segmentally repeated mitotic domains of mVN.

label: ventral neurectoderm intermediate zone 3
description: The second most posterior of the 4 segmentally repeated mitotic domains of iVN (FBbt:00015559).

label: ventral neurectoderm intermediate zone 4
description: The most posterior of the segmentally repeated mitotic domains of iVN (FBbt:00015559).

label: ventral neurectoderm medial zone 1
description: Most anterior of the segmentally repeated mitotic domains of mVN (FBbt:00015550).

label: ventral neurectoderm medial zone 2
description: The second most anterior of the 4segmentally repeated mitotic domains of mVN (FBbt:00015550).

label: abdominal 6 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 1 neuroblast M
description: Medial, superficial neuroblast of larval abdominal segment 1. A single neuroblast is located caudally in each thoracic segment, on the ventral midline.

label: abdominal 1 neuroblast al
description: Anterior lateral neuroblast of larval abdominal segment 1. One of a pair of these neuroblasts is present per thoracic segment - located superficially and at the lateral margin of the CNS.

label: abdominal 7 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 2 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A2.

label: abdominal 2 dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in the larval abdominal segment A2.

label: abdominal 5 lateral VUM motor neuron
description: Any A1-7 lateral VUM motor neuron (FBbt:00002255) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 2 ventro-medial neuroblast
description: Neuroblast ventromedially located in the larval abdominal segment A2.

label: abdominal 3 dorso-lateral neuroblast
description: Neuroblast dorsolaterally located in larval abdominal segment A3.

label: abdominal 1 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal V neuron
description: V neuron of the embryonic and larval abdominal segments.

label: abdominal 2 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: V neuron
description: A neuron that is one of the two anterior most VUM neurons, and develops from the VUM precursor.

label: abdominal 5 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 V neuron
description: Any abdominal V neuron (FBbt:00002271) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Neuron of the embryonic or larval abdominal segment that is located laterally on each segment, anterior and posteriorly to the intersegmental nerve root. There are 5 of these cells: 3 anterior, and 2 posterior to the nerve root.

label: abdominal 1 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 7 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 1 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 lateral ipsisegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal lateral ipsisegmental neuron (FBbt:00002287) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 3 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 ventral intersegmental neuron
description: Any abdominal ventral intersegmental neuron (FBbt:00002295) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: prothoracic tibial sense organ
description: An oval sense organ in the dorsal, proximal prothoracic tibia. It is composed of 4 sensilla campaniform.

label: prothoracic leg sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some prothoracic leg (FBbt:00004663).

label: medullary tangential neuron vGlutMtnew2
description: Medullary tangential neuron that branches extensively in medulla layers M4 to M7. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: translobula plate neuron vGlutTlpnew1
description: Translobula plate neuron with dendritic terminals in lobula layers 4 to 6 and in all layers of the lobula plate. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: transmedullary neuron ChaTmnew2
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layer 5. It also has arborizations in medulla layers M5, M6, M7, M8 and M9. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: transmedullary neuron ChaTmnew3
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layer 1. It also has arborizations in medulla layers M4, M5, M7, M8 and M9. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: cation transport
description: The directed movement of cations, atoms or small molecules with a net positive charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: transmedullary Y neuron TmY12
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that terminates in lobula layer 3 and lobula plate layer 1. It displays arborizations in medulla layers M2, M3 and M9. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: transmedullary neuron ChaTmnew1
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layers 5 and 6. It also has arborizations in medulla layers M4, M5, M6 and M7. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: organic cation transport
description: The directed movement of organic cations into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Organic cations are atoms or small molecules with a positive charge which contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron ChaMinew3
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron that forms arborizations in medulla layers M3 to M7. It is very similar to Dm3, except that it shows blob-like protrusions in its terminals. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: lobula columnar neuron ChaLcnnew1
description: An extrinsic columnar neuron that arborizes in lobula layers 3, 4, 5 and 6 and extends its processes to the central brain. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron ChaMinew1
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron which projects along one medulla column without forming many lateral branches until it reaches layers M9 and M10, where it arborizes extensively. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron ChaMinew2
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron that forms extensive fine layered arborizations in medulla layers M3, M4, M5, M8 and M9. It is very similar to Mi10, except for its fine arborization pattern. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: transmedullary Y neuron ChaTmYnew1
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that terminates in lobula layers 2, 3 and 4 and layer 1 of lobula plate. It displays arborizations in medulla layers M4 to M9. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: medullary tangential neuron ChaMtnew1
description: Medullary tangential neuron with extensive branching that covers the proximal medulla. It arborizes in layers M3 to M9. Its cell body lies outside the medulla rind, close to the serpentine layer. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: late embryonic primordium of adult eye
description: Primordium of the late embryo that develops from the early primordium, and will give rise to the adult eye.

label: embryonic primordium of adult eye
description: Primordium of the embryo that will give rise to the adult eye. It corresponds to the most anterior region that develops from the visual primordium.

label: early embryonic primordium of adult eye
description: Early primordium of the late extended germ band and dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the adult eye. It develops from the visual primordium.

label: T neuron ChaTnew1
description: T neuron whose cell body sits in the cortex adjacent to the gap between the medulla and lobula plate. Its cell body fibers project through this gap before branching in the second optic chiasm. One branch projects into medulla layer M10, the other branch forms a terminal arborization in lobula layers 1 and 2 and lobula plate layer 1. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: lobula plate intrinsic neuron ChaLPinew1
description: A lobula plate intrinsic neuron that arborizes in lobula plate layers 1 and 2. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: lobula intrinsic neuron ChaLinew1
description: Lobula intrinsic neuron that arborizes in lobula layers 2, 3, 4 and 5 and extends its processes to the central brain. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: physical object quality
description: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi1
description: A lobula plate intrinsic neuron that arborizes in lobula plate layers 2 to 4. It seems to be capable of both glutamatergic and GABAergic neurotransmission.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron vGlutMinew2
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron which arborizes in medulla layer M1 and then projects along one medulla column without forming many lateral branches until it reaches layers M7 to M9, where it arborizes extensively. In M1, it contacts 14-15 columns in both the anterior-posterior and dorsal-ventral axes. In M7-M9 it innervates four to five columns in the dorsal-ventral axis (Jagadish et al., 2014). It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: medullary tangential neuron vGlutMtnew1
description: Medullary tangential neuron that branches extensively to cover the whole medulla, except for layers M1 and M10. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle LL1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 2 lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000600) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: medullary intrinsic neuron vGlutMinew1
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron which projects along one medulla column without forming many lateral branches until it reaches layers M8 and M9, where it arborizes extensively. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle VL2
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 (FBbt:00000603) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron vGlutDmnew1
description: Distal medullary amacrine neuron that branches extensively in medulla layers M1 to M4, with blob-like protrusions at the terminals. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle VL1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000602) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: Y neuron vGlutYnew1
description: Y neuron with arborizations in medulla layers M8, M9 and M10, and layer 1 of both lobula and lobula plate. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: medullary intrinsic amacrine neuron vGlutMi Amnew1
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron that forms arborizations in medulla layers M5 to M7 and whose cell body is in the posterior part of the medulla. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: transmedullary neuron vGlutTmnew1
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layers 2 and 3. It also has arborizations in medulla layers M2, M4, M5, M6 and M7. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: transmedullary Y neuron vGlutTmYnew1
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that terminates in lobula layer 1 and in the four layers of the lobula plate. It displays arborizations in medulla layers M7-M10 (Jagadish et al., 2014, Raghu and Borst, 2011). It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: abdominal 2 temporary eclosion muscle SBM
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 2 segment border muscle of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 2 segment border muscle
description: Any A1-7 segment border muscle (FBbt:00000606) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult Leucokinin LHKL lateral horn neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) and whose large cell body is located in the lateral horn. Its thin processes run ventrally before bifurcating into two main collateral branches which innervate the superior lateral and median protocerebrum, the region around the mushroom body pedunculus and the mushroom body calyx. There is one neuron per hemisphere (de Haro et al., 2010).
synonyms: adult lateral horn LHKL Leucokinin neuron

label: adult Leucokinin neuron of the central nervous system
description: An adult neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) and that is located in the central nervous system (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: larval Leucokinin LHKL lateral horn neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) whose cell body is located in the anterodorsal brain and projects to a ventromedial location. The main neurite bifurcates into two collaterals during late larval stages, with the main one being in close proximity to the medial antennal lobe tract. The collaterals arborize close to the mushroom body pedunculus and calyx. There is one neuron per hemisphere (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: adult Leucokinin LK anterior neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) and whose cell body is located superficially in the posterior side of the median protocerebrum (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: CCP-VMP-PB 8 neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slices 8 and 9.

label: CCP-VMP-PB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the ventral regions of the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in one or more glomeruli of the protocerebral bridge, except for glomerulus 1, not necessarily adjacent.

label: CCP-VMP-PB 7 neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slices 7 and 8.

label: adult Leucokinin SELK neuron of the subesophageal zone
description: Adult neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) whose cell body is located in the ventromedial subesophageal zone. The axon collaterals in the brain innervate the gnathal ganglion ipsi- and contralaterally, the tritocerebrum and fasciculate with the maxillary and labral nerve. Four axons extend along the cervical connective to the ventral nerve cord. The axons that extend along the ventral nerve cord connect to the leucokinin ABLK neurons. There are two to three pairs of neurons (de Haro et al., 2010).
synonyms: adult leucokinin SELK neuron of the subesophageal ganglion

label: adult maxillary nerve
description: The adult maxillary nerve is a mixed sensory-motor nerve of the gnathal ganglion (GNG). It ~120 axons contains axons from the sensory cells of the maxillary appendages entering the maxillary neuromere of the GNG and GNG motor axons to maxillary musculature. The maxillary nerve is fused with the labial nerve and for much of its length, forming the maxillary-labial nerve.

label: larval Leucokinin neuron of the central nervous system
description: A larval neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) and that is located in the central nervous system (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: CCP-VMP-PB 5 neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slices 5 and 6.

label: CCP-VMP-PB 4 neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slices 4 and 5.

label: adult Leucokinin ABLK neuron of the abdominal ganglion
description: Adult neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) whose cell body is located dorsally in the abdominal ganglion, with their cell bodies and neurites resembling a ladder-like appearance. From each neuron emerge two axons: one fasciculates with the abdominal nerves and the other branches toward the anterior and posterior ABLK.

label: larval Leucokinin SELK neuron of the subesophageal ganglion
description: Larval neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) whose cell body is located in the subesophageal ganglion. The axon colaterals in the brain form a complex pattern of thin neurites that project in the subesophageal ganglion and tritocerebrum. The axons extend along the ventral nerve cord innervating the contralateral side and to form a ladder-like structure. The axons connect to the end of the abdominal ganglia in a terminal plexus. The axons that extend along the ventral nerve cord connect to the leucokinin ABLK neurons. There are two to three pairs of neurons (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic or larval body wall.

label: CCP-VMP-PB 3 neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the ipsilateral or contralateral protocerebral bridge slices 3 and 4.

label: PB slice 6-FB-NO subunit 2 dorsal domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 6 and axon terminals in both fan-shaped body segment pair Z (column 1) and layer 3 (layer d) and the contralateral dorsal domain of the nodulus subunit II.

label: PB-FB-NO subunit 2 dorsal domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in a single glomerulus of the protocerebral bridge (except glomerulus 1) and axon terminals in fan-shaped body layer 3 and the contralateral dorsal domain of the nodulus subunit II.

label: PB slice 5-FB-NO subunit 2 dorsal domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 5 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair Y (column 2) and layer 3 (layer d) and the contralateral dorsal domain of the nodulus subunit II.

label: PB slice 4-FB-NO subunit 2 dorsal domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 4 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair X (column 3) and layer 3 (layer d) and the contralateral dorsal domain of the nodulus subunit II.

label: pupal Tachykinin neuron of the central nervous system
description: Pupal neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) and that is located in the central nervous system (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB slice 3-FB-NO subunit 2 dorsal domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 3 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 3 (layer d) and the contralateral dorsal domain of the nodulus subunit II.

label: PB slice 2-FB-NO subunit 2 dorsal domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 2 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 3 (layer d) and the contralateral dorsal domain of the nodulus subunit II.

label: larval Tachykinin neuron of the central nervous system
description: A larval neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) and that is located in the central nervous system (Winther et al., 2003).

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm8b
description: Distal medullary amacrine neuron that branches in medulla layers M6, M7 and M8 (Hasegawa et al., 2011).

label: PB slice 5-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 5 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair Y (column 2) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: transmedullary Y neuron Tm27Y
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4 and lobula plate. It displays arborizations in medulla layers M1, M4, M5, M8, M9 and M10 (Hasegawa et al., 2011).

label: PB slice 4-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 4 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair X (column 3) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: PB slice 3-FB-NO subunit 3 anterior domain neuron
description: Small field neuron of the central complex with dendritic arbors in the protocerebral bridge slice 3 and axon terminals in the contralateral fan-shaped body segment pair W (column 4) and layer 2 (layer e) and the contralateral anterior domain of nodulus subunit III.

label: lamina wide-field cell Lawf2
description: An intrinsic columnar neuron of the visual system whose cell body is located in the medulla cortex and that has a main projection into the lamina making wide-field arborizations in the distal lamina, innervating 28 cartridges. These neurons also arborize in the medulla (Hasegawa et al., 2011). In the M1 layer, the branches are large and overlapping, encompassing around 120 cartridges. In medulla layers M8 to M10 the branches are smaller, encompassing around 17 cartridges and show less overlap. Putative cholinergic presynaptic sites are observed in the lamina.

label: proximal medullary amacrine neuron Pm3
description: Proximal medullary amacrine neuron that branches at the proximal surface of the medulla, with both branches forming a broad terminal arbor in medulla layer M9. The processes of different cells intermingle significantly, and the arbor density is heterogenous. It occupies a peripheral intracolumnar position.

label: abdominal 3 temporary eclosion muscle DA1
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 3 that develops from abdominal 3 dorsal acute muscle 1 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000591) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: transmedullary neuron Tm4a
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layer 4. It also has arborizations in medulla layers M2, M3, M4 and M9. It is a cholinergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011).

label: abdominal 3 temporary eclosion muscle DA3
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 3 that develops from abdominal 3 dorsal acute muscle 3 of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: photoreceptor cell R7 of yellow ommatidium
description: Photoreceptor cell R7 located in the yellow ommatidium. It outputs to transmedullary neuron Tm5a (Gao et al., 2008; Karuppudurai et al., 2014) and transmedullary Y neuron Rh4TmY.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi10b
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron with arborizations in medulla layers M1, M2, M4-M10 (Hasegawa et al., 2011).

label: transmedullary neuron Tm3b
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates in lobula layers 1 and 4 with bleb-like terminal arborizations. It has fine arborizations in medulla layers M1, M4, and M5, and has bleb-type arborization in medulla layers M1, M4, M9 and M10 (Fischbach and Dittrich, 1989). It has a small branch at medulla layer M8 that projects towards medulla layer M10 (Hasegawa et al., 2011).

label: pupal large descending DN Tachykinin neuron
description: Pupal neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the lateral protocerebrum and that innervates the ventral nerve cord (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB-EB-NO 1 neuron
description: A pb-eb-no neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2 and axon terminals in the posterior ring of both ellipsoid body slices 8, and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: larval tritocerebral Tr Tachykinin neuron
description: A larval neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the tritocerebral neuropils and that innervates the subesophageal ganglion. There are one to two pairs in first instar larvae, and three in the other larval stages (Winther et al., 2003; Siviter et al., 2000).

label: adult lobula plate astrocyte-like glial cell
description: Astrocyte-like glial cell of the adult lobula plate.

label: reticular neuropil associated glial cell
description: Neuropil associated glial cell of the adult brain that has a dendritic morphology which elaborates inside the associated neuropil. It extends membrane processes deeply into the neuropil and ramifies profusely in synaptic-rich regions, both in the ventral nerve cord and in the adult brain. In the third instar larval ventral nerve cord, the glial cells are organized into three groups: a dorsomedial group with 3 cells, a dorsolateral group with two cells and a ventrally positioned cell.

label: adult optic lobe glial cell
description: Glial cell of the adult that is associated with the optic lobe.

label: Tachykinin cell of the adult midgut
description: Adult cell of the midgut that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976). These cells have an elongated shape, often spanning the gut epithelium, similar to the morphology of other midgut endocrine cells. They are found throughout the midgut except for a medial domain.

label: larval anterior large descending DN Tachykinin neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the anterior protocerebrum and that innervates the ventral nerve cord. At the third instar larval stage, these neurons also form arborizations at two sites near the midline of the protocerebrum and in the subesophageal ganglion. At the level of the ventral nerve cord, this neuron has one main axon and two additional processes, one longer and one shorter than the main axon. There is one neuron per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003; Siviter et al., 2000).

label: adult lobula astrocyte-like glial cell
description: Astrocyte-like glial cell of the adult lobula.

label: adult carpet glial cell
description: Large glial cell of the adult optic lobe. These cells are found on the dorsal and ventral edges of the lamina, proximal to marginal glial cells.

label: adult brain subperineurial glial cell
description: Large, sheet-like glial cell that is a component of the basal glial layer of the adult brain surface. It is located below the apical glial layer that is composed of the perineurial glial cells.
synonyms: adult brain subperineurial surface associated glial cell

label: embryonic/larval carpet glial cell
description: Very large glial cell of the embryonic/larval eye disc. There are two per eye disc, each covering approximately half of the differentiated part of the disc, with their nuclei generally being found at the posterior end of the imaginal disc, but always posterior to the differentiating neurons. The glial substrate formed by the carpet glia separates the basal-most migrating glia from the more apical ones (Silies et al., 2007). These cells migrate inwards to give rise to the adult carpet glial cells.

label: dorsal anterior lateral neuron of the protocerebrum
description: A neuron whose cell body is located in the adult dorsal anteriolateral protocerebrum (Xia et al., 2005), extending its dendrites mainly in the superior dorsofrontal protocerebrum. It projects its axons in three different regions: where the dendritic tree is located and in the dorsolateral and inferior dorsofrontal protocerebrum domains. It establishes synaptic contacts with the pioneer mushroom body alpha/beta neurons in a small dorsal frontal domain of the mushroom body calyx (Chen et al., 2012). There are two pairs of DAL neurons per hemisphere (Xia et al., 2005). These neurons are involved in the retrieval of long-term memories (Chen et al., 2012).

label: adult medulla distal astrocyte-like glial cell
description: Astrocyte-like glial cell of the distal adult medulla. Its cell body lies at the posterior edge of the distal medulla, with branches that extend into medulla columns as deep as the serpentine layer (M7). Other branches extend in a centrifugal direction, along chiasmal axons or glia that approaches from the lamina.

label: medulla neuropil glial cell
description: Glial cell located in the medulla neuropil. The cell body lies at the border between the medulla cell body cortex and the medulla neuropil and send long regular extensions into the medulla neuropil (Tix et al., 1997).

label: adult chandelier glial cell
description: Glial cell of the proximal adult medulla. Its cell body lies at the edge of the neuropil, immediately distal to the inner chiasm giant glia. It extends astrocyte-like branches above medulla layer M10 and beneath M7.

label: adult neuropil associated glial cell
description: Glial cell of the adult that is associated with a neuropil of the brain. There are approximately 200 neuropil associated glial cells per hemisphere of the adult brain (Hartenstein, 2011).

label: tachykinin cell of the embryonic/larval midgut
description: Cell of the embryonic/larval midgut that expresses tachykinin (FBgn0037976). In the late third instar, tachykinin expressing cells in the midgut are located posteriorly, just anterior to the attachment of the Malpighian tubules and have a morphology consistent with an endocrine role.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron vGlutMinew1a
description: Medullary intrinsic neuron which projects along one medulla column forming some small lateral branches in layers M1-M5, until it reaches layers M8 and M9, where it arborizes extensively. It is a glutamatergic neuron (Raghu and Borst, 2011).

label: adult serpentine glial cell
description: Amorphous glial cell of the serpentine layer of the adult medulla. It is located at the posterior margin of the serpentine layer (M7), extending thin branches distally toward the terminals of photoreceptor R7 in medulla layers M6 and M8.

label: larval protocerebral Pr Tachykinin neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) and whose cell body and arborization are located in the dorsal or medial protocerebrum (Siviter et al., 2000). The number of neurons increases during larval stages: 5 pairs are observed at first instar stage and 11 at prepupal stage P1. In third instar larvae some of these neurons have bilateral arborizations crossing the midline by two commissures (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB-EB-NO 6 neuron
description: A pb-eb-no neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7 and axon terminals in the posterior ring of ipsilateral ellipsoid body slices 2 and 3, and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: PB-EB-NO 5 neuron
description: A pb-eb-no neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6 and axon terminals in the posterior ring of both ellipsoid body slices 1, and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: pupal antennal lobes Tachykinin neuron
description: Pupal neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the cortex of the antennal lobes (Winther et al., 2003).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VC3m
description: Medial-most compartment of glomerulus VC3. It lies along the dorsomedial edge of the lateral compartment of glomerulus 3, and immediately dorsal to glomerulus VM6.

label: PB-EB-NO 3 neuron
description: A pb-eb-no neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 4 and axon terminals in the posterior ring of contralateral ellipsoid body slices 4 and 5, and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: pupal protocerebral LPP2 Tachykinin neuron
description: Pupal neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the lateral posterior protocerebrum and that innervates the superior median protocerebrum and fan-shaped body (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB-EB-NO 2 neuron
description: A pb-eb-no neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 3 and axon terminals in the posterior ring of contralateral ellipsoid body slices 6 and 7, and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VA7m
description: Medial-most compartment of glomerulus VA7. It lies along the medial edge of the lateral compartment and dorsolateral to glomerulus VA2.

label: adult anterior large descending DN Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) whose cell body is located in the anterior subesophageal zone and innervates the thoracico-abdominal ganglia. There is one neuron per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003; Siviter et al., 2000).

label: PB slice 6-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 6 and axon terminals in the inner ring of the ipsilateral ellipsoid body slices 4 and 5, and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body).

label: PB 1 glomerulus-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that connects the protocerebral bridge (except slice 9), the inner ring of the ellipsoid body and dorsal or ventral gall (dorsal or ventral spindle body). Neurons that arborize a odd-numbered protocerebral bridge slice project to the dorsal gall, whereas even-numbered ones project to the ventral gall.

label: adult optic lobe OL Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) and whose cell body is located at the base of the optic lobe. There are about 10 pairs of cell bodies per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003).

label: larval Tachykinin neuron of the ventral cord
description: Larval neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) whose cell body is located in the abdominal neuromere. The number of neurons increases throughout larval development: 1 pair at first instar, two to three at second instar, 4 to 8 pairs at early third instar, 7 to 10 late third instar and 7 to 8 at prepupal stage P1 (Winther et al., 2003).

label: cell body rind of larval ventral nerve cord
description: Region of the larval cell body rind that overlies the ventral nerve cord.

label: PB slice 5-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 5 and axon terminals in the inner ring of the ipsilateral ellipsoid body slices 2 and 3, and in the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body).

label: PB slice 4-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 4 and axon terminals in the inner ring of both ellipsoid body slices 1, and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body).

label: adult protocerebral MPP Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) and whose cell body is located in the median posterior protocerebrum. One cluster of around 3 cell bodies is found per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003).

label: adult deutocerebrum DC Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) whose cell body is located in the cortex of the anterior deutocerebrum close to the antennal lobes. There are about 8 pairs of cell bodies per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB slice 1-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 1 and axon terminals in the inner ring of the contralateral ellipsoid body slices 6 and 7, and in the dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body).

label: imaginal disc epithelial cell
description: A columnar epithelial cell with distinct apical-basal polarity. The apical surface has microvilli with dense plaques at their tips. A cortical network (ring) of actin filaments underlies the apical surface, extends into the microvilli and is associated with a zonula adherens which encircles each cell. Below this is a broad region of pleated sheet type septate junctions connecting all lateral surfaces to adjacent cells. Plaque-like gap junctions occur mainly interspersed among septate junctions and, at a lower frequency, below them. Small, sparsely distributed hemidesmosomes attach these cells to the underlying basal lamina.

label: adult protocerebral LPP2 Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the lateral posterior protocerebrum and that innervates the superior median protocerebrum and the fan-shaped body. One cluster of around 10 cell bodies is found per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003).

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VC3l
description: Lateral-most compartment of glomerulus VC3. It lies along the ventrolateral edge of the medial compartment of glomerulus VC3, and immediately dorsal to glomerulus VM7.
synonyms: antennal lobe glomerulus VC3 lateral compartment

label: adult protocerebral LPP1 Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) and whose cell body is located in the posterior protocerebrum. One cluster of around 12 cell bodies is found per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB-EB-NO 7 neuron
description: A pb-eb-no neuron of the adult central complex with dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8 and axon terminals in the posterior ring of ipsilateral ellipsoid body slices 4 and 5, and the contralateral nodulus subunit I.

label: larval Leucokinin LK anterior neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) whose cell body is located in the lateral protocerebrum and projects towards the midline forming a loop and innervating the corpus cardiacum and the prothoracic gland within the ring gland. There are three to four neuron per hemisphere (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: CCP-VMP-PB 2 neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the antler and inferior bridge (caudalcentral protocerebrum, CCP), the dorsal region of the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the ipsilateral protocerebral bridge slices 2 and 3.

label: larval Leucokinin ABLK neuron of the abdominal ganglion
description: Larval neuron that expresses Leucokinin (FBgn0028418) whose cell body is located ventrolaterally in each neuromere of the abdominal ganglion. Each neuron produces a pair of axons, one of which projects dorsally and emerges from the ventral ganglia through an anterior segmental nerve of each hemineuromere. The other branch divides centrally into two branches: one send its neurites to the anterior ABLK and the other ventrally to the posterior ABLK. From each segmental nerve one axon emerges that synapses to the adjacent segment border muscle, close to the spiracle (Haro et al., 2010; Landgraf et al., 2003). These synapses lack the typical morphology of motor-neuron synapses (Landgraf et al., 2003) and are not glutamatergic (Haro et al., 2010). There is one pair of neurons in each of seven abdominal neuromeres (de Haro et al., 2010).

label: CVLP-IDFP-VMP-PB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arborizations in the inferior region of the posterior lateral protocerebrum (caudal ventrolateral protocerebrum, CVLP), the lateral accessory lobe (lateral hammer body), the ventral complex and posterior slope (ventromedial protocerebrum, VMP) and axon terminals in the whole protocerebral bridge.

label: adult tritocerebral TC1 Tachykinin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976), whose cell body is located in the tritocerebrum and which innervates, among other regions, the fan-shaped body. One cluster of around 16 cell bodies is found per hemisphere (Winther et al., 2003).

label: adult Tachykinin neuron of the thoracic-abdominal ganglion
description: Adult neuron that expresses Tachykinin (FBgn0037976) whose cell body is located in the thoracic-abdominal ganglion. There are 10 to 12 pairs in the prothoracic, 5 to 6 in the mesothoracic, 8 to 12 in the metathoracic and 1 to 2 in the abdominal neuromeres (Winther et al., 2003).

label: PB slice 8-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 8 and axon terminals in the inner ring of both ellipsoid body slices 8, and in the contralateral ventral gall (ventral spindle body).

label: PB slice 7-EB core-IDFP DSB neuron
description: Interneuron that has dendritic arbors in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 7 and axon terminals in the inner ring of the ipsilateral ellipsoid body slices 6 and 7, and in the contralateral dorsal gall (dorsal spindle body).

label: larval Basin-1 neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 9. Its soma is located in the lateral intermediate cell body rind region. Its dendrites span a ventrolateral domain of the ventral nerve cord and overlap with the axon terminals of the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2), from which it receives input. The primary neurite fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve. Its axon is ventral to the axons of Basin-3 and -4, and extends anteriorly and posteriorly near the midline, on the ipsilateral side. It synapses onto the A00c-a6 neuron.

label: larval subesophageal zone descending SEZ DN neuron
description: Descending neuron of the larva, whose soma is located at the level of the subesophageal zone. Its dendrites are located medially in both hemispheres in the subesophageal zone. Its axon extends posteriorly, close to the midline. It synapses throughout its length with the A00c, A05q, Basin-1 and -2 neurons.

label: larval A00c-a6 neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 0 whose soma is at the level of abdominal segment 6. It receives input from Basin-1 neuron and synapses onto the subesophageal zone descending SEZ DN and Ipsiphone neurons in the brain. Its axon is on or crossing the midline.

label: mechanosensory neuron of humeral bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the humeral bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with one of the prothoracic nerves, following the dorsal and then medial edge of the prothoracic neuromere until it reaches the main course of the pathway and extends posteriorly.

label: humeral bristle
description: Macrochaeta of the humerus, on the adult prothorax. There are two of these.

label: mechanosensory neuron of posterior scutellar bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the posterior scutellar bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, with a very short branch that extends to the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the abdominal ganglion. The main crossbranch extends contralaterally. Occasionally, a metathoracic crossbranch is observed.

label: posterior scutellar bristle
description: Posterior-most macrochaeta of the scutellum. There is one pair of these.

label: mechanosensory neuron of anterior scutellar bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the anterior scutellar bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, extending to the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the metathoracic crossbranch. The main crossbranch extends contralaterally. Occasionally, a metathoracic crossbranch is observed.

label: anterior scutellar bristle
description: Anterior-most macrochaeta of the scutellum. There is one pair of these.

label: mechanosensory neuron of posterior dorsocentral bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the posterior dorsocentral bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, extending halfway along the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the metathoracic crossbranch. The main crossbranch extends contralaterally. Occasionally, anterior and posterior crossbranches are observed. The central branches form mostly terminal but also en passant synapses. Presynaptic terminals are enriched near the midline, along the anterior branch, contralateral branches and on four stereotypic locations on the posterior projecting branch.

label: posterior dorsocentral bristle
description: Posterior-most of the two dorsocentral bristles.

label: mechanosensory neuron of anterior dorsocentral bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the anterior dorsocentral bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, along the medial edge and halfway along the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, along the mesothoracic neuromere. The main crossbranch extends contralaterally. Occasionally, anterior and posterior crossbranches are observed. The central branches form mostly terminal but also en passant synapses. Presynaptic terminals are enriched near the midline, along the anterior branch, contralateral branches and on the distal tip of the posterior projecting branch.

label: anterior dorsocentral bristle
description: Anterior-most of the two dorsocentral bristles.

label: larval Basin-2 neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 9. Its soma is located in the lateral intermediate cell body rind region. Its dendrites span a ventrolateral and ventromedial domains of the ventral nerve cord. These domains overlap with the axon terminals of the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2) and the class IV dendritic arborizing neuron, respectively, from which it receives input. The primary neurite fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve, with no ventral branch extending from it. Its axon is ventral to the axons of Basin-3 and -4, and extends anteriorly and posteriorly near the midline, on the ipsilateral side. It synapses onto the A00c-a5, A00c-a4 and the A05q neurons.

label: larval A00c-a5 neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 0 whose soma is at the level of abdominal segment 5. It receives input from Basin-2 and Basin-4 neurons and synapses onto the subesophageal zone descending SEZ DN and Ipsiphone neurons in the brain. Its axon is on or crossing the midline.

label: larval A00c-a4 neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 0 whose soma is at the level of abdominal segment 4. It receives input from Basin-2 and Basin-4 neurons and synapses onto the subesophageal zone descending SEZ DN and Ipsiphone neurons in the brain. Its axon is on or crossing the midline.

label: larval A05q neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 5. Its dendrites are located ipsilaterally, and extending anteriorly close to the midline. It receives input from the Basin-2 and SEZ DN neurons. Its axon extends anteriorly, on or crossing the midline. It synapses onto the Goro neuron.

label: larval Basin-3 neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 9. Its soma is located in the lateral intermediate cell body rind region. Its dendrites span a ventrolateral domain of the ventral nerve cord and overlap with the axon terminals of the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2), from which it receives input. The primary neurite fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve. Its axon is dorsal to the axons of Basin-1 and -2, and extends anteriorly and posteriorly near the midline, on the ipsilateral side. It synapses onto the A00c-a5, A00c-a4 and the A23g neurons.

label: larval A23g neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 23. It receives input from the Basin-3 neuron. Its axon is on or crossing the midline. It synapses onto the Goro neuron.

label: larval Basin-4 neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 9. Its soma is located in the lateral intermediate cell body rind region. Its dendrites span a ventrolateral and ventromedial domains of the ventral nerve cord. These domains overlap with the axon terminals of the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2) and the class IV dendritic arborizing neuron, respectively, from which it receives input. The primary neurite fasciculates with the intersegmental nerve, with no ventral branch extending from it. Its axon is ventral to the axons of Basin-3 and -4, and extends anteriorly and posteriorly to or across the midline. It synapses onto the A00c-a5 and A00c-a4 neurons.

label: larval Contragoro neuron
description: Descending neuron of the larva. It has an ipsilateral dendritic domain in the larval brain and a descending axonal domain that crosses the midline extending into the ventral nerve cord. It receives input from the Ipsiphone and Contraphone neurons and synapses onto the Goro neuron.

label: larval Ipsiphone neuron
description: Neuron of the larval brain. It has an ipsilateral dendritic and axonal domains. It receives input from the A00c neuron and synapses onto the Contragoro neuron.

label: larval Contraphone neuron
description: Neuron of the larval brain. It has an ipsilateral dendritic domain, with its axon crossing over the midline. It receives input from the A00c neuron and synapses onto the Contragoro neuron.

label: larval Goro neuron
description: Neuron of the larval ventral nerve cord, whose soma is located at the level of the mesothoracic segment. Its dendrites are located ipsilaterally, lateral to the midline. It receives input from the descending Contragoro, Ipsigoro neurons and from the abdominal A23g and A05q neurons. Its axon extends posteriorly in the dorsal region, close to the midline, in the motor domain of the ventral nerve cord. It is a downstream neuron of the pathway involved in the rolling behaviour.

label: larval Ipsigoro neuron
description: Descending neuron of the larva. It has an ipsilateral dendritic domain in the larval brain and a descending axonal domain that extends into the ventral nerve cord. It receives input from the Ipsiphone and Contraphone neurons and synapses onto the Goro neuron.

label: dopaminergic medulla neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose small cell body is located on the surface of the medulla. It projects to a deeper layer of the medulla where it forms a fibre plexus.

label: dopaminergic lamina neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in the lateral cell body region. It projects through the anterior surface of the medulla and branches extensively throughout the lamina. There are 4 of these neurons in a cluster.

label: dorsal compartment of chamber III of sacculus
description: Dorsal compartment of chamber III of the sacculus. It contains sensillum of the type grooved sensillum 2 (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: ventral compartment of chamber III of sacculus
description: Ventral compartment of chamber III of the sacculus. It contains sensillum of the type grooved sensillum 1 (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: maintenance of location
description: Any process in which a cell, substance or cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is maintained in a location and prevented from moving elsewhere.

label: mechanosensory neuron of posterior supraalar bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the posterior supraalar bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, along the medial edge and halfway along the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch.

label: posterior supraalar bristle
description: Posterior-most of the two supraalar bristles.

label: mechanosensory neuron of anterior supraalar bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the anterior supraalar bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, along the medial edge and halfway along the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch and main crossbranch.

label: anterior supraalar bristle
description: Anterior-most of the two supraalar bristles.

label: mechanosensory neuron of posterior notopleural bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the posterior notopleural bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, along the medial edge and halfway along the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch.

label: posterior notopleural bristle
description: Posterior-most of the two notopleural bristles.

label: mechanosensory neuron of anterior notopleural bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the anterior notopleural bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, along the medial edge of the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch.

label: anterior notopleural bristle
description: Anterior-most of the two notopleural bristles.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir64a DP1m
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptor (Ir) 64a (FBgn0035604) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomeruli DP1m and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomeruli DP1m (Ai et al., 2010; Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the grooved sensillum 2 of the dorsal compartment of chamber III of sacculus (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: grooved sensillum 2
description: Sensillum of the dorsal compartment of chamber III of the sacculus of the antenna. The sensilla are slender than the grooved sensillum 1 and bear 6-8 grooves with slit channels. They are innervated by 2 sensory cells, one olfactory and one thermo-sensitive neuron. There are 11 sensilla of this type (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DC4 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DC4. Its axon terminal bifurcates to form stereotypical dorsal and ventral branches in the anterior medial region of the lateral horn.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus DC4
description: Dorsal glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies ventral to glomerulus DM3 and posterior to DC2 and DC1, and is innervated by coeloconic olfactory receptor neurons (Couto et al., 2005).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir64a DC4
description: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the ionotropic glutamate receptor (Ir) 64a (FBgn0035604) and the co-receptor Ir8a (FBgn0052704). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomeruli DC4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomeruli DC4 (Ai et al., 2010; Silbering et al., 2011). Its dendrite transduces signals from the grooved sensillum 1 of the ventral compartment of chamber III of sacculus (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: grooved sensillum 1
description: Sensillum of the ventral compartment of chamber III of the sacculus of the antenna. The sensilla are thick, blunt-tipped and bear 9-12 grooves with slit channels. They are innervated by 2 sensory cells, one olfactory and one thermo-sensitive neuron. There are 11-13 sensilla of this type (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: mechanosensory neuron of posterior postalar bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the posterior postalar bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, reaching the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch. The main crossbranch extends contralaterally.

label: posterior postalar bristle
description: Posterior-most of the two postalar bristles.

label: mechanosensory neuron of anterior postalar bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the anterior postalar bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, reaching the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, along the mesothoracic neuromere up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch.

label: anterior postalar bristle
description: Anterior-most of the two postalar bristles.

label: mechanosensory neuron of presutural bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates the presutural bristle in the adult thorax. It fasciculates with the posterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve, extends ventrally and medially, bifurcates and follows the main course of the pathway anteriorly, along the medial edge and halfway along the prothoracic neuromere, and posteriorly, up to the bifurcation of the posterior crossbranch.

label: presutural bristle
description: A macrochaeta of the prescutum, located medial to the notopleural bristles.

label: adult optic chiasma glial cell
description: Glial cell of the adult fly that is located in the optic chiasm (Tix et al., 1997). Members of this group of glial cells are arranged in rows between successive dorsoventral sheets of intercrossing fibers of the outer and inner chiasmata (Edwards and Meinertzhagen, 2010; Tix et al., 1997).

label: adult outer optic chiasma giant glial cell
description: Large glial cell located in the outer optic chiasm of the adult optic lobe. It extends many cytoplasmic processes that enwraps fiber bundles at and near the sites of axonal intersection (Tix et al., 1997).
synonyms: adult outer optic chiasm large glial cell

label: adult inner optic chiasma giant glial cell
description: Large glial cell of the inner optic chiasm of the adult optic lobe. It extends many cytoplasmic processes that enwraps fiber bundles at and near the sites of axonal intersection (Tix et al., 1997).
synonyms: adult inner optic chiasm large glial cell

label: distal medulla glial cell
description: Glial cell located proximal to the marginal glial cells. They elaborate long processes and wrap R cell axons in the medulla, which stop precisely at the base of expanded R8 and R7 growth cones. They also extend processes to the bottom of the lamina furrow (Poeck et al., 2001).

label: pseudocartridge glial cell
description: Surface glial cell of the adult optic lobe. The pseudocartridge glial cells form a glial layer beneath the distal fenestrated glial cells.

label: subretinal glial cell
description: Surface glial cell of the adult lamina located in one of the two most distal layers of glial cells of the optic lobe.

label: embryonic/larval wrapping glial cell of the eye disc
description: Glial cell of the embryonic/larval eye disc that lies above the outgrowing photoreceptor axons and ensheathes bundles of axons extending through the optic stalk (Hummel et al., 2002; Edwards and Hartenstein, 2010). The wrapping glial cells are, in turn, surrounded and wrapped by surface glial cells.
synonyms: embryonic/larval wrapping glia of the eye disc

label: embryonic/larval optic stalk
description: Receptor axons that arise in the eye disc gain access to the developing optic lobe in the supraesophageal hemisphere in the embryonic/larval brain by way of the optic stalk connecting these two structures. The optic stalk is tube-like and provides a funnel through which not only the imaginal receptor axons reach the brain, but also the axons of Bolwig's nerve (Meinertzhagen and Hanson, 1993).

label: embryonic/larval optic stalk surface glial cell
description: Glial cell associated with the optic stalk that separates the R cells axons from the eye disc and hemolymph. The surface glial cells envelop the wrapping glia (Hummel et al., 2002).

label: distal satellite glial cell
description: Satellite glial cell of the adult optic lobe. It lies in a glial layer beneath the pseudocartridge glial cell layer, and above the proximal satellite glial cell layer. It ensheathes cell bodies of monopolar neurons of the lamina cortex.

label: satellite glial cell
description: Glial cell with long ensheathing processes of the optic lobe that are interspersed among the lamina neurons (Poeck et al., 2001). In the lamina it receives synaptic input from photoreceptors R1 and R2 (Rivera-Alba et al., 2011).

label: adult proximal satellite glial cell
description: Satellite glial cell of the adult optic lobe. It is located in a layer between the distal satellite glial layer and the epithelial glia. These glial cells invest the photoreceptor axon bundles and the necks of monopolar neurons. There is approximately one proximal satellite glial cell for every 2-3 groups of monopolar cell bodies.

label: embryonic/larval epithelial glial cell
description: Epithelial glial cell of the embryo/larva.

label: epithelial glial cell
description: Cuboidal glial cell found in the visual system of larvae and adults, located more distal than the row of marginal glial cells. These glial cells contact marginal glia at their base (proximal) and satellite glia at their apex (distal), and constitute the only class of cells with nuclei in the neuropil proper, in the distal lamina.

label: fenestrated glial cell
description: Surface glial cell of the adult optic lobe. The fenestrated glia form a layer overlying the pseudocartridge glial cell layer and contact the basement membrane.

label: embryonic/larval CNS perineurial glial cell
description: Glial cell of the perineurial glial sheath in the embryonic/larval CNS.

label: embryonic/larval PNS perineurial glial cell
description: Glial cell of the embryonic/larval peripheral nervous system that ensheathes axons and dendrites. The perineurial layer of glial cell lie on top of the inner, subperineurial glial cells (Banerjee et al., 2006).

label: ensheathing neuropil associated glial cell
description: Glial cell of the adult brain that elaborates along the outer surface of its associated neuropil. Glia of this class may also surround neuropil bundles such as commissures or tracts.

label: acid secretion
description: The controlled release of acid by a cell or a tissue.

label: dMP2 ILP7 neuron of abdominal segment 7
description: dMP2 neuron located in embryonic/larval abdominal segment 7, and which expresses ILP7.

label: embryonic/larval dMP2 ILP7 neuron
description: A dMP2 neuron that expresses ILP7. All dMP2 neurons that survive in the larva (those in A6-9) are of this type. There are two per segment. All project to the hindgut. These projections have ILP7 positive swellings associated with circular visceral muscle. Their terminals are also sites of ILP7 localization.

label: dMP2 ILP7 neuron of abdominal segment 8
description: dMP2 neuron located in embryonic/larval abdominal segment 8, and which expresses ILP7.

label: dMP2 ILP7 neuron of abdominal segment 9
description: dMP2 neuron located in embryonic/larval abdominal segment 9, and which expresses ILP7.

label: adult dMP2 ILP7 neuron
description: An adult dMP2 neuron that expresses ILP7. There are two per abdominal segment, all projecting to the hindgut. These projections have ILP7 positive swellings and connect to the anterior intestines and the rectum. Their terminals are also sites of ILP7 localization (Miguel-Aliaga et al., 2008).

label: embryonic/larval eye disc marginal glial cell
description: Glial cell located at the margins of the eye disc, showing an elongated, clapboard-like shape (Silies et al., 2007; Edwards and Meinertzhagen, 2010).

label: dMP2 ILP7 neuron of abdominal segment 6
description: dMP2 neuron located in embryonic/larval abdominal segment 6, and which expresses ILP7.

label: mesothoracic ungulfus
description: Any ungulfus (FBbt:00004657) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: mesothoracic pulvillar membrane
description: Any pulvillar membrane (FBbt:00004656) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: mesothoracic empodium
description: Any empodium (FBbt:00004659) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: mesothoracic unguitractor plate
description: Any unguitractor plate (FBbt:00004658) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: metathoracic tibia
description: Segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the femur and distally with the first tarsal segment. On its posterior side it has 1 transverse row of bristles, between and including longitudinal rows 2 and 3.

label: presumptive metathoracic tibia
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tibia.

label: presumptive metathoracic coxa
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic coxa.

label: mesothoracic unguis scale
description: Any unguis scale (FBbt:00004661) that is part of some mesothoracic unguis (FBbt:00004704).

label: mesothoracic unguis
description: Claw at the distal end of the mesothoracic pretarsus of the mesothoracic leg.

label: presumptive mesothoracic unguis
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic unguis.

label: mesothoracic retineria
description: Any retineria (FBbt:00004662) that is part of some mesothoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004697).

label: glial mesh
description: Mesh-like structure composed of glial cells and covering the cortex of the adult brain. It is composed of glial cells that locally elaborate and enwrap neuronal cell bodies.

label: adult brain perineurial glial cell
description: Small, oblong-shaped glial cell that is part of the (outer) perineurial sheath layer on the surface of the adult brain. It is located on top of the basal glial cell layer that is composed of the subperineurial glial cells.

label: adult surface associated glial cell
description: Glial cell of the adult that is associated with the surface of the brain.

label: adult cell body glial cell
description: Glial cell of the adult that is associated with the cortex of the brain.

label: metathoracic femur
