description: Segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the trochanter and distally with the tibia. In the posterior compartment, it has a region without any bristles or hairs (zone of no bristles, ZNB).

label: presumptive metathoracic femur
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic femur.

label: metathoracic metatarsus
description: First tarsal segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the tibia and distally with the second tarsal segment. Its surface is covered with eight longitudinal rows of bristles and with 11 transverse rows of bristles (TR) in the posterior compartment, between rows 1 and 1.

label: presumptive metathoracic metatarsus
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic metatarsus.

label: regulation of cellular process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter.

label: metathoracic pretarsus
description: Any pretarsus (FBbt:00004653) that is part of some metathoracic leg (FBbt:00004707).

label: metathoracic tarsal segment 3
description: Third tarsal segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 2, and distally with the fourth tarsal segment.

label: presumptive metathoracic tarsal segment 3
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tarsal segment 3.

label: metathoracic tarsal segment 2
description: Second tarsal segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the metatarsus, and distally with the third tarsal segment. It has 6 transverse rows of bristles (TR).

label: presumptive metathoracic tarsal segment 2
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tarsal segment 2.

label: presumptive metathoracic tarsal segment 5
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tarsal segment 5.

label: metathoracic tarsal segment 4
description: Fourth tarsal segment of the metathoracic leg. Proximally it articulates with the tarsal segment 3, and distally with the fifth tarsal segment.

label: presumptive metathoracic tarsal segment 4
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tarsal segment 4.

label: metathoracic ungulfus
description: Any ungulfus (FBbt:00004657) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: metathoracic pulvillar membrane
description: Any pulvillar membrane (FBbt:00004656) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: metathoracic empodium
description: Any empodium (FBbt:00004659) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: metathoracic unguitractor plate
description: Any unguitractor plate (FBbt:00004658) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: metathoracic pulvillus
description: Any pulvillus (FBbt:00004655) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: metathoracic auxilia
description: Any auxilia (FBbt:00004654) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: metathoracic unguis scale
description: Any unguis scale (FBbt:00004661) that is part of some metathoracic unguis (FBbt:00004726).

label: metathoracic unguis
description: Claw at the distal end of the metathoracic pretarsus of the metathoracic leg.

label: presumptive metathoracic unguis
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic unguis.

label: metathoracic retineria
description: Any retineria (FBbt:00004662) that is part of some metathoracic pretarsus (FBbt:00004719).

label: G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals that proceeds with an activated receptor promoting the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha-subunit of an associated heterotrimeric G-protein complex. The GTP-bound activated alpha-G-protein then dissociates from the beta- and gamma-subunits to further transmit the signal within the cell. The pathway begins with receptor-ligand interaction, or for basal GPCR signaling the pathway begins with the receptor activating its G protein in the absence of an agonist, and ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.  The pathway can start from the plasma membrane, Golgi or nuclear membrane (PMID:24568158 and PMID:16902576).
synonyms: G-protein coupled receptor protein signaling pathway

label: mesothoracic depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: skeletal muscle of mesothoracic leg
description: Skeletal muscle of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: humeral sclerite
description: An anteriorly located sclerite of the wing hinge, closely associated with the anterior arm of the 1st axillary sclerite (FBbt:00004738). It is immediately distal to the tegula (FBbt:00004730) and its distal end as associates with the proximal end of the costal vein.

label: wing hinge
description: The small plates and sclerites at the proximal part of the wing lending support to the costal and radial veins.

label: pleural wing sclerite
description: Ventrally located sclerite of the wing hinge, located immediately posterior to the pleural wing process (FBbt:00004595) and distal to the axillary pouch (FBbt:00004745).

label: mesothoracic intracoxal depressor muscle 67
description: Intracoxal depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic trochanter. It is a small muscle that arises ventrally in the base of the anterior coxa and attaches to the trochanter.

label: unnamed wing hinge sclerite
description: Small sclerite of the wing hinge that lies immediately posterior to the humeral sclerite (FBbt:00004734) and closely associated with the 1st axillary sclerite (FBbt:00004738).

label: median sclerite
description: The small sclerite at the base of the first anal vein (FBbt:00004753).

label: section of wing margin
description: A subdivision of the wing margin along its length.

label: mesothoracic spiracle occlusor muscle 76
description: Any spiracular occlusor muscle (FBbt:00013333) that is part of some adult mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00003021) and that connected to some adult anterior thoracic spiracle (FBbt:00004609).

label: mesothoracic sternal promotor muscle 64
description: Sternal promotor muscle of the adult mesothoracic coxa that arises anteriorly in the same region as the mesothoracic sternal promotor muscle 65 and extends posteriorly to the anterior rim of the coxa.

label: mesothoracic tibial depressor muscle 71
description: Depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic tibia that extends along the medial femur, proximal to the tibial depressor muscle 72.

label: mesothoracic tibial depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic tibia.

label: mesothoracic tarsal depressor muscle 74
description: Depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic tarsus that extends along the tibia, medial to the tarsal levator muscle 73.

label: mesothoracic tibial depressor muscle 72
description: Depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic tibia that extends mediolaterally in the distal femur, distal to the tibial depressor muscle 71.

label: 2nd axillary sclerite
description: A small, irregularly shaped sclerite of the wing hinge, located immediately distal to the 1st axillary sclerite (FBbt:00004738) with which it articulates.

label: mesothoracic tarsal levator muscle 73
description: Levator muscle of the adult mesothoracic tarsus that extends in the distal tibia, lateral to the tarsal depressor muscle 74.

label: mesothoracic levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: axillary pouch
description: A pouch-shaped specialisation of the integument located at the base of the ventral side of the wing hinge, adjacent to the pleural wing process.

label: mesothoracic tibial levator muscle 70
description: Levator muscle of the adult mesothoracic tibia that extends along the lateral femur.

label: axillary cord
description: A thickened, corrugated region of the posterior margin of the wing hinge.

label: mesothoracic femoral reductor muscle 69
description: Reductor muscle of the adult mesothoracic femur that extends along the trochanter.

label: mesothoracic reductor muscle
description: Reductor muscle of the adult mesothoracic leg.

label: alula
description: A small lobe at the posterior base of the wing.

label: mesothoracic pretarsal depressor muscle 75
description: Depressor muscle of the adult mesothoracic pretarsus that extends along the tarsal segments.

label: 4th axillary sclerite
description: The most posterior and proximal of the sclerites of the wing hinge. The proximal end of this sclerite is adjacent to the distal end of the posterior notal wing process.

label: mesothoracic intracoxal levator muscle 68
description: Intracoxal levator muscle of the adult mesothoracic trochanter. It arises ventrally in the base of the posterior coxa and attaches to the trochanter.

label: yellow club
description: Club-shaped, anteriorly located ventral sclerite of the wing hinge.

label: basal sclerite
description: Small sclerite of the wing that is embedded in the pleural membrane ventrally adjacent to where the wing articulates (Sink, 2006).

label: haltere muscle
description: Muscle involved in the movement of the haltere of the adult fly.

label: skeletal muscle of metathorax
description: Somatic muscle that is part of the adult metathorax.

label: wing septum 1
description: Most proximal of the wing septa, located in the region between the sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc25 and sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc12.

label: wing septum
description: Septum on the dorsal surface of the wing, in the proximal region of the wing vein L3 (dorsal radius).

label: haltere muscle 77
description: Muscle of the haltere that extends dorsoventrally and attaches to the cuticle near the base of the haltere and to the metathoracic pleurum.

label: wing septum 2
description: Most distal of the wing septa, located in the region between the sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc12 and sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc1.

label: metathoracic pleural promotor muscle 82
description: Pleural promotor muscle of the adult metathoracic coxa that extends dorsoventrally. It attaches dorsally to the metathoracic pleurum and ventrally to the anterior margin of the metathoracic coxa.

label: distal costal vein
description: Distal-most of the three segments of the costal vein. It bears two rows of widely spaced, recurved microchaetae and two large macrochaetae at its distal tip.

label: costal vein
description: The most longitudinal vein of the anterior wing blade. It is made up of a proximal, medial and distal segments. The distal vein is contiguous with the wing vein L1.

label: metathoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 81
description: Ventral longitudinal muscle of the adult metathorax that extends anterioposteriorly. It attaches anteriorly to the metafurca and posteriorly to an apophysis of the first abdominal segment.

label: wing vein
description: Wing veins are epidermal sclerotizations above hemolymph lacunae that run between the dorsal and the ventral wing surfaces and carry trachea and nerves. The two-dimensional pattern of wing veins is the result of the cuticular differentiation of stripes of epidermal cells on the wing blade, which can be contrasted with the two-dimensional pattern of sensory organs derived from discrete cells.

label: metathoracic pleural remotor muscle 83
description: Pleural remotor muscle of the adult metathoracic coxa that extends dorsoventrally. It attaches dorsally to the metathoracic pleurum and ventrally to the posterior margin of the metathoracic coxa.

label: proximal costal vein
description: Proximal-most segment of the costal vein. It bears two rows (dorsal an ventral) of bracted microchaetae with a single unbracted microchaeta between the two rows.

label: metathoracic sternal promotor muscle 84
description: Sternal promotor muscle of the adult metathoracic coxa that extends anterioposteriorly. It attaches anteriorly to the metathoracic pleurum and posteriorly to the anterior margin of the metathoracic coxa.

label: medial costal vein
description: Second most proximal (middle) segment of the costal vein. It bears 8 microchaetae, one of which curves away from the cuticle, and a single macrochaeta.

label: haltere muscle 78a
description: Small muscle of the haltere that extends dorsoventrally, posterior to the haltere and anterior to haltere muscle 78.

label: second anal vein
description: Most proximal anal vein, that is connected to the wing vein L5.

label: haltere muscle 78
description: Small muscle of the haltere that extends dorsoventrally, posterior to the haltere and to haltere muscle 78a.

label: presumptive wing vein
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into a wing vein.

label: metathoracic lateral intersegmental muscle 80
description: Lateral intersegmental muscle of the adult metathorax that extends anterioposteriorly. It attaches anteriorly to the metafurca and posteriorly to the posterior margin of the pleural membrane of the first abdominal segment.

label: axillary vein
description: Smaller anterior longitudinal vein that arises from the humeral crossvein.

label: metathoracic pleurosternal muscle 79
description: Pleurosternal muscle of the adult metathorax, that attaches to anteriorly to the metafurca and posteriorly to the metathoracic pleurum.

label: metathoracic spiracle occlusor muscle 97
description: Any spiracular occlusor muscle (FBbt:00013333) that is part of some adult metathoracic segment (FBbt:00003022) and that connected to some adult metathoracic spiracle (FBbt:00004631).

label: metathoracic sternal remotor muscle 85
description: Sternal remotor muscle of the adult metathoracic coxa that extends anterioposteriorly. It attaches anteriorly to the metathoracic pleurum and posteriorly to the posterior margin of the metathoracic coxa.

label: wing vein L1
description: One of the most anterior and longitudinal veins of the wing blade. It is contiguous with the distal costal vein, that follows the anterior wing margin.

label: presumptive wing vein L1
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into wing vein L1.

label: skeletal muscle of metathoracic leg
description: Skeletal muscle of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: wing vein L3
description: The third most anterior longitudinal vein of the wing blade.
synonyms: fused fourth and fifth branches of radius

label: presumptive wing vein L3
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into wing vein L3.

label: wing vein L2
description: The second most anterior longitudinal vein of the wing blade.

label: presumptive wing vein L2
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into wing vein L2.

label: vertical lobe of adult mushroom body
description: Bundle of Kenyon cell projections in the adult mushroom body that arises from the anterior end of the pedunculus and projects dorsally.
synonyms: vertical branch of adult mushroom body

label: lobe system of adult mushroom body
description: The adult mushroom body lobe system consists of a dorsal branch composed of two intertwined lobes (alpha and alpha') and a medial branch consisting of three parallel lobes (beta, beta' and gamma). The lobes may have either a concentric or laminar layered structure.

label: mesothoracic intersegmental nerve
description: Intersegmental nerve of the mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic nerve
description: Any nerve (FBbt:00005105) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: metathoracic tibial depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic tibia.

label: metathoracic depressor muscle
description: Depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: anterior crossvein
description: Crossvein that connects the wing vein L3 and wing vein L4.

label: crossvein
description: A short wing that runs anterior-posterior, joining two longitudinal wing veins.

label: metathoracic intracoxal depressor muscle 88
description: Intracoxal depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic trochanter. It is a small muscle that arises ventrally in the base of the anterior coxa and attaches to the trochanter.

label: humeral crossvein
description: Crossvein that connects the anterior wing margin (proximal costal vein) and the axillary vein.

label: mesothoracic anterior fascicle neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that fasciculates with some mesothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002104).

label: mesothoracic desA neuron
description: Any desA neuron (FBbt:00001999) that is part of some mesothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1 (FBbt:00002749) and that fasciculates with some mesothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002104).

label: mesothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: metathoracic tibial depressor muscle 93
description: Depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic tibia that extends mediolaterally in the distal femur, distal to the tibial depressor muscle 92.

label: wing cell
description: A region of wing cuticle interposed between wing veins.

label: presumptive intervein
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into an intervein (wing cell).

label: metathoracic tibial depressor muscle 92
description: Depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic tibia that extends along the medial femur, proximal to the tibial depressor muscle 93.

label: posterior crossvein
description: Crossvein that connects the wing vein L4 and wing vein L5.

label: mesothoracic desB neuron
description: Any desB neuron (FBbt:00002000) that is part of some mesothoracic dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002747) and that fasciculates with some mesothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002104).

label: mesothoracic dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: The most ventral of the two trichodeum sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002056) that is part of some embryonic/larval prothoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007306).

label: metathoracic extracoxal depressor muscle
description: Extracoxal depressor muscle of the metathoracic trochanter.

label: wing vein L5
description: The fifth most anterior longitudinal vein of the wing blade.

label: presumptive wing vein L5
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into wing vein L5.

label: wing vein L4
description: The fourth most anterior longitudinal vein of the wing blade.

label: presumptive wing vein L4
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into wing vein L4.

label: prothoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002057) that is part of some embryonic/larval prothoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007306).

label: metathoracic sternal extracoxal depressor muscle 87
description: Sternal extracoxal depressor muscle of the metathoracic trochanter that extends obliquely, attaching anteriorly to the mesothoracic pleurum and posteriorly to the trochanter.

label: prothoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002058) that is part of some embryonic/larval prothoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007306).

label: metathoracic ternal extracoxal depressor muscle 86
description: Tergal extracoxal depressor muscle of the metathoracic trochanter that extends anterioposteriorly, attaching anteriorly to the postnotum and posteriorly to the trochanter.

label: wing vein L6
description: Smaller posterior vein that arises from the wing vein L5.

label: mesothoracic desC neuron
description: Any desC neuron (FBbt:00002001) that is part of some mesothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2 (FBbt:00002750) and that fasciculates with some mesothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002104).

label: mesothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc2
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: metathoracic tarsal depressor muscle 95
description: Depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic tarsus that extends along the tibia, medial to the tarsal levator muscle 94.

label: mesothoracic desD neuron
description: Any desD neuron (FBbt:00002002) that is part of some mesothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc3 (FBbt:00002751) and that fasciculates with some mesothoracic intersegmental nerve (FBbt:00002104).

label: mesothoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc3
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: costal cell
description: Anterior/proximal wing cell (intervein) region bounded by wing vein L1 posteriorly, the costal vein anteriorly and the humeral crossvein proximally.

label: metathoracic levator muscle
description: Levator muscle of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: submarginal cell
description: Wing cell (intervein) region between L2 and L3.

label: metathoracic pretarsal depressor muscle 96
description: Depressor muscle of the adult metathoracic pretarsus that extends along the tarsal segments.

label: marginal cell

description: Monoscolopidial chordotonal organ of the ventral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral multidendritic neuron
description: A multidendritic neuron of the ventral cluster sensory cluster of the larval metathoracic segment. There are four of these per cluster, all of which have axons that fasciculate with the metathoracic segmental nerve.

label: metathoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaA (FBbt:00002055) that is part of some embryonic/larval metathoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007308).

label: metathoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaB (FBbt:00002056) that is part of some embryonic/larval metathoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007308).

label: metathoracic v'es3 neuron
description: V'es3 neuron of the metathoracic segment. It is located dorsal to the v'esB neuron.

label: metathoracic v'esA neuron
description: Any v'esA neuron (FBbt:00002048) that is part of some metathoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1 (FBbt:00002776) and that fasciculates with some metathoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002163).

label: metathoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc1
description: The most ventral of the two campaniformium sensilla of the ventral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic v'esB neuron
description: Any v'esB neuron (FBbt:00002049) that is part of some metathoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2 (FBbt:00002777) and that fasciculates with some metathoracic segmental nerve (FBbt:00002163).

label: metathoracic ventral sensillum campaniformium vc2
description: The most dorsal of the two campaniformium sensilla of the ventral sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaC (FBbt:00002057) that is part of some embryonic/larval metathoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007308).

label: metathoracic ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD
description: Any ventral multidendritic neuron vdaD (FBbt:00002058) that is part of some embryonic/larval metathoracic ventral sensory cluster (FBbt:00007308).

label: abdominal 3 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Bipolar multidendritic neuron in the lateral sensory cluster of larval abdominal segments 1-7. Located at the anterior segment boundary, it emits two long dendritic branches along the segment border muscle (muscle 8) (Williams and Shepherd, 1999).

label: abdominal 4 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 1 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 7 intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp
description: Any abdominal intersegmental bidendritic neuron isbp (FBbt:00002181) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Trachea associated multidendritic neuron located anteriorly in the lateral sensory cluster of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: abdominal 1 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 6 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 2 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd
description: Any abdominal intersegmental trachea-associated neuron istd (FBbt:00002189) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: RP1 motor neuron
description: A motor neuron that develops from neuroblast NB3-1 and whose large cell body is located between the anterior and posterior commissures at the dorsal surface of the CNS.

label: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi4-3
description: A lobula plate intrinsic neuron whose cell body is on the ventral region of the cell body rind of the lobula plate. The primary neurite is short, terminating in lobula plate layers 3 and 4. It has presynaptic terminals in layer 3 and postsynaptic ones in layer 4. It is a glutamatergic neuron.

label: transmedullary Y neuron TmY13
description: Transmedullary Y wide-field neuron that terminates in lobula layers 4 and 5 and lobula plate layers 1 to 2. It displays fine arborizations in medulla layers M1, M3-M4 and M8.

label: transmedullary Y neuron TmY14
description: Transmedullary Y wide-field neuron that terminates in the lobula and lobula plate. It displays fine arborizations in medulla layers M3-M5 and M8-M10. It projects to the central brain, an unusual feature in TmY neurons.

label: adult proboscis extension reflex inhibitory neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the adult prothoracic neuromere whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the prothoracic neuromere. It arborizes bilaterally in the prothoracic neuromere and projects to the subesophageal zone. It is involved in inhibiting the proboscis extension reflex.

label: ventrolateral protocerebrum projection neuron 1
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of lateral neuropils. It arborizes in the wedge and projects dorsally to the region surrounding the mushroom body peduncle (superior intermediate protocerebrum and clamp). This neuron is not found in females. It responds to both pulse and sine song at 80dB.

label: adult fruitless aSP-k (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl1. The cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. The neurites first curve ventrally before entering a tract in neuropil region below lateral horn, then projects medially forming arborizations in the region medial to the lateral horn.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center local AMMC anteromedial neuron
description: Local neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the ventral region of the gnathal region. The primary neurite innervates the ipsilateral zones C and E of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC PN4 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that innervates the ipsilateral zone A of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and projects to the ipsilateral posterior lateral protocerebrum. The cell body is located near the midline.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC PN3 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located near the dorsal midline. The primary neurite projects ventrally and bifurcates in the vest to innervate the ipsilateral zones B and E of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The neurites that arborize in zone B extend further into the ipsilateral medial region of the inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (wedge).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC PN2 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that innervates the ipsilateral zones C and E of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and projects to the ipsilateral medial region of the inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum. The cell body is lateral to the one from AMMC projection neuron 3.

label: lobula plate tangential neuron Hx
description: A lobula plate tangential neuron whose cell body is found in the cell body rind of lateral neuropils. It arborizes in lobula plate layer 2 and projects contralaterally into the ventrolateral protocerebrum and anterior wedge. This neuron responds to front-to-back and back-to-front motion.

label: adult feeding behavior
description: Feeding behavior in a fully developed and mature organism.

label: adult subesophageal zone DSOG1 neuron
description: Descending neuron of the adult subesophageal zone whose large cell body is located in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. It arborizes extensively and bilaterally in the ventral subesophageal zone, including around the esophageal passage. It has a contralateral descending projection that terminates throughout the thoracico-abdominal ganglion. It is involved in regulating food consumption. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm13
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in anterior region of the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite extends deeper into the medulla layer, and then turns back to form to branches in M4. The arbors overlap, forming a grid-like arrangement and covering around 50-100 columns. The arbor is located in a peripheral intracolumnar position. There are around 15-20 Dm13 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm12
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite extends into the M6 layer, and then turns back to project to M3B. The arbor is circular in shape, overlapping and covering around 15-20 columns. The arbor is located in a peripheral intracolumnar position. There are around 120 Dm12 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm11
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the dorsal region of the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite extends beyond M6A layer, and then turns back, forming recurrent processes from M6A to M1, and into the first optic chiasm. The arbor varies in shape between cells, covering around 9 columns and showing tiling. The terminals in M6A layer occupy the whole layer, whereas in the other layers the processes are thin, occupying only one column, and being associated with R7 and R8 photoreceptor axons. There are around 70 Dm11 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm9
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the ventral region of the cell body rind of the medulla. It as a tubular shape, and extends between the distal M1 and M6A layers. The arbors overlap in M1 and M6A, but otherwise tile. The processes in M2 and M5 occupy a central column position and are closely associated with R7 and R8 photoreceptor axons, covering around 7 columns. There are around 110 Dm9 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm18
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite branches in the boundary between M1 and M2 layers, in the same sublayer as Dm1. The arbors form a grid-like arrangement and cover around 50-100 columns. The arbor is located in a peripheral intracolumnar position. There are around 20 Dm18 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm17
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located near the anterior edge of the medulla. Its primary neurite branches in the M2 layer, in the same sublayer as Dm14 and Dm19, and often shows bifurcations that cover separate medulla regions. It is a very large cell, with its arbor covering up to half of the whole M2 layer. The arbor is located in a intracolumnar position. There are 5 Dm17 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm16
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite branches in both the M1/M2 and M2/M3 boundary regions. The arbor is elongated along the dorsal-ventral axis, with higher arbor density located at the dorsal end of the cell. The arbor is located in a peripheral columnar position. There are around 100 Dm16 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm15
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite branches in the M2 layer, in the same sublayer as Dm14, Dm17 and Dm19 though its branches extend slightly deeper. The arbor resembles an ellipse, overlapping with that of other cells, and with the longer axis oriented at a slight angle to the anterior-posterior axis. It covers less than 10 columns. The arbor is located in a peripheral intracolumnar position. There are around 250 Dm15 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm14
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in dorsal anterior region of the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite branches in the M2 layer, in the same sublayer as Dm17 and Dm19. The arbors overlap, forming a grid-like arrangement and covering around 50-100 columns. The arbor is located in a peripheral intracolumnar position. There are around 15 Dm14 neurons per hemisphere.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi15
description: Medullary intrinsic narrow field neuron. The primary neurite bifurcates in the M1 layer, with each branch extending as far as the M7 layer, and several fine branches extending throughout. Extensive arbors are seen in M1 and M4-M7 layers. It receives input from photoreceptor cell R8.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi14
description: Medullary intrinsic narrow field neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. It has extensive arborizations in M2-M5 and M8-M9 layers.

label: medullary intrinsic neuron Mi13
description: Medullary intrinsic narrow field neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the medulla. It has bushy arborizations in the boundary region between M1 and M2 layers, and additional arbors in M3 and M8-M10.

label: proximal medullary amacrine neuron Pm4
description: Proximal medullary amacrine neuron that branches at the proximal surface of the medulla, in medulla layers M8 and M9. Its arbor covers around 11 columns. It occupies a central intracolumnar position. There are around 60 Pm4 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm20
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the dorsal and ventral regions of the cell body rind of the medulla. Its arbor is mainly located in the M3B layer, though there are branches in more proximal and distal layers, and processes branch multiple times between the edge of M1 and M3B layers. The arbor varies in shape between cells, covering 50-100 columns, and overlapping considerably. The processes are located in a peripheral intracolumnar position, similar to Dm12. There are around 50 Dm20 neurons per hemisphere.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm19
description: Distal medullary wide-field amacrine neuron whose cell body is located in the dorsal region of the cell body rind of the medulla. Its primary neurite branches in the M2 layer, in the same sublayer as Dm14 and Dm17. The arbor is very large, covering 100-200 columns. The majority of processes are located in a central columnar position, similar to Dm6. There are around 15 Dm19 neurons per hemisphere.

label: larval A02o neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 2. Its primary neurite extends anterior and posteriorly close to, or crossing the midline. It receives input from the Basin-2 and -4 and the class IV dendritic arborizing neuron.

label: larval A02m neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 2. Its soma is located in the ventral cortex region close to the medial abdominal neuromere. It is a small neuron, receiving input from the Basin-2, the chordotonal abdominal lch1 neuron and the abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaC. It only differs from the A02n neuron because its soma it more dorsal.

label: larval A02n neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 2. Its soma is located in the ventral cortex region close to the medial abdominal neuromere. It is a small neuron, receiving input from the Basin-2, the chordotonal abdominal lch1 neuron and the abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaC. It only differs from the A02m neuron because its soma it more ventral.

label: larval A29b neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 29. Its primary neurite extends anterior and posteriorly close to the midline. The dendritic terminals are located more anteriorly and the axonal terminals more posteriorly. It receives input from the Basin-1 neuron and the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2).

label: larval A12q neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 12. Its primary neurite extends anterior and posteriorly close to or crossing the midline, for most of the length of the ventral nerve cord. The dendritic terminals are located more anteriorly and the axonal terminals more posteriorly. It receives input from the Basin-2 neuron.

label: larval A08d neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. Its primary neurite extends mediodorsally to terminate close to or crossing the midline. It receives input from the 4 Basin neurons.

label: larval A00b2 neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 0. Its dendritic and axonal domains are located in the medial ventral nerve cord, crossing the midline. It receives input from the Basin-1, -2 and -4 neurons and from the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2). It is an unpaired neuron.

label: larval A00b neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 0. Its dendritic and axonal domains are located in the medial ventral nerve cord, crossing the midline. It receives input from the 4 Basin neurons, from the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2) and the class IV dendritic arborizing neuron. It is an unpaired neuron.

label: larval A08m neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. Its primary neurite extends anteriorly and arborizes close to, or crossing the midline. It receives input from the Basin-1, -3 and -4, and the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2).

label: larval A05e neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 5. Its primary neurite arborizes close to the midline and projects laterally. It receives input from the Basin-3 neuron.

label: larval A03o neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 3. Its primary neurite arborizes close to the midline. It receives input from the Basin-1 and the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2).

label: larval A08y neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing close to and across the midline. It then projects anteriorly to terminate in the brain. It receives input from the Basin-1 and -2 neurons.

label: larval A08x neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 8. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing close to and across the midline. It then extends anteriorly to terminate in the brain. It receives input from the Basin-2 and -4 neurons.

label: larval A19c neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 19. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing across the midline. It receives input from the Basin-2 and -4 neurons.

label: larval A12m neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 12. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing across the midline, with both dendritic and axonal domains extending anteroposteriorly. It receives input from the Basin-1 and -2 neurons.

label: larval A10l neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 10. It is a small neuron that arborizes close to or across the midline. It receives input from the Basin-1 and -3 neurons.

label: larval A10f neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 10. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing across the midline, with both dendritic and axonal domains extending anteroposteriorly. It receives input from the Basin-1, -2, and -3 neurons.

label: larval A10a neuron
description: Neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 10. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing across the midline. It receives input from the Basin-2, -4 and the class IV dendritic arborizing neuron.

label: larval TePn04 neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 4. Its primary neurite extends anteriorly arborizing close to and across the midline and terminates in the brain. It receives input from the Basin-2 neurons.

label: larval T08x neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval thoracic neuromere that is part of lineage 8. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing close to and across the midline. It then projects anterior and posteriorly to terminate in the brain and ventral nerve cord. It receives input from the Basin-2, -3 and -4 neurons.

label: larval T05t neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval thoracic neuromere that is part of lineage 5. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing close to and across the midline. It then projects anteriorly to terminate in the brain. It receives input from the Basin-2, -3 and -4 neurons and the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2).

label: larval A10j neuron
description: Ascending neuron of the larval abdominal neuromere that is part of lineage 10. Its primary neurite extends dorsomedially arborizing close to and across the midline. It then extends anteriorly to terminate in the brain. It receives input from the Basin-1 and -2 neurons and the eight abdominal chordotonal neurons (lch1, lch5, vch1, vch2).

label: medulla forming neuroblast
description: A neuroblast that is the precursor of the medulla. The neuroblasts that give rise to the outer medulla neurons are located in the medial edge of the larval outer optic anlage, whereas the neuroblasts that give rise to the inner medulla neurons are located in the larval inner optic anlage.

label: A1-7 oblique muscle
description: Any oblique muscle (FBbt:00000466) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: posterior midgut primordium
description: The primordium that will develop into the posterior midgut of both larva and adult. This forms from the endodermal component of the amnioproctodeal invagination when it undergoes an epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition during stage 10 and so becomes distinct from the hindgut primordium with which it was previously contiguous. This primordium forms two lobes that extend laterally on either side of the yolk. During early stage 11, the interstitial cell precursors delaminate from the tip of the primordium. During stage 11/12 the precursors of the adult posterior midgut become distinct and the remaining primordium undergoes a mesenchymal to epithelial transition after which (during stage 12) fusion of anterior and posterior midgut primordia begins, forming the fused midgut primordium.

label: posterior endoderm
description: The posterior part of the endoderm from its invagination as part of the amnioproctodeal invagination during stage 7, until it becomes morphologically distinct from the hindgut primordium due to a epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition at the end of stage 10 (Reuter et al., 1993). This epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition is also the transition from posterior endoderm to posterior midgut primordium.

label: lamina forming neuroblast
description: A neuroblast that is the precursor of the lamina. The neuroblasts that give rise to the lamina neurons are located in the lateral edge of the larval outer optic anlage.

label: abdominal dorsal oblique muscle 3 founder cell
lateral oblique muscle 1
description: The only laterally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal anterior muscle attachment site to a ventral posterior one.

label: abdominal lateral oblique muscle 1 founder cell
medial proliferation zone
description: Zone of proliferating neuroblasts that forms at the end of the second instar at the medial edge of the outer optic anlage.

label: lamina plexus
description: Region of the lamina where the axons of photoreceptor cells R1-R6 form a dense layer of expanded growth cones nestled between two layers of glial cells (Garrity et al., 1999).

label: embryonic inner optic lobe primordium
description: Primordium of the late extended germ band and closure embryo that gives rise to the larval inner optic anlage. It develops from the anterior lip of the visual primordium.

label: lobula forming neuroblast
description: A neuroblast that is the precursor of the lobula. The neuroblasts that give rise to the lobula neurons are located in the larval inner optic anlage.

label: larval inner optic anlage
description: A ribbon-like layer of neuroepithelial cells (and later of proliferating neuroblasts) in the larval optic lobe that gives rise to the adult inner medulla, lobula and lobula plate neurons. In early larval stages it is composed of neuroepithelial cells that divide symmetrically. It is wrapped around the larval antennal nerve. In the early second instar it becomes U shaped, with the opening of the U pointing in a dorso-caudal direction. It becomes distinguished from the outer optic anlage during the second half of the first instar period (Meinertzhagen and Hanson, 1993). In the third instar, neuroepithelial cells in the medial region give rise to neuroblasts that divide asymmetrically to generate the adult optic lobe neurons.

label: central plug
description: Region of the larval inner optic anlage, between the lamina and the posterior part of the outer optic anlage, composed of neuroblast progeny and ganglion cells.

label: dorsal proliferation zone
description: A zone of proliferating neuroblasts at the posterior shank of the inner optic anlage.

label: response to mechanical stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a mechanical stimulus.

label: response to abiotic stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an abiotic (non-living) stimulus.

label: intersegmental muscle
description: A hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that spans multiple segments.

label: A1-7 transverse muscle
description: Any transverse muscle (FBbt:00000470) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: abdominal dorsal transverse muscle 1 founder cell
anterior deutocerebral neuromere
description: Anterior domain of the deutocerebral neuromere of the embryo.

label: inner proliferation zone
description: A lateral zone of proliferating neuroblasts arising from the central part of the inner optic anlage near the Bolwig's nerve. Neuroblasts segregate from the anlage at the beginning of the third larval instar, and are displaced towards the point of entry of the Bolwig's nerve and then separate from each other by newly formed fiber bundles ("Zellenstrange"). One group will form the central plug, and the distal group are pushed up against the posterior face of the lamina surrounding the Bolwig's nerve.

label: inner optic anlage neuroblast
description: A neuroblast located in the larval inner optic anlage that will give rise to the adult inner medulla, lobula and lobula plate neurons. It develops from a neuroepithelial cell in the medial region of the inner optic anlage.

label: posterior deutocerebral neuromere
description: Posterior domain of the deutocerebral neuromere of the embryo.

label: abdominal 7 ventral transverse muscle 2
description: Second ventral transverse muscle of larval abdominal segment 7.

label: abdominal 7 ventral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000631) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: A1-7 ventral transverse muscle
description: Any ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000473) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: abdominal ventral transverse muscle 1 founder cell
central deutocerebral neuromere
description: Central domain of the deutocerebral neuromere of the embryo.

label: papilla nerve
description: Nerve of the larval head that carries axons from the dorsolateral papilla.

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdominal 1
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: embryonic/larval labral nerve
description: Nerve of the larval head that carries axons from the epiphysis, pharyngeal chordotonal organ, dorsopharyngeal organ, hypopharyngeal organ and the laterohypopharyngeal organ (Schmidt-Ott et al., 1994).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal acute muscle
description: Any dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000475) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 acute muscle
description: Any acute muscle (FBbt:00000474) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: response to gravity
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a gravitational stimulus.

label: A1-7 acute muscle
description: Any acute muscle (FBbt:00000474) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: larval mandibular neuromere
description: Any larval gnathal neuromere (FBbt:00111045) that is part of some larval mandibular segment (FBbt:00001738).

label: larval labial neuromere
description: Any larval gnathal neuromere (FBbt:00111045) that is part of some larval labial segment (FBbt:00001740).

label: larval maxillary neuromere
description: Any larval gnathal neuromere (FBbt:00111045) that is part of some larval maxillary segment (FBbt:00001739).

label: abdominal 1 ventral acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000595) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle (FBbt:00000594) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: A1-7 ventral acute muscle
description: Any ventral acute muscle (FBbt:00000477) that is part of some larval abdominal segment A1-7 (FBbt:00007586).

label: hypopharyngeal nerve
description: Nerve of the larval head that carries axons from the hypopharyngeal sense organ. It is joined by a branch carrying axons from the latero-hypopharyngeal organ. It joins the labral nerve before it enters the tritocerebrum.

label: abdominal 1 longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000598) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: associative learning
description: Learning by associating a stimulus (the cause) with a particular outcome (the effect).

label: abdominal 1 ventral acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000596) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: subesophageal nerve
description: Nerve that is part of the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: maxillary/labial embryonic fiber tract
description: Tract of the embryonic maxillary and labial neuromeres.

label: embryonic/larval labial nerve
description: Nerve carrying axons from the embryonic or larval head, including the hypophysis and the labial organ, to the embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion.

label: hypophysis
description: Paired compound sense organ of the labial segment in the larval head, located on the floor of the atrium, anterior to the opening of the salivary duct. It is composed of 4 sensilla. Sensory neurons travel via the labial nerve and innervate area 2 of the embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion. Neurons of the hypophysis and labial organ form a large cluster flanking the salivary duct.

label: mandibular/maxillary embryonic fiber tract
description: Tract of the embryonic mandibular and maxillary neuromeres.

label: hypomaxillary organ
description: A multiply innervated sensillum of the larval head, located next to the labial organ whose axons project into the maxillary nerve.

label: ventral organ
description: External compound sense organ of the antenno-maxillary complex of the larval head, located amongst the cirri. It contains three 'knob-like' sensilla, one bi-dendritic and two mono-dendritic. Neurons of the ventral organ connect with the larval maxillary nerve and terminate in area 2 of the subesophageal ganglion.

label: digestive system process
description: A physical, chemical, or biochemical process carried out by living organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: system process
description: A multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system. An organ system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a biological objective.

label: abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000602) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: quality
description: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities.

label: abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 4 (FBbt:00000605) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: serotonergic SE1 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 3 clusters on either side of the ventral midline in the ventral nerve cord of the mandibular segment. Axons from this cluster cross the midline in the mandibular segment. In the adult they are located adjacent to the esophagus foramen. There are 2 cells in this cluster.

label: abdominal 1 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3 (FBbt:00000604) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: FMRFamide SE2 neuron
description: Bilaterally paired (Kolhekar et al., 1997) FMRFamide expressing interneuron of the subesophageal neuromere (Schneider et al., 1993). They are located more anteriorly than the FMRFamide SE3 cells (Schneider et al., 1993).

label: serotonergic SE3 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 3 clusters on either side of the ventral midline in the ventral nerve cord of the labial segment. Axons from this cluster cross the midline in the labial segment. In the adult they are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000610) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000608) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000609) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 oblique muscle (FBbt:00000607) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal oblique muscle 5
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 5 (FBbt:00000613) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 4 (FBbt:00000612) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000611) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000617) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle (FBbt:00000616) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 lateral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000615) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral oblique muscle 5
description: Fifth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 1. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 2 where it attaches to the anterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina1).

label: abdominal 1 ventral oblique muscle 4
description: Fourth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 1. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 2 where it attaches to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2).

label: abdominal 1 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000625) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 transverse muscle
description: Any transverse muscle (FBbt:00000470) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000619) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 lateral transverse muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 3 (FBbt:00000629) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 lateral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000626) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 lateral transverse muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 2 (FBbt:00000628) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000627) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 lateral transverse muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 4 (FBbt:00000630) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 1 ventral internal muscle 1
description: A large, longitudinally oriented hypodermal muscle located internal to the ventral longitudinal muscles of larval abdominal segment 1. Serial homologs of this muscle are not found in any other segment.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000590) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 acute muscle (FBbt:00000589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdominal 2
description: Any hypodermal muscle of larval abdomen (FBbt:00000681) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: adult behavior
description: Behavior in a fully developed and mature organism.

label: hypodermal muscle of abdomen
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that is part of some abdomen (FBbt:00000020).

label: abdominal 2 ventral acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle (FBbt:00000594) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000595) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: ectodermal derivative
description: Any germ layer derivative (FBbt:00000000) that develops from some ectoderm (FBbt:00000111).

label: abdominal 2 ventral acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000596) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000610) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000608) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 oblique muscle (FBbt:00000607) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: olfactory learning
description: Any process in an organism in which a relatively long-lasting adaptive behavioral change occurs in response to (repeated) exposure to an olfactory cue.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle 5
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 5 (FBbt:00000613) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 4 (FBbt:00000612) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000611) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: endodermal derivative
description: Any germ layer derivative (FBbt:00000000) that develops from some endoderm (FBbt:00000125).

label: endoderm
description: The innermost germ layer of the embryo.

label: mesoderm
description: Germ layer that forms the middle layer of the embryo (between ectoderm and endoderm) following gastrulation. Its restricted fate includes forming muscle, heart, hemocytes and fat body.

label: anterior endoderm
description: The anterior part of the endoderm from its invagination during stage 7 to the epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition in late stage 8 when it become anterior midgut primordium. The invaginating anterior endoderm makes a short furrow that forms the cross bar of a T whose stem is the ventral furrow. After invagination, the cells divide once before the mesenchymal to epithelial transition.

label: mesectodermal derivative
description: Any germ layer derivative (FBbt:00000000) that is part of some late extended germ band embryo (FBbt:00004450) and that develops from some mesectoderm (FBbt:00000136).

label: mesectoderm
description: A double row of cells located at the midline from the end of gastrulation. The morphology of these cells is distinct from adjacent ectodermal cells - they are elongated such that one end remains exposed to the outside of the embryo at the midline while the other end bisects the internalized mesoderm.

label: axonal dopamine secretion
description: The regulated release of dopamine from an axon.

label: dopamine secretion
description: The regulated release of dopamine by a cell. Dopamine is a catecholamine and a precursor of adrenaline and noradrenaline. It acts as a neurotransmitter in the central nervous system but it is also produced peripherally and acts as a hormone.

label: axon
description: The long process of a neuron that conducts nerve impulses, usually away from the cell body to the terminals and varicosities, which are sites of storage and release of neurotransmitter.

label: presumptive tibial preapical bristle
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the tibial preapical bristle.

label: presumptive femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1.

label: presumptive femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11.

label: presumptive coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the coxal sensillum trichodeum St4.

label: presumptive coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the coxal sensillum trichodeum St8.

label: presumptive coxa-trochanter joint
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the coxa-trochanter joint.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the mesothoracic leg disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the metathoracic leg disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the metathoracic leg disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the metathoracic leg disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the metathoracic leg disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the metathoracic leg disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the prothoracic leg disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the prothoracic leg disc into dorsal and ventral compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the prothoracic leg disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the prothoracic leg disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the mesothoracic leg disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the mesothoracic leg disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the genital disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the genital disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: primary segmental branch
description: A primary branch of the tracheal system.

label: primary segmental branch primordium
description: Primordium that develops into a primary trachea.

label: genital disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the genital disc.

label: embryonic/larval thoracic alary-related muscle T2
description: A thoracic alary-related muscle that attaches anteriorly to tendon cells along the posterior boundary of the mesothoracic segment, and extends posteriorly to an attachment point on the midgut at the position of the first constriction.

label: embryonic/larval thoracic alary-related muscle
description: Thin, elongated, multinucleated visceral muscle that displays oblique orientation and extends over several adjacent segments, connecting the midgut to the exoskeleton. These muscles connect anteriorly to the exoskeleton via attachment to tendon cells along the posterior boundary of thoracic segments, and extend posteriorly, intertwining with cephalic tracheal branches, to attachment points on the midgut.

label: embryonic/larval thoracic alary-related muscle T1
description: A thoracic alary-related muscle that attaches anteriorly to tendon cells along the posterior boundary of the prothoracic segment, and extends posteriorly to an attachment point on the gastric caecum.

label: roof cell
description: A dorsal appendage forming follicle cell that forms the roof of the cellular tube encircling the developing dorsal appendages. These cells are initially located in two bilaterally symmetric domains in the dorso-anterior of the oocyte associated follicular epithelium, located immediately posterior and lateral of the floor cells. The roof cells that are adjacent to the floor cells lead the anterior migration of the whole population of roof cells and are responsible for tube elongation during dorsal appendage development.

label: oocyte associated follicle cell
description: Any follicle cell (FBbt:00004904) that is part of some oocyte associated follicular epithelium (FBbt:00007030).

label: floor cell
description: A dorsal appendage forming follicle cell that forms the floor of the cellular tube encircling the developing dorsal appendages. These cells are initially located in two bilaterally symmetric domains in the dorso-anterior of the oocyte associated follicular epithelium, located immediately posterior to the centripetally migrating follicle cells and lateral of the dorsal midline. Each domain consists of a single cell width arc that borders the roof cell domain on its anterior and dorsal sides. During elongation and sealing of the dorsal appendage forming cellular tube, the two sides of each floor cell domain extend beneath the roof cells and meet to form a seam.

label: presumptive wing margin
description: Region of the wing pouch that will develop into the wing margin.

label: embryonic central brain
description: Brain of the embryo that excludes the optic lobes. It includes the protocerebrum, deutocerebrum and tritocerebrum.

label: presumptive trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1.

label: presumptive trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5.

label: presumptive trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3.

label: presumptive trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt.

label: presumptive trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5.

label: presumptive trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8
description: Region of the ventral thoracic disc that will develop into the trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8.

label: embryonic primordium of adult clypeo-labral structure
description: Primordium of the dorsal closure and late embryo that will give rise to the adult structures that develop from the clypeo-labral imaginal disc.

label: embryonic imaginal precursor
description: Embryonic structure that will proliferate during larval development into a larval imaginal disc. During early embryogenesis the precursor is part of the epithelial sheet before segregating from the epithelial sheet by late embryogenesis (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

label: leg disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells from one of the larval leg imaginal discs.

label: pars intercerebralis primordium
description: Primordium of the late embryonic pars intercerebralis. At stage 12, the primordium of each hemisphere forms a narrow cluster of approximately 40-50 cells, in the antero-medial procephalon, behind the furrow that separates the procephalon from the clypeolabrum. The primordium then invaginates from the procephalic ectoderm between stages 11 to 13. During stages 13 to 14, the invagination pinches off the surface ectoderm and forms small vesicles in between the outer epithelium and the brain surface.

label: embryonic primordium of adult hindgut precursor
description: Primordium of the late extended germ band embryo that will give rise to the embryonic precursor of the adult hindgut.

label: presumptive embryonic salivary gland
description: The sum of the primordia in the embryo that will contribute to the embryonic/larval salivary gland.

label: somatic muscle primordium
description: Primordium of the embryonic/larval somatic musculature of the trunk. It arises from the outer layer of the trunk mesoderm. During germ band shortening (stage 13), it segregates into loose segmental clusters. Within these clusters, muscle formation proceeds by fusion of fusion competent myoblasts to muscle founder cells.

label: fat body/gonad primordium
description: Primordium which develops into the fat body and gonadal sheath. The first morphological sign of its development comes during stage 11, when the outer of the two layers of the trunk mesoderm thickens medially to become 2-3 cells thick. Segmentally arranged groups of cells split off from inner most layer of this thickening, becoming sandwiched between the somatic muscle primordium and the circular visceral muscle primordium. By stage 13, these segmental clusters have fused into continuous columns on either side of the embryo. These bands split into dorsal and ventral subdivisions. A sub-population of cells in the dorsal subdivision in parasegments 10-12 split off to form the gonadal sheath primordium during stage 14-15.

label: fat cell
description: A cell that is the principal cell type of the fat body and is filled with lipid droplets.

label: male genital disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the male genital disc.

label: male genital disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the male genital disc.

label: genital disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the genital disc.

label: amnioproctodeal invagination
description: The posterior invagination of ectoderm that gives rise to part of the digestive system.

label: female genital disc posterior compartment
description: The posterior compartment of the female genital disc.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the male genital disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the male genital disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: female genital disc anterior compartment
description: The anterior compartment of the female genital disc.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the female genital disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the female genital disc into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labral sensillum 4
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechanosensory labral sensillum 4 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: accessory pharyngeal nerve
description: The ~5um thick accessory pharyngeal nerve of the adult brain (Miller, 1950) contains axons connecting with the lower, anterior half of the adult head capsule including sensory organs along the esophagus. The two contralateral nerves fuse with the pharyngeal nerves in their exit from the gnathal ganglion, probably from the mandibular neuromere, but penetrate at a lower level into the space between the anterior cibarial plate and the dilator muscles. From here, the nerve enters the labrum to connect with its muscles and sense organs.

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum 4
description: Fourth most sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. The external sensory structure is a hair of 5 micrometers long by 0.5-1 micrometers thick. It is innervated by a mechanosensory receptor neuron.

label: wing disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells from the larval wing imaginal discs.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labral sensillum 5
