description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechanosensory labral sensillum 5 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum 5
description: Fifth most sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. The external sensory structure is a hair of 5 micrometers long by 0.5-1 micrometers thick. It is innervated by a mechanosensory receptor neuron.

label: proximal costal bract
description: A bract associated with a bristle of the proximal costa.

label: bract
description: A specialised, enlarged trichome-like structures that is located close to the base of a bristle. Bracts are induced by bristles, but are not a product of the bristle lineage (del Alamo et al., 2002 and refs therein). They are located on the proximal side of the bristle and share the same polarity. Bracts are found in the legs and wings.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labral sensillum 6
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechanosensory labral sensillum 6 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum 6
description: Sixth most sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. The external sensory structure is a hair of 5 micrometers long by 0.5-1 micrometers thick. It is innervated by a mechanosensory receptor neuron.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labial sensillum 9
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum 9 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum 9
description: Most distal sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. It is innervated both by a gustatory and mechanosensory receptor neurons. One of two medium sized, hairless sensilla of the labral sense organ.

label: dorsal margin photoreceptor
description: Any eye photoreceptor cell (FBbt:00006009) that is part of some dorsal margin ommatidium (FBbt:02000000).

label: dorsal margin ommatidium
description: An ommatidial subtype located in a single row at the dorsal margin of the eye. This ommatidial subtype is specialised to detect the e-vector of polarized sunlight.

label: chemosensory neuron of adult labial sensillum 8
description: Chemosensory neuron innervating the mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum 8 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the adult pharynx
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the adult pharynx and projects to the subesophageal zone.

label: mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum 8
description: Second most distal sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. It is innervated both by a gustatory and mechanosensory receptor neurons. One of two medium sized, hairless sensilla of the labral sense organ.

label: hindgut anlage in statu nascendi
description: Anlage in statu nascendi of the hindgut in a stage 5 embryo that will give rise to the hindgut anlage.

label: posterior endoderm anlage
description: The precursor of the posterior part of the endoderm, prior to its invagination during stage 7.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labial sensillum 8
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum 8 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: chemosensory neuron of adult labial sensillum 9
description: Chemosensory neuron innervating the mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum 9 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: chemosensory neuron of adult labial sensillum 7
description: One of seven chemosensory neuron innervating the chemosensory labral sensillum 7 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: chemosensory labral sensillum 7
description: Third most distal sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. It is innervated by 8 gustatory receptor neurons, arranged as two triplets and a pair. It is the largest of the three chemosensory sensilla of the labral sense organ.

label: dorsal margin photoreceptor cell R8
description: Any photoreceptor cell R8 (FBbt:00004227) that is part of some dorsal margin ommatidium (FBbt:02000000).

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labral sensillum 3
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechanosensory labral sensillum 3 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum 3
description: Third most proximal sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. The external sensory structure is a hair of 5 micrometers long by 0.5-1 micrometers thick. It is innervated by a mechanosensory receptor neuron.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labral sensillum 1
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechanosensory labral sensillum 1 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum 1
description: Most proximal sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. The external sensory structure is a hair of 5 micrometers long by 0.5-1 micrometers thick. It is innervated by a mechanosensory receptor neuron.

label: mechanosensory neuron of adult labral sensillum 2
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating the mechanosensory labral sensillum 2 of the adult labral sense organ (Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum 2
description: Second most proximal sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx. The external sensory structure is a hair of 5 micrometers long by 0.5-1 micrometers thick. It is innervated by a mechanosensory receptor neuron.

label: detection of light stimulus involved in sensory perception
description: The series of events in which a light stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal as part of the sensory perception of light.
synonyms: sensory perception, sensory detection of light stimulus

label: rhodopsin mediated signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of excitation of rhodopsin by a photon and the events that convert the absorbed photons into a cellular response.

label: rhabdomere R2
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R2 (FBbt:00004215).

label: rhabdomere R3
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R3 (FBbt:00004217).

label: marginal glial cell
description: Cuboidal glial cell of the optic lobe elaborating numerous fine processes, with irregular distal and lateral edges and a flat basal surface. It is located in a layer at the proximal surface of the lamina, with one marginal glial cell per cartridge (Edwards and Meinertzhagen, 2010). Processes extend from the apical side into the lamina to envelop axons and trachea. It is between the marginal glial cells and epithelial glial cells that the R1-R6 growth cones terminate (Poeck et al., 2001; Winberg et al., 1992). In the lamina, it receives synaptic input from photoreceptors R1, R5-R6 and lamina monopolar cell L4 (collaterals from adjacent columns) (Rivera-Alba et al., 2011).

label: haploid cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from haploid cells.

label: rhabdomere R1
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R1 (FBbt:00004213).

label: L-type sensilla L9
description: If present, ninth most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: rhabdomere R4
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R4 (FBbt:00004219).

label: rhabdomere R5
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R5 (FBbt:00004221).

label: rhabdomere R8
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R8 (FBbt:00004227).

label: mystery cell
description: Epithelial cell that is part of early ommatidial preclusters but which, unlike the rest of the cells in the precluster, rejoins the surrounding undifferentiated tissue of the eye disc. Mystery cells are usually located between putative R3 and R4 cells.

label: repressed primordium
description: Repressed primordium of the genital disc corresponding to that of the opposite sex (Epper and Nothiger, 1982).

label: rhabdomere R6
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R6 (FBbt:00004223).

label: rhabdomere R7
description: Any rhabdomere (FBbt:00004212) that is part of some photoreceptor cell R7 (FBbt:00004225).

label: primary pigment cell
description: Retinal pigment cell that is part of an ommatidium. Each ommatidium has two primary pigment cells. These cells line the pseudocone and are in contact basally with the cone cells. They contain coarse granules of ommochrome screening pigment. Along with the cone cells, they secrete the lens.

label: tertiary pigment cell
description: Inter-ommatidial pigment cell that lies between the vertices of adjacent ommatidia. Except at the margins of the eye, vertices alternate between those with tertiary pigment cells and those with bristles. Vertices at the margins all have tertiary pigment cells. These cells contain the red screening pigment pteridine, as well as ommochrome granules. Together with secondary pigment cells, it secretes the lens between the facets.

label: secondary pigment cell
description: Inter-ommatidial pigment cell that lies between the edges of adjacent ommatidia. It contains the red screening pigment pteridine, as well as ommochrome granules. Together with tertiary pigment cells, it secretes the lens between the facets.

label: ocellus cornea
description: Chitinous extracellular laminar secretion that covers the adult ocelli. The lens is laminated with around 45 strata. Underlying it is a monolayer of corneagenous cells.

label: ocellus lens
description: Lens of the adult ocelli. It is composed of the outer cornea and underlying monolayer of corneagenous cells.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval tracheal system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval tracheal system. This corresponds to the tracheal primordia and their component tracheal branch primordia along with primordia of the spiracles.

label: midline neuron
description: Neuron of the embryonic or larval midline.

label: ventral midline neuroblast
description: Neuroblast of the embryonic and larval ventral midline.

label: primary pigment cell pigment granule
description: Any pigment granule (FBbt:00004234) that is part of some primary pigment cell (FBbt:00004231).

label: tertiary pigment cell pigment granule
description: Any pigment granule (FBbt:00004234) that is part of some tertiary pigment cell (FBbt:00004233).

label: secondary pigment cell pigment granule
description: Any pigment granule (FBbt:00004234) that is part of some secondary pigment cell (FBbt:00004232).

label: ocellus retinula cell
description: Photoreceptor cell of the adult ocellus. The lateral ocelli have around 75 photoreceptor cells, whereas the medial one has around 100.

label: ocellus pigment granule
description: Pigment granule of the photoreceptor cell of the adult ocellus. Pigment granules are found distally around the rim of the ocellus, and proximally down from the level of the nucleus. They are composed of ommatins (brown color pigments) which do not migrate in response to light.

label: photoreceptor cell pigment granule
description: Any pigment granule (FBbt:00004234) that is part of some photoreceptor cell (FBbt:00004211).

label: tracheal branch primordium
description: Developing tracheal branch of the embryo.

label: ocellus rhabdomere
description: Rhabdomere of the adult ocellus. In contrast to the ones in the compound eye, it is open on its distal lateral surface.

label: ocellus corneagenous cell
description: Corneagenous cells of the adult ocellus. The cells form a monolayers that separates the ocellus cornea from the rhabdomeres.

label: corneagenous cell
description: Cell that separates the cornea from the underlying rhabdomeres.

label: embryonic tracheole
description: Tracheole of the embryo.

label: tracheole
description: Terminal branch of the tracheal system. Tracheoles consist of fine cuticular tubes (around 1 micrometre in diameter or less) that extend from individual tracheolar cells. Tracheoles lack a mestracheon.

label: secondary branch/tracheole primordium
description: Precursor tissue of secondary trachea and tracheoles.

label: adult prothoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult prothoracic segment (FBbt:00003020).

label: macrochaeta
description: A long, unicellular, setiform outgrowth that is strongly chitinized and may be in connection with a sensory nerve.

label: S-type sensilla S5
description: Fifth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: S-type sensilla S6
description: Sixth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum, located slightly more dorsally than S-type sensilla S5.

label: adult thoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult thorax (FBbt:00003018).

label: S-type sensilla S7
description: Seventh most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: S-type sensilla S8
description: Eighth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: S-type sensilla S9
description: Ninth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum, located slightly more dorsally than S-type sensilla S8.

label: lateral trunk primordium
description: Region of the tracheal primordium that gives rise to the embryonic/larval lateral trunk.

label: tracheal pit
description: Deep and narrow pit formed by the invagination of a tracheal placode in a late extended germ band embryo. Invagination of the placode begins during stage 11. Branches begin to bud from the pit during stage 11, with a dorsal and ventral stem being apparent by mid-stage 12. The pit closes over during stage 13. There are 10 pairs of tracheal pits - one pair in each tracheal metamere (each segment from T2 to A8). Pits are located in the central one third of each parasegment, with the most anterior in parasegment 4 and the most posterior in parasegment 14.

label: L2 GRN
description: Gustatory receptor neuron responsive to high concentrations of salt (Montell, 2009) and bitter compounds (Meunier et al., 2003).

label: S-type sensilla S1
description: Second most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some prothoracic coxa (FBbt:00004664).

label: S-type sensilla S2
description: S-type chemosensilla of the labellum, located posterodorsal to S-type sensilla S1, and more dorsally than S-type sensilla S3.

label: dorsal group branch precursor
description: Precursor of a dorsal group branch of the embryonic/larval tracheal system. These branches arise from late in stage 16 into the larval stages.

label: sensillum trichodeum of cervical membrane of prothoracic leg
description: Sensillum trichoideum of the cervical membrane of the prothoracic leg. There is a group of 12.

label: S-type sensilla S3
description: Anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum. Less dorsally located than S-type sensilla S2.

label: transverse connective primordium
description: Region of the tracheal primordium that develops into the embryonic/larval transverse connective. During stages 11 and 12, the invaginating tracheal pit forms an L shape. The arm of the L heading inwards from the surface forms the spiracular branch primordium, the other arm forms the transverse connective primordium.

label: S-type sensilla S4
description: Fourth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: lower humeral bristle
description: The most ventral of the humeral bristles.

label: dorsal branch primordium
description: Dorsally directed branch from the dorsal region of the tracheal primordium that develops into the embryonic/larval dorsal branch. It initially appears (during stage 12) as a continuation of the transverse connective primordium.

label: upper humeral bristle
description: The most dorsal of the humeral bristles.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Dorsal, bi-innervated hair of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Any one of a row of 4 trichoid sensilla located proximally and laterally, near the joint between the prothoracic coxa and the thorax.

label: presumptive prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4.

label: S cell
description: Gustatory receptor neuron responsive to sugars (Montell, 2009), and/or amino acids (Dunipace, et al., 2001, Ganguly et al., 2017).

label: prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St3
description: Any one of a row of 3 trichoid sensilla located laterally, in the joint between the prothoracic coxa and the thorax.

label: presumptive prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St3
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St3.

label: W cell
description: Gustatory receptor neuron responsive to water (Montell, 2009).

label: prothoracic coxal bristle on hairy island
description: A relatively long bristle located on a small island of hairs (trichomes) in an otherwise bare region of cuticle on the lateral side of the costa at the distal end, adjacent to its joint with the trochanter.

label: microchaeta
description: A sensillum of the adult whose external sensory structure is a hair or short thin bristle.

label: presumptive prothoracic coxal bristle on hairy island
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic coxal bristle on hairy island.

label: L1 GRN
description: Gustatory receptor neuron responsive to low concentrations of salt (Montell, 2009).

label: spiracular branch primordium
description: Region of a tracheal primordium that develops into an embryonic/larval spiracular branch. During stages 11 and 12, the invaginating tracheal pit forms an L shape. The arm of the L heading inwards from the surface forms the spiracular branch primordium. In all except the first and tenth tracheal metameres, the spiracular branch collapses, forming a solid cord.

label: prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Any one of a group of 8 trichoid sensilla located proximally and medially in two rows near the joint between the prothoracic coxa and the thorax.

label: presumptive prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8.

label: larval abdominal sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: fat body branch primordium
description: Precursor of the embryonic/larval fat body branch. All originate as a branch from the transverse connective during stage 15 apart from the primordium in the first tracheal metamere which arises during the first instar larval stage.

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13
description: Any one of a cluster of ~11-13 campaniform sensilla located posteriorly and distally on the prothoracic trochanter - near to its joint with the femur.

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some prothoracic trochanter (FBbt:00004666).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Any one of 5 medially located prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13. These are located in hairy cuticle.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5.

label: abdominal 2 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: A single, isolated sensillum trichodeum located medially and distally on the prothoracic trochanter.

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some prothoracic trochanter (FBbt:00004666).

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1.

label: lateral group branch precursor
description: Precursor of an embryonic lateral group branch. These branches begin to sprout during stage 14.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: ganglionic branch primordium
description: Precursor of the embryonic/larval ganglionic branch. It originates as the region of the posterior trunk lateral branch proximal to the lateral spur that becomes the point of fusion between anterior and posterior lateral trunk branches.

label: abdominal 5 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh2 (FBbt:00100033) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Any one of a row of 3 campaniform sensilla located laterally distally on the trochanter.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3.

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8
description: Any one of 8 laterally located prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13. These are located in naked cuticle.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8.

label: L-type sensilla L2
description: Second most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: L-type sensilla L3
description: Third most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: L-type sensilla L4
description: Fourth most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: L-type sensilla L5
description: Fifth most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: embryonic/larval spiracle primordium
description: A primordium that develops into an embryonic/larval spiracle.

label: spiracle primordium
description: A primordium in the embryo that will develop into a spiracle.

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Any one of ~10-14 trichoid sensilla located medially in two adjacent clusters of ~5-7 each (GSt1 and GSt2) on the condyle of the joint between the prothoracic coxa and the trochanter.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt.

label: L-type sensilla L6
description: Sixth most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Any one of a row of 5-6 trichoid sensilla located proximally and laterally on the prothoracic coxa.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5.

label: L-type sensilla L7
description: Seventh most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: L-type sensilla L8
description: If present, eighth most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic trochanter edge bristle
description: A distinctive, posterior pointing bristle located on the posterior edge of the medial side of the trochanter.

label: presumptive prothoracic trochanter edge bristle
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic trochanter edge bristle.

label: I-type sensilla I8
description: Eight most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some prothoracic femur (FBbt:00004667).

label: femoral sensillum campaniformium
description: Sensillum campaniformium located in the femur.

label: I-type sensilla I9
description: Ninth most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 3
description: One of the small chordotonal organ of the adult prothoracic femur. It is located in the center of the femur and has between 25-28 scolopidia. Distally, the scolopidia are more scattered than the prothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1, with a majority of them connected to the femoral muscle membrane.

label: prothoracic femoral chordotonal organ
description: Chordotonal organ of the adult prothoracic femur. There are three chordotonal organs, located in the ventral chamber near the longitudinal septum. There is one large group, on the ventro-medial side, and two smaller ones in the center of the femur.

label: I-type sensilla I10
description: Tenth most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Any one of a group of 11 campaniform sensilla located in a cluster in the posterior proximal region of the femur, close to the joint between the femur and the trochanter. They are arranged in 3 rows with 4, 4 and 3 sensilla each.

label: presumptive prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11.

label: L-type sensilla L1
description: Most anterior L-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: An isolated campaniform sensillum located proximally on the anterior edge of the prothoracic femur, close to the joint between the femur and the trochanter.

label: presumptive prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1.

label: prothoracic femoral bract
description: Any bract (FBbt:00005180) that is part of some prothoracic femur (FBbt:00004667).

label: prothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 2
description: One of the small chordotonal organ of the adult prothoracic femur. It is located in the center of the femur and has around 14 scolopidia. Distally, the scolopidia are more scattered than the prothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1, with a majority of them connected to the femoral muscle membrane.

label: prothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1
description: Large chordotonal organ of the adult prothoracic femur. It is located on the ventro-medial side and has around 32 well-aligned scolopidia. Its distal tip terminates at the distal epicuticular surface of the tip of the femur.

label: I-type sensilla I2
description: Second most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: I-type sensilla I3
description: Third most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: I-type sensilla I4
description: Fourth most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic tibial transverse row bristle
description: Any bristle located in one of 5-7 transversely oriented rows (TR) in the anterior distal side of the tibia. These bristles are thin, straight, more yellow and without bracts.

label: I-type sensilla I5
description: Fifth most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic tibial bract
description: Any bract (FBbt:00005180) that is part of some prothoracic tibia (FBbt:00004665).

label: I-type sensilla I6
description: Sixth most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: I-type sensilla I7
description: Seventh most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic tibial sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some prothoracic tibia (FBbt:00004665).

label: S-type sensilla S10
description: Tenth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row
description: Any bristle in one of the 8 longitudinal bristle rows in a prothoracic tarsal segment. Row 1 is at the most ventral position.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle
description: Any microchaeta (FBbt:00005182) that is part of some prothoracic tarsal segment (FBbt:00004668).

label: S-type sensilla S11
description: If present, eleventh most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic metatarsal segment transverse row bristle
description: Any bracted bristle in one of the transverse bristle rows (TR) of the prothoracic metatarsus (tarsal segment 1). The TRs are located in the anterior compartment. There is sexual dimorphism, with females having 7 to 8 TRs, whereas in males, 2 of the TRs have been replaced by the male specific sex comb and central bristle.

label: S-type sensilla S12
description: If present, twelfth most anterior S-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 2
description: Any bristle of the second longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, dorsal to row 1.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 1
description: Any bristle of the ventral-most longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments.

label: I-type sensilla I1
description: Most anterior I-type chemosensilla of the labellum.

label: prothoracic tibial apical bristle
description: Longer and thicker bristle in the anterior compartment, on the ventral distal region of the tibia, near the joint with the first tarsal segment.

label: presumptive prothoracic tibial apical bristle
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tibial apical bristle.

label: prothoracic tibial preapical bristle
description: Longer and thicker bristle in the anterior compartment, on the dorsal distal region of the tibia, near the joint with the first tarsal segment.

label: presumptive prothoracic tibial preapical bristle
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic tibial preapical bristle.

label: prothoracic metatarsal segment central bristle
description: A distinctive, large, straight microchaeta located on the medial prothoracic metatarsus (tarsal segment 1) of males, posterior to the sex comb.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 3
description: Any bristle of the third longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, dorsal to row 2.

label: zone C Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron that innervates zone C of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The cell bodies of these neurons are co-mingled with those of zone E Johnston organ neurons, forming a broad ring mainly in the medial and outer layers of the Johnston's organ. These neurons show a tonic response to static deflections of the arista (Kamikouchi et al., 2009) and are involved in sensing air-flow (Yorozu et al., 2009), gravitational forces (Kamikouchi et al., 2009) and initiating antennal grooming (Hampel et al., 2015). Their response is strongest when the arista is displaced anteriorly, corresponding to air flow applied to the back of the head. They are required for wind-induced suppression of locomotion behaviour (WISL) (Yorozu et al., 2009).
synonyms: Johnston's organ neuron activated by tonic anterior arista deflection

label: gravity sensitive Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron (JON) that is tonically activated by aristal deflection and is necessary for normal gravitaxis behaviour. These neurons form a broad 'ring' in the medial and outer layers of the JON array (Kamikouchi et al., 2009).

label: wind sensitive Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron (JON) tonically activated by arista deflection and required for 'wind-induced suppression of locomotion' behaviour (WISL; Yorozu et al., 2009). The cell bodies of these neurons form a broad ring in the medial and outer layers of the JON array (Kamikouchi et al., 2006).

label: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of wind
description: The series of events involved in the perception of wind in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: perception of wind, detection of mechanical stimulus

label: zone A Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron that innervates zone A of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The cell bodies of these neurons are located mainly in the inner layer of Johnston's organ, directly surrounding the antennal nerve. These neurons plays a role in hearing and are activated when stimulated with courtship song pulses (between 19-952Hz, 90dB). They are phasically activated, with the strongest activation by higher-frequency vibrations (Kamikouchi et al., 2009).

label: sound activated Johnston organ neuron
description: A Johnston organ neuron (JON) that is activated by near-field sound ranging from 19 Hz to 952 Hz, maximally at 90dB (Kamikouchi et al., 2009; Yorozu et al., 2009). These neurons are transiently (phasically) activated by the onset and offset of arista displacement. Cells preferentially activated by low-frequency vibration are loosely distributed as a ring in the middle layer of JON cell bodies. Higher frequencies preferentially activate JON neurons with cell bodies located mainly in the inner layer, directly surrounding the antennal nerve (Kamikouchi et al., 2006).

label: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of sound
description: The series of events involved in the perception of sound vibration in which the vibration is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: sensory detection of mechanical stimulus during perception of sound

label: zone B Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron that innervates zone B of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The cell bodies of zone B Johnston organ neurons are distributed as a ring in the middle layer of cells within the Johnston's organ (Kamikouchi et al., 2006). These neurons plays a role in hearing and are activated when stimulated with courtship song pulses (between 19-952Hz, 90dB). They are phasically activated, with stronger activation by low-frequency vibrations. They are required for the detection of the courtship song (Kamikouchi et al., 2009).

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 5
description: Any bristle of the fifth longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, anterior to row 4.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 4
description: Any bristle of the fourth longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, the most dorsoposterior.

label: Johnston organ bundle of antennal nerve
description: Bundle formed from the fasciculated axons of the Johnston's organ neurons (JONs) within the antennal nerve (AN). The JONs form two bundles (dorsolateral and medioventral) within the antennal nerve by the point it reaches the base of antennal segment 1 (a1/scape). Shortly before entering the brain, these two bundles combine and spread over a large area of the AN cross-section. Upon entering the brain, the JONs predominantly occupy the ventral part of the AN. At the ventrolateral side of the antennal lobe, the bundle bifurcates. One side of the bifurcation gives rise to the main trunk of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The other side defasciculates and innervates zone A of the AMMC.

label: Johnston organ
description: Compound chordotonal organ of antennal segment 2 involved in hearing (Gopfert and Robert, 2002), direction-sensitive wind detection (Yorozu et al., 2009) and gravitaxis (Kamikouchi et al., 2009). The actin-filament rich basal tips of the Johnston's organ scolopidia connect to the inner surface of antennal segment 2, and the apical tips connect to the hook of antennal segment 3 (Gopfert and Robert, 2002). Its sensory neurons (Johnston's organ neurons or JONs) are connected to the Johnston's organ nerve (Kamikouchi et al., 2006), and predominantly innervate the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). There are 477 +/- 24 cell bodies, arranged in a bowl shape lying vertically with the 'top' facing the lateral side, and forming a ring around the antennal nerve (Kamikouchi et al., 2006). JONs connecting to opposing sides of the hook are alternatively stimulated by stretching or compression according to the hook's oscillatory movement (Gopfert and Robert, 2002).

label: adult mesothoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00003021).

label: main trunk of antennal mechanosensory and motor center
description: The main trunk (MT) of antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) is one of two bundles formed by the initial bifurcation of the Johnston's organ nerve projection, ventro-laterally to the antennal lobe. The second, more lateral bundle forms the anterior portion of AMMC zone A. The MT progresses posteriorly and exhibits a second bifurcation that gives rise to the bundle forming AMMC zone B. A final posterior MT bifurcation gives rise to the AMMC lateral core and EA bundle. The MT is devoid of presynaptic sites.

label: sex comb
description: A row of darkly pigmented, male specific chaetae located on the prothoracic metatarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. The number of chaetae (teeth) per sex comb varies between individuals, e.g.- Hannah-Alava and Stern report 10-13.

label: sensilla row
description: A row of sensilla.

label: auditory sensory neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of sound (GO:0050910).

label: mesothoracic bristle
description: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some adult mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00003021).

label: presutural bristle precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell that develops into a presutural bristle.

label: Johnston organ neuron tonically activated by arista deflection
description: Johnston's organ neuron whose response is maintained so long as unidirectional aristal deflection is sustained.
synonyms: Johnston's organ neuron tonically activated by arista deflection

label: chaeta
description: A sensillum with a long, unicellular, setiform outgrowth that is strongly chitinized.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 6
description: Any bristle of the sixth longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, anterior to row 5.

label: EA bundle of antennal mechanosensory and motor center
description: Bundle, devoid of presynaptic sites, formed from one branch of the final, most posterior bifurcation of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) main trunk (MT). The other side of the bifurcation gives rise to the lateral core of the AMMC (LC). It is directly connected to zone E of the AMMC and consists of the projections of zone E Johnston's organ neurons.

label: lateral core of antennal mechanosensory and motor center
description: Neuron projection bundle containing the axons of Johnston's organ neurons (JONs) that arises from the final, most posterior bifurcation of the main trunk of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). (The other bundle arising from this bifurcation is the EA region of the AMMC). The lateral core is devoid of presynaptic sites. It terminates in a bifurcation that gives rise to the synapse rich AMMC zones C and D.

label: prothoracic metatarsal segment bristle longitudinal row
description: Any bristle in one of the 8 longitudinal bristle rows in the metatarsal segment. Row 1 is at the most ventral position.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 8
description: Any bristle of the eight longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, anterior to row 1.

label: prothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 7
description: Any bristle of the seventh longitudinal row of the prothoracic tarsal segments, ventral to row 6.

label: abdominal 6 lch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 6 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002829).

label: abdominal 6 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 lch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 7 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002830).

label: abdominal 7 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: lch1 neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 of the lateral cluster in a larval segment.

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle (FBbt:00000616) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 lateral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000615) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 6
description: Any A2-7 ventral oblique muscle 6 (FBbt:00000622) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 5
description: The fifth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 2. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 3 where it attaches to the anterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina1).

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most, ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 2. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 3 where it attaches to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2).

label: abdominal 2 ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000619) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000598) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: antennal segment 2 microchaeta
description: Bristles of antennal segment 2. There are around 25 of these.

label: antennal segment 2 sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some second segment of antenna (FBbt:00004514).

label: external sensory organ precursor cell IIc
description: Second-order precursor cell of multi-innervated external sense organs. It divides to produce only neuronal progeny.

label: external sensory organ precursor cell I
description: First-order precursor cell: mother of all the clonally related cells of an external sensory organ.

label: abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Monoscolopidial chordotonal organ of the lateral sensory cluster of larval segments A1-7. There is one of these organs per cluster. It is innervated by the abdominal v'ch1 neuron.

label: abdominal 1 lch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 1 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002824).

label: abdominal 1 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 l ch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 2 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002825).

label: abdominal 2 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 lch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 3 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002826).

label: abdominal 3 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 lch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 4 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002827).

label: abdominal 4 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 lch1 neuron
description: Any abdominal lch1 neuron (FBbt:00100024) that is part of some abdominal 5 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002828).

label: abdominal 5 lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1
description: Any abdominal lateral monoscolopidial chordotonal organ lch1 (FBbt:00002823) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: zone D Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron that innervates zone D of the most posterior region of the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) with little arborization. The cell bodies of these neurons are distributed as a pair of clusters in JO. These neurons plays a role in hearing and are activated when stimulated with courtship song pulses. They are phasically activated, with the strongest activation by medium range-frequency vibrations. These neurons are also activated by an anterior deflection of the arista, corresponding to air flow applied to the back of the head, similarly to zone C Johnston organ neuron.

label: zone E Johnston organ neuron
description: Johnston's organ neuron that innervates zone E of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The cell bodies of these neurons are co-mingled with those of zone C Johnston organ neurons, forming a broad ring mainly in the medial and outer layers of the Johnston's organ. These neurons show a tonic response to static deflections of the arista (Kamikouchi et al., 2009) and are involved in sensing air-flow (Yorozu et al., 2009), gravitational forces (Kamikouchi et al., 2009) and initiating antennal grooming (Hampel et al., 2015). Their response is strongest when the arista is displaced posteriorly, corresponding to air flow applied to the front of the head and are required for wind-induced suppression of locomotion behaviour (WISL) (Yorozu et al., 2009).

label: abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3 (FBbt:00000604) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000601) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 transverse muscle (FBbt:00000623) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 4 (FBbt:00000605) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000625) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: histoblast nest
description: One of several groups of cells in the larval abdomen that gives rise to the adult external abdomen.

label: adult accessory mesothoracic neuromere
description: Region of dense neuropil located ventrally between the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres. It mostly contains sensory afferents that enter the central nervous system via the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (ADMN).

label: ventral campaniform sensillum L3-v of wing vein L3
description: Mono-innervated campaniform sensilla of wing vein L3. It is found close to the point where L3 connects with wing vein L2. It is a large circular sensilla, with a high profile and a distinct discontinuity between the dome and socket.
synonyms: ventral campaniform sensillum of wing vein L3

label: wing sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some wing (FBbt:00004729).

label: ventral histoblast nest abdominal 1
description: Any ventral histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001818) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: accessory metathoracic nerve
description: A nerve that originates close to the root of the metathoracic nerve and that projects postero-laterally.

label: dorsal metathoracic nerve
description: A nerve that carries sensory fibers from the haltere to the metathoracic neuromere.

label: metathoracic leg nerve
description: Nerve that originates in the ventral metathoracic neuromere and carries fibers that innervate the muscles and sense organs of the metathoracic leg.

label: spiracular histoblast nest abdominal 1
description: Any spiracular histoblast nest abdominal (FBbt:00001826) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: prothoracic oblique muscle
description: Any oblique muscle (FBbt:00000466) that overlaps some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: hypodermal muscle of prothorax
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that overlaps some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: ventral mouthpart muscle 1
description: A ventrally located, embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle that extends from the lateral pharyngeal wall to the ventral epidermis of T1.

label: mouthpart muscle
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that connected to some embryonic/larval pharynx (FBbt:00001866).

label: prothoracic pharyngeal muscle
description: Any pharyngeal muscle (FBbt:00000487) that overlaps some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: prothoracic intersegmental muscle
description: Any intersegmental muscle (FBbt:00000478) that overlaps some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: midgut imaginal island
description: A cluster of adult midgut precursor cells adjacent to the basement membrane of the larval midgut. These clusters are scattered throughout the larval midgut. They form by division of adult midgut precursor cells (FBbt:00000449) during larval stages. There are two such divisions during larval life, producing quartets of cells by the wandering third instar stage. Usually one, but sometimes two peripheral cells extend their processes around the adult midgut precursor that form an imaginal island.

label: embryonic/larval imaginal precursor
description: Imaginal precursor that is part of the embryo/larva.

label: embryonic precursor cell of adult midgut
description: A cell that is a progenitor of the adult midgut and is part of the embryonic/larval midgut. These cells occupy a basal position in the midgut epithelium and divide twice during larval stages to form clusters of four cells called midgut imaginal islands.

label: prothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000467) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: prothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: anterior midgut imaginal island
description: Imaginal island of the anterior midgut.

label: anterior adult midgut progenitor
description: A cell that is a progenitor of the adult midgut and is part of the anterior embryonic/larval midgut. These cells occupy a basal position in the midgut epithelium and proliferate during larval stages.

label: abdominal ventral acute muscle 1 founder cell
muscle founder cell
description: A mononucleate cell of the embryo that determines the properties of a myofiber. It arises by asymmetric division of a muscle progenitor and does not proliferate further. There is one founder cell for each embryonic/larval somatic muscle. At the beginning of the fusion process, it fuses with one fusion competent cell. Additional fusion events follow, with other fusion competent cells being recruited by the founder cell.

label: prothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: posterior midgut imaginal island
description: Imaginal island of the posterior midgut.

label: posterior adult midgut progenitor
description: A cell that is a progenitor of the adult midgut and is part of the posterior embryonic/larval midgut. These cells occupy a basal position in the midgut epithelium and proliferate during larval stages.

label: abdominal ventral acute muscle 3 founder cell
prothoracic ventral transverse muscle 1
description: The only ventral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment. This muscle is branched, with one ventral attachment point and two lateral ones.

label: prothoracic ventral transverse muscle
description: Any ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000473) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: abdominal ventral acute muscle 2 founder cell
prothoracic transverse muscle
description: Any transverse muscle (FBbt:00000470) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: imaginal ring
description: A ring shaped structure in the embryo/larva that gives rise to part of the adult.

label: salivary gland imaginal ring
description: Ring of imaginal cells situated where the larval salivary glands join the salivary ducts, from which the adult salivary glands develop.

label: embryonic primordium of adult salivary gland
description: Primordium of the dorsal closure embryo that give rise to the salivary gland imaginal ring which in turn develops into the adult salivary gland.

label: salivary gland
description: Paired secretory organ connected to the atrium via the salivary duct. It is essentially composed of two cell types: cuboidal epithelial duct cells that form tubes connecting the secretory cells to the larval mouth; and secretory cells that synthesize and secrete high levels of protein (Andrew et al., 2000).

label: foregut imaginal ring
description: Ring of imaginal tissue located in the embryonic/larval gut, at the junction of the foregut and midgut epithelia in the anterior part of the proventriculus. It is the precursor of the posterior region of the adult foregut.

label: embryonic precursor of adult foregut
description: Imaginal cell of the embryo that will give rise to the adult foregut. The cells that are precursors to the posterior foregut originate from a ring of cells found at the anterior part of the proventriculus, the foregut imaginal ring.

label: prothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: hindgut imaginal ring
description: Ring of imaginal tissue located at the anterior region of the embryonic/larval hindgut, posterior to where the Malpighian tubules join the hindgut, from which the adult hindgut forms. The hindgut imaginal ring cells are densely clustered, appear immature and have little cytoplasm (Murakami and Shiotsuki, 2001).

label: embryonic precursor of adult hindgut
description: Imaginal cell of the embryo that will give rise to the adult hindgut. The cells that are precursors to the posterior foregut originate from two rings of cells found at the hindgut immediately posterior to the ureters of the Malpighian tubules and at the anus. These two rings grow out and eventually unite.

label: anal imaginal ring
description: Imaginal tissue from which the adult anus develops.

label: digestive system
description: The organ system involved in the absorption of nutrients.

label: embryonic/larval mouth
description: Most anterior region of the embryonic/larval gut which opens anteriorly.

label: prothoracic lateral acute muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most lateral acute muscle of the prothoracic segment.

label: prothoracic lateral acute muscle
description: Any lateral acute muscle (FBbt:00000476) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: prothoracic acute muscle
description: Any acute muscle (FBbt:00000474) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: lateral acute muscle
description: A laterally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal posterior muscle attachment site to a ventral anterior one.

label: acute muscle
description: A hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that runs from a dorsal posterior muscle attachment site to a ventral anterior one.

label: epipharyngeal sclerite
description: Unpaired sclerite to which the median tooth (labrum) posteriorly merges, and bears the cuticular pores of the labral sense organ.

label: cephalopharyngeal skeleton
description: A group of connected sclerites of the anterior embryonic/larval digestive system (atrium, pharynx and dorsal pouch). The cibarial dilator muscles connect to the cephalopharyngeal skeleton to lift the roof of the pharynx and thereby widen its lumen (Jurgens, 1986).

label: prothoracic ventral intersegmental muscle 2
description: Second dorsal-most ventral intersegmental muscle attached to the anterior apodeme of the prothoracic segment. Its posterior end is attached to the anterior apodeme of the first abdominal segment.

label: ventral intersegmental muscle
description: A ventrally located hypodermal muscle of the embryonic/larval musculature that spans multiple segments.

label: hypostomal sclerite
description: Part of the pharyngeal sclerite consisting of two lateral bars connected by a bridge (H) across the floor of the atrium, just anterior to the opening of the salivary duct.

label: prothoracic lateral acute muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most lateral acute muscle of the prothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval cibarium
description: Posterior portion of the embryonic/larval pharynx, posterior to the atrium.

label: prothoracic ventral intersegmental muscle 5
description: The most ventral of the ventral intersegmental muscle attached to the anterior apodeme of the prothoracic segment. Its posterior end is attached to the anterior apodeme of the first abdominal segment.

label: prothoracic ventral intersegmental muscle 4
description: Fourth dorsal-most ventral intersegmental muscle attached to the anterior apodeme of the prothoracic segment. Its posterior end is attached to the anterior apodeme of the first abdominal segment.

label: mouth hooks
description: A moveable pair of chitinous structures at the anterior tip of the cephalopharyngeal skeleton of the larva, on either side of the atrium. Each mouth hook has three processes: a hooked oral process extending anteriorly, a ventral process, and a dorsal process extending dorso-posteriorly to the median tooth. The mouth hooks develop from the maxillary segment.

label: dental sclerite
description: Sclerite that helps root the mouth hooks into their epidermal pockets (Jurgens et al., 1986).

label: prothoracic ventral intersegmental muscle 3
description: Third dorsal-most ventral intersegmental muscle attached to the anterior apodeme of the prothoracic segment. Its posterior end is attached to the anterior apodeme of the first abdominal segment.

label: lateral process
description: Anterior portion of the cephalopharyngeal skeleton which connects posteriorly with the vertical plates. The lateral process is tightly linked to the H piece of the hypostomal sclerite (Jurgens et al., 1993).

label: vertical bridge
description: Paired structure of the pharyngeal sclerite that connects the dorsal and ventral arms.

label: mesothoracic dorsal acute muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic dorsal acute muscle
description: Any dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000475) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic acute muscle
description: Any acute muscle (FBbt:00000474) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: hypodermal muscle of mesothorax
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: outer layer of dorsal pouch
description: Dorsal epidermal layer of the embryonic/larval dorsal pouch.

label: mesothoracic oblique muscle
description: Any oblique muscle (FBbt:00000466) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic dorsal acute muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic dorsal acute muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic dorsal acute muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: dorsal bridge
description: Unpaired part of the pharyngeal sclerite that connects the paired vertical bridges (vertical plates) .

label: embryonic/larval tentorium
description: Duct that arises from invagination from the maxillary and intercalary segments and runs between the dorsal pouch and the pharynx. Its ventral arm serves as a muscle attachment site for the ventral pharyngeal muscles (VPM 1-3).

label: embryonic tentorium
description: Specialized ectodermal structure that serves as the major muscle attachment site of the embryonic head. Its anterior arm develops from the intercalary segment, whereas its posterior arm develops from the maxillary segment.

label: mesothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000467) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: inner layer of dorsal pouch
description: Ventral epidermal layer of the embryonic/larval dorsal pouch.

label: foregut
description: An anterior part of the alimentary canal derived from the ectoderm. It is lined on its luminal side by a impermeable cuticle. The proventriculus (cardia) is located at the junction between the foregut and midgut.

label: embryonic foregut
description: Foregut of the embryo.

label: mesothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: hypopharyngeal lobe
description: Protuberance of the procephalon that marks the rudimentary third (intercalary) head segment (Hartenstein, 1993). It first becomes apparent at stage 11 of embryogenesis. This lobe bears the primordium of the hypopharyngeal organ (Jurgens and Hartenstein, 1993).

label: keyhole structure
description: Proventriculus primordium during embryonic stage 15 when it has a keyhole shape due to buckling of the foregut tube.

label: alveolar cell
description: Cell of the intermediate layer of the larval proventriculus. Alveolar cells are interspersed within this layer.

label: proventriculus intermediate layer
description: The intermediate layer of the proventriculus, with the posterior region derived from the ectodermal foregut and the anterior region from the midgut. The foregut region extends from the apex to the neck of the valve and can be divided into 3 zones of epithelium according to cellular morphology. The midgut epithelium is characterized by the presence of a prominent brush border on the apical surface, instead of the cuticle that marks the foregut.

label: mesothoracic lateral oblique muscle 1
description: The only lateral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic lateral oblique muscle
description: Any lateral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000468) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: dorsal fold
description: Epidermal structure of the embryo head which is part of the dorsal pouch. It is formed during germ band elongation shortening, at the time when the dorsal ridge moves dorsally to reach the midline and fuse with its complement on the other side. The fold progressively moves over the clypeolabrum and procephalic lobe, advancing from caudal to rostral and from lateral to medial.

label: median tooth
description: A grey, shovel-like structure that marks the site where the posterior roof of the atrium merges with the inner layer of the dorsal pouch. It is on the midline of the atrium, at the level of the anterior processes of the H-piece (hypostomal sclerite). It is characteristic of the first larval stage.

label: mesothoracic dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic segment border muscle
description: Any segment border muscle (FBbt:00000483) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic ventral oblique muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic ventral oblique muscle
description: Any ventral oblique muscle (FBbt:00000469) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic ventral oblique muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: pharynx
description: Section of the foregut anterior to the esophagus.

label: pharyngeal bar
description: Longitudinal chitinous ridge that extends ventrally along the entire length of the floor of the larval pharynx. There are 9 of these folds in third instar larvae and 7 in the second.

label: epipharynx
description: Roof of the pharynx.

label: embryonic/larval hypopharynx
description: Roof of the embryonic-larval pharynx.

label: hypopharynx
description: Floor of the pharynx.

label: hypopharynx proper primordium
description: Primordium of the late extended germ band and closure stage embryo that will give rise to the embryonic and larval hypopharynx.

label: mesothoracic transverse muscle
description: Any transverse muscle (FBbt:00000470) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: embryonic/larval proventriculus intermediate layer
description: Intermediate layer of the proventriculus (cardia) of the embryo or larva.
synonyms: recurrent wall of the embryonic/larval cardia

label: mesothoracic lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic lateral transverse muscle
description: Any lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000472) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: proventriculus outer layer
description: The outer layer of the proventriculus, produced from the anterior projection of the endodermal midgut which grows over the esophagus. It can be divided into 2 zones, with the anterior region being formed by columnar cells and the posterior region by cuboidal cells. It is covered by a loose network of muscle fibers.

label: embryonic/larval peritrophic membrane
description: Peritrophic membrane of the embryo and larva.

label: peritrophic mill
description: Neck of the proventriculus (cardia), in the posterior region, where it meets the midgut.

label: mesothoracic longitudinal muscle
description: Any longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000480) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic lateral transverse muscle 4
description: The fourth anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: esophagus
description: Section of the foregut posterior to the pharynx.

label: mesothoracic lateral transverse muscle 3
description: The third anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: proventriculus
description: Bulb-shaped organ at the junction of the foregut and midgut that regulates the passage of food into the midgut. The proventriculus folds back on itself to produce three epithelial layers: internally the posterior region of the esophagus, an intermediate (recurrent) layer derived from the ectodermal foregut and midgut and an external anterior projection of the endodermal midgut, which grows over the esophageal region. The inner two layers form the gastric valve (cardial valve) while the outer layer is defined as the wall of the proventriculus. The cuticle the lines the inner wall is thicker than other regions in the cardia, and it forms several longitudinal folds, causing the esophageal lumen to appear irregular in cross section. Between the inner and intermediate layers is the hilus which contains longitudinal muscle fibers in a fibrous extracellular matrix. Between the intermediate and outer wall is the cardia lumen, which opens posteriorly into the lumen of the midgut. The anterior region secretes the peritrophic membrane into the cardia lumen. The epithelium is surrounded by a thin tunic of striated muscle fibers.

label: embryonic proventriculus
description: Proventriculus of the embryo. It contains three distinct cell layers: inner, intermediate and outer. At the anterior end, corresponding to the most anterior region of the midgut, imaginal cells are found at the level of the intermediate layer.

label: embryonic/larval proventriculus inner layer
description: Inner layer of the proventriculus (cardia) of the embryo or larva.
synonyms: inner wall of the embryonic/larval cardia

label: proventriculus inner layer
description: The inner layer of the proventriculus, produced from the invagination of the posterior region of the esophagus (foregut). It is formed by a simple low cuboidal epithelium. The cuticle the lines the inner wall is thicker than other regions in the cardia, and it forms several longitudinal folds, causing the esophageal lumen to appear irregular in cross section.

label: mesothoracic lateral transverse muscle 2
description: The second anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: mesothoracic ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000482) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mesothoracic lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The only laterally located longitudinal muscle in embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment 1.

label: mesothoracic lateral longitudinal muscle
description: Any lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000481) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: mid embryonic/larval midgut
description: Central part of the embryonic/larval midgut. This region is acidic (Filshie et al., 1971; Shanbhag and Tripathi, 2009). The epithelium of the anterior part consists of alternating copper cells and interstitial cells (Poulson and Bowen, 1952; Filshie et al., 1971; Shanbhag and Tripathi, 2009). Immediately posterior to this is a region of large flat cells (Poulson and Waterhouse, 1960). Posterior to this, the most posterior part of the middle midgut consists of iron accumulating cells (Poulson and Bowen, 1952).

label: hypodermal muscle of metathorax
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: mesothoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: posterior embryonic/larval midgut
description: Posterior-most portion of the embryonic/larval midgut. The posterior half of this region is highly alkaline (> pH10; Shanbhag and Tripathi, 2009).

label: posterior fused midgut primordium
description: The posterior half of the fused midgut primordium. Precursor of the embryonic/larval posterior midgut.

label: mesothoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval copper cell
description: Specialised cell of the larval midgut. It secretes acid and accumulates copper. It shows a distinct apical invagination, with an opening to the lumen. The invagination is flask shaped in the posteriormost coper cells with a narrow opening, while anteriormost copper cells are beaker shaped and their opening to the lumen is larger.

label: copper cell
description: Large cell in the middle region of the midgut that is cup-shaped with long microvilli. These cells accumulate copper and secrete acid.

label: embryonic/larval salivary gland duct
description: Y-shaped tube that carries the secretions from the salivary glands to the embryonic/larval mouth.

label: metathoracic dorsal acute muscle 2
description: Second dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: metathoracic dorsal acute muscle
description: Any dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000475) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval salivary gland common duct
description: Anterior length of the salivary gland duct. Anteriorly it connects to the atrium of the foregut. Posteriorly it bifurcates into the ducts of the individual salivary glands (Skaer, 1993).

label: salivary gland common duct primordium
description: Primordium of the dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the salivary gland common duct.

label: metathoracic acute muscle
description: Any acute muscle (FBbt:00000474) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: midgut
description: The part of the alimentary canal extending posteriorly from the proventriculus to close to the point where the Malpighian tubes are attached and where the hindgut starts. It is predominantly derived from the endoderm and it is lined by the peritrophic membrane.

label: anterior fused midgut primordium
description: The anterior half of the fused midgut primordium. Precursor of the embryonic/larval anterior midgut.

label: metathoracic ventral acute muscle
description: Any ventral acute muscle (FBbt:00000477) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic dorsal acute muscle 4
description: Fourth dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: metathoracic dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Third dorsal-most dorsal acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval midgut interstitial cell
description: Columnar cell of the middle midgut, with short microvilli and deep infolding of the basement membrane forming a basal labyrinth. In the anterior region of the middle midgut, these cells alternate with copper cells. Their diameter increases from anterior to posterior.

label: embryonic/larval principal midgut epithelial cell
description: A columnar/cuboidal, absorptive epithelial cell of the embryonic/larval midgut epithelium. It has an apical brush border and a basal labyrinth.

label: midgut interstitial cell
description: Interstitial cell of the midgut. There are 30-40 cells that initially delaminate from the tip of the posterior midgut rudiment during embryonic stages 10 and 11. Later on, they intercalate into the midgut epithelium.

label: interstitial cell precursor
description: A large basophilic cell that is a precursor of the midgut interstitial cells. These cells delaminate from the tip of the posterior midgut primordium during stage 11 to form the midgut interstitial cell primordium. They intercalate back into the midgut epithelium towards the end of stage 14.

label: iron accumulating cell
description: A cell type of the posterior-most region of the middle midgut of the larva that accumulates iron when this is present at low concentrations in the food (1ug/g of ferric ferrocyanide (Prussian blue)).

label: principal midgut epithelial cell
description: Cell that forms an epithelium during germ band retraction. It corresponds to the majority of midgut rudiment cells.

label: anal slit
description: External opening of the anus.

label: embryonic/larval anus
description: Posterior opening of the embryonic/larval hindgut.

label: metathoracic dorsal oblique muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most dorsal oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000467) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic oblique muscle
description: Any oblique muscle (FBbt:00000466) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule
description: Malpighian tubule of the embryo/larva. The larval tubule is very similar to that of the adult, except that the initial segment of the anterior tubule is bigger in the larva.

label: Malpighian tubule
description: Epithelial tube with excretory and osmoregulatory roles connected, via a ureter, to the alimentary canal at the junction of the hindgut and midgut. At mid-embryogenesis, there are 6 to 10 cells encircling the lumen, whereas later on, after a phase of tubule elongation, only 2 cells encircle the lumen. There are two pairs of Malpighian tubules: one pair arises from the dorsal part of the hindgut and lies at the anterior end of the abdomen; the other pair arises from the ventral part of the hindgut and lies at the posterior end of the abdomen. Each pair shares a common ureter. The anterior pair is longer than the posterior pair.
