label: embryonic Malpighian tubule
description: Malpighian tubule of the embryo. By mid-embryogenesis when cell division ceases, a phase of tubule elongation starts, and the number of cells surrounding the lumen decreases from 6 to 10 to only 2.

label: embryonic/larval excretory system
description: Excretory system of the embryo and larva.

label: embryonic/larval posterior Malpighian tubule
description: Malpighian tubule lying in a posterior orientation (Wessing and Eichelberg, 1978).

label: posterior Malpighian tubule
description: Posterior Malpighian tubule that extends from the midgut hindgut border. It is formed from the ventral part of the hindgut. There is a pair of these that are connected to a common ureter that is on the midgut/hindgut border. The posterior tubules extend towards the tail of the embryo, with each tubule positioned on opposite sides within the body cavity. At the end of embryogenesis, the distal ends switch sides by crossing over the posterior region of the hindgut. In the mature tubules, the tip cell of the posterior tubules makes contact with the a9 abdominal visceral nerve. The posterior tubule pair is shorter than the posterior one.

label: embryonic posterior Malpighian tubule
description: Posterior Malpighian tubule of the embryo.

label: metathoracic ventral acute muscle 1
description: The only ventral acute muscle of the embryonic/larval mesothorax.

label: embryonic/larval anterior Malpighian tubule
description: Malpighian tubule attached to the right hand side of the alimentary canal and lying in an anterior orientation (Wessing and Eichelberg, 1978).

label: anterior Malpighian tubule
description: Anterior Malpighian tubule that extends from the midgut hindgut border. It is formed from the dorsal part of the hindgut. There is a pair of these that are connected to a common ureter that is on the midgut/hindgut border. The anterior tubules extend forward towards the head, with each tubule on opposite sides within the body cavity. The tubules bend back on themselves so the apex of the bend -the elbow or kink region- extends forward, leading the anterior tubules towards the head. Towards the end of embryogenesis, the kink region dips ventrally while the distal tips extend to retain their dorsal position. In the mature tubules, the tip cell of the anterior tubules makes contact with alary muscles of the heart. The anterior tubule pair is longer than the posterior one.

label: embryonic anterior Malpighian tubule
description: Anterior Malpighian tubule of the embryo.

label: metathoracic lateral oblique muscle
description: Any lateral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000468) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Fourth dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval rectum
description: Posterior-most portion of the embryonic/larval alimentary canal, terminating in the anus.

label: rectum
description: Posterior-most portion of the alimentary canal, terminating in the anus.

label: metathoracic dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: Third dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval anal pad
description: Organ consisting of paired symmetrical plates composed of large cuboidal cells, covered in a thin cuticle, and located ventrally on the last segment of the embryo/larva surrounding the anus.

label: embryonic anal pad
description: Anal pad of the embryo.

label: metathoracic dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: Second dorsal-most oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral oblique muscle
description: Any ventral oblique muscle (FBbt:00000469) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic lateral oblique muscle 1
description: The only lateral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule segment
description: Malpighian tubule segment of the embryo/larva.

label: Malpighian tubule segment
description: Segment of the Malpighian tubule. Each tubule can be divided into 4 distinct segments based on differences in appearance, cell structure and function: initial, transitional, main and ureter, from distal to proximal, respectively. The initial segment is involved in calcium homeostasis and excretion, the transitional and upper part of the main segment are secretory, whereas the lower part of the main segment is reabsorptive. Type I cells are found throughout the 4 segments, but Type II cells are absent from the lower part of the main segment and the ureter.

label: metathoracic ventral oblique muscle 1
description: Dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic transverse muscle
description: Any transverse muscle (FBbt:00000470) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic segment border muscle
description: Any segment border muscle (FBbt:00000483) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Third dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Second dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic lateral transverse muscle 3
description: The third anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic lateral transverse muscle
description: Any lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000472) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic lateral transverse muscle 2
description: The second anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Anterior-most lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic lateral transverse muscle 4
description: The most posterior lateral transverse muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic lateral longitudinal muscle
description: Any lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000481) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic longitudinal muscle
description: Any longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000480) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: superficial trachea
description: Tracheal branch of the adult abdomen that arises directly from the spiracular trachea or from the lateral trunks near the spiracular junction. There is generally one dorsal and one ventral superficial trachea in each spiracle-bearing segment.

label: metathoracic ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000482) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: dorsal superficial trachea 3
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).

label: dorsal superficial trachea
description: Dorsal branch of the superficial trachea in the adult abdomen. There is generally one dorsal superficial trachea in each spiracle-bearing segment.

label: tracheal metamere 3
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 1.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 4
description: A mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 8 (MB-M8) of the dopaminergic PAM cluster that projects bilaterally to the beta lobe slice 2. Dendritic arborizations are found in the superior intermediate and lateral protocerebrum. There are between 8-19 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 8
description: A neuron, which is part of a cluster of approximately 15 per brain hemisphere, whose cell body is found in the inferior neuropils in the dopaminergic PAM cluster. Its axon projects bilaterally to the beta lobe slices 1 or 2, both in the surface and core regions.

label: dopaminergic PAM neuron 10
description: A mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 8 (MB-M8) of the dopaminergic PAM cluster that projects bilaterally to the surface and core layers of the beta lobe slice 1. Dendritic arborizations are found in the superior intermediate and lateral protocerebrum. There are between 4-6 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body beta lobe surface layer
description: Surface layer of the mushroom body beta lobe.
synonyms: mushroom body beta lobe surface stratum

label: mushroom body beta lobe core layer
description: Inner-most layer of the mushroom body beta lobe.

label: metathoracic lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: The only lateral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: metathoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: The ventral-most (fourth dorsal-most) ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron Ir40a
description: Ipsilateral olfactory receptor neuron that expresses the Ionotropic receptor (Ir) 40a (FBgn0259683) and the co-receptor Ir25a (FBgn0031634). It innervates the antennal lobe glomeruli VP1 and VP4. Its dendrite transduces signals from the basiconic and blunt-tipped sensillum of chamber I and II of the sacculus.

label: antennal lobe glomerulus VP4
description: Ventro-posterior glomerulus of the adult antennal lobe. It lies dorsoposterior to glomerulus VP3, ventral to glomeruli DP1l.

label: blunt-tipped sensillum of sacculus
description: Coeloconic sensillum of chamber II of the sacculus of the antenna. The sensilla are blunt-tipped with a smooth cuticular surface and have a pore-like structure at their distal end. They are innervated by three sensory cells, which include water- and thermo-sensitive neurons. There are 6 sensilla of this type (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: basiconic sensillum of sacculus
description: Sensillum of chamber I of the sacculus of the antenna. The sensilla are devoid of pores, have no socket at the base and gradually taper at the distal end. The sensilla have an irregularly sculpted external surface at their distal end. They are innervated by two or three sensory cells. There are 5-7 of these sensilla; two of these contain both water- and thermo-sensitive neurons, the remaining are water-sensitive (Shanbhag et al., 1995).

label: metathoracic ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: The third dorsal-most ventral longitudinal muscle of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: ventral superficial trachea 5
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: tracheal metamere 5
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 3.

label: ventral superficial trachea 3
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).

label: ventral superficial trachea 4
description: Any ventral superficial trachea (FBbt:00110995) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: tracheal metamere 4
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 2.

label: detection of chemical stimulus
description: The series of events in which a chemical stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label: larval serotonergic T1-1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic T1 neuron whose cell body is located close to the ventral midline in the first thoracic segment. It branches next to the cell body, with the contralateral branch densely innervating the ventral and lateral regions of the prothoracic neuromere. The ipsilateral branch splits again, with one branch extending to the dorsal border and the other to the midline, sparsely innervating the contralateral side.

label: serotonergic T1-1 neuron
description: Serotonergic T1 neuron located in the first thoracic ganglion of the larva, and ventromedial and posterior in the prothoracic neuromere of the adult (Valles and White, 1988). It sparsely innervates the contralateral hemisphere.

label: larval serotonergic T1-2 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic T1 neuron whose cell body is located close to the ventral midline in the first thoracic segment. It bifurcates into an ipsi- and contralateral branch. The former splits again and innervates the ipsilateral hemineuromere completely from ventral to dorsal. The contralateral branch arborizes less extensively in the ventromedial region.

label: serotonergic T1-2 neuron
description: Serotonergic T1 neuron located in the first thoracic ganglion of the larva, and ventromedial and posterior in the prothoracic neuromere of the adult (Valles and White, 1988). It extensively arborizes the ipsilateral neuromere.

label: serotonergic T1 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron located in the first thoracic ganglion of the larva, and ventromedial and posterior in the prothoracic neuromere of the adult (Valles and White, 1988). There are three cell bodies in this cluster.

label: adult serotonergic T1 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic T1 neuron whose cell body is located in ventromedial and posterior in the prothoracic segment.

label: larval mushroom body anterior paired lateral cell
description: Intrinsic GABAergic neuron of the larval mushroom body whose large cell body is located ventromedially. It extends one primary process dorsally that bifurcates at the level of the pedunculus, sending one secondary process to innervate the calyx and another one to the lobes. The calyx process branches into fine processes that terminates in boutons. The lobe secondary process runs along the lower pedunculus and terminates in fine branches in the terminal regions of the medial lobe, the proximal region of the vertical lobe and an area connecting the lower pedunculus and vertical lobe. Pre-synaptic terminals are mainly found in the calyx, whereas dendrites are observed in the lobes.

label: serotonergic abdominal lateral neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located laterally in one of two clusters either side of the ventral midline in the larval abdominal segments A1 to A7 or adult abdominal neuromere.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center D1 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located in the posterior brain, close to the superior posterior slope. It projects ipsilaterally to the posterior side of AMMC zone D, branching to form postsynaptic terminals in zones B, C, D and E. It then passes through the posterior side of the gnathal ganglion, extending into the dorsolateral region of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: cell body rind of posterior slope
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the posterior slope.

label: serotonergic abdominal medial neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located medially in one of two clusters either side of the ventral midline in the larval abdominal segments A1 to A7 or adult abdominal neuromere.

label: dopaminergic T1 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a medial position near the esophageal foramen. It innervates the tritocerebrum, projecting to the protocerebral bridge.

label: adult feeding interneuron
description: Neuron of the adult brain whose soma is located in the subesophageal zone. The primary neurite extends ventromedially and splits into 5 dendritic branches (dorsolateral, dorsomedial, medial, ventromedial, ventral) that form a dense network of arborization mostly in the medial subesophageal zone. The main axon extends along the lateral subesophageal zone. It is involved in inducing the proboscis extension reflex and might also be involved in regulation consumption. There is one of these neurons in each hemisphere.

label: lobula tangential neuron vGATLtnew1
description: Lobula tangential neuron that arborizes in layers 2 to 4 of the lobula. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: lobula tangential neuron vGATLtnew2
description: Lobula tangential neuron that branches in layer 1 of the lobula. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: medullary tangential neuron vGATMtnew
description: Medullary tangential neuron with extensive branching that covers layers M7 to M10. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: transmedullary neuron vGATTmnew
description: Transmedullary neuron that terminates branches in layers M4 and M5, and terminates in lobula layer 6. It is a GABAergic neuron (Varija Raghu et al., 2011). It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: transmedullary Y neuron Rh5TmY
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that projects to medulla layers M7-M10, to all four lobula plate layers and to the innermost lobula layer (Lo1) in a columnar manner. In the medulla, it contacts to two to three columns while in the lobula it is three columns. It is synapsed by the photoreceptor cell R8 of pale ommatidium.

label: photoreceptor cell R8 of pale ommatidium
description: Any photoreceptor cell R8 (FBbt:00004227) that is part of some pale ommatidium (FBbt:02000002).

label: transmedullary Y neuron Rh6TmY
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that projects to medulla layers M7-M10, to all four lobula plate layers and to the innermost lobula layer (Lo1) in a columnar manner. In the medulla, it contacts two to three columns while in the lobula it is three columns. It is synapsed by the photoreceptor cell R8 of yellow ommatidium.

label: photoreceptor cell R8 of yellow ommatidium
description: Any photoreceptor cell R8 (FBbt:00004227) that is part of some yellow ommatidium (FBbt:02000001).

label: transmedullary Y neuron Rh3TmY
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that projects to medulla layers M7-M10, to all four lobula plate layers and to the innermost lobula layer (Lo1) in a columnar manner. In the medulla, it contacts to two to three columns while in the lobula it is three columns. It is synapsed by the photoreceptor cell R7 of pale ommatidium.

label: photoreceptor cell R7 of pale ommatidium
description: Any photoreceptor cell R7 (FBbt:00004225) that is part of some pale ommatidium (FBbt:02000002).

label: transmedullary Y neuron Rh4TmY
description: Transmedullary Y neuron that projects to medulla layers M7-M10, to all four lobula plate layers and to the innermost lobula layer (Lo1) in a columnar manner. In the medulla, it contacts to two to three columns while in the lobula it is three columns. It is synapsed by the photoreceptor cell R7 of yellow ommatidium.

label: adult serotonergic SE2 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic SE2 neuron whose cell body is located in the posteriolateral subesophageal ganglion.

label: larval serotonergic SE3 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SE3 neuron whose cell body is located in the maxillary segment, in a anterior ventromedial position.

label: larval serotonergic SE2 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SE2 neuron whose cell body is located in the maxillary segment, in a anterior ventromedial position.

label: larval serotonergic SP2-2 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SP2-2 neuron. It mainly innervates the basolateral protocerebrum, with one of its processes projecting to the region around the mushroom body peduncle and another process sparsely innervating the lateral region.

label: serotonergic SP2-2 neuron
description: Serotonergic SP2 neuron whose cell body is located posterior to the medial lobes of the mushroom bodies, and innervates both the ipsilateral hemisphere.

label: larval serotonergic SP2 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SP2 neuron whose cell body is located posterior to the medial lobes of the mushroom bodies, posterior to the cell bodies of SP1 neurons.

label: adult serotonergic SP2 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic SP2 neuron whose cell body is located in the anterior medial protocerebrum, posterior to the cell bodies of SP1 neurons.

label: larval serotonergic SP2-1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SP2-1 neuron that projects ipsilaterally and innervates the dorsomedial and basomedial regions, next to the vertical mushroom body lobes. From there, neurites extend contralaterally to sparsely innervate the dorsomedial and basomedial regions.

label: serotonergic SP2-1 neuron
description: Serotonergic SP2 neuron whose cell body is located posterior to the medial lobes of the mushroom bodies, and innervates both the ipsi- and contralateral hemispheres.

label: adult serotonergic SP1 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic SP1 neuron whose cell body is located in the frontal rind of the anterior medial protocerebrum. Their axons enter the anterior neuropil. There are 3 neurons in this cluster.

label: adult serotonergic SE3 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic SE3 neuron whose cell body is located in the posteriolateral subesophageal ganglion, close to the midline.

label: larval serotonergic SP1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SP1 neuron whose cell body is located in the anterodorsal cortex. The primary neurite projects ventrally and bifurcates in the posterior basomedial region, broadly innervating both the ipsi- and contralateral basomedial region. There is only one neuron of this type.

label: serotonergic T3 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron located in the third thoracic ganglion of the larva, and ventromedial and posterior in the metathoracic neuromere of the adult (Valles and White, 1988). There are two cell bodies in each cluster.

label: larval serotonergic T3 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic T3 neuron whose cell body is located close to the ventral midline in the third thoracic segment.

label: larval serotonergic T1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic T1 neuron whose cell body is located close to the ventral midline in the first thoracic segment.

label: larval serotonergic T2 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic T2 neuron whose cell body is located close to the ventral midline in the second thoracic segment.

label: serotonergic T2 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron located in the second thoracic ganglion of the larva, and ventromedial and posterior in the mesothoracic neuromere of the adult (Valles and White, 1988). There are two cell bodies in each cluster.

label: adult serotonergic T2 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic T2 neuron whose cell body is located in ventromedial and posterior in the mesothoracic segment.

label: adult serotonergic T3 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic T3 neuron whose cell body is located in ventromedial and posterior in the metathoracic segment.

label: secretion by tissue
description: The controlled release of a substance by a tissue.

label: round stem cell fusome
description: Round fusome near the anterior end of the female germline stem cell, in region 1 of the germarium.

label: stem cell fusome
description: Fusome of the germline stem cell, found in the anterior region.

label: elongated stem cell fusome
description: Elongated fusome near the anterior end of the female germline stem cell, in region 1 of the germarium.

label: ovarian sheath cell
description: Cell of the ovarian sheath.

label: adult epidermis
description: Epidermis of the adult.

label: pupal epidermis
description: Epidermis of the pupa.

label: pupal integumentary system
description: Integumentary system of the pupa.

label: spermatocyte cell spectrosome
description: Spherical fusome found in spermatocyte cells.

label: furrow canal
description: Stable infoldings of plasma membrane, rich in the cytoskeletal proteins F-actin and myosin II, present at the leading edge of membrane invagination during cellularization.

label: foregut anlage in statu nascendi
description: Anlage in statu nascendi of the foregut in a stage 5 embryo that will give rise to the foregut anlage.

label: amnioserosa anlage in statu nascendi
description: Anlage in statu nascendi of the amnioserosa in a stage 5 embryo that will give rise to the amnioserosa anlage.

label: visual anlage in statu nascendi
description: Anlage in statu nascendi of the visual system in a stage 5 embryo that will give rise to the visual system anlage.

label: Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere
description: Pdf positive neuron whose soma is located in the cortex of the fused adult abdominal ganglia. There are 4-6 of these, all of which project posteriorly, fasciculating with the abdominal nerve trunk.

label: larval Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere
description: Pdf (FBgn0023178) expressing neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster in the eighth larval abdominal neuromere of the ventral ganglion. There are 8 of these per cluster - each projecting though the paired eighth abdominal nerve to the posterior end of the larva.

label: abdominal segment 3 nerve
description: Any abdominal segment nerve (FBbt:00004104) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027).

label: abdominal segment nerve
description: Nerve that extends posteriorly from the abdominal ganglion. There is one that extends from each abdominal segment 1 to 5.

label: abdominal segment 2 nerve
description: Any abdominal segment nerve (FBbt:00004104) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00003026).

label: abdominal segment 5 nerve
description: Any abdominal segment nerve (FBbt:00004104) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029).

label: abdominal segment 4 nerve
description: Any abdominal segment nerve (FBbt:00004104) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028).

label: abdominal segment 1 nerve
description: Any abdominal segment nerve (FBbt:00004104) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00003025).

label: hypopharynx anlage in statu nascendi
description: Anlage in statu nascendi in the blastoderm embryo that will give rise to the embryonic hypopharynx.

label: middle orbital bristle
description: Medial orbital bristle that points posteriorly.

label: orbital bristle
description: Large bristle at the medial edge of the eye. There are three of these.

label: anterior orbital bristle
description: Anterior-most orbital bristle that points anteriorly.

label: posterior orbital bristle
description: Posterior-most orbital bristle that points posteriorly.

label: head bristle
description: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some head capsule (FBbt:00004482).

label: presumptive orbital bristle
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the orbital bristles.

label: midgut interstitial cell primordium
description: Primordium of the midgut interstitial cells. This becomes distinct from the posterior midgut inclusive primordium during stage 11, when its cells delaminate from the tip of the posterior midgut primordium and move postero-ventrally to form a ventral plate of basophilic cells (interstitial cell precursors) wedged between the extending lobes of the posterior midgut primordium. This primordium disappears when its cells intercalate back into the midgut epithelium towards the end of stage 14.

label: vertical bristle
description: Large bristle on top of the adult head, immediately medial to the eye. There are two pairs of these.

label: presumptive vertical bristle
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the vertical bristles.

label: occipital bristle
description: Small bristle of the posterior head, located just above the neck (occipital foramen) arranged in a dense cluster. There are around 17 bristles in each cluster.

label: presumptive occipital bristle
description: Region of the medial eye-antennal disc that will develop into the occipital bristles.

label: occiput
description: The back of the head between the vertex (dorsally), the postocciput (ventrally) and the postgena (laterally).

label: posterior vertical bristle
description: The posterior-most of each pair of vertical bristles that curves outwards.

label: anterior vertical bristle
description: The anterior-most of each pair of vertical bristles that curves inwards.

label: interocellar bristle
description: Small bristle of the dorsal head, located between the ocelli, arranged in two anterior-posterior rows.

label: presumptive interocellar bristle
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the interocellar bristles.

label: ocellar bristle
description: Large bristle of the adult dorsal head, located immediately ventral to the lateral ocelli. There are two of these.

label: presumptive ocellar bristle
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the ocellar bristles.

label: fronto-orbital bristle
description: Small bristle of the anterior head, located on the postfrons immediately medial to the eye and arranged in a dorsal to ventral line. There are around 6 of these.

label: presumptive fronto-orbital bristle
description: Region of the eye disc that will develop into the fronto-orbital bristles.

label: fronto-orbital plate
description: Integument of the anterior adult head which is located in between the postfrons and the eye.

label: frontal bristle
description: Small bristle of the anterior head, located above the antennae on the medial postfrons in two arcs of 6 bristles each, arranged so that the ventral-most bristle occupies a more medial position than the dorsal-most.

label: presumptive frontal bristle
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the frontal bristles.

label: postfrons
description: Integument that covers the anterior head capsule, in between the ptilinum and the ocelli.

label: postorbital bristle
description: Small bristle of the adult postgena, located immediately adjacent to the posterior of the eye. There is a row of these from dorsal to ventral.

label: presumptive postorbital bristle
description: Region of the lateral eye disc that will develop into the postorbital bristles.

label: postvertical bristle
description: Large bristle of the adult dorsal head, located immediately posterior to the ocelli. There are two of these.

label: presumptive postvertical bristle
description: Region of the medial eye disc that will develop into the postvertical bristles.

label: postgenal bristle
description: Bristle at the ventral margin of the postgena of the adult head, ventral to the postorbital bristles. There is a group of these.

label: presumptive postgenal bristle
description: Region of the lateral eye disc that will develop into the postgenal bristles.

label: subvibrissal bristle
description: Microchaeta that is posterior to the line of vibrissae in the adult head, below the eye.

label: premandibular bristle
description: Small bristle on the dorsal postgena of the adult head. There is a group of these.

label: presumptive premandibular bristle
description: Region of the mediodorsal eye disc that will develop into the premandibular bristles.

label: interommatidial bristle
description: Mechanosensory microchaete that projects from alternate facet vertices of the ommatidia, over most of the adult eye, usually at the anterior end of the horizontal face. The placement is less regular towards the anterior region of the eye.

label: vibrissae
description: Curved bristle of head capsule, located under the eyes and above the mouthparts.

label: presumptive vibrissae
description: Region of the lateral eye disc that will develop into the vibrissae.

label: cibarial sense organ
description: Compound sense organ located in the cibarium of the adult pharynx, near the upper end of the posterior cibarial plate. It comprises two sense organs, dorsal and ventral, that are innervated by gustatory receptor neurons.

label: cibarial fish-trap bristle
description: Sensory bristle on the anterior plate of the cibarium of the adult pharynx, near the ventral cibarial sense organ (VCSO). These bristles project upwardly and are arranged in two rows, dorsal and ventral to the VCSO. There are 18 to 23 bristles, each innervated by a mechanosensory neuron.

label: ventral row bristle of the cibarium
description: One of 12-15 singly innervated small bristles of the ventral row of the cibarial fish-trap bristle, ventral to the ventral cibarial sense organ. They are innervated by mechanosensory neurons.

label: ventral row of the cibarium
description: Cibarial bristle row that is ventral to the ventral cibarial sense organ in the adult pharynx. It consists of twelve to fifteen small bristles in the cibarium, each innervated by a single mechanoreceptor (Stocker and Schorderet, 1981; Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: dorsal row bristle of the cibarium
description: One of 6-8 singly innervated bristles of dorsal row of the cibarial fish-trap bristle, dorsal to the ventral cibarial sense organ. They are innervated by mechanosensory neurons.

label: dorsal row of the cibarium
description: Cibarial bristle row that is dorsal to the ventral cibarial sense organ in the adult pharynx. It consists of six to eight large bristles in the cibarium, each innervated by a single mechanosensory neuron (Stocker and Schorderet, 1981; Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label: ventral cibarial sense organ
description: Ventral-most cibarial gustatory sense organ near the upper end of the posterior cibarial plate of the adult pharynx, and innervated by the pharyngeal nerve (Demerec, 1994; Nayak and Singh, 1983). It is flanked distally and proximally by the ventral row bristles and the dorsal row bristles, respectively. It comprises three sensilla (distal, middle and proximal), containing in total about 8 gustatory receptor neurons.

label: anterior sensillum of dorsal cibarial sense organ
description: Most anterior of the two dorsal cibarial sensilla of the adult pharynx (Montell, 2009). It is innervated by three gustatory receptors (Gendre et al., 2004).

label: dorsal cibarial sense organ
description: Dorsal-most cibarial sense organ near the upper end of the posterior cibarial plate of the adult pharynx, and innervated by the pharyngeal nerve. It comprises two sensilla (anterior and posterior), each containing three gustatory receptor neurons.

label: posterior sensillum of dorsal cibarial sense organ
description: Most posterior of the two dorsal cibarial sensilla of the adult pharynx (Montell, 2009). It is innervated by three gustatory receptors (Gendre et al., 2004).

label: mechanosensory labral sensillum
description: Sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx that is innervated only by a mechanosensory receptor neuron. There are 6 of these sensilla, numbered from proximal to distal.

label: mechanosensory sensory organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050974).

label: adult hypopharynx
description: Anterior wall of the labral channel, the anterior-most portion of the adult foregut.

label: adult labral sense organ
description: Sense organ that extends along the adult hypopharynx. It comprises a heterogeneous group of nine sensilla, numbered from proximal to distal, containing a total of 8 mechanosensory and 10 gustatory receptor neurons. Three of these sensilla are gustatory, one with 3 neurons and the others with one each. The remaining 6 sensilla are mechanosensory (Nayak and Singh, 1985). It develops from the epiphysis (larval labral sense organ).

label: cellular response to light stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a light stimulus, electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light.

label: cellular response to radiation
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an electromagnetic radiation stimulus. Electromagnetic radiation is a propagating wave in space with electric and magnetic components. These components oscillate at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation.

label: mechano-chemo-sensory labral sensillum
description: Sensillum of the adult labral sense organ in the adult pharynx that is innervated both by a mechanosensory and gustatory receptor neuron. There are 2 of these sensilla.

label: maxillary palp sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some maxillary palpus (FBbt:00004546).

label: sensillum basiconicum
description: A eo-type sensillum in which the external part has the form of a minute projecting cone or peg.

label: response to radiation
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an electromagnetic radiation stimulus. Electromagnetic radiation is a propagating wave in space with electric and magnetic components. These components oscillate at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation.

label: cellular response to abiotic stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an abiotic (non-living) stimulus.

label: sessile hemocyte
description: A hemocyte that is not freely circulating, but is attached to the inner surface of the integument or attached to the imaginal discs. Sessile hemocyte islets are segmentally distributed and often located near crystal cells or along the posterior region of the dorsal vessel, concentrated in 2 denser organ-like clusters. These islets contain plasmatocytes, crystal cells and lamellocyte precursors.

label: pseudotracheal taste peg
description: Taste peg located in rows between and on the lateral sides of the 6 pseudotracheal rows of the adult labellum. Each peg sensillum contains one putative chemosensory and one mechanosensory neuron. The lateral rows contain 1-5 taste pegs per row, whereas the remaining rows contain 7-9 pegs.

label: labellar taste peg
description: Gustatory peg between the cuticular folds of pseudotrachea of the adult labellum. They measure around 4um in length with a distal shaft of about 2.5um arising from a base that is 1-1.5um high. They are innervated by one chemosensory neuron and one mechanosensory neuron.

label: pseudotrachea
description: Open channel that extends from the dorsal medial region of the labellum, pointing slightly around the outside of each half of the labellum. The pseudotrachea is kept open by narrow, somewhat variably shaped, transverse, sclerotised bands, the ends of which are free from the derm. There are 6 of these per palpus, conducting food to the tip of the labrum.

label: presumptive pseudotrachea
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the pseudotrachea.

label: rostral sensillum
description: Sensillum trichodeum of the rostral membrane of the adult head.

label: rostral membrane
description: Integument which covers the basiproboscis, extending dorsally to the occipital foramen. It is covered with grouped hairs, with the distal rostral sensilla located near its ventral edge, at the insertion of the maxillary palpus.

label: prothoracic gland primordium
description: The primordium that will form the embryonic/larval prothoracic gland, a substructure of the embryonic/larval ring gland. It originates in the dorsal ectoderm of T1, from which it segregates during stage 15 to form bilateral clusters near the heart precursors. In late embryogenesis, it partially fuses with the corpus allatum.

label: postoccipital sensillum
description: Sensillum trichodeum that is located on the dorsal region of a narrow band that borders the occipital foramen of the adult head dorsally. There are two of these.

label: presumptive postoccipital sensillum trichodeum
description: Region of the anterior eye-antennal disc that will develop into the postoccipital sensillum trichodeum.

label: postocciput
description: Narrow sclerotized area immediately surrounding the dorsal and lateral margins of the occipital foramen.

label: labellum sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some labellum (FBbt:00004531).

label: maxillary palp bristle
description: Trichoid sensillum of the maxillary palp with an external sensory structure that is anchored in a socket and consists of a small bundle of closely apposed fibers, each of which has grooves running longitudinally. No obvious pores are present.

label: mechanosensory chaeta
description: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050974).

label: embryonic primordium of adult tracheal precursor
description: Primordium of the late embryo that will give rise to the embryonic precursor of the adult trachea.

label: tracheal primordium
description: Primordium of a single tracheal metamere of the embryonic/larval tracheal system from its appearance as a placode during stage 11 to the completion of fusion with adjacent tracheal metameres in stage 15/16. There are 10 pairs of tracheal primordia - one pair in each segment from T2 to A8. Each tracheal primordium originates as a slight depression in the lateral ectoderm during stage 10 known as a tracheal placode. During stage 11, these placodes invaginate to form tracheal pits that elongate and branch. These pits close over during stage 13. Fusion of tracheal primordia begins at stage 14 with fusion of the dorsal trunk primordia and is complete by early stage 16.

label: proximal rostral sensillum
description: Sensillum trichodeum located medial to the anterior tentorial pit in the rostral membrane of the adult head. There are four of these.

label: presumptive proximal rostral sensillum
description: Region of the lateral eye-antennal disc that will develop into the proximal rostral sensillum.

label: distal rostral sensillum
description: Sensillum trichodeum located at the distal end of the rostral membrane of the adult head, near to the insertion of the palpus. There are two to four of these.

label: presumptive distal rostral sensillum
description: Region of the lateral eye-antennal disc that will develop into the distal rostral sensillum.

label: postgenal sensillum
description: Sensillum trichodeum of the postgena of the adult head, located in the medial region, ventral to the premandibular bristles. There is a group of these.

label: presumptive postgenal sensillum
description: Region of the lateral eye-antennal disc that will develop into the postgenal sensilla.

label: small sensillum basiconicum
description: The smallest subtype of basiconic sensilla. It measures around 9 micrometers in length and around 1.7 micrometers in width at the base. It shows slight tapering towards the tip. The cuticular wall is 100-200nm thick and contains pores or around 40nm wide. Except for the base, the pores are arranged in longitudinal rows, with 80nm between pores and 200nm between parallel rows. It is innervated by two sensory neurons. Small basiconic sensillum are found in the antennal segment 3.

label: large sensillum basiconicum
description: The largest subtype of basiconic sensilla. It measures 12 micrometers and 2.5 micrometers wide with blunt tips. Directly above the base of the sensillum, the shaft diameter is often somewhat reduced resulting in a club-shaped appearance. The pores are arranged in lines, positioned wider apart than in the small sensillum basiconicum. It is innervated by two or 4 sensory neurons. Two subtypes can be identified, base on the internal morphology of the peg (LB-I and LB-II). Large basiconic sensillum are found in the antennal segment 3.

label: auditory sense organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of sound (GO:0050910).

label: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in equilibrioception
description: The series of events involved in equilibrioception in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal. During equilibrioception, mechanical stimuli may be in the form of input from pressure receptors or from the labyrinth system of the inner ears.
synonyms: equilibrioception, sensory transduction of mechanical stimulus

label: sensillum coeloconicum
description: A general name for various or olfactory gustatory sense organs of conical shape in which the external process is sunken in a cavity of the body wall. Usually found in the extra-oral cavity or other mouthparts.

label: presumptive sacculus
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the sacculus.

label: embryonic/larval ureter
description: Proximal segment connecting a pair of Malpighian tubules to the alimentary canal in the embryo/larva. The ureter is surrounded by longitudinal and circular muscles.

label: ureter
description: Proximal segment connecting a pair of Malpighian tubules to the alimentary canal. The ureter is surrounded by longitudinal and circular muscles.

label: embryonic ureter
description: Proximal segment connecting a pair of Malpighian tubules to the alimentary canal in the embryo. The ureter is surrounded by longitudinal and circular muscles.

label: embryonic/larval specialised Malpighian tubule cell
description: Specialised cell of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubules.

label: specialised Malpighian tubule cell
description: Specialised cell of the Malpighian tubules. There are four different types: type I, type II, tip and tiny cell.

label: embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule tip cell
description: Tip cell of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule.

label: Malpighian tubule tip cell
description: Cell at the distal tip of each Malpighian tubule. It is involved in tube elongation in embryogenesis by stimulating cell proliferation in neighboring cells and in positioning the tubules.

label: embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule Type I cell
description: Type I cell of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubules.
synonyms: larval Malpighian tubule Type I cell

label: Malpighian tubule Type I cell
description: Morphologically distinct cell type found throughout the Malpighian tubules. It is a large epithelial cell joined by septate junctions to other Type I cells, with apical microvilli and infolding of the basal membrane. There are small differences between Type I cells in different tubule segments: in the initial segment, the cells have few microvilli and are relatively narrow compared with the larger, flatter cells of the main segment. Type I cells originate from division of the ectodermal Malpighian tubules primordial cells that are found in the junction between the hindgut and midgut. Type I cell proliferation is complete by late stage 13 of embryogenesis. In the mature tubules there are on average 484 Type I cells.

label: embryonic/larval initial segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Distal segment of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule. The initial segment of the larva is bigger than in the adult.
synonyms: larval initial segment of Malpighian tubule

label: initial segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Distal segment of the Malpighian tubule. It is involved in calcium homeostasis and excretion. The initial segment of the adult is smaller than in the larva.

label: embryonic initial segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Distal segment of the embryonic Malpighian tubule.

label: embryonic/larval transitional segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Second most distal segment of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule.
synonyms: larval transitional segment of Malpighian tubule

label: transitional segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Second most distal segment of the Malpighian tubule. It is involved in secretion.

label: embryonic transitional segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Second most distal segment of the embryonic Malpighian tubule.

label: embryonic/larval main segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Third most distal segment of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule.
synonyms: larval main segment of Malpighian tubule

label: main segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Third most distal segment of the Malpighian tubule. Its upper region is involved in secretion and the lower region in reabsorption.

label: embryonic main segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Third most distal segment of the embryonic Malpighian tubule.

label: grooved sensillum
description: Sensillum that is double-walled, containing an open slit channel system. For three-fourths of its length from the tip, the cuticular surface bears alternating longitudinal grooves and ridges. In cross-section, the cuticle is hollow and looks like a ring of spheres, each with a small solid cuticular ridge on its external surface. In the groove, between two ridges, there is a small slit, exposing the interior of the sensilla to the outside. Proximally, the lateral walls of adjacent cuticular ridges fuse. The inner wall surrounds the lumen of the hair, which contains a thin, loosely scattered, electron-lucent homogeneous material. It is innervated by two sensory neurons. There are 2 types of grooved sensilla, both found in chamber III of the sacculus.

label: embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule Type II cell
description: Type II cell of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubules. These cells show a cuboidal-shaped morphology.
synonyms: larval Malpighian tubule Type II cell

label: Malpighian tubule Type II cell
description: Morphologically distinct cell type found only in the initial, transitional and main segments of the Malpighian tubules interspersed with Type I cells. Type II cells are smaller and flatter than Type I cells, with shorter (main segment) or no (initial region) apical microvilli. Type II cells originate from a subset of caudal visceral mesoderm cells that overlie the tubule primordia as they evert from the hindgut. By stage 15, Type II cells have been incorporated in the tubules and adopt epithelial characteristics. In the mature tubules there are on average 110 Type II cells.

label: adult excretory structure
description: Anatomical structure of the adult excretory system.

label: yellow body
description: During adult midgut development, the epithelia of the larval proventriculus, gastric caeca, and midgut are sloughed off into the lumen of the new midgut, to form the yellow body, which is evacuated as the meconium after adult eclosion (Skaer, 1993).

label: aristal sensillum
description: Sensillum of the arista. There are three of these per arista, each consisting of a pair of sensory neurons surrounded by 2 sheath cells. They project into the lymph space of the arista core, where they float freely - unattached to the epidermis. These projections consist of specialised dendrites surrounded throughout their length by sheath cells and distally by an electron dense dendritic sheath. The three projections terminate at different points along the shaft.

label: blunt-tipped sensillum
description: Sensillum of the coeloconic type that does not have a pore. It is 2 micrometers long and 1.7 micrometers wide at the base, tapering towards the tip. A pore-like structure at the distal end is plugged by electron-dense material. At the very tip, the sensillum is covered by a similar electron-dense structure. The outer cuticular surface is smooth. Internally, the cuticle has a spongy appearance. There is a single central lumen that terminates below the electron-dense layer.

label: glutamate secretion
description: The controlled release of glutamate by a cell. The glutamate is the most abundant excitatory neurotransmitter in the nervous system.

label: dicarboxylic acid transport
description: The directed movement of dicarboxylic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: larval DN period neuron
description: Neuron whose soma is located in a cluster between the larval optic lobe and the central brain and innervate the larval optic neuropil (Keene et al., 2011; Mazzoni et al., 2005) with branches in the dorsomedial protocerebrum. Pre-synaptic sites are present in these dorsomedial branches (Hamasaka and Nassel, 2006). Their arborizations in the larval optic neuropil overlap those of Rh5 and Rh6 photoreceptors of Bolwig organ. LN neurons show strong cycling of Period (FBgn0003068) expression from 4-5hr old L1 larvae located starting from around 4-5 hours after hatching. There are about 5 neurons per cluster.

label: larval pacemaker neuron
description: Pacemaker neuron that is part of the larval nervous system.

label: larval DN1 neuron
description: A neuron whose soma is located in the dorso-anterior region of the larval brain cortex and projects to the larval optic neuropil (Keene et al., 2011). Some of the processes run along the axons of the larval s-LNv neurons and arborize near the s-LNv dendrites. It exhibits strong circadian cycling of Period (FBgn0003068) expression starting at about 15 hours post-hatching. There are one or two of these cells per hemisphere.

label: larval DN2 neuron
description: Neuron whose soma is located in a region lateral and posterior to that of the DN1 neurons in the dorsal region of the larval brain, in the vicinity of the dorsal s-LNv terminals. It arborizes in this area and projects to the contralateral side of the brain, arborizing in the dorsomedian protocerebrum. It does not arborize in the larval optic neuropil (Keene et al., 2011). It exhibits strong circadian cycling of Period (FBgn0003068), with expression starting at about 15 hours post-hatching. There are one or two of these cells per hemisphere.

label: larval DN3 neuron
description: Period (FBgn0003068) expressing neuron whose soma is located in the larval brain cortex in a cluster dorso-anterior to the DN2 cluster. Expression of Period in this cell does not show circadian cycling.

label: meconium
description: The contents of the gut at eclosion.

label: larval neuromere
description: Neuromere of the larva.

label: larval LN period neuron
description: Neuron whose soma is located in a cluster between the larval optic lobe and the central brain that shows strong cycling of Period (FBgn0003068) expression from 4-5hr old L1 larvae located starting from around 4-5 hours after hatching. There are about 5 neurons per cluster.

label: cornea
description: Chitinous extracellular laminar secretion that covers each ommatidia of the adult eye. It is optically clear and biconvex, being around 5um thick at its centre, and it covers the pseudocone layer. It is secreted by the underlying four cone cells and two primary pigment cells. The cornea between the facets is secreted by the secondary and tertiary pigment cells and although continuous with the lens, it is not stacked in deep layers.

label: lens
description: Lens of the adult eye. It is composed of the outer cornea and underlying pseudocone layer.

label: pseudocone
description: Extracellular secretion that is found between the corneal lens and the apical surface of photoreceptors and cone cells. It is made up of a gelatinous, clear substance that is secreted in pupal stage by the four underlying cone cells and primary pigment cells.

label: equatorial cone cell
description: Equatorial cone cell. It is a mirror-image of the polar cone-cell, abutting it.

label: cone cell
description: A cell type of the ommatidium. Each ommatidium contains four cone cells. The four cell bodies form a plate that is the floor of the pseudocone and the roof of the rhabdomere chamber. The surface facing the pseudocone is covered with small papillae that secrete lens materials. The lower surface, facing the photoreceptors, makes numerous hemi-desmosomes with the extracellular cap above the rhabdomeres. Each cone cell extends a thin process, the inter-retinular fiber, between the photoreceptors to the base of the ommatidium where it makes a foot. The four cone cell feet make a plug at the base of the rhabdomere chamber. Cone cells contain coarse ommochrome pigment granules.

label: posterior cone cell
description: Posterior cone cell. It is a mirror-image of the anterior cone-cell, but does not abutt it.

label: polar cone cell
description: Polar cone cell. It is a mirror-image of the equatorial cone-cell, abutting it.

label: anterior cone cell
description: Anterior cone cell. It is a mirror-image of the anterior cone-cell, but does not abutt it.

label: acetylcholine secretion
description: The regulated release of acetylcholine by a cell.

label: anterior protocerebral neuromere
description: Anterior domain of the protocerebral neuromere of the embryo.

label: central protocerebral neuromere
description: Central domain of the protocerebral neuromere of the embryo.

label: gamma-aminobutyric acid secretion
description: The regulated release of gamma-aminobutyric acid by a cell or a tissue. The gamma-aminobutyric acid is the principal inhibitory neurotransmitter in the brain but is also found in several extraneural tissues.

label: embryonic/larval supraesophageal connective
description: Connective of the embryonic/larval supraesophageal ganglion.

label: embryonic/larval cervical connective
description: Longitudinal connective of the embryonic/larval nervous system that forms the anterior continuation of the connective from the ventral nerve cord into the brain. It is pioneered by three tracts: lateral, posterior and medial cervical tracts. Dorsally, after passing the foregut, it branches into the supraesophageal and protocerebral connectives. The antennal nerve and the frontal connective branch off the cervical connective in the deutocerebrum.

label: embryonic/larval protocerebral connective
description: Horizontal connective of the embryonic/larval protocerebrum that branches from the cervical connective. It is pioneered by the medial and lateral protocerebral tracts.

label: posterior protocerebral neuromere
description: Posterior domain of the protocerebral neuromere of the embryo.

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 6
description: Any A2-7 ventral oblique muscle 6 (FBbt:00000622) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle (FBbt:00000616) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 5
description: The fifth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 5. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 6 where it attaches to the anterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina1).

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 5. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 6 where it attaches to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2).

label: abdominal 5 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000601) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000598) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000600) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdominal 5
description: Any hypodermal muscle of larval abdomen (FBbt:00000681) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3 (FBbt:00000604) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 (FBbt:00000603) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000602) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: upper lateral accessory lobe
description: Upper region of the lateral accessory lobe (LAL), divided from the lower region by fibers extending from the LAL commissure, through the center of the LAL.

label: cell body rind of anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label: superior pharyngeal sensory center
description: Region of the prow containing terminals of peripheral axons from the superior branch of the pharyngeal and accessory pharyngeal nerves.

label: cell body rind of superior lateral protocerebrum
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label: anterior maxillary sensory center
description: Region of the gnathal ganglion of the adult brain containing terminals of peripheral axons from the anterior secondary branch from the anterior branch of the maxillary-labial nerve, from a subset of gustatory receptor neurons of labellum sensilla. Three distinct subregions can be identified: a lateral anteriormost zone (AMS1), a lateralmost zone (AMS2) and a medial zone that reaches the midline (AMS3).

label: posterior maxillary sensory center
description: Region of the gnathal ganglion of the adult brain containing terminals of peripheral axons from the posterior secondary branch from the anterior branch of the maxillary-labial nerve, from a subset of gustatory receptor neurons of labellum sensilla. Five distinct subregions can be identified: a horn-like protrusion in the dorsolateral GNG (PMS1), a dorsal medial region (PMS2), a ventral medial region (PMS3), a zone near the entry point of the labial nerve (PMS4) and a zone ventral to PSM3 (PSM5).

label: labial sensory center
description: Region of the gnathal ganglion of the adult brain containing terminals of peripheral axons from the posterior branch of the maxillary-labial nerve, from a subset of gustatory receptor neurons of labellum sensilla. Three distinct subregions can be identified: a posterior zone (LS1), a ventral protrusion on the posterior side of LS1 (LS2) and an anterior medial zone (LS3).

label: inferior pharyngeal sensory center
description: Region of the subesophageal zone of the adult brain containing terminals of peripheral axons from the inferior branch of the pharyngeal and accessory pharyngeal nerves. Two distinct subregions can be identified: one dorsal to the AMS1 (VPS1) and another medial to AMS1 and dorsal to AMS3 (VPS2).

label: abdominal 5 transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 transverse muscle (FBbt:00000623) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 4 (FBbt:00000605) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 lateral transverse muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 2 (FBbt:00000628) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 lateral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000626) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000627) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000625) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 lateral transverse muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 4 (FBbt:00000630) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 lateral transverse muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 3 (FBbt:00000629) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: anterior superior lateral protocerebrum
description: Anterior subregion of the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label: mushroom body calyx arborizing neuron 2
description: A neuron whose cell body is located on the posterior superior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain, close to the pars intercerebralis. There are 3 of these per hemisphere. Their cell bodies form a cluster. The cell body fiber runs ventrally and bifurcates near the protocerebral bridge to form a laterodorsal and a lateroventral projection. The dorsal projection arborizes in the superior and inferior neuropils, with some branches entering the accessory calyx of the mushroom body. Some of these fibers connect the accessory calyx and the ventral peripheral zone of the main calyx. The ventral projection forms extensive arborization in the superior and inferior neuropils, and further projects to the posteriorlateral protocerebrum.

label: abdominal 5 ventral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000631) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000590) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 acute muscle (FBbt:00000589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdominal 6
description: Any hypodermal muscle of larval abdomen (FBbt:00000681) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 2
description: A neuron whose cell body lies on the inferior neuropils above the anterior surface of the middle part of the gamma lobe of the adult brain. The cell body fiber runs dorsally on the anterior surface of the gamma lobe, with one branch innervating the middle part of the gamma lobe (slice 3). Another branch further bifurcates on the dorsal surface of the medial lobe. One of these branches terminates in the crepine and superior medial protocerebrum behind the medial lobe, whilst the other turns medially through the border between the gamma and beta' lobes and enters the opposite hemisphere. The fibers from the opposite hemisphere run horizontally, enter the medial lobe through border between the gamma and beta' lobes and forms arborization in the middle part of the gamma lobe (slice 3). It is a dopaminergic neuron of the PAM cluster. There are approximately 9-23 neurons of this type per hemisphere.

label: cell body rind of crepine
description: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the crepine.

label: abdominal 5 ventral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A2-7 ventral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000632) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 ventral acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle (FBbt:00000594) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000591) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000595) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: dopaminergic PPL2c neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 2 cell bodies in the cortex of the posterior lateral protocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: adult mushroom body anterior paired lateral cell
description: A single, bilaterally paired mushroom body intrinsic neuron. Its large (~10um) cell body is located on the dorsal margin of the ventrolateral protocerebrum, in the lateral cell body region, between the anterior lateral superior clamp and the optic lobe. A single fiber projects dorsomedially towards the mushroom body and bifurcates into two branches (Tanaka et al., 2008). One merges with the mediolateral antennal lobe tract at the lateral side of the calyx before entering and extensively arborizing over the calyx. The other branch enters the mushroom body in the medial region of the vertical lobes. Arborizations are found in the pedunculus, in the vertical and medial lobes of the mushroom body (Liu and Davis, 2009) and in the accessory calyx (Tanaka et al., 2008). This neuron is GABA-ergic (Liu and Davis, 2009), with pre-synaptic terminals found throughout the mushroom body lobes, being more pronounced in the alpha' and beta' lobes (Pitman et al., 2011). This neuron is electrically connected to the mushroom body dorsal paired medial cell (Wu et al., 2011). These neurons respond to odors and are involved in olfactory learning (Liu and Davis, 2009).

label: mushroom body dorsal paired medial cell
description: A serotonergic mushroom body intrinsic neuron (Lee et al., 2011) whose large cell body (~12um) is part of a bilateral pair of neurons located on the posterior ventral superior medial protocerebrum and antler region of the brain. A single neurite extends towards the ipsilateral mushroom body and bifurcates in the superior neuropils. One branch arborizes extensively within the mushroom body alpha and alpha' lobes, whilst the other branch arborizes extensively within the mushroom body beta, beta' and gamma lobe complexes. The cell processes also form a network of fibers and terminations in the mushroom body spur and anterior region of the pedunculus. There are no detectable projections to any other brain neuropil region (Waddell et al., 2000). Pre-synaptic terminals are found throughout the mushroom body lobes, being more pronounced in the alpha and beta lobes (Pitman et al., 2011). This neuron is electrically connected to the mushroom body anterior paired lateral cell (Wu et al., 2011).

label: medial lobe of adult mushroom body
description: A bundle of Kenyon cell projections in the adult mushroom body that arises from the anterior end of the pedunculus and projects medially.

label: mushroom body anterior inferior medial cell
description: A neuron, whose cell body is located in front of the anterior inferior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain, anterior to the vertical and medial mushroom body lobes. The cell body fiber enters the medial lobe through the gap between the gamma and beta' lobes. Within the gamma lobe, neurite projection is limited to the middle segment between the tip and the base of the lobe, named as gamma4. In the beta', neurites arborize in the lateral part of the beta'a stratum (beta'a1) and the medial segment of beta'm and beta'p strata (beta'm2 and beta'p2). At the medial edge of the beta'm and beta'p strata, some of the fibers project to the contralateral lobe. There is only neuron of this type per hemisphere.

label: mushroom body calyx arborizing neuron 1
description: GABAergic neuron whose cell body is located at the posterior area of the lateral cell body region between the posteriolateral protocerebrum and the optic lobe of the adult brain. It projects dorsally towards the lateral horn before branching and extensively arborizing in the ventral part of the lateral horn, then turning medially and terminating in the calyx. There is more than two of these per hemisphere.

label: abdominal 6 ventral acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000596) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000610) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000608) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: mushroom body medial-vertical lobe arborizing neuron 1
description: A neuron whose cell body is located in the inferior neuropils, ventrolateral to the calyx of each adult brain hemisphere. The cell body fiber projects towards the anterior of the inferior neuropils. On the way there it bifurcates with one branch turning ventrally and terminating in the ventral complex. The second branch further branches in the crepine close to the beta lobe. One of these branches runs medially to the opposite hemisphere. Another turns ventrolaterally and arborizes in the basal segments of the gamma lobe (slice 2) and alpha' lobe (slice 1). The final branch arborizes in the superior medial protocerebrum. It is a dopaminergic neuron of the PPL1 cluster. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: abdominal 6 oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 oblique muscle (FBbt:00000607) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle 5
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 5 (FBbt:00000613) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 4 (FBbt:00000612) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000611) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: dopaminergic PPM2 neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 8 cell bodies in the cortex of the posterior inferior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: lower lateral accessory lobe
description: Lower region of the lateral accessory lobe (LAL), divided from the upper region by fibers extending from the LAL commissure, through the center of the LAL.

label: dopaminergic PAL neuron
description: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 5 cell bodies in the cortex located lateral to the dorsal portion of the vertical lobes in the middle of the superior lateral protocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: dopaminergic PPM1 neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a small cluster along the dorsoventral midline of the posterior superior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain.

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle (FBbt:00000616) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 lateral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000615) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 5
description: The fifth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 6. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 7 where it attaches to the anterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina1).

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 6. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 7 where it attaches to the posterior intrasegmental apodeme (ina2).

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000619) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000618) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000598) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral oblique muscle 6
description: Any A2-7 ventral oblique muscle 6 (FBbt:00000622) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: 1-1M
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911) and that develops from some neuroblast NB1-1 (FBbt:00001371).

label: abdominal 6 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 (FBbt:00000603) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000601) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000602) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000600) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 transverse muscle (FBbt:00000623) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 4 (FBbt:00000605) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3 (FBbt:00000604) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000625) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: presumptive humeral sclerite
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the humeral sclerite.

label: embryonic garland cell
description: Garland cell of the embryo.

label: garland cell
description: Large binucleate cell that forms a 'garland' around the anterior end of the proventriculus (cardia) at its junction with the esophagus in both adults and larvae. There are a group of these, with each cell surrounded by a basement membrane, with numerous micro-invaginations (lacunae) extending from the surface into the cytoplasm. At the mouth of each lacuna is a doubled filament forming a specialised filtration system (diaphragm). The filtrate is endocytosed from the lacunae.

label: hemocyte
description: Blood cell of the circulating hemolymph that is involved in the cellular immune response.

label: embryonic hemocoel
description: Hemocoel of the embryo.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval adipose system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval adipose system.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval endocrine system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval endocrine system.

label: embryonic fat body
description: Fat body of the embryo.

label: embryonic peritrophic membrane
description: Peritrophic membrane of the embryo.

label: excretory system
description: The system of organs and cells involved in the excretion of waste products.

label: yellow ommatidium
description: Ommatidial subtype with stochastic distribution throughout the retina making up about 70% of all ommatidia. This ommatidial subtype is specialised to detect longer wavelengths (far UV + green).

label: pale ommatidium
description: Ommatidial subtype with stochastic distribution throughout the retina, making up about 30% of all ommatidia. This ommatidial subtype is specialised to detect shorter wavelengths (near UV + blue) than yellow ommatidia.

label: adult posterior Malpighian tubule
description: Malpighian tubule of lying in a posterior orientation (Wessing and Eichelberg, 1978).

label: adult Malpighian tubule
