description: Malpighian tubule of the adult. It is very similar to that of the larva, except that the initial segment of the anterior tubule is much smaller in the adult.

label: lamina anlage glial cell
description: Any glial cell (FBbt:00005144) that is part of some lamina anlage (FBbt:00001939).

label: adult Malpighian tubule segment
description: Malpighian tubule segment of the adult.

label: adult anterior Malpighian tubule
description: Malpighian tubule attached to the right hand side of the adult alimentary canal and lying in an anterior orientation (Wessing and Eichelberg, 1978).

label: adult initial segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Distal segment of the adult Malpighian tubule. The initial segment of the adult is smaller than in the larva.

label: adult Malpighian tubule Type I cell
description: Type I cell of the adult Malpighian tubules.

label: adult specialised Malpighian tubule cell
description: Specialised cell of the adult Malpighian tubules.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 6.5
description: Longitudinal bractless bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 6, in an antero-anterioventral position.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row
description: Any bristle in one of the 8 longitudinal bracted or 4 bractless bristle rows in a mesothoracic tarsal segment. Row 1 is at the ventro-posterioventral position, with numbering continuing through the posterior, dorsal, and anterior surfaces.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 6
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 5.5, in an anterior position.

label: adult Malpighian tubule tip cell
description: Tip cell of the adult Malpighian tubule. The tip cell of the adult anterior tubules makes contact with alary muscles of the heart, whereas the tip cell of the posterior tubules contacts the a9 hindgut visceral nerve on the surface of the hindgut.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 8
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is posterior to row 1, in a ventral position.

label: S2 cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells of late embryos (20h-24h AEL), likely from a macrophage-like lineage. They grow in a loose monolayer.

label: embryo-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from embryonic cells.

label: adult Malpighian tubule Type II cell
description: Type II cell of the adult Malpighian tubules. These cells show a bar-shaped morphology in the initial and transitional segments and stellate-shaped morphology in the main segment.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 7
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is posterior to row 6.5, in an anterioventral position.

label: adult main segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Third most distal segment of the adult Malpighian tubule.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 4
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 3.5, in a posteriodorsal-dorso position.

label: adult transitional segment of Malpighian tubule
description: Second most distal segment of the adult Malpighian tubule.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 5.5
description: Longitudinal bractless bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 5, in an anteriodorsal position.

label: adult ureter
description: Proximal segment connecting a pair of Malpighian tubules to the alimentary canal in the adult. The ureter is surrounded by longitudinal and circular muscles.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 5
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 4, in a dorsal position.

label: eyelet
description: A cluster of 4 extra-retinal photoreceptors located beneath the basement membrane, at the posterior margin of the compound eye, near to the equator. Derived from the larval Bolwig's organ.

label: metathoracic bristle
description: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some adult metathoracic segment (FBbt:00003022).

label: adult metathoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult metathoracic segment (FBbt:00003022).

label: metathoracic papilla
description: One of a pair of campaniform sensilla of the haltere sclerite. It is an elliptical sensillum with a high profile and socket (type 5). The two sensilla are fused to each other by the cuticle of their sockets. It is around 5 micrometers in diameter.

label: presumptive metathoracic papilla
description: Region of the lateral haltere disc, anterior to the presumptive metathoracic spiracle, that develops into the metathoracic papilla.

label: eyelet photoreceptor
description: Cholinergic, rhabdomeric photoreceptor cell which is part of the eyelet (Yasuyama and Meinertzhagen, 1999). Eyelet photoreceptors function in entrainment of the circadian clock to photoperiod (Helfrich-Forster et al., 2002). Their axons terminate in the accessory medulla (Helfrich-Forster et al., 2007).

label: embryonic dorsal epidermis
description: Epidermis of the dorsal region of the embryo.

label: dorsal pedicellar sensillum campaniformium
description: A campaniform sensillum that is one of around 40 sensilla arranged in 10 transverse rows on the dorsal side of the pedicel. It is elliptical with a low profile and socket (type 5). The central cuticular specialisation has a raised profile, and the sockets are fused to the sockets of adjacent sensilla in the same row. It is around 3-4 micrometers in length.

label: haltere sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some haltere (FBbt:00004783).

label: presumptive dorsal pedicellar sensillum campaniformium
description: Region of the haltere disc, surrounding the presumptive capitellum, that develops into the dorsal pedicellar sensillum campaniformium.

label: capitella sensillum trichodeum
description: A trichoid sensillum of the capitellum. There are around 15-19 of these, all unpigmented. Close to 6 of these cluster into a group, the others are more dispersed.

label: presumptive capitellum sensillum trichodeum
description: Central region of the haltere disc that develops into the capitellum sensillum trichodeum.

label: embryonic dorsal apodeme
description: Dorsal halve of an embryonic apodeme. The discontinuity between dorsal and ventral halves is visible on a lateral view.

label: dorsal apodeme primordium
description: Primordium of the embryonic dorsal apodeme in the dorsal closure embryo.

label: pedicellar brush
description: A dense field of trichomes that lies between the dorsal and ventral arrays of campaniform sensilla on the pedicel. Each pedicel has two of these, anterior and posterior.

label: trichome field
description: A group of trichomes covering a region of integument.

label: anal pad primordium
description: Primordium of the anal pad of the late extended germ band and dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the embryonic anal pads.

label: embryonic ventral epidermis
description: Epidermis of the ventral region of the embryo.

label: embryonic epidermis
description: Epidermis of the embryo.

label: ventral pedicellar sensillum campaniformium
description: A campaniform sensillum that is one of around 46 sensilla arranged in 10 transverse rows on the ventral side of the pedicel. It is elliptical with a low profile and socket (type 5). The central cuticular specialisation has a raised profile, and the sockets are fused to the sockets of adjacent sensilla in the same row. It is around 3.5-4 micrometers in length.

label: presumptive ventral pedicellar sensillum campaniformium
description: Region of the haltere disc, surrounding the presumptive capitellum, that develops into the ventral pedicellar sensillum campaniformium.

label: chordotonal organ of scabellum
description: Any chordotonal organ (FBbt:00005215) that is part of some scabellum (FBbt:00004786).

label: large chordotonal organ of scabellum
description: Large chordotonal organ of the base of the haltere, that is inserted axially in this region.

label: small chordotonal organ of scabellum
description: Small chordotonal organ of the base of the haltere, that spans the this region transversely.

label: dorsal scabellar sensillum campaniformium
description: One of around 42 circular socket-less campaniform sensilla with a high profile (type 2), arranged in 6 longitudinal rows on the dorsal surface of the scabellum. Their diameters increase distally in each row, to be around 2.5-4.0 micrometers.

label: presumptive dorsal scabellar sensillum campaniformium
description: Region of the haltere disc, surrounding the presumptive pedicel, that develops into the dorsal scabellar sensillum campaniformium.

label: ventral scabellar sensillum campaniformium
description: One of 4-5 elliptical socketed campaniform sensilla with a high profile (type 5) arranged in a diamond shape on the ventral side of the scabellum. It is around 4 micrometers in diameter.

label: presumptive ventral scabellar sensillum campaniformium
description: Region of the haltere disc, surrounding the presumptive pedicel, that develops into the ventral scabellar sensillum campaniformium.

label: embryonic ventral apodeme
description: Ventral halve of an embryonic apodeme. The discontinuity between dorsal and ventral halves is visible on a lateral view.

label: ventral apodeme primordium
description: Primordium of the ventral apodeme of the dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the ventral apodemes.

label: metathoracic leg sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some metathoracic leg (FBbt:00004707).

label: metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Any one of a group of 8 trichoid sensilla located proximally and medially in two rows near the joint between the metathoracic coxa and the thorax.

label: metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some metathoracic coxa (FBbt:00004708).

label: presumptive metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8
description: Any one of 8 laterally located metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13. These are located in naked cuticle.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some metathoracic trochanter (FBbt:00004710).

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8.

label: foregut visceral muscle fiber
description: Muscle fibers of the visceral muscles of the foregut.

label: visceral muscle fiber
description: Muscle fiber of visceral muscles. It is uninucleate and the contractile material packs the whole fiber.

label: hindgut visceral muscle fiber
description: Muscle fibers of the visceral muscles of the hindgut.

label: metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Any one of a row of 4 trichoid sensilla located proximally and laterally, near the joint between the metathoracic coxa and the thorax.

label: presumptive metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Any one of a row of 3 campaniform sensilla located laterally distally on the trochanter.

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13
description: Any one of a cluster of ~11-13 campaniform sensilla located posteriorly and distally on the metathoracic trochanter - near to its joint with the femur.

label: scolopale rod
description: Cylindrical structure that surrounds the dendrites of the scolopidial neuron. The scolopale rod is often irregular and fenestrated, with desmosome-like junctions present laterally between the rod and the dendrites.

label: scolopidium
description: Sensilla unit of a chordotonal organ, consisting of a cap cell, a ligament cell, a scolopale cell (sheath cell) and one or more sensory neurons. The basal end of the scolopidium is held in place by a ligament cell, usually attached to the integument. The dendrite of each sensory neuron has a cilium projecting from its tip through the scolopale, a rod like structure secreted by the scolopale cell. The cilium terminates in a dendritic cap, embedded in the cap cell. The cap cell is attached to the integument.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Any one of 5 medially located metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13. These are located in hairy cuticle.

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5.

label: cibarial muscle trachea
description: Tracheal branch of the adult head that splits anteroventrally from each frontal air sac and joins with the branch of the opposite side. It supplies small branches to the pumping muscles of the cibarium.

label: adult trachea
description: Trachea of the adult.

label: frontal head air sac
description: Largest tracheal air sac of the adult head, extending ventrally and anteriorly to the brain. It corresponds to the expansion of a ventral branch of the cervical trachea. It flanks the cibarium and extends forward and upward around the gnathal ganglion and brain to the level of the antennae and the ptilinal suture. A small dorsal branch extends into the antenna and forms the antennal air sac.

label: postgenal air sac
description: A small tracheal air sac of the adult head, located ventrally and posterior to the eye. It corresponds to the expansion of a ventral branch of the cervical trachea. It tapers ventrally to form the labial trachea and its branch, the maxillary palpus trachea.

label: labial trachea
description: Trachea of the adult head that results from the ventral tapering of the postgenal air sac. It extends down into the proboscis, with the maxillary palpus trachea splitting from it, and terminates in the labial muscles.

label: metathoracic femoral bract
description: Any bract (FBbt:00005180) that is part of some metathoracic femur (FBbt:00004711).

label: anteroscutal air sac
description: Sickle-shaped air sac that arises as a dorsal diverticulum of the anterior connective of the parenteric air sac. It extends upwards and backwards between the dorsal muscles.

label: parenteric air sac
description: Elongated air sac of the adult thorax. It is a continuation of the abdominal dorsal trunk. It flanks the digestive tube in the thorax and becomes the cervical trachea in the neck region. It anastomoses anteriorly with the lateral system of the same side through a wide medial extension of the propleural sac, and posteriorly through a short connective near the posterior thoracic spiracle. The two parenteric sacs are connected by a short, straight dorsal commissure in the prothorax and a longer curved commissure under the mesophragma, both passing above the alimentary canal.

label: lateroscutal air sac
description: Lobe of the dorsal air sac in the lateral scutum.

label: metathoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1
description: Large chordotonal organ of the adult metathoracic femur. It is located on the ventrolateral side and has around 32 well-aligned scolopidia. Its distal tip terminates at the distal epicuticular surface of the tip of the femur.

label: metathoracic femoral chordotonal organ
description: Chordotonal organ of the adult metathoracic femur. There are three chordotonal organs, located in the ventral chamber near the longitudinal septum. There is on large group, on the ventrolateral side, and two smaller ones in the center of the femur.

label: medioscutal air sac
description: Lobe of the dorsal air sac in the medial scutum.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: A single, isolated sensillum trichodeum located medially and distally on the metathoracic trochanter.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some metathoracic trochanter (FBbt:00004710).

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1.

label: cervical trachea
description: Trachea of the adult neck that arises from the parenteric air sac of the thorax. It enters the head through the foramen magnum and it splits into a dorsal and ventral branches which eventually expand to form the head air sacs.

label: scolopidial cilium
description: Non-motile cilium at the distal end of the dendrite of a scolopidial neuron.

label: scolopidial dendrite
description: Specialised dendrite of scolopidial neuron. Its distal end is a cilium, surrounded by a scolopale and terminating in a dendritic cap.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Any one of ~10-14 trichoid sensilla located medially in two adjacent clusters of ~5-7 each on the condyle of the joint between the metathoracic coxa and the trochanter.

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt.

label: dorsal head air sac
description: A tracheal air sac located dorsally in the adult head, above the brain. It corresponds to the expansion of an ascending trachea that splits from a lateral branch of the cervical trachea.

label: antennal air sac
description: A very small tracheal air sac located in the antenna. It arises from a dorsal fine branch of the frontal head air sac.

label: metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Any one of a row of 5-6 trichoid sensilla located proximally and laterally on the metathoracic coxa.

label: presumptive metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5.

label: hypopleural air sac
description: A ventrally located air sac of the metathorax. It arises from the lateral trunk and extends ventrally into the base of the metathoracic leg. The metathoracic (posterior thoracic) spiracle opens into this air sac.

label: adult lateral trunk
description: Longitudinal tracheal branch of the adult, ventral to the dorsal trunk. It joins the dorsal trunk immediately behind the first thoracic spiracle. In the thorax it is extended into a series of air sacs (propleural, sternopleural and hypopleural). In the abdomen, at the level of the third pair of spiracles it becomes more tracheate and extends through to the seventh spiracle. It is connected to the lateral trunk in each abdominal segment by a long transverse connective. At the level of the second pair of spiracles, these connectives are much shorter and stouter.

label: metathoracic femoral chordotonal organ 2
description: One of the small chordotonal organ of the adult metathoracic femur. It is located in the center of the femur and has around 14 scolopidia. Distally, the scolopidia are more scattered than the metathoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1, with a majority of them connected to the femoral muscle membrane.

label: notopleural air sac
description: Lobe of dorsal air sac underlying the prothoracic episternum (propleurum).

label: metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some metathoracic femur (FBbt:00004711).

label: metathoracic femoral chordotonal organ 3
description: One of the small chordotonal organ of the adult metathoracic femur. It is located in the center of the femur and has between 25-28 scolopidia. Distally, the scolopidia are more scattered than the metathoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1, with a majority of them connected to the femoral muscle membrane.

label: adult dorsal trunk
description: Longitudinal tracheal branch of the adult, dorsal to the lateral trunk. It begins anteriorly as a backwards continuation of the first spiracular trachea. It joins the lateral trunk immediately behind the first thoracic spiracle. The dorsal trunk is very broad in diameter and sac-like (forming the parenteric air sac) until reaching the region of the fifth pair of spiracles. It then narrows, extending until abdominal segment 8. In the abdomen, it is connected to the lateral trunk in each segment by a long transverse connective. At the level of the second pair of spiracles, these connectives are much shorter and stouter. The right and left abdominal dorsal trunks of each segment are connected by a transverse dorsal commissure, or dorsal anastomose.

label: adult metathoracic dorsal branch
description: Posterior dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is a long and curved commissure that passes under the mesophragma and connects the left and right parenteric air sacs in the thorax. It passes above the alimentary canal.

label: adult prothoracic dorsal branch
description: Anterior dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is a short and straight commissure that connects the left and right parenteric air sacs in the thorax. It passes above the alimentary canal.

label: scutellar air sac
description: Lobe of the dorsal air sac underlying the scutellum.

label: metathoracic tibial preapical bristle
description: Longer and thicker bristle in the anterior compartment, on the dorsal distal region of the metathoracic tibia, near the joint with the first tarsal segment.

label: presumptive metathoracic tibial preapical bristle
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tibial preapical bristle.

label: metathoracic tibial sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some metathoracic tibia (FBbt:00004709).

label: sternopleural air sac
description: A ventrally located air sac of the adult mesothorax, lying above the base of the mesothoracic leg. It arises from the lateral trunk and extends into the base of the mesothoracic leg. A trachea that extends into the mediosternal region arises from the sternopleural air sac.

label: mediosternal trachea
description: Tracheal branch that arises from the adult sternopleural air sac and that tracheates the mediosternal region.

label: mesothoracic leg trachea
description: Tracheal branch that extends into the adult mesothoracic leg. It arises from the sternopleural air sac.

label: metathoracic air sac
description: Small diverticulum of the adult thoracic tracheal branches that arises just above the posterior thoracic spiracle.

label: dorsal margin photoreceptor cell R7
description: Any photoreceptor cell R7 (FBbt:00004225) that is part of some dorsal margin ommatidium (FBbt:02000000).

label: postnotal air sac
description: An air sac located deep in the thorax, under the scutal air sac and forming the posterior continuation of the lateroscutal air sac.

label: metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Any one of a group of 11 campaniform sensilla located in a cluster in the posterior proximal region of the metathoracic femur, close to the joint between the femur and the trochanter. They are arranged in 3 rows with 4, 4 and 3 sensilla each.

label: presumptive metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11.

label: metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: An isolated campaniform sensillum located proximally on the anterior edge of the metathoracic femur, close to the joint between the femur and the trochanter.

label: presumptive metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1.

label: prothoracic leg trachea
description: Tracheal branch that extends into the adult prothoracic leg. It arises from the propleural air sac.

label: adult spiracular branch 1
description: Tracheal branch of the mesothoracic segment (tracheal metamere 1) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle. It connects the propleural air sac to the anterior thoracic spiracle.

label: metathoracic tibial transverse bristle row
description: Any bristle located in the only transversely oriented row (TR) on the posterior side of the metathoracic tibia.

label: presumptive metathoracic tibial transverse bristle row
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tibial transverse bristle row.

label: postocular air sac
description: Tracheal air sac of the adult head, located dorsally and posterior to the eye. It corresponds to the enlargement of a lateral branch that extends from the dorsal branch of the cervical trachea.

label: pleural air sac
description: An air sac located deep in the thorax, between the notopleural and lateroscutal air sacs, with which it is continuous.

label: metathoracic tibial bract
description: Any bract (FBbt:00005180) that is part of some metathoracic tibia (FBbt:00004709).

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle transverse row
description: Any bracted bristle in one of the transverse bristle rows (TR) of the metathoracic tarsal segments. There are 11 TRs in the posterior region of the metatarsus, and 6 TRs in tarsal segment 3. These transverse rows replace the tarsal bristle longitudinal row 2.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle
description: A bristle of the tarsal segment of the adult metathoracic leg.

label: presumptive metathoracic tarsal bristle transverse row
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic tarsal bristle transverse row.

label: gastric caecum
description: Blind sac that branches from the anterior-most region of the embryonic/larva midgut (ventriculus). There are four of these per animal. Their cells have a similar morphology to those of the midgut epithelium.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 1
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is at a ventro-posterioventral position.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row
description: Any bristle in one of the 8 longitudinal bracted or bractless bristle rows in a metathoracic tarsal segment. Row 1 is at the ventro-posterioventral position, with numbering continuing through the posterior, dorsal, and anterior surfaces. Row 2 has been replaced by the transverse bristle rows.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 7
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is posterior to row 6, in a anterioventral position.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 6
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is anterior to row 5.5, in an anterior position.

label: adult epipharynx
description: Posterior wall of the labral channel, the anterior-most portion of the adult foregut.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 4
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is anterior to row 3, in a posteriodorsal-dorso position.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 3
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is dorsoposterior anterior to row 1, in a postero-posteriodorsal position.

label: labellar gland
description: Pyriform group of cells, consisting of about seven large epithelial cells. It surrounds an irregular lumen that opens medially, through a short small-celled duct, in close proximity to the tip of the labrum. A thin basement membrane surrounds the gland externally and a thin intima lines the lumen. There are two of these, one on each side of the labellum lobes.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 5.5
description: Longitudinal bractless bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is anterior to row 5, in an anteriodorsal position.

label: adult mouth
description: The opening of the adult alimentary canal in the tip of the labrum.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 5
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the metathoracic leg. It is anterior to row 4, in a dorsal position.

label: abdominal tergite marginal bristle
description: Microchaeta found on the posterior margin of a tergite of the abdominal segments.

label: adult abdominal sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some adult abdomen (FBbt:00003023).

label: abdominal sternite bristle
description: Microchaeta of a sternite of the abdominal segments.

label: metathoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 8
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is posterior to row 1, in a ventral position.

label: male terminalia sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some male terminalia (FBbt:00004835).

label: adult common salivary gland duct
description: A duct that connects the left and right adult salivary gland ducts to the salivary canal. It connects to the salivary ducts in the neck region and runs along posterior wall of the proboscis. At the base of the hypopharynx, the duct is dilated to form a small chamber, the salivary pump (FBbt:00003134), which connects to the salivary canal.

label: Malpighian tubule Type II cell primordium
gonopod thorn bristle
description: Thorn bristle of the female gonopod. There are 11-16 of these.

label: female terminalia sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some female terminalia (FBbt:00004830).

label: chemosensory sensory organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050907).

label: presumptive gonopod thorn bristle
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the gonopod thorn bristle.

label: gonopod sensillum trichodeum
description: Sensillum trichodeum of the female gonopod. There are three of these.

label: presumptive gonopod sensillum trichodeum
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the gonopod sensillum trichodeum.

label: adult salivary gland duct
description: A narrow epithelial tube (around 7um in diameter) that carries saliva from the secretory part of the adult salivary glands to the salivary gland common duct. It is lined with a chitinous intima, stiffened by annular, transverse ridges (taenidia). The epithelial cells are stretched thin with nuclei at wide intervals in a narrow band of cytoplasm.

label: excretory structure
description: Anatomical structure of the excretory system.

label: gonopod long bristle
description: Single long bristle of the female gonopod.

label: presumptive gonopod long bristle
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the gonopod long bristle.

label: hypandrial hair
description: Fine hair of the hypandrium process in the male genitalia. There is a group of these.

label: hypandrial bristle
description: Bristle of the hypandrium process in the male genitalia. There is one large and a group of three small bristles.

label: clasper long bristle
description: Single long bristle at the end of the clasper in the male genitalia.

label: clasper tooth
description: Thorn-like bristle of the clasper in the male genitalia. There are 25 of these arranged in a curved band.

label: adult rectal valve
description: Valve at the posterior end of the adult hindgut, anterior to the rectal sac. It corresponds to a slight thickening of the intestine, followed by a constriction where it joins the rectum.

label: adult rectal papilla
description: Paired papilla projecting from the side wall into the lumen of the rectal sac. Each papillae is a conical thick-walled invagination of the epithelium 100-150um high and 65-85um in diameter basally, containing a narrow central cavity occupied by a bundle of five trachea (Miller, 1950).

label: adult rectal sphincter
description: Sphincter located at the narrow posterior end of the rectum. The epithelium forms several longitudinal folds, with circular muscles acting a a sphincter, and dilator muscle fibers extending to the surrounding body wall.

label: adult anus
description: Posterior opening of the adult hindgut.

label: adult dorsal vessel
description: Dorsal vessel of the adult. It extends from the sixth abdominal segment to the dorsal anterior region of the brain (Curtis et al., 1999). The anterior portion, which is devoid of ostia, is the aorta, whilst the posterior (caudal) region, which has ostia, forms the heart proper.

label: ptilinal suture
description: Suture across the front of the head, in between the eyes and just dorsal to the base of the antennae. It is a remnant of the internalization of the ptilinum after eclosion.

label: presumptive ptilinum
description: Region of the medial eye-antennal disc that will develop into the ptilinum.

label: paraocciput
description: Ventral area of the occiput sclerite of the adult head.

label: adult hemocoel
description: Hemocoel of the adult. It is not divided into dorsal, perivisceral and ventral sinuses as in other insects. However, the hemocoel of each leg is divided into dorsal and ventral sinuses by a delicate membrane that extends across the leg and that bears the leg trachea.

label: hemocoel
description: General body cavity that surrounds all of the internal organs and is filled with hemolymph.

label: adult hemolymph
description: Hemolymph of the adult circulatory system.

label: hemolymph
description: The plasma, or liquid part of the circulatory system.

label: endocuticular specialization
description: Specialized structure that is found on the endocuticle.

label: adult heart chamber
description: Chamber of the adult heart. Between each chamber, one or two spongy cells project inwards from the wall on each side.

label: antennal foramen
description: Foramen of the adult head in which the antenna is articulated. There are two of these.

label: adult heart chamber 2
description: Second anterior-most chamber of the adult heart. It is subcylindrical and is located in abdominal segment 3.

label: adult heart chamber 3
description: Third anterior-most chamber of the adult heart. It is subcylindrical and occupies abdominal segment 4.

label: prefrons
description: Integument that covers the anterior head capsule ventral to the ptilinum.

label: adult ostium 2
description: Ostium of the second chamber of the adult heart.

label: adult ostium
description: An obliquely oriented, laterally located slit in the wall of the adult heart. There are 4 pairs of these, one per chamber.

label: adult ostium 3
description: Ostium of the third chamber of the adult heart.

label: adult ostium 4
description: Ostium of the fourth chamber of the adult heart.

label: adult heart chamber 4
description: Fourth and posterior-most chamber of the adult heart. It tapers posteriorly through segment 5 to the middle of segment 6. Here the slender posterior portion is abruptly expanded and the closed end is stretched between its points of attachment on the rectum and dorsal wall.

label: premandibular suture
description: Suture of the posterior adult head that is on the border between the postgena and the occiput.

label: presumptive premandibular suture
description: Region of the mediodorsal eye disc that will develop into the premandibular suture.

label: ostium
description: A small opening in the heart that allows hemolymph to enter.

label: adult ostium 1
description: Ostium of the first chamber of the adult heart.

label: ostiolar valve 1
description: The ostiolar valve of adult ostium 1.

label: occipital foramen
description: Foramen of the adult head with which the neck articulates.

label: mushroom body alpha' lobe slice 2
description: Largest, central-most shaft slice of the mushroom body alpha' lobe.

label: ostiolar valve 2
description: The ostiolar valve of adult ostium 2.

label: ostiolar valve 3
description: The ostiolar valve of adult ostium 3.

label: scutellar pulsatile organ
description: A small band of muscle fibers that spans the angle where the scutellum joins a ridge running down to the base of the wing. It functions in the pumping of hemolymph.

label: pulsatile organ
description: Small muscular organ that functions in pumping of the hemocoel.

label: tibial pulsatile organ
description: A pulsatile organ located distally in each tibia.

label: wing pulsatile organ
description: Pulsatile organ of the wing. There are 5 of these, all located in or near the wing hinge. They all beat independently of the main heartbeat and asynchronously with each other except for 3 and 4 which pulsate synchronously.

label: ostiolar valve 4
description: The ostiolar valve of adult ostium 4.

label: dorsal diaphragm
description: A free-edged fibrous mesh along each side of the heart, bearing the pericardial cells and reaching its greatest width in the fifth abdominal segment. Attached to it are 4 pairs of delicate an inconspicuous muscle fibers (the alary muscles ??). Along the first chamber, the dorsal diaphragm extends upwards toward the body wall and contains closely spaced longitudinal muscles that stretch from the ventral wall of the heart to the junction between thorax and abdomen.

label: terminal opening
description: Opening of the anterior region of the adult aorta, in the adult aortic funnel.

label: abdominal 6 lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000627) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 lateral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000626) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 ventral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000631) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 lateral transverse muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 4 (FBbt:00000630) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 lateral transverse muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 3 (FBbt:00000629) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 6 lateral transverse muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 2 (FBbt:00000628) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000590) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 acute muscle (FBbt:00000589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: hypodermal muscle of larval abdominal 7
description: Any hypodermal muscle of larval abdomen (FBbt:00000681) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 6 ventral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A2-7 ventral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000632) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: adult oenocyte
description: Large, acidophilic cell found in rows under the epidermis of each abdominal segment. Two dorsal rows run from the heart tube to the spiracle, close to the posterior boundary of the segment. A single, or sometimes split, transverse row is found under each sternite.

label: adult garland cell
description: Any garland cell (FBbt:00005059) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004).

label: pericardial cell
description: Cell which forms the outer layer of the dorsal vessel.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: alpha'/beta' anterior-posterior Kenyon cell
description: A subgroup of the mushroom body alpha'/beta' neurons that has dendrites in the main calyx and project axons to the anterior and posterior layers of the alpha'/beta' lobes. There are around 210 neurons in each hemisphere.

label: alpha'/beta' Kenyon cell
description: Mushroom body neuron that bifurcates at the anterior end of the pedunculus, projecting into the mushroom body alpha'-lobe and beta'-lobe. The alpha'/beta' neurons are the second born of the Kenyon cells, born during the mid-larval stage before the alpha and beta neurons, but after the gamma neurons. In the pedunculus, the alpha' and beta' neurons occupy the intermediate stratum between the gamma axons at the periphery and the alpha/beta neurons at the core. The alpha'/beta' neuron also arborizes in the calyx, forming post-synaptic terminals (Christiansen et al., 2011).

label: mushroom body beta'' lobe
description: A narrow division lying between the gamma and beta' lobes of the adult brain. Axons innervating the beta'' lobe have axons innervating the alpha' lobe front surface.

label: mushroom body alpha'' lobe
description: A subregion of the alpha' lobe occupied by the vertical lobe projecting branches of the neurons composing the mushroom body beta'' lobe of the adult brain.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal oblique muscle 5
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 5 (FBbt:00000613) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 4 (FBbt:00000612) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000619) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: mushroom body pedunculus-medial lobe and vertical lobe arborizing neuron 2
description: A GABAergic neuron whose cell body is located on the inferior neuropils in each adult brain hemisphere. The cell body fiber runs posteriorly and bifurcates laterally and medially. The lateral branch arborizes in the lateral-most spur area of the gamma lobe (slice 1) and the core of the pedunculus. Its axon projects bilaterally to the alpha and beta lobes and contralaterally to the core of the pedunculus and, to a lesser extent, to the crepine. In the alpha lobe slice 3, its terminals are enriched in the surface layer. There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

label: alpha/beta Kenyon cell
description: Mushroom body neuron that bifurcates at the anterior end of the pedunculus and projects into the alpha and beta lobes of the mushroom body. The alpha/beta neurons are the last born of the Kenyon cells, born during the pupal stage. In the pedunculus, the alpha/beta neurons occupy the core stratum with the gamma axons at the periphery and the alpha'/beta' neurons in the intermediate stratum (Awasaki et al., 2006). It also arborizes in the calyx, forming pre- and post-synaptic terminals (Christiansen et al., 2011).

label: abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 4
description: The fourth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 7. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 8 where it attaches to an intrasegmental apodeme.

label: mushroom body calyx-pedunculus arborizing neuron 1
description: A neuron whose cell body is located on the posteriorlateral protocerebrum, ventrolateral to the calyx of the adult brain. The cell body fiber projects to and arborizes with the pedunculus where it bifurcates, with one branch turning posteriorly to extensively arborize in the calyx with a few fibers extending into the lateral horn. The other branch projects anteriorly through the pedunculus, turns medially and runs below the medial lobe. The fiber then turns dorsally and bifurcates, forming terminals in the crepine in both hemispheres.

description: Any A1-7 longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000598) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 6
description: Any A2-7 ventral oblique muscle 6 (FBbt:00000622) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 ventral oblique muscle 5
description: The fifth dorsal-most ventral oblique muscle of larval abdominal segment 7. Its posterior end extends into abdominal segment 8 where it attaches to an intrasegmental apodeme.

description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 (FBbt:00000603) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3 (FBbt:00000604) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 4
description: Glutamatergic neuron whose cell body is located on the superior neuropils of each hemisphere, anterior to the pars intercerebralis of the adult brain. The cell body fiber is sent ventrally towards the medial lobe, crossing the midline. Dendritic arborizations are found in the anterior and posterior layers of beta' lobe slice 2, with the main axon projecting to the crepine and superior medial protocerebrum, with a minor axon extending to the ipsilateral side.

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 5
description: A neuron, which is part of a cluster of approximately 5 neurons per brain hemisphere, whose cell body is located on the inferior neuropils, anterior to the vertical lobe of the adult brain. The cell body fiber travels medially and arborizes in the inferior neuropils above the middle part of the medial lobe. The main fibers then intermingle with the MB-M4 neurons and enter the medial lobe through the same pathway as MB-M4.

label: mushroom body medial lobe arborizing neuron 7
description: A neuron, which is part of a cluster of approximately two neurons per brain hemisphere, whose cell body is found in the inferior neuropils, anterior to the medial lobe of the adult brain. The cell body fibers project mediodorsally and bifurcate in the inferior neuropils. One branch arborizes here and the other runs ventromedially in the anterior surface of the medial lobe and innervates the gamma lobe.

label: mushroom body vertical lobe arborizing neuron 1
description: A dopaminergic neuron of the PPL1 cluster whose cell body is located on the superior neuropils lateral to the calyx of each brain hemisphere of the adult brain. The cell body fiber projects anterior-medially and forms branches in the superior neuropils posterior to the vertical lobes. One of these branches projects to the opposite hemisphere and others project to the vertical lobe and form extensive arborizations in the middle segment of both the alpha and alpha' lobes (slice 2). There is one neuron of this type in each hemisphere.

description: The only dorsal oblique muscle in larval abdominal segment 8. It is much shorter and narrower than dorsal oblique muscles of larval segments A1-7. It inserts caudally into the epidermis, anterior to and above the posterior spiracle.

label: alpha'/beta' middle Kenyon cell
description: A subgroup of the mushroom body alpha'/beta' neurons that has dendrites in the main calyx and projects axons to the middle layer of the alpha' and beta' lobes. In the beta' lobe slice 2, their axons are located in the area between the bifurcating axons of the alpha'/beta' anterior-posterior Kenyon cell. In the alpha' lobe, their axons are medial to those of alpha'/beta' anterior-posterior Kenyon cell. There are around 140 neurons in each hemisphere.

label: ventral double row
description: Ventral-most row of the double row bristles of the adult wing composed of singly-innervated mechanosensory bristles and multiply-innervated chemosensory bristles.

label: chemosensory ventral double row bristle
description: Multiply innervated, recurved chemosensory bristle of the ventral double row with a conspicuous terminal pore.

label: mechanosensory ventral double row bristle

label: Rh5 photoreceptor of Bolwig organ
description: Cholinergic photoreceptor cell of the larval Bolwig's organ that expresses the blue-absorbing rhodopsin Rh5 (lambda[max] = 437nm; FBgn0014019). Fibers pass along the larval optic nerve and terminate medioventrally in the larval optic neuropil where they are surrounded by the projections of Rh6 photoreceptors of Bolwig organ. Same neurites bypass the larval optic neuropil and project to the adjacent ipsilateral central brain (Keene et al., 2011). Their projections in the larval optic neuropil have been shown to overlap with serotonergic arborizations (Rodriguez Moncalvo and Campos, 2005) and with the dendrites of pacemaker lateral neurons (LN's) (Keene et al., 2011; Mazzoni et al., 2005). There are about 4 Rh5 photoreceptors per Bolwig organ.

label: mechanosensory neuron of dorsal row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a dorsal row bristle of the cibarium in the adult pharynx.

label: mechanosensory neuron of ventral row bristle

label: dorsal triple row bristle
description: Multiply innervated, recurved bristle of the dorsal triple row involved in chemosensation. This bristle has a conspicuous terminal pore.

label: dorsal triple row
description: Dorsal-most row of the triple row. It is composed of multiply innervated, recurved chemosensory bristles, with females having approximately 23 and males approximately 22 (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

label: chemosensory neuron of dorsal triple row bristle
description: Chemosensory neuron innervating a dorsal triple row chemosensory bristle.
synonyms: dorsal triple row bristle chemosensory neuron

label: marginal nerve
description: The marginal nerve carries axons of bristle sensilla of the triple row and the double row plus the large twin sensilla of the margin and the giant sensillum of the radius (Palka et al., 1979).

label: mechanosensory neuron of dorsal triple row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a dorsal triple row chemosensory bristle.

label: ventral triple row bristle
description: Bristle of the ventral triple row.

label: ventral triple row
description: Ventral-most row of the triple row bristles composed of approximately 77-79 singly innervated, slender mechanosensory bristles interspersed with approximately 17-20 multiply innervated, recurved chemosensory bristles (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

label: imaginal tracheal precursor
description: Precursor cells of the adult tracheal system, found in the embryo or larva.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval digestive system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval digestive system.

label: embryonic proventriculus intermediate layer
description: Intermediate layer of the proventriculus of the embryo. It corresponds to the invaginated foregut with alveolar cells. It contains imaginal cells at the level of the intermediate layer at the anterior end of the proventriculus.

label: embryonic proventriculus inner layer
description: Inner layer of the proventriculus of the embryo. It corresponds to the invaginated esophagus.

label: embryonic epipharynx
description: Floor of the embryonic pharynx.

label: embryonic hypopharynx
description: Roof of the embryonic pharynx.

label: embryonic foregut sensory structure
description: Any internal compound sense organ (FBbt:00007236) that is part of some embryonic foregut (FBbt:00005606).

label: embryonic proventriculus outer layer
description: Outer layer of the proventriculus of the embryo. It corresponds to the visceral mesoderm, containing cells that secrete the peritrophic membrane.

label: embryonic esophagus
description: Esophagus of the embryo. It invaginates to form part of the proventriculus.

label: midgut primordium
description: Any primordium that is a precursor of all or some part of the larval or adult midgut.

label: embryonic midgut chamber
description: Chamber of the developing midgut that is a transient subdivision along its length resulting from circumferential constrictions of the embryonic midgut between stages 15 and mid-stage 16.

label: embryonic hindgut
description: Posterior region of the embryonic gut, posterior to the embryonic midgut. It is divided into 3 domains: small and large intestine and rectum. Border cells separate these three regions.

label: supraalar bristle
description: A large, macrochaeta of the scutum located immediately posterior to the intrascutal suture (FBbt:00004602). There are two pairs of these, anterior and posterior.

label: dorsocentral bristle
description: A large, dorso-centrally located macrochaeta of the scutum. There are two pairs of these, anterior and posterior.

label: embryonic Malpighian tubule segment
description: Malpighian tubule segment of the embryo.

label: dorsocentral bristle precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell that develops into a dorsocentral bristle.

label: embryonic large intestine
description: Middle and long domain of the embryonic hindgut, posterior to the small intestine.

label: notopleural bristle
description: A laterally located macrochaeta of the prescutum. There are two pairs of these per prescutum, anterior and posterior.

label: notopleural bristle precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell that develops into a notopleural bristle.

label: embryonic small intestine
description: Anterior and small domain of the embryonic hindgut, posterior to the midgut.

label: supraalar bristle precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell that develops into a supraalar bristle.

label: embryonic rectum
description: Posterior domain of the embryonic hindgut, posterior to the large intestine.

label: postalar bristle
description: The most posterior macrochaeta of the scutum, located laterally in two pairs, anterior and posterior.

label: postalar bristle precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell that develops into a postalar bristle.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval muscle system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval muscle system.

label: anterior sternopleural bristle
description: The most anterior of the sternopleural bristles of the adult mesothoracic preepisternum, located at the same dorso/ventral level as the middle and posterior bristles.

label: sternopleural bristle
description: Macrochaeta of the adult mesothoracic preepisternum. There are four of these.

label: posterior sternopleural bristle
description: The most posterior of the sternopleural bristles of the adult mesothoracic preepisternum, located at the same dorso/ventral level as the anterior and middle bristles.

label: embryonic somatic muscle
description: Somatic muscle of the embryo.

label: middle sternopleural bristle
description: The middle of the sternopleural bristles of the adult mesothoracic preepisternum, located at the same dorso/ventral level as the anterior and posterior bristles.

label: embryonic Malpighian tubule tip cell
description: Tip cell of the embryonic Malpighian tubule.

label: embryonic specialised Malpighian tubule cell
description: Specialised cell of the embryonic Malpighian tubules.

label: scutellar bristle
description: A macrochaeta of the scutellum. Each scutellum bares two pairs of these, located close to the lateroposterior margin of the scutellum, with one pair being anterior to the other.

label: scutellar bristle precursor cell
description: A sensory mother cell that develops into a scutellar bristle.

label: embryonic Malpighian tubule Type II cell
description: Type II cell of the embryonic Malpighian tubules. These cells show a cuboidal-shaped morphology.

label: embryonic Malpighian tubule Type I cell
description: Type I cell of the embryonic Malpighian tubules.

label: ventral sternopleural bristle
description: The most ventral of the sternopleural bristles of the adult mesothoracic preepisternum.

label: katepisternal bristle
description: Bristle of the mesothoracic episternum or katepisternum. On the dorsal aspect there are 5 to 8 bristles, with 1 to 3 of them being very large (Bb-). In the ventral aspect there is an isolated bristle (I) and in the anterior region there are 2 to 4 yellow bristles (YB).

label: embryonic hypodermal muscle
description: Hypodermal muscle of the embryo.

label: acrostichal bristle
description: Microchaeta of the scutum of the adult dorsal mesothorax in the acrostichal region. They are located on either side of the midline and medially to the dorsocentral region. These bristles are arranged roughly in anterior/posterior rows, with a few rows present.

label: triple row
description: Three rows of sensilla proximally located on the anterior wing margin. The boundary between the triple row and the double row is a short distance distal of the point where the second longitudinal vein merges with the wing margin.

label: array of sensilla rows
description: Multiple, parallel rows if sensilla.

label: dorsal row
description: The dorsal row consists of all of the wing margin bristles on the dorsal side of the wing: the medial and dorsal components of the triple row and the dorsal component of the double row.

label: double row
description: Two rows of sensilla located towards the distal end of the anterior wing margin. The boundary between the triple row and the double row is a short distance distal of the point where the second longitudinal vein merges with the wing margin.

label: notal microchaeta
description: A short sensory bristle of the notum (mesothoracic tergum ; FBbt:00004580). There are around 200 of these, all with a bristle pointing posterior to their socket. They are arranged into approximately parallel rows running anterior to posterior.

label: embryonic visceral muscle
description: Visceral muscle of the embryo.

label: anterior notal wing process sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some anterior notal wing process (FBbt:00004585).

label: embryonic esophageal muscle
description: Muscle of the embryonic esophagus.

label: chordotonal organ of wing
description: Any chordotonal organ (FBbt:00005215) that is part of some wing (FBbt:00004729).

label: non-functional pupal spiracle 3
description: Any non-functional pupal spiracle (FBbt:00002998) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028) and that connected to some pupal spiracular branch 3 (FBbt:00002978).

label: non-functional pupal spiracle
description: A non-functional spiracle of the pupa. There are 4 of these, connected to small branches arising from transverse connectives 2-5.

label: pupal spiracular branch 3
description: Non-functional branch connecting pupal transverse connective 2 to non-functional pupal spiracle 3.

label: dorsal double row
description: The dorsal component of the double row, consisting of two sensillum types: slender, singly-innervated mechanosensory bristles and multiply-innervated, recurved bristles that are involved in chemosensation.

label: embryonic central brain glial cell
description: Glial cell of the embryonic central brain.

label: medial triple row
description: Medial-most sensilla row of the triple row. It is composed of approximately 80 (for males) and 86 (females) stout, singly innervated mechanosensory bristles (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

label: non-functional pupal spiracle 4
description: Any non-functional pupal spiracle (FBbt:00002998) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029) and that connected to some pupal spiracular branch 4 (FBbt:00002979).

label: pupal spiracular branch 4
description: Non-functional branch connecting pupal transverse connective 3 to non-functional pupal spiracle 4.

label: twin sensillum of margin 1
description: One of two large bristle sensilla at the most distal point of the wing margin of the distal costa. It is innervated by the first born of the twin sensilla neurons.

label: ventral row
description: Single row of sensilla anteriorly located on the ventral aspect of the wing margin. It is composed of approximately 77-79 (for males/females) singly innervated, stout mechanosensory bristles interspersed with approximately 17-20 recurved, multiply innervated chemosensory bristles (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

label: adult tagma
description: Any tagma (FBbt:00000002) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004).

label: adult ocular segment
description: Any ocular segment (FBbt:00000005) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: adult procephalic segment
description: Any procephalic segment (FBbt:00000007) that is part of some adult head (FBbt:00003007).

label: twin sensillum of margin 2
description: One of two large bristle sensilla at the most distal point of the wing margin of the distal costa. It is innervated by the second born of the twin sensilla neurons (Murray et al., 1984).

label: adult head segment
description: Segment of the adult head.

label: non-functional pupal spiracle 5
description: Any non-functional pupal spiracle (FBbt:00002998) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030) and that connected to some pupal spiracular branch 5 (FBbt:00002980).

label: pupal spiracular branch 5
description: Non-functional branch connecting pupal transverse connective 4 to non-functional pupal spiracle 5.

label: embryonic central brain neuron
description: Neuron of the embryonic central brain.

label: air bubble
description: Bubble of gas that appears in the center of the prepupa. It then translocates to the posterior of the animal. Rhythmic contractions of the abdominal muscles, accompanied by a swaying motion of the prepupa, moves the gas bubble along the sides of the animal towards the anterior end, driving larval/pupal apolysis (the separation of cuticle from the epidermis) and creating a space at the anterior of the puparium for subsequent adult head eversion.

label: pupal tracheal system
description: Tracheal system of the pupa.

label: embryonic central brain surface glia
description: Surface glial cell of the embryonic central brain.

label: mechanosensory ventral triple row bristle
description: Slender, singly innervated mechanosensory bristle of the ventral triple row.

label: embryonic pars intercerebralis
description: Pars intercerebralis of the late embryo that develops from the pars intercerebralis primordium. From stage 15, the primordia of both hemispheres merge at the midline.

label: chemosensory ventral triple row bristle
description: Multiply innervated, recurved taste bristle of the ventral triple row and the ventral row. This bristle also shows a conspicuous terminal pore.

label: denticle row
description: Individual row of denticles in a denticle belt.

label: denticle belt
description: Multiple rows of denticles located on the ventral surface of the larva. The orientation of the denticles within the belt changes from segment to segment.

label: larval LNd neuron
description: Larval neuron of the period-expressing LNd cluster, whose soma is located in the dorsal lateral brain.

label: adult period glial cell
description: Period (FBgn0003068) expressing glial cell.

label: wing hair
description: The posteriorly oriented trichome of a cell of the wing blade. Each cell makes one of these trichomes at its posterior vertex.

label: sensillum campaniformium of proximal dorsal radius
description: Sensillum campaniformium of the proximal dorsal radius of the adult wing.

label: sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius
description: Sensillum campaniformium found on the dorsal radius of the adult wing.

label: prothoracic leg disc-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from cells from the larval prothoracic leg imaginal disc.

label: trichome of the posterior wing margin
description: Any wing hair (FBbt:00004340) that is part of some posterior wing margin (FBbt:00027001).

label: posterior wing margin
description: Wing margin of the posterior compartment of the wing.

label: sensillum campaniformium of ventral radius Sc4vm
description: Most proximal sensillum campaniformium of the proximal ventral radius of the adult wing. There are four or five elliptical sensilla with low profile and with a socket (type 6), often arranged in a diamond pattern. Each sensilla is between 2.5-3.5 micrometers in length.

label: sensillum campaniformium of proximal ventral radius
description: Sensillum campaniformium of the proximal ventral radius of the adult wing.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval circulatory system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval circulatory system.

label: sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc25
description: Second most proximal sensillum campaniformium of the proximal dorsal radius of the adult wing. It consists of two distinct fields. The first has seven elliptical sensilla with low profile and with a socket (type 6), distributed in a round patch, with each sensilla between 2.5-3.0 micrometers in length (d.Rad.B). The second has around 17 circular sensilla, with low profile and without socket (type 4), with each sensilla between 2.5-3.5 micrometers in diameter (d.Rad.C).

label: sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc4d
description: Most proximal sensillum campaniformium of the proximal dorsal radius of the adult wing. It consists of four circular sensilla with high profile and without socket (type 2), arranged in a row and increasing in diameter distally, between 3.5-4.5 micrometers in diameter.

label: embryonic pericardial cell
description: Pericardial cell of the embryo.

label: sensillum campaniformium of dorsal radius Sc12
description: Third most proximal sensillum campaniformium of the medial dorsal radius of the adult wing. It consists of two distinct fields. The first has four circular sensilla with high profile and with a socket (type 1), distributed on the anterior face of the medial radius, with each sensilla around 4.5 micrometers in diameter (d.Rad.D). The second has eight circular sensilla, with low profile and with socket (type 3), with each sensilla between 5.0-5.5 micrometers in diameter (d.Rad.E).

label: sensillum campaniformium of ventral radius Sc5
description: Sensillum campaniformium on the border of the medial ventral radius of the adult wing. There are five circular sensilla with low profile and with a socket (type 3), arranged linearly along the medial radius. Each sensilla is around 4.5 micrometers in diameter.

label: aorta primordium
description: The region of the dorsal vessel primordium that gives rise to the embryonic/larval aorta.

label: heart primordium
description: The region of the dorsal vessel primordium that gives rise to the embryonic/larval heart.

label: sensillum campaniformium of ventral radius Sc3
description: Sensillum campaniformium on the border of the proximal and medial ventral radius of the adult wing. There are three circular sensilla with high profile and with a socket (type 1), with the cuticle of the domes often peaked. Each sensilla is between 2.5-3.5 micrometers in diameter.

label: mesothoracic leg sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some mesothoracic leg (FBbt:00004685).

label: mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some mesothoracic coxa (FBbt:00004686).

label: chordotonal organ of tegula
description: Any chordotonal organ (FBbt:00005215) that is part of some tegula (FBbt:00004730).

label: peripheral tegula sensillum campaniformium
description: Sensillum campaniformium found on the anterior medial surface of the tegula of the adult wing. There are two large elliptical sensilla with high profile and with a socket (type 5), arranged orthogonally to the main tegula sensillum campaniformium, with their long axis parallel to the proximo-distal axis of the wing. Each sensilla is around 5 micrometers in diameter.
synonyms: Teg. sensilla peripheral to main field

label: adult dorsal branch
description: Adult trachea that branches dorsally from the dorsal trunk. It tracheates the dorsal epidermis and dorsal vessel. Each dorsal branch connects the left and right dorsal trunks of the same tracheal metamere via the dorsal anastomosis. In the thorax, the dorsal branches connect the parenteric air sacs, which correspond to the enlarged dorsal trunks.

label: adult transverse connective
description: Transverse tracheal branch of the adult. It connects the lateral trunk and the dorsal trunk at seven different locations. At the level of the second pair of spiracles, these connectives are much shorter and stouter than the six abdominal connectives.

label: extra LNd neuron
description: LNd neuron of the adult brain characterized by having a slightly larger nucleus and cytoplasmic area compared to the other LNd neurons.

label: LNd neuron
description: Lateral period-expressing neuron (LN) of the adult brain whose cell body is located in the dorsal-most cluster of LNs. These neurons project axons to the dorsal protocerebrum and terminate predominantly in the neuropil region close to the pars intercerebralis. These projections overlap with those of the DN neurons and many project contralaterally through the dorsal fusion commissure. Some dendrites from these neurons follow a complicated, looping path from the rest and project to the accessory medulla.

label: pupal Pdf neuron
description: Pdf expressing neuron that is part of the pupa.

label: embryonic hemolymph
description: Hemolymph of the embryo.

label: mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Any one of a group of 8 trichoid sensilla located proximally and medially in two rows near the joint between the mesothoracic coxa and the thorax.

label: presumptive mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St8.

label: pupal s-LNv neuron
description: Larval neuron of the period-expressing LNv cluster, with a small cell body and generally located more dorsally than the l-LNv neurons. There are 5 cells present in each cluster, all except one of which express Pdf (FBgn0023178).

label: mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Any one of the row of 4 sensillum trichoideum, on the hindside of the mesothoracic coxa.

label: presumptive mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic coxal sensillum trichodeum St4.

label: pupal LN period neuron
description: Laterally located period (FBgn0003068) expressing neuron of the pupal brain.

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some mesothoracic trochanter (FBbt:00004688).

label: larval Pdf neuron close to calyx
description: Larval Pdf (FBgn0023178) expressing neuron whose cell body lies in a cluster within the dorsal cortex. Pdf expression begins late in L1. Its process project into the median ventral brain dorsolateral to the esophagus. There are two to four of these neurons per cluster.

label: mesothoracic coxal bristle on hairy island
description: A relatively long bristle located on a small island of hairs (trichomes) in an otherwise bare region of cuticle on the ventral side of the mesothoracic coxa, adjacent to its joint with the trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic coxal bristle on hairy island
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic coxal bristle on hairy island.

label: pupal pacemaker neuron
description: Pacemaker neuron that is part of the pupa.

label: adult transverse connective 1
description: Most anterior transverse connective of the adult trachea. It connects the lateral and dorsal trunk at the level of the posterior thoracic spiracles.

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some mesothoracic trochanter (FBbt:00004688).

label: larval Pdf neuron
description: Larval neuron that expresses Pdf (FBgn0023178).

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13
description: Any one of a cluster of ~11-13 campaniform sensilla located posteriorly and distally on the mesothoracic trochanter - near to its joint with the femur.

label: adult transverse connective 2
description: Any adult transverse connective (FBbt:00003041) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00003025).

label: larval s-LNv neuron
description: Larval neuron of the period-expressing LNv cluster, with a small cell body and generally located more dorsally than the l-LNv neurons and that innervates the larval optic neuropil. There are 5 cells present in each cluster, all except one of which express Pdf (FBgn0023178). The four Pdf positive s-LNv neurons project into a distinct domain of the dorsal protocerebrum (Keene et al., 2011).

label: adult transverse connective 3
description: Any adult transverse connective (FBbt:00003041) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00003026).

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Any one of a row of 5-6 trichoid sensilla located proximally and laterally on the mesothoracic coxa.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St5.

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: A single, isolated sensillum trichodeum located medially and distally on the mesothoracic trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum St1.

label: adult transverse connective 4
description: Any adult transverse connective (FBbt:00003041) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00003027).

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-
description: Any one of 8 laterally located mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13. These are located in naked cuticle.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc-8.

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Any one of 5 medially located prothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc13. These are located in hairy cuticle.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc+5.

label: adult spiracular branch
description: Tracheal branch of the adult that connects the spiracle to the lateral trunk. There are nine pairs of spiracular branches, two in the thorax and seven in the abdomen.

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Any one of a row of 3 campaniform sensilla located laterally distally on the mesothoracic trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter sensillum campaniformium Sc3.

label: ventral cibarial sense organ neuron of distal sensillum
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the distal sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are four of these per sensillum.

label: ventral cibarial sense organ neuron
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx.

label: distal sensillum of ventral cibarial sense organ
description: Distal-most sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. It is innervated by four gustatory receptor neurons (Gendre et al., 2003).

label: adult transverse connective 5
description: Any adult transverse connective (FBbt:00003041) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00003028).

label: mesothoracic trochanter edge bristle
description: A distinctive, posterior pointing bristle located on the posterior edge of the medial side of the mesothoracic trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter edge bristle
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter edge bristle.

label: mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Any one of ~10-14 trichoid sensilla located medially in two adjacent clusters of ~5-7 each (GSt1 and GSt2) on the condyle of the joint between the mesothoracic coxa and the trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic trochanter sensillum trichodeum 2GSt.

label: adult transverse connective 6
description: Any adult transverse connective (FBbt:00003041) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00003029).

label: adult transverse connective 7
description: Any adult transverse connective (FBbt:00003041) that is part of some adult abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00003030).

label: mesothoracic femoral bract
description: Any bract (FBbt:00005180) that is part of some mesothoracic femur (FBbt:00004689).

label: array of rows
description: Multiple parallel rows.

label: mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: An isolated campaniform sensillum located proximally on the anterior edge of the mesothoracic femur, close to the joint between the femur and the trochanter.

label: mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium
description: Any sensillum campaniformium (FBbt:00005183) that is part of some mesothoracic femur (FBbt:00004689).

label: presumptive mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc1.

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch
description: Dorsal tracheal branch of the adult abdominal segments that connects the left and right dorsal trunks. There are six abdominal dorsal branches, in segments 1 to 6.

label: proximal sensillum of ventral cibarial sense organ
description: Most proximal sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. It is innervated by two gustatory receptor neurons (Gendre et al., 2003).

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch 3
description: First abdominal dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is the third most anterior dorsal branch.

label: mesothoracic tibial bract
description: Bract of the bristle of the distal region of the mesothoracic tibia.
