label: mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Any one of a group of 11 campaniform sensilla located in a cluster in the posterior proximal region of the mesothoracic femur, close to the joint between the femur and the trochanter. They are arranged in 3 rows with 4, 4 and 3 sensilla each.

label: presumptive mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic femoral sensillum campaniformium Sc11.

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch 4
description: Second abdominal dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is the fourth most anterior dorsal branch.

label: middle sensillum of ventral cibarial sense organ
description: Middle-most sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. It is innervated by 2 gustatory receptor neurons (Gendre et al., 2003).

label: mesothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1
description: Large chordotonal organ of the adult mesothoracic femur. It is located on the ventrolateral side and has around 32 well-aligned scolopidia. Its distal tip terminates at the distal epicuticular surface of the tip of the femur.

label: mesothoracic femoral chordotonal organ
description: Chordotonal organ of the adult mesothoracic femur. There are three chordotonal organs, located in the ventral chamber near the longitudinal septum. There is one large group, on the ventrolateral side, and two smaller ones in the center of the femur.

label: ventral cibarial sense organ neuron of middle sensillum
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the middle sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are two of these per sensillum.

label: mesothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 3
description: One of the small chordotonal organ of the adult mesothoracic femur. It is located in the center of the femur and has between 25-28 scolopidia. Distally, the scolopidia are more scattered than the mesothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1, with a majority of them connected to the femoral muscle membrane.

label: anterior wing margin
description: Wing margin of the anterior compartment of the wing.

label: mesothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 2
description: One of the small chordotonal organ of the adult mesothoracic femur. It is located in the center of the femur and has around 14 scolopidia. Distally, the scolopidia are more scattered than the mesothoracic femoral chordotonal organ 1, with a majority of them connected to the femoral muscle membrane.

label: mechanosensory neuron of medial triple row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a medial triple row bristle.
synonyms: medial triple row bristle mechanosensory neuron

label: medial triple row bristle
description: Stout, singly innervated bristle of the medial triple row. This bristle is mechanosensory.

label: chemosensory dorsal double row bristle
description: Multiply innervated, recurved bristle of the dorsal double row involved in chemosensation. This bristle also shows a conspicuous terminal pore.

label: dorsal double row bristle
description: Bristle that is part of the dorsal double row.

label: mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle
description: Slender, singly-innervated mechanosensory bristle of the dorsal double row.

label: chemosensory neuron of dorsal double row bristle
description: Chemosensory neuron that is part of a bristle of the dorsal double row.

label: mechanosensory neuron of chemosensory dorsal double row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates a chemosensory dorsal double row bristle.

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch 5
description: Third abdominal dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is the fifth most anterior dorsal branch.

label: mesothoracic tibial spur bristle
description: Short, thick and peg-shaped bracted bristle that surrounds the mesothoracic tibial apical bristle. There are 4 or 5 of these.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tibial spur bristle
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tibial spur bristle.

label: mechanosensory neuron of mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates a mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle.
synonyms: neuron of mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch 6
description: Fourth abdominal dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is the sixth most anterior dorsal branch.

label: mechanosensory neuron of chemosensory ventral double row bristle
description: Neuron involved in mechanosensation that is a part of the ventral double row chemosensory bristles.

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch 7
description: Fifth abdominal dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is the seventh most anterior dorsal branch.

label: mechanosensory neuron of chemosensory ventral triple row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a chemosensory ventral triple row bristle.

label: mesothoracic tibial sensillum trichodeum
description: Any sensillum trichodeum (FBbt:00005184) that is part of some mesothoracic tibia (FBbt:00004687).

label: pupal DN1 period neuron
description: Neuron of the DN1 cluster, that is located dorsal to the DN2 cluster at 70% pupal development. There are around 7 neurons in this cluster.

label: pupal DN period neuron
description: A Per (FBgn0003068) expressing neuron that is located in a dorsoanterior cluster in the pupal brain.

label: adult ganglionic branch 1
description: Tracheal branch of the adult thorax that branches from the propleural air sac. It connects at the midline with the branch of the opposite side via the ventral anastomosis 1.

label: adult ganglionic branch
description: Tracheal branch of the adult thorax that branches from the expanded lateral trunk. It connects at the midline with the branch of the opposite side via a ventral anastomosis. There are three of these branches that branch from the prothoracic leg trachea, propleural and hypopleural air sacs.

label: adult ventral anastomosis 1
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right propleural air sacs.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 2
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is posterior to row 1, in a posterioventral position.

label: pupal DN2 period neuron
description: Neuron of the DN2 cluster, that is located ventral to the DN2 cluster at 70% pupal development. There are between 1-2 neurons in this cluster.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 1
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is at a ventro-posterioventral position.

label: adult ganglionic branch 2
description: Tracheal branch of the adult thorax that branches from the hypopleural air sac. It connects at the midline with the branch of the opposite side via the ventral anastomosis 2.

label: adult ventral anastomosis 2
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right hypopleural air sacs. It is dilated and saccular medially.

label: pupal DN3 period neuron
description: Neuron of the DN3 cluster, that is located lateral to the DN1 and DN2 clusters at 70% pupal development. There are around 16 neurons in this cluster.

label: adult ventral anastomosis
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right ganglionic branches of the adult tracheal system. There are 3 of these anastomoses in the thorax.

label: tracheal node
description: Part of the tracheal system where 2 tracheal metameres are connected by a tracheal fusion. Tracheal nodes have a distinctive cuticular lining and are populated by tracheal node cells.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 3
description: Longitudinal bracted bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 2.5, in a postero-posteriodorsal position.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 2.5
description: Longitudinal bractless bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is posterior to row 2, in a posterior position.

label: adult ventral anastomosis 0
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right prothoracic leg trachea.

label: adult ganglionic branch 0
description: Tracheal branch of the adult thorax that branches from the prothoracic leg trachea. It connects at the midline with the branch of the opposite side via the ventral anastomosis 0.

label: adult abdominal dorsal branch 8
description: Sixth abdominal dorsal branch of the adult trachea. It is the eighth most anterior dorsal branch.

label: mesothoracic tibial apical bristle
description: Longer and thicker bristle without bracts in the anterior compartment, on the ventral distal region of the mesothoracic tibia, near the joint with the first tarsal segment. It is part of the longitudinal bristle row 8 and it is surrounded by 4 or 5 spur bristles.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tibial apical bristle
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tibial apical bristle.

label: mesothoracic tibial preapical bristle
description: Longer and thicker bristle without bracts in the anterior compartment, on the dorsal distal region of the mesothoracic tibia, near the joint with the first tarsal segment. It is part of the longitudinal bristle row 5.

label: presumptive mesothoracic tibial preapical bristle
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tibial preapical bristle.

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle
description: Any microchaeta (FBbt:00005182) that is part of some mesothoracic tarsal segment (FBbt:00004690).

label: pupal Pdf negative s-LNv neuron
description: Pupal s-LNv neuron that does not express Pdf (FBgn0023178) (Kaneko et al., 1997). There is only one of these per ventral cluster of LN period neurons.

label: small larval Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere
description: Larval Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a smaller cell body than the larger Pdf neurons that are located more ventral and anteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label: large larval Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere
description: Larval Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a larger cell body than the larger Pdf neurons that are located more posteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label: small adult Pdf neuron of abdominal segment
description: Adult Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a smaller cell body than the larger Pdf neurons that are located more ventral and anteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label: large adult Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere
description: Adult Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a larger cell body than the larger Pdf neurons that are located more posteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label: mesothoracic tarsal bristle longitudinal row 3.5
description: Longitudinal bractless bristle row of the adult tarsi of the mesothoracic leg. It is anterior to row 3, in a posteriodorsal position.

label: visceral branch
description: Adult trachea that branches mainly from the lateral trunks and from the transverse connectives. It tracheates the viscera. One visceral trachea arises between spiracles 2 and 3, one or two between spiracles 3 and 4, one between spiracles 4 and 5, two between spiracles 6 and 7, 0-2 from the fourth transverse connective and one each from the fifth, sixth and seventh transverse connective. Smaller branches arise from the dorsal trunks.

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 3
description: Tracheal branch of the first abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 3) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: adult abdominal spiracular branch 4
description: Tracheal branch of the second abdominal segment (tracheal metamere 4) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: larval Pdf negative s-LNv neuron
description: Larval s-LNv neuron that does not express Pdf (FBgn0023178). It innervates the larval optic neuropil significantly and projects to a broader domain than the four Pdf positive s-LNv neurons (Keene et al., 2011). There is only one of these per ventral cluster of LN period neurons.

label: adult spiracular branch 2
description: Tracheal branch of the metathoracic segment (tracheal metamere 2) that connects the lateral trunk to the spiracle.

label: E-T neuron
description: Neuron located near to the neuron innervating the twin sensillum of margin 1 and 2. It does not possess a typical dendrite whose conspicuous distal tip can be seen near the surface of the epithelium (Murray et al., 1984).

label: chemosensory sensillum of the female genitalia
description: Short, blunt-tipped thorn bristle or spine bristle located on the adult vaginal plate. There are around 10 bilateral pairs of thorn bristles and around 3 bilateral pairs of spine bristles.

label: abdominal 4 ventral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000602) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral longitudinal muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle (FBbt:00000601) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 lateral longitudinal muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral longitudinal muscle 1 (FBbt:00000600) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral longitudinal muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 4 (FBbt:00000605) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral longitudinal muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 3 (FBbt:00000604) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral longitudinal muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral longitudinal muscle 2 (FBbt:00000603) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: E-2 neuron
description: Neuron located near to the campaniform sensillum L3-2 of wing vein L3 neuron, but does not possess a typical dendrite whose conspicuous distal tip can be seen near the surface of the epithelium (Murray et al., 1984).

label: L3 nerve
description: Nerve bundle running through wing vein L3.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 dorsal transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000625) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 transverse muscle (FBbt:00000623) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: E-1 neuron
description: Neuron associated with the anterior crossvein campaniform sensillum neuron, but does not possess a typical dendrite whose conspicuous distal tip can be seen near the surface of the epithelium (Murray et al., 1984).

label: dorsal superficial trachea 6
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: campaniform sensillum dorsal humeral crossvein neuron
description: Neuron innervating the dorsal humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum.
synonyms: dorsal humeral crossvein sensillum campaniformium neuron

label: costal nerve
description: Nerve composed of axons collected from the marginal sensilla of the distal, medial and proximal costa, as well as the tegula.

label: campaniform sensillum of dorsal humeral crossvein
description: Humeral crossvein campaniform sensilla located on the dorsal side of the wing. It is situated close to the ventral humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum separated by the intermediate portion of the costal nerve (Murray et al., 1984). It is circular with a high profile and with a socket which is prominent on one side but becomes indistinct on the other. The sensilla is around 8 micrometers in diameter.

label: dorsal superficial trachea 7
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: wing nerve
description: A nerve that carries sensory fibers from the sense organs of the wing, eventually joining the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (FBbt:00004060 ; Power, 1948).

label: dorsal superficial trachea 8
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: campaniform sensillum ventral humeral crossvein neuron
description: Neuron innervating the ventral humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum.
synonyms: ventral humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum neuron

label: campaniform sensillum of ventral humeral crossvein
description: Humeral crossvein campaniform sensilla located on the ventral side of the wing. It is situated close to the dorsal humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum separated by the intermediate portion of the costal nerve (Murray et al., 1984). It is a large circular sensilla which bears a socket that is tightly fused to the dome and diminishes on one side. The sensilla is around 6.5 micrometers in diameter.

label: dorsal superficial trachea 9
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034).

label: campaniform sensillum L3-v of wing vein L3 neuron
description: Neuron innervating the ventral sensillum of wing vein L3.
synonyms: ventral sensillum of L3-v of wing vein L3 neuron

label: campaniform sensillum L3-1 of wing vein L3 neuron
description: Neuron innervating the L3-1 campaniform sensillum of wing vein L3.
synonyms: sensillum campaniformium L3-1 of wing vein L3 neuron

label: campaniform sensillum L3-1 of wing vein L3
description: Most proximal of the three dorsal campaniform sensilla of wing vein L3. It is a large circular sensilla, with a high profile and a distinct discontinuity between the dome and socket.

label: campaniform sensillum L3-2 of wing vein L3 neuron
description: Neuron innervating the second, medially located campaniform sensillum of wing vein L3.
synonyms: sensillum campaniformium L3-2 of wing vein L3 neuron

label: campaniform sensillum L3-2 of wing vein L3
description: Medial of the three dorsal campaniform sensilla of wing vein L3. It is a large circular sensilla, with a high profile and a distinct discontinuity between the dome and socket.

label: dorsal superficial trachea 4
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: campaniform sensillum L3-3 of wing vein L3 neuron
description: Neuron innervating the campaniform sensillum L3-3 of wing vein L3.
synonyms: sensillum campaniformium L3-3 of wing vein L3 neuron

label: campaniform sensillum L3-3 of wing vein L3
description: Distal most of the three dorsal campaniform sensilla of wing vein L3. It is a large circular sensilla, with a high profile and a distinct discontinuity between the dome and socket.

label: dorsal superficial trachea 5
description: Any dorsal superficial trachea (FBbt:00003083) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: campaniform sensillum anterior crossvein neuron
description: Neuron associated with the wing anterior crossvein sensillum (Murray et al., 1984).
synonyms: sensillum campaniformium of anterior crossvein neuron

label: campaniform sensillum of anterior crossvein
description: Campaniform sensilla associated with the anterior cross vein and wing vein L3. It is a large circular sensilla, with a high profile and a distinct discontinuity between the dome and socket.

label: abdominal 4 lateral transverse muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 3 (FBbt:00000629) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 lateral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000626) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 lateral transverse muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 2 (FBbt:00000628) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 lateral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000627) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral transverse muscle 1
description: Any A2-7 ventral transverse muscle 1 (FBbt:00000632) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 ventral transverse muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral transverse muscle (FBbt:00000631) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 4 lateral transverse muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 lateral transverse muscle 4 (FBbt:00000630) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: mechanosensory neuron of ventral double row bristle
description: Neuron involved in mechanosensation innervating a mechanosensory ventral double row bristle.
synonyms: mechanosensory ventral double row bristle neuron

label: synaptic neuropil
description: The part of the neuropil consisting largely of synapsing neuron projections.

label: adult wing branch
description: Tracheal branch in the adult thorax that tracheates the wing. It arises from a small air sac.

label: abdominal 5 dorsal acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle (FBbt:00000590) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 acute muscle (FBbt:00000589) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: adult haltere branch
description: Tracheal branch in the adult thorax that tracheates the haltere.

label: adult leg trachea
description: Tracheal branch that tracheates the adult leg and arises from the thoracic air sacs. There are three distinct leg trachea, each extending into one of the legs.

label: chemosensory neuron of ventral triple row bristle
description: Chemosensory neuron innervating a ventral triple row chemosensory bristle.
synonyms: ventral triple row bristle chemosensory neuron

label: maxillary palpus trachea
description: Trachea of the adult head that corresponds to a branch of the labial trachea and tracheates the maxillary palpus.

label: mechanosensory neuron of mechanosensory ventral triple row bristle
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a mechanosensory ventral triple row bristle.
synonyms: ventral triple row bristle mechanosensory neuron

label: Rh6 photoreceptor of Bolwig organ
description: Cholinergic photoreceptor cell of the larval Bolwig's organ expressing the green-absorbing opsin Rh6 (lambda[max] = 508nm; FBgn0019940). Fibers pass along the larval optic nerve and terminate in the larval optic neuropil, where they surround the projections of Rh5 photoreceptor of Bolwig organ. Their projections in the larval optic neuropil have been shown to overlap with, and influence the development of, serotonergic arborizations (Rodriguez Moncalvo and Campos, 2005), and to overlap with the dendrites of pacemaker lateral neurons (LN's) (Keene et al., 2011; Mazzoni et al., 2005). There are approximately 8 of these per Bolwig organ.

label: twin sensillum of margin 1 neuron
description: Neuron innervating the twin sensillum of margin 1. This neuron, which begins axonogenesis 1hr AP, pioneers the segment of nerve L1 which joins the L3 bundle (Murray et al., 1984).

label: twin sensillum of margin 2 neuron
description: Neuron innervating the twin sensillum of margin 2. This neuron begins axonogenesis at approximately 9-10 hours AP (Murray et al., 1984).

label: giant sensillum of the dorsal radius neuron
description: Large sensory neuron (approximately 20 by 10 micrometres) innervating the single large campaniform sensillum of the dorsal radius (Palka et al., 1979).

label: giant sensillum of the dorsal radius
description: Large, singly-innervated campaniform sensillum on the posterior face of the distal radius of the adult wing. It is a large circular sensilla, with a high profile and a distinct discontinuity between the dome and socket. It is around 9 micrometers in diameter.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DC3 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DC3. Neurons of this class are derived from the sixth larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010). The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the anterior edge of the lateral horn, in a similar region to VL2a and VA1lm PNs.

label: metathoracic leg trachea
description: Tracheal branch that extends into the adult metathoracic leg. It arises from the hypopleural air sac.

label: chemosensory neuron of ventral double row bristle
description: Chemosensory neuron innervating a chemosensory ventral double row bristle.
synonyms: chemosensory ventral double row bristle neuron

label: row
description: Anatomical group whose component structures are arranged in a row.

label: abdominal 5 ventral acute muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 1 (FBbt:00000595) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral acute muscle
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle (FBbt:00000594) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000593) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle (FBbt:00000608) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 oblique muscle
description: Any A1-7 oblique muscle (FBbt:00000607) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral acute muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 3 (FBbt:00000597) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral acute muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 ventral acute muscle 2 (FBbt:00000596) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: terminal organ neuron of dorsal organ ganglion
description: Gustatory receptor neuron whose dendrites innervate the terminal organ on the surface of the larval head but whose soma is located in the dorsal organ ganglion rather than the terminal organ ganglion (terminal organ dorso-lateral group). The axons of these neurons project via the antennal nerve into area 4 of the subesophageal ganglion. There are 3 of these neurons per terminal organ.

label: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 4
description: Large chemosensory target area of the larval subesophageal ganglion, located adjacent to the antennal lobes. One or a few neurites from dorsal pharyngeal sense organ neuron(s), and an atypical dorsal organ neuron whose dendrites extend into the terminal organ, target this region (Colomb et al., 2007).

label: regulation of biological process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the dorsal organ
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the dorsal organ on the surface of the larval head. Projections from at least some of these neurons innervate `subesophageal ganglion area 3` (FBbt:00100141) (Colomb et al., 2007). There are 11 of these neurons.

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the ventral organ
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the ventral organ on the surface of the larval head.

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the epiphysis
description: Gustatory receptor that innervates the epiphysis in the larval pharynx.
synonyms: gustatory receptor neuron of the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the hypophysis
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the hypophysis in the larval pharynx.
synonyms: gustatory receptor neuron of the ventral pharyngeal organ

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the hypopharyngeal organ
description: Gustatory receptor organ that innervates hypopharyngeal organ in the larval pharynx.
synonyms: gustatory receptor neuron of the posterior pharyngeal sense organ

label: abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000611) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle 2
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 2 (FBbt:00000610) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 3
description: Small chemosensory target area located laterally in the larval subesophageal ganglion. This region receives input from non-olfactory neurons of the dorsal organ and from thoracic projections originating in the Kolbchen (also called the 'ventral pit'; Colomb et al., 2007).

label: abdominal 5 lateral oblique muscle 1
description: Any A1-7 lateral oblique muscle 1 (FBbt:00000615) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle 5
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 5 (FBbt:00000613) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal oblique muscle 4
description: Any A1-7 dorsal oblique muscle 4 (FBbt:00000612) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 5 ventral oblique muscle 3
description: Any A1-7 ventral oblique muscle 3 (FBbt:00000619) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: mesothoracic leg taste bristle mechanosensory neuron
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a mesothoracic leg taste bristle. Each bristle is singly innervated by a mechanosensory neuron (Stocker 1994).

label: metathoracic leg taste bristle mechanosensory neuron
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a metathoracic leg taste bristle. Each bristle is singly innervated by a mechanosensory neuron (Stocker 1994).

label: prothoracic leg taste bristle mechanosensory neuron
description: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a prothoracic leg taste bristle. Each bristle is singly innervated by a mechanosensory neuron (Stocker 1994).

label: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 1
description: Chemosensory neuron target area located at the midline of the larval subesophageal ganglion (SOG). This area receives input from pharyngeal chemosensory neurons (the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ, the dorsal pharyngeal organ, and the posterior pharyngeal sense organ) (Colomb et al., 2007).

label: fat body primordium
description: The fat body primordium after the gonadal sheath primordium splits from it during stage 14. During late embryogenesis, various holes and clefts form, giving the fat body its larval form. The cells of this primordium do not accumulate fat during their differentiation (this only happens in the larval fat body).

label: lipid storage
description: The accumulation and maintenance in cells or tissues of lipids, compounds soluble in organic solvents but insoluble or sparingly soluble in aqueous solvents. Lipid reserves can be accumulated during early developmental stages for mobilization and utilization at later stages of development.

label: circular visceral muscle fiber
description: Circular fiber of the visceral muscles, which surround the intestinal tract.

label: circular visceral muscle primordium
description: Primordium of the circular visceral muscle of the trunk. Becomes distinct from the rest of the trunk mesoderm by stage 11 when two distinct layers of trunk mesoderm are apparent, the inner of which is the circular visceral muscle primordium. By stage 12, these cells form a palisade consisting of a dorsal row an a ventral row of tightly packed cells. These cells adhere to the anterior and posterior midgut rudiments as they extend. During dorsal closure they spread out to encircle the midgut.

label: asynchronous muscle
description: Skeletal muscle that does not exhibit a direct relationship between motor neuron activity and muscle contraction. Asynchronous muscles have very large fibrils, with nuclei scattered between them and distributed throughout the entire cross-section of the fiber. Indirect flight muscles are asynchronous.

label: fusion competent cell
description: A mononucleate cell of the embryo that is committed to a muscle-specific program of differentiation but not yet fused. It undergoes limited additional proliferation. Many fusion competent cells fuse with a single muscle founder cell, taking on the identity of that founder cell.

label: embryonic myoblast
description: Muscle progenitor cell of the embryo. Prior to myoblast fusion, two types can be distinguished: fusion competent and muscle founder cells.

label: synchronous muscle
description: Skeletal muscle that exhibits a direct relationship between motor neuron activity and muscle contraction. The fibrils of synchronous muscles are smaller than the ones from asynchronous ones. Most skeletal muscles are synchronous.

label: tubular muscle
description: Muscle that has the myofibrils arranged radially around a central core of cytoplasm containing the nuclei. Muscles of this type are usually found in the legs and trunk.

label: tonofibrilla
description: Attachment fibers that are embedded in the cuticle, and attach the tendon cells to it. Tonofibrils are closely associated with hemidesmosomes found in the external, apical face of the tendon cell that abuts the cuticle. Tonofibrils are made up of dense extracellular material.

label: tendon cell
description: Cell of epidermal origin that is attached to the end of muscles and connects them to the exoskeleton. The attachment between the muscle and tendon cell is done via interdigitating desmosomes. The attachment of the tendon cell to the cuticle relies on interdigitating hemidesmosomes in this cell that are closely associated with tonofibrils embedded in the cuticle.

label: posterior male adult hindgut
description: Posterior hindgut of the adult male.

label: presumptive posterior male adult hindgut
description: Region of the thickened posterior part of the dorsal epithelium of the male genital disc that will develop into the posterior male adult hindgut.

label: 5-3I
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB5-3 lineage.

label: 5-3Ica
description: Interneuron of the NB5-3 lineage that projects through the anterior commissure.

label: 5-3Icp
description: Interneuron of the NB5-3 lineage that whose projections form a bundle that projects through the posterior commissure.

label: 5-6Ica of abdomen
description: Contralateral interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the abdomen that projects through the anterior commissure.

label: 5-6I of abdomen
description: Interneuron that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of abdomen.

label: 5-6Icp of abdomen
description: Contralateral interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax that projects through the posterior commissure.

label: 5-6Ii of abdomen
description: Ipsilateral interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the abdomen.

label: 5-6I
description: Interneuron that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6.

label: 5-6Ica of thorax
description: Contralateral interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax that projects through the anterior commissure.

label: 5-6I of thorax
description: Interneuron that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of thorax.

label: 5-6Icp of thorax
description: Contralateral interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax that projects through the posterior commissure.

label: 5-6Ii of thorax
description: Ipsilateral interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax.

label: 6-1I
description: Interneuron originating from neuroblast the NB6-1 lineage.

label: 6-1Ii
description: Ipsilateral posterior projecting interneuron originating from 6-1I.

label: 6-1Ic
description: Interneuron originating from 6-1I that projects through the posterior commissure.

label: 6-2I
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB6-2 lineage.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron ab12b
description: An olfactory receptor neuron that whose dendrite transduces signals from the antennal basiconic sensillum ab11. It is distinguishable from ORN ab12a and ORN ab12c by its odor response profile.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab12
description: An olfactory basiconic sensillum of the lateral surface of the antenna, innervated by 3 ORNs.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron ab12c
description: An olfactory receptor neuron that whose dendrite transduces signals from the antennal basiconic sensillum ab11. It is distinguishable from ORN ab12a and ORN ab12b by its odor response profile.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron ab11c
description: An olfactory receptor neuron that whose dendrite transduces signals from the antennal basiconic sensillum ab11. It is distinguishable from ORN ab11a and ORN ab11b by its odor response profile.

label: antennal basiconic sensillum ab11
description: An olfactory basiconic sensillum of the lateral surface of the antenna, innervated by 3 ORNs.

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron ab12a
description: An olfactory receptor neuron that whose dendrite transduces signals from the antennal basiconic sensillum ab11. It is distinguishable from ORN ab12b and ORN ab12c by its odor response profile.

label: 6-4Ic
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB6-4 lineage in the embryonic thorax and projects contralaterally across the posterior commissure.

label: 6-4I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB6-4 lineage in the embryonic thorax. There are 4 to 6 neurons.

label: 6-4Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB6-4 lineage in the embryonic thorax and projects ipsilaterally.

label: 6-2Ii
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB6-2 lineage whose projections form a small, ipsilaterally projecting bundle that projects anteriorly along the lateral border of the ipsilateral connective.

label: 6-2Icp1
description: Contralaterally projecting interneuron originating from 6-2I. It is distinguished from 6-2cp2 by crossing the posterior commissure along the anterior margin.

label: 6-2Icp2
description: Contralaterally projecting interneuron originating from 6-2I. It is distinguished from 6-2cp1 by crossing the posterior commissure along the posterior margin then bending posteriorly in the contralateral connective.

label: presumptive female accessory gland
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the female accessory gland.

label: 7-1Ica
description: Contralaterally projecting interneuron originating from 7-1I. It projects through the middle of the anterior commissure.

label: 7-1I
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB7-1 lineage.

label: 7-1Icp
description: Contralaterally projecting interneuron originating from 7-1I. It projects through the posterior border of the posterior commissure.

label: abdominal 7 lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2
description: Any abdominal lateral sensillum trichodeum lh2 (FBbt:00002847) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: 7-2I
description: Interneuron originating from neuroblast the NB7-2 lineage.

label: 7-2Ii
description: Ipsilateral posterior projecting interneuron originating from 7-2I.

label: 7-4Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB7-4 lineage in the embryonic thorax and projects ipsilaterally.

label: 7-4I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB4-4 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord. There are 8 to 12 neurons.

label: 7-2Ic
description: Contralaterally projecting interneuron that projects through the posterior commissure.

label: 7-3I
description: Interneuron of the NB7-3 lineage. The projections of these interneurons form a bundle that projects across the anterior border of the posterior commissure.

label: 7-4Ic
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB7-4 lineage in the embryonic thorax and projects contralaterally across the posterior commissure.

label: pseudotracheal terminal taste peg
description: Taste peg at the distal end of the pseudotrachea in the adult labellum.

label: adult maxillary-labial nerve
description: The adult maxillary-labial nerve is a fused nerve of the maxillary and labial nerves. It enters the maxillary neuromere of the gnathal ganglion and then bifurcates to project to the maxillary and labial neuromeres.

label: yIi
description: Interneuron that develops from an unidentified neuroblast lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects ipsilaterally.

label: y interneuron
description: Interneuron that develops from an unidentified neuroblast lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord.

label: metathoracic tracheal pit
description: Tracheal pit of the third thoracic segment of the embryo.

label: metathoracic tracheal primordium
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic metathoracic segment (FBbt:00000170).

label: fan-shaped body layer 7
description: Second-most dorsal layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: yIc
description: Interneuron that develops from an unidentified neuroblast lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects contralaterally across the posterior commissure.

label: adult pars lateralis
description: Pars lateralis of the adult.

label: 1-1Ms
description: Motor neuron developing from the thoracic neuroblast NB1-1 which fasciculates with the segmental nerve. The axon terminates amongst ventrolateral muscles without a detectable end-plate (Bossing et al., 1996).

label: adult labro-frontal nerve
description: The adult labro-frontal nerve is a fused nerve of the labral and frontal nerves.

label: posterior chiasma of the central complex
description: Chiasma that lies on the midline between the protocerebral bridge (PB) and fan-shaped body (FB). Some fibers from one side of the PB project to the contralateral side of the FB.

label: abdominal tracheal pit 3
description: Tracheal pit of the third abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal pit
description: Tracheal pit of the abdomen.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 3
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000175).

label: anterior chiasma of the central complex
description: Chiasma that lies on the midline between the fan-shaped body (FB) and ellipsoid body (EB). Some fibers from one side of the FB project to the contralateral side of the lateral accessory lobe and EB.

label: abdominal tracheal pit 2
description: Tracheal pit of the second abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 2
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000174).

label: abdominal tracheal pit 1
description: Tracheal pit of the first abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 1
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000173).

label: TB neuron
description: Developing from neuroblast NB1-2, the TB neuron is located apart from the other cells of this lineage. Axogenesis begins early, at embryonic stage 13, and has a distinctive 'bent' morphology.

label: abdominal tracheal pit 7
description: Tracheal pit of the seventh abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 7
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000179).

label: abdominal tracheal pit 6
description: Tracheal pit of the sixth abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 6
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000178).

label: abdominal tracheal pit 5
description: Tracheal pit of the fifth abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 5
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000177).

label: abdominal tracheal pit 4
description: Tracheal pit of the fourth abdominal segment of the embryo.

label: abdominal tracheal primordium 4
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000176).

label: sensory system neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that capable of part of some sensory perception (GO:0007600).

label: hygrosensory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of humidity.

label: fan-shaped body layer 8
description: Dorsal most layer of the fan-shaped body.

label: 2-2M
description: Any embryonic/larval motor neuron (FBbt:00007675) that develops from some neuroblast NB2-2 (FBbt:00001385).

label: 2-2M of thorax
description: Any embryonic/larval motor neuron (FBbt:00007675) that is part of some larval thorax (FBbt:00001741) and that develops from some neuroblast NB2-2 (FBbt:00001385).

label: abdominal tracheal pit 8
description: Tracheal pit of the most posterior abdominal segment of the embryo. During stages 14-15, the pit fuses with special cells of the abdominal segment 8 to give rise to the posterior spiracle.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center B2 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron whose cell body is located ventrally to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). The primary neurite extends posteriomedially, forming postsynaptic terminals in the medial surface of the ipsilateral zone B and zone E. It then crosses the midline fasciculating with the inferior AMMC commissure and extends into the medial side of AMMC zone B, forming presynaptic terminals. It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: embryonic/larval trachea
description: Larval trachea from their maturation in late embryonic stages, to their degeneration/transformation during metamorphosis.

label: adult male posterior abdominal ganglion neuron
description: Neuron of the adult male that is located in the posterior region of the abdominal ganglion. It fasciculates with the abdominal nerve trunk and innervates the testicular duct, seminal vesicles, accessory glands and an anterior part of the ejaculatory duct. There are 4 to 6 of these neurons, in a dorsal cluster. It is a serotonergic neuron.

label: adult female posterior abdominal ganglion neuron
description: Glutamatergic motor neuron of the adult female that is located in the posterior region of the abdominal ganglion. It fasciculates with the abdominal nerve trunk and innervates the oviduct muscle. There are 3 to 4 of these neurons, in a ventral cluster.

label: 2-5M
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911) and that develops from some neuroblast NB2-5 (FBbt:00001374).

label: cephalic branch primordium
description: Primordium of the embryonic/larval cephalic branch.

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 3
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 1 (FBbt:00000190).

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch
description: Anteriorly directed dorsal branch of the tracheal primordium. Fuses to the posterior branch of the dorsal trunk of the tracheal primordium of the next segment anterior to it during stage 14.

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 2
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some metathoracic tracheal primordium (FBbt:00000188).

label: dorsal trunk primordium
description: Region of the tracheal primordium that gives rise to the embryonic/larval dorsal trunk.

label: sensory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception.

label: embryonic/larval dorsal trunk
description: The main airway of the larval/embryonic tracheal system, linking its metameric units and spanning the length of the animal from the anterior spiracle in the prothoracic segment to the posterior spiracle in A8 on the same side. There are two per larva, left and right.

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 7
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 5 (FBbt:00000194).

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 6
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 4 (FBbt:00000193).

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 5
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 3 (FBbt:00000192).

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 4
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 2 (FBbt:00000191).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron ab11b
description: An olfactory receptor neuron that whose dendrite transduces signals from the antennal basiconic sensillum ab11. It is distinguishable from ORN ab11a and ORN ab11c by its odor response profile.

label: 3-2M
description: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is part of some embryonic/larval nervous system (FBbt:00001911) and that develops from some neuroblast NB3-2 (FBbt:00001388).

label: adult olfactory receptor neuron ab11a
description: An olfactory receptor neuron that whose dendrite transduces signals from the antennal basiconic sensillum ab11. It is distinguishable from ORN ab11b and ORN ab11c by its odor response profile.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-IVLP projection neuron 1
description: Projection neuron that innervates the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zone B and the projects to the contralateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (Lai et al., 2012).

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 10
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 8 (FBbt:00007470).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-IVLP projection neuron 2
description: Projection neuron that innervates the ipsilateral zones A of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and projects to the contralateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum. A small dorsal branch distinguishes this neuron class from AMMC-IVLP PN1 (Lai et al., 2012).

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 9
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 7 (FBbt:00000196).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center local AMMC-AMMC 2 neuron
description: Projection neuron that innervates both antennal mechanosensory and motor centers (AMMC) with unequal fibre distributions between the two AMMC regions (Lai et al., 2012).
synonyms: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-AMMC projection neuron 2

label: dorsal trunk anterior branch 8
description: Any dorsal trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000213) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 6 (FBbt:00000195).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VNC projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that innervates both zones A and B of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and projects to the contralateral thoracico-abdominal ganglion. One branch innervates the contralateral AMMC zones A and B.

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 3
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 1 (FBbt:00000190).

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch
description: Posteriorly directed dorsal branch of the tracheal primordium. Fuses to the anterior branch of the dorsal trunk of the tracheal primordium of the next segment posterior to it during stage 14.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA1v adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA1 ventral compartment. Neurons of this class are derived from the 13th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010). Their axons innervate the ventral half of the lateral horn (Marin et al., 2002).

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 2
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some metathoracic tracheal primordium (FBbt:00000188).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM6 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DM6. Neurons of this class are derived from the 12th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 1
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some mesothoracic tracheal primordium (FBbt:00000187).

label: mesothoracic tracheal primordium
description: Any tracheal primordium (FBbt:00005037) that is part of some embryonic mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000169).

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 6
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 4 (FBbt:00000193).

label: adult supraesophageal zone
description: Neuropil mass above the esophagus in the adult brain. It is part of the cerebral ganglion.

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 5
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 3 (FBbt:00000192).

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 4
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 2 (FBbt:00000191).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center AMMC-VLP7 projection neuron
description: Projection neuron that innervates the ipsilateral zone A of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) and projects to the contralateral ventrolateral protocerebrum. These axonal terminals are not arborized (Lai et al., 2012).

label: bilateral local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe
description: Local interneuron of the adult antennal lobe that innervates both the ipsi- and contralateral antennal lobes.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron D adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus D. This neuron is derived from the fourth larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DC2 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DC2. This neuron is derived from the third larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL1 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL1. Neurons of this class are derived from the first larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010). The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the ventroposterior edge of the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA2 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA2. This neuron is born from the 14th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VM2 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VM2. Neurons of this class are derived from the 11th larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010). The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the dorsoposterior edge of the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA1d adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA1d. Neurons of this class are derived from the seventh larval division of the ALad1 neuroblast (FBbt:00067346) and their axons innervate the anterior/ventral region of the lateral horn (Marin et al., 2002, Tanaka et al., 2004).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA3 adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA3. Neurons of this class derive from the fifth larval division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) (Yu et al., 2010).

label: embryonic/larval lateral trunk
description: Laterally located, embryonic/larval trachea that, like the dorsal trunk, runs the length of the larva from T1 to A8. It is much thinner than the dorsal trunk and follows a jagged path from segment to segment. There are two per larva, left and right.

label: fan-shaped body slice 2
description: Second medial-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 9
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 7 (FBbt:00000196).

label: fan-shaped body slice 3
description: Third medial-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 8
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 6 (FBbt:00000195).

label: dorsal trunk posterior branch 7
description: Any dorsal trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000223) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 5 (FBbt:00000194).

label: fan-shaped body slice 1
description: Medial-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 4
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 2 (FBbt:00000191).

label: lateral trunk anterior branch
description: Anteriorly directed ventral branch of the tracheal primordium that gives rise to the anterior portion of the lateral trunk in each tracheal metamere. It arises as the anterior side of a bifurcation at the ventral end of the tracheal primordium during stage 12. It fuses with posterior branch of the lateral trunk of the next segment to its anterior during stage 14 or 15.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 3
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 1 (FBbt:00000190).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DA1 vPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ventral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DA1. This neuron is GABAergic.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 2
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some metathoracic tracheal primordium (FBbt:00000188).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA1v vPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the ventral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA1 ventral compartment. This neuron is GABAergic.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 6
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 4 (FBbt:00000193).

label: fan-shaped body slice 8
description: Lateral-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 5
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 3 (FBbt:00000192).

label: A1-7 DO1sib motor neuron
description: Sibling neuron to the A1-7 DO1 motor neuron developing from the first ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: fan-shaped body slice 6
description: Third lateral-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped body slice 7
description: Second lateral-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped body slice 4
description: Fourth medial-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: fan-shaped body slice 5
description: Fourth lateral-most slice in each hemisphere of the fan-shaped body.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA5 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA5. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron VA7m lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus VA7m. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: A1-7 DA2sib motor neuron
description: Sibling neuron to the A1-7 DA2 motor neuron developing from the second ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL3 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DL3. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: A1-7 DO2sib motor neuron
description: Sibling neuron to the A1-7 DO2 motor neuron developing from the third ganglion mother cell that differentiates from neuroblast NB7-1.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DA1 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DA1. The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the anterior edge of the lateral horn.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 7
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 5 (FBbt:00000194).

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM1 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DM1. The axons of these neurons innervate a small area at the dorsoposterior edge of the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM2 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DM2. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM5 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DM5. The axons of these neurons innervate the lateral horn.

label: NH neuron
description: Neuron that expresses engrailed (FBgn0000577) near the ventral surface of the anterior region of each embryonic thoracic and abdominal segment, anterior to the PI neurons. There are 2 neurons in each cluster, with 2 clusters per hemisegment.

label: lateral trunk posterior branch
description: Posteriorly directed ventral branch of the tracheal primordium that gives rise to the posterior portion of the lateral trunk in each tracheal metamere. It arises as the posterior side of a bifurcation at the ventral end of the tracheal primordium during stage 12. It fuses with posterior branch of the lateral trunk of the next segment to its posterior during stage 14 or 15.

label: adult fruitless pIP-e (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DL1. The cell bodies are located in the posteriolateral brain. Neurites project anteriorly forming arbors in the entire ring and regions ventral to the ring. One branch projects medially and crosses the midline.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 10
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 8 (FBbt:00007470).

label: PL neuron
description: Neuron that expresses engrailed (FBgn0000577) in a posterior lateral cluster in each embryonic thoracic and abdominal segment, on either side of the midline, lateral to the PI neurons. There are 8 to 10 neurons in each cluster.

label: adult fruitless pIP-e (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-e (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110610) and that develops from some neuroblast DL1 (FBbt:00050184) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 9
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 7 (FBbt:00000196).

label: PI neuron
description: Neuron that expresses engrailed (FBgn0000577) in a posterior intermediate cluster in each embryonic thoracic and abdominal segment, on either side of the midline. There are 4 to 6 neurons in each cluster.

label: lateral trunk anterior branch 8
description: Any lateral trunk anterior branch (FBbt:00000234) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 6 (FBbt:00000195).

label: EG neuron
description: Interneuron that is part of a cluster of 10-12 eagle (FBgn0000560) expressing neurons deriving from multiple neuroblasts. Axons extend across the midline via the anterior commissure.

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 4
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 2 (FBbt:00000191).

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 3
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 1 (FBbt:00000190).

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 2
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some metathoracic tracheal primordium (FBbt:00000188).

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 1
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some mesothoracic tracheal primordium (FBbt:00000187).

label: adult fruitless pMP-c (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM4.

label: adult fruitless pMP-c (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-c (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110618) and that develops from some adult DM4 lineage clone (FBbt:00050253) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless pMP-b (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM2.

label: embryonic ventral trunk epidermis
description: The epidermis of the embryonic ventral trunk.

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 5
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 3 (FBbt:00000192).

label: adult fruitless pMP-b (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-b (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110616) and that develops from some neuroblast DM2 (FBbt:00050121) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless pMP-a (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM1.

label: adult fruitless pMP-a (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-a (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110614) and that develops from some neuroblast DM1 (FBbt:00050018) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless pIP-h (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum. The cell bodies are located medial to pIP-a neurons. Neurites enter the neuropil through the same tract opening as pIP-a and branches. One branch travels dorsoanteriorly, towards the medial ring. Another projects to the ventromedial region of the contralateral ring. The third branch crosses the midline above the oesophageal foramen and travels ventrally and exits the brain to terminate in the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: adult fruitless pIP-h (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-h (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110612) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: PM neuron
description: Neuron that is part of a cluster of 10-12 eagle (FBgn0000560) expressing neurons deriving from multiple neuroblasts. These neurons develop form the same cluster as EG neurons, but leave the cluster in early stage 13. At embryonic stage 15, these neurons are found just medial to the EG cluster, both anterior and posteriorly.

label: PQ neuron
description: Interneuron that is part of a cluster of 10-12 eagle (FBgn0000560) expressing neurons deriving from multiple neuroblasts. These neurons develop form the same cluster as EG neurons, but leave the cluster in early stage 13. At embryonic stage 15, these neurons are found just medial to the EG cluster, both anterior and posteriorly. At stage 16, they become undetectable.

label: EW neuron
description: Interneuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments from the 7-3 lineage.

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 7
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 5 (FBbt:00000194).

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 6
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 4 (FBbt:00000193).

label: serotonergic IP neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 2 (bilateral) clusters in the brain located in the ventral larval brain lobes or in the adult supraesophageal ganglion. There are three cells in this cluster.

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 1
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that connects the dorsal and lateral trunks.

label: adult fruitless pMP-e (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-e (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110620) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless pMP-e (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior medial protocerebrum.

label: serotonergic LP1 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 2 (bilateral) clusters, in the lateral region of the brain. There are 2 neurons in this cluster.

label: adult fruitless pMP-f (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM6.

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 9
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 7 (FBbt:00000196).

label: lateral trunk posterior branch 8
description: Any lateral trunk posterior branch (FBbt:00000244) that is part of some abdominal tracheal primordium 6 (FBbt:00000195).

label: EW1 neuron
description: Serotonergic interneuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments A1-A7. The axon bifurcates into two thick branches as it enters dorsally into the contralateral neuropil. These two primary branches initially diverge in opposite directions and grow along the medial two-thirds of the neuropil, forming a circular pattern, with the branches meeting at the dorsal end of the neuropil. These neurons also extend an ipsilateral neurite, that seems to fasciculate with the respective neurite of the serotonergic abdominal lateral neuron and follow a similar pathway, projecting anteriorly to form the majority of its branches in the next anterior segment. In the A7 abdominal segment, this neuron has a single primary neurite that extends centrally and forms extensive varicosities. It is born from the first-born ganglion mother cell of the 7-3 lineage (GMC 7-3a).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 5
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 4
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: EW2 neuron
description: Serotonergic interneuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segments A1-A7. Its contralateral branch forms a complex pattern at the ventral border of the contralateral neuropil that extends along the lateral margins. Its ipsilateral branch seems to fasciculate with the respective neurite of the serotonergic abdominal medial neuron and follows a similar pathway, though extending a contralateral neurite about mid-level in the dorso-ventral and anterior-posterior axis. This neurite extends a short way anterior along a midline tract. It is born from the second-born ganglion mother cell of the 7-3 lineage (GMC 7-3b).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 3
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).

label: EW3 neuron
description: Peptidergic interneuron of embryonic/larval abdominal segment. It differentiates directly from the third GMC in the 7-3 lineage (GMC 7-3c).

label: GW neuron
description: Motor neuron of embryonic and larval abdominal segment. It is born from the first ganglion mother cell in the 7-3 lineage (GMC 7-3a).

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center local AMMC-AMMC 1 neuron
description: Commissural projection neuron that innervates both the ipsi- and contralateral zones A and B of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). It expresses fruitless and it is a GABAergic neuron.

label: adult fruitless pSG-d neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG-d lineage clone (FBbt:00110518).

label: adult fruitless pSG-d lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

label: nervus corporis cardiaci III
description: Bilaterally paired nerve bundle that connects the larval ring gland to the brain. It comprises the axons of neurons from the neurosecretory cells of the tritocerebrum and subesophageal ganglion (Hartenstein, 2006).

label: ring gland
description: A closely associated cluster of three neuroendocrine glands located anterior to the aorta and dorsal to the esophagus. At embryonic stage 17 and in larva it is found anterior to the brain and is formed by the corpus cardiacum ventrally, the prothoracic gland laterally and the corpus allatum dorsally. The adult ring gland is located anterior to the proventriculus and is formed by the corpus cardiacum ventrally, the corpus allatum dorsally and the hypocerebral ganglion posterior to the corpus cardiacum. It is innervated by neurons of the nervus corporis cardiaci (NccI-III).

label: adult fruitless pSP-b (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-b (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110624) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpl1 (FBbt:00050228) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless pSP-b (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpl1.

label: nervus corporis cardiaci II
description: Bilaterally paired nerve bundle that connects the larval ring gland to the brain. It comprises the axons of neurons from the neurosecretory cells of the pars lateralis. After leaving the pars lateralis, the axons pass the mushroom body calyx and peduncle medially, before reaching the medial edge of the protocerebrum where it joins the nervus corporis cardiaci I (NccI), continuing towards the ring gland (de Velasco et al., 2007; Hartenstein, 2006).

label: adult fruitless pMP-f (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-f (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110622) and that develops from some neuroblast DM6 (FBbt:00050142) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 8
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 7
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 6
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: VUM interneuron 3
description: One of the three ventral unpaired median interneurons of the embryonic and larval ventral nerve cord midline.

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 1
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches dorsally from the dorsal trunk. It tracheates the dorsal epidermis and dorsal vessel. Each dorsal branch connects to the contralateral branch of the same tracheal metamere via the dorsal anastomosis.

label: MP1 neuron
description: Interneuron residing slightly anterior and ventral to the posterior commissure in the corner formed by the connectives and the posterior commissure (Bossing and Technau, 1994). Its ipsilateral projection bifurcates in an anterior and posterior branch (which spans up to three neuromeres) that run within the medial sector of the connective.

label: MP1 precursor
description: Unpaired precursor cell that divides to produce two MP1 interneurons.

label: MP1 tract
description: Tract pioneered by the MP1 neuron in the ventral nerve cord. The MP1 neurons send a bifurcating axon anterior and posterior along two or three segments in a medial fascicle of the longitudinal connectives (Schmid et al., 1999).

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 10
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 10 (FBbt:00005035).

label: tracheal branch of Tr10
description: Any embryonic/larval trachea (FBbt:00000211) that is part of some tracheal metamere 10 (FBbt:00005035).

label: tracheal metamere 10
description: The tracheal system of abdominal segment 8.

label: embryonic/larval transverse connective 9
description: Any embryonic/larval transverse connective (FBbt:00000254) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 4
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 3
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).
