label: VUM interneuron 1
description: One of the three ventral unpaired median interneurons of the embryonic and larval ventral nerve cord midline.

label: VUM interneuron 2
description: One of the three ventral unpaired median interneurons of the embryonic and larval ventral nerve cord midline.

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 8
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 7
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 6
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 5
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: response to temperature stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a temperature stimulus.

label: dorsal anastomosis 2
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 2 (FBbt:00000267).

label: adult fruitless aSP-g (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal2. The cell bodies are located away from the neuropil, lateroanteriorly from the lateral horn. A neurite enters a neuropil tract anterior to lateral horn and projects medially to arborize in the lateral junction and the lateral crescent. It also projects to the contralateral hemisphere.

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 10
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 10 (FBbt:00005035).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal branch 9
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal branch (FBbt:00000265) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034).

label: dorsal anastomosis 4
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 4 (FBbt:00000269).

label: dorsal anastomosis 3
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 3 (FBbt:00000268).

label: adult fruitless aSP-k (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-k (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110606) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl1 (FBbt:00050047) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless pIP-a (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast PSp3. Its cell bodies are located laterally in a cluster close to the tract entrance below the protocerebral bridge. A neurite projects anteriorly before branching. The dorsal branch leads to dense arborizations in the ventral and medial ipsilateral ring. The dorsal projection travels lateroventrally forming dense arborizations in multiple regions including the lateral accessory lobe, posterior antennal mechanosensory motor center and subesophageal zone before exiting the brain. In the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, the projections travel along a lateral tract and arborize mostly in the meso- and metathoracic neuromeres.

label: adult fruitless aSP-i (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-i (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110604) and that develops from some neuroblast AOTUv3 (FBbt:00050127) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aSP-i (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv3. Its cell bodies are located ventrally to the anterior optic tubercle. Neurites project medially to arborize in the ipsilateral anterior optic tubercle. Arborization localizes to the dorsal region of the anterior optic tubercle. A neurite also branches to cross the midline in a distinctive V shape to arborize in the contralateral anterior optic tubercle.

label: adult fruitless aSP-h (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-h (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110602) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl2 (FBbt:00050032) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aSP-h (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl2.

label: adult fruitless aSP-g (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-g (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110600) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPal2 (FBbt:00050267) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless pIP-a (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP-a (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110608) and that develops from some neuroblast PSp3 (FBbt:00050092) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: dorsal anastomosis 5
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 5 (FBbt:00000270).

label: dorsal anastomosis 9
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 9 (FBbt:00000274).

label: dorsal anastomosis 8
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 8 (FBbt:00000273).

label: dorsal anastomosis 7
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 7 (FBbt:00000272).

label: dorsal anastomosis 6
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal anastomosis (FBbt:00000276) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031) and that connected to some embryonic/larval dorsal branch 6 (FBbt:00000271).

label: dorsal group branch 3
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).

label: embryonic/larval dorsal group branch
description: Secondary trachea that branches from the dorsal branch. The number and position of these branches is variable.

label: dorsal group branch 2
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027).

label: dorsal group branch 1
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026).

label: dorsal group branch 4
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: dorsal group branch 6
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: dorsal group branch 5
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: dorsal group branch 10
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 10 (FBbt:00005035).

label: dorsal group branch 9
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034).

label: dorsal group branch 8
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: dorsal group branch 7
description: Any embryonic/larval dorsal group branch (FBbt:00000285) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: visceral branch 5
description: Any embryonic/larval visceral branch (FBbt:00000296) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: embryonic/larval visceral branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches from a transverse connective and tracheates the viscera.

label: visceral branch 4
description: Any embryonic/larval visceral branch (FBbt:00000296) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: visceral branch 2
description: Any embryonic/larval visceral branch (FBbt:00000296) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027).

label: visceral branch primordium
description: Tracheal primordium that develops into the embryonic/larval visceral branch. It branches anteriorly from the dorsal portion of the transverse connective primordium during stage 12, coursing anteriorly and inwardly towards the gut.

label: female abdominal tergite 8 bristle
description: Small unpigmented bristle of the female abdominal tergite 8. There are 4 to 5 of these.

label: presumptive female abdominal tergite 8 bristle
description: Region of the female genital disc that will develop into the female abdominal tergite 8 bristle.

label: female abdominal tergite 8
description: Paired horse-shoe shaped tergite of female abdominal segment 8 that surrounds the anal plates. It is lightly chitinized and contains four or five small unpigmented bristles on either side.

label: presumptive female abdominal tergite 8
description: Region of the thick ventral epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the female abdominal tergite 8.

label: posterior female adult hindgut
description: Posterior hindgut of the adult female.

label: presumptive posterior female adult hindgut
description: Region of the thickened posterior dorsal epithelium of the female genital disc that will develop into the posterior female adult hindgut.

label: cell body
description: The cell body of a neuron, containing the nucleus.

label: dendritic tree
description: The arborization of dendrites, defined by the number, position, branching structure, density and stratification of its branches. Dense body. Synaptic ribbon at neuromuscular junction.

label: dendrite
description: The region of a neuron receiving inputs from other neurons, typically a slender neurite, often branched. In insect neurons, this is often not a clear designation and often presynaptic sites co-extend with postsynaptic ones.

label: neurite
description: One of the processes or extensions of a neuron, axon or dendrite or cell body fiber.

label: nerve terminal
description: The output region of a neuron, generally presynaptic but in insects often also locally postsynaptic. Typically containing large numbers of mitochondria in addition to presynaptic organelles.

label: end plate
description: The complex postsynaptic specialization at the site of contact between a neuron and a muscle fiber.

label: synapse
description: The structural contact that is the site of transmission between neurons, identified by a presynaptic ribbon and synaptic vesicles as the input element and one or (usually) more postsynaptic elements with various specializations (membrane densities, cisternae, etc.).

label: t-bar
description: T-shaped density that is found in the presynaptic region of a neuron.

label: presynaptic ribbon
description: An organelle at the input site of a synapse, the presumed structure for vesicle exocytosis, comprising a central pedestal but often with several components (e.g. a platform in recent groups of Diptera).

label: dorso-lateral dopaminergic neuron
description: Dopaminergic neuron of the dorso-lateral cluster of the adult brain.

label: ganglion cell
description: The neuron of a ganglion.

label: abdominal 3 temporary eclosion muscle SBM
description: Temporary eclosion muscle of adult abdominal segment 2 that develops from abdominal 3 segment border muscle of the larva by a process of remodelling.

label: chemosensory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of chemical stimuli.

label: mechanosensory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of mechanical stimuli.

label: neurilemma
description: Acellular, uniform and extracellular layer that covers the nervous system, and is secreted by the underlying glial cells.

label: gustatory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of taste.

label: olfactory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of smell.

label: detection of temperature stimulus involved in sensory perception
description: The series of events in which a temperature stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal as part of sensory perception.

label: thermosensory system
description: An anatomical system consisting of all of the anatomical entities that function in some part of the sensory perception of temperature.

label: external sensory organ precursor cell IIa
description: Second-order precursor cell. It develops from external sensory organ precursor cell I, and divides to give rise to the tormogen cell and the trichogen cell of an external sensory organ.

label: hygrosensitive sensory organ
description: Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that capable of some detection of humidity stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0098512).

label: trichogen cell
description: The eo support cell that makes the innervated cuticular sensory structure of an eo-type sensillum.

label: tormogen cell
description: The eo support cell that makes the socket that supports the innervated cuticular sensory structure of an eo-type sensillum.

label: thecogen dendritic cap
description: A cuticle-like matrix secreted by the thecogen cell around the tip of the eo dendrite(s).

label: thecogen cell
description: The eo support cell that makes the thecogen dendritic cap - a cuticle-like matrix around the tip of the eo-dendrite and which encloses the soma of the eo-neuron.

label: eo sensory structure
description: The external sensory structure that is part of a trichogen cell. It can have a variety of shapes, including bristles with pointed tips in mechanosensory organs, bristles with open tips in chemosensory ones, or dome-shaped structures in campaniform sensilla.

label: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of touch
description: The series of events involved in the perception of touch in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.
synonyms: perception of touch, sensory transduction of mechanical stimulus

label: eo dendrite
description: Dendrite of an eo neuron, that innervates the cuticular external sensory structure of that sensillum.

label: adult fruitless aSP-f (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-f (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110598) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aSP-f (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior superior protocerebrum. Neurites project ventrally in the dorsal lateral protocerebrum and form arbors extending down to the lateral crescent.

label: adult fruitless aSP-b (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-b (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110596) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad2 (FBbt:00050201) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aSP-b (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad2. Its cell bodies are located in the dorsal pars intercerebralis. Neurites project ventroposteriorly and then bifurcate. One branch projects ipsilaterally and terminates in the medial protocerebrum. The other branch projects ventromedially, turns dorsally at the midline and then joins the path of the same cluster on the contralateral side possibly arborizing in the contralateral hemisphere. The dendritic arbors are likely to be located in the lateral junction while the axonal arbors are in the ventral medial protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless aSP-a (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP-a (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110594) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPad1 (male) (FBbt:00050243).

label: adult fruitless aSP-a (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad1. Its cell bodies located are located in the pars intercerebralis. Projections extend laterally away from the pars intercerebralis and then ventrally to the lateral junction. The extensive arbors span the arch, lateral junction and the medial ring. The axonal arbors are likely to be enriched in the lateral junction. Females have less extensive arbors compared with males.

label: adult fruitless aIP-g (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-g (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110592) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl&p1 (FBbt:00050065) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aIP-g (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl_p1. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite projects medially through the ring and crosses the midline. Another branch projects to the lateral junction.

label: adult fruitless aDT-b (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa1. Its cell bodies are located dorsal to the antennal lobe. Neurites project medioventrally, with differences between males and females. Neurites form bilateral dendritic arborizations in the subesophageal zone, and then project dorsally to terminate in lateral junction.

label: adult fruitless Mb neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless Mb lineage clone (FBbt:00110574) and that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624).

label: adult fruitless Mb lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from one of the mushroom body neuroblasts.

label: pit sensillum of distal group
description: Pit sensillum located in the distal region of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. There are five of these sensilla. Each sensillum is innervated by one sensory neuron.

label: pit sensillum
description: Sensillum that resembles a pit, with a terminal pore which is plugged by an electron-dense material. It can be innervated by one or several dendrites.

label: pit sensillum T1
description: The most ventral of the five pit sensilla located in the distal region of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is innervated by three dendrites.

label: adult fruitless aIP-i neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-i lineage clone (FBbt:00110572) and that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624).

label: adult fruitless aIP-i lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label: ventral organ sensillum
description: Any external sensillum (FBbt:00007231) that is part of some ventral organ (FBbt:00002707).

label: ventral organ sensillum V1
description: Sensillum of the ventral organ innervated by 4 dendrites.

label: pit sensillum T2
description: One of the five pit sensilla located in the distal region of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is distal to pit sensillum T3. It is innervated by four dendrites.

label: pit sensillum T3
description: One of the five pit sensilla located in the distal region of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is proximal to pit sensillum T2. It is innervated by two dendrites.

label: adult fruitless aDT-b (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT-b (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110578) and that develops from some neuroblast CREa1 (male) (FBbt:00050246).

label: pit sensillum T4
description: One of the five pit sensilla located in the distal region of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is proximal to pit sensillum T5. It is innervated by two dendrites.

label: pit sensillum T5
description: One of the five pit sensilla located in the distal region of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is distal to pit sensillum T4. It is innervated by three dendrites.

label: adult fruitless aDT-d (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located junction of the ventrolateral protocerebrum and the antennal lobe. A neurite projects medially and forms two arbors: a dendritic arbor in the lateral junction and an axonal arbor in the anterior medial protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless aDT-d (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT-d (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110580) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aIP-d (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior inferior protocerebrum. Neurites project medially.

label: ventral organ sensillum V2
description: Mono-dendritic sensillum of the ventral organ.

label: adult fruitless aIP-d (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-d (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110588) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: ventral organ sensillum V3
description: Mono-dendritic sensillum of the ventral organ, linked to the exterior by a pore. Putative taste sensillum (Singh, 1997).

label: adult fruitless aIP-c (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl&d1.

label: ventral organ sensillum V4
description: Mono-dendritic sensillum of the ventral organ.

label: adult fruitless aIP-c (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-c (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110586) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl&d1 (FBbt:00050074) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aIP-b (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPa1.

label: adult fruitless aIP-b (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-b (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110584) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPa1 (FBbt:00050157) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aDT-e (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast ALl1.

label: adult fruitless aDT-e (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT-e (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110582) and that develops from some neuroblast ALl1 (FBbt:00067347) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: labial sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some labial segment (FBbt:00000014).

label: ventral organ sensillum V5
description: Mono-dendritic sensillum of the ventral organ.

label: dorsal pit
description: One of 14 innervated pits located in two groups of 7 on either side of the dorsal midline in the dorsal-most part of the larval head. There is no associated external cuticular sensory structure.

label: knob in pit sensillum
description: Paired external sensillum situated dorso-laterally on the larval head and consisting of a knob shaped cuticular structure located in a pit and innervated by 3 dendrites - one terminating at its base and the other two extending into the knob. Putative combined mechanoreceptor (Singh and Singh, 1984) and taste sensillum (Singh, 1997).

label: embryonic/larval maxillary chordotonal organ with two scolopidia
description: Chordotonal organ of the larval maxillary segment that possesses two scolopidia.

label: adult fruitless aIP-e (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP-e (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110590) and that develops from some neuroblast VLPl2 (FBbt:00050225) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aIP-e (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLP2. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region, away from the neuropil and always ventral to aSP-k cell bodies. Neurites project dorsally on the surface of the ventrolateral protocerebrum before entering a tract in the neuropil region below the lateral horn. Unlike aSP-k, the projection from the cell body does not bend before entering the tract. Within the tract, the neurite projects medially arborizing first in the ventral lateral horn, then projects medially to arborize a discrete ventral region in the ring.

label: adult fruitless aSP4 (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP4 (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110554) and that is part of some male organism (FBbt:00007004).

label: adult fruitless aSP4 (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located between the anterior optic tract and the ventrolateral protocerebrum, immediately medial to aSP5 lineage clone. A neurite projects ventrally before turning dorsally and extends superficially along the arch to the contralateral hemisphere. Arbors span the lateral junction, lateral and medial ring. Females do not have extensive arbors in the ring structure.

label: adult fruitless pIP4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless aSP3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aSP3 lineage clone (FBbt:00110552).

label: adult fruitless aSP3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in a cleft between the anterior optic tubercle and the mushroom body lobe junction. A neurite projects medioventrally in the neuropil forming arborizations in the ventral body and then descends out of the brain. The neurites in the thoracico-abdominal ganglion terminate in the pro-, meso- and metathoracic neuromere. These are likely to be axonal based on morphology.

label: labial sensillum 1
description: One of the three labial sensilla located in the labial organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is innervated by one dendrite, similarly to labial sensillum 2.

label: labial sensillum 2
description: One of the three labial sensilla located in the labial organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is innervated by one dendrite, similarly to labial sensillum 1.

label: adult fruitless pIP2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP2 lineage clone (FBbt:00110550).

label: adult fruitless pIP2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum. Neurites enter a tract in the medial posterior brain and project anteriorly behind the mushroom body lobes. The projections are likely to terminate in the lateral crescent and medial ring.

label: prothoracic basiconical sensillum dbd
description: Basiconic sensillum of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult MBp2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp2.

label: labial sensillum 3
description: One of the three labial sensilla located in the labial organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is innervated by three dendrites.

label: adult fruitless pIP4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP4 lineage clone (FBbt:00110556).

label: adult MBp4 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast MBp4 (FBbt:00110564).

label: adult MBp4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp4.

label: prothoracic dorsal triscolopidial chordotonal organ dch3
description: Triscolopidial chordotonal organ located in the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval prothoracic segment.

label: adult MBp3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp3.

label: adult MBp3 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast MBp3 (FBbt:00110561).

label: adult MBp2 lineage neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult brain (FBbt:00003624) and that develops from some neuroblast MBp2 (FBbt:00110558).

label: neuroblast X
description: Stage 3 neuroblast that expresses achaete (FBgn0000022).

label: adult anteriolateral neurosecretory cell
description: Neurosecretory cell of the adult pars lateralis that innervates the corpus cardiacum and aorta (Siegmund and Korge, 2001).

label: anteriolateral neurosecretory cell
description: Neurosecretory cell of the larval and adult pars lateralis.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron V adPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus V and projects to the anterior superior medial protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless pSP-e neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-e lineage clone (FBbt:00110532) and that develops from some neuroblast LHp2 (FBbt:00050139).

label: adult fruitless pSP-e lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHp2.

label: adult fruitless pSP-f lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl3.

label: T1 beard
description: Cluster of fine denticles found at the posterior edge of the ventral surface of the larval prothoracic (T1) segment.

label: adult fruitless pSP-d neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-d lineage clone (FBbt:00110530).

label: adult fruitless pSP-d lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl2.

label: prothoracic dorsal trichome
description: Any dorsal hair (FBbt:00004980) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: prothoracic ventral denticle belt
description: Any denticle belt (FBbt:00005201) that is part of some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).

label: neuroblast NB3-4
description: Neuroblast NB3-4 delaminates at S5. It produces a single motorneuron located on the posterior boundary of the clone and projects into the anterior root of the ISN by embryonic stage 15. Along with several local interneurons, it also produces at least 2 intersegmental interneurons by embryonic stage 17, one extending ipsilaterally, the other crossing the anterior commissure before extending anteriorly.

label: stage 5 neuroblast
description: A neuroblast delaminating in the fifth and final wave of neuroblast delamination from the ventral neurectoderm. This wave begins during embryonic in late stage 11. The S5 neuroblasts delaminate into columns in between the existing intermediate and lateral columns of neuroblasts (Doe, 1992).

label: neuroblast NB2-1
description: Neuroblast NB2-1 delaminates at S4 and generates approximately 9-15 local interneurons by embryonic stage 17. The fibers from these cells cross the midline via a single projection in a posterior fascicle of the anterior commissure. In the third instar larva, the lineage originated by this neuroblast is located near the midline on the anterior margin of the neuromere. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 2.

label: adult fruitless aDT4 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT4 lineage clone (FBbt:00110538).

label: adult fruitless aDT4 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located ventrolateral to the antennal lobe, usually away from the neuropil. Neurites project dorsally, fasciculating with the mediolateral antennal lobe tract until the fan-shaped body. It then makes a lateral dorsal turn. Neurites form web-like arborizations, likely to be axonal in the ipsi- and contralateral in the posterior region of the superior lateral and intermediate protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless aDT1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT1 lineage clone (FBbt:00110536).

label: adult fruitless aDT1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located dorsomedial to the antennal lobe. Neurites project bilaterally terminating with granular arborizations in the medial suboesophageal zone and in the ipsilateral dorsal medial protocerebrum.

label: larval mesothoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: neuroblast NB4-4
description: Neuroblast NB4-4 delaminates at S4. It generates a single motorneuron located at the posterior ventral boundary of the clone and projects into the anterior root of the ISN by stage 5. Amongst several local interneurons, it generates at least two intersegmental interneurons, one extending anterior ipsilaterally and the other crossing the anterior commissure. In the larva, it resumes proliferation in all thoracic segments. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 24, composed exclusively of motorneurons.

label: neuroblast NB5-4
description: Neuroblast NB5-4 most frequently delaminates at S4 in an intermediate column. In the third instar larva, the lineage originated by this neuroblast is located at the ventro-lateral region of the neuromere.

label: adult fruitless pSP-f neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-f lineage clone (FBbt:00110534) and that develops from some neuroblast LHl3 (FBbt:00050255).

label: adult fruitless aIP2 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites innervates a thin region in the lateral crescent.

label: adult fruitless aIP2 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP2 lineage clone (FBbt:00110544).

label: neuroblast NB4-3
description: Neuroblast NB4-3 delaminates at S5. It generates 2-3 neurosecretory cells that project together out of the CNS, appearing to join the transverse nerve in the periphery. In addition, 10-12 small, axonless interneurons are also produced at stage 17. In the larva, it resumes proliferation in all thoracic segments. The neurons that develop from this neuroblast form postembryonic lineage 21.

label: adult fruitless aDT8 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medially, between the antennal lobe and the subesophageal zone. A neurite forms dense bilateral arbors in the antennal lobe and the subesophageal zone. A major neurite exits the brain via the posterior subesophageal zone to terminate in the pro-, meso, and metathoracic neuromeres.

label: neuroblast NB5-1
description: Neuroblast NB5-1 delaminates at S5 in the medial column. It generates approximately 6-9 local interneurons that predominantly project across the posterior commissure (Schmid et al., 1999). This neuroblast does not seem to resume proliferation in the larva.

label: adult fruitless aDT8 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT8 lineage clone (FBbt:00110542).

label: neuroblast NB5-5
description: Neuroblast NB5-5 delaminates at S5. Thoracic and abdominal clones contain 8-11 large neurons including interneurons and neurosecretory cells. This neuroblast does not seem to resume proliferation in the larva.

label: adult fruitless aDT7 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located medioventral to the antennal lobe. A neurite projects through the oesophageal foramen posteriorly then ipsilaterally to form axonal arbors in the anterior dorsal region of the lobula. There is also arborization in the posterior brain.

label: adult fruitless aDT7 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aDT7 lineage clone (FBbt:00110540).

label: mesothoracic dorsal triscolopidial chordotonal organ dch3
description: Triscolopidial chordotonal organ located in the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: neuroblast NB2-3
description: Neuroblast NB2-3 delaminates at S5. It generates three large, round axonless cells at the dorsal side of the thoracic clones which are proposed by Schmid et al., (1999) to be latent leg motorneurons that will extend axons during leg disk eversion. It also generates 2-4 small interneurons at the ventral side of the clone. In the abdominal segments only a single large neuroblast is observed at embryonic stage 17, which either does not divide or all progeny die.

label: adult fruitless aSP13 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior inferior protocerebrum. Neurites project posteromedially arborizing in the superior intermediate and medial protocerebrum, and a discrete region at the medial terminal of the mushroom gamma lobes in both hemispheres.

label: adult fruitless aIP3 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites terminate in the ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless aIP3 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP3 lineage clone (FBbt:00110546).

label: posterior VUM precursor
description: The most posterior of the three VUM precursors, located anteriorly to the MNB neuroblast.

label: adult fruitless pMP-g neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-g lineage clone (FBbt:00110510).

label: adult fruitless pMP-g lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior medial protocerebrum.

label: larval metathoracic sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: adult fruitless pSG-a lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC1-1a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB1-1.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC2-5a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB2-5.

label: metathoracic dorsal sensillum campaniformium dc1
description: One of the three campaniformium sensilla of the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC3-2a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB3-2.

label: mid VUM precursor
description: The middle of the three VUM precursors, located in between the anterior and posterior VUM precursors.

label: mesothoracic dorsal trichome
description: Any dorsal hair (FBbt:00004980) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: anterior VUM precursor
description: The most anterior of the three VUM precursors, located posteriorly to the MP3 precursor.

label: mesothoracic ventral denticle belt
description: Any denticle belt (FBbt:00005201) that is part of some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).

label: germ band
description: The ventral, metameric region of the developing embryonic thorax and abdomen.

label: adult fruitless pSG-c neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG-c lineage clone (FBbt:00110516).

label: adult fruitless pSG-c lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

label: adult fruitless pSG-b neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG-b lineage clone (FBbt:00110514).

label: adult fruitless pSG-b lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC3-5a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB3-5.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC4-2a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB4-2.

label: adult fruitless pSG-a neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG-a lineage clone (FBbt:00110512).

label: ganglion mother cell GMC4-2b
description: Second born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB4-2.

label: metathoracic dorsal triscolopidial chordotonal organ dch3
description: Triscolopidial chordotonal organ located in the dorsal sensory cluster of the embryonic/larval metathoracic segment.

label: adult fruitless pSP-a lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPpd1.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC7-4a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB7-4.

label: adult fruitless pSP-a neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-a lineage clone (FBbt:00110522) and that develops from some neuroblast SMPpd1 (FBbt:00050021).

label: ganglion mother cell GMC7-4b
description: Second born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB7-4.

label: adult fruitless pSG-e lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior subesophageal ganglion.

label: adult fruitless pSG-e neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSG-e lineage clone (FBbt:00110520).

label: ganglion mother cell GMC5-2a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB5-2.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC5-2b
description: Second born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB5-2.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC5-6a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB5-6.

label: ganglion mother cell GMC6-2a
description: First born ganglion mother cell of neuroblast NB6-2.

label: adult fruitless aIP5 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites form a local arbor and then project dorsally.

label: adult fruitless aIP5 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless aIP5 lineage clone (FBbt:00110528).

label: adult fruitless pSP-c lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHp2.

label: pCC neuron
description: The pCC is an interneuron whose large, round cell body is located just posterior, medial and ventral to the MN-DA1 (aCC) motor neuron (FBbt:00001447). It extends a neurite anteriorly along one of the longitudinal fascicles (Doe et al., 1988).

label: adult fruitless pSP-c neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-c lineage clone (FBbt:00110526) and that develops from some neuroblast LHp2 (FBbt:00050139).

label: fpCC neuron
description: Interneuron that develops from neuroblast NB7-1. It projects anteriorly in a medial fascicle of the ipsilateral connective, then across the anterior commissure and then anteriorly in the contralateral connective. Its cell body is the most medial cell of this lineage clone.

label: adult fruitless pSP-b (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPpl1.

label: adult fruitless pSP-b (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pSP-b (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110524) and that develops from some neuroblast SLPpl1 (FBbt:00050228) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: metathoracic dorsal trichome
description: Any dorsal hair (FBbt:00004980) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: metathoracic ventral denticle belt
description: Any denticle belt (FBbt:00005201) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: segmental nerve pioneer neuron
description: Neuron that, along with one or two other neurons, pioneers the segmental nerve. The cell bodies of this cluster of 2-3 neurons are located posterior and slightly more lateral than the aCC and pCC neurons.

label: abdominal 3 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Small, mono-innervated hair of the dorsal sensory complex of larval abdominal segments 1-7.

label: RP neuron
description: Neuron of the embryonic/larval CNS. The RP neurons are mainly motor neurons. An RP motor neuron innervates each of muscles 2, 3, 6, 7, 11, 12, 13, 14, 19, 20, 28 and 30. RP2sib is the only RP neuron not to be a motor neuron.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: 1-1I
description: Ipsilaterally projecting interneuron developing from neuroblast NB1-1 segment specific lineages.

label: abdominal 1 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: RP2sib neuron
description: Neuron developing from GMC4-2a, the first born ganglion mother cell differentiating from neuroblast NB4-2 (Bhat et al., 1995). Its ultimate fate is unknown, but can be distinguished from its sibling motor neuron, RP2 (FBbt:00001453), by lower expression of markers such as the membrane protein recognized by monoclonal antibody 22C10, eve (FBgn0000606), or ftz (FBgn0001077).

label: 1-1I of thorax
description: Ipsilaterally projecting interneuron developing from neuroblast NB1-1 of the thorax.

label: abdominal 7 dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1
description: Any abdominal dorsal sensillum trichodeum dh1 (FBbt:00002783) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: 1-1I of abdomen
description: Ipsilaterally projecting interneuron developing from neuroblast NB1-1 of the abdomen.

label: 1-2I
description: Interneuron that develops from neuroblast NB1-2.

label: adult fruitless pMP-b (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM2.

label: 2-1I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-1 lineage.

label: adult fruitless pMP-b (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-b (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110500) and that develops from some neuroblast DM2 (FBbt:00050121) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: 2-1Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-1 lineage and that fasciculates with an ipsilaterally projecting bundle.

label: 2-1Ic
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-1 lineage and that projects through the anterior commissure.

label: 2-2I
description: Interneuron deriving from the neuroblast NB2-2 lineage.

label: 1-2Ii
description: Interneuron originating from neuroblast NB1-2 whose axon fasciculates with an ipsilaterally directed fascicle formed at the end of embryonic stage 16.

label: parasegment
description: Metameric unit of a Drosophila embryo whose boundaries are the compartment boundaries that run through the middle of adjacent segments, parallel to the segment boundaries.

label: embryonic tagma
description: Any tagma (FBbt:00000002) that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: 1-2Icp
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-1 lineage and that fasciculates with a contralaterally projecting bundle that projects through the posterior commissure of the neuromere.

label: 1-2Ica
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-1 lineage and that fasciculates with a contralaterally projecting bundle that projects through the anterior commissure of the adjacent neuromere before turning anteriorly.

label: adult fruitless pMP-f (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM6.

label: adult fruitless pMP-f (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-f (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110508) and that develops from some neuroblast DM6 (FBbt:00050142) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: adult fruitless pMP-e (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior medial protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless pMP-e (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-e (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110506) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: parasegment 1
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of the mandibular segment and the anterior compartment of the maxillary segment.

label: adult fruitless pMP-d lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior medial protocerebrum.

label: adult fruitless pMP-d neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-d lineage clone (FBbt:00110504).

label: adult fruitless pMP-c (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM4.

label: adult fruitless pMP-c (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pMP-c (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110502) and that develops from some adult DM4 lineage clone (FBbt:00050253) and that is part of some female organism (FBbt:00007011).

label: mesothoracic dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF
description: Multidendritic ddaF neuron of the dorsal sensory cluster in the embryonic/larval mesothoracic segment.

label: 2-2I of thorax
description: Interneuron that develops from NB2-1 of the thorax. These neurons form a fascicle of about 10 axons that projects contralaterally through the anterior commissure. Unlike the 2-2I of abdomen, the 2-2I fascicle of thorax does not turn anteriorly after reaching the contralateral connective.

label: 2-2I of abdomen
description: Interneuron that develops from the NB2-1 of the neuroblast of the abdomen. Projections from these neurons form a fascicle that projects through the anterior commissure and then turns anteriorly after reaching the contralateral connective.

label: 2-4I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-4 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord.

label: parasegment 3
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of the labial segment and the anterior compartment of thoracic segment 1 .

label: parasegment 2
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of the maxillary segment and the anterior compartment of the labial segment.

label: 2-5Ic1
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects contralaterally across the anterior commissure and anteriorly to the next segment.

label: 2-5I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord.

label: parasegment 7
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 1 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 2.

label: parasegment 6
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of thoracic segment 3 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 1.

label: 2-5Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects ipsilaterally and anteriorly to the next segment.

label: parasegment 5
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of thoracic segment 2 and the anterior compartment of thoracic segment 3 .

label: 3-1I
description: Interneuron deriving from the neuroblast NB3-1 lineage.

label: parasegment 4
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of thoracic segment 1 and the anterior compartment of thoracic segment 2 .

label: 2-4I of thorax
description: Interneuron that develops from the NB2-4 neuroblast in the embryonic thorax. It projects ipsilaterally across.

label: parasegment 11
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 5 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 6.

label: parasegment 10
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 4 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 5.

label: 2-4I of abdomen
description: Interneuron that develops from the NB2-4 neuroblast in the embryonic abdomen. It projects ipsi- and contralaterally across the anterior commissure to exit the neuromere through the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve.

label: parasegment 9
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 3 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 4.

label: 2-5Ic
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB2-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects contralaterally across the anterior commissure.

label: parasegment 8
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 2 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 3.

label: 3-1I of thorax
description: Interneuron that develops from neuroblast NB3-1 of the thorax. The projections of these interneurons form a fascicle that projects through the anterior commissure. Unlike the fascicle formed by abdominal 3-1I, it does not show any appreciable bifurcation in the contralateral connective.

label: 3-1I of abdomen
description: Interneuron that develops from neuroblast NB3-1 of the abdomen 3-1I. The projections of these interneurons form a fascicle that projects through the anterior commissure and bifurcates in an anterior-posterior direction along the contralateral connective.

label: 3-2I
description: Interneuron derived from the neuroblast NB3-2 lineage. There are only one or two of these per lineage. Their fibers project contralaterally.

label: 3-3I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB3-3 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord.

label: parasegment 14
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 8 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 9.

label: parasegment 13
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 7 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 8.

label: parasegment 12
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 6 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 7.

label: 3-5Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB3-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects ipsilaterally, extending anteriorly more than one segment.

label: 3-5I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB3-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord.

label: embryonic ocular segment
description: Any ocular segment (FBbt:00000005) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: 4-1I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB4-1 lineage.

label: embryonic segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: parasegment 15
description: Embryonic metameric unit comprising the posterior compartment of abdominal segment 9 and the anterior compartment of abdominal segment 10.

label: 3-3Ic
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB3-3 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects contralaterally across the anterior commissure.

label: 3-3Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB3-3 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects ipsilaterally.

label: embryonic head segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: 3-5Ic
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB3-5 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects contralaterally across the anterior commissure, extending anteriorly more than one segment.

label: 4-1Ica
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB4-1 lineage whose projections form a bundle that projects contralaterally projecting via the anterior commissure.

label: 4-1Icp
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB4-1 lineage whose projections form a bundle that projects contralaterally projecting via the posterior commissure. This fascicle develops during mid to late embryonic stage 16.

label: 4-2I
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB4-2 lineage. These project contralaterally via the anterior commissure.

label: 4-4I
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB4-4 lineage in the embryonic ventral nerve cord and projects contralaterally across the anterior commissure, extending anteriorly more than one segment. There are 8 to 11 neurons.

label: embryonic gnathal segment
description: Any gnathal segment (FBbt:00000011) that is part of some embryonic head (FBbt:00000155).

label: 4-1Ii
description: Interneuron that develops from the neuroblast NB4-1 lineage whose projections form a bundle that projects ipsilaterally and anteriorly.

label: 5-2Icp
description: Interneuron derived from the NB5-2 lineage and whose projections form a prominent bundle that runs through the posterior commissure.

label: 5-2I
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB5-2 lineage.

label: 5-1I
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB5-1 lineage. These neurons form a bundle that projects contralaterally through the posterior commissure.

label: 5-2Ica1
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB5-2 lineage whose projections form a bundle that projects through the anterior commissure, along its anterior border and immediately turns anteriorly upon reaching the contralateral connective.

label: 5-2Ica2
description: Interneuron originating from the neuroblast NB5-2 that projects along the posterior of the border of the anterior commissure.

label: thermoception
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a temperature stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Thermoception in larger animals is mainly done in the skin; mammals have at least two types of sensor, for detecting heat (temperatures above body temperature) and cold (temperatures below body temperature).

label: detection of temperature stimulus
description: The series of events in which a temperature stimulus (hot or cold) is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: sensory perception of temperature stimulus
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory temperature stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: detection of mechanical stimulus
description: The series of events by which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: sensory perception of touch
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a touch stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process. The perception of touch in animals is mediated by mechanoreceptors in the skin and mucous membranes and is the sense by which contact with objects gives evidence as to certain of their qualities. Different types of touch can be perceived (for example, light, coarse, pressure and tickling) and the stimulus may be external or internal (e.g. the feeling of a full stomach).

label: equilibrioception
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive an orientational stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Equilibrioception refers to a combination of processes by which an organism can perceive its orientation with respect to gravity. In animals, stimuli come from labyrinth system of the inner ears, monitoring the direction of motion; visual stimuli, with information on orientation and motion; pressure receptors, which tell the organism which body surfaces are in contact with the ground; and proprioceptive cues, which report which parts of the body are in motion.
synonyms: sensory perception of orientation with respect to gravity

label: embryonic telson
description: Any telson (FBbt:00000033) that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: embryonic abdominal segment 11
description: Any abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00000032) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (FBbt:00000171).

label: embryonic abdominal segment 10
description: Any abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00000031) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (FBbt:00000171).

label: mesothoracic tracheal pit
description: Tracheal pit of the second thoracic segment of the embryo. During stages 14-15, the pit fuses with special cells of the prothorax to give rise to the anterior spiracle.

label: posterior spiracle primordium
description: Primordium of the posterior spiracle of the larva. Originates in the posterior half of the lateral ectoderm of abdominal segment 8 during stage 12. A a group of cells that are more basophilic that those surrounding them form a deep groove and fuse with the posterior arm of the tracheal primordium of A8 (tracheal metamere 10).

label: neuromuscular process controlling balance
description: Any process that an organism uses to control its balance, the orientation of the organism (or the head of the organism) in relation to the source of gravity. In humans and animals, balance is perceived through visual cues, the labyrinth system of the inner ears and information from skin pressure receptors and muscle and joint receptors.

label: abdominal segment 1 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022).

label: abdominal segment 1 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00000022).

label: left pb-fb tract W
description: Tract that connects the left protocerebral bridge glomeruli 7 and 8 to segment H of the fan-shaped body.

label: ion transport
description: The directed movement of charged atoms or small charged molecules into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: abdominal segment 10 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00000031).

label: abdominal segment 10 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00000031).

label: abdominal segment 2 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023).

label: abdominal segment 5 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026).

label: abdominal segment 6 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027).

label: abdominal segment 4 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025).

label: abdominal segment 5 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00000026).

label: abdominal segment 3 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024).

label: abdominal segment 4 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00000025).

label: abdominal segment 2 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00000023).

label: abdominal segment 3 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00000024).

label: abdominal segment 6 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00000027).

label: abdominal segment 7 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028).

label: abdominal segment 7 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000028).

label: maxillary segment anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some maxillary segment (FBbt:00000013).

label: maxillary segment posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some maxillary segment (FBbt:00000013).

label: mandibular segment anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some mandibular segment (FBbt:00000012).

label: mandibular segment posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some mandibular segment (FBbt:00000012).

label: abdominal segment 9 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00000030).

label: abdominal segment 9 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00000030).

label: abdominal segment 8 anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00000029).

label: abdominal segment 8 posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00000029).

label: serotonin transport
description: The directed movement of serotonin into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine) is a monoamine neurotransmitter occurring in the peripheral and central nervous systems.

label: labial segment posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some labial segment (FBbt:00000014).

label: prothoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000017).

label: labial segment anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some labial segment (FBbt:00000014).

label: metathoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some metathoracic segment (FBbt:00000019).

label: mesothoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000018).

label: metathoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some metathoracic segment (FBbt:00000019).

label: prothoracic segment posterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment posterior compartment (FBbt:00111532) that is part of some prothoracic segment (FBbt:00000017).

label: mesothoracic segment anterior compartment
description: Any embryonic segment anterior compartment (FBbt:00111533) that is part of some mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00000018).

label: dorsal-ventral compartment boundary of the wing disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the wing pouch into dorsal and ventral compartments. This boundary corresponds to the wing margin in the adult. It arises during the third instar stage.

label: anterior-posterior compartment boundary of the wing disc
description: A compartment boundary that divides the wing pouch into anterior and posterior compartments.

label: anterior midgut primordium
description: The primordium that will develop into the anterior midgut of both larva and adult. This forms during stage 8 when anterior endoderm cells, which have invaginated at the anterior end of the ventral furrow, divide and undergo an epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition. During stage 9, its cells divide a second time. During stage 10, the primordium attaches to the internal end of the stomodeum and spreads posteriorly with the stomodeal invagination, splitting into two lobes extending on either side of the yolk sac. A separate group of cells fuse with this primordium during stage 11. These cells delaminate from the stomodeum, becoming mesenchymal and mingling with the existing cells of the primordium. Fate mapping suggests that these cells will form the anterior-most part of the midgut, including the gastric caeca (Technau and Campos-Ortega, 1985). Adult midgut progenitors separate from the primordium during late stage 11 and stage 12. The remaining cells reorganize to become epithelial plates which then begin to fuse with the posterior midgut primordium during stage 12, forming the fused midgut primordium.

label: prosternal nerve
description: A slender nerve that projects anteriorly from the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, near the base of the dorsal prothoracic nerve (FBbt:00004055) to innervate the prosternal sense organ.

label: prosternal sense organ
description: A sense organ located in a pit in the anterior wall of the thorax - immediately under the neck. It consists of a plate of sensory hairs whose innervating neurons have their cell bodies in a small ganglion behind the organ and project through the prosternal nerve to the prothoracic neuromere.

label: prothoracic leg nerve
description: A nerve that connects carries a mix of motor and sensory fibres from the prothoracic leg to the adult prothoracic neuromere. Each nerve extends laterally and slightly anteriorly from a slight swelling at the lower anterior corner of the ventral-anterior region of the prothoracic neuromere.

label: anterior prothoracic chordotonal organ
description: A chordotonal organ of the adult prothorax with a V-shape in which the two arms are opened widely. One arm is attached to the anterior wall of the thorax at the articulation with the head, immediately below the prosternal sense organ (FBbt:00007655). The other arm is attached to the hypotremal apodeme and the angle between the two arms is pressed against the anterolateral corner of the prothoracic neuromere, immediately below the dorsal prothoracic and prosternal nerves. A thick, short group of fibers, the anterior prothoracic chordotonal nerve, connect this organ to the thoracico-abdominal ganglion (prothoracic neuromere).

label: proximal joint of metathoracic coxa
description: A joint between the proximal end of the metathoracic coxa and the body of the metathoracic segment. This joint is located ventrally. Unlike the pro- and mesothoracic legs, there are two of these joints per metathoracic leg.

label: presumptive proximal joint of metathoracic coxa
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the proximal joint of metathoracic coxa.

label: proximal joint of mesothoracic coxa
description: The joint between the proximal end of the mesothoracic coxa and the mesothoracic episternum or katepisternum. The fossa (socket) of this joint is part of the katepisternum. The condyle (ball) is part of the coxa. This joint is located ventrally.

label: presumptive proximal joint of mesothoracic coxa
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the proximal joint of mesothoracic coxa.

label: mesothoracic coxa-trochanter joint
description: The joint between the distal end of the mesothoracic coxa and the proximal end of the trochanter. The fossa (socket) of this joint is part of the coxa. The condyle (ball) is part of trochanter.

label: presumptive mesothoracic coxa-trochanter joint
description: Region of the mesothoracic leg disc that will develop into the mesothoracic coxa-trochanter joint.

label: proximal joint of prothoracic coxa
description: The joint between the proximal end of the prothoracic coxa and the body of the prothoracic segment. The fossa (socket) of this joint is part of the coxa. The condyle (ball) is part of the body.

label: prothoracic coxa-trochanter joint
description: The joint between the distal end of the prothoracic coxa and the proximal end of the trochanter. This joint is located dorsally, with the fossa (socket) of being part of the coxa and the condyle (ball) part of trochanter.

label: presumptive prothoracic coxa-trochanter joint
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic coxa-trochanter joint.

label: metathoracic coxa-trochanter joint
description: A joint between the distal end of the prothoracic coxa and the proximal end of the trochanter.

label: presumptive metathoracic coxa-trochanter joint
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic coxa-trochanter joint.

label: prothoracic ventral eclosion muscle
description: A muscle of the prothorax that forms a broad attachment onto the lateral region of the sternal apodeme and extends towards the neck. It dies within 24 hours of eclosion and (probably) function in the thoracic contractions that are part of eclosion behavior.

label: cell body rind of posterior superior medial protocerebrum
description: Region of the cell body rind that overlies the posterior superior medial protocerebrum.

label: antennal nerve branch
description: One of the terminal branches of the antennal nerve in the antenna. One branch goes to the Johnston's organ in the second antennal segment. In the third antennal segment, the nerve splits into 3 major branches, which further ramify to innervate the external sensory organs of this segment.

label: anterior spiracle primordium
description: Primordium of the anterior spiracle of the larva. Originates in the posterior third of the lateral ectoderm of the prothoracic segment during stage 14. A group of cells that are more basophilic than those surrounding them fuse with the tracheal pit of the mesothoracic segment (tracheal metamere 1).

label: sensory perception of wind
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive sensory mechanical stimulus resulting from air flow, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal.

label: amnioserosa anlage
description: Anlage of the amnioserosa in the gastrula embryo that will give rise to the amnioserosa primordium.

label: tracheal metamere
description: Segmental subdivision of the tracheal system. The most anterior tracheal metamere corresponds to the mesothoracic segment, whereas the most posterior corresponds to abdominal segment 8.

label: embryonic primordium of adult posterior midgut
