description: An embryonic primordium that consists of the progenitors of the adult posterior midgut from the time of their segregation from the anterior midgut inclusive primordium during late embryonic stage 11 and early stage 12 until they intercalate into the posterior midgut epithelium during stage 15.

label: sensory perception of taste
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a gustatory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Gustation involves the direct detection of chemical composition, usually through contact with chemoreceptor cells. This is a neurological process.

label: tracheocyte
description: Epithelial cell of the tracheal epithelium.

label: embryonic/larval tracheocyte
description: Any tracheocyte (FBbt:00005038) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727) and that is part of some embryo (FBbt:00000052).

label: oenocyte primordium
description: A 'whorl' of larval oenocyte precursors which forms transiently around each 'chordotonal precursor cell C1' during stage 11. It ceases to exist when these cells delaminate during stages 11 and 12.

label: taenidium
description: A thread-like cuticular substructure that runs along the length a taenidial fold, just below the surface of the tracheal lumen.

label: taenidial fold
description: A specialization of the cuticular lining of the trachea consisting of annular or helical ridges that project into the tracheal lumen (their precise pattern varies along trachea). They prevent the collapse of branches while allowing them to expand and contract along their length, like the corrugated hose of a vacuum cleaner.

label: mestracheon
description: Membrane that surrounds some tracheoles, separating them from the cytoplasm of the surrounding tracheolar cell.

label: tracheal precursor cell
description: Somatic cell that gives rise to a tracheoblast. At embryonic stage 10 the tracheal precursor cells form ectodermal placodes that invaginate to form the tracheal pits by early stage 11.

label: adult tracheocyte
description: Any tracheocyte (FBbt:00005038) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004).

label: tracheal node cell
description: Specialized tracheocyte found at tracheal nodes. These cells play a critical role in fragmentation of the tracheal cuticle during moults and in remodelling of the tracheal epithelium during metamorphosis.

label: gastric caecum primordium
description: Primordium of the gastric caecum of the larva. There are four of these per midgut. They first become apparent as evaginations at the anterior end of the fused midgut primordium during stage 16.

label: embryonic primordium of adult anterior midgut
description: An embryonic primordium that consists of the progenitors of the adult anterior midgut from the time of their segregation from the anterior midgut inclusive primordium during late embryonic stage 11 and early stage 12 until they intercalate into the anterior midgut epithelium during stage 15.

label: tracheal tip cell
description: Cell at the tip of a developing trachea. There are two types: tracheal or terminal cells.

label: abdominal 5 larval oenocyte group
description: Any abdominal larval oenocyte group (FBbt:00001695) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal larval oenocyte group
description: A cluster of 4-9 larval oenocytes situated bilaterally in each of abdominal segments 1-7 in a space between the dorsoventral muscles and the body wall. Each cell group is closely associated with an 'abdominal lateral pentascolopidial chordotonal organ lch5' and is supplied by its own tracheal branch.

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 1
description: Most anterior region of the larval fat body. It is of triangular shape and located over the brain.

label: embryonic/larval fat body
description: Fat body of the embryo/larva.

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 2'
description: Region of the larval fat body, posterior to region 1. It consists of a descending band of cells extending over the salivary gland that joins with a ventral commissure that connects to the two main lateral sheets of the fat body. There are two of these similar branches per larvae (2' and 2'').

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 2''
description: Region of the larval fat body, posterior to region 1. It consists of a descending band of cells extending over the salivary gland that joins with a ventral commissure that connects to the two main lateral sheets of the fat body. There are two of these similar branches per larvae (2' and 2'').

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 3'
description: Region of the larval fat body, dorsal and posterior to the ventral commissure that connects to the two main lateral sheets of the fat body.

label: abdominal 6 larval oenocyte group
description: Any abdominal larval oenocyte group (FBbt:00001695) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 larval oenocyte group
description: Any abdominal larval oenocyte group (FBbt:00001695) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: embryonic/larval adipose system
description: Adipose system of the embryo/larva.

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 3''
description: Region of the larval fat body, ventral and posterior to the ventral commissure that connects to the two main lateral sheets of the fat body.

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 4
description: Region of the larval fat body, posterior to regions 3' and 3'', and anterior to the gonad.

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 5
description: Region of the larval fat body, posterior to region 4 and to the gonad.

label: corpus allatum primordium
description: The primordium that will form the embryonic/larval corpus allatum, a substructure of the embryonic/larval ring gland. It is a paired structure that becomes distinct in early dorsal closure between the head mesoderm and the epidermis of the gnathal segments. During dorsal closure the paired primordia move dorsally to meet and fuse above the cardioblasts of the developing aorta.

label: corpus cardiacum primordium
description: The corpora cardiaca precursor first appear during stage 10 as two pairs of head mesoderm cells between the roof of the stomodeum and the inner surface of the brain primordium that derive from the anterior lip of the ventral furrow. Between stages 11 and 15, these cells migrate posteriorly, gradually increasing in number. During stage 15, they fuse with the precursors of the corpus allatum from the gnathal mesoderm to form the ring gland.

label: retrocerebral complex
description: The larval endocrine complex which consists of the corpus cardiacum and corpus allatum (Hartenstein, 2006).

label: embryonic/larval fat body region 6
description: Region of the larval fat body, that runs parallel to the heart and the tracheal trunks and dorsal to the gonad.

label: anterior fat body plate
description: Horizontal plate of the embryonic fat body from stage 13 that is located anteriorly, beneath the foregut.

label: posterior fat body plate
description: Horizontal plate of the embryonic fat body from stage 13 that is located posteriorly, beneath the hindgut.

label: larval tagma
description: Any tagma (FBbt:00000002) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: larval segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some larva (FBbt:00001727).

label: larval procephalic segment
description: Any procephalic segment (FBbt:00000007) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: larval head segment
description: Any segment (FBbt:00000003) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: lateroposterior branch
description: Thin, ventro-posteriorly directed branch from the posterior of the lateral trunk in tracheal metamere 10 (A8).

label: ventral cephalic branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches anteriorly from the lateral trunk, just ventral to the lateral cephalic branch. At the end of stage 16 there are typically ten or more branches that target the epidermis and muscles of the head.

label: cephalic branch
description: Embryonic/larval branch of the first tracheal metamere the tracheates the head but not (largely) the brain or foregut.

label: embryonic/larval spiracle
description: Spiracle of the embryo or larva. In the latter, there are 10 pairs of spiracles, but only the most posterior is functional at all larval instars. The anterior spiracle becomes functional at the second larval stage.

label: hindgut branch
description: Primary trachea that arises as a posterior bifurcation of the caudal-hindgut branch of tracheal metamere 10 (A8) and ramifies into four or more branches on the surface of the hindgut.

label: caudal-hindgut branch
description: Primary trachea that branches from the point where the lateral trunk meets the transverse connective of tracheal metamere 10 (A8).

label: caudal branch
description: Primary trachea that arises as a posterior bifurcation of the caudal-hindgut branch of tracheal metamere 10 (A8) and splits into 4 branches that project posteriorly.

label: anterior spiracular gland
description: A mass of about 30-50 polytene cells located in the protrusion of the prothoracic segment that houses the anterior spiracle of the larva. During the second instar, it is linked by ducts to the lobes of the anterior spiracle.

label: embryonic/larval anterior spiracle
description: Embryonic/larval spiracle housed in a protrusion of the prothoracic segment. These spiracles only become functional in the second instar when the spiracle has a club-like structure with eight lobes. A fine thread from the anterior spiracular gland is associated with each of the lobes. Late in the second instar, 8 protruding branches (papillae) develop around this club like structure, these become the spiracular ducts of the third instar spiracle, each with a spiracular opening.

label: papilla of larval anterior spiracle
description: Retractable finger of the anterior spiracle of the third instar larva. Each has a spiracular opening and serves as a spiracular duct. There are 8 of these per spiracle: 4 long and 4 short.

label: non-functional larval spiracle of thoracic segment
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval thoracic segment (FBbt:00001742).

label: non-functional larval spiracle
description: Spiracle that only opens during moulting, allowing ejection of the chitinous lining of or the trachea of the previous instar. The rest of the time, these are only identifiable as a thickening of the cuticle. During larval stages, the spiracles of tracheal metameres 2-9 are all of this type.

label: anterior spiracular scar
description: Cuticular scar associated with the anterior spiracle that is a remnant of moulting.

label: anterior spiracle retractor muscle
description: Muscle of the anterior spiracle of the embryo or larva that pulls the spiracle back into the body.

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 1
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment (FBbt:00001747).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of thoracic segment 3
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 3
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 2
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 4
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: embryonic/larval posterior spiracle
description: The main spiracle of the larva on the dorsal side of the eight (last) abdominal segment. During the first larval instar it is the only functional spiracle of the larva. A bilateral pair of these spiracles is housed in a bilateral pair of integumentary specializations - the stigmatophores. Each consists of a plate containing the spiracular openings. These connect to a spiracular chamber which in turn connects to the posterior end of the dorsal trunk. In the second instar there are three ovoid openings on the stigmatic plate and four alternating tufts of slightly branched hairs. In the third instar, the spiracles are somewhat larger and the hairs more markedly branched.

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 7
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 6
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 5
description: Any non-functional larval spiracle (FBbt:00000412) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: spiracular opening
description: Opening of the embryonic/larval posterior spiracles spiracular chamber to the exterior.

label: spiracular plate
description: Sclerotized plate of the embryonic/larval posterior spiracle containing the spiracular openings.

label: spiracular chamber
description: Epithelial tube that connects the spiracular branch 10 derived from the dorsal trunk to the embryonic/larval posterior spiracle. At one end, it is lined with cuticular threads call filzkorper, covered in oily secretions from the spiracular gland. At the other end, the chamber divides into 3 flattened branches that terminate at the surface as three major spiracular openings.

label: larval telson
description: Any telson (FBbt:00000033) that is part of some larval abdomen (FBbt:00001746).

label: posterior spiracular scar
description: Deformation in the spiracular plate that is a remnant of molting.

label: peripodial epithelium
description: A squamous epithelium that makes up one side of the epithelial sac of which each imaginal disc consists. The anterior-posterior compartment boundary of each disc runs through the middle of this epithelium. During the third larval instar stage, the cells in this epithelium send out long processes, known as lumenal extensions, which contact cells of the disc epithelium proper.

label: spiracular filament
description: Cuticular filament that connects the spiracular scar to the base of the spiracular chamber in the larval posterior spiracle during the second and third instars. It is a remnant of the expulsion of the spiracular cuticle during molting.

label: labial disc primordium
description: Primordium that will form the labial disc.

label: eye-antennal disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the eye-antennal disc develops.

label: posterior spiracular gland
description: Spiracular gland of the posterior spiracle. It is a single, elongated and club-shaped cell with a polytene nucleus. It has an efferent duct leading to a very small opening in the spiracular plate near the outer edge of the spiracular opening. There are three of these glands per spiracle.

label: filzkorper
description: Fine cuticular thread that lines the spiracular chamber.

label: prepupa
description: The prepupa is the name given to the organism at the period of the life cycle that begins at puparium formation and ends when larval/pupal apolysis is complete, as indicated by the completion of imaginal head sac eversion and the expulsion of the oral armature of the larva. Duration at 25 degrees C is approximately 12 hours. It occurs 120-132.2 hours after egg laying, and is the period of 0-12.2 hours after puparium formation.

label: posterior spiracle retractor muscle
description: Muscle of the posterior spiracle of the embryo or larva that pulls the spiracle back into the body.

label: posterior spiracular gland ductule
description: Small cuticle-lined ducts found in the cytoplasm of the gland cell of the posterior spiracle. The ductules fuse to form the main spiracular duct.

label: posterior spiracular duct
description: Duct that connects the spiracular gland of the posterior spiracle to a very small opening in the spiracular plate near the outer edge of the spiracular opening. There are three spiracular glands per spiracle.

label: morphogenetic furrow
description: A furrow in the eye disc, caused by apical constriction of cells in the developing eye disc epithelium, in which the assembly of ommatidia begins.

label: adult midgut region R2c
description: Subregion at the posterior of the adult midgut region R2. It is composed of enterocytes containing less lipid vesicles than in regions R2a or R2b, with a typical columnar morphology, and with cells not as long in R2a or R2b.

label: adult midgut region R2
description: Region of the adult midgut located in the abdomen that is dorsally located and that falls back ventrally at the posterior part. It can be divided into 3 subregions, based on histology and gene expression. It is composed of enterocytes with a typical columnar morphology.

label: two cone-cell ommatidial precursor cluster
description: Ommatidial precursor cluster composed of eight future photoreceptors and two cone cell precursors. The two cone-cell ommatidial precursor stage is defined by the apical arrival of the nuclei of R7 and the anterior and posterior cone-cells. The nuclei of R1 and R6 are displaced basally. R4 loses its apical contact with R8, and R3 contacts R5 (Cohen, 1993).

label: mature eight-cell ommatidial precursor cluster
description: Ommatidial precursor cluster composed of eight future photoreceptors. The nuclei of R8, R2 and R5 are displaced basally compared to the immature eight cell precursor clusters, whereas R7's nucleus is still ascending. The bilateral symmetry of the ommatidium is prominent at this stage. The apical processes of the cells that will become the anterior and posterior cone cells occupy their definitive niches, contacting R2 and R5, respectively (Cohen, 1993).

label: adult midgut region R3
description: Region of the adult midgut that contains the copper cells. This region initiates a retrograde folding of the midgut, (from posterior to anterior), and it follows a ventral-dorsal axis. It can be subdivided into an anterior section containing the copper cells (R3ab) and a posterior one with large flat cells (R3c).

label: adult midgut region
description: Region of the adult midgut. There are 5 regions with distinct histology, delimited by six constrictions.

label: four cone-cell ommatidial precursor cluster
description: Ommatidial precursor cluster composed of eight future photoreceptors and four cone cell precursors. The four cone-cell ommatidial precursor cluster is achieved with the apical arrival of the nuclei of the polar and equatorial cone cells that have risen over future photoreceptors R3 and R4 on the polar side and R7 on the equatorial side. At this stage all nuclei are displaced basally. R8 begins to move anteriorly squeezing between R1 and R2, where it will remain through adult life (Cohen, 1993).

label: adult midgut region R2a
description: Subregion at the anterior end of the adult midgut region R2. It is composed of enterocytes containing lipid vesicles with an apical extrusion and a typical columnar morphology. It is distinguished from region R2b by gene expression.

label: proctodeum
description: The posterior part of the alimentary canal deriving from the amnioproctodeal invagination of the ectoderm.

label: adult midgut region R2b
description: Subregion at the middle of the adult midgut region R2. It is composed of enterocytes containing lipid vesicles with an apical extrusion and a typical columnar morphology. It is distinguished from region R2a by gene expression.

label: adult midgut region R1b
description: Subregion at the posterior end of the adult midgut region R1. It is composed of long enterocytes, with an extended labyrinth and a highly folded lumen.

label: adult midgut region R1
description: Region of the adult midgut located in the thorax. It ends at a position that corresponds to an anatomical hub where the midgut, the crop, and the Malpighian tubules physically interact. It can be subdivided into 2 subregions: R1a, composed of flat enterocytes, and R1b composed of long folded enterocytes.

label: five-cell ommatidial precursor cluster
description: Ommatidial precursor cluster composed of five prospective photoreceptors: R8, R2, R5, R3 and R4. This precursor cluster is formed when the mystery cells leave the cluster to rejoin the surrounding, unpatterned epithelium. The nuclei of the remaining cells rise apically whereas the nuclei of the surrounding cells descend.

label: immature eight-cell ommatidial precursor cluster
description: Ommatidial precursor cluster composed of eight future photoreceptors. It forms when the precursors of photoreceptors of R1, R7 and R6 form during the second mitotic wave and join the cluster. The nuclei of these newly joined cells begin to climb apically, with R7 lagging behind R1 and R6.

label: adult midgut region R1a
description: Subregion at the anterior end of the adult midgut region R1. It is composed of flat enterocytes, a large lumen and a multilayered peritrophic membrane.

label: adult salivary gland anlage
description: Primordium of the late extended germ band embryo that will give rise to the embryonic primordium of the adult salivary gland.

label: adult midgut anterior region R3a
description: Subregion at the anterior end of the adult midgut region R3. It is composed of copper cells (cuprophilic cells) interspersed with interstitial cells. The posterior region R3b is distinguishable from R3a by gene expression.

label: adult midgut anterior region R3b
description: Subregion at the middle zone of the adult midgut region R3. It is composed of copper cells (cuprophilic cells) interspersed with interstitial cells. The anterior region R3a is distinguishable from R3b by gene expression.

label: male genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the male genital disc derives.

label: midgut chamber 1
description: Anterior-most chamber of the embryonic midgut. The posterior boundary of this chamber results from the formation of the midgut constriction 1 in early stage 16.

label: female repressed primordium
description: Region of the female genital disc that corresponds to the male repressed primordium. It is located at the thickened anterior and lateral regions of the dorsal epithelium. It does not give rise to any adult structures.

label: female genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the female genital disc derives.

label: male repressed primordium
description: Region of the male genital disc that corresponds to the female repressed primordium. It is located at the thickened posterior part of the ventral epithelium. It does not give rise to any adult structures.

label: midgut constriction
description: Constriction forming in the embryonic midgut between stage 15 and 16 caused by contraction of the mesoderm which, as a result, penetrates the underlying endoderm.

label: midgut chamber 4
description: Posterior-most chamber of the embryonic midgut. The anterior boundary of this chamber forms from the midgut constriction 3.

label: midgut chamber 3
description: Second posterior-most chamber of the embryonic midgut. The anterior boundary of this chamber forms from the midgut constriction 2, and the posterior from the midgut constriction 3.

label: genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the genital disc develops.

label: midgut chamber 2
description: Second anterior-most chamber of the embryonic midgut. The anterior boundary of this chamber forms from the midgut constriction 1, and the posterior boundary from the midgut constriction 2.

label: midgut constriction 2
description: First of the midgut constrictions to form. At stage 15 this constriction forms in the middle position of the midgut close to the anterior bend of the hindgut.

label: midgut constriction 1
description: Third, and final, of the midgut constrictions to form, doing so during early stage 16 anterior to the midgut constriction 2.

label: histoblast
description: A progenitor of the adult external abdomen.

label: midgut constriction 3
description: Second of the midgut constrictions to form, doing so during early stage 16 posterior to midgut constriction 2.

label: inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum local IVLP neuron
description: Neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the ventrolateral protocerebrum and innervates the unilateral inferior ventrolateral protocerebrum (IVLP) (Lai et al., 2012).

label: embryonic/larval somatic muscle
description: Any somatic muscle (FBbt:00005073) that is part of some embryonic/larval muscle system (FBbt:00000462).

label: peripheral cell
description: A cell in the larval midgut and early pupal midgut that extends its processes around the midgut imaginal islands. These cells are formed at late second larval instar, usually by the first asymmetric division of one adult midgut precursor cell (AMP). There is usually one peripheral cell by imaginal island. These cells undergo apoptosis shortly after pupariation (0-2h APF) and do not contribute to the adult midgut. Peripheral cells act as a niche for AMPs to keep them undifferentiated until metamorphosis.

label: small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 2
small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal
apterous-expressing neuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax
description: Interneuron of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax that is part of a cluster of four neurons. It is only found in the thoracic hemisegments and expresses apterous (FBgn0000099). There are four different neuron types: Ap1, Ap2, Ap3 and Ap4. These neurons are born at the end of the lineage of NB5-6T, with Ap1 generated at stage 13, followed by Ap2, Ap3 and Ap4. The 4 neurons are generated directly from the neuroblast, without a ganglion mother cell intermediate.

label: antennal mechanosensory and motor center local AMMC anterolateral neuron
description: Neuron whose cell body is located in the cell body rind of the anteroventral region of the gnathal region. The primary neurite extends anteriomedially and turns sharply to form predominantly postsynaptic sites in the ipsilateral zone B and both post- and presynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral zone D of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC). It is a GABAergic neuron.

label: small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 3
apterous-expressing neuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax Ap2
description: Interneuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax. It expresses apterous (FBgn0000099). It is the second neuron of the cluster to be generated, after the Ap1 neuron. It is not a peptidergic neuron.

label: apterous-expressing neuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax Ap3
description: Interneuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax. It expresses apterous (FBgn0000099). It is the third neuron of the cluster to be generated, after the Ap2 neuron. It is not a peptidergic neuron.

label: small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 1
longitudinal glial cell
description: Interface glial cell located that are derived from longitudinal glioblasts and at early stages are found above the longitudinal connectives. At stage 14, 5 or 6 of the 7 or 8 interface glia (IG) cells above the longitudinal connectives (per hemineuromere) are longitudinal glia. At late embryonic stage 16 (close to the end of the migration of the lateral and ventral IG) and first instar, longitudinal glia comprises the two lateral, the one ventral and 2 to 3 of the 5 dorsal IG cells.

label: GPA2/GPB5 neuron
description: Neuron that expresses the heterodimer formed by Gpa2 (FBgn0261386) and Gpb5 (FBgn0063368).

label: adult lateral horn type I neuron
description: Neuron of the adult lateral horn that has dendrites in the lateral horn and projects to the superior medial protocerebrum and whose cell body is dorsomedial to the lateral horn. These neurons are activated by olfactory stimuli of a broad range and receive input from the antennal lobe projection neurons DM1 lPN, DM2 lPN and DM4 adPN.

label: adult lateral horn type II neuron
description: Neuron of the adult lateral horn that has dendrites in the dorsolateral lateral horn and projects to the superior lateral protocerebrum and whose cell body is anterior and ventrolateral to the lateral horn. These neurons are activated by olfactory stimuli of a more selective range than lateral horn type I, and receive input from the antennal lobe projection neuron DP1m adPN.

label: distal medullary amacrine neuron Dm8
description: Distal medullary amacrine neuron that arborizes in layer M6, with arbors projecting back to layers 4 and 5.

label: dorsal cibarial sense organ neuron of anterior sensillum
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the anterior sensillum of the dorsal cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are three of these per sensillum.

label: dorsal cibarial sense organ neuron
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the dorsal cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx.

label: dorsal cibarial sense organ neuron of posterior sensillum
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the posterior sensillum of the dorsal cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are three of these per sensillum.

label: adult GPA2/GPB5 neuron of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion
description: An adult neuron that expresses GPA2/GPB5 (FBgn0261386 and FBgn0063368). There are 4 pairs of bilateral neurons in the first 4 abdominal neuromeres.

label: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DA2 lPN
description: Antennal lobe projection neuron from the lateral antennal lobe neuroblast lineage whose dendrites innervate only antennal lobe glomerulus DA2. The axons of these neurons innervate the posteriomedial region of the lateral horn.

label: larval GPA2/GPB5 neuron of the ventral nerve cord
description: A larval neuron that expresses GPA2/GPB5 (FBgn0261386 and FBgn0063368) and that is located in the ventral nerve cord ganglion. There are 4 pairs of bilateral neurons in the first 4 neuromeres. The axons of these neurons leave the neuropil via the segmental nerves and innervate abdominal muscles.

label: adult midgut region R0
description: Region of the adult midgut that is embedded in the cardia. It is separated from region 1, the anterior region of the midgut, by the R0-R1 boundary.

label: gustatory receptor neuron of the labellum
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the adult labellum. It projects to distinct regions in the subesophageal zone, which include the anterior maxillary, posterior maxillary and labellar sensory centers, via specific terminal branches.

label: hypodermal muscle of head
description: Any embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle (FBbt:00000465) that overlaps some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

label: adult fruitless vAB3 (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vAB3 (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110851).

label: adult fruitless vAB3 (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral abdominal ganglion. It is composed of ascending neurons that innervate the three leg pairs and the subesophageal zone, terminating in the superior lateral protocerebrum. It is a sexually dimorphic clone: neuron arborization in the subesophageal zone is dorsal to female vAB3 clones.

label: peritreme of abdominal spiracle
description: The rim of an adult abdominal spiracle. Unlike the peritremes of the thoracic spiracles, this is a rigid, circular structure that does not close.

label: adult fruitless pIP10 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the medial posterior brain. Its neurons extend neurites bilaterally, branching ventrally to innervate the periesophageal region and dorsally to the superior protocerebrum. One process descends to the thoracico-abdominal ganglion innervating the wing neuropil of the mesothoracic ganglion. This clone is not found in females.

label: adult fruitless vAB3 (female) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vAB3 (female) lineage clone (FBbt:00110849).

label: adult fruitless vAB3 (female) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult female that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral abdominal ganglion. It is composed of ascending neurons that innervate the three leg pairs and the subesophageal zone, terminating in the superior lateral protocerebrum. It is a sexually dimorphic clone: neuron arborization in the subesophageal zone is ventral to male vAB3 clones.

label: dorsal pharyngeal muscle
description: A vertically oriented muscle that inserts ventrally into the dorsal pharynx (FBbt:00001866) and dorsally at the bottom of the dorsal pouch (FBbt:00001857).

label: adult fruitless vPR1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR1 lineage clone (FBbt:00110857).

label: adult fruitless vPR1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral anterior region of the prothoracic ganglion close to the midline. Its neurons extend neurites into the brain to innervate the medial ring in the protocerebrum. It projects posteriorly forming arborizations in a distinct 'A' shape extending to the anterior of the mesothoracic segment. This clone is not found in females.

label: adult fruitless vPR6 (male) lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the male adult thoracico-abdominal ganglion that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located laterally near the border of the prothoracic and mesothoracic ganglia. Its neurons extend neurites medially and posteriorly within the wing neuropil. This clone is dimorphic, with differences in arborization in the mesothoracic triangle between males and females.

label: adult fruitless dPR1 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless dPR1 lineage clone (FBbt:00110855).

label: adult fruitless dPR1 lineage clone
description: A clone of neurons in the adult male thoracico-abdominal ganglion that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the medial anterior region of the prothoracic ganglion. Its neurons extend neurites bilaterally to innervate the wing neuropil of the anterior mesothoracic ganglion. This clone is not found in females.

label: adult fruitless pIP10 neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless pIP10 lineage clone (FBbt:00110853).

label: ventral pharyngeal muscle 3
description: The ventral-most ventral pharyngeal muscle.

label: ventral pharyngeal muscle
description: A ventrolaterally located embryonic/larval muscle that inserts on the ventral arm of the tentorium (FBbt:00001856).

label: ventral pharyngeal muscle 2
description: The second dorsal-most ventral pharyngeal muscle.

label: ventral pharyngeal muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most ventral pharyngeal muscle.

label: dorsal mouthpart muscle
description: A dorsolaterally located, embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle that extends from the wall of the pharynx to the epidermis of the prothoracic segment.

label: embryonic Malpighian tubule tiny cell
description: Tiny cell of the embryonic Malpighian tubules.

label: Malpighian tubule tiny cell
description: Morphologically distinct cell type found in the lower part of the main segment and in the ureter. It contains a reduced cytoplasm, a compact nucleus and thin processes and it lies close to the tubular walls. It do not overlap with stellate cells.

label: embryonic/larval Malpighian tubule tiny cell
description: Tiny cell of the embryonic/larval Malpighian tubules.

label: pericommissural muscle
description: An embryonic/larval hypodermal muscle of the head that flanks the supraesophageal commissure.

label: adult Malpighian tubule tiny cell
description: Tiny cell of the adult Malpighian tubules.

label: adult fruitless vPR6 (male) neuron
description: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult fruitless vPR6 (male) lineage clone (FBbt:00110859).

label: dorsal mouthpart muscle 2
description: The ventral-most of the two dorsal mouthpart muscles.

label: dorsal mouthpart muscle 1
description: The dorsal-most of the two dorsal mouthpart muscles.

label: apterous-expressing neuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax Ap1
description: Interneuron of the lateral cluster of the thorax that is part of the lineage of the neuroblast NB5-6 of the thorax. It expresses apterous (FBgn0000099). It is the first neuron of the cluster to be generated, at stage 13. It is a peptidergic neuron.

label: presumptive dorsal medial bristle of antennal segment 1
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the dorsal medial bristles of antennal segment 1.

label: presumptive shingle cuticle of lateral ptilinum
description: Region of the eye disc that will develop into the shingle cuticle of lateral ptilinum.

label: shingle cuticle of lateral ptilinum
description: Cuticle of the lateral region of the ptilinum of the adult head.

label: neuromuscular process
description: Any process pertaining to the functions of the nervous and muscular systems of an organism.

label: alpha/beta surface Kenyon cell
description: Alpha/beta mushroom body neuron that has dendrites in the main calyx and projects axons to the surface layer of the alpha and beta lobes, where they form a continuous layer surrounding the alpha/beta core. There are around 500 neurons in each hemisphere.

label: larval serotonergic IP neuron
description: Larval serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located anteriorly to the dorsal basolateral protocerebrum.

label: alpha/beta posterior Kenyon cell
description: Alpha/beta mushroom body neuron that has dendrites in the accessory calyx. It occupies the outermost stratum and the posterior layer at the tip of the alpha and beta lobes. In the shaft region of the alpha lobe, alpha/beta posterior Kenyon cell form mesh-like arrangements, with one or two nodes where axons appear to gather. In the pedunculus, their axons form several bundles, which run through the outermost layer of the central zone. In the calyx, the dendrites run along the surface of the main calyx without forming any arborization. They are the first-born Kenyon cells. There are around 90 neurons in each hemisphere.

label: gamma dorsal Kenyon cell
description: Gamma mushroom body neuron subtype whose dendritic arbor occupies the ventral accessory calyx, and its axon extends to the gamma lobe, taking the most peripheral layer in the pedunculus, the ventral anterior layers in gamma lobe slices 1 to 4, terminating in the dorsal region in slice 5. There are around 75 neurons of this subtype per hemisphere.

label: serotonergic IP1-2 neuron
description: Serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located anteriorly to the dorsal basolateral protocerebrum. It arborizes extensively in the contralateral hemisphere.

label: larval serotonergic IP1-2 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located anteriorly to the dorsal basolateral protocerebrum. A primary neurite projects to and innervates the antennal lobe. Another process projects dorsally to innervate the lateral and medial region of the posterior brain, including the region around the mushroom body. A single neurite crosses the midline and arborizes extensively in the contralateral posterior dorsolateral and anterior basolateral regions.

label: larval serotonergic SE1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic SE1 neuron whose cell body is located on either side of the ventral midline in the mandibular segment. There are two cells in this cluster.

label: adult serotonergic SE1 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic SE1 neuron whose cell body is located laterally to the esophagus foramen.

label: serotonergic LP1-1 neuron
description: Serotonergic neuron whose cell body is located in one of 2 (bilateral) clusters, in the lateral region of the brain.

label: larval serotonergic LP1-1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic LP1 neuron whose cell body is located in the mid-lateral region, at the optic lobe margin. It projects medially to the basolateral region.

label: larval serotonergic LP1 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic LP1 neuron whose cell body is located in the mid-lateral region, at the optic lobe margin. Its axon joins a midline-crossing tract.

label: adult serotonergic LP1 neuron
description: Adult serotonergic LP1 neuron whose cell body is located in the cortex of the lateral protocerebrum, anterior to the optic tract and that projects its axon centrally into the midbrain.

label: serotonergic IP1-3 neuron
description: Serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located anteriorly to the dorsal basolateral protocerebrum.

label: larval serotonergic IP1-3 neuron
description: Larval serotonergic IP neuron whose cell body is located anteriorly to the dorsal basolateral protocerebrum. A primary neurite projects posteriorly, bifurcates and innervates the basomedial brain regions.

label: sex comb tooth
description: A stout, darkly pigmented, slightly curved chaeta that is a single element of the sex comb. Each tooth has a small bract at the base.

label: adult midgut constriction R1-R2
description: Constriction of the adult midgut that is at the border between the thorax and abdomen, where the crop, the Malpighian tubules and the midgut interact. It separates region 1 (R1) from region (R2).

label: adult midgut constriction
description: Constriction of the adult midgut. There are 6 of these that delimit 5 distinct regions.

label: adult midgut constriction R2-R3
description: One of the two large constrictions of the adult midgut. It corresponds to an area where the midgut abruptly folds and turns up. It is the most ventral point of the midgut. The area is composed of a range of enterocytes with distinct identities. It separates region 2 (R2) from region 3 (R3).

label: adult midgut constriction R0-R1
description: Constriction of the adult midgut that separates the endodermal part of the proventriculus (cardia) (R0) from the anterior part of the midgut (R1).

label: embryonic/larval midgut large flat cell
description: Large flat cell of the embryonic/larval lower middle midgut, located posteriorly to the copper cell region.

label: midgut large flat cell
description: Large flat cell of the middle midgut, located posteriorly to the copper cell region. It has a large nuclei.

label: adult midgut large flat cell
description: Large flat cell of the adult midgut region R3c. It is located posteriorly to the copper cell region.

label: adult midgut posterior region R3c
description: Subregion at the posterior zone of the adult midgut region R3, located posterior to the copper cell region. It is composed by large flat cells.
synonyms: region D of the adult middle midgut

label: adult midgut constriction R3-R4
description: One of the two large constrictions of the adult midgut. It corresponds to an area where the midgut abruptly folds and turns up. It is the most dorsal point of the midgut. The cells in this area accumulate ferritin. It separates region 3 (R3) from region 4 (R4).

label: adult midgut constriction R4-R5
description: Constriction of the adult midgut. It corresponds to the beginning of the midgut ascension towards the hindgut, where the radius of the midgut uniformly decreases. It separates region 4 (R4) from region 5 (R5).

label: penis retractor muscle
description: Muscle of the adult male 9th sternite that originates from the inner side of the basal part of the sternite and inserts upon the base of the penis. There is a pair of these muscles.

label: larval dopaminergic DM1a neuron
description: Subtype of the dopaminergic neuron of the DM cluster of the larval brain. Its arborizations are restricted to the ipsilateral side. The primary neurite extends ventrally into the lower part of the ipsilateral brain lobe. There is one of these neurons per hemisphere.

label: adult Hugin neuron
description: Adult neuron that expresses Hugin (FBgn0028374). These neurons have their soma in the gnathal ganglion and arborize the thoracico-abdominal ganglion, corpus cardiacum and the protocerebrum. The latter neurites traverse along the median neurosecretory cells in the pars intercerebralis and terminate near the mushroom bodies.

label: Hugin neuron
description: Neuron that expresses hugin (FBgn0028374). These neurons have their soma in the subesophageal ganglion.

label: larval Hugin neuron of the protocerebrum
description: Larval neuron that expresses Hugin (FBgn0028374) and that arborizes the protocerebrum. This neuron arborizes the ipsilateral or both hemispheres of the protocerebrum and the ventrolateral region of the esophagus foramen. It is likely that there are 8 of these neurons.
synonyms: larval hugin cell of the protocerebrum

label: larval Hugin neuron of the ventral nerve cord
description: Larval neuron that expresses Hugin (FBgn0028374) and that projects to the ventral nerve cord. This neuron has a long projection travelling down contralaterally along the lateral neuropil border of the ventral nerve cord. Three or four shorter fibers project on either side of the midline. Two fibers project anteriorly and pass along either side of the esophagus foramen, terminating at the medial end of the protocerebrum. It is likely that there are 4 of these neurons.
synonyms: larval hugin cell of the ventral nerve cord

label: larval secretory cell of the proventriculus
description: Secretory cell of the larval proventriculus that synthesizes and secretes the peritrophic membrane. They are part of the outer layer of the proventriculus, near the anterior end. They have large secretory granules and a highly polarized secretory apparatus.

label: larval dopaminergic DM1b neuron
description: Subtype of the dopaminergic neuron of the DM cluster of the larval brain. Its arborizations are restricted to the ipsilateral side. The primary neurite extends ventrally and bifurcates in the basolateral protocerebrum. One small axon innervates the basomedial protocerebrum. It densely innervates the mushroom body spur, with one single fiber extending into the lateral appendix. One axon projects further ventrally and branches in the subesophageal ganglion and dorsal thoracic ganglion. There are 3 of these neurons per hemisphere.

label: alpha/beta core Kenyon cell
description: Alpha/beta mushroom body neuron that has dendrites in the main calyx, with their axons occupying the core layer of the peduncle, alpha and beta lobes. They can be morphologically subdivided into inner and outer core cells, although the border between these regions is not well defined. There are around 400 neurons in each hemisphere.

label: tyramine secretion
description: The regulated release of a tyramine by a cell.

label: primary amine secretion
description: The regulated release of a primary amine by a cell.

label: synaptic transmission, glutamatergic
description: The process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter glutamate.

label: octopamine secretion
description: The controlled release of octopamine by a cell.

label: histamine secretion
description: The regulated release of histamine by a cell or tissue. It is formed by decarboxylation of histidine and it acts through receptors in smooth muscle and in secretory systems.

label: stage 2 embryo
description: Nuclear divisions 3-8. The egg cytoplasm contracts producing a clear separation from the vitelline membrane and empty spaces at the anterior and posterior. The cleavage nuclei migrate towards the periphery. Duration at 25 degrees C approximately 40 minutes (25-65 minutes AEL).

label: stage 4 embryo
description: Nuclear division 10-13. Polar buds divide twice and become tightly grouped at the posterior pole by the end of this stage. Nuclei visible at the rim of the embryo. Stage 4 ends with the beginning of cellularization. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 50 minutes (80-130 minutes after egg laying).

label: stage 3 embryo
description: Nuclear division 9. The cleavage nuclei complete there migration to the periphery. Polar buds form at the posterior pole and divide once. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 15 minutes (65-80 minutes after egg laying).

label: adult midgut region R4c
description: Subregion at the posterior end of the adult midgut region R4. It is composed of enterocytes with small apical protrusions. It can be distinguished from the anterior region R4b by gene expression.

label: adult midgut region R4
description: Region of the adult midgut that forms a complex loop and that re-orients the gut towards the posterior part of the abdomen and ends ventrally. It can be subdivided into an anterior part containing an extremely folded epithelium (R4a) and two posterior regions composed of cells with short apical protrusions resulting in an enlarged lumen (R4b and R4c).

label: adult midgut region R5
description: Region of the adult midgut that corresponds to an ascending segment of the midgut that joins the hindgut. It is composed of an anterior region containing enterocytes with a typical columnar morphology, containing lipid vesicles and a posterior region which contains fewer cells with a smoothed brush border.

label: adult midgut region R4a
description: Subregion at the anterior zone of the adult midgut region R4. It contains a highly folded lumen, with enterocytes sometimes organized in multilayers, and containing lipid vesicles.

label: adult midgut region R4b
description: Subregion at the middle of the adult midgut region R4. It is composed of enterocytes with small apical protrusions. It can be distinguished from the posterior region R4c by gene expression.

label: adult copper cell
description: Specialised cell of the adult midgut found in the anterior and middle midgut sections of region R3 (R3a and R3b, copper cell region). It secretes acid and accumulates copper. They show a distinct apical invagination, basally located nuclei, numerous mitochondria and a deeply invaginated apical membrane covered with long microvilli. Interstitial cells arch over the apex of the copper cell, forming a narrow channel that connects the apical invagination of the copper cell to the gut lumen. The highly folded area of apicolateral contact between copper and interstitial cells contains smooth septate junctions.

label: adult midgut interstitial cell
description: Interstitial cell of the adult midgut. It is found in the anterior midgut subregions of region R3 (R3a and R3b, copper cell region), interspersed with copper cells. They have apically localized nuclei, short microvilli in the apical membrane and a broad apical profile. The interstitial cell arches over the apex of the copper cell, forming a narrow channel that connects the apical invagination of the copper cell to the gut lumen. The highly folded area of apicolateral contact between copper and interstitial cells contains smooth septate junctions.

label: adult midgut region R5a
description: Subregion at the anterior end of the adult midgut region R5. It is composed of enterocytes of a typical columnar morphology, containing lipid vesicles.

label: adult midgut region R5b
description: Subregion at the posterior end of the adult midgut region R5. It contains fewer enterocytes, with a smoothed brush border.

label: synaptic transmission, dopaminergic
description: The process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter dopamine.

label: stage 11 embryo
description: Stage 11 begins with the invagination of the tracheal placodes. Para-segmental furrows form and segment boundary furrows become deep folds. Within the head, gnathal protuberances become apparent. The end of this stage is signalled by the appearance of a distinct cleft at the posterior pole of the embryo, which becomes detached from the vitelline membrane. This marks the beginning of germ band retraction. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 120 minutes (320-440 minutes after egg laying).

label: stage 10 embryo
description: Stage 10 begins with the appearance of the stomodeal invagination, slightly ventral to the anterior pole. Periodic furrows appear in the embryonic epidermis around the middle of the stage. The germ band continues to extend, reaching its maximum extent of 75% egg length towards the end of the stage. The end of the stage is marked by the beginning of invagination of the tracheal placodes. Duration at 25 degrees: approximately 60 minutes (260-320 minutes after egg laying).

label: tritocerebral center
description: Region of the adult tritocerebrum that processes gustatory input from the internal mouthparts.

label: stomodeal nerve projection
description: Projections of the fibers of the stomodeal nerve of the adult (ascending fibers), in the tritocerebrum, close to the midline. Three different types can be distinguished: a, b and c.

label: tritocerebral commissure
description: Commissure of the adult tritocerebrum, formed by the terminals of the fibers ascending through the cervical connective that extend to either half of the tritocerebrum.

label: labial nerve projection
description: Projection of the sensory fibers that make up the labial nerve, located close to the adult tritocerebrum. Projections of fibers that extend anteroventrally arborize at the level of the ventral pharyngeal and accessory pharyngeal nerve's projections.

label: accessory pharyngeal nerve projection
description: Projection of the sensory fibers that make up the accessory pharyngeal nerve in the adult tritocerebrum. The accessory pharyngeal nerve coalesces with the pharyngeal nerve, and the projections of these two nerves are located ventral to the esophagus. Fibers have a predominantly ipsilateral arborization. Two levels of arborization can be distinguished: dorsal and ventral.

label: stage 17 embryo
description: Stage 17 begins when the dorsal ridge (frontal sac) has overgrown the tip of the clypeolabrum, which is thereby enclosed in the atrium. It lasts until hatching of the embryo (approximately 24 hours after egg laying), during which time much terminal differentiation occurs, the tracheal tree fills with air, so becoming completely visible, and the ventral nerve cord continues to retract. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 8 hours (960-1440 minutes after egg laying).

label: type b stomodeal nerve projection
description: Stomodeal nerve projection found in the adult tritocerebrum. It has a relatively profuse arborization, bifurcates at the origin of the recurrent nerve and projects to both halves of the tritocerebrum.

label: type a stomodeal nerve projection
description: Stomodeal nerve projection found in the adult tritocerebrum. It has a clustered appearance, bifurcates at the origin of the recurrent nerve and projects to both halves of the tritocerebrum.

label: pharyngeal nerve projection
description: Projection of the sensory fibers that make up the pharyngeal nerve in the adult tritocerebrum. The pharyngeal nerve coalesces with the accessory pharyngeal nerve, and the projections of these two nerves are located ventral to the esophagus. Fibers have a predominantly ipsilateral arborization. Two levels of arborization can be distinguished: dorsal and ventral.

label: hemocyte-derived cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from hemocytes.

label: type c stomodeal nerve projection
description: Stomodeal nerve projection found in the adult tritocerebrum. It extends secondary branches and arborizes around the terminals of the type a and b fibers. It does not bifurcate at the origin of the recurrent nerve and projects to only one half of the tritocerebrum.

label: taste-sensory glomerulus VM
description: Glomerular region in the ventromedial adult subesophageal zone, medial to the ventrolateral taste-sensory glomerulus M and by the midline. It is found in both hemispheres.

label: taste-sensory region glomerulus
description: Glomerular region in the adult subesophageal zone which contains the terminals of labial sensory neurons. There are 4 distinct regions, three of them present in both hemispheres.

label: Kc167 cell-line
description: Somatic cell of a cultured cell-line that originated from embryonic cells and that displays hemocyte characteristics.

label: taste-sensory glomerulus DA
description: Glomerular region in the dorsoanterior adult subesophageal zone, lateral to the medial taste-sensory glomerulus M. It is found in both hemispheres.

label: taste-sensory glomerulus VL
description: Glomerular region in the ventrolateral adult subesophageal zone, lateral to the ventromedial taste-sensory glomerulus VM. It is found in both hemispheres.

label: stage P4(ii) prepupa
description: Moving bubble/pupation (12-13.5 hours): Bubble within abdomen disappears; posterior bubble gradually displaced to anterior of puparium, while the (pre?) pupa withdraws to posterior end; imaginal head sac everted and mouthparts of larva expelled.

label: stage P4(i) prepupa
description: Bouyant (approximately 6.5-12 hrs at 25'C). Prepupa floats on water (6.5-7 hours). Other events: lateral trachea become obscured (6.5-8 hours); everted wing and legs discs visible (translucent); bubble appears in posterior of puparium, displacing prepupa anteriorly.

label: taste-sensory glomerulus M
description: Glomerular region in the medial adult subesophageal zone, crossing the midline.

label: stage P5(ii) pupa
description: Malpighian tubules become prominent and green.

label: stage P5(i) pupa
description: Malpighian tubules migrating - enlarged initial segments of anterior pair of Malpighian tubules move from thorax to abdomen. Translucent patch lacking adhering fat body cells becomes apparent in the middle of the eye region.

label: adult labial sensory neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the labial sensilla, and fasciculates with the adult labial nerve. There are around 195 of these, with seven distinct types. These neurons project to defined glomeruli in the adult subesophageal zone.

label: labral sense organ neuron
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labral sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are 18 of these, 8 mechanosensory and 10 gustatory receptor neurons.

label: ventral cibarial sense organ neuron of proximal sensillum
description: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the proximal sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are two of these per sensillum.

label: stage P11(i) pharate adult
description: Dorsal thoracic micro- and macrochaetae become visible.

label: denticle field primordium
description: Primordium of the denticle field of the dorsal closure embryo that will give rise to the larval denticle fields.

label: denticle field
description: Region of embryonic and larval ventral cuticle that displays denticle belts. It develops from the denticle field primordium.

label: ventral apodeme anlage
description: Anlage of the ventral apodeme of the late extended germ band embryo that will give rise to the ventral apodeme primordium.

label: stage P12(ii) pharate adult
description: Sex comb darkens.

label: type IV sensory neuron of dorsal ipsilateral fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type III fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, neurons terminate in the ipsilateral anterodorsal region (taste-sensory glomerulus DA). The terminal branches give rise to lateral branches that extend away from the midline.

label: type III sensory neuron of ventral ipsilateral fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type III fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, neurons terminate in the ipsilateral anteroventral region (taste-sensory glomerulus VL). The terminal branches have sparse terminals.

label: stage P12(i) pharate adult
description: Bristles on abdominal tergites become visible; wings become gray (approximately 73-78 hours at 25'C).

label: type VI sensory neuron of dorsal contralateral fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type III fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, neurons terminate in the ipsilateral mediodorsal region (taste-sensory glomerulus M), with some branches extending contralaterally.

label: type V sensory neuron of ventral contralateral fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type III fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, neurons extend contralaterally in the ventral region (taste-sensory glomerulus VM). They arborize throughout their length, giving off several small branches.

label: stage P11(ii) pharate adult
description: Tips of folded wings become gray.

label: type II sensory neuron of shrubby fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type II fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, most neurons terminate in the anteroventral region (taste-sensory glomerulus VL) or in the ventromedial region (taste-sensory glomerulus VM). The fibers are thick, with profuse and dense branches in the ipsilateral hemisphere, with a few branches crossing the midline.

label: type I sensory neuron of coiled fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type I fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, the neuron gives rise to 2-3 coiled branches, forming many knot-like structures ipsi- and contralaterally. A few neurons show a bilaterally symmetric branching pattern. These arborizations occupy a large volume in the ventrolateral and ventromedial regions (taste-sensory glomerulus VL and VM).

label: stage P15(ii) pharate adult
description: Eclosion.

label: stage P15(i) pharate adult
description: This is the stage immediately prior to emergence. It is characterized by the black appearance of the wings, frequent movements of the legs and the presence of the meconium, a pale green patch which appears at the posterior tip of the abdomen. Wings at this stage closely resemble those 87hr after pupariation as described by Tucker et al., (1986). The cuticle is highly folded, and numerous epidermal cell processes containing transalar microtubule arrays span the lumen. Malpighian tubules and yellow body become obscured by tanning of the tergite. Legs twitch (flies can walk if dissected from puparium).

label: adult labial interneuron
description: Interneuron that arborizes in the adult subesophageal zone where the labial sensory neurons terminate and in the same or other neuropils. It fasciculates with the adult labial nerve. There are four distinct types.

label: type VII sensory neuron of central fibers
description: Sensory neuron that innervates the adult labial sensilla with type III fibers. After entering the subesophageal zone, neurons terminate in the ipsilateral central most region (taste-sensory glomerulus VM and M). They branch throughout their length.

label: type B interneuron
description: Interneuron of the adult subesophageal zone, that arborizes in the taste sensory neuropil (taste-sensory region glomerulus). It soma is located in the anteroventral cell body rind. The primary neurite extends in the ventrodorsal direction, giving out many branches in the dorsal region. A single branch then exits the brain into the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: type A interneuron
description: Local interneuron of the adult subesophageal zone, that arborizes in the taste sensory neuropil (taste-sensory region glomerulus). It soma is located in the anteroventral cell body rind. It gives out two short processes, which further divide into many collaterals.

label: dorsal apodeme anlage
description: Anlage of the embryonic dorsal apodeme in the late extended germ band embryo.

label: LNv neuron
description: Lateral period-expressing neuron (LN) of the adult brain whose cell body is located in the ventral cluster of LNs, at the level of the esophageal foramen (Helfrich-Forster, 1998). It has neurites associated with the accessory medulla (aMe) (Helfrich-Forster et al., 2007). The LN neuronal group are necessary and sufficient for generation of robust adult locomotor rhythms in the absence of environmental cues (Helfrich-Forster et al., 2007).

label: type C interneuron
description: Interneuron of the adult subesophageal zone, that arborizes in the taste sensory neuropil (taste-sensory region glomerulus). It soma is located posteriorly, near the mushroom body calyx. The primary neurite extends in the ventral direction, giving out three branches. The first branch extends back into the direction of the soma, giving out small collateral arborizations. The second branch extends to the anterodorsal subesophageal zone and branches profusely, in the same region as type B interneurons. The third branch projects to the posterior region, exiting the brain into the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: type D interneuron
description: Interneuron of the adult subesophageal zone, that arborizes in the taste sensory neuropil (taste-sensory region glomerulus). It soma is located anteroventral cell body rind. It arborizes in the anterior and ventral regions of the subesophageal zone. A branch extends into the supraesophageal neuropils and another exits the brain into the thoracico-abdominal ganglion.

label: stomodeal ganglion
description: Elongated ganglion of the adult central nervous system, located anteriorly to the prothorax, lying between the esophagus and the aorta. Two types of cells can be distinguished: anterior cells have a strong eosinophilic cytoplasm - secretory cells of the corpus cardiacum -, whereas the posterior ones stain more lightly - stomodeal nerve cells. Two nerves exit anteriorly and follow the esophagus to terminate in the protocerebrum. Five nerves exit anteriorly: two to the cardia, one to the crop and two to the salivary glands.

label: cardia nerve
description: Nerve of the adult that exits the stomodeal ganglion posteriorly to innervate the cardial valve of the adult proventriculus (cardia). There are two of these nerves.

label: dorsal prothoracic nerve
description: A nerve that projects latero-anteriorly from the antero-lateral corner of the thoracico-abdominal ganglion (prothoracic neuromere). It splits into 4 or more branches before innervating various horizontally and vertically oriented tubular muscles.

label: ventral prothoracic nerve
description: A nerve that carries fibers from two clusters of microchaetae on the prothoracic coxa (FBbt:00004259) and from motor neuron fibers from lateral anterior muscles. It connects to the thoracico-abdominal ganglion just dorsal to the root of the prothoracic leg nerve and branches about halfway along its length into a motor branch that stays within the body and a sensory branch that projects to the leg.

label: accessory prothoracic nerve
description: A nerve that connects to the thoracico-abdominal ganglion (prothoracic neuromere) slightly posterior and ventral to the anterior prothoracic chordotonal organ (FBbt:00007656) and slightly dorsal to the root of the ventral prothoracic nerves. It extends laterally and dorsally almost to the lateral body wall before branching to innervate obliquely placed vertical muscles.

label: salivary gland nerve
description: Nerve of the adult that exits the stomodeal ganglion posteriorly to innervate the salivary glands. There are two of these.

label: crop nerve
description: Nerve of the adult that exits the stomodeal ganglion posteriorly to innervate the crop.

label: cervical nerve
description: A bilaterally paired nerve that connects laterally to the cervical connective immediately posterior to where it enters the thorax. Each cervical nerve extends laterally, branching and innervating horizontal muscles of the anterior thorax.

label: pupal tagma
description: Main division of the pupal body, formed from groups of segments.

label: anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve
description: The largest and anterior-most of the two dorsal mesothoracic nerves. It extends dorso-anteriorly from the thoracico-abdominal ganglion and then dorso-laterally, bending around the anterior face of the anterior tergosternal muscles before splitting into branches that innervate the lateral muscles near the body wall, beneath the base of the wing. It also sends a branch between the tergosternal muscles. The fine sensory fibers of this nerve project along with a smaller number of coarse motor fibers, dorsally between various muscle groups. The sensory fibers extend into the wing where they innervate various sensory organs.

label: pupal abdomen
description: The most posterior tagma of the pupal body.

label: pupal thorax
description: The middle tagma of the pupal body.

label: presumptive embryonic/larval integumentary system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval integumentary system.

label: direct flight muscle motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the direct flight muscles. Their aspect can be stubbly, fibrous or tufted.

label: prepupal epidermis
description: Epidermis of the prepupa.

label: embryonic/larval epidermis
description: Epidermis of the late embryo or larva.

label: accessory mesothoracic nerve
description: A nerve that arises from the lateroposterior side of the mesothoracic neuromere at a point in front of the origin of the haltere nerve. It extends posteriorly and slightly dorsally and laterally around the anterior wings of the mesofurca, before branching, with one branch innervating furcoentopleural muscles (= muscles 59 and 60 ?) and another innervating laterally placed vertical tubular muscles close to the anterior of the halteres (muscle 87?).

label: mesothoracic leg nerve
description: A nerve that arises from a ventral protuberance on the adult mesothoracic neuromere. It splits at its base, with a small number of fibers innervating a ventral tubular muscle, posterior-lateral to the tergal depressor of the trochanter and the rest projecting into the mesothoracic leg.

label: indirect flight muscle motor neuron
description: Motor neuron that innervates the indirect flight muscles.

label: small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 6
small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 7
small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 4
small cell associated with anterior dorsal histoblasts abdominal 5
receptor lymph space of small sensillum basiconicum
description: Any sensillar lymph space (FBbt:00007347) that is part of some small sensillum basiconicum (FBbt:00005186).

label: receptor lymph space of large sensillum basiconicum
description: Any sensillar lymph space (FBbt:00007347) that is part of some large sensillum basiconicum (FBbt:00005188).

label: abdominal 3 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal dorsal trichome
description: Dorsal hair (trichome) of the larval abdominal segment.

label: abdominal 4 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: abdominal 6 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 1 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 2 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 7 dorsal trichome
description: Any abdominal dorsal trichome (FBbt:00002912) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal ventral denticle belt
description: Ventral denticle belt of the larval abdominal segment. It is more complex, though similarly organized to the thoracic denticle belts. It exhibits a clear polarity, with the first and fourth rows oriented anteriorly, while the remaining are oriented posteriorly.

label: abdominal 1 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 1 (FBbt:00001748).

label: abdominal 6 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 6 (FBbt:00001753).

label: abdominal 7 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00001754).

label: abdominal 2 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 2 (FBbt:00001749).

label: abdominal 3 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 3 (FBbt:00001750).

label: abdominal 4 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

label: abdominal 5 ventral denticle belt
description: Any abdominal ventral denticle belt (FBbt:00002920) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 5 (FBbt:00001752).

label: MP1a neuron
description: Lateral-most of the two bilateral MP1 neurons found at the midline, anterior to the posterior commissure (Schmid et al., 1999).

label: MP1b neuron
description: Medial-most of the two bilateral MP1 neurons found at the midline, anterior to the posterior commissure (Schmid et al., 1999).

label: spiracular hair
description: Sensory spiracular hair on the spiracular plate of the embryonic/larval posterior spiracles. It is chitinized and branched. There are four of these per spiracle, surrounding the spiracular opening. One sensory neuron innervates each of these sensory organs.

label: supraesophageal embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster located in the supraesophageal ganglion.

label: embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Cluster of typically 2-6 embryonic neuronal somata prior to axon outgrowth. Neurons of the founder clusters then extend axons that grow along the surface of the founder cluster and form a simple system of pioneer tracts for each of the components of the neuropil.

label: protocerebral embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster more dorsally located than the D/T founder cluster, and belongs to the protocerebrum.

label: P1 fiber tract founder cluster
description: Fiber tract founder cluster located in the protocerebrum between the D/T and P3m founder clusters. Along with these clusters, fibers from the P1 fiber tract founder cluster pioneer the cervical connective.

label: P2l fiber tract founder cluster
description: Fiber tract founder cluster located at the junction between the protocerebrum and the deutocerebrum. Along with the P2m founder cluster, fibers from the P2l form a transverse track that pioneers the supraesophageal commissure. This cluster derives from the Dc1 or the Dc2 lineage.

label: dMP2 neuron
description: Insulinergic intersegmental interneuron that is one of two cells differentiating from neuroblast MP2. It projects posteriorly in a medial fascicle of the connective. Axons from dMP2 neurons innervate the hindgut, forming two fascicles that extend on opposite sides of the hindgut (Miguel-Aliaga et al., 2008). By the adult stage, arbors have formed that innervate the anterior intestines and the rectum. dMP2 neurons perform a pioneer function in embryos then undergo apoptosis in all but segments A1-A9 (Miguel-Aliaga et al., 2008).

label: vMP2 neuron
description: Intersegmental interneuron that is one of two cells differentiating from neuroblast MP2. It projects anteriorly in a medial fascicle of the connective.

label: vMP2 tract
description: Tract of the ventral nerve cord pioneered by vMP2 which projects anteriorly in a medial fascicle of the connective, and extends across segment boundaries (Schmid et al., 1999; Bossing et al., 1996).

label: UMI interneuron
description: Bilaterally projecting interneuron located along the midline in the ventral nerve cord. There are two of these per segment.

label: abdominal 8 dorsal trichome
description: Dorsal trichome of larval abdominal segment 8.

label: abdominal 8 ventral denticle belt
description: Ventral denticle belt of larval abdominal segment 8.

label: P2m fiber tract founder cluster
description: Fiber tract founder cluster located in the protocerebrum, adjacent to the P2m founder cluster. Along with the P2l founder cluster, fibers from the P2m form a transverse track that pioneers the supraesophageal commissure.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 9 sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00001756).

label: P3l fiber tract founder cluster
description: Fiber tract founder cluster located laterally adjacent to the fiber tract founder cluster P3m in the protocerebrum.

label: P3m fiber tract founder cluster
description: Fiber tract founder cluster located dorsally in the protocerebrum. Along with founder clusters D/T and P1, fibers from the P3m fiber tract founder cluster pioneer the cervical connective.

label: abdominal 10 caudal sensory organ vas
description: Sensillum campaniformium of the ventral region of the larval abdominal segment 10, in the ventral midline, anteriorly adjacent to the anal pads. It is innervated by 2 neurons.

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 10 sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00001757).

label: deutero/tritocerebral embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster that overlaps with parts of the deutocerebrum as well as of the tritocerebral neurectoderm. It is located ventral to the protocerebral embryonic fiber tract founder cluster.

label: subesophageal embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster located in the subesophageal ganglion.

label: labial/prothoracic embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster which is located at the boundary of the labial/prothoracic neuromeres.

label: P4l fiber tract founder cluster
