description: Fiber tract founder cluster located in the protocerebrum posterior to founder cluster P3m. Along with founder clusters P5l and P5m, fibers developing from the P4l fiber tract founder cluster pioneer a lateral component of the protocerebral connective.

label: lipid metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving lipids, compounds soluble in an organic solvent but not, or sparingly, in an aqueous solvent. Includes fatty acids; neutral fats, other fatty-acid esters, and soaps; long-chain (fatty) alcohols and waxes; sphingoids and other long-chain bases; glycolipids, phospholipids and sphingolipids; and carotenes, polyprenols, sterols, terpenes and other isoprenoids.

label: P4m fiber tract founder cluster
description: The P4m fiber tract founder cluster in a relatively large group of neurons situated posterior to the P3m founder cluster in the medial cortex of the supraesophageal ganglion. Fibers originating from this cluster pioneer a medial component of the protocerebral connective.

label: abdominal 9 ventral denticle belt
description: Ventral denticle belt of larval segment 9.

label: P5l fiber tract founder cluster
description: The P5l fiber tract founder cluster is located in the posterior-ventral region of the protocerebrum, adjacent to the optic lobes. Along with founder clusters P4l and P5m, fibers developing from the P5l fiber tract founder cluster pioneer a lateral component of the protocerebral connective.

label: P5m fiber tract founder cluster
description: The P5m fiber tract founder cluster is located in the posterior-ventral region of the protocerebrum, adjacent to the optic lobes. Along with founder clusters P4l and P5l, fibers developing from the P5m fiber tract founder cluster pioneer a lateral component of the protocerebral connective.

label: taxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to an external stimulus.
synonyms: directed movement in response to stimulus

label: abdominal 11 anal tuft
description: Small group of densely packed denticles located at the most ventral point of larval abdominal segment 11, and flanked by the anal sense organs (caudal sense organs).

label: embryonic/larval abdominal 11 sensillum
description: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 11 (FBbt:00001758).

label: maxillary/labial embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster which is located at the boundary of the maxillary/labial neuromeres. It includes the aCC and SN clusters.

label: mandibular/maxillary embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster which is located at the boundary of the mandibular/maxillary neuromeres.

label: thoracic-abdominal embryonic fiber tract founder cluster
description: Embryonic fiber tract founder cluster located in the thoracic and abdominal neuromeres.

label: embryonic fiber tract
description: Fiber tract of the embryo.

label: pupal transverse connective
description: A pupal trachea that connects the dorsal and lateral trunks. There are four of these branches.

label: pupal dorsal trunk
description: The main airway of the pupal tracheal system, linking its metameric units from the (T1) pupal spiracle to tracheal metamere 5.

label: medial protocerebral tract
description: Tract of the embryonic protocerebrum. One of the two axon fascicles that pioneers the protocerebral connective. It is formed by the anteriorly projecting axons of the neurons of the P4m cluster, which project toward the P3m cluster.

label: protocerebral embryonic fiber tract
description: Fiber tract of the embryonic protocerebrum.

label: lateral protocerebral tract
description: Tract of the embryonic protocerebrum. One of the two axon fascicles that pioneers the protocerebral connective. It is composed of axons of the P5l and P4l clusters that converge and extend anteriorly. At a later stage, axons of the P5m cluster join this tract.

label: coiled tracheole
description: Tracheole of a tracheolar cell that develops in the pupa and displays a striking coiled structure. Coiled tracheoles uncoil during the pupal period and extend toward and attach to the developing pharate adult tissues.

label: supraesophageal embryonic fiber tract
description: Large tract of neurons crossing the midline at the boundary of the deutocerebrum and pars intercerebralis. It is pioneered by fibers from fiber tract founder clusters P2l and P2m.
synonyms: transverse component of embryonic brain neuropil

label: pupal dorsal branch
description: A pupal trachea that extends dorsally across the midline to connect the left and right dorsal trunks.

label: posterior cervical tract
description: Tract of the embryonic brain that pioneers part of the cervical connective that is mainly composed of afferents from the ventral nerve cord to the ipsilateral brain hemisphere.

label: abdominal 7 ventro-lateral serotonergic neuron
description: Paired ventrolateral serotonergic neuron of abdominal segment A7.

label: pupal transverse connective 3
description: Third most anterior transverse connective of the pupa. It connects the dorsal and lateral trunks just posterior to the origin of the fourth dorsal branch.

label: medial cervical tract
description: Tract of the embryo that pioneers part of the cervical connective. It is located in the border between the deutocerebrum and tritocerebrum. In the embryo, it is composed of axons from the D/T cluster. Axons that project ventrally fasciculate with the incoming maxillary pCC axon and pioneer the ventral segment of the cervical connective. Other ventrally projecting axons grow along the floor of the stomodeum and pioneer the subesophageal commissure. Axons that project dorsally converge upon the P2l cluster and pioneer the dorsal segment of the cervical connective. In the larva, it is connected to (among other compartments) the centro-anterior synaptic neuropil domain (CA) and the dorso-anterior (DA) and dorso-posterior (DP) compartments.

label: deutero/tritocerebral embryonic fiber tract
description: Tract of the embryonic deutocerebrum and tritocerebrum.

label: metathoracic femoral yellow bristles
description: A short yellow bristle that borders a region of naked cuticle (ZNB) in the metathoracic femur. There are two incomplete rows running proximo-distally.

label: presumptive metathoracic femoral yellow bristles
description: Region of the metathoracic leg disc that will develop into the metathoracic femoral yellow bristles.

label: pupal transverse connective 4
description: Most posterior transverse connective of the pupa. It connects the dorsal and lateral trunks just posterior to the origin of the fifth dorsal branch.

label: supraesophageal commissural pioneer tract
description: Pioneer commissural tract of the embryonic supraesophageal ganglion. It is formed by the continuing axons of the medial cervical, lateral cervical and lateral protocerebral pioneer tracts that form three fascicles. First axons of the medial cervical tract (P2l and D/T clusters) grow medially towards the P2m cluster. Following the outline of this cluster, the axons reach the dorsal midline where they meet and fasciculate with their contralateral counterparts, and form the anterior ventral commissural tract (anterior VCT). A second commissural tract, the posterior VCT, is formed just posterior to the anterior VCT by collaterals of the lateral cervical tract. The third tract, the dorsal commissural tract, is formed by axons of the P4l and P3l clusters that grow anteriorly, make a sharp turn medially and form a commissural bundle dorsally to the anterior VCT.

label: anterior ventral commissural pioneer tract
description: One of the supraesophageal commissural pioneer tracts. It is formed by the axons that reach the P2m cluster, follow its outline and reach the dorsal midline where they meet and fasciculate with their contralateral counterparts.

label: pupal cerebropharyngeal branch
description: A pupal specific tracheal branch that branches from a point close to the prothoracic (functional) pupal spiracle and tracheates ventral regions of the developing head including the proboscis. It is composed of two distinct branches: the cerebral and the pharyngeal branches.

label: posterior ventral commissural pioneer tract
description: One of the supraesophageal commissural pioneer tracts. It is formed by the collaterals of the axons of the lateral cervical tract, just posterior to the anterior ventral commissural pioneer tract.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches from a transverse connective and connects to a spiracle.

label: visceral branch 8
description: Any embryonic/larval visceral branch (FBbt:00000296) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: visceral branch 7
description: Any embryonic/larval visceral branch (FBbt:00000296) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: pupal transverse connective 1
description: Most anterior transverse connective of the pupa. It connects the dorsal and lateral trunks posteriorly to the origin of the second dorsal branch.

label: pupal transverse connective 2
description: Second most anterior transverse connective of the pupa. It connects the dorsal and lateral trunks just posterior to the origin of the third dorsal branch.

label: visceral branch 6
description: Any embryonic/larval visceral branch (FBbt:00000296) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: subesophageal embryonic fiber tract
description: A massive bundle of neurons crossing the midline at the boundary between subesophageal and supraesophageal ganglia. It carries axons of mainly tritocerebral origin although some axons of neurons located in the mandibular neuromere also contribute to this commissure.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 4
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of A2 and transverse connective 4.

label: non-functional spiracular branch
description: A trachea attached to a non-functional spiracle and whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 3
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of A1 and transverse connective 3.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 2
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of T3 and transverse connective 2.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 1
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that connects to the anterior spiracle.

label: pupal cerebral branch
description: A pupal specific tracheal branch that arises from the cerebropharyngeal branch, lateral to the cerebral anastomosis and anterior to the pharyngeal branch. It tracheates the developing eyes and brain.

label: pupal cerebral anastomosis
description: Pupal tracheal node formed from the fusion of the left and right cerebral branches at the midline.

label: central anastomosing tract
description: Tract of the embryonic protocerebrum. It is formed from an interchange of axons between the medial/lateral cervical tracts and the lateral protocerebral tract. Before approaching the midline, bundles of axons branch off the lateral protocerebral tract and join the medial/lateral cervical tracts.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 6
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of A4 and transverse connective 6.

label: pupal pharyngeal branch
description: A pupal specific tracheal branch that arises from the cerebropharyngeal branch, lateral to the cerebral anastomosis and posterior to the cerebral branch. It tracheates the pharynx and cephalothorax.

label: labial/prothoracic embryonic fiber tract
description: Tract of the embryonic labial neuromere.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 5
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of A3 and transverse connective 5.

label: thoracic-abdominal pioneer tract
description: Pioneer tract of the embryonic ventral nerve cord. There are two of these: the lateral MP1 and the medial vMP2.

label: thoracic-abdominal embryonic fiber tract
description: Fiber tract of the embryonic ventral nerve cord.

label: pupal dorsal branch 4
description: Fourth most anterior dorsal anastomosing branch of the pupal tracheal system.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 7
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of A5 and transverse connective 7.

label: pupal dorsal branch 5
description: Most posterior dorsal anastomosing branch of the pupal tracheal system.

label: pupal spiracular branch
description: Tracheal branch that connects to the spiracle in each tracheal metamere. Apart from the first branch, that connects to the functional anterior pupal spiracle, the other four spiracular branches appear to be collapsed.

label: pupal spiracle
description: Spiracle of the pupa. Spiracles are present in the anterior five tracheal metameres, but only one of these, the prothoracic spiracle, is functional. It is connected to the tracheal system via a spiracular branch.

label: pupal spiracular branch 1
description: Branch that connects to the anterior pupal spiracle. It is very broad at the opening of the spiracle and continues posteriorly as a longitudinal dorsal tracheal trunk.

label: anterior pupal spiracle
description: The only functional spiracle of the pupa. These spiracles form as evaginations of the epithelium in the prothoracic segment, first apparent in the contracted third instar, just prior to pupariation. They are biperforate and open into the space between the pupa and the hardened puparium.

label: dorsal-medial tract
description: Fiber tract of the embryonic ventral nerve cord that develops from the vMP2 tract from stage 15.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 10
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that is the part of the dorsal longitudinal trunk and that runs from its branch point with transverse connective 10 to the spiracular chamber of the posterior spiracle.

label: pupal dorsal branch 1
description: Most anterior dorsal anastomosing branch of the pupal tracheal system. Numerous tracheoles arising from this branch supply oxygen to the developing mesothoracic muscles.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 9
description: Any non-functional spiracular branch (FBbt:00000314) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 9 (FBbt:00000263) and that connected to some non-functional larval spiracle of abdominal segment 7 (FBbt:00000423).

label: pupal dorsal branch 2
description: Second most anterior dorsal anastomosing branch of the pupal tracheal system. Numerous tracheoles arising from this branch supply oxygen to the developing mesothoracic muscles.

label: pupal dorsal branch 3
description: Third most anterior dorsal anastomosing branch of the pupal tracheal system. Numerous tracheoles arising from this branch supply oxygen to the developing thoracic flight muscles.

label: embryonic/larval spiracular branch 8
description: An embryonic larval trachea whose lumen has collapsed, forming a solid cord and that is connected to the non-functional spiracle of A6 and transverse connective 8.

label: pupal spiracular branch 2
description: Non-functional branch connecting pupal transverse connective 1 to non-functional pupal spiracle 2.

label: non-functional pupal spiracle 2
description: Any non-functional pupal spiracle (FBbt:00002998) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027) and that connected to some pupal spiracular branch 2 (FBbt:00002977).

label: ventro-medial tract
description: Fiber tract of the embryonic ventral nerve cord that develops from the MP1 tract from stage 15.

label: lateral tract
description: Lateral most of the tracts forming the longitudinal connectives of the ventral nerve cord. It is first observed in late stage 16 embryos (Nassif et al., 1998).

label: imaginal disc primordium
description: Population of contiguous, morphologically distinct cells that will form an imaginal disc.

label: pupal leg trachea
description: A pupal trachea that tracheates one of the developing legs. These arise from the pupal ventral branches.

label: pupal prothoracic leg trachea
description: A pupal trachea that tracheates the developing prothoracic leg.

label: pupal mesothoracic leg trachea
description: A pupal trachea that tracheates the developing mesothoracic leg.

label: pupal metathoracic leg trachea
description: A pupal trachea that tracheates the developing metathoracic leg.

label: mesothoracic tibial sense organ
description: An oval sense organ in the dorsal, proximal mesothoracic tibia. It is composed of 4 sensilla campaniform.

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches from the lateral trunk and which tracheates the ventral nerve cord. The three most anterior ganglionic branches (GB0-GB2) anastomose mid-ventrally with the branch from the opposite hemisphere, forming a ventral anastomose. In the larva, the last two pairs of ventral ganglionic branches terminate without tracheating the posterior ventral nerve cord.

label: pupal abdominal trachea
description: Specialised trachea of the pupa that branches from tracheal metameres 4 and 5 (A2 & A3 respectively) and projects posteriorly. It develops from tracheoblasts of the 4th and 5th spiracular branches, near the junctions with the transverse connectives, forming 3 - 5 major branches and many fine terminals branches. It becomes functional at pupation.

label: pupal wing branch
description: Trachea that branches from the anterior region of the pupal lateral trunk to tracheate the developing wing.

label: pupal haltere branch
description: Trachea that branches from the pupal lateral trunk between transverse connectives 2 and 3 to tracheate the developing haltere.

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 3
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 2
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 1
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 0
description: Embryonic/larval tracheal branch of the first tracheal metamere that extends ventrally, in a distinct and anterior trajectory to the ganglionic branch of tracheal metamere 1 (GB1).

label: pupal ganglionic branch
description: A pupal tracheal branch that connects the lateral trunk to one of the ventral anastomosing branches and tracheates the developing thoracic abdominal ganglion.

label: pupal ganglionic branch 0
description: A pupal ganglionic branch arising from pupal ventral branch 0. It mainly tracheates the prothoracic neuromere.

label: pupal ganglionic branch 1
description: A pupal ganglionic branch arising from pupal ventral branch 1. It mainly tracheates the mesothoracic neuromere.

label: embryonic/larval circulatory system
description: Tubular system of the embryo/larva through which hemolymph flows.

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 6
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 5
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 4
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029).

label: embryonic/larval pericardial cell
description: Cell type forming the outer layer of the dorsal vessel in the embryonic/larval abdomen. These cells sequester macromolecules from the hemolymph.

label: pupal ganglionic branch 2
description: A pupal ganglionic branch arising from pupal ventral branch 2. It mainly tracheates the metathoracic neuromere.

label: embryonic/larval ventral anastomosis
description: Tracheal node that connects the left and right ganglionic branches of an embryonic/larval tracheal metamere. Only 3 pairs of ganglionic branches are joined at the midline by a ventral anastomosis: ganglionic branches 0, 1 and 2. Forms during embryonic stage 16.

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 9
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 8
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033).

label: embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 7
description: Any embryonic/larval ganglionic branch (FBbt:00000325) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032).

label: ventral anastomosis 2
description: Any embryonic/larval ventral anastomosis (FBbt:00000336) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027) and that connected to some embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 2 (FBbt:00000328).

label: ventral anastomosis 1
description: Any embryonic/larval ventral anastomosis (FBbt:00000336) that is part of some tracheal metamere 1 (FBbt:00005026) and that connected to some embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 1 (FBbt:00000327).

label: ventral anastomosis 0
description: Any embryonic/larval ventral anastomosis (FBbt:00000336) that connected to some embryonic/larval ganglionic branch 0 (FBbt:00000326).

label: secondary lobe of embryonic/larval lymph gland
description: Second most anterior pair of lobes of the third instar larval lymph gland. They are bulbous like the anterior lobes, but smaller than them. It is composed of prohemocytes, and rarely it contains a differentiated cell.

label: embryonic/larval dorsal vessel
description: A contractile tube in the embryo/larva that extends from immediately behind the posterior commissure of T1 to the arthrodial membrane of A7, into which it inserts via two caudally directed muscles which connect to lateral apodemes in A8. Throughout its length, its lumen is enclosed by just two cardial cells. This single-cell thick layer of cardial cells is surrounded by a single-cell thick layer of pericardial cells, except in the posterior thorax. In this region, it is surrounded by lymph gland in the anterior thorax where it passes through the ring gland. The whole tube is attached to the anterior region of each abdominal segment boundary by alary muscles.

label: fat body branch 3
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 3 (FBbt:00000257).

label: embryonic/larval fat body branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches from the transverse connective and tracheates the fat body.

label: fat body branch 2
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 2 (FBbt:00000256).

label: fat body branch 1
description: Larval trachea that branches from the transverse connective and tracheates the fat body. Develops during the larval stages.

label: embryonic/larval ostia
description: Opening in the side of the embryonic/larval heart that permits hemolymph to enter the heart for circulation.

label: embryonic/larval ostia 1
description: Ostia of the embryonic/larval heart located at the A5/A6 segmental boundary.

label: tertiary lobe of embryonic/larval lymph gland
description: Pair of lymph gland lobes posterior to the secondary lobes. Unlike the more anterior lobes, these are small and elongate. The tertiary lobe is composed of prohemocytes. There may be multiple pairs of these lobes.

label: fat body branch 7
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 7 (FBbt:00005032) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 7 (FBbt:00000261).

label: fat body branch 6
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 6 (FBbt:00005031) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 6 (FBbt:00000260).

label: alary cell
description: Twist (FBgn0003900) expressing cell associated with the alary muscles in late stage embryos (present by late stage 15, early stage 16).

label: fat body branch 5
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 5 (FBbt:00005030) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 5 (FBbt:00000259).

label: fat body branch 4
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 4 (FBbt:00005029) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 4 (FBbt:00000258).

label: fat body branch 9
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 9 (FBbt:00005034) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 9 (FBbt:00000263).

label: fat body branch 8
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 8 (FBbt:00005033) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 8 (FBbt:00000262).

label: embryonic/larval ostia 2
description: Ostia of the embryonic/larval heart located at the A6/A7 segmental boundary.

label: embryonic/larval ostia 3
description: Ostia of the embryonic/larval heart located at the A6/A7 segmental boundary.

label: periligament cell
description: Paired cells that are attached either side of the pericardial cells on both sides of the dorsal vessel, located where the alary muscle inserts into the dorsal vessel.

label: fat body branch 10
description: Any embryonic/larval fat body branch (FBbt:00000340) that is part of some tracheal metamere 10 (FBbt:00005035) and that connected to some embryonic/larval transverse connective 10 (FBbt:00000264).

label: macrophage
description: Hemocyte that shows phagocytic activity. Morphologically, these cells are plasmatocytes (Tepass et al., 1994; Sorrentino et al., 2002). They only differentiate from plasmatocytes in embryos and at metamorphosis.

label: plasmatocyte
description: Hemocyte of the embryo and larva. Relatively large, irregularly shaped hemocyte (Brehelin, 1982). At the end of the third instar larval stage, plasmatocytes contains numerous inclusions, digitations and pinocytotic vesicles, well developed rough endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus and small lysosome-like bodies. By the end of the third instar period they also contain numerous phagosomes. Plasmatocytes represent 90-95% of all mature larval hemocytes. They function in the removal of dead cells and microbial pathogens.

label: lateral E branch 3
description: Any lateral E branch (FBbt:00000352) that is part of some tracheal metamere 3 (FBbt:00005028).

label: lateral E branch
description: Ventrally directed secondary tracheal branch from the lateral trunk in the anterior of a segment.

label: lateral E branch 2
description: Any lateral E branch (FBbt:00000352) that is part of some tracheal metamere 2 (FBbt:00005027).

label: lamellocyte
description: Hemocyte of the larva. Large, flat and regularly shaped hemocyte involved in the immune response of encapsulation. They contain short and narrow vesicles of rough endoplasmic reticulum, a well developed Golgi apparatus and some free ribosomes. Lamellocytes are not found in embryos and adults, and are rare in healthy larvae, although their differentiation can be induced by parasitoid wasp infection. Lamellocytes are involved in encapsulating and killing parasites. They differentiate both from the lymph gland and from the sessile hemocyte population.

label: prolamellocyte
description: An immature lamellocyte.

label: embryonic/larval lateral group branch
description: Branch from the lateral trunk that remains superficial and tracheates the ventral/lateral epidermis and/or musculature.

label: podocyte
description: Hemocyte of the embryo and larva that differentiates from plasmatocytes, flattening and extending long cytoplasmic extensions.

label: procrystal cell
description: An immature crystal cell. These cells measure 8 to 9 micrometers in diameter and can be distinguished from prohemocytes by the lack of cytoplasmic processes and fewer ribosomes, rough endoplasmic reticulum, mitochondria and Golgi bodies (Shrestha and Gateff, 1982). They are found in the cortical zone of the primary lobe of the embryonic/larval lymph gland.

label: crystal cell
description: Hemocyte of the embryo and larva. A cell that is slightly larger than the plasmatocytes and is distinguished by containing large crystalline inclusions of prophenol oxidase that are not membrane bound (Brehelin, 1982). Crystal cells represent less than 5% of all mature larval hemocytes. They are non-phagocytic cells that facilitate innate immune and wound-healing responses by mediating the process of melanization. They are found in the cortical zone of the primary lobe of the embryonic/larval lymph gland.

label: embryonic/larval garland organ

label: embryonic/larval oenocyte
description: Embryonic/larval oenocytes are large, polyploid cells whose cytoplasm contains yellowish granules. They are arranged in clusters in abdominal segments 1-7, under the epidermis, to which they are attached by fine elastic cellular extensions. As the animal ages, the number of granules increases and the cells become highly enlarged relative to their neighbors. These cells have been shown to function in the breakdown of stored lipids and may also control feeding behaviour (Gutierrez et al., 2007). These cells degenerate during late pupal stages.

label: border hair
description: Slender trichome that is located on the border between the inner and outer surface of the labellum. There is a uniform row of these.

label: presumptive border hair
description: Region of the wing disc that will develop into the border hair.

label: pharyngeal branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that arises from a bifurcation of the cerebropharyngeal branch and targets (tracheates) the pharynx.

label: cerebropharyngeal branch
description: Anterodorsally oriented, embryonic/larval trachea that branches from the dorsal trunk in tracheal metamere 1.

label: lateral H branch 10
description: Any lateral H branch (FBbt:00000382) that is part of some tracheal metamere 10 (FBbt:00005035).

label: dorsal cephalic branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches anteriorly from dorsal branch 1. In the late stage 14 and 15, the dorsal branch begins to branch and forms four or more terminal branches that tracheate the epidermis and muscles of the dorsal and lateral head.
synonyms: forward branch of large anterior dorsal commissure

label: embryonic/larval cerebral anastomosis
description: Tracheal node of the embryo or larva head formed by fusion of spurs from the left and right cerebral branches.

label: cerebral branch
description: Anteriorly oriented, embryonic/larval trachea that arises from a bifurcation of the cerebropharyngeal branch and targets (tracheates) the brain.

label: lateral cephalic branch
description: Embryonic/larval trachea that branches anteriorly from the lateral trunk close to transverse connective 1 and courses anterodorsally and superficially. At the end of stage 16, it forms around four fine branches that tracheate the epidermis and muscles of the head.

label: metatarsus of female prothoracic leg
description: First tarsal segment of the female prothoracic leg. In contrast to males, it has 7 to 8 transverse rows of bristles (TR).

label: abdominal 4 dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF
description: Any abdominal dorsal multidendritic neuron ddaF (FBbt:00006025) that is part of some larval abdominal segment 4 (FBbt:00001751).

description: An oval sense organ in the dorsal, proximal metathoracic tibia. It is composed of 4 sensilla campaniform.

label: presumptive large anterior bristle of antennal segment 2

label: small anterior bristle of antennal segment 2
description: Small bristle on the anterior side of antennal segment 2. There are around 13 of these forming a row.

label: large anterior bristle of antennal segment 2
description: Large bristle on the anterior side of antennal segment 2. There are 5 of these.

label: dorsal medial bristle of antennal segment 1
description: Bristle on the dorsal medial side of antennal segment 1. There are four of these.

label: denticle
description: A small tooth on the surface of the body.

label: denticle row 6
description: Posterior-most, and sixth from anterior, row of denticles in the ventral denticle belt.

label: denticle row 5

label: dorsal denticle
description: Large and pigmented denticle of the dorsal region of the larval cuticle. There is one row of denticles per segment. Posterior to it, there are two rows of cells that secrete smooth cuticle.

label: denticle row 2
description: Second most-anterior row of denticles in the ventral denticle belt.

label: denticle row 1
description: Anterior-most row of denticles in the ventral denticle belt.

label: denticle row 4
description: Fourth anterior-most row of denticles in the ventral denticle belt.

label: denticle row 3
description: Third from anterior-most row of denticles in the ventral denticle belt.

label: multidendritic dendrite
description: Any dendrite (FBbt:00005110) that is part of some multidendritic neuron (FBbt:00005209).

label: scolopidial dendritic cap cell
description: Elongate cell that is part of a scolopidium. It is located at the distal end of the scolopidial dendrite, encompassing it. A conical deposit of electron opaque material fills the cap cell at its proximal end and connects the scolopale to the endoskeleton. Hemidesmosomes and septate junctions connect the scolopale cell to the cap cell.

label: scolopale cell
description: Cell that surrounds the distal tip of the scolopidial neuron dendrite. It secretes a cylindrical structure around the dendrite, known as a scolopale rod, that is juxtaposed to the apical, extracellular tube (or cap) also secreted by the scolopale cell.

label: scolopidial ligament cell
description: Cell that is part of a scolopidium, anchoring the cell body of the scolopidial neuron, usually, but not always, directly to the integument.

label: hemangioblast
description: A cell type of the cardiogenic mesoderm whose progeny become pericardial cells, cardioblasts and hemocytes of the lymph gland.

label: posterior cone cell pigment granule
description: Any pigment granule (FBbt:00004234) that is part of some posterior cone cell (FBbt:00004194).

label: cone cell pigment granule

label: embryonic/larval heart anchoring cell

label: embryonic heart anchoring cell primordium
description: A group of cells at the distal tip of the frontal sac that develop into the heart anchoring cells (FBbt:00005254).

label: cardiac outflow muscle
description: Muscles extending from the esophagus to the anterior aorta.

label: stage 1 embryo
description: Nuclear divisions 1 and 2. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 25 minutes (0-25 minutes after egg laying).
